COPY public.days (id, trecena_id, day, number, nawal, chapter, horoscope, affirmation, meditation, energy_of_the_day, birthday, colors, created_at, updated_at) FROM stdin;
13	1	13	13	Kan					{"nawal": {"title": "The Serpent of Wisdom", "content": "Kan is the feather serpent, the Kundalini energy, and the spark of life force in the blood. It represents power, evolution, and the transmutation of energy. Kan is the wisdom that comes from the body, the instinct, and the DNA. It governs sexuality, justice, and the truth that is felt rather than thought. This nawal is intense and demanding; it asks us to shed our old skins like the snake and to embody our power. It is the energy of the magician who knows how to move energy to create change.", "keywords": ["Power", "Life Force", "Wisdom", "Transformation", "Serpent"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascension of Spirit", "content": "The number Thirteen is the completion, the ascension, and the return to the source. It represents the highest vibration of the cycle, where the wave returns to the ocean. Thirteen is mystical, transformative, and powerful. It is the number of the ancestors and the spirit world. On this day, the energy is not about doing, but about becoming. It is a time of synthesis, where the lessons of the previous twelve days are fully integrated and transcended. Thirteen prepares us for the flight into the next trecena.", "keywords": ["Completion", "Ascension", "Transformation", "Ancestors", "Synthesis"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in physical movement (yoga, dance) to move stagnant energy.", "Meditate on your spine as a channel of light connecting Earth and Sky.", "Release an old identity or label that no longer fits your evolved self.", "Trust your body's wisdom over your mind's logic today.", "Offer gratitude for the vitality and health that sustains you."], "title": "The Transmutation of Power", "content": "13 Kan brings the Aj trecena to a magnificent, high-frequency close. The ascending energy of Thirteen combines with the evolutionary power of the Serpent to create a day of profound transformation. This is the moment where the stable authority of Aj (Day 1) evolves into spiritual wisdom. The energy is electric, vital, and surging. You are asked to shed the skin of who you were thirteen days ago and step fully into your power. It is a day to honor the life force within you, to trust your instincts, and to channel your energy toward a higher purpose. The staff of authority has become the wand of the magician."}}	{"title": "The Master of Evolution", "content": "To be born on 13 Kan is to be a powerhouse of spiritual and physical energy. You represent the culmination of the cycle, holding the wisdom of the ancients in your blood. The number Thirteen gives you a connection to the otherworld and a sense of completing things, while Kan grants you an intense vitality and charisma. You are a natural leader, healer, or teacher who transforms others simply by your presence. You have a magnetic quality that can be both seductive and intimidating.\\n\\nYour challenge is managing the intensity of your own power. You may struggle with the 'shadow side' of Kan—manipulation, ego, or misuse of sexual energy. Because you feel everything so intensely, you must learn to ground yourself or risk burning out. Your soul's purpose is to master the serpent energy, using it not for personal gain but for the evolution of consciousness. You are here to demonstrate that true power is the ability to constantly shed your skin and be reborn closer to the light."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a98563", "primary": "#1b1c15", "secondary": "#4c4330"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.739245	2026-04-25 13:46:57.635432
3	1	3	3	Tz'ikin					{"nawal": {"title": "The Visionary Bird", "content": "Tz'ikin is the eagle, the condor, the bird of power that flies highest and sees furthest. It represents vision, prosperity, and the ability to see the 'big picture' of life. Tz'ikin is the messenger between heaven and earth, bringing news from the spirit world to the physical plane. It governs abundance, not just in money but in relationships, opportunities, and spiritual richness. This nawal encourages us to rise above the minutiae of daily struggles and view our lives from a higher perspective. It is an energy of freedom, lightness, and the joy of seeing dreams manifest into reality.", "keywords": ["Vision", "Prosperity", "Freedom", "Abundance", "Perspective"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Creation", "content": "The number Three breaks the stalemate of duality and introduces movement, rhythm, and flow. It is the vibration of the triangle, the tripod that creates stability through dynamism. Three represents the integration of the inner and outer to create a third state—expression. It is often associated with creativity, communication, and the restless energy of germination. While it brings the joy of movement, it can also bring instability if not directed, like a stream overflowing its banks. It is a day to let things flow, to experiment, and to trust the rhythm of the process.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Creativity", "Flow", "Rhythm", "Expression"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Write down your dreams or visions immediately; insights come fast today.", "Engage in creative activities that allow your mind to wander freely.", "Look for financial or professional opportunities that align with your higher purpose.", "Communicate your big-picture ideas to a team or partner.", "Take a literal or metaphorical 'view from above' to solve a problem."], "title": "The Flight of Creative Vision", "content": "3 Tz'ikin is a day of dynamic, soaring energy. The movement of the number Three combines with the visionary power of the Eagle to create a potent force for manifesting dreams. It is a day where ideas can take flight rapidly, and communication flows with inspiration. You may feel a restless urge to break free from routine and explore new horizons. The energy supports brainstorming, artistic expression, and sharing your vision with others. However, be mindful of scattering your energy too thin; the Eagle sees everything, but must dive with precision to catch its prize. Use the rhythm of the day to propel your long-term goals forward."}}	{"title": "The Messenger of Abundance", "content": "To be born on 3 Tz'ikin is to be a restless visionary, forever seeking the horizon. You carry the gift of the Eagle's sight combined with the communicative flair of the number Three. You are likely a natural storyteller, an artist, or an entrepreneur who spots trends long before others do. Your energy is infectious, often lifting the spirits of those around you. You are designed to circulate prosperity and ideas, acting as a bridge between the abstract world of potential and the concrete world of results.\\n\\nYour challenge lies in the intensity of your mental movement. You may struggle with focus, flitting from one shiny opportunity to the next without landing. Because you see so much, you can become overwhelmed by the possibilities. Your soul's growth comes from learning to harness your powerful rhythm, grounding your vision so that you can manifest the abundance you are destined to create. You are here to show others that true freedom comes from disciplined flight."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#9fbcaf", "primary": "#181e1d", "secondary": "#465e5e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.731747	2026-04-25 13:46:57.638667
71	6	6	6	No'j	The labor of the ledger gives way to a garden of breathtaking intellectual harmony. Here, the 'flora' consists of giant, silent paper gears and golden compasses that rotate in a perfect, synchronized dance. To cross this plaza, you must synchronize your breath with the ticking sand of the environment, allowing your mind to find the 'rhythm of No’j.' You encounter a complex road-puzzle where the streets are locked in a geometric knot. Instead of overthinking, you let your thoughts flow into the gears. The moment your internal rhythm matches the external geometry, the puzzle solves itself with a soft, paper-click, unrolling a perfectly symmetrical mandala of a path that leads you toward a sustainable and innovative future.	Today, the world is arranging itself into a beautiful, geometric mandala, and you are sitting at the absolute center. You may feel an unusual clarity of thought, a way of seeing the "big picture" without losing sight of the tiny, essential details. This is the energy of the intellect in harmony with the heart. The universe is asking you to refine your plans, to trim the excess, and to focus on the solutions that bring balance to your environment. It is a day of steady, rhythmic progress where every thought is a brick in the foundation of your future. Notice how your insights seem to "rhyme" with the experiences of those around you. This is a day for collaborative wisdom and the sharing of practical innovations. You don't need to reinvent the wheel; you just need to oil it with your own unique perspective. The atmosphere is charged with a quiet, efficient grace, making it easy to finish tasks that once felt daunting. By honoring the rhythm of your own growth, you create a ripple of harmony that touches everything you do. Step into the day with a focused mind and a steady hand. The universe is ready to help you build something that lasts.	I synchronize my thoughts with the natural rhythm of the world, finding elegant solutions to every puzzle.	Sit quietly and visualize a series of golden gears slowly turning behind your forehead. Breathe in a rhythm of six counts, and imagine the gears clicking into perfect synchronization with your breath. Feel your mind becoming a calm, orderly garden where every thought has its place and every question finds its natural, elegant answer.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, enter the Garden of Kinetic Geometry. See the giant paper gears and golden compasses rotating around you in a silent, perfect dance. Focus on a complex geometric knot in the path before you. As you match your internal rhythm to the ticking sand of the garden, watch the knot solve itself with a soft paper-click, unrolling into a symmetrical mandala of pure, workable logic.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Earth's Intellect", "content": "No'j is the Nawal of the mind, knowledge, and the sacred science. It represents the intellect of the Earth—the patterns, the logic, and the wisdom that structures reality. No'j is the energy of the scholar, the planner, and the problem-solver. It transforms raw information into usable wisdom. In human experience, No'j manifests as clarity of thought, good ideas, and the urge to learn. It is the 'Aha!' moment. When aligned, No'j brings brilliant solutions, noble thoughts, and a connection to the cosmic mind; when misaligned, it can lead to overthinking. It is the thought that precedes the action.", "keywords": ["Wisdom", "Intellect", "Knowledge", "Planning", "Solutions"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Harmony", "content": "The number Six represents the first point of true stability and flow in the cycle. It is the energy of the cube with a center, or the four directions plus the Above and Below. In Mayan cosmology, Six is the number of organic life and vital flow. Experientially, this energy feels gentle, rhythmic, and stabilizing. It is a day where things begin to click into place, and the struggle of the Five yields to a sustainable pace. The shadow of Six can be complacency, but its light is the grace of harmony. Today, the universe breathes easy.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Flow", "Stability", "Growth", "Rhythm"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in study or reading; your mind is receptive and calm.", "Brainstorm with a group; the energy favors shared wisdom.", "Organize your workspace to create better mental flow.", "Trust the 'obvious' solution; today, clarity is simple.", "Share an idea or teach a skill to someone else."], "title": "Harmonious Intelligence", "content": "The stabilizing flow of Tone 6 meets the brilliant mind of No'j to create a day of 'Intellectual Flow.' 6 No'j is a day where thinking feels effortless. The mental struggle dissolves, replaced by a rhythmic, intuitive understanding of complex subjects. It is an excellent day for study, writing, or collaborative brainstorming. The energy suggests that the best ideas come not from force, but from being in the flow. It is a time to organize your thoughts and your reality in a way that promotes organic growth. You may find that solutions to problems simply 'appear' today, carried on the gentle current of the number 6. This is also a day for sharing knowledge with others; the flow of 6 encourages exchange. Let your mind be a river, not a dam. Trust that your intelligence is aligned with the natural order."}}	{"title": "The Wise Counselor", "content": "To be born on 6 No'j is to be a vessel of calm, practical wisdom. You are the 'Flowing Mind'—someone whose intellect is not sharp and jagged, but smooth and permeating like water. You have a natural gift for solving problems in a way that benefits everyone involved, bringing harmony through logic. People seek your advice because you listen deeply and offer solutions that are grounded in reality yet elevated in perspective. You are likely a lifelong student, absorbing knowledge from the world around you effortlessly.\\n\\nYour life path is one of integrating the mind with the heart. The number 6 brings a quality of love and family to the intellectual No'j, making you a compassionate thinker. You are not the ivory tower academic; you are the wise elder in the village square. Your challenge is to ensure that your flow does not become passivity—that you use your brilliant mind to actively shape your reality, rather than just observing it. You are here to show us that true intelligence is always in harmony with life."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#bbbed5", "primary": "#121817", "secondary": "#3c455c"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.777304	2026-04-25 14:38:01.297604
6	1	6	6	Tijax					{"nawal": {"title": "The Blade of Truth", "content": "Tijax is the double-edged obsidian knife, the healer and the warrior. It represents the power to cut away illness, negativity, and illusion to reveal the truth. Tijax is the surgeon who wounds in order to heal, and the warrior who fights to protect the sacred. It governs sudden shocks, decisive actions, and the release of suffering. This nawal is intense and sharp, clearing the path of obstacles. It reminds us that sometimes we must sever our attachment to what is comfortable in order to survive and thrive. It is the spark of flint that starts the fire.", "keywords": ["Healing", "Truth", "Cutting", "Obsidian", "Discernment"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Harmony", "content": "The number Six represents the ultimate stability of flow. It is the energy of the six directions (East, West, North, South, Heart of Sky, Heart of Earth) coming into alignment. Six brings a gentle, rocking motion that stabilizes the efforts of the Five. It is associated with family, physical health, and the rhythm of life. This vibration does not force; it allows. It is the point in the cycle where the initial struggle of creation gives way to a sustainable momentum. Six asks us to attend to the details of our daily lives with grace and to find the balance between doing and being.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Flow", "Balance", "Health", "Rhythm"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Schedule a medical check-up, massage, or acupuncture session.", "Clean out a closet or drawer, physically cutting ties with the old.", "Have a difficult conversation with the intent of restoring harmony.", "Identify one daily habit that drains you and surgically remove it.", "Meditate on the 'Heart of Sky and Heart of Earth' to center yourself."], "title": "Healing the Rhythm of Life", "content": "6 Tijax brings a surprisingly gentle touch to the sharp energy of the Obsidian Blade. The harmonizing influence of Six softens the cut, making this a profound day for holistic healing. It is about finding the rhythm in your recovery or the balance in your truth-telling. Instead of a violent severance, today offers a surgical precision that aligns with the natural flow of your life. It is an excellent day to cut out unhealthy habits, toxic relationships, or negative thought patterns, but to do so with a sense of self-care rather than self-punishment. The energy supports practical adjustments to your routine that promote long-term well-being."}}	{"title": "The Gentle Surgeon", "content": "To be born on 6 Tijax is to be a healer of the highest order. You possess the incisive clarity of the obsidian knife, but it is tempered by the nurturing stability of the number Six. You are likely the person friends turn to when they need the 'hard truth' delivered with love. You have a talent for seeing exactly where the problem lies—whether in a body, a machine, or a relationship—and knowing precisely what needs to be adjusted to restore flow.\\n\\nYour challenge is that you may be prone to taking on the suffering of others or becoming overly critical when things are out of alignment. You feel the dissonance of the world acutely. Your soul's path is to master the art of detachment—to wield the knife of truth without cutting yourself. You are here to show that healing is not a one-time event but a daily rhythm, a constant pruning that allows life to flourish."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#bd876f", "primary": "#101110", "secondary": "#41332e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.734181	2026-04-25 13:46:57.642598
8	1	8	8	Ajpu					{"nawal": {"title": "The Hero of Light", "content": "Ajpu is the sun, the blowgunner, the spiritual warrior, and the artist. It represents the divine spark within the human being—the 'light' of consciousness. Ajpu is the nawal of the hero's journey, the one who overcomes trials to claim their divinity. It governs hunting, precision, and the clarity of purpose. This energy is victorious, creative, and connected to the cycles of the sun. It asks us to stand in our own light, to act with nobility, and to recognize that we are co-creators of our reality. It is the flower of life blooming in full glory.", "keywords": ["Sun", "Hero", "Divinity", "Light", "Purpose"]}, "number": {"title": "The Weaver of Justice", "content": "The number Eight represents the octave, the resumption of the cycle on a higher level. It is the number of harmony, justice, and pure energy. In the Mayan tradition, Eight is often associated with the 'male' or projective energy, balancing the reflective Seven. It represents the wholeness of the weaving, where the threads come together to form a pattern. Eight is the day of the art, the ceremony, and the return of energy. It asks us to organize the insights gained at the peak (Seven) and begin to integrate them back into the fabric of reality.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Justice", "Weaving", "Wholeness", "Ceremony"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a personal ceremony to honor your life's purpose.", "Create art or music that expresses your inner light.", "Stand up for a cause you believe in with noble confidence.", "Spend time in direct sunlight to recharge your solar plexus.", "Acknowledge the divinity in everyone you meet today (Namaste in action)."], "title": "Ceremony of the Inner Sun", "content": "8 Ajpu is one of the most auspicious days in the calendar. It represents the perfect harmony of spiritual light. The wholeness of Eight combines with the solar power of Ajpu to create a day of total alignment between the human and the divine. This is the 'Golden Day,' a time to honor the light within yourself and others. It is ideal for ceremonies, artistic performances, or any act that celebrates life. The energy is clear, bright, and regal. You are asked to wear your crown today, to walk with the dignity of a spiritual warrior who knows who they are. Shadows have nowhere to hide under this zenith sun."}}	{"title": "The Solar King/Queen", "content": "To be born on 8 Ajpu is to carry the energy of a spiritual royalty. You are a beacon of light, possessing a natural charisma and a clear sense of purpose that draws others to you. The number Eight grants you a deep sense of harmony and justice, while Ajpu fills you with the courage of the hero. You are likely an artist, a performer, or a leader who shines brightest when you are authentic. Life for you is a quest, a series of trials that you face not with fear, but with the certainty of your own divine origin.\\n\\nYour challenge is overcoming the ego. The brightness of your light can sometimes blind you to the needs of others, or you may fall into the trap of thinking you must be 'perfect' to be worthy. Your soul's journey is to learn that true heroism is about service, not glory. You are here to remind the world that everyone carries a spark of the divine, using your light to ignite the candles of those around you."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#ddcc99", "primary": "#1d1f18", "secondary": "#605036"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.735834	2026-04-25 13:46:57.645302
70	6	5	5	Ajmaq	Your path narrows into a stall where a Calligrapher silhouette is hunched over a massive ledger that seems to weep black ink. The pages are heavy with the 'stains' of your lineage—old debts of guilt and inherited patterns that smell of cold woodsmoke. To proceed, you must take up a heavy iron ink-scrubber and apply the effort of your own hands to the vellum. This is the labor of 5 Ajmaq; the work of active forgiveness. As you scrub with disciplined intent, the black stains don't just disappear—they transform into glowing silver threads that begin to mend the tears in your family tree. By taking responsibility for the 'ink' of the past, you find the strength to weave a cleaner story for the road ahead.	The universe is handing you a heavy iron brush and a bucket of silver light, and it’s pointing toward the stains on your own history. Today is not a day for the soft, passive release of the past; it is a day for the "hand of action". You may feel a sudden, driving willpower to confront the ghosts that have been whispering in the margins of your mind. This is a sacred labor—the disciplined work of scrubbing away the inherited patterns that no longer fit the person you are becoming. The air feels thick with the scent of woodsmoke and old ink, a reminder that every mistake is merely a lesson waiting to be refined into wisdom. Do not shy away from the effort. Forgiveness is a muscle, and today it needs a workout. You might find yourself reconciling with a memory or reaching out to mend a rift with a persistent, steady intent. As you apply your will to the task of emotional purification, notice how the weight of the world begins to shift. What felt like a burden is transforming into a legacy of strength. You are the one who breaks the cycle. By putting in the work to pardon yourself and others, you clear the road for a future that is unburdened and bright.	I work with disciplined intent to forgive myself and others, clearing the road for my future.	Close your eyes and imagine you are holding a soft, glowing silver cloth. Breathe into any areas of tension or guilt in your body, and as you exhale, imagine using the cloth to gently wipe away dark ink-stains from your spirit. Feel the effort of your breath mending the fibers of your being, leaving behind a surface that is clean and bright.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, see yourself standing before the Ink-Stained Ledger of Ghosts. Take up the heavy iron ink-scrubber and apply the willpower of your breath to the heavy black pages of your lineage. Watch as the ink doesn't vanish, but transforms into glowing silver threads. Visualize yourself weaving these threads back into your family tree, mending old tears with the light of active forgiveness.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Owl of Wisdom", "content": "Ajmaq is the Nawal of the Owl, the ancestors, and the concept of forgiveness. It represents the wisdom that comes from experience—specifically, the wisdom gained through making mistakes. Ajmaq is the energy of pardon, redemption, and the sweetness of life that returns when we release guilt. It governs the lineage and the unseen connection to those who came before. In human experience, Ajmaq manifests as curiosity, a probing mind, and a deep capacity for empathy. It is the 'sinner' and the saint wrapped in one. It is the gentle hand that wipes the slate clean.", "keywords": ["Forgiveness", "Ancestors", "Wisdom", "Curiosity", "Redemption"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Action", "content": "The number Five represents the center point of the first wave of creation. It is the energy of the hand (five fingers) and the power to grasp, work, and manipulate reality. In Mayan cosmology, Five is the force of 'doing'; it breaks the static stability of Four and puts it into motion through effort. Experientially, this energy feels like a surge of willpower and a drive to get things done. It is the number of work, discipline, and the application of energy. The shadow of Five can be forcing things, but its light is the satisfaction of a job well done.", "keywords": ["Action", "Discipline", "Work", "Willpower", "Effort"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Reach out to someone you have wronged and take action to make it right.", "Do the 'work' of forgiveness—journaling, therapy, or honest conversation.", "Pay a debt or return a favor you owe.", "Research your family history or ancestral patterns actively.", "Use your curiosity to solve a complex problem; dig deep."], "title": "Active Redemption", "content": "When the working energy of Tone 5 meets the forgiving nature of Ajmaq, we encounter a day of 'Working on the Past.' 5 Ajmaq is not a day of passive forgiveness; it is a day to actively make amends. The energy asks you to put in the effort to heal old wounds, clear debts (karmic or financial), and restore balance with your lineage. It is a day to say 'I'm sorry' and back it up with action. The Owl sees where the mistake was made, and the Hand (5) reaches out to fix it. This energy also supports deep research and investigation; if you need to dig for the truth or uncover a hidden pattern, today provides the drive to do so. It is a day of 'sweet labor'—the work of reconciliation. Don't shy away from the messy parts of human connection today; rolling up your sleeves to clean up a misunderstanding will bring profound peace."}}	{"title": "The Seeker of Truth", "content": "To be born on 5 Ajmaq is to be a tireless worker in the fields of wisdom and redemption. You are the 'Active Healer'—someone who is not content to simply understand human nature but who actively works to improve it. You possess a curious, probing mind that loves to uncover secrets and solve mysteries. You may find yourself drawn to history, psychology, or genealogy—anything that allows you to dig into the past to explain the present. You are hard-working and disciplined, often taking on the burden of healing generational patterns for your family.\\n\\nYour life path involves learning through experience. You are likely to make your fair share of mistakes (Ajmaq), but the energy of the 5 gives you the resilience to get back up and work through them. You don't wallow in guilt; you fix it. Your superpower is your ability to forgive—not by ignoring the wrong, but by understanding the mechanics of why it happened. You are here to teach us that redemption is a verb, requiring effort, courage, and action."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a49db3", "primary": "#11191b", "secondary": "#40424e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.776958	2026-04-25 14:38:01.296534
31	3	5	5	K'at					{"nawal": {"title": "The Net of Abundance", "content": "K'at is the nawal of the net, the web, and the gathering. It represents the energy of abundance that comes from connection and storage. K'at is the lizard that carries the seeds and the mesh bag that holds the corn. It governs the gathering of people, resources, and ideas. However, the net can also represent entanglement—the debts, burdens, and emotional baggage we carry. In its shadow, K'at can manifest as feeling trapped, hoarding, or being unable to let go. Its highest purpose is to help us sort through what we have gathered, keeping what nurtures us and releasing what weighs us down.", "keywords": ["Net", "Gathering", "Abundance", "Entanglement", "Release"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Effort", "content": "Five is the number of work, empowerment, and the human hand. It represents the energy of application—using one's will and effort to move things forward. Five is the center point that drives the four directions into action. It is an industrious, net-gathering energy. Experientially, a Five day asks for participation; it is not a day for passivity. It feels busy, driven, and capable. The shadow of Five can be forcing things, overworking, or losing the spiritual connection in the busyness of the material. It reminds us that we have the power to shape our reality.", "keywords": ["Work", "Effort", "Action", "Empowerment", "Center"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Pay a bill or resolve a lingering financial task to clear your net.", "Reach out to five people in your network to reconnect.", "Spend 30 minutes decluttering a specific area of your home.", "Visualize cutting cords to burdens you no longer want to carry.", "Make a list of resources you need for your goals and take action to acquire them."], "title": "Working the Net", "content": "Today, the industrious energy of Five combines with the gathering power of K'at to create a day of 'Active Sorting' or 'Empowered Gathering.' The energy is focused on the work of the net: pulling in resources, connecting with community, and sorting through your catch. It is a powerful day for networking, fundraising, or organizing your physical and digital lives. The Five gives you the drive to deal with the 'mess' that K'at can sometimes bring. You have the power today to untangle knots that have been bothering you for a long time. Whether it's a financial debt, a cluttered closet, or a complicated relationship, put your 'hand' (Five) to the 'net' (K'at) and get to work. The challenge is the potential for overwhelm; the net can feel heavy. Do not try to carry it all. Use the discernment of the day to keep only the golden fish and throw the rest back. Effort applied today yields a rich harvest."}}	{"title": "The Weaver of Abundance", "content": "To be born on 5 K'at is to be a master of resources and connection. You have a natural talent for bringing things and people together. The number Five gives you a strong work ethic and a drive to make things happen, while K'at endows you with a magnetic quality—opportunities, people, and material goods seem to find their way into your net. You are likely the 'connector' in your social circle, the one who knows the guy who knows the guy. You have a potential for great material and spiritual abundance.\\n\\nYour life path involves learning the balance between holding on and letting go. Because you gather so easily, you can become weighed down by your own success or by the emotional demands of the many people you support. You may struggle with a cluttered life—either physically or mentally. Your lesson is to constantly curate your net, ensuring that what you carry is serving your highest purpose. You are a worker for the collective, weaving a web that supports not just yourself, but your entire community."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#bab56d", "primary": "#111a16", "secondary": "#474d2e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.747988	2026-04-25 13:46:57.688704
79	7	1	1	Imox	You find the lake by accident, or at least that is what you tell yourself.\n\nThe path you follow is barely a path at all, just a thinning of trees and a feeling that something ahead has been waiting. Branches lean closer, as if they want to see what you will do, and the air grows damp and cool against your skin. There is a hush that is not quite silence, more like a held breath.\n\nThen you see it.\n\nThe water is impossibly still. Not a ripple, not a breeze. The surface reflects the sky with such clarity that for a moment you cannot tell which way is up. Clouds float above you and beneath you at the same time. When you step closer, the reflection shifts, and something inside the lake shifts with it.\n\nYou kneel at the edge. It feels like standing on the threshold of a story that has not been written yet.\n\nThere is no sign, no instruction, only the quiet invitation of the water. You notice how your thoughts try to rush in, filling the silence with plans and questions, but the lake does not respond to noise. It responds to attention. So you stay, and you let the thoughts thin out, one by one, until you can hear the small, steady rhythm of your own breathing.\n\nThe surface begins to change.\n\nIt is not dramatic. No storm, no sudden wave. Just a soft glow rising from beneath, as if the water remembers a light it has not shown in a very long time. Shapes flicker in the reflection, not quite images, more like ideas that have not decided what to become. A song you have not written. A conversation you have not had. A version of you that feels strangely honest.\n\nFor a moment you feel the urge to reach in, to grab one of those half-formed visions and pull it out, force it into reality. But something in your chest whispers, "Not yet." The timing is delicate. This is not the day to rush. This is the day to notice that possibility exists at all.\n\nThe water does not tell you who to be. It only shows you that you could be more than the story you have rehearsed.\n\nYou stand again, a little unsteady, as if the ground beneath you has shifted by a fraction of an inch. Nothing around you has changed. The trees are the same. The sky is the same. Yet there is a quiet difference inside you, a sense that the world has opened one small door and is waiting to see if you will walk through it.\n\nYou leave the shore with no grand decision, only a simple truth: there is a place within you as still as that lake, and it is finally ready to be seen.	The world feels a little quieter today, like the universe turned the volume down so you could hear your own pulse more clearly. There is a still pool inside you that has been waiting for your attention, reflecting back versions of your life that you have not dared to claim.\n\nLet yourself linger at the edge of that inner water. You do not need to define anything yet. Just notice what glows under the surface when you stop rushing, the ideas that keep returning, the dreams that refuse to die. This is the soft beginning, the inhale before the next chapter.\n\nYou are not late. You are right on time for yourself.	I honor the quiet beginnings inside me, and I give my deepest dreams space to breathe.	Find a place where you can sit comfortably for a few minutes. Close your eyes and imagine a still body of water in front of you. With each inhale, see the surface grow clearer. With each exhale, let scattered thoughts dissolve. Ask gently, 'What wants to begin inside me?' Let whatever arises come naturally. Before opening your eyes, send quiet gratitude to the lineages and ancestors who learned to listen to cycles and the living world. Carry that stillness with you into the day.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Primordial Ocean", "content": "Imox is the Nawal of water, the collective subconscious, and the primordial dream from which reality emerges. It represents the feminine aspect of creation—the womb, the intuition, and the fluid chaos of imagination. Imox is the energy that connects us all telepathically and emotionally; it is the 'dream that dreams us.' In human experience, Imox manifests as wild creativity, psychic sensitivity, and sometimes 'crazy wisdom.' When aligned, it brings profound inspiration and adaptability; when misaligned, it can lead to emotional overwhelm, confusion, or losing touch with practical reality. It is the ocean that can be a calm mirror or a raging storm, asking us to trust the flow.", "keywords": ["Intuition", "Dreams", "Water", "Subconscious", "Creativity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Creation", "content": "The number One represents the primordial spark, the moment of inception, and the unity of all things. It is the seed that contains the entire blueprint of the future within its tiny shell. In Mayan cosmology, One is the energy of initiation and firm beginnings; it is not merely a start, but a powerful concentration of potential that requires focus and intent. Experientially, this energy feels like a surge of inspiration or a sudden clarity of purpose. It asks you to stand alone if necessary, to be the single point of origin for a new cycle. The shadow of One can be isolation or a failure to launch due to the overwhelming weight of potential, but its light is the unstoppable force of creation itself. Today, you are the origin point.", "keywords": ["Beginnings", "Unity", "Seed", "Potential", "Focus"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Start a dream journal; your subconscious is speaking loudly.", "Spend time near water (shower, bath, ocean) to connect with the energy.", "Set a creative intention for the next 13 days.", "Trust your intuition over your logic; feelings are the compass today.", "Allow yourself to daydream; it is productive work today."], "title": "Seeding the Dream", "content": "When the initiating spark of Tone 1 meets the vast, watery depths of Imox, we stand at the birthplace of a new reality. 1 Imox is the day to plant the seed of a dream. It is the beginning of the Imox trecena, a 13-day cycle dedicated to navigating the subconscious and birthing new visions. The energy today is potent, mysterious, and fluid. You may feel a strong pull toward introspection or a sudden influx of creative ideas that seem to come from nowhere. This is the time to set intentions that are not based on logic, but on feeling. What does your soul want to create? The universe is listening to your internal frequency today. It is a day to honor your sensitivity as a superpower and to trust that the strange images floating in your mind are actually seeds waiting to be watered. Dive in."}}	{"title": "The Dreamer of Origins", "content": "To be born on 1 Imox is to be a vessel for the collective unconscious and a pioneer of the imagination. You are the 'First Dreamer'—a soul who lives close to the source of all creation. You likely have a profound psychic sensitivity and a creative mind that operates on a different frequency than the rest of the world. You are the person who feels the mood of a room instantly, who knows things without knowing how, and who can birth ideas that seem ahead of their time. \\n\\nYour life path is one of initiating new ways of seeing and feeling. With the number 1, you have a strong sense of individuality, yet Imox connects you to everyone. This can create a tension where you feel like a loner in a crowded room, overwhelmed by the emotions of others. Your challenge is to learn to filter the waters—to distinguish your own feelings from the collective and to use your immense creative power to ground your visions into reality. You are here to dream the world anew."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#59bcb1", "primary": "#0c1a18", "secondary": "#2b4e49"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.782169	2026-04-25 13:46:57.768113
24	2	11	11	Kame					{"nawal": {"title": "The Transformer", "content": "Kame is the nawal of death, rebirth, and the ancestors. It represents the dimensional door between worlds. Kame is the only certainty in life—change. It governs the cycles of ending and beginning, the compost that feeds the flower. Kame is a peaceful, quiet energy, like the silence of the grave, but it commands total respect. It is the patron of spiritual mediums and those who help souls cross over. In its shadow, Kame can be fear of change, morbidness, or clinging to the past. Its highest expression is the profound peace of surrender—knowing that death is simply a transformation of energy, an undressing of the soul.", "keywords": ["Death", "Rebirth", "Ancestors", "Transformation", "Peace"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Dissolution", "content": "Eleven is the number of dissonance, change, and the breaking of patterns. It is often considered a 'master number' but in the sense of a challenge—it is the energy that disrupts the status quo to clear the way for higher order. Eleven is not about stability; it is about testing the structure. Experientially, an Eleven day can feel chaotic, surprising, or liberating. It is the loose brick in the wall that, when pulled, changes the whole shape of the room. The shadow of Eleven is overwhelm or destruction without purpose. It asks us to be flexible and to find the freedom in letting things fall apart.", "keywords": ["Change", "Dissonance", "Liberation", "Testing", "Clearing"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Clean out a closet, drawer, or digital folder—delete what is dead.", "Write a letter to someone or something you are ready to say goodbye to, then burn it.", "Practice 'corpse pose' (Savasana) in yoga; consciously relax every muscle into the earth.", "Avoid starting new major projects today; focus on closing loops.", "Remind yourself: 'I am not what I lose; I am what remains.'"], "title": "The Great Release", "content": "Today, the disruptive force of Eleven meets the transformative power of Kame. This is a day of 'Radical Clearing' or 'The Great Let-Go.' It is perhaps the most powerful day in the trecena for breaking addictions, ending outdated contracts, or finally grieving a loss. The energy is stripping away the non-essential. It might feel intense or turbulent, as Eleven shakes the foundations while Kame dissolves the form. Do not try to hold on tightly to anything today; the grip will only cause friction. Instead, surrender to the process of shedding. This is a day to trust that what is leaving your life is making space for something much more alive. It is a 'phoenix' energy—the fire must burn before the bird can rise. The challenge is the fear of the void. But if you can sit in that emptiness without panicking, you will find a profound sense of liberation. You are being unburdened."}}	{"title": "The Agent of Transformation", "content": "To be born on 11 Kame is to be a catalyst for profound change and a walker between worlds. You carry a powerful, somewhat mysterious energy. The number Eleven makes you a non-conformist, someone who is here to shake up the system, while Kame gives you a deep comfort with the cycles of life and death. You are not afraid of endings; in fact, you are likely the person who helps others navigate them. You may be drawn to psychology, hospice work, shamanism, or crisis management—any field where you help people through their darkest nights.\\n\\nYour life path is a series of ego-deaths and rebirths. You reinvent yourself many times, shedding identities like old clothes. This can be disorienting for those around you, but for you, it is essential survival. You have a direct line to the ancestors and may possess strong mediumistic or intuitive abilities. You see the fragility of life, which gives you a unique, often dark, sense of humor and a desire to live authentically.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is stability. Your life can feel like a constant earthquake if you don't find a spiritual center. You may also struggle with a sense of fatalism or heaviness. Your lesson is to learn that while everything changes, the spirit is eternal. You are here to teach the world the art of surrender and to show that on the other side of every death, there is a new, brighter life waiting."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#ded3db", "primary": "#161318", "secondary": "#6d5263"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.744699	2026-04-25 13:46:57.658502
119	10	2	2	Kej					{"nawal": {"title": "The Guardian of the Wild", "content": "Kej is the deer, the sovereign of the wilderness, and the keeper of the four directions. It represents strength, agility, and a deep, harmonious connection with the natural world. Kej carries the energy of authority that is earned through grace rather than force. It is the alert sensitivity of the deer, sensing shifts in the wind, and the sturdy legs that can climb the mountain. It asks us to stand tall, ground our energy, and find our rightful place within the ecosystem of life.", "keywords": ["Nature", "Strength", "Balance", "Leadership", "Harmony"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "The number 2 represents polarity, relationship, and the dynamic tension between opposites. It is the separation of the one into the many, creating the space for interaction. This energy governs partnerships, choices, and the reflection we see in others. It brings the challenge of balance—navigating between light and dark, male and female, self and other. In the cycle of 13, it is the reaction to the initial impulse, where the seed meets the soil and the first dialogue of creation begins.", "keywords": ["Duality", "Partnership", "Reflection", "Choice", "Balance"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Take a walk in nature with a partner or friend to ground your connection.", "Notice where you are compromising your truth to keep the peace.", "Stand barefoot on the earth and ask for balance in your relationships.", "Observe the animals you see today; they carry messages for you.", "Practice active listening, acting as a clear mirror for someone else."], "title": "Balancing the Wild Forces", "content": "2 Kej brings the energy of transformation into the realm of relationship and the physical world. It asks us to look at how we balance our wild, instinctive nature with our commitments to others. The 'death' energy of the trecena here manifests as a shedding of artificiality in our connections. Are your relationships grounded in truth? Do they allow you to stand in your full sovereign power, or do they diminish you? Today is about finding the middle path between dominance and submission, between the needs of the self and the needs of the partner. It is a day to seek answers in nature, letting the wilderness mirror your own inner landscape."}}	{"title": "The Partner of the Wild", "content": "To be born on 2 Kej is to carry the soul of a diplomat of the natural world. You possess a unique blend of sensitivity and strength, able to navigate complex human relationships with the grace of a deer moving through the forest. You are constantly seeking balance, not just for yourself, but for the environment around you. You have a gift for seeing both sides of any situation, which makes you an excellent mediator and a trusted friend. Your connection to nature is not just a hobby; it is a vital source of your stability and clarity.\\n\\nYour life path involves mastering the art of partnership—with people, with nature, and with the spiritual realm. You shine when you are in a supportive duo or working in harmony with others. However, your high sensitivity means you can easily become overwhelmed by harsh environments or discordant energies. You need wild spaces to recharge your spirit and remind you of your own rugged capabilities.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 2 Kej is to avoid indecision. Seeing all perspectives can sometimes paralyze you or lead you to over-compromise. Your growth comes from learning to trust your instincts—that 'deer sense'—and acting on it decisively. When you align your relationships with your highest truth, you become a powerful force for harmony, bridging the gap between the civilized world and the sacred wild."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#71a975", "primary": "#0b1614", "secondary": "#314539"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.806087	2026-04-25 13:46:57.872339
198	16	3	3	Tz'i'	The balance you struck has triggered an explosion. The Veldt is no longer a quiet garden; it is a riot of motion. The golden stalk has branched into a thousand vines, and the obsidian roots have spread like a web. But they are moving too fast. The vines whip through the air, thrashing in a rhythmic frenzy that creates a barrier of green and violet blurs.\n\nYou are trapped at the center. The air crackles with static. You try to step forward, but a vine snaps just inches from your face. The rhythm is chaotic, impossible to predict. You are paralyzed by the sheer volume of life you have unleashed.\n\nThen, the air shifts. A low growl vibrates in your chest. Emerging from the wall of thrashing vines is a creature of pure, sharp light—a White Wolf. It is not flesh and blood; it is geometric instinct given form. Its eyes are burning coals.\n\nThe Wolf does not look at you. It trots directly into the storm of vines. It ducks, weaves, and pauses in a syncopated rhythm that perfectly matches the chaos. It is showing you the pattern. You take a breath and step. You do not watch the vines; you watch the Wolf. When it ducks, you duck. When it runs, you run. You surrender your logic to the instinct of the guide, flowing through the danger like water.	The rhythm of your life has just shifted into a frantic, syncopated blur, and the old predictable patterns are snapping like brittle vines. You might feel trapped at the center of a riotous explosion of motion, where every step you try to take is met by a thrashing unpredictable energy. This is not chaos; it is a test of your instinct. Today, logic is a lead weight that will only slow you down. You need the sharp, geometric clarity of a predator—a guide that knows how to weave through the storm without overthinking the obstacles. \n\nStop trying to map the path and start watching the patterns. There is a specific frequency to the madness, a hidden beat in the static. If you can surrender your need for control and trust the 'animal' part of your soul, you’ll find yourself ducking and weaving through the danger with a grace you didn't know you possessed. The static behind your eyes is actually the sound of your potential vibrating at a higher speed. Move with the guide, even if it seems to be leading you directly into the thick of it. The wind is restless, carrying messages between the clouds, and the air itself is ready to applaud your agility. Integrity isn't about standing still; it's about staying loyal to your truth while moving at the speed of light.	I move with the grace of instinct, trusting my internal guide to navigate the chaos.	Find a seated position and place your hands on your knees. Begin a subtle, rhythmic tapping with your fingertips, matching the natural pace of your heartbeat. Surrender your thoughts to this physical pulse, letting the 'doing' of the rhythm carry you past the noise of the day.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine yourself standing amidst a storm of thrashing vines. Visualize a White Wolf of pure light appearing before you. Close your eyes and move your body slightly in your seat, mimicking the wolf’s syncopated weave. Trust the animal instinct in your gut to find the stillness within the motion.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Faithful Guide of Law", "content": "Tz'i' is the nawal of law, justice, and the dog. It represents the principle of divine order and the instinctual guidance that keeps us on the path of truth. Tz'i' is the faithful companion who guards the threshold, ensuring that we remain loyal to our highest purpose and to our community. Associated with the element of fire and the concept of authority, it brings a protective and corrective energy. It is the archetype of the judge, the lawyer, and the loyal friend. In daily life, Tz'i' manifests as questions of ethics, fidelity, and the right use of power. Its shadow aspect can be judgmentality, rigidity, or the corruption of authority—using the law to punish rather than to restore. Tz'i' teaches us that true justice is not about rules, but about alignment with cosmic love.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Loyalty", "Faith", "Guidance", "Protection"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Movement", "content": "Tone 3 is the energy of movement, vibration, and communication. It breaks the static balance of the number 2, introducing flow and dynamism. If 1 is the point and 2 is the line, 3 is the triangle—the first geometric form that implies stability yet encourages motion. It represents the integration of the right brain, left brain, and the central nervous system, or the union of mind, body, and spirit. Experientially, Tone 3 feels busy, expressive, and sometimes restless. It is a day of 'doing,' where ideas seek to be spoken and energies seek to be circulated. While it fosters creativity and connection, its shadow can manifest as scattered energy, anxiety, or a lack of focus. It is the pulse that keeps the universe from standing still.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Expression", "Energy", "Instability", "Flow"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Take concrete action to correct an unfair situation.", "Communicate your boundaries clearly and without hesitation.", "Use physical movement (walking, running) to process ethical dilemmas.", "Check in on your loyalty—are you being true to yourself?", "Avoid gossip or scattered words; speak only what aligns with integrity."], "title": "The Active Pursuit of Justice", "content": "When the dynamic movement of Tone 3 combines with the authoritative energy of Tz'i', we experience a day of active alignment with truth. 3 Tz'i' is not a day for sitting idly by; it is a day to walk your talk. The energy demands that our internal values be expressed through our external actions. It is the 'running dog'—faithful, energetic, and purposeful. This combination facilitates the communication of boundaries and the active restoration of balance. If things have been stagnant or unjust, 3 Tz'i' provides the momentum to correct them. It feels like a busy courtroom where the arguments are flowing, or a pilgrimage where the movement itself is the prayer. The risk today is becoming scattershot in your judgments or overly zealous in your corrections. The lesson is to let your actions be guided by loyalty to your soul's truth, moving swiftly but with the precision of a faithful guide."}}	{"title": "The Voice of Divine Law", "content": "To be born on 3 Tz'i' is to be a dynamic advocate for truth and a restless seeker of justice. You possess a sharp, communicative mind that is constantly weighing right and wrong. Unlike the silent observer, you are compelled to speak up and take action when you perceive an imbalance. You are the lawyer of the zodiac, the one who argues passionately for the underdog or for the principles you hold dear. Your energy is infectious and moving; you likely have a hard time sitting still, preferring to be in the mix of life where you can influence the flow of events.\\n\\nYour life path involves the expression of integrity through movement and communication. You are a natural guide, helping others navigate the complexities of moral and ethical choices. Because Tone 3 governs the nervous system and rhythm, you likely have a physical need to be active—dancing, writing, or traveling are ways you process your intense connection to divine law. You are loyal to a fault, often sticking by your friends and causes with a fierce determination. However, your version of 'law' is intuitive and instinctual, guided more by your internal compass than by societal rules.\\n\\nChallenges for a 3 Tz'i' soul include a tendency towards anxiety or over-involvement in others' drama. Your desire to fix things and your high energy can sometimes lead to burnout or scattered efforts. You may also struggle with being overly critical or sharp-tongued when you feel justice has been violated. Your growth lies in learning to channel your restless energy into focused, compassionate action. When you learn to communicate your truth with love rather than judgment, you become a powerful force for restoring harmony in the world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b8c4d5", "primary": "#0e1a1a", "secondary": "#3a5055"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.852387	2026-04-25 14:38:01.320995
18	2	5	5	Ajpu					{"nawal": {"title": "The Solar Hero", "content": "Ajpu is the nawal of the Sun, the blowgunner, and the spiritual warrior. It represents the light of divinity within the human form. Ajpu is the archetype of the hero who descends into the underworld (Xibalba) to overcome darkness and rise again as the sun. It governs art, performance, leadership, and the clarity of purpose. Ajpu energy is confident, radiant, and resilient. It is the hunter who aims true. In its shadow, Ajpu can manifest as ego, arrogance, or a need for validation. It can also be judgmental or overly perfectionistic. However, at its core, it is the energy of Christ-consciousness or Buddha-nature—the realization that we are light walking on earth.", "keywords": ["Sun", "Hero", "Divinity", "Purpose", "Art"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Action", "content": "Five is the number of empowerment, work, and the human hand (five fingers). It represents the energy of doing—gathering resources, applying effort, and making things happen in the material world. After the stability of Four, Five sets things in motion again through work and will. It is often associated with the 'center' or the core that drives the four directions. Experientially, a Five day asks for participation. It is not a day to sit on the sidelines. It carries a net-gathering quality, pulling in what is needed. The shadow of Five can be overworking, forcing outcomes, or losing the spiritual connection in the busyness of the physical. It reminds us that we have the power to shape our reality through our actions.", "keywords": ["Action", "Work", "Empowerment", "Effort", "Center"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Dedicate one hour of focused work to a creative passion or hobby.", "Stand in the sunlight for a few minutes and visualize recharging your solar plexus.", "Do a physical act of service that aligns with your personal values.", "Practice confidence; speak up in a meeting or share your work with others.", "Reflect on what 'heroism' looks like in your daily life."], "title": "The Work of Illumination", "content": "Today, the industrious energy of Five combines with the solar radiance of Ajpu to create a day of 'Practical Divinity' or 'Empowered Purpose.' This is not a day to just dream about your higher self; it is a day to *act* like it. The energy supports doing the work that aligns with your soul's mission. Whether that means practicing an art form, leading a team, or standing up for a value you believe in, the universe is handing you the tools to make it manifest. Five Ajpu is the 'working artist' or the 'servant leader.' It reminds us that spiritual light is not just a concept, but a practice. You might feel a strong drive to finish a project or to polish a skill. The challenge is to ensure your ego doesn't hijack the effort—remember that you are the vessel, not the source, of the light. Aim your blowgun with steady hands, put in the effort, and trust that your work is clearing the path for the sun to rise."}}	{"title": "The Radiant Worker", "content": "To be born on 5 Ajpu is to be a beacon of practical light and a tireless champion for the divine. You combine the work ethic of the number Five with the visionary leadership of the Sun. You are not content to simply have a vision; you are compelled to build it, brick by brick. You are likely a natural leader who leads by example—you wouldn't ask anyone to do a task you aren't willing to do yourself. People are drawn to your confidence and your capability; you have a 'can-do' aura that makes difficult feats seem possible. You often find yourself in roles where you must perform or present, and you shine in the spotlight, but always with a sense of duty behind it.\\n\\nYour life path involves mastering the art of manifestation. You are a hunter of dreams, using your focus and determination to bring spiritual ideals down into physical reality. You may be drawn to the arts, athletics, or advocacy, any field where discipline meets expression. You have a strong sense of justice and a warrior's spirit when it comes to defending the weak. However, your battle is often internal—the quest to refine your own character until it is pure gold.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is the potential for burnout or perfectionism. The Five energy drives you to keep working, while Ajpu demands the highest standard. You may struggle to rest or to accept 'good enough.' Your evolution lies in realizing that you are already worthy, not because of what you do, but because of who you are. You are here to show the world that the holiest act is often the simple, daily labor of love."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#dfc68c", "primary": "#1d1f17", "secondary": "#654e31"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.742605	2026-04-25 13:46:57.669355
123	10	6	6	B'atz'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Weaver of Time", "content": "B'atz' is the thread of time, the artist, and the weaver of destiny. It represents the creative principle that organizes chaos into beauty. B'atz' is the monkey, the playful trickster who reminds us not to take the illusion too seriously, yet who holds the sacred calendar (the Cholq'ij) in its hands. It is the beginning of time and the continuity of the thread of life. It governs the arts, marriage, and the weaving together of community and purpose.", "keywords": ["Creativity", "Weaving", "Time", "Art", "Thread"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Stability", "content": "The number 6 represents ultimate stability, flow, and the physical vitality of the solar system (from a Mayan perspective). It is an even number that brings balance to the work of the 5. 6 is often associated with the heart of the sky and the heart of the earth in perfect alignment. It facilitates responsiveness and organic growth. It is a day where things come together with less friction, allowing for a harmonious expansion of the journey.", "keywords": ["Flow", "Stability", "Vitality", "Harmony", "Responsiveness"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in a creative act: draw, write, knit, or cook.", "Visualize the timeline of your life and rewrite the current chapter.", "Connect with community or family to strengthen your social fabric.", "Trust the timing of your life; stop pulling at the threads.", "Find the humor in your situation; play with the possibilities."], "title": "Weaving the New Pattern", "content": "6 B'atz' offers a beautiful, harmonious energy for weaving the strands of your new life together. After the rigor of 5 Tz'i', today brings flow and artistic grace. The transformation process of the Kame trecena here reaches a point of creative integration. It is a day to see the bigger picture—the tapestry—rather than just the individual knots. The energy supports artistic endeavors, the strengthening of family ties, and the intuitive understanding of your destiny's pattern. The 'rebirth' is being woven into reality now, thread by thread, with a sense of stability and joy."}}	{"title": "The Artist of Destiny", "content": "To be born on 6 B'atz' is to be a master weaver of reality. You are blessed with a natural grace and a creative intelligence that allows you to make life look easy, even when it is complex. You are likely an artist, a planner, or a connector of people. You have an intuitive understanding of time and timing—you know when to act and when to wait. Your presence brings harmony and beauty; you are the one who knows how to arrange the room, the conversation, or the project so that it flows perfectly.\\n\\nYour life path is one of creative expression and the preservation of wisdom. You may feel a deep connection to ancient traditions or the arts. You are a 'maker' in the truest sense, whether you are making art, making deals, or making families. You have a playful side, a 'monkey mind' that is curious and quick, but the 6 energy grounds you, giving your creativity a stable and productive outlet.\\n\\nYour challenge is to not get tangles in your own threads. You can sometimes become so involved in the details of the weaving that you lose sight of the design, or you may struggle with procrastination (the shadow of the monkey). Your soul's task is to trust your own masterpiece. When you align your creative will with the divine flow, you weave a life that is not only beautiful for yourself but serves as a sheltering tapestry for everyone around you."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#db9fba", "primary": "#191d1e", "secondary": "#754b57"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.806781	2026-04-25 13:46:57.876517
203	16	8	8	Tz'ikin	The white energy lines you saw in the dark begin to vibrate. Suddenly, the flat Veldt erupts. The spirit-lines pull the earth upward, forming a steep, sudden peak—a pyramid of soil rising from the bioluminescent plain. You climb it.\n\nAt the summit, the air is thin, cold, and clear. You are no longer in the humid garden; you are in the realm of the Sky. You look out and see the pattern of the Veldt stretching to the horizon—a perfect mandala of growth. You scream your intention into the vastness. It does not vanish; the horizon catches it and throws it back as a song. The Sky has heard you.	The flat horizon of your daily life has just erupted into a steep, sudden peak. The spirit-lines are pulling you upward into a realm where the air is thin, cold, and blindingly clear. You are no longer in the humid gardens of the ego; you are in the realm of the Sky. From this summit, the chaotic details of your life finally organize themselves into a perfect mandala of growth. You can see how the giving and the receiving form an infinite loop, a harmonious song that the horizon catches and throws back to you as a blessing. The universe is finally echoing your name.\n\nThis is a day of 'Manifested Abundance.' It’s time to perform your own internal ceremony for the vision you’ve been carrying. Scream your intentions into the vastness and listen to the resonance. Today, your words don't just vanish—they carry the weight of a decree. If you have been asking for a breakthrough or a sign of prosperity, look to the wings of synchronicity. The high-flying ideas you've been nursing are ready to land in a structure that allows them to be shared with the world. Don't be afraid of your own success. Claim your seat at the summit and realize that the view from the top was always your birthright. The sky isn't just watching; it’s listening. Sing out.	I am a magnet for prosperity, balancing my spiritual sight with material wholeness.	Close your eyes and visualize a single note of music ringing out from your chest. Imagine this note traveling out to the horizon, hitting the sky, and returning to you as a rich, harmonious echo. Feel your body resonating with this feedback loop, aligning you with the frequency of abundance.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine yourself at the summit of a steep soil pyramid. Look down and see the Veldt as a perfect, glowing mandala. Visualize the spirit of the Eagle carrying your vision into the clouds, expanding your perspective until you see the infinite connections that fuel your prosperity.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Visionary Bird of Prosperity", "content": "Tz'ikin is the nawal of the bird, the eagle/condor, and vision. It represents the ability to see the big picture, rising above the details to perceive the interconnectedness of all things. Tz'ikin is the energy of prosperity, abundance, and the freedom of the spirit. Associated with the element of air and the sky, it carries a light, expansive, and high-frequency energy. It is the archetype of the visionary who brings messages from the divine to the earth. In daily life, Tz'ikin manifests as financial luck, good news, dreaming, and artistic inspiration. Its shadow aspect can be spacing out, greed, or becoming distracted by 'shiny objects' without grounding. Tz'ikin teaches us that abundance is a natural state of being when we align with our highest vision.", "keywords": ["Vision", "Prosperity", "Freedom", "Abundance", "Perspective"]}, "number": {"title": "The Harmonious Weaver", "content": "Tone 8 is the energy of resonance, justice, and the octave. Following the peak of the 7, the 8 represents the return to the material world but with a higher frequency. It is the number of the 'infinite loop' (infinity symbol), representing the continuous flow of spirit into matter and back again. Experientially, Tone 8 feels harmonious, balanced, and ceremonial. It is often associated with the male energy or the father, bringing structure that honors the spirit. It is a day of resonance, where actions echo loudly. While it fosters integrity and wholeness, its shadow can be rigidity or a dogmatic adherence to form over feeling. It is the weaver who tightens the threads to create a strong cloth.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Justice", "Resonance", "Infinity", "Ceremony"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a ceremony or ritual to honor abundance.", "Review your finances and envision them flowing in an infinite loop of giving/receiving.", "Look at a problem from a higher 'bird's eye' perspective.", "Express gratitude for the resources you already have to attract more.", "Share your vision with others; today your words carry resonance."], "title": "Harmonizing the Vision", "content": "The resonant balance of Tone 8 combined with the expansive vision of Tz'ikin creates a day of 'Manifested Abundance.' 8 Tz'ikin is a day where spiritual vision finds its harmonious landing in the physical world. It is traditionally a day of ceremony, specifically for asking for prosperity and clarity. The energy feels like a choir singing in perfect harmony—uplifting, powerful, and ordered. Today, the high-flying ideas of the Eagle are not just dreams; they are brought into a structure (8) that allows them to become real. It is a powerful time to align your financial and material goals with your spiritual values. If you have been asking for a sign or a breakthrough, 8 Tz'ikin often delivers it on the wings of synchronicity. The challenge is to receive the abundance without guilt and to ensure that your vision includes the well-being of the whole. The opportunity is to resonate with the frequency of prosperity."}}	{"title": "The Resonant Visionary", "content": "To be born on 8 Tz'ikin is to be a bridge between the heavens and the earth, gifted with the ability to manifest high visions into reality. You possess a rare combination of expansive imagination and structural integrity. You are the dreamer who actually gets things done, the artist who knows how to sell their work, the spiritualist who understands economics. Tone 8 gives you a natural sense of rhythm, justice, and balance, while Tz'ikin grants you the eyes of the Eagle—always seeing the possibilities, the trends, and the bigger picture. You are likely a natural magnet for abundance, often finding that opportunities come to you seemingly out of thin air.\\n\\nYour life path is one of mediating between the material and spiritual realms. You are here to demonstrate that spirituality and prosperity are not mutually exclusive. You may be drawn to philanthropy, business leadership, or the arts, where you can use your resources to uplift others. People trust you because you carry an air of authority and fairness (8), but they are inspired by you because of your optimism and freedom (Tz'ikin). You are a natural ceremonialist, instinctively knowing how to create spaces where people feel connected to something larger than themselves.\\n\\nThe challenge for an 8 Tz'ikin soul can be managing the intensity of your vision. You may become frustrated when others cannot see what is so obvious to you. There is also a shadow risk of becoming overly focused on material accumulation or status, losing the spiritual freedom that is your birthright. Your lesson is to remain the hollow bone through which the universe flows—holding onto nothing, but allowing the abundance to pass through you for the benefit of all. When you keep your vision clear and your heart open, you become a powerful agent of harmonious evolution."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#add5c7", "primary": "#111f1e", "secondary": "#416a69"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.854063	2026-04-25 14:38:01.323958
157	13	1	1	Kawoq	You fall into step with the caravan without ever remembering when you made the choice to follow. One moment you are alone on the road, listening to the quiet persistence of rain, and the next you are walking among them, your pace adjusting as though it has always belonged there.\n\nThe path beneath your feet is thick with mud, each step sinking slightly before releasing with a soft resistance. It feels as though the earth is aware of your presence, holding the impression of every traveler who has passed before you. Ahead, the caravan moves steadily, their shapes blurred by mist and distance, their lanterns glowing faintly through the storm.\n\nNo one turns to greet you, yet no one questions your presence either. The group shifts subtly, creating space as naturally as a body breathes. You find yourself walking among them without needing permission.\n\nThe rain does not come in waves or bursts. It is constant, patient, and thorough. It settles into your clothing, your skin, and eventually your awareness. At first, you try to resist it, tightening your shoulders, holding your breath, preserving some small part of yourself that remains untouched. But the storm does not negotiate. It simply continues.\n\nWhen a wagon wheel sinks too deeply into the mud, several travelers step forward without hesitation. There is no command, no leader directing them. Hands press into the wood, shoulders lean forward, and together they lift the wheel free. The moment passes without recognition, and the caravan continues.\n\nSomething inside you begins to shift. The storm is not something to wait out, nor something to conquer. It is part of the path itself.\n\nYou take another step, and this time, you allow the rain to fall without resistance.	The world doesn't ask for your permission before it begins to change.\n\nIt arrives the way rain does—quiet at first, then everywhere at once, slipping into the cracks you didn't realize were open. You may feel the instinct to brace yourself today, to tighten your grip on what feels stable, to hold your shape against something that refuses to hold still. But the deeper truth is this: the storm is not here to take something from you. It is here to meet you where you have already outgrown yourself.\n\nThere is a strange intelligence in what you are feeling. A quiet knowing beneath the discomfort. The places where you feel most unsettled are not random—they are precise. They are the edges of something ready to soften.\n\nYou are not losing control. You are being invited into a different relationship with it.\n\nWatch how your body responds. Notice where you resist, where you clench, where you try to stay dry in a world that has already decided to soak you through. There is no shame in that instinct. It has protected you before. But today, protection may look different.\n\nToday, it might look like allowing.\n\nIf you let yourself stand in it—really stand in it—you may begin to feel something unexpected. Not chaos. Not destruction. But movement. A kind of clearing that does not ask you to understand it before it begins.\n\nYou don't need to fix anything today.\n\nYou don't need to solve the storm.\n\nJust take one step. Then another.\n\nLet that be enough.	I allow what is unfolding to move through me without resistance.	Sit comfortably and close your eyes.\nTake a slow breath in through your nose, and let it fall out gently through your mouth.\nImagine a soft rain beginning to fall around you. Not harsh, not overwhelming—just steady.\nWith each inhale, feel the air cool and settle inside your body.\nWith each exhale, allow tension to drip off of you like water.\nYou don't need to change anything. Just let yourself be here, as you are, in this moment.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine yourself standing at the edge of a vast open landscape as a storm rolls in. The clouds are alive, but they are not threatening—they are cleansing. As the rain touches your skin, it dissolves old weight you've been carrying. Behind the storm, you sense something being born. Stay there long enough to feel that this storm is not here to harm you—it is here to begin something.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Compassionate Storm", "content": "Kawoq is the energy of the rainstorm, the midwife, and the turtle. It represents the duality of the storm—the force that can destroy but also the water that brings life. Kawoq is the energy of the family, the community, and the compassionate cleansing that clears the path for rebirth. It is the protective shell of the turtle and the fierce love of the mother. It asks us to value the collective over the individual and to allow the waters of emotion to flow freely to heal the hardened earth.", "keywords": ["Storm", "Midwife", "Compassion", "Community", "Cleansing"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of the Storm", "content": "The number 1 represents the spark of creation, the unity of all things, and the seed that contains the potential for the entire cycle. It is the beginning, the impulse to exist, and the singular focus required to start a new journey. In the Kawoq trecena, the 1 energy initiates a cycle of deep emotional cleansing and communal rebirth. It is the first drop of rain that promises the deluge. It acts as the gathering of clouds—a concentration of intent to wash away what is stagnant and to nurture the roots of the family and community.", "keywords": ["Unity", "Initiation", "Potential", "Seed", "Focus"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Initiate a conversation that heals a family rift.", "Take a ritual bath or spend time near moving water.", "Allow yourself to cry; tears are the storm that clears the soul.", "Set an intention for what you wish to 'birth' during this cycle.", "Clean your home to prepare a sanctuary for the new energy."], "title": "Initiating the Sacred Cleanse", "content": "1 Kawoq initiates the 13-day cycle with a powerful surge of cleansing energy. Today, the seed of the storm is planted. The singular intent of the 1 combines with the watery, communal force of Kawoq to begin a process of deep purification. This is not a day to hide from the rain; it is a day to stand in it. The energy asks you to initiate healing within your family or your own heart. It is the beginning of a cycle where we learn that true strength comes from softness, and that sometimes the old structures must be washed away to birth the new. The midwife is present; the labor begins."}}	{"title": "The Bringer of Renewal", "content": "To be born on 1 Kawoq is to be a force of nature, carrying the dual power of the storm and the shelter. You are a natural initiator of healing and community growth. Like the rain, you have the ability to wash away the old to make way for the green and new. You possess a strong, nurturing presence that draws others to you for protection and guidance. You are likely the 'midwife' in your social circles—the one who helps others birth their ideas, their true selves, or literal children.\\n\\nYour life path is defined by the rhythm of gathering and releasing. You accumulate wisdom and resources not for yourself, but to sustain your 'village.' You have a deep connection to the feminine mysteries and the cycles of nature. However, your intensity can sometimes be overwhelming, like a thunderstorm that stays too long. You feel things deeply and may struggle to distinguish your own emotions from the collective current.\\n\\nYour challenge is to learn the timing of the storm. You must know when to unleash the rain and when to offer the shelter of the turtle shell. When you master your own emotional tides, you become a powerful healer who can cleanse the world without drowning in it, offering a sanctuary where life can flourish."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#84ded3", "primary": "#13211f", "secondary": "#367068"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#9d9eb3", "primary": "#14131f", "secondary": "#444560"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#cf9284", "primary": "#201a2d", "secondary": "#613d55"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#6e788e", "primary": "#161922", "secondary": "#393c4e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.834045	2026-04-25 14:25:01.110127
20	2	7	7	Iq'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Breath of Spirit", "content": "Iq' is the nawal of the wind, the breath, and communication. It represents the spirit (Ruach/Prana) that animates all living things. Iq' is the messenger of the gods, carrying prayers up to the sky and inspiration down to the earth. It governs the respiratory system and the mind's agility. Iq' energy is quick, changeable, and purifying. It brings the winds of change that sweep away the old to make space for the new. In its shadow, Iq' can be fickle, angry (hurricanes), or prone to gossip and empty words. Its highest expression is the clear, inspired voice of the poet or the prophet who speaks truth from the spirit.", "keywords": ["Wind", "Breath", "Communication", "Change", "Inspiration"]}, "number": {"title": "The Summit of Vision", "content": "Seven is the number of the midpoint, the top of the pyramid, and the power of mystical alignment. Sitting exactly in the middle of the 1 to 13 cycle, Seven represents the ability to see both the past (1-6) and the future (8-13) simultaneously. It is a number of reflection, choice, and equilibrium. Unlike the static balance of Two or Four, Seven is a dynamic, spiritual balance. It is often a day where energy peaks or shifts. Experientially, a Seven day feels like reaching a lookout point—there is clarity, perspective, and a sense of 'anything is possible.' The shadow of Seven can be indecision born of seeing too many options or a detachment from the ground. It asks us to look at the whole picture before taking the next step.", "keywords": ["Midpoint", "Reflection", "Vision", "Mysticism", "Perspective"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Practice conscious breathwork or pranayama to align with the wind.", "Go to a high place (a hill, a rooftop, a balcony) to physically embody the perspective.", "Write a letter to your future self or to the universe.", "Ventilate your home; open windows to let fresh air and energy circulate.", "Listen to wind chimes or the sound of the breeze to clear your mind."], "title": "The Voice of the Summit", "content": "When the visionary peak of Seven combines with the communicative wind of Iq', we experience a day of 'Higher Inspiration' or 'Spiritual Perspective.' The energy is airy, expansive, and electric. It is one of the best days in the calendar for seeing the 'big picture' of your life and understanding the messages the universe has been trying to send you. The wind blows freely at the top of the pyramid, clearing away mental fog. You may feel a sudden shift in perspective regarding a problem that has plagued you, or receive a flash of insight that connects the dots of your past and future. It is a powerful day for prayer, meditation, and setting intentions, as the channel between earth and sky is wide open. The challenge is to stay grounded enough to catch these messages without getting lost in the ether. The wind can be erratic; use the Seven's balance to center yourself in the eye of the storm. Breathe deeply, listen to the silence between thoughts, and let the spirit speak."}}	{"title": "The Visionary Messenger", "content": "To be born on 7 Iq' is to be a conduit for higher truth and a catalyst for change. You stand at the crossroads of the seen and unseen, possessed of a mind that is constantly synthesizing information from both worlds. The number Seven gives you a mystical, reflective nature—you are a seeker who is always looking for the deeper meaning. Combined with the wind of Iq', this makes you a powerful communicator of spiritual or visionary concepts. You may be a writer, a philosopher, a traveler, or a teacher who brings 'fresh air' into stale systems. You have a knack for seeing the trajectory of things, knowing which way the wind is blowing before anyone else does.\\n\\nYour life is likely marked by periods of rapid change and movement. You are not meant to stay stagnant; your soul requires freedom and circulation. You are the person who brings the news, the new idea, or the necessary disruption that clears the air. People look to you for perspective because you seem to float a little above the fray, able to see the layout of the land with detachment and clarity.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is consistency. Like the wind, you can be unpredictable, here one moment and gone the next. The Seven energy can also lead you to over-intellectualize or detach from emotional realities. Your growth involves learning to land your ideas—to not just be the wind that blows through, but the breath that sustains. You are here to remind the world that spirit is as real as the air we breathe, and that change is the only constant."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#99e1d0", "primary": "#11201e", "secondary": "#317269"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.7433	2026-04-25 13:46:57.672343
207	16	12	12	Kawoq	The surgery is done, but the garden is raw, covered in the sap of the cut vines. Then, the sky opens. A warm, heavy rain begins to fall—not water, but thick, indigo fluid. It washes over the wounds, soothing and sealing them.\n\nAs the soil drinks the rain, the ground becomes translucent to your sight. You look down and see the truth: the roots of the remaining plants are moving. They are reaching out through the wet earth and knitting together into a single, massive knot. The garden is holding hands underground. You realize you did not grow a forest of individuals; you grew a family. The storm did not scatter them; it forced them to integrate into one unbreakable, resilient organism.	The surgery is over, and a heavy, indigo rain is falling to wash over the wounds. This isn't a storm of destruction; it’s a warm, emotional cleansing that seals the places where you had to cut. As the soil drinks this rain, the ground becomes translucent, revealing that the roots of your life have knitted together into a single, unbreakable knot. You didn't grow a collection of individuals; you grew a family. The rain has forced everything to integrate, turning a group of survivors into a resilient, collective organism. \n\nToday is the day for 'Collective Understanding.' It’s time to gather the people who have stood by you and recognize the profound safety of belonging. You are part of an unbreakable bond, a web of support that thrives on compassion rather than logic. Host the gathering, share the meal, and tell the stories of the storm. The air is fresh, and the people are emerging to rebuild with a wisdom that only comes after the clearing. Don't try to navigate this alone—you are a drop in a very powerful ocean. Let the empathy flow, mend the fences, and realize that your individual strength is nothing compared to the power of the 'we.' The calm has arrived, and it is beautiful.	I understand the power of our unity, for we are a family of roots knitted together.	Imagine a warm, heavy indigo rain falling over your body. Feel it washing away the grit and soothing any raw places where you have recently let go of the old. Every drop is full of compassion, sealing your spirit and preparing you for a state of total integration.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, look beneath the surface of the wet earth in your mind's eye. See the roots of your relationships and your dreams knitting together into one massive, unbreakable knot. You are not a solitary tree; you are part of a resilient family organism. Feel the profound safety of this underground unity.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Compassionate Storm", "content": "Kawoq is the nawal of the storm, the turtle, and the midwife. It represents the community, the family bloodline, and the power of feminine cleansing. Kawoq is the energy of the rain that washes away the dust and nourishes the crops. Associated with the element of water and the color green/blue, it carries a fluid, emotional, and collective energy. It is the archetype of the caregiver who holds space for birth and rebirth. In daily life, Kawoq manifests as family gatherings, emotional release, and the protection of the vulnerable. Its shadow aspect can be emotional overwhelm, lack of boundaries, or 'smothering' care. Kawoq teaches us that we are all drops in the same ocean.", "keywords": ["Community", "Compassion", "Cleansing", "Rebirth", "Midwife"]}, "number": {"title": "The Understanding of the Whole", "content": "Tone 12 is the energy of understanding, gathering, and the retrospective view. It represents the summation of the cycle's lessons before the final transcendence. It is the number of the 'crystal clear' comprehension that comes after the storm of the 11. Experientially, Tone 12 feels communal, settled, and wise. It is a day to gather the scattered pieces and make sense of them. It fosters cooperation and the ability to summarize complex experiences. While it is generally a positive energy, its shadow can be a refusal to move on or looking backward for too long. It is the librarian who organizes the stories.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Unity", "Cooperation", "Summary", "Review"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Reach out to family members or close friends to check in.", "Host a gathering or a meal that brings people together.", "Reflect on the lessons of the last 11 days with compassion.", "Allow yourself to feel and express emotions freely.", "Offer support to someone who is going through a 'rebirth' process."], "title": "The Gathering of the Family", "content": "The synthesizing wisdom of Tone 12 meets the communal heart of Kawoq to create a day of 'Collective Understanding.' 12 Kawoq is the energy of the Village Council. It is a day to come together, not to work or to fight, but to understand who we are as a group. The energy is soft, inclusive, and deeply healing. It suggests that our individual understanding (12) is incomplete without the compassion of the community (Kawoq). Today is excellent for resolving family issues through empathy rather than logic. It feels like the calm after the storm, where the air is fresh and the people emerge to rebuild together. The combination encourages us to look at the 'we' instead of the 'I.' The challenge is to not get lost in the collective emotional current, but to help navigate it. The opportunity is to feel the profound safety of belonging."}}	{"title": "The Compassionate Unifier", "content": "To be born on 12 Kawoq is to be the heart of your community and a vessel of profound emotional intelligence. You possess a soul that naturally understands the interconnectedness of all people. Tone 12 gives you the ability to see the sum of the parts, to understand the history and the context of situations, while Kawoq gifts you with immense empathy and the protective instincts of the midwife. You are the glue that holds groups together—the one who remembers birthdays, mediates conflicts, and ensures that no one is left out in the cold.\\n\\nYour life path is one of service to the collective. You are here to heal the family line, to build community, and to facilitate the rebirth of those around you. You may be drawn to professions in nursing, social work, counseling, or community organizing. You have a 'weather-wise' nature, often sensing emotional storms before they arrive. People feel safe with you because you offer understanding without judgment. You are a natural teacher, not by lecturing, but by gathering people and helping them learn from each other.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 12 Kawoq soul is the risk of drowning in others' emotions. Your boundaries can be porous, and you may take on the suffering of the world as your own. You might also struggle with dependency, fearing to be alone or defining yourself solely by your relationships. Your growth lies in learning that you can be the midwife without being the mother of everyone. When you cultivate your own inner sanctuary (the Turtle shell), your compassion becomes a sustainable, healing rain rather than a flood."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#7a5cc0", "primary": "#15181a", "secondary": "#343553"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.855784	2026-04-25 14:38:01.326151
37	3	11	11	Tz'i'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Dog of Justice", "content": "Tz'i' is the nawal of law, authority, and justice. It represents the dog, the guide, and the faithful companion. Tz'i' governs the natural order and the laws of the universe, as well as human legal systems. It is an energy of loyalty, protection, and unconditional love. However, Tz'i' also has a carnal side—it can represent instinct, desire, and the temptation to stray from the path. In its shadow, Tz'i' can manifest as judgment, betrayal, or legal trouble. Its highest expression is the 'Secretary of God'—the one who records the truth with absolute fidelity.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Law", "Loyalty", "Dog", "Truth"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Dissolution", "content": "Eleven is the number of dissonance, change, and the breaking of patterns. It is the energy that disrupts the status quo to clear the way for higher order. Eleven is often a challenge—it tests the structures we have built to see if they are truly sound. Experientially, an Eleven day can feel chaotic, surprising, or liberating. It is the loose brick in the wall. The shadow of Eleven is overwhelm or destruction without purpose. It asks us to be flexible and to find the freedom in letting things fall apart.", "keywords": ["Change", "Dissonance", "Liberation", "Testing", "Clearing"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Review your own 'code of ethics'; does it still fit who you are?", "Be careful with legal documents; read the fine print.", "Practice forgiveness for a betrayal (yours or someone else's).", "Spend time with a dog; observe its loyalty and presence.", "If a plan falls apart today, ask: 'What higher law is intervening here?'"], "title": "Refining the Law", "content": "Today, the disruptive force of Eleven meets the order-seeking energy of Tz'i'. This creates a day of 'Correction' or 'Karmic Adjustment.' The Eleven comes to shake up our ideas of justice and truth. It is a day where hidden things may come to light, or where rigid rules are broken to serve a higher law. You might feel a conflict between your instincts and your morals, or between what you want to do and what you 'should' do. The energy is testing your integrity. It is not a comfortable day for those who are hiding something, but it is a liberating day for those seeking truth. Old contracts (Tz'i') may be dissolved (Eleven) to make way for new, more authentic agreements. The challenge is to navigate the chaos without losing your moral compass. Trust that the disruption is actually a course correction. Let the Eleven strip away the hypocrisy so that the true justice of Tz'i' can shine."}}	{"title": "The Challenger of Systems", "content": "To be born on 11 Tz'i' is to be a revolutionary for truth. You possess a sharp mind and a deep sense of justice, but you are not content with the status quo. The number Eleven makes you a change-agent, someone who sees the flaws in the system and wants to fix them, often by breaking them first. Tz'i' gives you a strong moral compass and a loyalty to your cause. You are likely an advocate, a lawyer, a reformer, or a critic—someone who barks when they see injustice.\\n\\nYour life path is one of refining your own integrity. You may face many tests of character, situations where you must choose between the easy path and the right path. You have a complex relationship with authority; you respect true leadership but rebel against tyranny. Your challenge is to temper your revolutionary zeal with compassion. You can be harsh in your judgments. Your lesson is to learn that the highest law is love, and that true justice restores rather than destroys."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#afcfc8", "primary": "#132120", "secondary": "#486767"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.750125	2026-04-25 13:46:57.681358
21	2	8	8	Aq'ab'al					{"nawal": {"title": "The Dawn of Possibility", "content": "Aq'ab'al is the nawal of the dawn, the twilight, and the threshold. It represents the moment when night turns to day (and vice versa)—the mixing of light and shadow. Aq'ab'al is the energy of new beginnings, potential, and the realization of hope. It governs the polarity of young and old, darkness and light. It is a romantic, optimistic energy that sees the beauty in transition. In its shadow, Aq'ab'al can manifest as duality, deception, or the inability to fully emerge from the dark—staying in the 'half-light' of ambiguity. Its highest purpose is to bring the light of clarity to the darkness of confusion, acting as the harbinger of a new day.", "keywords": ["Dawn", "New Beginnings", "Duality", "Hope", "Transition"]}, "number": {"title": "The Weaver of Harmony", "content": "Eight is the number of wholeness, justice, and the octave. In Mayan tradition, it represents the masculine energy (related to the father) and the fabric of the weave. It is considered a lucky number, representing the completion of a harmonic cycle—like the notes in a musical scale returning to the tonic. Eight brings the energy of organization, return, and infinite flow. Experientially, an Eight day feels balanced, potent, and ceremonial. It is the traditional number for day-keeping rituals. The shadow of Eight can be rigidity or a feeling of being caught in a loop if the flow is not maintained. It asks us to weave the threads of our lives into a coherent pattern.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Harmony", "Weaving", "Ceremony", "Wholeness"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Wake up early to watch the sunrise and set a specific intention for the cycle.", "Organize your calendar or schedule to support a new habit.", "Perform a small ritual of gratitude (lighting a candle) for the 'dark' times that taught you lessons.", "Look for 'signs' or coincidences today; the veil is thin at the threshold.", "Wear colors that represent dawn (orange, pink, grey) to align with the energy."], "title": "Harmonizing the New Light", "content": "Today, the harmonic wholeness of Eight meets the hopeful dawn of Aq'ab'al, creating a day of 'Balanced Beginnings' or 'Ceremonial Renewal.' This is a very auspicious day. The Eight provides a stable, ceremonial container for the new potentials that Aq'ab'al brings. It is a day where the changes you are implementing (or the new chapters you are starting) can be integrated smoothly into the fabric of your life. The 'wildness' of the new is tamed by the harmony of the Eight. It is an excellent day for marriage, signing contracts, or initiating a long-term project. The energy feels like a sunrise witnessed from a perfectly built temple—beautiful, orderly, and sacred. The challenge is to ensure you are honoring both the light and the shadow. Aq'ab'al reminds us that every dawn leaves a night behind. Use the justice of the Eight to give thanks for what is ending as you welcome what is beginning. Weave the polarity into a single, strong cloth."}}	{"title": "The Harmonizer of Transitions", "content": "To be born on 8 Aq'ab'al is to be a weaver of hope and a master of timing. You carry the energy of the eternal dawn—a perpetual freshness and optimism that inspires those around you. The number Eight gives you a strong sense of structure, justice, and community standing, while Aq'ab'al fills you with the creative potential of the new day. You are the person who can walk into a chaotic or dark situation and see exactly how to bring the light in. You don't just hope for a better future; you have the organizational skills to build it.\\n\\nYour life path is one of bridging worlds. You are comfortable in the liminal spaces where others feel lost. You may find yourself working in fields that involve transition—hospice, midwifery, career counseling, or renovation—helping people move from one state of being to another. You have a romantic soul and an artist's eye for contrast. You understand that light is defined by shadow, and you are not afraid of the dark corners of the human experience.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is indecision or getting stuck in the 'in-between.' You may have a tendency to keep your options open for too long, loving the potential of the dawn so much that you hesitate to step into the full light of day. Your lesson is to commit—to choose a path and weave it into reality. When you do, you become a powerful agent of renewal, showing the world that every ending is simply the raw material for a beautiful beginning."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#dbb79e", "primary": "#141b1a", "secondary": "#62514c"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.74369	2026-04-25 13:46:57.673559
73	6	8	8	Kawoq	A sudden, whimsical storm of warm indigo rain sweeps through the Bazaar, but the droplets do not dampen the vellum; they dissolve the 'ink-clogged' debris of the community maps. This is the energy of 8 Kawoq—the justice of the Storm Midwife. You find yourself standing at a blocked drainage pipe made of ancient, rolled parchment. To proceed, you must join a group of Calligrapher shadows in a ceremony of reciprocity, using your hands to clear the stagnation. As the indigo water begins to flow freely, the Bazaar responds with a birth: a vibrant, new section of the city unspools from the wet silk beneath your feet. By restoring balance to the collective road, you have earned your place in its ongoing rebirth.	A drumbeat is echoing through the clouds today, calling you to the center of your own tribe. You may feel a profound sense of responsibility for the emotional climate of your home or workplace, sensing where the balance has tilted too far in one direction. This is the day of the Storm Midwife—the one who knows that the most intense moments of pressure are often the ones that lead to the most beautiful births. You are being asked to be the calm center of the tempest, ensuring that justice and mercy are served in equal measure. The energy of the day is a cleansing rain that targets the places where you have grown rigid or defensive. As the old structures dissolve, you are gifted with the vision to see a new, more collaborative way of being. This is not a solo journey; it is a celebration of the "we." By settling your debts of gratitude and offering your strength to others, you manifest a field of peace that survives any weather. Trust the wisdom of the turtle-shell: stay grounded, move with steady intent, and know that your protection is found in your connection to the whole. The storm is passing, and it is leaving a world that is fresh, fair, and ready for your next big step.	I stand as the calm center of the storm, protecting the vulnerable and honoring the bonds of my tribe.	Imagine a warm, indigo rain falling gently on your head and shoulders. Close your eyes and feel each drop dissolving a small piece of stagnation or isolation within you. Breathe in the fresh scent of petrichor and old books, and feel yourself part of a vast, connected community, all sheltering under the same great sky.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, see yourself in the Plaza of the Cleansing Rain. Join the shadowy calligraphers as they clear the blocked parchment pipes of the bazaar. As the water begins to flow, watch as a vibrant new section of the world unspools from the wet silk at your feet. Feel the justice of the storm as it births new life through the simple act of communal reciprocity.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Storm of Compassion", "content": "Kawoq is the Nawal of the storm, the turtle, and the midwife. It represents the family unit, community, and the chaotic but necessary energy that brings new life. Kawoq is the rain that nourishes the crops and the thunder that wakes us up. In human experience, Kawoq manifests as compassion, the drive to care for others, and the ability to weather emotional storms. It is the energy of the 'group' rather than the individual. When aligned, Kawoq brings abundance, renewal, and deep emotional cleansing; when misaligned, it can lead to overwhelm. It is the water breaking before the birth.", "keywords": ["Community", "Storm", "Compassion", "Rebirth", "Cleansing"]}, "number": {"title": "The Harmony of Justice", "content": "The number Eight represents the octave, the return to power, and the weaving of the spiritual into the material. In Mayan cosmology, Eight is the number of the 'Primordial Male' energy, mirroring the 'Primordial Female' of Nine. It is often associated with ceremonies and the harmonization of energy. Experientially, this energy feels like a solid, resonant chord—it is balanced, organized, and powerful. It is a day to take the insights of Seven and begin to apply them with authority. The shadow of Eight can be rigidity, but its light is the strength of integrity.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Balance", "Ceremony", "Reciprocity", "Fairness"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Host a dinner or gathering for friends and family.", "Perform a ceremony to bless your home and community.", "Offer support to someone who is struggling; be the 'midwife' for them.", "Celebrate a new beginning or a 'birth' of a project with others.", "Let yourself be held by the group; you don't have to do it alone."], "title": "Ceremony of the Community", "content": "When the ceremonial balance of Tone 8 meets the communal energy of Kawoq, we experience a day of 'Sacred Belonging.' 8 Kawoq is a day to celebrate the family—both blood and chosen. It is a powerful time for gatherings, feasts, and rituals that honor the collective. The energy is warm, abundant, and flowing. The storm of Kawoq is tamed by the harmony of the 8, resulting in a gentle, nourishing rain rather than a hurricane. It is an ideal day to acknowledge the support systems in your life and to give back. If there has been tension in your community, 8 Kawoq offers the energy to restore balance through compassion and shared experience. It reminds us that we are all in the same boat (or under the same shell). Open your heart to the group; there is strength in numbers today."}}	{"title": "The Pillar of the Family", "content": "To be born on 8 Kawoq is to be the beating heart of your community. You are the 'Ceremonial Midwife'—a soul dedicated to the well-being and rebirth of the collective. You possess a strong, nurturing presence that makes people feel safe and seen. The number 8 gives you a sense of authority and ritual; you are likely the one who organizes the holidays, remembers the birthdays, and holds the traditions together. You thrive in groups and have a natural talent for managing the complex emotions of others.\\n\\nYour life path is one of service and abundance. You are a provider, often manifesting resources to share with your tribe. However, the storm energy of Kawoq means your life may be periodically cleansed by intense emotional waves. Your challenge is to maintain your own balance (8) amidst the chaos of caring for everyone else. You are here to remind us that we are stronger together and that love is the only true shelter in the storm."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#89cdba", "primary": "#0c1614", "secondary": "#2a4d48"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.778002	2026-04-25 14:38:01.300154
22	2	9	9	K'at					{"nawal": {"title": "The Net of Abundance", "content": "K'at is the nawal of the net, the web, and the gathering. It represents the lizard (the seed-carrier) and the energy of abundance that comes from connection. K'at is the force that pulls things together—people, resources, ideas. It governs the harvest and the storage of grain. However, the net can also trap. K'at also represents our entanglements—debts, burdens, and emotional baggage that we carry in our 'net.' In its shadow, K'at can manifest as hoarding, feeling trapped by obligations, or being unable to let go. Its highest purpose is to gather what nurtures us and release what weighs us down, keeping our net light and full of blessings.", "keywords": ["Net", "Gathering", "Abundance", "Entanglement", "Release"]}, "number": {"title": "The Circle of Gestation", "content": "Nine is the number of the feminine, patience, and the completion of cycles (associated with the 9 months of pregnancy). It represents the deep, subterranean work that happens before manifestation. Nine is emotional, intuitive, and connected to the mysteries of life and death. Experientially, a Nine day feels slower, deeper, and more internal. It is not a day for quick results, but for nurturing what is growing in the dark. The shadow of Nine can be moodiness, withdrawal, or getting stuck in the past. It asks us to trust the timing of the universe and to care for the seeds we have planted.", "keywords": ["Feminine", "Patience", "Gestation", "Completion", "Depth"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Visualize a net of golden light and mentally place your worries into it to be transmuted.", "Pay a debt (financial or energetic) to clear your 'net.'", "Spend time organizing a collection or a storage space in your home.", "Connect with a female mentor or mother figure.", "Reflect on what you are 'pregnant' with—what project or feeling is almost ready to be born?"], "title": "Gestating Freedom", "content": "The feminine depth of Nine meets the gathering power of K'at, creating a day of 'Deep Sorting' or 'Nurtured Release.' Today asks you to look into your net—your subconscious, your emotional baggage, your stored memories—and see what is truly worth carrying. The Nine energy allows you to do this with patience and compassion, without the rush to just 'fix it.' It is a day of emotional accounting. You might feel the weight of old stories more heavily today, but this is so you can acknowledge them and prepare to set them down. It is also a powerful day for fertility and creativity; the 'net' is full of potential life waiting to be born. The challenge is the risk of becoming overwhelmed by how much you are carrying. If you feel heavy, remember that the purpose of the net is to hold the harvest, not the trash. Use the gentle, gestation energy of Nine to slowly untangle the knots. Nurture the connections that feed your soul and let the rest slip through the mesh."}}	{"title": "The Keeper of the Harvest", "content": "To be born on 9 K'at is to be a soul of deep abundance and complex emotional richness. You are a gatherer of life's experiences, carrying a net that is overflowing with stories, connections, and wisdom. The number Nine gives you a profound feminine intuition and a patient, nurturing nature. You understand that good things take time. K'at makes you a connector—you likely have a vast network of friends and resources, and you love to bring people together. You are the 'glue' in your community, the one who holds the collective memory.\\n\\nYour life path involves learning the art of release. Because you are such a powerful attractor and container, you can easily become weighed down by the burdens of others or by your own past. You may struggle with letting go—whether of possessions, relationships, or old hurts. Your journey is to learn that your net is magical; it will always refill. You do not need to hoard. You are a natural psychologist or archivist, able to sort through the clutter of the human psyche and find the gems hidden therein.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is avoiding the trap of your own making. You can become entangled in drama or obligations because you have a hard time saying no. Your lesson is to keep your net clean and repaired. When you master this, you become a source of infinite nourishment for the world, holding space for everyone without ever being trapped by anyone."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b6a75e", "primary": "#161710", "secondary": "#4b442b"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.74401	2026-04-25 13:46:57.67433
47	4	8	8	Tz'i'	When you descend from the rooftop, the city feels changed — not repaired, not reborn, but softened. The seams where shadow and light overlap glow a little brighter. The streets feel less labyrinthine, as if they recognize you now.\n\nA soft warmth follows you, like the echo of the offering you made. You walk without rushing, guided by something quieter than thought.\n\nSoon the alleys widen into a long corridor between tall buildings whose windows shimmer with faint golden reflections. The air smells cleaner here, touched with a sweetness you can’t place. You notice that even the cracked pavement feels aligned, as if the city has straightened its spine.\n\nAt the end of the corridor, you find a gentle curve in the street that leads to a small open square — a place you are certain wasn’t here before. A shallow pool of water sits in the center, perfectly still, reflecting the twilight sky with uncanny clarity.\n\nYou step closer.\n\nThe surface of the pool shimmers. Shapes form — not memories, not shadows, but something more intimate. You see yourself, but not the version that’s been wandering through broken streets. This reflection carries a softness you don’t remember letting yourself have.\n\nThen another shape joins the reflection.\n\nIt is not a person. It is a presence made of warm gold and gentle movement, shaped like a long, flowing ribbon of light. It curls beside your reflection the way a loyal companion would sit at your side. It radiates a simple message without words:\n\nYou are not alone.\n\nThe pool glows brighter. Threads of soft light rise from its surface, swirling around you like faithful guardians. They carry neither judgment nor demand. They feel like patience, like forgiveness, like unconditional loyalty offered without condition.\n\nYour chest loosens. You didn’t realize how tightly you’d been holding yourself together.\n\nThe golden-ribbon presence nudges the water, breaking the reflection. Rings ripple outward, catching glimmers of both cities — the broken one and the luminous one — unifying them for a brief, breath-stealing moment.\n\nThen the pool settles. The presence fades into the warm air.\n\nBut the feeling remains.\n\nLove that asks for nothing.\n\nLoyalty that doesn’t bind.\n\nForgiveness that doesn’t erase but soothes.\n\nYou leave the square lighter than you arrived, carrying a softness you once believed was no longer meant for you.	Today softens the edges of your heart. You may feel more open, more trusting, more willing to let warmth in. Not because you are naïve — because you are healing.\n\nThis is the energy of loyalty that nourishes rather than binds. Something or someone may remind you that you are not walking your path alone. Even if no one appears outwardly, an inner presence rises — a deeper self, a quiet guide, a sense of companionship you haven’t felt in a while.\n\nLet yourself receive the softness. Let yourself trust what feels genuinely warm. Let love — in all its forms — meet you halfway.	I honor connections that guide me toward balance and love.	Close your eyes and imagine walking into a quiet square at twilight. In the center lies a perfectly still pool, mirroring the sky. Kneel beside it.\n\nAs you look into the water, see a soft reflection of yourself — not wounded or weary, but tender and honest. A golden ribbon of light curls beside the reflection, a loyal spirit of warmth and unconditional care.\n\nLet the presence rest near you. Breathe in its gentleness. Feel the tight spaces in your chest loosen.\n\nNow imagine touching the surface of the pool. Rings of golden light ripple outward, blending shadow and luminous reflections into a unified glow. Allow that harmony to enter you.\n\nThank the guardians of loyalty and truth. When you’re ready, rise from the square and open your eyes, carrying that gentle loyalty with you.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Dog of Justice", "content": "Tz'i' is the nawal of law, authority, and justice. It represents the dog, the guide, and the faithful companion. Tz'i' governs the natural order and the laws of the universe. It is an energy of loyalty, protection, and unconditional love. In its shadow, Tz'i' can manifest as judgment, betrayal, or sexual temptation. Its highest expression is the 'Secretary of God'—the one who records the truth with absolute fidelity.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Law", "Loyalty", "Dog", "Truth"]}, "number": {"title": "The Weaver of Harmony", "content": "Eight is the number of wholeness, justice, and the octave. It represents the completion of a harmonic cycle and the masculine energy. Eight is the weaver, bringing together threads to create a pattern. It is considered a lucky, ceremonial number. Experientially, an Eight day feels balanced, potent, and organized. It is a time of return and reciprocity. The shadow of Eight can be rigidity. It asks us to weave the threads of our lives with integrity.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Justice", "Wholeness", "Weaving", "Ceremony"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Review any legal documents or contracts carefully.", "Stand up for someone who is being treated unfairly.", "Practice loyalty to a friend or partner.", "Reflect on where you might be judging yourself or others too harshly.", "Trust that the universe is balancing the scales, even if you can't see it yet."], "title": "The Apex of Justice", "content": "When the harmonic justice of Eight meets the legal authority of Tz'i', we have a day of 'Absolute Law' or 'Divine Justice.' This is a day where the scales are balanced. It is one of the best days in the calendar for legal matters, signing contracts, or seeking resolution to a conflict. The energy is clear, fair, and authoritative. The unconditional love of the dog (Tz'i') is structured by the harmony of the Eight, creating a 'tough love' vibration that seeks truth above all else. If you have been acting with integrity, this day brings rewards and protection. If you have been out of alignment, it may bring a correction. The challenge is to not be too rigid or judgmental. Justice is not just about rules; it is about love and balance. Use this day to realign yourself with your own highest truth. Be loyal to your soul's code."}}	{"title": "The Keeper of the Code", "content": "To be born on 8 Tz'i' is to be a pillar of justice and a guardian of the truth. You possess an innate sense of right and wrong that guides your every move. The number Eight gives you a love for order and harmony, while Tz'i' endows you with loyalty and a protective instinct. You are the faithful friend, the honest lawyer, the fair judge. People trust you implicitly because they know you cannot lie. You have a 'golden retriever' energy—loving, loyal, but fierce if your pack is threatened.\\n\\nYour life path is one of upholding the law—whether that is man's law or spiritual law. You may find yourself in positions of authority where you must make difficult decisions. Your challenge is to balance justice with mercy. You can be prone to black-and-white thinking or moral rigidity. Your lesson is to learn that true justice includes compassion and that we are all human and prone to error. When you lead with love, your authority becomes a source of safety for everyone around you."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#9ecbc7", "primary": "#111d1d", "secondary": "#395353"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#af737f", "primary": "#2d3368", "secondary": "#544884"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#c27a24", "primary": "#0e0920", "secondary": "#643e34"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#ac655f", "primary": "#2b2737", "secondary": "#684257"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.760377	2026-04-25 13:46:57.717293
169	13	13	13	B'atz'	The storm surrounds the caravan as the moment arrives, not in chaos, but in a steady, rhythmic presence that feels almost intentional. Everything that has led to this point gathers at once—the effort, the strain, the moments of connection, the quiet acts of support that have held the group together.\n\nThe traveler within the wagon moves through the final stages of labor, supported by those around them. Hands move with care and purpose. Breath is shared, guided, steadied. No one acts alone. Each movement is part of something larger, something that has been building since the beginning of the journey.\n\nTime feels different here, stretched and woven together. The past and present seem to overlap, each moment connected to the next by an invisible thread. You feel it clearly now, the way every step you have taken has led here, the way every experience has become part of a pattern you are only just beginning to see.\n\nAnd then, within the steady presence of the storm, something new enters the world.\n\nThe moment is not loud or dramatic, but it is undeniable. A shift moves through the caravan, not as a reaction, but as a recognition. Something has changed, not only for the one who carried it, but for all of you.\n\nThe rain softens, not stopping, but taking on a different quality. It feels lighter, almost luminous, as though it is no longer washing things away, but nourishing what has been brought into being.\n\nYou stand among the others, no longer separate, no longer uncertain of your place. The journey has not ended, and the storm has not passed. But you understand now that neither was meant to.\n\nThe path continues, and you continue with it, carrying the quiet knowledge that you are not simply moving through the storm.\n\nYou are part of what it creates.	Everything is connecting.\n\nNot in a way that demands explanation, but in a way that can be felt if you pause long enough to notice. The experiences, the challenges, the moments that once felt separate now begin to reveal themselves as part of a larger pattern.\n\nYou may find yourself reflecting on where you started and where you are now. Not just externally, but internally. The way you respond. The way you feel. The way you understand yourself and your place within your life.\n\nSomething has shifted.\n\nNot because everything is resolved.\n\nBut because you are no longer relating to it in the same way.\n\nThere is a sense of completion here—not an ending, but a weaving. Threads coming together to form something cohesive, something meaningful, something that can now be carried forward with clarity.\n\nTake a moment to recognize that.\n\nTo acknowledge what has changed.\n\nTo feel the weight and the lightness of it at the same time.\n\nThis is not the end of the journey.\n\nBut it is the end of this chapter.\n\nAnd what you carry forward now is different than what you began with.\n\nMore integrated.\n\nMore aligned.\n\nMore you.	I honor the journey that has shaped me and carry its wisdom forward.	Sit comfortably and close your eyes.\nTake a slow, steady breath.\nFeel your entire body as one connected space.\nNotice how far you've come, even if you can't fully see it.\nLet yourself rest in that awareness.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine threads of light weaving through your entire being, connecting every experience, every lesson, every moment. They form a complete pattern—not perfect, but whole. The storm has passed, and in its wake, something new stands quietly within you.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Weaver of Time", "content": "B'atz' is the thread of time, the artist, and the weaver of destiny. It represents creativity, the arts, and the beginning of new cycles. B'atz' is the monkey, the playful trickster who holds the sacred calendar. It governs the weaving together of community and purpose. It reminds us that we are the artists of our own lives.", "keywords": ["Creativity", "Weaving", "Time", "Art", "Joy"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascension of Spirit", "content": "The number 13 represents completion, ascension, and the spirit world. It is the final step where energy transcends physical form. 13 is a number of great power, sensitivity, and psychic expansion. It brings the cycle to a close and offers a connection to the ancestors. In the Kawoq trecena, 13 is the rainbow after the storm. We ascend, renewed and cleansed, into a new creation.", "keywords": ["Ascension", "Completion", "Spirit", "Ancestors", "Renewal"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Start a creative project that feels 'divinely inspired.'", "Celebrate the end of the cycle with music or dance.", "Visualize the thread connecting you to your ancestors and descendants.", "Look for the beauty in everything today.", "Laugh; the monkey reminds us that the game is meant to be played."], "title": "Weaving the Cosmic Tapestry", "content": "13 B'atz' is the magnificent conclusion to the Kawoq trecena. The storm has passed, the earth is clean, and now we weave the new timeline. The 13 elevates the creativity of B'atz' to a cosmic level. Today, we are not just weaving our own lives; we are weaving with the spirit world. It is a day of celebration, of art, and of recognizing the beautiful pattern that connects us all. The cleansing was for this: so that the thread would be bright and strong. The energy is joyful, transcendent, and full of potential. We step out of the trecena as master weavers, ready to create a new world."}}	{"title": "The Cosmic Weaver", "content": "To be born on 13 B'atz' is to be a visionary artist of the highest order. You possess a direct line to the divine creative source. You are here to weave the threads of time, spirit, and matter into a new reality. You have a playful, trickster energy that hides a profound wisdom. You see the connections that no one else sees. You are a natural unifier, bringing people together through art, humor, and shared vision.\\n\\nYour life path is one of transcendent expression. You are not bound by the rules of linear time or convention. You are a master of beginnings and endings. You may be drawn to the arts, to timekeeping, or to community building. You have a charisma that is otherworldly.\\n\\nYour challenge is grounding the infinite. You have so many ideas and such a high vibration that you can struggle to function in the mundane world. You may feel like a visitor from another dimension. Your lesson is to love the loom. When you apply your cosmic creativity to the fabric of everyday life, you become a magician, reminding the world that we are all threads in the same divine tapestry."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c9b790", "primary": "#10130e", "secondary": "#404436"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.838554	2026-04-25 14:25:01.126574
28	3	2	2	Imox					{"nawal": {"title": "The Dream of the Waters", "content": "Imox is the nawal of the primordial ocean, the collective unconscious, and the dream world. It represents the fluid, chaotic potential from which all form emerges. Imox is the energy of intuition, empathy, and the hidden currents of the psyche. It governs the waters of the earth and the waters of the body (blood, lymph). Imox is the source of artistic inspiration but also of 'divine madness.' In its shadow, Imox can manifest as confusion, emotional overwhelm, or a loss of touch with reality. However, its aligned state is the profound receptivity of the mystic who can hear the whispers of the universe. It is the womb of creation.", "keywords": ["Water", "Intuition", "Dreams", "Subconscious", "Collective"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "Two is the energy of relationship, polarity, and the dynamic tension between opposites. It represents the separation of the One into two—masculine and feminine, day and night, sun and moon. In the Mayan cosmology, Two is the number of the partner and the mirror. It brings choices into focus and asks us to find balance between competing forces. Experientially, a Two day feels like a conversation or a negotiation. It is rarely solitary; it involves the 'other.' The shadow of Two can be indecision, conflict, or seeing separation where there is unity. It teaches us that we define ourselves through our relationships and that duality is the engine of creation.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Balance", "Relationship", "Choice", "Mirror"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Share a dream with a partner or friend and explore its meaning together.", "Practice 'mirror gazing' meditation to connect with your deeper self.", "Be mindful of boundaries; it is easy to absorb others' emotions today.", "Create art that explores a duality (light/dark, happy/sad).", "Take a bath with sea salt to cleanse your energetic field."], "title": "Reflecting on the Dream", "content": "When the polarizing mirror of Two meets the watery depths of Imox, we enter a day of 'Reflective Intuition' or 'Dream Partnering.' The solar clarity of the previous day (Ajpu) now plunges into the subconscious ocean. Today is about understanding the dual nature of your own psyche—the rational mind vs. the intuitive feeling. It is a powerful day for relationships, but specifically the emotional and psychic undercurrents within them. You may find that you and a partner are telepathically linked today, or that your dreams provide a direct answer to a waking dilemma. The energy is fluid, sensitive, and permeable. The challenge is that the 'mirror' of the Two can reflect distortions when placed in the rippling waters of Imox. Be careful of projecting your own unhealed emotions onto others. Use the balance of the Two to navigate the waves; don't just float, steer. It is a day to find the harmony between what you see and what you feel."}}	{"title": "The Intuitive Partner", "content": "To be born on 2 Imox is to be a soul who navigates life through deep feeling and connection. You are the ultimate empath, possessing the watery intuition of Imox balanced by the relational focus of the number Two. You do not experience life alone; you are constantly feeling the emotional temperature of those around you. You have a gift for understanding the hidden dynamics in relationships—what is *not* being said is often louder to you than what is. You are likely a natural healer, counselor, or artist, using your sensitivity to bridge the gap between souls.\\n\\nYour life path involves learning to trust your intuition as a valid form of intelligence. You may struggle with the logical, rigid structures of society, preferring the fluid world of dreams and feelings. You are a 'mirror' for others, reflecting their deepest truths back to them, often without even trying. This makes you a magnetic but sometimes intense companion.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is maintaining your own center. Because you are so open and focused on the 'other,' you can easily lose yourself in the currents of someone else's life. You may struggle with codependency or emotional overwhelm. Your lesson is to build a strong vessel for your water—to learn where you end and others begin. When you master this boundary, you become a powerful conduit for collective wisdom."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#71cbbb", "primary": "#0e1c1a", "secondary": "#315750"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.747065	2026-04-25 13:46:57.685562
90	7	12	12	E'	You walk the path to the lake without hurry.\n\nThe forest is bright today—brighter than you remember seeing it. Light filters through the branches in long, gentle beams, illuminating the ground in soft, shifting patches. Every step feels familiar, but not routine. It feels like revisiting a place from childhood: the same, yet different because you are different.\n\nWhen the lake comes into view, something new stands beside it.\n\nA path.\n\nNot a trail on the earth—an illuminated path made of soft, glowing stones hovering just above the water’s edge. Each stone shines with its own faint color: blue, gold, green, violet, rose. They stretch out in a gentle curve across the shoreline, not leading away from the lake but around it, forming a looping arc.\n\nYou step closer, and the stones respond.\n\nEach one brightens when your shadow touches it, warming with a quiet hum, as if greeting you by name. You realize that the colors are not random. Each stone holds the memory of a day you have lived here.\n\nThe deep blue one echoes the stillness of the first day.\nThe pale rose one carries the trembling honesty of the second.\nAnother glimmers with dawn-gold, reflecting the in-between world of the third.\nOthers shimmer with knots loosened, power awakened, old selves released, clarity gained.\n\nThe path becomes a mirror—not of your face, but of your journey.\n\nYou walk slowly along the arc, touching each stone with the toe of your shoe or the palm of your hand. With every touch comes a small ripple of memory—not overwhelming, not heavy, just clear. You see the threads you’ve walked, the choices you’ve made, the moments that felt small at the time but now reveal themselves as turning points.\n\nHalfway along the path, you pause.\n\nThe arc curves inward, offering a vantage point you hadn’t noticed before. From here, the lake looks different—wider, deeper, more whole. The reflections of the sky and trees merge seamlessly. The places where dawn split the world in two, where serpent-light coiled, where seeds glowed, all exist together in a single, fluid image.\n\nFor the first time, you see the entire story at once.\n\nYou realize the lake was never the destination.\nIt was the teacher.\n\nEvery return to the water has changed you. Every moment you sat, breathed, watched, untangled, witnessed, or listened has shaped the path beneath your feet.\n\nYou place your hand on the final stone.\n\nIt is brighter than the rest, shimmering with colors that shift too quickly to name—like a path that is still being written. When you touch it, a soft warmth spreads through your chest, not of nostalgia but of readiness.\n\nYou understand: reflection is not the end of the journey.\nIt is the moment you recognize that you are walking it consciously.\n\nYou look once more across the lake. It shines back at you—not as a mystery to solve, but as a companion that has walked every step with you.\n\nWhen you leave the shore, the path of glowing stones slowly fades behind you, but something remains: the certainty that the way forward is alive, welcoming, and already unfolding beneath your feet.	Today brings gentle clarity.\n\nYou may find yourself thinking about where you’ve been—not with regret, but with recognition. Patterns make sense. Threads connect. Experiences that once felt random now reveal their purpose.\n\nThis is a day for reflection, for walking your inner path with awareness. Trust the perspective you gain today. Let it guide your next steps with quiet confidence.	I honor the journey I have walked, and I step forward with clarity, trust, and conscious intention.	Sit comfortably and imagine a curved path of glowing stones forming around you. Each stone represents a moment of your recent journey.\n\nWalk it slowly in your mind. Touch each one. Let its memory rise and fade without pressure or judgment.\n\nWhen you reach the final stone, place your hand on it and silently say:\n“My path is mine to walk, and I walk it with awareness.”\n\nOffer gratitude to the ancient guardians of travelers, seekers, and wandering souls. Then gently return to your breath and open your eyes.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Pathfinder", "content": "E' is the Nawal of the path, the road, and the journey. It represents the energy of movement, exploration, and the exchange of wisdom that comes from travel. E' governs the physical roads we walk as well as the spiritual destiny we are carving out. In human experience, it manifests as curiosity, restlessness, and a desire to see what lies beyond the horizon. It is the archetype of the Guide. When aligned, E' brings clarity of direction; when misaligned, it can lead to aimless wandering.", "keywords": ["Path", "Journey", "Exploration", "Destiny", "Guidance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Crystal of Understanding", "content": "The number Twelve represents the grouping together, the village, and the understanding that comes from retrospection. In Mayan cosmology, Twelve is the energy of the 'Great Gathering.' It stabilizes the chaos of Eleven and integrates the lessons learned. Experientially, this energy feels inclusive, cooperative, and wise. It is a day to summarize, to discuss, and to connect the dots. The shadow of Twelve can be difficulty with individuality, but its light is the strength of the collective mind.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Integration", "Cooperation", "Review", "Community"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Share a story from your life journey with a group.", "Reflect on the people who have walked with you so far.", "Plan a group trip or a community outing.", "Seek advice from a mentor or a 'guide' figure.", "Acknowledge that every person you meet is a teacher on your path."], "title": "The Collective Journey", "content": "When the integrative understanding of Tone 12 meets the traveling energy of E', we arrive at a day of 'Shared Destiny.' 12 E' is the caravan. It represents the realization that we are not walking the path alone, but are part of a great migration of souls. Today is an excellent day to share your journey with others—tell your story, listen to theirs, and realize how your paths intersect. The energy supports summing up the lessons of your recent travels (inner or outer). It is a day to look at the map together and decide on the next leg of the trip. 12 E' brings a sense of belonging to the road; the path itself becomes the village. If you have felt lost, look to your companions for guidance today. The wisdom is in the group. Walk together, and the road will be easy."}}	{"title": "The Guide of the People", "content": "To be born on 12 E' is to be a shepherd of souls on the journey of life. You are the 'Collective Compass'—someone who gathers experience from your travels and uses it to help the village find its way. You are likely a natural teacher, storyteller, or tour guide (literal or metaphorical). You love to explore, but you love it even more when you can share the discovery with others. You are not a solitary wanderer; you need the company of the caravan.\\n\\nYour life path is one of gathering wisdom through movement and sharing it to build understanding. The number 12 gives you a gift for synthesis; you can take disparate experiences and weave them into a coherent map. Your challenge is to ensure that you don't lose your own direction while trying to herd the cats. You are here to remind us that while we each walk our own path, we are all heading home together."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c1d2c9", "primary": "#0e191a", "secondary": "#394645"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.791444	2026-04-25 13:46:57.771044
165	13	9	9	Kej	By dawn, the road has led the caravan into a forest so old and rain-fed that the air itself feels green. Water drips from high branches in slow, measured rhythms, and the storm, though still present, loses its harshness beneath the shelter of leaves. Every sound is softened here: the creak of wheels, the shuffle of boots over roots, the breath of the horses, the low murmurs between travelers.\n\nYou feel the change in your body before you fully register it in your mind. Your shoulders lower. Your jaw unclenches. Your breath deepens without effort, as if the forest has reached into you and adjusted something quietly out of place.\n\nThe path winds between trunks draped in moss, and on either side the undergrowth glows with the dark richness of things well watered and deeply rooted. The travelers move differently here. More slowly, but not from fatigue. Their steps seem to listen before they land. Even the restless one has softened, their attention no longer cast toward escape, but toward the living world immediately around them.\n\nAt midday the caravan stops beside a clearing where rainwater has gathered in a shallow pool ringed by ferns and stones. Some travelers kneel to wash their hands. Others lean against tree trunks with closed eyes, letting the forest hold them. No one calls it rest, though that is partly what it is. It feels more like rebalancing.\n\nYou wander a little way from the others, not to leave them, but to feel the land directly beneath your own feet. The rain filters through the canopy in silver threads. Somewhere in the distance a bird calls once, then again. You place your hand against the bark of a tree and feel, beneath the wet roughness of its surface, a steadiness so complete it almost undoes you.\n\nThe storm and the forest are not opposing forces here. One nourishes what the other roots. One cleanses what the other steadies. Standing there, you understand balance differently than before. Not as stillness. Not as perfection. But as the ability to let strength and softness exist in the same body, the same day, the same breath.\n\nWhen you return to the caravan, the group feels subtly renewed. The covered wagon remains at the center, its importance deepening, yet the entire caravan seems better able to hold that importance now. As the road leads onward through the dripping green, you carry some of the forest with you, a steadier axis around which the storm can turn.	After intensity, there is a natural movement toward balance.\n\nToday carries a steadying energy, one that invites you back into your body, back into your environment, back into the simple experience of being present. You may notice a desire to slow down, to reconnect with something tangible, something real.\n\nThis is not a step backward.\n\nThis is integration.\n\nYou have moved through emotional depth, through release, through transformation. Now your system is asking for alignment. For grounding. For a moment to recalibrate before continuing forward.\n\nSpend time with what feels stable.\n\nNature, if it's available. Stillness, if you can access it. Even small actions—walking, breathing, noticing the physical world around you—can create a sense of balance that supports everything else you've been moving through.\n\nThere is strength in this kind of presence.\n\nNot the kind that pushes or forces, but the kind that holds steady regardless of what is happening around it.\n\nYou are learning how to move within intensity without being consumed by it.\n\nThat is not a small thing.\n\nThat is mastery in motion.	I move through life with balance, presence, and steady awareness.	Sit comfortably and close your eyes.\nBring your attention to your breath.\nNotice the rhythm—inhale, exhale.\nIf it feels uneven, gently guide it into a steady flow.\nLet your body settle into that rhythm.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine yourself standing in a calm forest after rain. Everything is balanced—light and shadow, stillness and movement. You feel yourself becoming part of that balance. Nothing needs to be forced. Everything already knows how to align.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Guardian of the Wild", "content": "Kej is the deer, the sovereign of the wilderness, and the keeper of the four directions. It represents strength, agility, and a deep, harmonious connection with nature. Kej carries the energy of authority that is earned through grace. It asks us to stand tall and find our rightful place within the ecosystem.", "keywords": ["Nature", "Strength", "Balance", "Leadership", "Harmony"]}, "number": {"title": "The Circle of Life", "content": "The number 9 represents the feminine principle, gestation, and the circle of life. It is the number of the nine months of pregnancy and the deep, internal nurturing of the dark. 9 brings patience and stealth. In the Kawoq trecena, 9 represents the gestation of the new life that the storm has watered. It is the quiet growth in the forest.", "keywords": ["Gestation", "Feminine", "Patience", "Depth", "Mystery"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Spend time alone in the woods or a park; just listen.", "Connect with the four directions in a quiet ritual.", "Nurture your physical body with natural foods and rest.", "Trust the slow, invisible growth of your projects.", "Stand barefoot on the earth and feel the pulse of the planet."], "title": "Gestating in the Wild", "content": "9 Kej brings a deep, feminine power to the wilderness. It is the image of the pregnant deer in the forest—alert, strong, yet carrying new life. Today, the cleansing of the Kawoq trecena turns inward to nurture the seeds of the new. The energy is quiet, elemental, and profoundly connected to the earth. It is a day to retreat into nature, to find a quiet spot, and to let your own strength gestate. The storm has passed, the earth is drinking the water, and life is swelling in the silence. We find our authority not in dominance, but in our connection to the cycles of the wild."}}	{"title": "The Nature Spirit", "content": "To be born on 9 Kej is to be a true child of the earth. You possess a gentle strength and a profound, intuitive connection to the natural world. You are the guardian of the forests and the animals. You have a feminine, nurturing quality (regardless of gender) that seeks to protect the wild places. You are comfortable in solitude, preferring the company of trees to the noise of the city. You carry a quiet authority that comes from knowing who you are in the great web of life.\\n\\nYour life path is one of stewardship and gestation. You are here to nurture the relationship between humanity and nature. You may be an herbalist, a ranger, or an artist who draws inspiration from the wild. You move through life with the grace of a deer, always alert but never aggressive.\\n\\nYour challenge is over-sensitivity. The 9 energy makes you porous, and the Kej energy makes you alert; modern life can be overwhelming for you. You may retreat too far into the woods to avoid the harshness of society. Your lesson is to bring the peace of the forest into the village. When you stand in your strength, you become a powerful leader who reminds the world of its sacred roots."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#86ad77", "primary": "#0c1615", "secondary": "#374537"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.836897	2026-04-25 14:25:01.122158
25	2	12	12	Kej					{"nawal": {"title": "The Stag of the Wild", "content": "Kej is the nawal of the deer, the four directions, and the natural world. It represents the balance between the wild and the tame. Kej is the guardian of the forest and the conductor of natural harmony. It governs strength, agility, and the authority of the shaman. Kej energy is noble, strong, and sensitive. It stands with one foot in the physical world and one in the spiritual. In its shadow, Kej can be dominating, manipulative, or overly stubborn. It can also be skittish or fearful. Its highest expression is the graceful leadership that respects the laws of nature and protects the sanctity of the earth.", "keywords": ["Deer", "Nature", "Strength", "Balance", "Four Directions"]}, "number": {"title": "The Crystal of Understanding", "content": "Twelve is the number of understanding, summation, and the gathering of scattered parts into a whole. It represents the family, the tribe, and the complex stability that comes after the disruption of Eleven. Twelve is the number of the 'council'—it holds space for all previous experiences to be integrated. Experientially, a Twelve day feels rich, cooperative, and reflective. It is a time to look back at the journey and see the lesson. The shadow of Twelve can be heaviness or the difficulty of managing too many moving parts. It asks us to find the unity in diversity.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Integration", "Community", "Cooperation", "Summation"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Spend time in a forest or park; listen to the 'council' of the trees.", "Hold a family meeting or team check-in to ensure everyone is aligned.", "Physically ground yourself: stand on the earth, do squats, or hug a tree.", "Reflect on the 'four directions' of your life: Work, Home, Spirit, Self.", "Eat simple, natural foods today to honor the deer's connection to the earth."], "title": "Integrating Natural Law", "content": "When the integrative understanding of Twelve meets the natural strength of Kej, we have a day of 'Holistic Balance' or 'The Council of Nature.' The energy today is stable, strong, and wise. It is a day to understand your place in the larger ecosystem—of your family, your community, and the planet. Twelve Kej asks you to bring all the parts of yourself into harmony with the natural order. It is an excellent day for group activities, spending time in nature, or resolving conflicts through a 'council' approach where everyone is heard. You may feel a sense of sturdy calm, like an old tree. The disruption of yesterday (11 Kame) has settled into a new, stronger landscape. The challenge is to not be too rigid or dominant in your quest for order. Let the 'wildness' of the deer soften the structure of the Twelve. Lead with grace, not force. Remember that true strength comes from balance, not from overpowering the opposition."}}	{"title": "The Noble Guardian", "content": "To be born on 12 Kej is to be a pillar of strength and a guardian of natural wisdom. You possess a regal, dignified presence that commands respect without you having to demand it. The number Twelve gives you a deep understanding of community dynamics and a desire for social cohesion, while Kej connects you to the raw power and balance of nature. You are likely a leader in your field, someone who can manage complex systems while keeping a 'human' touch. You have a shamanic quality—an ability to read the winds and understand the unspoken laws of a situation.\\n\\nYour life path is one of service through leadership. You are the 'chief' archetype, responsible for the well-being of the tribe. You may be drawn to environmental work, politics, coaching, or any role where you guide others toward balance. You are strong, but you are also sensitive; like the deer, you are always alert to the subtle shifts in your environment.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is the weight of the crown. You can be prone to taking on too much responsibility or becoming authoritarian when you feel out of control. Your lesson is to trust the strength of others and to remember that true leadership involves vulnerability. You are here to remind us that we are part of nature, not separate from it, and to model a strength that is as graceful as it is powerful."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b7b370", "primary": "#111917", "secondary": "#4f4c31"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.745029	2026-04-25 13:46:57.660025
35	3	9	9	Q'anil					{"nawal": {"title": "The Golden Seed", "content": "Q'anil is the nawal of the seed, the rabbit, and the star. It represents the spark of life, fertility, and the potential for organic growth. Q'anil is the energy of the planter and the harvester—the promise that what you plant, you will reap. It is a joyful, abundant energy that governs biological life and artistic creation. In its shadow, Q'anil can manifest as impatience, vanity, or problems with fertility. Its highest expression is the blooming garden—the realization of potential into beautiful form.", "keywords": ["Seed", "Harvest", "Fertility", "Star", "Creation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Circle of Gestation", "content": "Nine is the number of patience, the feminine, and the completion of cycles. It is associated with the nine months of pregnancy and the nine lords of the night. Nine represents the deep, subterranean work that happens in the dark before manifestation. It is an emotional, intuitive number. Experientially, a Nine day feels slower and more internal. It is a time for nurturing, planning, and waiting. The shadow of Nine can be moodiness, withdrawal, or getting stuck in the past. It asks us to trust the timing of the universe.", "keywords": ["Patience", "Gestation", "Feminine", "Depth", "Nurturing"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Spend time nurturing a plant or a garden.", "Work on a creative project in private; don't share it yet.", "Connect with feminine energy or a mother figure.", "Practice patience in a queue or traffic; see it as time given, not lost.", "Visualize your biggest dream as a glowing seed in your belly."], "title": "Gestating the Star", "content": "When the feminine depth of Nine meets the fertile seed of Q'anil, we enter a day of 'Deep Gestation' or 'Nurtured Potential.' This is a profoundly creative and fertile day. The seed (Q'anil) is being held in the womb of the Nine, growing in the dark, safe and warm. It is not a day to force results or to pull the plant up to check the roots. It is a day to water, to sing to, and to trust your creations. Whether you are birthing a child, a project, or a new version of yourself, 9 Q'anil asks for patience and tender care. The energy is soft, golden, and heavy with promise. It is an excellent day for working on long-term projects or for healing reproductive/creative blocks. The challenge is the wait. Q'anil wants to bloom, but Nine says 'not yet.' Trust the timing. The longer the gestation, the more robust the life that emerges."}}	{"title": "The Nurturer of Dreams", "content": "To be born on 9 Q'anil is to be a cosmic gardener with a touch of magic. You possess a deep, nurturing spirit and a profound connection to the cycles of life. The number Nine gives you patience and intuition, while Q'anil fills you with creative potential and a love for beauty. You are likely the person who helps others grow—a teacher, a parent, a mentor, or an artist whose work feeds the soul. You understand that everything has its season, and you are rarely in a rush.\\n\\nYour life path is one of bringing things to fruition. You may have a 'green thumb' in all areas of life—plants, businesses, and relationships seem to thrive under your care. You have a quiet, magnetic abundance. However, you can sometimes be overly protective or hesitant to let your creations go out into the world. Your lesson is to trust that you have prepared them well. You are here to populate the world with beauty and to remind us that life is a miracle worth waiting for."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#bfb36f", "primary": "#101311", "secondary": "#403d31"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.74947	2026-04-25 13:46:57.693257
166	13	10	10	Q'anil	Something in the caravan has been growing quietly, and on the tenth day that growth can no longer be mistaken for possibility alone. It has become presence. It has become form.\n\nThe traveler within the covered wagon is no longer hidden in the same way. Though the draped cloth still shields them from direct view, their changing condition shapes the movements of everyone around them. The wagon is attended with greater care. Its wheels are checked more often. Hands steady its frame when the road turns rough. Water is brought before it is asked for. Blankets are dried near lantern heat and returned still warm.\n\nThe storm, too, feels altered. The rain no longer strikes with the randomness of earlier days. It falls in a nourishing rhythm, as though the sky itself has entered into agreement with what is ripening among you. The earth beneath the caravan, though wet, is no longer treacherous. It has become strangely receptive, as if all the previous days of cleansing and release have prepared the way for this one.\n\nYou notice how the group moves now, not with urgency but with responsibility. The earlier chaos has given way to a kind of maturity. The restless one has become attentive. The overwhelmed one now notices when another begins to falter. The one who has held space from the beginning remains steady as ever, but their steadiness is no longer solitary. It has spread.\n\nBy afternoon, the one inside the wagon shifts with a new intensity. Their breath changes. The space around the wagon seems to gather inward, drawing focus the way a fruit gathers sweetness before it opens. No one says what everyone understands.\n\nThe long work of becoming has entered its final stage.\n\nYou walk close to the wagon now, listening to the rain, to the wheels, to the subtle changes in breath from within. Everything in the caravan feels ripened by the journey, not only the life waiting to emerge, but the people who will receive it. What has been seeded is readying itself for manifestation, and the whole storm-dark world seems to lean closer in witness.	Something you have been carrying is beginning to take form.\n\nIt may not be fully visible yet, but you can feel it. A sense of readiness, of something gathering into shape after a period of growth that was mostly unseen. This is not sudden. It is the result of everything you have moved through.\n\nThe effort.\n\nThe release.\n\nThe reflection.\n\nAll of it has been preparing this moment.\n\nYou may feel a quiet anticipation today, a sense that something is about to shift into visibility. The important thing is not to rush it. Manifestation is not forced. It unfolds when the conditions are aligned.\n\nAnd they are aligning.\n\nYour role is to remain present with what is emerging. To support it without trying to control it. To trust that what has been developing beneath the surface knows how to continue.\n\nThis is a moment of ripening.\n\nOf readiness.\n\nOf something becoming real.\n\nStay with it.\n\nYou are closer than you think.	I trust what is growing within me to unfold in its own time.	Close your eyes and take a deep breath.\nBring awareness to something in your life that is growing or changing.\nYou don't need to rush it.\nJust observe it, like watching a plant grow.\nStay with that feeling of quiet trust.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine a glowing seed within you. With each breath, it slowly opens, revealing layers of light. It does not rush. It unfolds exactly as it should. You realize that growth happens even when you are not watching.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Seed of Abundance", "content": "Q'anil is the energy of the seed, the star, and the ripening crop. It represents fertility, potential, and the inevitable unfolding of life. Q'anil is the promise that what is planted with intention will grow. It carries a gentle, golden energy of nourishment. It reminds us to tend the soil and trust the process.", "keywords": ["Seed", "Fertility", "Abundance", "Growth", "Ripening"]}, "number": {"title": "The Wheel of Manifestation", "content": "The number 10 represents manifestation, responsibility, and the hands coming together. It signifies the agreement of community and the crystallization of intention into form. 10 brings a sense of weight and solidity. In the Kawoq trecena, 10 is the day the new life becomes visible. The storm's work is done, the sun is out, and the garden is blooming.", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Community", "Agreement", "Results"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Host a dinner party or share food with neighbors.", "Launch a project that is ready to be seen by the world.", "Plant a physical garden or buy fresh flowers.", "Acknowledge the growth you have made over the last 10 days.", "Make a toast to the abundance of life."], "title": "Manifesting the Harvest", "content": "10 Q'anil is a day of joyous manifestation and community abundance. The storm of Kawoq was necessary to water these seeds, and now, under the influence of the 10, they burst into fruit. Today is a day to celebrate the results of your emotional labor. The rebirth is no longer a concept; it is a reality you can touch and taste. It is a day for community gatherings, for sharing food, and for recognizing the fertility that exists in your life. The energy is golden, ripe, and heavy with blessing. We take responsibility for our harvest, sharing it so that all may be fed."}}	{"title": "The Manifestor of Beauty", "content": "To be born on 10 Q'anil is to be a bringer of abundance and a creator of community. You possess the 'Midas touch'—not just for gold, but for life itself. Where you go, things grow. You are a natural organizer, able to bring people together to create something greater than the sum of its parts. You have a sunny, optimistic disposition and a deep sense of responsibility toward your community. You are the one who ensures the harvest is brought in and that everyone gets a plate.\\n\\nYour life path is one of fruition. You are here to manifest beauty and to show others the potential within themselves. You are likely drawn to agriculture, business, or the arts—any field where you can nurture a seed into a star. You are reliable, generous, and deeply connected to the cycles of the seasons.\\n\\nYour challenge is superficiality. You love the bloom so much you may avoid the rot. You might struggle when things decay or fail, wanting everything to be perpetually ripe. Your lesson is to embrace the full cycle. When you accept that the compost is as holy as the flower, you become a true master of life, sustaining your community through all seasons."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#bac28e", "primary": "#151c1a", "secondary": "#505640"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.837257	2026-04-25 14:25:01.123254
167	13	11	11	Toj	The eleventh day begins with a heat you do not expect. It is not in the air exactly, for the storm remains cool and wet, but beneath it there is warmth, a hidden fire moving through the caravan like a second weather. Lantern flames burn brighter. The travelers' faces are more sharply lit. Even the rain seems to hiss when it strikes the rims of metal cups or the stones beneath the wagon wheels.\n\nBy now, everyone knows that what is coming will require more than attention. It will require offering.\n\nThe caravan stops before dusk in a place where flat stones rise from the mud like a half-buried altar. There, a small fire is built once more, not for ceremony in the same way as before, but for service. Water is heated. Cloth is dried. Herbs are laid out. Hands are washed and prepared. Every act becomes an offering because every act is done for something beyond the self.\n\nYou begin to see how sacrifice truly works. It is not grand or theatrical. It is the giving of what is needed when it is needed. The restless one gives up the instinct to flee discomfort and stays close. The one who once moved under invisible weight now lends their careful strength to practical tasks. The one who has guided all along gives without spectacle, their service so complete it almost disappears into the work itself.\n\nYou, too, feel what is being asked of you. Not heroism. Not perfection. Simply willingness. Your time, your attention, your steadiness, your body's presence in the circle of care. You bring water, adjust a lantern, hold a blanket edge against the wind, and with each simple action you understand more clearly that service is a kind of fire. It burns away self-importance. It clarifies intention. It makes warmth where warmth is needed most.\n\nThe storm presses close around the camp, but the center holds. Fire and rain, offering and cleansing, sacrifice and blessing. Beneath the wagon's canvas, labor deepens, and around it the caravan gives what it can, not counting cost, because love has already decided the answer.	Today asks something of you.\n\nNot in a demanding or overwhelming way, but in a clear and undeniable one. There is a moment where you will feel the opportunity to give—your time, your attention, your presence, your energy. And in that moment, you will understand that what you offer matters.\n\nThis is not about sacrifice in the way it is often misunderstood. You are not being asked to diminish yourself or give beyond your capacity. You are being asked to engage.\n\nTo participate in something that extends beyond your individual experience.\n\nThere is a quiet power in that.\n\nWhen you give from a place of alignment, something shifts. The act itself becomes meaningful, not because of how it is received, but because of what it activates within you. A sense of purpose. A sense of connection. A sense of being part of something larger.\n\nNotice where you feel called.\n\nIt may not be obvious at first. It may be something small, something simple. But if it feels genuine, it matters.\n\nThe fire you offer today does not burn you.\n\nIt illuminates what is already there.	I give my energy with intention and receive meaning in return.	Sit quietly and close your eyes.\nTake a slow breath in.\nAs you exhale, imagine offering something—kindness, energy, presence.\nThen as you inhale, allow yourself to receive.\nLet this exchange feel natural and balanced.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine a gentle fire surrounded by small glowing lights. Each light represents something given or received. You see that the flow never stops—it moves in cycles. The more freely you allow the flow, the brighter the entire space becomes.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Fire", "content": "Toj is the energy of offering, payment, and reciprocity. It is the sacred fire that transmutes matter into spirit. Toj represents the law of karma and the necessity of giving back to maintain balance. It is the day to pay spiritual debts and offer gratitude. It reminds us that the storm clears the debt of the earth.", "keywords": ["Offering", "Payment", "Reciprocity", "Fire", "Gratitude"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Resolution", "content": "The number 11 represents dissonance, clearing, and the testing of the structure. It has a high, thin vibration that shakes loose the non-essential. 11 is the energy of 'sorting'—separating the grain from the chaff. In the Kawoq trecena, 11 brings a final purification. It is the aftershock that ensures the cleansing is complete.", "keywords": ["Dissonance", "Clearing", "Testing", "Resolution", "Change"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Pay a debt you have been avoiding.", "Make a significant offering to charity or spirit.", "Burn a list of regrets or old patterns safely.", "Apologize where an apology is due; clear the air.", "Accept a challenge as an opportunity to balance your karma."], "title": "Clearing the Karmic Debt", "content": "11 Toj is a day of intense but necessary payment. The dissonance of the 11 meets the fire of Toj to burn away any lingering debts or imbalances. The storm of Kawoq has washed the exterior; now 11 Toj purifies the interior. It is a day to settle accounts, both financial and emotional. You may feel the heat today—a pressure to resolve things that have been hanging over you. It is a powerful day for ceremony, for feeding the fire, and for letting go of what you owe to the past. The clearing allows you to move forward light and free. The fire dries the earth after the rain."}}	{"title": "The Fire Cleanser", "content": "To be born on 11 Toj is to be a powerful agent of karmic resolution. You are a firekeeper who is not afraid of the heat. You possess a unique ability to transmute heavy energy into light. You are often the 'sin eater' of the family, the one who deals with the difficult issues so that others can be free. You have a strong sense of justice and reciprocity, but your path is rarely smooth. You learn through the friction of life, through trial and fire.\\n\\nYour life path is one of clearing and service. You are here to help balance the scales. You may feel a constant need to give or to pay back, which can make you incredibly generous but also prone to depletion. You have a high-frequency energy that can be unsettling to those who prefer stagnation.\\n\\nYour challenge is martyrdom. You may feel that you have to pay for everyone's mistakes. Your lesson is to know when the debt is paid. When you realize that you are worthy of receiving as well as giving, you become a powerful healer, using your fire to warm the world rather than burning yourself up."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c19373", "primary": "#10110f", "secondary": "#473831"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.837581	2026-04-25 14:25:01.124512
191	15	9	9	Kan					{"nawal": {"title": "The Serpent of Vitality", "content": "Kan is the energy of the plumed serpent, the Kundalini, and the vital life force that runs through the spine. It represents power, sexuality, evolution, and the DNA helix. Kan is the raw electricity of the universe—the spark that animates matter. It governs wisdom, justice, and the transformation that comes from shedding one's skin. In its shadow, Kan can be manipulative, ego-driven, or sexually exploitative. It is the energy of the sorcerer who uses power for personal gain. But in its light, it is the 'Wise Serpent,' the teacher who shows us how to transmutate our base instincts into higher consciousness. It is the force that pushes the corn stalk out of the seed and the human spirit toward enlightenment.", "keywords": ["Serpent", "Life Force", "Power", "Transformation", "Wisdom"]}, "number": {"title": "The Patience of Gestation", "content": "Tone 9 is the number of the Feminine, the circle of life, and the deep patience of gestation. It represents the 9 months of pregnancy and the dark, fertile soil where the seed transforms. After the active weaving of the 8, the 9 asks us to go inward and nurture what has been created. It is the energy of the 'Great Mother.' Tone 9 does not rush; it understands that true growth happens in the dark, away from prying eyes. It is a day of emotional depth, intuition, and strategic withdrawal. It concerns the larger cycles of life—destiny, karma, and the long game. It offers a soft, compassionate power that achieves its goals through persistence and love rather than force.", "keywords": ["Feminine", "Gestation", "Patience", "Nurture", "Cycles"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in physical movement or yoga to awaken your spine/energy.", "Be patient with your growth; power is building even if you can't see it.", "Honor the feminine aspect of leadership and wisdom.", "Trust your gut instincts; the serpent 'knows' through the body.", "Nurture a project or relationship that is in a delicate stage of development."], "title": "The Gestation of Power", "content": "9 Kan is a day of profound, quiet intensity. We have the patient, feminine gestation of the 9 holding the raw, masculine lightning of the serpent Kan. This creates an energy of 'incubating power.' It is not a day to explode into action, but to coil and gather strength. It represents the wisdom that is ripening within us. This is an incredible day for healing work, tantra, or deep internal alchemy. The 9 softens the sharp edges of the serpent, turning raw power into wise compassion. We are asked to look at where we are shedding skin in our lives and to be patient with the vulnerability of that process. The combined energy suggests that our greatest strength is currently underground, growing in the dark, preparing to rise. It is a day to honor the body's wisdom and trust the timing of your own evolution."}}	{"title": "The Wise Healer", "content": "To be born on 9 Kan is to be a vessel of ancient, transformative power. You are the 'Nurturing Serpent.' The number 9 gives you a compassionate, feminine, and patient nature, while Kan fills you with a high-voltage vitality and wisdom. You are a natural healer, often possessing 'hot hands' or an intuitive understanding of the body's energy systems. You do not just heal symptoms; you understand the deep, karmic cycles (9) that cause illness. Your presence is magnetic but soothing; you have the charisma of the serpent without its aggression.\\n\\nYour life path is one of evolution and service. You are likely drawn to the mysteries of life—birth, sex, death, and rebirth. You may work as a midwife, a yoga teacher, a doctor, or a spiritual guide. You have a deep respect for the processes of nature and understand that everything takes time to ripen. You are a 'keeper of the blood lightning,' able to hold high amounts of spiritual energy without burning out. People trust you with their deepest secrets because they sense your non-judgmental depth.\\n\\nHowever, the challenge of 9 Kan is managing your own intensity. You feel things deeply, and the 'coil' of Kan can sometimes result in inner pressure or anxiety if that energy isn't moved. You may struggle with the shadow of Kan—manipulation or misuse of sexual energy—if you do not stay aligned with your heart. Your soul's growth lies in trusting the feminine path of power: leading through love, healing through presence, and allowing your wisdom to unfold naturally rather than forcing it."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#85875e", "primary": "#191c19", "secondary": "#2f2c26"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.848744	2026-04-25 13:46:57.975693
199	16	4	4	B'atz'	The Wolf vanishes as the vines recede, leaving you on a patch of loose, shifting soil. The growth here is growing in a strange shape—a massive spiral that curls inward toward a glowing center. But the ground is unstable; the potential is there, but it has no form.\n\nYou realize that to stabilize this world, you must walk it into existence. You step onto the spiral path. At first, your feet sink into the dirt, but as you move, a change occurs. The friction of your movement causes the loose soil to knit together. Dust turns to gravel, gravel turns to smooth, glowing stone.\n\nWith every step you take toward the center, the chaotic vines snap into orderly rings, forming a structure around you. You are not just walking; you are weaving the foundation of the Veldt with your own momentum. You reach the center, standing on solid ground of your own making.	The world is waiting for you to walk it into existence today. You might find yourself standing on loose, shifting ground where your ideas feel brilliant but lacks a place to land. Don't wait for the foundation to appear—create it with the friction of your own momentum. Every step you take with intention today causes the dust to knit together, turning the gravel of 'maybe' into the smooth, glowing stone of 'done.' This is the masterstroke of the cosmic architect: the realization that playfulness and discipline are the two threads of the same master-weave. \n\nAs you move in your chosen spiral, notice how the chaotic vines of your life begin to snap into orderly rings. You are weaving a sanctuary with your own feet. It’s a day for the clever artisan, the one who can find the humor in the blueprints while ensuring every cornerstone is perfectly set. Don't be afraid to formalize the things that matter most to you. Draw the lines, set the boundaries, and finish what you started. The cosmos isn't interested in your abstract potential anymore; it wants to see the masterpiece you can build when you finally stop wandering and start weaving. The loom is ready, the threads are strong, and the design is entirely yours. Build something that can hold the weight of your dreams.	With every disciplined step, I turn the threads of potential into a lasting reality.	Sit in a posture that feels dignified and solid. Visualize a golden thread of light emerging from the base of your spine and weaving upward, spiraling through every vertebrae. Feel this thread organizing your energy, pulling the loose parts of your day into a singular, beautiful structure.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine yourself standing on a vast plain of loose, shifting stardust. With every mental breath, walk in a tight spiral. Watch as the friction of your steps weaves the dust into smooth, glowing stone beneath you. Feel the satisfaction of building a permanent sanctuary from the threads of your own intent.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Weaver of Time", "content": "B'atz' is the nawal of the thread, the monkey, and the weaver. It represents the creative life force that spins the fabric of time and reality. B'atz' is the artist, the trickster, and the initiator of new cycles. Associated with the element of fire and the arts, it carries a playful, clever, and masterful energy. It is the archetype of the artisan who weaves scattered threads into a beautiful tapestry. In daily life, B'atz' manifests as artistic expression, marriage, scheduling, and the unfolding of destiny. Its shadow aspect can be arrogance, manipulation, or becoming tangled in one's own complexities. B'atz' reminds us that we are the weavers of our own lives, holding the shuttle that moves between past and future.", "keywords": ["Creativity", "Weaving", "Time", "Artistry", "Initiation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Foundation of Form", "content": "Tone 4 is the energy of stability, structure, and definition. After the movement of 3, the 4 establishes a base, like the four walls of a house or the four legs of a table. It represents the four directions (East, West, North, South) and the four elements (Earth, Air, Fire, Water), grounding spiritual energy into physical reality. Experientially, Tone 4 feels calm, ordered, and reliable. It is a day for planning, organizing, and establishing boundaries. It brings the vague potential of the earlier numbers into concrete form. While it offers safety and predictability, its shadow can be rigidity, stagnation, or being 'boxed in.' It is the number of the builder who lays the cornerstone.", "keywords": ["Structure", "Balance", "Grounding", "Manifestation", "Stability"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create a solid plan or schedule for a creative project.", "Organize your physical space to allow for better flow.", "Commit to a relationship or partnership with a formal gesture.", "Weave disparate ideas into a coherent, structured whole.", "Ground your artistic impulses by finishing what you have started."], "title": "Structuring the Creative Tapestry", "content": "The combination of Tone 4's stability with B'atz's creative weaving creates a day of 'grounded artistry.' 4 B'atz' is the energy of the loom itself—the rigid frame that allows the thread to be woven into a usable cloth. This is not a day for wild, abstract splashing of paint, but for the disciplined application of skill. It is an excellent time to give structure to your creative projects, to organize your schedule, or to formalize a relationship. The playfulness of the Monkey (B'atz') is tempered and directed by the order of the 4, resulting in highly productive and tangible outcomes. It feels like the satisfaction of a craftsman seeing a design come to fruition. The energy supports taking the threads of your life—which may feel loose or chaotic—and weaving them into a solid foundation. The challenge is to maintain the joy of creation within the boundaries of necessary structure. The opportunity is to build a masterpiece that lasts."}}	{"title": "The Master Architect of Destiny", "content": "To be born on 4 B'atz' is to be a master builder of reality, blending the soul of an artist with the hands of an architect. You possess a unique ability to give form to the formless, taking wild, creative concepts and grounding them in practical, tangible structures. You are the weaver who not only spins the thread but also builds the loom. People see you as a reliable and stabilizing force, yet they are often surprised by the depth of your creativity and wit. You are likely drawn to fields where design meets function—architecture, engineering, event planning, or systems organization.\\n\\nYour life path is one of creating stability through creativity. You are here to show the world that art and order are not enemies, but partners. Tone 4 gives you a love for boundaries, rules, and foundations, while B'atz' ensures that what you build is beautiful and alive. You have a knack for timing and cycles, often knowing instinctively how long a project will take or when to launch a new venture. In relationships, you are a rock—steadfast and loyal—but you keep the spark alive through your playful, Monkey-like charm.\\n\\nChallenges for a 4 B'atz' soul usually involve a struggle with rigidity. You may become so focused on the 'plan' or the 'structure' that you lose the joy of the process. There is a risk of becoming a workaholic or resisting necessary changes because they threaten your established order. Your growth comes from learning to let the weave breathe. Remember that a tapestry is beautiful because of the tension in the threads, but if pulled too tight, it will snap. embrace flexibility within your strong foundations."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d188be", "primary": "#111617", "secondary": "#463944"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.852715	2026-04-25 14:38:01.321563
208	16	13	13	Ajpu	The storm passes, and the indigo clouds vanish. The Veldt undergoes a final, impossible transformation. The biological pulse stops. The swaying vines stiffen. In a wave of light moving from the center outward, the entire landscape turns to solid, unmoving gold.\n\nThe Veldt freezes in a moment of absolute perfection. It is a monument to the journey. The Grazers and the White Wolf step out from the golden trees and bow toward the center. You sit there, surrounded by the stillness of metal and light. The silence is not empty; it is heavy with presence. You have stabilized the chaos completely. You have brought the perfection of the Spirit World down to Earth, freezing time in a state of grace.	The clouds have vanished, and the world has undergone a final, impossible transformation. The biological swaying and the frantic growth have stopped. In a wave of brilliant light, your entire landscape has turned to solid, unmoving gold. This is the 'Golden Monument'—the moment where the chaos of your journey is finally stabilized into a state of absolute grace. The stillness is not an absence of life; it is the presence of perfection. You have brought the masterwork of your spirit down to earth, and it is flawless. \n\nToday is your 'Spiritual Victory.' Claim your divinity and stand in your full, radiant power. You have navigated the thorns, the storms, and the darkness to arrive at this solar peak. Celebrate your victories and honor the ancestors who whispered to you along the way. This is a day of mastery, where the rules of the physical world feel secondary to the light of the soul. You are a sovereign being of light, a hero who has fought for beauty and won. Don't be afraid to shine—just remember to hold the power with the humility of one who knows where the light truly comes from. The cycle is complete. You are the gold at the end of the road. Bask in it.	My light is eternal and my purpose is clear; I am the sun rising within myself.	Sit in absolute stillness. Imagine a wave of golden light moving from the center of your heart outward to your skin. As it touches you, feel your body becoming solid, unmoving, and perfected—like a monument of polished gold. You are a masterpiece of grace, and your journey is complete.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, visualize the internal sun rising within your chest. Its rays are made of absolute purpose and ancient power. See the White Wolf, the Grazer, and your ancestors standing at the edge of your golden Veldt, bowing to you. You are the hero who has returned to the light.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Hero of Light", "content": "Ajpu is the nawal of the sun, the blowgunner, and the hero. It represents the divine spark within the human, the mastery of self, and the triumph of light over darkness. Ajpu is the energy of the warrior who fights for beauty and truth. Associated with the element of fire and the sun, it carries a radiant, confident, and masculine energy. It is the archetype of the artist-warrior who walks the path of holiness in everyday life. In daily life, Ajpu manifests as clarity, leadership, overcoming challenges, and the recognition of one's own divinity. Its shadow aspect can be ego, arrogance, or the testing of one's integrity. Ajpu teaches us that we are the light of the world.", "keywords": ["Divinity", "Heroism", "Sun", "Purpose", "Mastery"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascended Renewal", "content": "Tone 13 is the energy of completion, transcendence, and the spirit realm. It is the final step of the cycle, where the energy transforms into a new octave. It represents the ancestors, the universal movement, and the unseen forces. Experientially, Tone 13 feels light, magical, and sometimes ungrounded. It is a day where the rules of the physical world feel less rigid. It marks the end of the trecena, wrapping up the lessons and preparing the seed for the next cycle. While it offers spiritual connection and a sense of accomplishment, its shadow can be spaciness or a feeling of being 'done' before the work is truly finished. It is the spirit rising from the body.", "keywords": ["Completion", "Ascension", "Transformation", "Ancestors", "Spirit"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Celebrate a personal victory, no matter how small.", "Connect with the sun; spend time in the light.", "Reflect on the growth of the last 13 days; what has ripened?", "Perform a closing ceremony for the trecena.", "Affirm your purpose and your right to be here."], "title": "The Ascended Master", "content": "The transcendent energy of Tone 13 culminates in the radiant light of Ajpu, creating a day of 'Spiritual Victory.' 13 Ajpu is the end of the Q'anil trecena, and it ends on a note of absolute brilliance. The seed that was planted on 1 Q'anil has now grown, flowered, and ascended into the sun. This is a day of mastery, where we are invited to claim our divinity and stand in our full power. The energy feels triumphant, holy, and clear. It suggests that the journey of growth is not just about biological life, but about the evolution of consciousness itself. 13 Ajpu connects us directly to the source of all light. It is a day to celebrate your victories, honor the ancestors who walked before you, and recognize the hero in the mirror. The challenge is to shine without blinding others—to hold the power with humility. The opportunity is to finish the cycle as a sovereign being of light."}}	{"title": "The Solar Mystic", "content": "To be born on 13 Ajpu is to be a person of immense spiritual power and radiant presence. You are the culmination of the cycle, carrying the energy of the Ascended Master and the Solar Hero. You possess a natural nobility and a sense of divine purpose that can be felt by everyone around you. Tone 13 gives you a foot in the spirit world, granting you psychic gifts and a deep connection to the ancestors, while Ajpu anchors that spirit in a strong, vital body and a clear will. You are a bridge between the human and the divine, here to demonstrate what is possible when we align with our highest truth.\\n\\nYour life path is one of mastery and shining your light. You are not here to play small. You are often thrust into leadership roles or situations where you must champion a cause. You have the heart of a warrior and the soul of a mystic. Your challenges in life are often 'mythic' in scale—tests of integrity, courage, and faith—but you have the strength to overcome them. You are a natural optimism, believing in the ultimate triumph of the good. \\n\\nThe challenge for a 13 Ajpu soul is the weight of the crown. The ego can be a trap; you may struggle with arrogance or a feeling of superiority if you forget that your light is a gift, not a personal possession. You may also feel ungrounded, living so high in the spiritual realms that practical life seems difficult. Your growth comes from humble service. When you use your immense light to illuminate the path for others rather than to dazzle them, you fulfill your destiny as a true Hero of the Sun."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#cfaf6c", "primary": "#0d1413", "secondary": "#303734"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.856172	2026-04-25 14:38:01.326834
80	7	2	2	Iq'	The next time you return to the lake, the air is different.\n\nYesterday, everything felt held in a glass jar, soundless and suspended. Today, a thin breeze moves through the trees, brushing the surface of the water with the lightest touch. It does not break the stillness completely, but it reminds you that stillness is not the same thing as silence.\n\nLeaves whisper above you. Reeds at the shoreline sway in small, hesitant arcs, as if they are practicing how to speak.\n\nYou stand at the edge and notice how the lake responds. When the wind moves, the reflection trembles. The sky doubles for a moment, one version clear and steady, the other rippling and soft. It feels like looking at two truths at once: the story you tell, and the story you feel.\n\nYou listen.\n\nAt first, all you hear is the rustle of branches and the faint lap of water against stone. But beneath that, something else begins to form, not with words but with intention. A pressure in your chest loosens, like a knot beginning to undo itself. Thoughts you have been holding back rise toward your mouth, testing their weight.\n\nThere are things you have not said, even to yourself. Questions you have swallowed whole. Apologies that never found a voice. Boundaries that dissolved quietly instead of being named. As the wind traces small circles across the lake, you feel each unsaid thing pulling at the surface of your life.\n\nYou take a breath.\n\nAir moves in, cool and steady. Air moves out, carrying a little of your tension with it. You try forming a sentence out loud, just for the water to hear. The first attempt is clumsy. The second is softer. By the third, your voice starts to sound honest.\n\nThe lake does not answer, but it does something better. Each time you speak, the ripples calm more quickly, as if the water is relieved that you are finally willing to be clear.\n\nYou realize that this place is not asking you to be quiet. It is asking you to be true.\n\nWhen you leave, the breeze follows you part of the way down the path, tugging at your hair and clothes like a playful reminder. Your words matter. Not because they are perfect, but because they are real.	The air around you is paying attention today. Every sigh, every held breath, every sentence you almost say but swallow instead leaves a trace. You do not have to be poetic or perfect. You only have to be honest.\n\nThis is a day to notice where your words get stuck. Where you soften your truth to keep the peace, or sharpen it to protect an old wound. Imagine your breath as a small, clear wind moving through your life, gently clearing dust from the corners. Let it carry out one story you no longer need to repeat.\n\nHave one real conversation—with another person, with your journal, with the part of you that has been waiting to be named. Speak slowly. Listen fully. Let your voice be a bridge between what you feel and the world you move through.	My breath clears the space between my inner truth and the world, and I choose words that carry clarity and care.	Find a place where you can sit upright with your spine relaxed and your chest open. Close your eyes and place one hand over your heart, the other over your belly. Inhale slowly through your nose for a gentle count of four, feeling your lower hand rise. Hold for a moment, then exhale for a count of six, imagining a soft breeze leaving your body.\n\nWith each exhale, picture a light wind carrying away one small piece of tension, one unsaid worry, one old phrase you no longer believe. Do this for several breaths. When you feel ready, silently ask, 'What truth wants to move through my voice today?' Do not force an answer. Let it arrive like a breeze, in its own time.\n\nBefore you open your eyes, offer a quiet thank you to the ancient keepers of breath, word, and story—those who spoke with the land and the winds long before you. Then take one final deep, clear breath and reenter your day.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Wind of Spirit", "content": "Iq' is the Nawal of the wind, the breath, and communication. It represents the vital spirit that animates all living things and the power of the spoken word. Iq' is the energy of inspiration, ideas, and the mind's agility. It clears the air, brings change, and carries messages from the divine. In human experience, Iq' manifests as intellect, curiosity, and a need for freedom. It is the voice that speaks the truth. When aligned, Iq' brings clarity and effective communication; when misaligned, it can lead to anger, fickleness, or destructive outbursts. It is the breath that sustains us.", "keywords": ["Breath", "Communication", "Wind", "Inspiration", "Change"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "The number Two represents the fundamental principle of polarity: light and dark, male and female, self and other. It is the energy of relationship and the tension that exists between two points. In the Mayan cosmology, Two is not a point of separation, but of connection and reflection; it teaches us that we define ourselves through our interaction with the 'other.' Experientially, this energy brings choices into sharp focus and asks for balance. It is a day where partnerships are tested and strengthened. The shadow of Two is indecision or conflict, but its light is the profound harmony that arises when opposites dance together.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Reflection", "Connection", "Balance", "Choice"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Have that difficult conversation you've been avoiding; the wind supports you.", "Practice conscious breathing with a partner.", "Listen twice as much as you speak (2 ears, 1 mouth).", "Open the windows to let fresh air and energy circulate.", "Look for messages in the wind or sudden changes in weather."], "title": "The Breath of Connection", "content": "When the duality of Tone 2 meets the communicative power of Iq', we enter a day of 'Relational Breath.' 2 Iq' is the energy of dialogue. It is the wind blowing between two people, carrying words, feelings, and understanding. This is a crucial day for relationships, specifically regarding communication. The energy asks: Are you speaking your truth to your partner? Are you listening to the wind of their spirit? It is a day to clear the air. If there have been misunderstandings, 2 Iq' provides the breeze to blow away the fog. The combination suggests that spirit (Iq') is found in the connection (2) between us. It is also a day of 'inspiration' in the literal sense—breathing in new ideas that come from a polarized perspective. Conflict today is merely the friction of the wind trying to move; let it blow through and clear the space."}}	{"title": "The Voice of Partnership", "content": "To be born on 2 Iq' is to be a communicator of the highest order, specifically within the realm of relationships. You are the 'Wind of Connection'—someone who thrives on the exchange of ideas and energy between people. You have a natural gift for diplomacy and for seeing both sides of an argument. The number 2 makes you deeply relational, while Iq' gives you the words to articulate complex feelings. You are likely the person who bridges gaps and translates languages (literal or emotional).\\n\\nYour life path is one of harmonizing duality through speech and breath. You may struggle with a changeable nature, blowing hot and cold depending on who you are with. Your challenge is to find your own voice amidst the voices of others, and to use your gift of communication to create unity rather than division. You are here to remind us that a conversation requires two participants, and that the space between them is sacred ground."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c1b6c3", "primary": "#0e1617", "secondary": "#3b3e41"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.783188	2026-04-25 13:46:57.772972
68	6	3	3	Ix	Suddenly, the crisp paper of the bazaar softens. The street beneath your feet transforms into a heavy, moss-colored velvet that ripples with the rhythmic pulse of a giant, sleeping cat. Shadows of jaguars made of pure, liquid ink move along the paper walls, their golden eyes flickering like dying embers. The air grows thick with the scent of wet earth and ancient magic. You cannot think your way through this alley; you must feel the vibration of the ink. As you move with the jaguar’s stealth, the bazaar begins to communicate through intuition rather than signs, unspooling a secret path that only reveals itself when you surrender to the wild flow of the Earth.	The universe is inviting you to a conversation that takes place in the silence between your heartbeats. You may feel a restless energy bubbling up, a desire to express the wilder parts of your soul that usually stay hidden in the gray margins of life. Today, the Jaguar of the Earth is walking beside you, teaching you the art of manifesting through focus and humility. The Bazaar has transformed into a series of shifting velvet corridors, and the only way to navigate them is to stop overthinking and start sensing. Your magic is "active" today, moving like ink through a quill. It is a day to speak your truth, but only if that truth is salted with gratitude. You might notice that your "gut feelings" are louder than the voices around you—trust them. The Jaguar doesn't second-guess the pounce, and neither should you. Whether you are planting a seed or finishing a masterpiece, do it with the stealthy certainty of someone who knows that the Earth is their primary collaborator. Breathe in the scent of cedar and shadow. The road is a rhythm, and today, you are the one keeping time.	I move with the stealthy grace of the jaguar, trusting the Earth to whisper the way forward.	Rest your hands on your lap and close your eyes. Feel the ground beneath you turn into soft, heavy moss-colored velvet. Breathe in the scent of wet earth and ancient magic, and listen for the rhythmic, low purr of the planet beneath your feet. Allow your breath to become slow and stealthy, moving with the quiet power of a cat in the dark.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine you are walking through the Jungle of Unfolding Velvets. See the shadows of ink-jaguars moving along the paper walls, their amber eyes flickering like embers. Feel your own heart begin to pulse in time with theirs, unspooling a secret path of intuition that only reveals itself when you surrender your logic to the wild flow of the night.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Jaguar of Earth Magic", "content": "Ix is the Nawal of the Jaguar, the night, and the magic of the Earth. It represents the feminine mysteries, intuition, and the high magic of the shrines and altars. Ix is the energy that sees in the dark; it connects us to the subtle forces of nature and the wisdom of the mountains. As the archetype of the Shaman and the Healer, Ix governs our capacity to transform and to manifest through intent. In human experience, Ix brings a heightened sensitivity, a love for solitude, and a deep connection to the natural world. It is the velvet darkness that holds the stars.", "keywords": ["Earth Magic", "Intuition", "Jaguar", "Sacred Sites", "Manifestation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Creation", "content": "The number Three introduces movement, rhythm, and flow into the equation. It represents the pulse of life—the heartbeat, the breath, and the natural oscillation of energy. Experientially, this energy feels active and sometimes restless; it pushes things forward and breaks stagnation. It is the energy of 'doing' rather than just 'being.' The shadow of Three can be scattered energy or instability, but its light is the joy of unimpeded expression. Today, the universe is humming, and it asks you to move with it.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Expression", "Energy", "Rhythm", "Instability"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Go into nature and move your body; dance or hike to connect with the Earth.", "Trust your gut instincts instantly today; do not overthink.", "Express your spirituality creatively (paint, drum, sing).", "Pay attention to signs in the natural world (animals, wind patterns).", "Let go of rigid structures and allow your magic to flow where it wants."], "title": "The Dance of Magic", "content": "When the rhythmic movement of Tone 3 meets the magical depths of Ix, we enter a day of 'Active Sorcery.' 3 Ix is the Jaguar in motion—not sleeping in the cave, but prowling the jungle. The energy is vibrant, mystical, and highly creative. It is a day where intuition flows effortlessly into action. You may feel a restless urge to do something spiritual—to visit a sacred site, to perform a ritual, or simply to wander in nature. The static energy of the shrine is put into motion today. It is an excellent time to express your inner magic outwardly, perhaps through art or healing work. The veil is thin, and the spirits are dancing. Trust the sudden impulses you get; the Jaguar moves by instinct, not by logic. If you have been feeling blocked, 3 Ix will shake loose the debris and get the energy flowing again."}}	{"title": "The Rhythm of the Earth", "content": "To be born on 3 Ix is to be a living conduit of natural magic. You are the 'Dancing Jaguar'—a soul who combines deep spiritual intuition with a restless, expressive energy. You are likely very creative and perhaps a bit unconventional, marching to the beat of a drum that only you can hear. You have a natural affinity for nature and animals, and you may find that your best ideas come when you are in motion—walking, running, or traveling. You are not a monk sitting in silence; you are a shaman in the marketplace, bringing magic into the everyday flow of life.\\n\\nYour life path is one of expressing the inexpressible. You have the ability to take the subtle energies of the Earth (Ix) and translate them into movement, art, or communication (3). However, the combination of high sensitivity and high energy can sometimes lead to anxiety or a feeling of being ungrounded. Your challenge is to find a rhythm that sustains you, allowing you to move freely without burning out. You are here to remind us that the sacred is alive, moving, and breathing right beside us."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#bbcb86", "primary": "#0f1c17", "secondary": "#3b5139"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.776309	2026-04-25 14:38:01.294395
48	4	9	9	B'atz'	Something in the air feels woven today.\n\nWhen you return to the streets, threads of light hang between buildings like drifting banners—thin, shimmering strands that sway even though there is no wind. They shift in colors reminiscent of dawn: amber, rose, pale blue, soft gold.\n\nYou follow them without thinking.\n\nThe city grows quieter as you walk. Not empty—alive in a different way. Each doorway hums softly. Each window glows with warmth. It feels like walking through a loom mid-weave, the world stitching itself one breath at a time.\n\nAhead, the street opens into a wide circular plaza. The ground is carved with swirling geometric patterns you’re sure weren’t there yesterday. Overhead, thousands of luminous threads stretch from rooftop to rooftop, forming a vast canopy of shifting color.\n\nThey pulse.\n\nThen descend.\n\nThe threads lower themselves until they hover just above your head, weaving through one another with gentle precision. Some brush your shoulders. Others curve around your hands. None of them bind. They only invite.\n\nYou lift your palm. A single thread drapes across it—a glowing strand of soft golden-white. It vibrates with a quiet rhythm, like a heartbeat woven into light. When you touch it, the plaza responds.\n\nShapes unfold in the air: loops and spirals, patterns that feel familiar even though you have never seen them. They move with choreography older than language, the dance of creation, of stories being spun into form.\n\nThen you notice: the thread in your hand mirrors your breath.\n\nInhale, it brightens.\n\nExhale, it softens.\n\nSlowly, you realize the threads around you are responding not just to movement, but to emotion, memory, desire. They weave around the parts of you you’ve been reclaiming—your clarity, your instinct, your grief, your hope.\n\nThey are making something.\n\nAnd for the first time, you feel yourself as part of the loom—not trapped, not tangled, but essential. A thread among threads. A story among stories.\n\nAbove you, the canopy ripples into a new shape—a great woven arc that bridges the broken city and the luminous one, tying them together with soft, intentional beauty.\n\nYou stand in the center of it all, breath syncing with the golden thread in your hand.\n\nCreation is not loud today.\n\nIt is gentle, rhythmic, patient.\n\nA reminder that your life is something you are allowed to weave anew.	Today brings a soft creative spark—one that doesn’t demand masterpiece-making or productivity. Instead, it invites you to gently express what has been growing inside you.\n\nYou might feel drawn to music, writing, color, movement, or simply daydreaming. Threads of inspiration may appear suddenly, connecting ideas you didn’t realize belonged together.\n\nLet yourself play. Let yourself weave. Let yourself create for the sake of feeling alive.\n\nYou’re stitching your story with new colors today.	I weave my life with intention and let creativity flow gently through me.	Close your eyes and imagine stepping into a vast circular plaza where glowing threads stretch overhead like a living canopy. Walk to the center.\n\nA single luminous thread drifts down and rests across your open palm. Feel its warmth pulse in rhythm with your breath.\n\nWith each inhale, the thread brightens. With each exhale, it softens. Around you, thousands of threads begin weaving themselves into patterns of gentle color—spirals, arcs, flowing loops.\n\nSee these patterns as the many parts of your life: experiences, dreams, old lessons, new hopes. Watch them weave themselves into something coherent and beautiful.\n\nWhen you are ready, offer gratitude to the weavers and creators who came before you. Open your eyes knowing you hold a thread of your own destiny.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Weaver of Time", "content": "B'atz' is the nawal of the thread, the monkey, and the artist. It represents the creative process and the weaving of destiny. B'atz' is the spark that starts the fire and the thread that connects the past to the future. It governs the arts and marriage. B'atz' energy is playful and clever. In its shadow, it can be superficial or scattered. Its highest expression is the Master Weaver who creates beauty out of the raw material of life.", "keywords": ["Weaving", "Creativity", "Thread", "Monkey", "Art"]}, "number": {"title": "The Circle of Gestation", "content": "Nine is the number of patience, the feminine, and the completion of cycles. It is associated with the nine months of pregnancy. Nine represents the deep, subterranean work that happens in the dark. It is an emotional, intuitive number. Experientially, a Nine day feels slower and more internal. It is a time for nurturing and waiting. The shadow of Nine can be withdrawal or getting stuck in the past. It asks us to trust the timing of the universe.", "keywords": ["Patience", "Gestation", "Feminine", "Depth", "Nurturing"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Work on a craft project that requires patience (knitting, pottery).", "Honor the women in your life or your female ancestors.", "Approach a problem with 'monkey mind' curiosity but 'nine mind' patience.", "Visualize your life as a tapestry being slowly woven.", "Allow yourself to play, but do it with soul."], "title": "Gestating the Masterpiece", "content": "When the feminine depth of Nine meets the creative weaving of B'atz', we have a day of 'Deep Creativity' or 'The Gestating Artist.' The artistic thread of B'atz' is being pulled into the deep womb of the Nine to be nurtured and refined. It is a day for slow, soulful creation. It is not about finishing the project quickly; it is about weaving intention into every stitch. This is a powerful day for women, for artists, and for healing the feminine line. The energy is soft, playful yet profound. You may feel a desire to create something that has lasting meaning. The challenge is patience; the Monkey wants to jump, but the Nine says 'wait.' Allow your creativity to ripen. Trust that the pattern you are weaving is part of a larger, beautiful design that takes time to reveal itself."}}	{"title": "The Soulful Artist", "content": "To be born on 9 B'atz' is to be a creator of deep beauty and a weaver of souls. You possess a unique blend of playful creativity (B'atz') and profound emotional depth (Nine). You are not just an entertainer; you are an artist who touches the heart. You have a natural intuition and a connection to the mysteries of time and destiny. You are likely drawn to the arts, healing, or counseling—any field where you can help weave the broken threads of life back together.\\n\\nYour life path is one of bringing the sacred into the creative. You understand that art is not just decoration, but a form of prayer. You may struggle with the timing of things, wanting your creations to manifest before they are ready. Your lesson is to trust the gestation process. You are here to show the world that true beauty takes time and that every life is a masterpiece in the making."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d59da7", "primary": "#1b1919", "secondary": "#634148"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.762621	2026-04-25 13:46:57.718548
201	16	6	6	Aj	You march through the crushing weight for what feels like days. Just as your legs are about to give out, the road widens. The oppressive gravity snaps—instantly gone. You stumble forward into a circular clearing where the grass has woven itself into a high, protective dome.\n\nThis is a Sanctuary. The air here is sweet, light, and smells of rain. The bioluminescence is soft and steady, not chaotic. You step inside and collapse onto the mossy floor. You realize that the journey requires these pauses; you cannot sprint a marathon.\n\nHere, you are safe. You sit up and align your spine, letting the tension drain out of your shoulders. You are the cane, the staff, the pillar of your own temple. You rest in the amber glow, gathering the silence you will need for the road ahead.	The crushing weight of the journey has suddenly snapped, and you’ve stumbled into a circular clearing where the air smells like fresh rain and sweet ozone. This is your mandatory sanctuary. You cannot sprint a marathon without learning the art of the pause. The bioluminescence here is soft and steady, mirroring the rhythm of a heart that has finally found its groove. Collapse into the moss. Align your spine like a pillar of your own temple. Today is not about the distance covered; it’s about the quality of your stillness.\n\nIn this dome of protective light, you are safe to drop the armor. You are the cane, the staff, the upright leader of your own internal world, and even leaders need to gather the silence. Notice how things 'click' into place when you stop forcing the gears. There is a fluid harmony available to you today that can mend the fences in your home and smooth the wrinkles in your soul. Don't mistake this rest for laziness; it is a spiritual regeneration. The journey ahead will demand your full presence, and you can only give what you have stored in the quiet. Breathe with the trees, let the tension drain into the velvet soil, and remember that you are the most important home you will ever tend. The cosmos is holding the door open for your rest.	I am a flexible pillar of strength, standing tall and hollow to receive cosmic grace.	Sit quietly and imagine a soft, bioluminescent dome of light forming around you. This is your sanctuary. Breathe in the scent of fresh rain and sweet ozone. With every exhale, let go of any need to lead or control. Feel the air inside the dome supporting you, allowing you to settle into a state of total regeneration.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, visualize your spine as a tall cane of bamboo. Feel it standing straight and strong, yet remaining hollow. Imagine the wind of the spirit blowing through the center of your hollow spine, creating a low, musical frequency that harmonizes your entire home and community.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Pillar of Community", "content": "Aj is the nawal of the cane, the reed, and the home. It represents the spine, the pillar of the family, and the authority that comes from integrity. Aj is the energy of resurrection and flexibility—like the corn stalk that bends in the wind but does not break. Associated with the element of earth and the color brown or yellow, it carries a gentle, protective, and paternal/maternal energy. It is the archetype of the rightful leader who serves the community. In daily life, Aj manifests as domestic harmony, questions of authority, and the strength of one's inner convictions. Its shadow aspect can be rigidity, authoritarianism, or problems within the home/family structure. Aj teaches us that true strength lies in flexibility and service.", "keywords": ["Home", "Leadership", "Harmony", "Integrity", "Authority"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Harmony", "content": "Tone 6 is the energy of flow, rhythm, and responsiveness. After the exertion of the 5, the 6 allows the energy to stabilize and find its natural groove. It is the number of ultimate balance in motion—like a surfer riding a wave or a heart beating in time. In Mayan cosmology, it is associated with the six directions (East, West, North, South, Up, Down), representing a spatial wholeness. Experientially, Tone 6 feels fluid and harmonious. It is a day where things often 'click' into place without force. While it fosters growth and family connection, its shadow can be passivity or a tendency to drift with the current rather than steering. It is the breath that connects the effort to the result.", "keywords": ["Rhythm", "Harmony", "Flow", "Balance", "Growth"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Spend quality, relaxed time with family or housemates.", "Beautify or declutter your living space to improve energy flow.", "Practice flexible leadership; listen more than you command.", "Attend to your spine and posture (the inner Aj).", "Resolve domestic disputes by seeking the path of least resistance."], "title": "Harmonizing the Home", "content": "The fluid energy of Tone 6 combined with the domestic stability of Aj creates a day of profound harmony within our personal sanctuaries. 6 Aj is the 'Flowing Home.' It is an energy that smooths over conflicts in the family and brings a sense of rhythmic peace to our environments. Today, authority does not need to be asserted; it is naturally recognized through gentle presence. It is a day where the home becomes a place of regeneration and growth. The stiffness of the cane (Aj) is softened by the flow of the 6, allowing for leadership that is listening and responsive. This energy supports mending fences, nurturing children, and tending to the physical body (the home of the soul). It feels like a family dinner where everyone is laughing, or a quiet afternoon where the house itself feels settled. The opportunity is to let go of the need to control the household and instead find the rhythm that allows everyone to thrive."}}	{"title": "The Gentle Pillar of Life", "content": "To be born on 6 Aj is to be a beacon of stability and gentle wisdom within your community. You carry the energy of the home and the hearth, but with a fluidity that makes you approachable and understanding. You are the person others lean on when their lives feel chaotic because you possess an innate sense of rhythm and balance. Unlike a rigid authoritarian, your leadership style is organic; you lead by example and by creating an environment where others feel safe to grow. You have a deep connection to family, tradition, and the protection of the vulnerable.\\n\\nYour life path is one of cultivating harmony in your immediate surroundings. You are likely drawn to roles that involve caretaking, community building, or restoring order to chaotic systems. The number 6 gives you a natural flow and responsiveness, preventing the potential rigidity of the Aj sign. You bend like the corn in the wind, surviving storms that would break harder people. This resilience is your superpower. You are also likely to have a strong physical constitution and a connection to nature's cycles, instinctively knowing when to act and when to rest.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 6 Aj soul is the tendency to absorb the imbalances of those around you. Your desire for harmony can lead you to avoid necessary conflicts or to enable others' bad behavior to keep the peace. You may also struggle with defining your own identity outside of your role as a supporter or pillar for others. Your growth comes from learning that your first duty of care is to your own inner home. When you establish strong energetic boundaries, your ability to harmonize the world around you becomes sustainable and truly transformative."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d1b474", "primary": "#151d1a", "secondary": "#5f523f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.853384	2026-04-25 14:38:01.322493
75	6	10	10	Imox	You reach a wide plaza where the mist from the ink-ocean begins to solidify. This is the manifestation of 10 Imox—the moment where responsibility is given to the dreamer. The fluid, intuitive mirages of the Bazaar no longer float out of reach; they are waiting for you to name them. As you speak your private dreams into the cooling air, the mist hardens into stone-textured paper and heavy silk buildings. You are now the architect of your own intuition. By taking mastery over the 'collective waters' of your imagination, you turn the shifting road into a permanent sanctuary. The anchor drops with a heavy thud into the ink below, marking the spot where your dream became a landmark.	The tides of your inner ocean are no longer just a restless swell; they are beginning to push against the shore with the weight of something solid. Today, the universe is asking you to take the fluid, shimmering matter of your most recurring dreams and give them a permanent address. You may feel a profound sense of responsibility for the visions you’ve carried, a realization that the "mystery" is now ready for its first brick. This is the energy of psychic mastery—the moment you stop being tossed about by your emotions and start using them as the primary current for your creative engine. The air is cool and misty, smelling of deep water and fresh stone. You are being invited to act as the architect of the collective dream, building structures that allow others to navigate the deep without getting lost. If you feel a surge of intuition, don't let it drift away; capture it in a blueprint, a conversation, or a physical act. Your responsibility today is to be the "anchor" in the shifting waters. By grounding your imagination in the physical world, you turn your private mirages into a sanctuary that provides stability for everyone who enters your sphere.	I am the master of my own creative flow, giving my imagination the weight and structure of reality.	Imagine you are standing on a quiet shoreline where the waves are made of deep teal ink. Close your eyes and breathe with the tide, feeling the vast ocean of the collective dream rising and falling. In your hand, you hold a heavy anchor. With a deep exhale, imagine dropping that anchor into the ink, grounding your intuition into solid reality.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, walk into the Plaza of the Manifested Mirage. See the thick teal mist begin to solidify into stone-textured paper buildings as you speak your dreams out loud. Feel the weight of responsibility as you become the architect of your own subconscious. Watch the ripples of collective memory settle as your anchor hits the bottom, turning a fluid vision into a permanent landmark.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Primordial Dreamer", "content": "Imox is the Nawal of the water, the lizard/crocodile, and the collective subconscious. It represents the primordial soup from which all things emerge. Imox is the energy of dreams, intuition, and the fluid, chaotic nature of the mind. In human experience, Imox manifests as wild creativity, psychic ability, and a connection to the 'crazy' wisdom of the universe. It is the ocean that can be a calm mirror or a raging storm. When aligned, Imox brings profound inspiration and adaptability; when misaligned, it can lead to confusion or losing touch with reality.", "keywords": ["Water", "Dreams", "Intuition", "Subconscious", "Creativity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Peak of Manifestation", "content": "The number Ten represents the manifestation of the intent. It is the two hands coming together (5+5) to finalize the creation. In Mayan cosmology, Ten is the energy of community agreement, collaboration, and the realization of the project. Experientially, this energy feels solid, accomplished, and social. It is the moment when the house is built and we invite the neighbors in. The shadow of Ten can be over-responsibility, but its light is the satisfaction of seeing your dreams take physical form. Today, the universe says: 'It is done.'", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Collaboration", "Realization", "Mastery"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Collaborate on a creative project; two heads are better than one today.", "Host a brainstorming session; the ideas will flow.", "Pay attention to the 'vibe' of your community; you are tuned in.", "Drink plenty of water to keep your energetic channels clear.", "Allow your weirdest ideas to be seen; they are the seeds of the new."], "title": "Manifesting the Dream", "content": "When the solid manifestation power of Tone 10 meets the fluid dream-world of Imox, we get a day of 'Collective Dreaming.' 10 Imox is the day the dream becomes real. It represents the ability to pull ideas from the ether and give them physical form through collaboration. This energy is fantastic for artistic groups, bands, or creative teams. It suggests that the 'madness' of inspiration can be harnessed if we work together. The energy is fluid but directed—like a canal channeling a river. You may find that your intuition is incredibly accurate today, especially regarding social dynamics. It is a day to trust the group mind; the collective subconscious is singing in harmony. If you have been feeling mentally scattered, the number 10 provides the container you need to hold your thoughts and turn them into something beautiful."}}	{"title": "The Collective Visionary", "content": "To be born on 10 Imox is to be a lightning rod for the collective consciousness. You are the 'Dream Architect'—someone who can tap into the hidden currents of the human psyche and bring them into the daylight of reality. You are likely very social, charismatic, and perhaps a bit eccentric, with a creative genius that thrives in collaboration. You don't just dream alone; you dream for the tribe. You have a unique ability to make the abstract tangible, turning feelings into art or intuition into business strategy.\\n\\nYour life path is one of mastering the waters of emotion and connection. The number 10 gives you a sense of responsibility to your community; you want your visions to help people. However, the sensitivity of Imox means you must be careful not to absorb the negativity of the crowd. Your challenge is to stay grounded in your own identity while swimming in the ocean of the collective. You are here to show us that our wildest dreams can, in fact, come true."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#9cceae", "primary": "#111813", "secondary": "#364b3b"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.778942	2026-04-25 14:38:01.30208
45	4	6	6	Q'anil	When you step back toward the city, the forest does not disappear. Instead, pieces of it cling to the edges of buildings — moss glowing faintly on cracked stone, thin vines weaving through broken balconies, tiny blossoms opening where rust once ruled.\n\nThe twilight sky feels lighter today, washed with soft gold beneath the violet haze. The air hums with a gentler rhythm, as if the city itself has begun to breathe differently.\n\nYou walk slowly, letting your senses tune to the subtle changes. At first you think the lights around you are flickering as usual, but then you notice the movement is too soft, too organic.\n\nFireflies.\n\nDozens of them drift between the alleyways — not ordinary ones, but small spheres of warm light that pulse with soft colors: pale amber, muted rose, faint green. They float like seeds carried on an invisible breeze.\n\nYou approach one. It hovers at eye level, glowing brighter when you exhale. More appear, gathering in gentle spirals, forming shifting patterns in the air. For a moment, they outline a trail between the two overlapping cities — the broken world and the one still forming.\n\nYou follow the trail.\n\nThe fireflies guide you into an open plaza where the pavement has cracked into geometric shapes. In the center, a small mound of soil rises from the fractured stone. Something grows from it: a delicate plant with translucent leaves, each one pulsing with soft inner light.\n\nA seedling.\n\nWhen you kneel beside it, the fireflies gather around you, settling into the cracks of the plaza like glowing grains. You touch the soil. It is warm, richer than the earth you felt in the forest. Alive with potential.\n\nAs you watch, the seedling shifts — not growing quickly, but steady, confident, reaching upward as if the city’s fractured heart has become a cradle instead of a cage.\n\nYou feel something stir inside you: a small joy, unfamiliar but real. It is not loud. It is not overwhelming. It feels like remembering that hope can be gentle.\n\nFor the first time, you see both cities clearly — the broken one and the luminous one — occupying the same space, layered like memory and dream. And in the middle of it all, the seedling grows.\n\nNot because the world is fixed.\n\nBecause something new has finally been planted.	Today brings a soft lift to your spirit, the kind that doesn’t demand anything from you but attention. You notice small sparks — tiny joys, subtle ideas, gentle urges to create or refresh something in your life.\n\nThis is seed energy. It doesn’t push. It invites.\n\nFollow what feels warm, what feels bright, what feels quietly alive. This isn’t a day to overhaul your world. It’s a day to tend to the tender beginnings emerging inside you.\n\nLet yourself feel a little hope without needing to explain it. Light grows where it’s welcomed, not forced.	I nourish the small lights within me and trust them to grow in their own time.	Find a comfortable seat and close your eyes. Imagine walking into a twilight plaza where the cracked pavement glows with soft golden light. Fireflies drift through the air, settling into patterns that guide your steps.\n\nIn the center of the plaza, see a small mound of warm earth rising from the broken stone. A single seedling grows from it, its translucent leaves pulsing with faint golden light.\n\nKneel beside it. Place your hands gently on the soil. Feel its warmth, its potential, its quiet promise. Each breath you take sends a soft glow through the seedling, encouraging it to grow at its own pace.\n\nInvite one intention — small, gentle, real — into your awareness. See it as a glowing seed resting in the soil with the plant.\n\nOffer gratitude to the keepers of growth and renewal. Allow the fireflies to gather around you, lighting the plaza with soft radiance.\n\nWhen you are ready, open your eyes, carrying that small glow with you.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Golden Seed", "content": "Q'anil is the nawal of the seed, the rabbit, and the star. It represents the spark of life, fertility, and the potential for organic growth. Q'anil is the energy of the planter and the harvester—the promise of abundance. It governs biological life, agriculture, and artistic creation. In its shadow, Q'anil can manifest as impatience or vanity. Its highest expression is the blooming garden—the realization of potential.", "keywords": ["Seed", "Harvest", "Fertility", "Star", "Creation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Stability", "content": "Six is the number of flow, organic balance, and responsiveness. It represents the point where the initial effort stabilizes and finds its rhythm. Six is associated with the vertical alignment of Heaven and Earth. Experientially, a Six day feels smoother and more harmonious. Obstacles dissolve if you flow with the current. It is a time for family, vitality, and acceptance. The shadow of Six can be passivity. It teaches us to trust the process.", "keywords": ["Flow", "Harmony", "Vitality", "Responsiveness", "Alignment"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Plant a seed or buy fresh flowers for your home.", "Spend quality time with children or pets.", "Engage in a creative activity purely for the joy of it.", "Practice gratitude for the food you eat; acknowledge its source.", "Wear yellow or gold to align with the energy of the star/seed."], "title": "Flowering Abundance", "content": "When the harmonious flow of Six meets the fertile seed of Q'anil, we enter a day of 'Organic Growth' or 'Flowering Life.' This is one of the most gentle and beautiful days in the calendar. The energy supports everything that wants to grow—plants, children, projects, relationships. The struggle of the earlier days dissolves into a natural unfolding. It is a perfect day for gardening, spending time with children, or engaging in creative hobbies. The Six ensures that the growth is balanced and sustainable, not forced. You may feel a sense of ease and joy today, a reminder that life is meant to be enjoyed. The challenge is to not become lazy in this comfort. Enjoy the flow, but keep steering the boat. Nurture what you have planted with love and presence. It is a day to celebrate the beauty of life in all its forms."}}	{"title": "The Joyful Gardener", "content": "To be born on 6 Q'anil is to be a bringer of joy and a nurturer of life. You have a sunny, optimistic disposition that warms everyone around you. The number Six gives you a natural flow and grace, while Q'anil fills you with creative potential and fertility. You make things grow simply by being present. You are likely drawn to nature, the arts, or working with children—anything where you can nurture potential into form. You have a talent for making life look easy and beautiful.\\n\\nYour life path is one of spreading abundance. You are a natural attractor of good fortune, often finding yourself in the right place at the right time. However, you may struggle with the harsher realities of life. You prefer harmony and beauty, and conflict can be very draining for you. Your lesson is to learn that even the storms are part of the garden's cycle. When you accept the whole of life, your capacity to create beauty becomes limitless. You are here to remind us that we are all star-seeds meant to bloom."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#bdbe89", "primary": "#151a19", "secondary": "#49493a"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#cd8b33", "primary": "#1c1b20", "secondary": "#533e35"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#c98b22", "primary": "#0a161a", "secondary": "#5a4822"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#d2970f", "primary": "#03281c", "secondary": "#19532e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.758957	2026-04-25 13:46:57.713528
82	7	4	4	K'at	The path to the lake feels heavier today.\n\nNot in a foreboding way, but in the way a backpack feels when you suddenly realize how much you’ve been carrying without noticing. Branches seem lower. The air feels thicker, as if holding its own memories close.\n\nWhen you reach the shoreline, something new waits for you.\n\nA tangle of nets lies draped across the stones — not fishing nets, not anything made for catching creatures, but woven cords of light and shadow, threads of memory and feeling braided together. Some strands look like old obligations. Some look like unfinished conversations. Some flicker with the soft glow of things you once desired but left hanging in the air.\n\nYou recognize pieces of yourself in the weave.\n\nYou kneel beside the nets and run your fingers across them. They resist at first, tightening like they do not want to be disturbed. Then, slowly, they loosen, as if relieved to finally be acknowledged. You pull one strand free and it reveals an old promise you made to yourself — something small but real. Another thread reveals a habit that feels more like a cage than comfort.\n\nYou notice that the nets are not inherently good or bad. They are simply evidence. Evidence of where your energy has gone. Evidence of what you have clung to. Evidence of what has clung to you.\n\nThe lake watches in silence, its surface still holding the gold-rose shimmer of dawn. A faint breeze stirs, and the nets shift in response, sighing against the stones.\n\nYou understand, suddenly, that you cannot carry everything forward.\n\nSo you begin. Not dramatically. Not all at once. You loosen one knot — an expectation that was never truly yours. Then another — an obligation that grew heavy because you never set a boundary. You keep going, unraveling only what feels ready.\n\nSome strands you leave where they are, knowing they still serve you. Some you fold neatly, acknowledging their place in your story. Others dissolve the moment you release them, unraveling into soft threads that drift toward the lake like fallen petals.\n\nWhen you stand, the nets look lighter. Not empty, not gone — just clearer. You breathe easier without even trying.\n\nAs you turn to leave, you notice a single open space among the weave, a circle where something new might someday belong. Not a burden, not a trap — but a possibility waiting for the right moment.\n\nYou walk back with one simple truth resting quietly inside you: clarity is a kind of freedom too.	Today asks you to look directly at what you’ve gathered — the choices, habits, obligations, and stories that have wrapped themselves around your life. Not everything you carry is meant to come with you.\n\nThis is a day for gentle sorting. For naming what still feels alive and what feels like a knot tightening in your chest. You do not have to tear anything apart. Just loosen what’s been pulling at you. Let one unnecessary thread fall away and notice how your breath opens.\n\nYou are not meant to drag the past forward in one tangled bundle. You are meant to choose what you carry with intention.	I release what weighs me down and keep only what supports my growth, clarity, and truth.	Sit comfortably and imagine a net resting in your lap — woven from threads of memory, responsibility, and emotion. Take a slow breath and picture one knot tightening. As you exhale, imagine gently loosening it. On the next inhale, see another knot appear; on the exhale, soften that one too.\n\nYou do not need to unravel the whole net. Focus on the knots that call your attention. Honor what remains useful. Let go of what dissolves. Before opening your eyes, offer a moment of gratitude to the ancient keepers of cycles and caretakers of community — those who understood the balance between holding and releasing. Carry that wisdom with you into the day.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Cosmic Net", "content": "K'at is the Nawal of the net, the spider web, and the gathering of abundance. It represents the principle of connection and entanglement. K'at is the energy that catches what we need (harvest, community) and tangles us in what we don't need (burdens, debts). It governs the storage of seeds and the release of what no longer serves. In human experience, K'at manifests as the ability to network, organize, and carry a load. It is the burning of the net to free the captive. When aligned, it brings fruitful connections; when misaligned, it brings feeling trapped.", "keywords": ["Gathering", "Release", "Abundance", "Net", "Entanglement"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cube of Stability", "content": "The number Four represents stability, definition, and the material world. It is the energy of the four cardinal directions, the four elements, and the four walls of a house. In Mayan cosmology, Four is the force that grounds spirit into form; it creates the container in which life can exist. Experientially, this energy feels solid, reliable, and sometimes a bit heavy. It is a day for building, organizing, and establishing boundaries. The shadow of Four can be rigidity or stagnation, but its light is the comfort of a secure foundation.", "keywords": ["Structure", "Balance", "Grounding", "Manifestation", "Stability"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Declutter a physical space; bring order to your home.", "Review your finances and debts; create a repayment plan.", "Sort your mental 'net'—what worries can you drop?", "Connect with your support network to stabilize a project.", "Define clear boundaries in your relationships."], "title": "Stabilizing the Harvest", "content": "When the structural stability of Tone 4 meets the gathering nature of K'at, we get a day of 'Organized Abundance.' 4 K'at is the well-built barn that holds the harvest. It is a day to bring order to your connections and your possessions. The energy supports sorting, organizing, and defining what you want to keep in your 'net' and what you are ready to release. It is not a day for casting the net wide (that's more of a 1 or 8 energy), but for securing what you have already caught. Look at your debts, your commitments, and your physical clutter. Use the stability of the 4 to create a plan to manage them. It is also a powerful day for community building—strengthening the 'net' of your social support system. Weave the threads tight; ensure the structure can hold the weight of your dreams."}}	{"title": "The Weaver of Stability", "content": "To be born on 4 K'at is to be a master organizer of life's abundance. You are the 'Grounded Gatherer'—someone who has an innate talent for bringing people and resources together and creating a stable structure for them. You are likely the person who organizes the events, manages the community funds, or keeps the family archives. You have a magnetic quality that draws things to you, and the discipline (4) to manage them once they arrive.\\n\\nYour life path is one of sorting the essential from the non-essential. You may struggle with feeling weighed down by obligations or material possessions, as your net catches everything. Your challenge is to learn the art of release—to trust that you can let go of what you don't need and still be safe. You are here to build a safety net for yourself and others, proving that true security comes from connection and order."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d59d70", "primary": "#121615", "secondary": "#4a3631"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.78465	2026-04-25 13:46:57.77518
145	12	2	2	Kan	You move deeper into the web. The nets here are not static; they sway and pulse. The ropes look less like hemp and more like veins, pumping golden light through the system.\n\nYou come to a section where the walkway is narrow. Coiled around the handrails are vines that move. No, not vines—snakes. Golden, shimmering serpents woven into the net itself.\n\nThis is the Coil of Vitality.\n\nKan is the Serpent, the energy of life and instinct. The number 2 is Duality and Relationship. The snakes block your path, their eyes watching you with cool detachment. They are asking: "Is your net supporting your life, or strangling it?"\n\nYou look at the burdens you are still carrying. You notice how some of them drain your energy, making you tired just looking at them. Others give you a spark of excitement.\n\nThe serpents hiss softly. They are drawn to the life-force, not the dead weight.\n\nYou realize that your energy is finite. Every dead thing you carry steals food from the living things.\n\nA serpent approaches the bundle of "Obligation" you are carrying. It strikes—not at you, but at the bundle. Its fangs sever the cords holding the heavy sack. The sack falls, tumbling down into the abyss. You feel a sudden rush of adrenaline, a return of blood flow to your limbs.\n\nThe serpent nods (or seems to). It curls into a shape that forms a bridge across a gap in the net.\n\nYou step across the living bridge. You feel the pulse of the serpent under your feet—strong, vital, alive. You are learning to choose vitality over heaviness.	Your energy is precious currency today. The energy of 2 Kan asks you to look at where you are spending it. Are you feeding a dead situation? Or are you feeding your own growth?\n\nListen to your body. If you feel heavy, bored, or drained, that is a sign. If you feel excited, scared-but-alive, or warm, that is a sign. Follow the warmth. Shed the skin that is too tight. You need your strength for the journey ahead.	I choose what gives me life and release what drains my spirit.	Visualize a snake made of green light coiled at the base of your spine. It begins to uncoil, rising up your back.\n\nAs it rises, it burns away any grey, sticky webs of fatigue or obligation. Feel the heat. Feel the power returning to your limbs. You are shedding your old skin.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Vital Force", "content": "Kan is the energy of the serpent, the kundalini, and the life force. It represents wisdom, sexuality, and the power of evolution. Kan is the teacher who shows us that true power comes from within and that growth often requires the shedding of old skins. It is the spark of biology and the intelligence of the body. It asks us to respect our instincts and to channel our raw energy into higher wisdom.", "keywords": ["Vitality", "Power", "Sexuality", "Growth", "Transformation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "The number 2 represents polarity, relationship, and the dynamic tension between opposites. It is the interaction between the self and the other, the masculine and the feminine, the light and the dark. 2 brings choices and mirrors into focus. In the context of the K'at trecena, it asks us to look at the relationships we have gathered. Are they balanced? Do they feed us or drain us? It is the separation of the single thread into a weave.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Reflection", "Connection", "Balance", "Duality"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Assess your energy levels after interacting with specific people today.", "Practice grounding exercises to balance your internal polarity.", "Have a conversation about boundaries and energy exchange.", "Move your body to release stagnant energy from your spine.", "Trust your gut instinct regarding a partnership."], "title": "Balancing the Vital Connection", "content": "2 Kan brings the question of energy exchange into sharp focus. Today, the gathering theme of K'at meets the vital force of Kan through the lens of relationship (2). This is a day to examine the energetic cost of your connections. Who or what are you plugged into? Is the exchange of energy reciprocal? The serpent energy demands authenticity; it will reveal where you are leaking power in your relationships. It is a potent day for sexual alchemy, for deep conversations that strip away pretense, and for finding the balance between your own needs and the needs of others. The net is tested today by the strength of the life force flowing through it."}}	{"title": "The Dynamic Catalyst", "content": "To be born on 2 Kan is to be a powerhouse of relational energy. You possess a charisma that is both magnetic and intense. You understand the dance of opposites intimately and thrive in one-on-one interactions where you can explore the depths of another person. You are a catalyst for growth; people often find that their lives accelerate or transform simply by being in relationship with you. You carry the wisdom of the serpent—instinctive, ancient, and deeply connected to the body.\\n\\nYour life path involves mastering the flow of power between self and other. You are likely drawn to roles involving counseling, coaching, or any form of partnership where transformation is the goal. You have a natural talent for spotting potential in others and helping to awaken it. However, your intensity can sometimes be overwhelming, or you may become entangled in the dramas of those you try to help.\\n\\nYour challenge is to maintain your own center while merging with others. The 2 energy seeks connection, but Kan seeks sovereignty. You must learn to share your power without giving it away. When you find the balance between intimacy and independence, you become a master of 'sacred duality,' teaching the world that true relationship is a path to enlightenment."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#5cb9aa", "primary": "#0d1a19", "secondary": "#284a46"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.817227	2026-04-25 13:46:57.908615
49	4	10	10	E'	The woven canopy stays with you long after you leave the plaza. Threads of light still trail overhead, drifting like soft indicators pointing somewhere new. The city feels more open today, its streets less tangled, its shadows lighter.\n\nYou walk without hesitation.\n\nThe pathways beneath your feet begin to change. They straighten. They widen. The cracks in the pavement form gentle lines that converge into a long, glowing corridor stretching between the dual cities. The broken world remains on one side, the luminous one on the other—but for the first time, a clear path connects them.\n\nAs you follow the corridor, you notice something you haven’t seen since entering this place.\n\nOthers are walking.\n\nNot people—figures made of soft, shifting light, outlines of travelers like you, but blurred around the edges as though they come from many different possibilities. Some move ahead of you, steady and sure. Some walk beside you, flickering with uncertainty. Some drift behind, taking their time.\n\nThe path itself pulses beneath your feet, responding to each step with subtle radiance. Every time you place your foot down, a small flare of gold spreads outward before fading.\n\nThis is a path that remembers.\n\nEventually the corridor opens into a long bridge suspended between the two overlapping cities. Below, the fractured architecture of the shadow-world merges with the shimmering forms of the dream-world, creating a landscape both familiar and impossible.\n\nHalfway across the bridge, the light-figures pause. They turn—not with faces, but with presence—acknowledging you. For a moment, you feel them more clearly: their hopes, their fears, their determination. They are not here to lead you. They are here to remind you that every path is a shared one.\n\nSomeone has walked a version of your journey before.\n\nSomeone will walk a version of it after.\n\nYou breathe, feeling the truth of that settle into your bones.\n\nThe bridge brightens, guiding you forward. With each step, you sense the momentum of the entire trecena gathering behind you—clarity, instinct, grounding, release, love, creativity—all converging into the path beneath your feet.\n\nBy the time you reach the far end of the bridge, the corridor widens into an open platform where both cities overlap seamlessly, neither dominant, both present.\n\nA sign you’ve never seen before flickers into view: a simple arrow pointing ahead.\n\nFor the first time, you know you’re not wandering.\n\nYou’re traveling.	Today, the path becomes clearer. You may feel called toward something specific—a project, a conversation, a new direction—something that feels like movement.\n\nTrust this.\n\nThis is a day to walk forward with purpose, knowing you’re supported both physically and spiritually. Even if you feel alone, you’re part of a larger flow of people growing, evolving, and making meaning in their own ways.\n\nFollow the signs. Follow the pull. Let momentum guide you.	I walk my path with purpose, clarity, and the support of those who walk beside me.	Close your eyes and picture a long glowing path stretching between two overlapping cities—one shadowed, one luminous. Walk toward it.\n\nAs you step onto the path, see soft figures of light traveling with you. Some ahead, some behind, some beside. Feel their presence as gentle support, a community of souls moving toward their own destinations.\n\nWalk until the path rises into a bridge. Pause in the middle. Look across the cities merging below—both the broken parts you’ve healed and the luminous parts you’re growing into.\n\nFeel your next step form clearly in your heart.\n\nWhen you are ready, cross the rest of the bridge. Open your eyes knowing your journey is shared, and your direction true.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Path of Destiny", "content": "E' is the nawal of the path, the road, and the journey. It represents the tooth (wisdom) and the destination. E' is the energy of the traveler, the explorer, and the guide. It governs the physical road as well as the spiritual path. E' energy is restless and forward-moving. In its shadow, E' can manifest as aimless wandering. Its highest expression is the conscious pilgrim who walks the path with purpose.", "keywords": ["Path", "Journey", "Road", "Exploration", "Destiny"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Manifestation", "content": "Ten is the number of manifestation, responsibility, and community agreement. It represents the two hands clasping together—collaboration and results. Ten is where intention becomes form. It is a solid, authoritative number. Experientially, a Ten day feels accomplished and 'real.' It is a day where things land. The shadow of Ten can be the burden of responsibility. It asks us to own our creations.", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Collaboration", "Fruition", "Authority"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Take a walk with a specific destination in mind.", "Plan a trip or a new career move; put it on the calendar.", "Collaborate with others who are on a similar path.", "Reflect on where your feet are taking you; do you like the direction?", "Visualize your path as a solid, golden road."], "title": "Manifesting the Path", "content": "When the manifesting power of Ten meets the journeying energy of E', we have a day of 'Realized Destiny' or 'The Solid Road.' Today, the path becomes clear and tangible. It is not a day for wandering; it is a day for walking. The Ten grounds the restless energy of E', turning a vague desire to travel into a concrete itinerary. It is an excellent day for starting a trip, moving house, or committing to a new life direction. The energy supports community on the path—walking together with others towards a shared goal. The challenge is responsibility; you must own the path you have chosen. There is no turning back today. Step forward with confidence, knowing that the road rises to meet you. You are manifesting your destiny with every step."}}	{"title": "The Guided Pilgrim", "content": "To be born on 10 E' is to be a leader on the path of life. You possess a restless spirit (E') that is grounded by a deep sense of purpose and responsibility (Ten). You are not a wanderer who gets lost; you are an explorer who draws the map for others. You have a natural authority and a talent for guiding groups, whether on physical journeys or spiritual ones. People follow you because you seem to know exactly where you are going.\\n\\nYour life path is one of manifestation through movement. You learn by doing and by going. You may have a career that involves travel, trade, or diplomacy. Your challenge is to not become too rigid in your itinerary. The road has twists and turns. Your lesson is to remain open to the detour while keeping your eyes on the destination. You are here to show us that the journey is real and that we can walk it together."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a0d0cc", "primary": "#0e1b1a", "secondary": "#344e4c"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.763361	2026-04-25 13:46:57.698889
147	12	4	4	Kej	The grey platform leads to a section of the canyon where the walls narrow. Here, the nets are anchored not to rock, but to four massive, ancient trees growing horizontally out of the cliffs. Their roots grip the stone like iron claws.\n\nThis is the Anchor of the Four Winds.\n\nThe nets here are thick, woven from heavy vines and bark. They do not sway. They are solid, stable, immovable. After the crumbling shells of yesterday, the solidity here feels like a blessing.\n\nKej is the Deer, the Guardian of the Wild. The number 4 is Stability. Today, the net catches you and holds you firm.\n\nA Stag stands on the suspended walkway. It is made of woven branches and moss, with antlers that reach up and interlock with the net above, supporting the roof of the canopy.\n\nYou approach the Stag. It stomps its hoof. The sound resonates through the entire structure, a deep, bass thrum that vibrates in your chest. *Thud.*\n\nIt reminds you that even in a world of suspension, you can be grounded. You don’t need the ground to be stable; you need your own four legs. You need your own four directions.\n\nYou stand next to the Stag. You spread your feet. You feel the strength of your own body. You look at the items in the net around you—here, they are tools. A walking stick. A compass. A cloak. A loaf of bread.\n\nThese are not burdens. These are provisions.\n\nYou realize that some of what you gathered is necessary. You need strength. You need protection. You need nourishment. The Stag teaches you to distinguish between the clutter and the kit.\n\nYou adjust your pack. It feels lighter, not because you dropped anything, but because you are carrying it correctly. You are balanced.	You are finding your footing today. The shaky ground of the last few days firms up. The energy of 4 Kej is like a strong oak tree. Lean on it.\n\nTake stock of your resources. You have more strength and support than you realize. Connect with nature to recharge your batteries. Stand tall, take up space, and don’t apologize for your power. You are the guardian of your own life.	I stand strong and stable, connected to the four directions of my life.	Stand up. Feel your feet rooting into the floor. Imagine roots going down through the building, into the soil, deep into the earth.\n\nFeel the energy of the Earth rising up into your legs. You are a tree. The wind can blow, the nets can sway, but you will not fall.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Guardian of the Wild", "content": "Kej is the deer, the sovereign of the wilderness, and the keeper of the four directions. It represents strength, agility, and a deep, harmonious connection with nature. Kej carries the energy of authority that is earned through grace. It is the alert sensitivity of the deer and the sturdy legs that climb the mountain. It asks us to stand tall, ground our energy, and find our rightful place within the ecosystem.", "keywords": ["Nature", "Strength", "Balance", "Leadership", "Harmony"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cube of Stability", "content": "The number 4 brings form, definition, and stability. It represents the four directions, the four elements, and the solid foundation of the physical world. 4 grounds the energy, creating a container or a structure where life can reside. In the K'at trecena, this is the day where the net is staked down. We establish the corners of our abundance and define the boundaries of what we are gathering. It is the pause to assess and measure.", "keywords": ["Stability", "Structure", "Grounding", "Foundation", "Definition"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Go to the four corners of your property and bless them.", "Spend time barefoot on the earth to discharge excess energy.", "Stand your ground in a situation that requires firm leadership.", "Work with the four elements (earth, air, fire, water) in a ritual.", "Observe the animals around you; they are teachers of balance today."], "title": "Stabilizing the Natural Order", "content": "4 Kej is one of the most stable and grounded days in the calendar. The structural energy of the 4 perfectly aligns with the four-legged stability of the Deer. Today, the K'at trecena asks us to ground our connections in the natural world. It is a day to stabilize your physical body, your home, and your relationship with the earth. The 'net' here becomes a physical structure—a safe perimeter. It is an excellent day for physical work, for spending time in the forest, and for asserting your boundaries with grace. The energy is calm, strong, and enduring. We are reminded that true abundance comes from being in right relationship with nature."}}	{"title": "The Guardian of the Four Directions", "content": "To be born on 4 Kej is to be a pillar of strength and a natural guardian of the earth. You possess a profound stability and a deep sense of responsibility toward the natural world. You are the person who holds the space, who keeps the vigil, and who ensures that the boundaries are respected. You have a regal quality, a quiet authority that commands respect without needing to be loud. You are deeply connected to the four elements and often feel most at home in the wilderness.\\n\\nYour life path is one of leadership and service to the natural order. You may be drawn to environmental work, land stewardship, or roles that require physical endurance and spiritual strength. You are reliable, grounded, and practical. People look to you for safety and direction when the world feels chaotic.\\n\\nYour challenge is flexibility. You can be so strong and so set in your ways that you become rigid or stubborn. The deer is agile, but the 4 is static; you must learn to move when the wind changes. Your lesson is to balance your strength with softness. When you learn to flow with the seasons of life while maintaining your strong roots, you become a majestic force for harmony, bridging the gap between civilization and the wild."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#7bb696", "primary": "#111a17", "secondary": "#414c3f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.827375	2026-04-25 13:46:57.910412
159	13	3	3	Imox	The storm remains steady, but your awareness begins to shift inward in a way that feels both unfamiliar and inevitable. The sound of the rain grows softer, not because it lessens, but because something deeper begins to draw your attention.\n\nYour thoughts loosen, drifting as though they are no longer anchored in the present moment. Images rise without effort—memories, emotions, fragments of experiences that do not always belong entirely to you. They move through your awareness like currents beneath the surface of water, connecting and dissolving in ways you cannot fully follow.\n\nThe caravan continues around you, but for a time, it feels distant, as though you are walking both within it and somewhere else entirely. The presence of others fades at the edges, and you find yourself alone within a vast, quiet interior space.\n\nIt is not empty.\n\nIt is full of movement, of memory, of something shared.\n\nYou begin to understand that the storm is not only external. It exists within this deeper layer as well, stirring the waters of something collective, something that connects each traveler in ways that are not immediately visible.\n\nFor a moment, the sensation is disorienting, as though you might lose yourself within it. But instead of resisting, you allow yourself to drift just slightly, trusting that the current will not carry you beyond what you can return from.\n\nGradually, the sound of footsteps returns. The presence of the caravan sharpens again. You lift your gaze and find yourself back among them, though something within you remains changed.	Something beneath the surface is stirring, and it may not speak in words.\n\nToday has a drifting quality to it, like your thoughts are moving through water rather than air. You may find it harder to stay anchored in linear thinking, harder to follow the straight lines you usually rely on to navigate your day. Memories may surface without warning. Emotions may arrive without clear origin.\n\nThis is not confusion.\n\nThis is depth.\n\nYou are touching something collective—something that does not belong only to you, but moves through you as part of a larger current. It can feel disorienting at first, like losing your footing in familiar territory. But if you resist the urge to immediately make sense of it, something else becomes available.\n\nA kind of listening.\n\nNot the kind that searches for answers, but the kind that allows meaning to rise on its own.\n\nYou don't need to chase clarity today. In fact, doing so may pull you further from what is trying to reveal itself. Instead, let yourself drift just slightly. Let your awareness soften around the edges. Notice what repeats. Notice what lingers.\n\nThere is intelligence in the patterns you're feeling.\n\nEven if you can't translate them yet.\n\nGive yourself space. Step back when needed. Spend time alone, not as avoidance, but as integration.\n\nYou are not lost.\n\nYou are in deeper water.\n\nAnd something within you knows how to swim here.	I trust the deeper currents within me to guide my understanding.	Sit quietly and close your eyes.\nBring your attention inward, as if you are listening to something just beneath the surface.\nNotice any thoughts, feelings, or sensations that arise.\nInstead of chasing them, let them come and go like waves.\nStay with your breath, steady and calm.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine yourself beneath the surface of a vast ocean. Around you, soft glowing currents drift in slow motion. Each current carries a feeling, a memory, or a truth. You do not need to grab any of them. Just observe. Over time, you begin to recognize which currents feel true and which feel distorted. Trust what settles naturally.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Dreamer of the Deep", "content": "Imox is the energy of the primordial ocean, the collective unconscious, and the dream world. It represents the left hemisphere of the brain—intuition, art, and the madness of divine inspiration. Imox is the water that connects all things, carrying the memories of the ancestors and the seeds of creation. It is the womb of the world, fluid and often chaotic.", "keywords": ["Water", "Dreams", "Intuition", "Collective", "Madness"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Movement", "content": "The number 3 introduces movement, flow, and the disruption of static balance. It is the energy of communication, expression, and the creative spark. 3 breaks the deadlock of duality to create a dynamic flow. In this trecena, 3 sets the waters of the storm into motion, creating currents of feeling and intuition that cannot be ignored.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Expression", "Flow", "Rhythm", "Creativity"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Keep a dream journal; the messages are loud today.", "Create art without thinking; let the hand move the brush.", "Spend time by a river or ocean to align with the flow.", "Trust your 'crazy' ideas; they are coming from the source.", "Practice grounding to keep from floating away completely."], "title": "The Current of Dreams", "content": "3 Imox is a day of profound fluidity and psychic movement. The rhythm of the 3 stirs the deep waters of Imox, creating high tides of emotion and intuition. The storm of the trecena here becomes an internal flood of images and feelings. It is a day where the veil between the conscious and unconscious is incredibly thin. You may feel ungrounded or 'spacetime' might feel slippery. It is a powerful day for artists, healers, and dreamers to ride the waves of the collective mind. However, it requires a paddle—some form of creative expression to channel the flow so it doesn't overwhelm you."}}	{"title": "The Weaver of Dreams", "content": "To be born on 3 Imox is to live with one foot in the physical world and one foot in the ocean of the collective soul. You are a conduit for the unseen, possessing a psychic sensitivity that is always 'on.' You are fluid, adaptable, and deeply emotional. Like water, you take the shape of the container you are in, which makes you incredibly empathetic but also prone to losing your own boundaries. You are a natural artist, musician, or healer, channeling the rhythms of the universe into form.\\n\\nYour life path is one of navigating the deep waters. You feel the emotions of others as if they were your own. You are often the 'weird' one in the family, the one who sees ghosts or knows things before they happen. Your mind is a swirling vortex of creativity, which can be a gift or a curse depending on how well you can direct the flow.\\n\\nYour challenge is mental stability. The 3 Imox energy can lead to overwhelm, anxiety, or a sense of drowning in the chaos of life. You may struggle to stay consistent or grounded. Your lesson is to become the surfer, not the driftwood. When you learn to harness your intuitive gifts with discipline, you become a visionary artist who can bring the healing waters of the spirit realm to a thirsty world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#7bc1b5", "primary": "#101d1b", "secondary": "#36524e"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#9b9586", "primary": "#202629", "secondary": "#4c5453"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#c0abc2", "primary": "#465e84", "secondary": "#7b81a6"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#84c0d2", "primary": "#0a2844", "secondary": "#307196"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.834912	2026-04-25 14:25:01.113611
94	8	3	3	K'at	The bridge ends on a large island covered in tall, swaying reeds made of silver metal. The wind whistles through them, creating a chaotic, atonal music.\n\nAs you walk through the silver grass, your feet get tangled. You look down. The ground is covered in a mesh of fine golden wires. They are everywhere, crisscrossing the path, snagging your boots, catching on your clothes.\n\nThis is the Wind-Trap.\n\nThe more you struggle to kick them off, the tighter they bind. The wind picks up, blowing harder, whipping the wires around you. You feel trapped in a web of your own making.\n\nK’at is the Net—the energy that gathers, but also the energy that tangles. The number 3 is movement. You are moving too fast, thrashing against the net.\n\nYou stop. You stand perfectly still in the howling wind.\n\nYou look at the wires closely. They are not barbed. They are just... accumulated. They are the thoughts you collected and never let go of. The "to-do" lists, the worries, the mental clutter.\n\nYou reach down and gently pick up one wire. You trace it back. It leads to a small, heavy stone labeled "Urgency." You untie it. The wire falls away.\n\nYou pick up another. "Distraction." You untie it.\n\nYou realize that the net is not a cage; it is a storage system you forgot to clean out. The wind is trying to help you—it is blowing away the loose ends, if you would only unhook them.\n\nYou spend time in the field, methodically untying the knots. With each release, the wind sounds less like screaming and more like singing.\n\nFreed from the snare, you step lightly out of the silver grass. Your mind feels spacious, like a room that has just been swept.	Your mind might feel a bit cluttered today, like a browser with too many tabs open. The energy of 3 K’at can feel frantic if you try to hold onto everything.\n\nThe solution is simple: Close the tabs. You don’t need to know everything, do everything, or be everything. Pick one thread and follow it. Let the rest go. The wind is here to help you declutter your headspace. Let it blow through.	I release the thoughts that tangle me and step into the freedom of clarity.	Imagine a golden net covering your body. In the gaps of the net are stuck grey leaves (your worries). \n\nVisualize a strong, warm wind blowing from your left to your right. Watch as it dislodges the grey leaves. They fly off into the distance, leaving the net clean and shining. Feel the lightness of being untangled.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Cosmic Net", "content": "K'at is the Nawal of the net, the spider web, and the gathering of abundance. It represents the principle of connection—how things are tied together. K'at is the energy that catches what we need (abundance) and what we don't need (entanglements). It governs the harvest, the storage of seeds, and the release of burdens. In human experience, K'at manifests as the ability to network, to organize, and to carry a load. It is the burning of the net to free the captive. When aligned, K'at brings fruitful connections; when misaligned, it can lead to feeling trapped.", "keywords": ["Gathering", "Release", "Abundance", "Net", "Entanglement"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Action", "content": "The number Three introduces movement, rhythm, and flow into the equation. It represents the pulse of life—the heartbeat, the breath, and the natural oscillation of energy. Experientially, this energy feels active and sometimes restless; it pushes things forward and breaks stagnation. It is the energy of 'doing' rather than just 'being.' The shadow of Three can be scattered energy or instability, but its light is the joy of unimpeded expression. Today, the universe is humming, and it asks you to move with it.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Expression", "Rhythm", "Energy", "Instability"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Reach out to three people you haven't spoken to in a while.", "Declutter one area of your home to keep the energy moving.", "Organize a social gathering or a team meeting.", "Check your 'nets'—are you holding onto things you don't need?", "Trust the flow of abundance; what is meant for you will be caught."], "title": "Active Gathering", "content": "The rhythmic movement of Tone 3 meets the gathering nature of K'at to create a day of 'Dynamic Networking.' 3 K'at is the energy of the spider weaving its web with speed and precision. It is a day to actively cast your net—to reach out to your community, to gather resources, and to organize your life. The energy is restless and productive. You may feel a strong urge to declutter (releasing the net) or to bring people together for a cause (gathering). It is not a day to sit still; the abundance is in the movement. Go out and find what you need. Connect the dots. However, be careful not to get tangled in your own busyness; the shadow of 3 K'at is scattering your energy in too many directions. Focus your rhythm on catching the specific dreams you want to harvest. Dance with your burdens until they feel light."}}	{"title": "The Weaver of Connections", "content": "To be born on 3 K'at is to be a social dynamo and a master of networks. You are the 'Active Gatherer'—someone who instinctively knows how to bring people and resources together in a rhythmic, harmonious way. You are likely very popular, with a wide circle of friends and a talent for organization. You are always in motion, spinning webs of connection that benefit everyone around you. You are the person who knows 'a guy for that' and who loves to facilitate introductions.\\n\\nYour life path is one of abundance through connection. The number 3 gives you a playful, expressive nature, preventing the 'net' of K'at from becoming too heavy or serious. However, you may struggle with over-commitment or feeling trapped by the very networks you create. Your challenge is to learn when to stop weaving and rest, and to ensure that you are gathering things that truly nourish your soul. You are here to show us that we are all connected in the great web of life."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d09e6b", "primary": "#111513", "secondary": "#4b3a33"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#a2977c", "primary": "#132136", "secondary": "#404c5b"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#909fab", "primary": "#2c3653", "secondary": "#5a6a82"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#a9aeaf", "primary": "#575752", "secondary": "#848783"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.79505	2026-04-25 13:46:57.822967
155	12	12	12	Tz'ikin	The night passes, and the sun rises. But you are not on the canyon floor anymore. The magic of the Jaguar lifted you up. You are standing on the High Mesa, overlooking the entire valley.\n\n12 is Understanding. Tz’ikin is the Bird, the Vision.\n\nYou look down. You see the canyon, the nets, the river, the village. But from up here, you don’t see the clutter. You see the pattern.\n\nYou see that the nets were catching exactly what you needed. You see how the river moved the energy to the right place. You see the village as a perfect mandala of abundance.\n\nA great Eagle lands beside you. Its feathers are made of clouds and sunlight. It offers you its eyes.\n\nYou look through them. You see your life not as a series of struggles, but as a masterpiece of gathering. Every heartbreak, every joy, every delay—it was all necessary to weave the net that caught *you*.\n\nYou feel a surge of prosperity. Not just money, but a wealth of experience, of soul. You are rich in life.\n\nThe Eagle spreads its wings. You realize that the net was never meant to hold you; it was meant to launch you. You are not the catch. You are the bird.	The view is spectacular today. The energy of 12 Tz’ikin lifts you up so you can see the whole map. You understand why you had to go through the messy parts. It was all leading here.\n\nOpen your eyes to opportunity. Prosperity is looking for you. Trust your vision. If you can see it, you can have it. You are free to fly.	I rise above the details to see the beautiful vision of my prosperous life.	Visualize yourself as an eagle flying over a mountain range. The air is crisp and clear. You can see for miles.\n\nSpot a golden shiny object in the distance. That is your goal. Fly towards it. Feel the wind in your wings. Nothing can stop you.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Visionary Eagle", "content": "Tz'ikin is the bird, the eagle, and the vision. It represents prosperity, freedom, and the ability to see the whole picture. Tz'ikin is the intermediary between heaven and earth, carrying prayers up and bringing abundance down. It governs business and the clear vision required to manifest dreams.", "keywords": ["Vision", "Prosperity", "Freedom", "Eagle", "Abundance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Crystal of Understanding", "content": "The number 12 represents understanding, wisdom, and the bundling of experience. It is the highest even number, representing a stable, complex wholeness. 12 brings the capacity to understand the 'why' of the journey and to synthesize lessons. In the K'at trecena, 12 is the day we review the harvest. We look at what we have gathered and understand its value and purpose.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Wisdom", "Synthesis", "Community", "Review"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Review your finances and goals with a sense of wisdom, not scarcity.", "Share your resources or your vision with others.", "Look for the 'golden thread' that runs through your life experiences.", "Ask for a vision of your highest future.", "Celebrate the freedom that comes from understanding your worth."], "title": "The Wisdom of Prosperity", "content": "12 Tz'ikin is a day of expansive vision and profound understanding regarding abundance. The wisdom of the 12 meets the prosperity of the Eagle. Today, we understand the true nature of the net we have woven. We see that true wealth is not just material, but spiritual and communal. It is a day of 'big picture' thinking. We can see how all the threads connect to create a life of freedom. The energy is joyful, wise, and abundant. It is a time to share your vision with the community and to give thanks for the prosperity that flows through you."}}	{"title": "The Wise Visionary", "content": "To be born on 12 Tz'ikin is to be a master of spiritual and material abundance. You possess a sweeping vision and the wisdom to understand how to bring it into reality. You are not just lucky; you are wise. You understand the laws of prosperity and the importance of flow. You are a natural philanthropist and a leader who lifts others up. You see the best in people and the potential in every situation.\\n\\nYour life path is one of synthesis. You bring together the spiritual and the material, the earth and the sky. You are a gatherer of wisdom as much as wealth. You have a magnetic personality and a joyous spirit that inspires those around you. You are here to demonstrate that abundance is our natural state.\\n\\nYour challenge is to not get lost in the clouds. While your vision is vast, you must remember the details of the ground. You may also struggle with the responsibility that comes with your gifts. Your lesson is to use your prosperity to serve the collective understanding. When you share your vision with humility and wisdom, you become a great uplifter, helping humanity soar to new heights."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a9d8c4", "primary": "#0f1918", "secondary": "#404740"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.832123	2026-04-25 13:46:57.905761
96	8	5	5	Kame	The garden fades into mist. The path spirals upward, steep and narrow, leading to a solitary spire of gray stone that pierces the highest cloud layer. \n\nThis is the Tower of Silence.\n\nAs you climb, the air gets colder. The playful wind of the lower levels is gone. Here, the air is still and heavy with presence. You reach the top—a flat, circular platform exposed to the void.\n\nIn the center sits a skull carved from white quartz. It is not frightening; it is beautiful. It glows with a pale inner light.\n\nKame is Death—not as an end, but as a transformation. It is the Great Silencer. The number 5 is the energy of work and empowerment. Today, the work is to let something die so you can speak a new truth.\n\nYou realize that to find your true voice, you must let the old voices die. The voice of your parents, your teachers, your fears, your society. They are all chattering in your head, clogging the channel.\n\nYou sit before the quartz skull. You close your mouth. You close your mind.\n\nYou offer the noise to the silence. You imagine the old scripts dissolving into the thin air. You let the part of you that is a "people pleaser" die. You let the part of you that is "afraid to be seen" die.\n\nIt feels like a weight falling off your throat.\n\nIn the absolute silence that follows, you hear it. A tiny, quiet sound. It is your own true voice, waiting for a turn to speak.\n\nYou stand up. You gather your power. You are not the same person who climbed the tower. You are quieter now, but much, much louder.	Silence is powerful today. In a world that is constantly shouting, the most radical thing you can do is be quiet and listen. The energy of 5 Kame asks you to let the noise die down.\n\nSomething in your life is ready to transform. Don’t be afraid of the ending; it’s just the universe making space for what you actually asked for. Trust the void. It’s not empty; it’s pregnant.	I release the old to make space for the new, trusting the cycle of my life.	Visualize a tree in autumn. Watch as it drops its leaves. It doesn’t fight the process. It trusts that the leaves will return in spring.\n\nImagine yourself as the tree. Drop your "leaves"—your worries, your old stories. Feel the lightness of your bare branches. Rest in the winter of your spirit.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Transformer", "content": "Kame is the Nawal of death, rebirth, and the ancestors. It represents the only certainty in life: change. Kame is the energy that closes one door so another can open. It governs spiritual initiation, mediumship, and the courage to face the unknown. In human experience, Kame manifests as a connection to the spirit world, a talent for helping others through transitions, and deep inner strength. It is the peaceful rest after the struggle. When aligned, Kame brings profound transformation and ancestral protection; when misaligned, it can lead to fear of change.", "keywords": ["Death", "Rebirth", "Ancestors", "Transformation", "Courage"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Action", "content": "The number Five represents the center point of the first wave of creation. It is the energy of the hand (five fingers) and the power to grasp, work, and manipulate reality. In Mayan cosmology, Five is the force of 'doing'; it breaks the static stability of Four and puts it into motion through effort. Experientially, this energy feels like a surge of willpower and a drive to get things done. It is the number of work, discipline, and the application of energy. The shadow of Five can be forcing things, but its light is the satisfaction of a job well done.", "keywords": ["Action", "Discipline", "Work", "Willpower", "Effort"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Actively let go of a habit that no longer serves you.", "Do the 'work' of grief or healing; don't just wait for time to heal it.", "Clean and organize a space to invite new energy.", "Make an offering to your ancestors and ask for their help in your work.", "Face a fear head-on; take action despite the uncertainty."], "title": "Active Transformation", "content": "When the working energy of Tone 5 meets the transformative power of Kame, we engage in the 'Work of Rebirth.' 5 Kame is not a passive change; it is a day to actively participate in your own transformation. The energy asks you to put in the effort to change your life. It is an excellent day to clean out the closets (literal and metaphorical), to break an addiction through discipline, or to work on resolving ancestral trauma. The ancestors are rolling up their sleeves to help you today. The feeling is one of purposeful transition—you are the midwife of your own rebirth. It may feel like hard work, but the results will be profound. Do not shy away from the difficult tasks today; face the 'death' of the old ways with courage and action. The compost you turn today will feed the garden of tomorrow."}}	{"title": "The Agent of Rebirth", "content": "To be born on 5 Kame is to be a catalyst for profound change. You are the 'Active Transformer'—a soul who is not afraid to get their hands dirty in the work of life and death. You have a resilient spirit and a practical approach to the mysteries. You are likely the person who helps others rebuild their lives after a crisis, offering not just sympathy but concrete solutions. You understand that transformation requires effort, and you are willing to do the heavy lifting.\\n\\nYour life path is one of constant evolution through work. You may face many 'deaths' and 'rebirths' in your lifetime—career changes, identity shifts, or deep spiritual awakenings. The number 5 gives you the strength and discipline to navigate these changes successfully. Your challenge is to not become hardened by the struggle, but to remain soft enough to feel the beauty of the cycle. You are here to show us that we have the power to reshape our destiny."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#dbd1b3", "primary": "#111210", "secondary": "#423c32"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.795745	2026-04-25 13:46:57.83006
160	13	4	4	Iq'	The next day brings a subtle but noticeable shift. The storm remains, but its rhythm feels more structured, as though it has settled into a pattern that can be followed.\n\nVoices begin to emerge within the caravan, quiet at first, then more frequent. A few words exchanged between travelers, a brief question, a simple acknowledgment. The effect is immediate, though difficult to describe. The air feels clearer, less heavy, as though something has been released.\n\nYou become aware of your own breath in a way you had not before. It has been shallow, restricted by tension you had not fully noticed. You take a deeper inhale, letting the damp air fill your lungs, and as you exhale, you feel a small but meaningful sense of grounding.\n\nNearby, two travelers who had previously clashed begin to speak again. This time, their words are measured, not reactive. There is no urgency in their tone, only an effort to understand. The storm does not disappear, but it aligns, its intensity evening out as if responding to the shift in communication.\n\nYou begin to recognize that movement is not only physical. It exists in breath, in speech, in the way people choose to relate to one another.\n\nWith each step, the caravan becomes more cohesive, not because the storm has lessened, but because something within it has found a rhythm.	There is a shift in the air today, and you can feel it if you slow down enough to notice.\n\nAfter the emotional depth of yesterday, something begins to organize itself—not by force, but through rhythm. Your breath becomes a guide. Your words begin to matter in a different way. The space between you and others becomes more responsive, more alive.\n\nThis is a day for clearing.\n\nNot in a dramatic sense, but in the small, meaningful adjustments that create space for something new to move through. A conversation that has been avoided may feel easier to approach. A misunderstanding may soften simply because you choose to listen differently.\n\nYou don't need the perfect words.\n\nYou need honest ones.\n\nThere is power today in speaking from a place that is grounded rather than reactive. In letting your breath lead your voice instead of your urgency. You may find that when you slow down just slightly, what needs to be said becomes clearer on its own.\n\nAnd just as important—what doesn't need to be said will become just as obvious.\n\nCommunication today is not about control. It is about alignment.\n\nWith yourself.\n\nWith others.\n\nWith the moment as it actually is, not as you wish it would be.\n\nTake a deep breath.\n\nLet it out slowly.\n\nThere is more clarity available than you think.	I express myself clearly and receive others with openness.	Close your eyes and take a deep inhale.\nFeel the air enter your body, filling your chest and belly.\nAs you exhale, imagine that breath extending outward beyond you.\nContinue this pattern, noticing that breath connects you to everything around you.\nThere is no separation—just flow.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine each breath as a glowing thread extending from you into the world. These threads gently connect you to others, to the earth, to the unseen. You notice that when your breath is calm, these threads are clear and steady. When your breath is tense, they become tangled. Simply breathe and allow the threads to soften and align.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Breath of Spirit", "content": "Iq' is the energy of the wind, the breath, and communication. It represents the vital spirit that animates all life. Iq' is the messenger of the gods, bringing inspiration, clarity, and change. It governs the mind, ideas, and the power of the spoken word. It can be the gentle breeze of inspiration or the hurricane of destruction.", "keywords": ["Wind", "Breath", "Communication", "Inspiration", "Spirit"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cube of Stability", "content": "The number 4 brings form, definition, and stability. It represents the four directions, the four elements, and the solid foundation of the physical world. 4 grounds the energy, creating a container where life can reside. In the Kawoq trecena, this is the day the storm finds its path. The chaotic waters of Imox are channeled into a stable riverbed.", "keywords": ["Stability", "Structure", "Foundation", "Definition", "Four Directions"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Practice breathwork or meditation to stabilize your mind.", "Write down your feelings to give them structure.", "Have a difficult conversation; the wind is steady today.", "Open the windows and let fresh air cleanse your home.", "Speak your intentions into the four directions."], "title": "The Stabilized Breath", "content": "4 Iq' brings a welcome clarity and stability to the stormy energy of the trecena. The grounding of the 4 gives structure to the wind of Iq'. Today, the wild emotions of the previous days can be articulated and understood. It is a day of 'grounded inspiration.' The storm clears, leaving the air crisp and fresh. It is an excellent day for communication, for writing, and for speaking your truth with calmness and authority. The breath is deep and steady. We find the eye of the storm, a place of stable center from which we can communicate clearly with the world."}}	{"title": "The Voice of Clarity", "content": "To be born on 4 Iq' is to be a stabilizing force for communication and truth. You possess a sharp mind and a gift with words, but unlike the erratic wind, your expression is grounded and purposeful. You are the person who can explain complex ideas simply, or who can bring calm to a heated argument with a few well-chosen words. You are a bridge between the realm of ideas and the realm of form, able to manifest inspiration into reality.\\n\\nYour life path is one of breathing life into structure. You may be drawn to writing, teaching, or architecture—any field where air (ideas) meets earth (form). You have a respiratory system that is sensitive to the 'atmosphere' of a room. You thrive in environments that are clean, open, and honest.\\n\\nYour challenge is rigidity vs. chaos. You may sometimes try to control the wind, becoming dogmatic or overly intellectual to avoid the messiness of emotion. Or, you may fear that if you speak freely, you will blow everything down. Your lesson is to trust your breath. When you speak from your centered, stable core, your words become a powerful medicine that clears the air and inspires the world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#dacde2", "primary": "#131b1d", "secondary": "#4c495b"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.835215	2026-04-25 14:25:01.114895
218	17	10	10	Kej					{"nawal": {"title": "The Guardian of the Wild", "content": "Kej is the nawal of the deer, the four directions, and the wilderness. It represents harmony with nature and balance between the physical and spiritual worlds. Protector of the forests and sacred paths. Associated with the element of earth and the color brown or green, it carries a strong, majestic, and grounded energy. It is the archetype of the spiritual leader who stands on four legs, stable and alert. In daily life, Kej manifests as connection to nature, physical strength, and the authority that comes from walking one's talk. Its shadow aspect can be stubbornness, dominance, or being overly demanding. Kej teaches us to stand our ground with grace.", "keywords": ["Nature", "Grounding", "Balance", "Strength", "Grace"]}, "number": {"title": "The Manifestation of Responsibility", "content": "Tone 10 is the energy of manifestation, collaboration, and the two hands coming together. It represents the realization of the intention set in Tone 1. In the cycle, 10 is where the work hits the physical plane in a concrete way. It is a number of community, agreement, and the solidity of creation. Experientially, Tone 10 feels grounded, productive, and social. It is a day to shake hands, sign contracts, and see the tangible results of your efforts. While it fosters achievement and connection, its shadow can be the heavy weight of responsibility or the pressure to perform for the group. It is the number of the builder who sees the walls rise.", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Collaboration", "Result", "Community"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Spend time outdoors connecting with the four directions.", "Take a leadership role in a community project.", "Stand firm on a decision you have made; do not wobble.", "Collaborate with others to create a physical result.", "Walk barefoot on the earth to ground your manifesting energy."], "title": "Manifesting Natural Authority", "content": "The manifesting power of Tone 10 combines with the grounded strength of Kej to create a day of 'Solid Leadership.' 10 Kej is the energy of the Stag standing firm in the center of the forest. It is a day to take your place in the world and own your authority. The energy supports tangible achievements, especially those that involve community or the environment. It feels stable, strong, and undeniable. 10 Kej asks us to collaborate with nature and with each other to build something lasting. It is an excellent day for outdoor work, community service, or asserting your boundaries in a respectful way. The combination suggests that true power is not about force, but about presence. The challenge is to lead without dominating, to be strong without being rigid. The opportunity is to manifest a reality that is in harmony with the natural laws."}}	{"title": "The Pillar of Natural Strength", "content": "To be born on 10 Kej is to be a pillar of your community and a guardian of the natural world. You possess a strong, stable presence that commands respect without you having to say a word. Tone 10 gives you a collaborative spirit and a drive to build tangible things, while Kej connects you to the four directions and the wisdom of the wilderness. You are the person others look to for protection and guidance. You are likely drawn to leadership roles, environmental work, or any path that allows you to be an authority figure who serves the greater good.\\n\\nYour life path is one of manifesting harmony. You are here to show how human society can coexist with nature's laws. You have a deep, physical intelligence; you 'know' things in your bones. You are a builder, a stabilizer, and a reliable friend. People trust you because you are consistent—like the sun or the seasons. You have a refined aesthetic sense, appreciating the beauty of the natural world and seeking to bring that beauty into human spaces.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 10 Kej soul is rigidity. You can be stubborn, digging your hooves in even when it would be better to move. You may have high standards for yourself and others, leading to frustration when things are not 'perfect' or 'correct.' The weight of responsibility can sometimes feel heavy on your shoulders. Your growth comes from learning flexibility—the grace of the Deer. When you learn to adapt without losing your ground, you become a true spiritual leader, guiding others with strength and compassion."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#e4d69e", "primary": "#1d1d14", "secondary": "#715934"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.860975	2026-04-25 13:46:57.999748
107	9	3	3	Ajmaq					{"nawal": {"title": "The Owl of Wisdom", "content": "Ajmaq is the Nawal of the Owl, the ancestors, and the concept of forgiveness. It represents the wisdom that comes from experience—specifically, the wisdom gained through making mistakes. Ajmaq is the energy of pardon, redemption, and the sweetness of life that returns when we release guilt. It governs the lineage and the unseen connection to those who came before. In human experience, Ajmaq manifests as curiosity, a probing mind, and a deep capacity for empathy. It is the 'sinner' and the saint wrapped in one. It is the gentle hand that wipes the slate clean.", "keywords": ["Forgiveness", "Ancestors", "Wisdom", "Curiosity", "Redemption"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Action", "content": "The number Three introduces movement, rhythm, and flow into the equation. It represents the pulse of life—the heartbeat, the breath, and the natural oscillation of energy. Experientially, this energy feels active and sometimes restless; it pushes things forward and breaks stagnation. It is the energy of 'doing' rather than just 'being.' The shadow of Three can be scattered energy or instability, but its light is the joy of unimpeded expression. Today, the universe is humming, and it asks you to move with it.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Expression", "Rhythm", "Energy", "Instability"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Write a letter of forgiveness (to yourself or another) and burn it.", "Move your body to release stored emotions.", "Ask curious questions about your family history.", "Do not dwell on mistakes; acknowledge them and move on.", "Be kind to yourself; perfection is not the goal today."], "title": "The Rhythm of Forgiveness", "content": "When the active movement of Tone 3 meets the forgiving nature of Ajmaq, we experience a day of 'Active Redemption.' 3 Ajmaq is the energy of moving through guilt rather than getting stuck in it. It is a day to take action on your forgiveness—to write the letter, make the call, or perform the ritual that releases the burden. The energy is fluid and curious. It asks: Why did this happen? What can I learn from it? How can I move forward? The Owl (Ajmaq) flies through the night, and the number 3 gives it speed and agility. This is a powerful day for ancestral work that involves movement, such as visiting a gravesite or dancing for those who came before. Don't let the past stagnate; let the river of forgiveness flow. It is also a day to be curious about your own shadows, approaching them with a playful rather than judgmental spirit."}}	{"title": "The Curious Healer", "content": "To be born on 3 Ajmaq is to be a soul in constant motion toward wisdom. You are the 'Active Owl'—someone who learns by doing, stumbling, and getting back up again. You have a restless, inquisitive mind that wants to understand the depths of human nature. You are likely very forgiving and non-judgmental, as you understand that making mistakes is part of the rhythm of life. You may be the person in your family who breaks the old patterns by simply refusing to sit still in them.\\n\\nYour life path is one of redemption through experience. You are not an armchair philosopher; you are out in the world, mixing it up, making messes, and finding the gold within them. The number 3 gives you a communicative, expressive gift, allowing you to share your hard-won wisdom with others. Your challenge is to ensure that your curiosity doesn't lead you into trouble you can't get out of, and to forgive yourself as easily as you forgive others. You are here to teach us that life is a dance of falling and rising."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c39dc8", "primary": "#101518", "secondary": "#3a3342"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.802087	2026-04-25 13:46:57.855666
174	14	5	5	B'atz'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Weaver of Time", "content": "B'atz' is the thread of time, the artist, and the weaver of destiny. It represents creativity, the arts, and the beginning of new cycles. B'atz' is the monkey, the playful trickster who holds the sacred calendar. It governs the weaving together of community and purpose. It reminds us that we are the artists of our own lives.", "keywords": ["Creativity", "Weaving", "Time", "Art", "Joy"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Empowerment", "content": "The number 5 represents empowerment, work, and the human hand. It is the energy of doing, gathering, and applying will to the structures created by the 4. 5 breaks the stability to put things into motion through effort. In this trecena, 5 represents the creative work required to weave our connection to nature.", "keywords": ["Action", "Work", "Effort", "Empowerment", "Clarity"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Dedicate time to a creative project; do the work.", "Weave a solution to a complex problem.", "Take action to bring people together.", "Start a new cycle or habit with determination.", "Use your hands to create something beautiful."], "title": "Weaving with Power", "content": "5 B'atz' is a day of industrious creativity. The empowerment of the 5 drives the weaving of B'atz'. In the Kej trecena, this is where we actively weave our life into the pattern of the wild. It is a day to work on your masterpiece—whether that is art, a business, or your own character. The energy is busy, fun, and productive. It asks us to put effort into our connections and to take action on our creative impulses. The Monkey is working hard today, spinning the threads of time into something tangible."}}	{"title": "The Active Creator", "content": "To be born on 5 B'atz' is to be a dynamo of creative energy. You are not just a dreamer; you are a maker. You possess the Monkey's artistic vision combined with the 5's drive to work. You are prolific, often juggling multiple projects at once. You have a talent for bringing people together and initiating new ventures. You are the one who starts the dance, organizes the festival, or launches the startup.\\n\\nYour life path is one of active expression. You learn by doing, by making, by weaving. You are likely charming, clever, and persuasive. You have a knack for timing and for seeing the patterns in things.\\n\\nYour challenge is scattered energy. You can be so busy starting things that you never finish them. The Monkey mind can be restless, and the 5 can be impulsive. Your lesson is discipline. When you focus your considerable energy on a single thread, you can weave a masterpiece that stands the test of time."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d38b86", "primary": "#1e1a1f", "secondary": "#763740"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.841788	2026-04-25 13:46:57.952177
177	14	8	8	Ix					{"nawal": {"title": "The Jaguar's Magic", "content": "Ix is the jaguar, the shaman, and the energy of the night. It represents earth magic, shrines, and deep feminine intuition. Ix is the power to see in the dark and to transform negativity into wisdom. It is independent, stealthy, and connected to the mysteries of nature. It asks us to trust the invisible forces.", "keywords": ["Magic", "Jaguar", "Intuition", "Earth", "Stealth"]}, "number": {"title": "The Harmonic Resonance", "content": "The number 8 represents the octave, wholeness, and the fabric of life. It wraps up the bundle of the previous seven days, bringing organic closure and harmony. 8 is the number of male spirituality and resonance. In this trecena, 8 brings the wild energy into harmony with the earth's magic.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Wholeness", "Resonance", "Fabric", "Ceremony"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a ceremony in nature to honor the earth spirits.", "Visit a sacred site or a place of power.", "Trust your intuition completely today.", "Offer gratitude to the feminine aspect of divinity.", "Feel the magic in the soil, the rocks, and the trees."], "title": "Harmonizing with Earth Magic", "content": "8 Ix is a day of profound ceremonial magic and connection to the earth. The wholeness of the 8 meets the shamanic power of the Jaguar. In the Kej trecena, this is where the Deer and the Jaguar meet—prey and predator—in a sacred balance. It is a day to honor the earth, the shrines, and the feminine mysteries. The energy is deep, velvet, and resonant. It is the perfect day for ritual, for visiting sacred sites, and for harmonizing with the natural world. We realize that we are part of a magical ecosystem."}}	{"title": "The Earth Shaman", "content": "To be born on 8 Ix is to be a guardian of the earth's magic. You possess a deep, resonant connection to nature and the invisible realms. You are a natural shaman, healer, or earth-keeper. You have a wholeness about you, a sense of being completely at home in your own skin and on the planet. You are independent and powerful, with a quiet intensity that draws others to you.\\n\\nYour life path is one of sacred service to the earth. You are here to remember the old ways and to keep the magic alive. You have a talent for ritual and for sensing the energies of a place. You are a protector of the wild.\\n\\nYour challenge is secrecy. The Jaguar is solitary and stealthy; you may struggle to share your inner world or to trust others. You may also feel the pain of the earth more acuteley than most. Your lesson is to bring your magic into the light. When you share your deep wisdom with the community, you become a powerful healer, restoring the sacred bond between humanity and the earth."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a3c881", "primary": "#111c1a", "secondary": "#43553e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.842863	2026-04-25 13:46:57.955923
140	11	10	10	Ix	You emerge from the hollow into a canopy where the light is dappled and the shadows feel alive. This is the realm of the Jaguar, where the magic of the earth is thick enough to touch. You find an ancient altar of stone embedded into the moss-covered wood of a massive root, its surface etched with the spots of the great cat. The number 10 demands manifestation; it is time to take responsibility for the power you have cultivated. You begin to gather stones of translucent quartz and pieces of fallen obsidian, arranging them on the altar with a shaman’s focus.\n\nAs you build the shrine, the veil between the Spire and the spirit world thins. You are not just placing rocks; you are anchoring your magic into the Heart of the Earth. With every stone, your intuition sharpens, granting you the jaguar’s ability to see in the dark. The Altar of the Heart becomes a battery for your intent, glowing with a deep, emerald-green light that reflects the vitality of the entire forest. You realize that your personal power is a tangible force, capable of shaping the reality around you. You stand before your creation, your eyes reflecting the velvet power of the night, ready to walk with the stealth and grace of a master who has bridged the gap between spirit and matter.	The canopy shadows are coming alive today, and the veil between what you see with your eyes and what you know with your gut has become paper-thin. You are stepping into the realm of the jaguar, where intuition is the only compass that matters. It is time to take absolute, radical responsibility for the magic you are currently manifesting into the world. \n\nYour thoughts are turning into tangible things with frightening speed today, so anchor them with fierce intention. Build a physical altar in your mind—or in your living space—and place your heart’s desires upon it like stones of raw quartz. Do not let your focus scatter. Move with stealth and deliberate grace. \n\nYou have the eyes to see in the dark now, spotting the truth behind the masks that others wear and the illusions you’ve told yourself. This isn't a day for loud declarations; it’s a day for the quiet, focused power of a predator who knows exactly what they are hunting. The earth itself is holding its breath, waiting to see what you will choose to bring into reality.	I take responsibility for my magic and anchor my intentions into the heart of the earth.	Focus on your heart as a battery of intent. Realize that your thoughts are tangible forces that can shape the reality around you. \n\nOptionally, move with stealth through a dappled canopy where the veil between worlds is thin, your eyes reflecting the velvet power of the magical night.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Jaguar's Magic", "content": "Ix is the jaguar, the shaman, and the energy of the night. It represents the magic of the earth, the shrines in the mountains, and the deep feminine intuition. Ix is the power to see in the dark and the ability to transform negativity into wisdom. It is independent, stealthy, and profoundly connected to the mysteries of nature. Ix asks us to trust our gut, to honor the invisible forces, and to walk with the velvet power of the great cat.", "keywords": ["Magic", "Jaguar", "Intuition", "Earth", "Stealth"]}, "number": {"title": "The Wheel of Manifestation", "content": "The number 10 represents manifestation, responsibility, and the hands coming together (two hands = ten fingers). It signifies the agreement between two people or the community. 10 is the number where the intention takes its final form in the physical world before the cycle begins to dissolve back into spirit. It brings a sense of weight, solidity, and the requirement to own the results of one's creation.", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Community", "Agreement", "Form"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create a physical altar or a magic tool.", "Spend time in nature and listen to the earth.", "Trust your 'gut feeling' on a practical matter.", "Take responsibility for a situation you have created.", "Honor the earth by picking up trash or planting something."], "title": "Manifesting Earth Magic", "content": "10 Ix is a powerful day where magic becomes real. The manifesting energy of the 10 brings the subtle, high-frequency magic of the Jaguar down into the physical world. In the Kan trecena, this is the realization of our personal power as a tangible force. It is a day to take responsibility for your own magic. What are you creating with your thoughts and energy? Today supports the physical manifestation of spiritual work—healing, art, or the creation of sacred space. It is a day where the veil is thin, but the ground is solid. Walk with confidence and let your intuition guide your hands."}}	{"title": "The Earth Shaman", "content": "To be born on 10 Ix is to be a bridge between the mystical and the material. You are a practical magician. You possess the Jaguar's intuition and connection to the invisible realms, but you also have the 10's ability to build, organize, and manifest in the real world. You are not a mystic who lives in a cave; you are a mystic who runs a business, heals a community, or protects a forest. You have a powerful presence that commands respect without saying a word.\\n\\nYour life path is one of using your spiritual gifts to create tangible change. You are deeply connected to the earth and likely have a talent for healing, gardening, or working with natural materials. You are a natural leader in spiritual communities. You understand the 'technology' of the sacred—how to use ritual and intention to produce results. You are independent and fierce, yet deeply responsible.\\n\\nYour challenge is to use your power wisely. The combination of high magic and high manifestation ability means your thoughts become things very quickly. You must be disciplined with your mind and your energy. You may also struggle with feeling misunderstood by the mundane world. Your lesson is to integrate your two halves. When you bring your magic into the marketplace with integrity, you heal the split between spirit and matter for everyone around you."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#93c5a5", "primary": "#111c1a", "secondary": "#455044"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.811557	2026-04-25 14:38:01.315877
57	5	5	5	Tz'ikin					{"nawal": {"title": "The Visionary Bird", "content": "Tz'ikin is the Nawal of the Bird, the Eagle, and the Condor. It represents vision, freedom, and the ability to rise above the mundane to see the big picture. Tz'ikin is the energy of prosperity and abundance, reminding us that spiritual vision attracts material resources. It governs the eyes and the ability to 'see' opportunities. In human experience, Tz'ikin manifests as optimism, sociability, and a drive for success. It is the intermediary between Earth and Sky, carrying our prayers up and bringing blessings down. When aligned, Tz'ikin brings financial flow, good luck, and a liberated perspective; when misaligned, it can lead to greed, superficiality, or losing touch with the details. It is the wings that lift us toward the sun.", "keywords": ["Vision", "Prosperity", "Opportunity", "Freedom", "Abundance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Action", "content": "The number Five represents the center point of the first wave of creation. It is the energy of the hand (five fingers) and the power to grasp, work, and manipulate reality. In Mayan cosmology, Five is the force of 'doing'; it breaks the static stability of Four and puts it into motion through effort. Experientially, this energy feels like a surge of willpower and a drive to get things done. It is the number of work, discipline, and the application of energy. The shadow of Five can be forcing things or working without a break, but its light is the satisfaction of a job well done. Today, the universe asks for your sweat equity.", "keywords": ["Action", "Discipline", "Work", "Willpower", "Effort"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Put effort into your finances or business plans today; the energy favors growth.", "Take one concrete action toward a big dream—make the call, send the email.", "Balance your high vision with necessary grunt work; don't skip the details.", "Network and communicate your vision to others; Tz'ikin loves connection.", "Look for opportunities where others see only work; your vision is sharp today."], "title": "Working for the Vision", "content": "When the industrious energy of Tone 5 combines with the visionary power of Tz'ikin, we get a day of 'Manifesting Prosperity.' This is not a day to just dream about success; it is a day to work for it. 5 Tz'ikin provides the practical discipline needed to ground high-flying ideas into profitable realities. The energy supports business ventures, networking, and applying effort toward your long-term goals. It feels like the moment an architect stops drawing and picks up a shovel. The bird sees the destination, and the hand does the work to get there. It is a powerful day for financial planning or for taking a concrete step toward a dream that has felt out of reach. The universe is willing to meet you halfway, but you must put in the effort. If you have been waiting for a sign to launch a product or pitch an idea, the energy of 5 Tz'ikin says: do the work, and the wind will catch your wings."}}	{"title": "The Visionary Builder", "content": "To be born on 5 Tz'ikin is to possess the soul of a prosperous builder. You are the 'Eagle with Hands'—someone who not only sees the mountain peak but has the stamina and discipline to climb it. You are naturally ambitious and likely have a talent for attracting resources, whether financial or social. People are drawn to your optimism and your ability to generate results. You don't just talk about your dreams; you build them brick by brick.\\n\\nYour life path is one of bridging the gap between potential and reality. You have a unique ability to operationalize vision, making you excellent in business, management, or any field that requires both strategy and execution. You are a hard worker, often driven by a desire for freedom and abundance for yourself and your loved ones. However, the intensity of the number 5 can sometimes make you a workaholic, causing you to lose the freedom that Tz'ikin cherishes. Your lesson is to remember that the work is a means to an end, not the end itself—fly high enough to remember why you are building."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#95d6d5", "primary": "#152223", "secondary": "#437075"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.769653	2026-04-25 13:46:57.74069
205	16	10	10	No'j	The light from the crack intensifies until the pod shatters completely. But what falls out is not a fruit. It is a complex, glowing geometric structure—a crystalline mind. It pulses with electric blue light, humming with a frequency that vibrates in your teeth.\n\nAs it touches the black soil, a shockwave of connection travels outward. The grass, the vines, and the trees all light up in a synchronized rhythm. You realize you haven't just grown a garden; you have grown an intelligence. The ecosystem wakes up and *looks* at you. The Veldt is no longer just alive; it is conscious. And it is waiting for your command.	The pod has shattered completely, but what has fallen out isn't a fruit—it’s an intelligence. A crystalline, geometric mind has touched the soil, and a shockwave of connection is traveling outward through your entire life. Suddenly, the plants, the people, and the projects you’ve been nurturing are all lighting up in a synchronized rhythm. Your world is no longer just alive; it is conscious, and it is looking back at you. This is the manifestation of your responsibility. You’ve built an ecosystem, and now it is waiting for your command.\n\nToday is the day the blueprint becomes the building. The ideas that were floating in your head are ready to be shaken into reality with a firm hand. It’s time to sign the contracts, make the agreements, and show the community the results of your hard work. Don't keep your brilliance to yourself; your thoughts gain power only when they are shared and manifested. You are the architect of a shared wisdom, the one who can bridge the gap between a wild theory and a working solution. The energy is competent, clear, and demanding of your best efforts. Take the director’s chair. The world you've been dreaming of is finally awake and ready to be led. What is your first command?	I manifest my wisdom through collaboration, sharing my light to solve and create.	Sit with your feet flat on the floor, feeling your 'plug' into the earth. Imagine your brain is a crystalline structure glowing with electric blue light. With every breath, feel this light extending down through your body and into the ground, connecting your personal intelligence to the vast, conscious network of the planet.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, visualize a complex geometric structure of light floating in front of you. As you breathe, see other spheres of light—the minds of your community—connecting to it. Feel the responsibility and the thrill of this shared intelligence waking up and looking back at you, ready for your command.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Crystal Mind of Wisdom", "content": "No'j is the nawal of the mind, knowledge, and the earth's brain. It represents the power of thought, logic, and the conversion of information into wisdom. No'j is the scholar, the scientist, and the planner. Associated with the element of earth and the color blue, it carries a cool, clear, and intellectual energy. It is the archetype of the sage who solves problems through clarity and innovation. In daily life, No'j manifests as study, brainstorming, and the spark of a good idea. Its shadow aspect can be overthinking, arrogance, or becoming trapped in mental loops. No'j teaches us that true intelligence is not just knowing facts, but knowing how to live in harmony with the cosmos.", "keywords": ["Wisdom", "Knowledge", "Thought", "Innovation", "Logic"]}, "number": {"title": "The Manifestation of Responsibility", "content": "Tone 10 is the energy of manifestation, collaboration, and the two hands coming together. It represents the realization of the intention set in Tone 1. In the cycle, 10 is where the work hits the physical plane in a concrete way. It is a number of community, agreement, and the solidity of creation. Experientially, Tone 10 feels grounded, productive, and social. It is a day to shake hands, sign contracts, and see the tangible results of your efforts. While it fosters achievement and connection, its shadow can be the heavy weight of responsibility or the pressure to perform for the group. It is the number of the builder who sees the walls rise.", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Collaboration", "Result", "Community"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Brainstorm with a team or partner to solve a complex problem.", "Write down your ideas to give them physical form.", "Commit to a course of study or a workshop.", "Use logic to organize a chaotic area of your life.", "Share a piece of wisdom or advice with someone who needs it."], "title": "Manifesting the Thought", "content": "The grounding power of Tone 10 combines with the intellectual clarity of No'j to create a day of 'Realized Wisdom.' 10 No'j is the energy of the Blueprint becoming the Building. Ideas that have been floating in the ether are ready to be brought down and made into something tangible and useful for the community. It is an exceptional day for collaborative problem-solving, strategic planning, or launching a project that requires smart design. The energy feels competent, clear, and purposeful. It suggests that our individual thoughts (No'j) gain power when they are shared and manifested with others (10). Today, do not keep your brilliance to yourself. Share your solutions, listen to feedback, and work together to manifest a better reality. The challenge is to avoid getting stuck in analysis paralysis; the 10 demands output, not just theory. The opportunity is to prove that a good idea can change the world."}}	{"title": "The Architect of Shared Wisdom", "content": "To be born on 10 No'j is to be a brilliant mind with a deep sense of social responsibility. You are the practical visionary, the one who doesn't just have great ideas but knows how to implement them for the benefit of the group. Tone 10 gives you a collaborative spirit and a drive to see tangible results, while No'j gifts you with a sharp intellect, intuition, and a love for knowledge. You are likely the 'brain' of your operation, the person others turn to when a solution is needed. You bridge the gap between the abstract world of thought and the concrete world of action.\\n\\nYour life path is one of turning wisdom into reality. You are not satisfied with knowledge for knowledge's sake; you want it to work. You may be drawn to fields like engineering, social planning, education, or technology—places where systems can be improved through intelligence. You have a natural authority when you speak, as people sense the depth of your understanding. You are also a collaborative learner, often finding that your best breakthroughs come when bouncing ideas off others.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 10 No'j soul is the burden of your own mind. You can be prone to worry, over-analysis, or feeling responsible for solving everyone's problems. The pressure to be the 'smart one' can be isolating. You may also struggle with perfectionism, delaying the release of your work until it is 'flawless.' Your growth comes from learning that wisdom is a living, evolving thing, not a static destination. When you learn to trust the collective mind and share the load, your intellect becomes a tool for connection rather than separation."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#8ed4c7", "primary": "#0f1c1b", "secondary": "#365752"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.855182	2026-04-25 14:38:01.325128
146	12	3	3	Kame	The living bridge drops you onto a platform of white bone-colored stone, suspended by chains rather than ropes. The air here is still and cold. The amber light of the canyon fades into a pale, ghostly grey.\n\nThis is the Ossuary of the Net.\n\nHanging from the chains are not sacks or bundles, but chrysalises. Thousands of them. They are grey and dusty, looking like dead leaves.\n\nKame is Death and Transformation. The number 3 is Movement. Today, the things in your net that are truly dead must be allowed to fall, so that what is transforming can move.\n\nYou walk among the chrysalises. You see one that represents an old identity—"The Victim," or "The One Who Always Fails." It looks dry and brittle.\n\nYou touch it. It crumbles instantly into dust. It was empty. The life had left it long ago; you were just carrying the shell.\n\nYou touch another. It crumbles.\n\nBut then you touch a third. It does not crumble. It shakes. Inside, something is moving. It is fighting to get out.\n\nYou realize that "Death" in the net is not just about loss; it is about the struggle of rebirth. You have been carrying these transforming parts of yourself, thinking they were burdens, but they were incubators.\n\nThe wind picks up, swirling the dust of the empty shells. It clears the air. The chrysalis that shook cracks open. A moth made of violet light crawls out, drying its wings.\n\nIt takes flight, pulling a thread of the net with it, weaving a new pattern in the air.\n\nYou watch it go. You understand that letting go of the dead shells makes room for the wings.	The energy is shifting fast today. Old structures are crumbling, and new wings are drying. The energy of 3 Kame is about active transformation. Don’t cling to the shell.\n\nIf something exits your life today, let it go. It was just a casing. If you feel a sudden urge to change your look, your route, or your mind—do it. The ancestors are breathing on your back, urging you to move. You are not who you were yesterday.	I release the empty shells of my past and welcome my transformation.	Imagine you are sweeping a dusty room. The dust is the old energy, the old thoughts. Sweep it out the door.\n\nNow, open the windows. Feel the fresh, cool breeze (the spirit) rushing in. The room is empty and clean, ready for new furniture. Feel the spaciousness.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Transformer", "content": "Kame is the energy of death, rebirth, and the ancestral realms. It represents the great transitions of life and the peace that follows necessary endings. Kame is the courage to face the unknown and the faith that something new will always be born from the ashes. It connects us to the wisdom of the ancients and offers protection during times of profound change. It is the owl seeing through the veil.", "keywords": ["Death", "Rebirth", "Transformation", "Ancestors", "Courage"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Movement", "content": "The number 3 introduces movement, flow, and the disruption of static balance. It is the energy of communication, expression, and the creative spark. 3 breaks the deadlock of duality to create a dynamic flow. It represents the pulse of life and the inevitable change that comes from interaction. In this trecena, 3 adds a restless, shifting quality to the net—shaking it to see what falls out and what sticks.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Expression", "Energy", "Flow", "Creativity"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in movement therapy or dance to release stored emotions.", "Write a letter to an ancestor or a past version of yourself.", "Allow yourself to change your mind or your direction today.", "Cleanse your energy field with smoke or water.", "Notice what is leaving your life and bid it a grateful farewell."], "title": "The Flow of Transformation", "content": "3 Kame brings a fluid, moving quality to the process of death and rebirth. Unlike a sudden stop, today's energy feels like a river carrying us through a transition. The 'net' of our lives is being washed in the waters of change. It is a day where endings happen quickly or where stagnant situations suddenly shift. You may find that things you were holding onto simply slip away, or that new inspirations arrive with the suddenness of a lightning bolt. The energy supports letting go through movement—crying, dancing, traveling, or speaking your truth. It is a day to trust the current of transformation, knowing it is taking you exactly where you need to go."}}	{"title": "The Agent of Change", "content": "To be born on 3 Kame is to be a soul constantly in motion, surfing the waves of transformation. You are uncomfortable with stagnation; your spirit demands growth, change, and evolution. You have a natural understanding of the cycles of life and death, and you are often the person who helps others navigate their own transitions. You are a bridge between the old and the new, possessing a creative adaptability that allows you to thrive in chaos.\\n\\nYour life path is one of continuous rebirth. You may reinvent yourself many times, shedding careers, homes, or identities like old clothes. You have a gift for communication, often able to articulate the difficult or taboo subjects surrounding death and change. You are deeply connected to the spirit world, and your intuition is active and dynamic.\\n\\nYour challenge is stability. The combination of 3 (movement) and Kame (death/change) can lead to a life that feels ungrounded or chaotic. You may struggle to finish what you start before the urge to transform hits again. Your lesson is to find the stillness within the storm. When you learn to anchor your transformative power in a deep sense of inner peace, you become a fearless guide, showing others that change is not something to fear, but a dance to be enjoyed."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c2adcc", "primary": "#0e1818", "secondary": "#40404c"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.826493	2026-04-25 13:46:57.909531
78	6	13	13	K'at	The road unrolls its final length, leading you to the very edge of the world-scroll. Beyond lies a shimmering void, and suspended within it is a net made of silver ink—the Altar of the Untangled Web. This is the ascension of 13 K'at. As you step into the shimmering fibers, you are met by the ancestors of the road, their forms made of swirling calligraphy. Together, you begin the sacred work of untangling. Every desire that turned into a trap, every attachment that became a knot, and every burden of 'stuff' you gathered is gently unpicked. You gather the pure wisdom of the thirteen days into your heart, and as the silver net begins to glow, the paper Bazaar dissolves entirely into spirit. You are no longer bound by the map; you have become the movement itself, ascending into the divine heart of the traveler.	The road has unrolled into an infinite tapestry today, and you are the one holding the golden thread that connects the Earth to the highest stars. You have reached the stage of transcendence, the culmination of the cycle where every lesson, every ink-stain, and every detour is being gathered into a single, magnificent whole. You may feel a thinning of the boundaries between worlds, a direct line of communication with the ancestors and guides who have been whispering directions from the margins of your maps. This is the day of the Weaver of the Final Knot, where you are invited to gather the absolute abundance of your journey into a shimmering silver net. This net is not used to entangle you, but to support your ascension; it is a web of wisdom that makes you light enough to float. You are being asked to tie the final knot of your intention and to release your 'net' into the universe as an offering of pure gratitude. By untangling the final traps of desire and the heavy baggage of the 'stuff' you thought defined you, you find the freedom to step off the map entirely. You are no longer just a traveler following a path; you have become the movement itself, a radiant presence ascending into the divine heart of the journey. Breathe out the last of the vellum world and step into the pure, unwritten light of your own transcendence.	I weave the threads of my experience into a masterpiece of completion, trusting the ancestors to guide my rebirth.	Imagine you are sitting in the center of a shimmering web made of silver light. Close your eyes and feel the threads of your experience connecting you to everything and everyone. Breathe deeply, and with every exhale, feel a different knot of desire or attachment gently untangle, leaving the net clean, open, and filled with stardust.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, enter the Weaver’s Grand Archive. Stand before the golden loom of light and gather the abundance of your trecena journey into the Altar of the Untangled Web. Watch as the ancestors, made of swirling calligraphy, help you unpick the final cords of the physical world. Feel the bazaar dissolve into spirit as you ascend, weightless, into the divine heart of the traveler.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Cosmic Net", "content": "K'at is the Nawal of the net, the spider web, and the gathering of abundance. It represents the principle of connection—how things are tied together. K'at is the energy that catches what we need (abundance) and what we don't need (entanglements). It governs the harvest, the storage of seeds, and the release of burdens. In human experience, K'at manifests as the ability to network, to organize, and to carry a load. It is the burning of the net to free the captive. When aligned, K'at brings fruitful connections and harvest; when misaligned, it can lead to feeling trapped or overwhelmed by stuff.", "keywords": ["Gathering", "Release", "Abundance", "Community", "Traps"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascension", "content": "The number Thirteen represents the completion of the cycle, the ascension to the next level, and the spirit world. In Mayan cosmology, Thirteen is the number of the ancestors and the highest vibration of time. It is the moment where the wave crashes onto the shore and recedes to become part of the ocean again. Experientially, this energy feels magical, heightened, and sometimes ungrounded. It is a day of 'déjà vu' and profound intuition. The shadow of Thirteen can be a disconnection from reality, but its light is the ultimate transformation and the preparation for a new beginning.", "keywords": ["Completion", "Ascension", "Ancestors", "Transformation", "Spirit"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a release ceremony; write down what you are letting go of and burn it.", "Declutter your physical space to mirror the spiritual clearing.", "Gather your 'seeds'—write down the key insights from this trecena.", "Connect with the spirit world to ask for freedom from old patterns.", "Celebrate the harvest; acknowledge the abundance in your life."], "title": "Ascended Harvest", "content": "The journey of the E' trecena concludes with 13 K'at, a day of 'Spiritual Unbinding.' We have traveled the path (E') and now we reach the destination: the gathering of the harvest. 13 K'at is the energy of the great cosmic net that catches the wisdom of the journey. It is a day to look back at the last 13 days and collect the lessons, the memories, and the growth. But it is also a day of release. K'at asks us to cut the cords of anything that is weighing us down before we ascend to the next cycle. The energy is high, transformative, and liberating. It is the moment the butterfly breaks free from the net. Offer your burdens to the spirit world (13); they are heavy, but the ancestors can carry them. Keep only the seeds of wisdom to plant in the next cycle. You are free."}}	{"title": "The Cosmic Gatherer", "content": "To be born on 13 K'at is to be a master of destiny's web. You are the 'Ascended Weaver'—a soul who understands the intricate connections between all things. You have a powerful, almost psychic ability to gather people, resources, and wisdom. You are likely a connector, a networker, or someone who brings abundance to your community. But your gift goes beyond just accumulating; with the energy of the 13, you also know how to release. You are a liberator, helping others untangle themselves from the traps of the material world.\\n\\nYour life path is one of spiritual sorting. You are here to learn—and teach—what is worth keeping and what must be let go. You have a foot in the spirit world, giving you a perspective that is vast and transformative. Your challenge is to ensure that you do not become entangled in your own net, carrying the burdens of the world on your shoulders. You are here to show us that true abundance is not about how much we hold, but how freely we flow."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d7b557", "primary": "#141614", "secondary": "#573a2a"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.779946	2026-04-25 14:38:01.304523
67	6	2	2	Aj	The unrolling road leads you to a cozy, paper-walled tea shop perched precisely where two different silk scrolls overlap. Inside, the Calligrapher guides move with a silent, mirrored grace, serving ink-tea in porcelain cups that reflect not your face, but the face of the person you are becoming. To pass through the shop, you must find the balance between your need for the road and your need for a sanctuary. As you sip the steaming, cedar-scented brew, the tea shop stabilizes, its bamboo-like cane walls glowing with a soft forest light. You realize that your 'home' is not a fixed place, but the integrity you carry between your dual desires.	The bazaar is building a house around you today, but the walls are made of your own promises. You might find yourself standing between two pillars of glowing green cane, realizing that your stability depends entirely on the balance of your own heart. This is a day for domestic diplomacy and the sacred work of harmonizing your "tribe". You may feel a sudden urge to organize your physical space or mend a lingering rift with a loved one. Do not view these as chores; view them as the "feet-work" of your soul's foundation. The universe is acting as a mirror, reflecting your choices back to you through the faces of those you encounter. If the world feels rigid, check if you have forgotten how to bend like the willow. Today’s energy asks you to be an upright leader who listens as much as they speak. By creating a sense of order in your inner home, you manifest a field of peace that calms the chaotic unrolling of the streets outside. Trust the duality of this moment. You are both the protector of the hearth and the explorer of the horizon, and today, those two roles finally decide to hold hands.	I honor the duality of my spirit, finding a sanctuary within myself that travels wherever I go.	Close your eyes and breathe into the center of your chest. Imagine two glowing pillars of green cane rising on either side of you, creating a doorway of perfect balance. As you inhale, feel the strength of the road; as you exhale, feel the warmth of the hearth. Find the point of stillness exactly in the middle, where your inner home and your outer path meet in harmony.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, visualize yourself sitting in the Tea Shop of Reflections. See a porcelain cup before you filled with steaming ink-tea. Look into the liquid and see the face of the traveler you are becoming. Watch as the bamboo walls of the shop glow with a soft forest light, sheltering you while the great silk scrolls of the world continue to unroll outside.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Pillar of Community", "content": "Aj is the Nawal of the home, the cane, and the spinal column. It represents the principle of authority, leadership, and the upright growth of the cornstalk. Aj is the energy that holds up the roof—strong yet flexible. It governs the home, the family, and the community, emphasizing harmony, ethics, and protection. In human experience, Aj manifests as the desire to build a safe container for life to flourish. It is the archetype of the benevolent leader or the wise parent. When aligned, Aj brings peace, stability, and a deep sense of belonging; when misaligned, it can lead to rigidity or authoritarianism.", "keywords": ["Home", "Leadership", "Harmony", "Community", "Integrity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "The number Two represents the principle of polarity: light and dark, male and female, self and other. It is the energy of relationship and the tension that exists between two points. In the Mayan cosmology, Two is not a point of separation, but of connection and reflection; it teaches us that we define ourselves through our interaction with the 'other.' Experientially, this energy brings choices into sharp focus and asks for balance. It is a day where partnerships are tested and strengthened. The shadow of Two is indecision or conflict, but its light is the profound harmony that arises when opposites dance together.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Reflection", "Connection", "Balance", "Choice"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Discuss household responsibilities with your partner or housemates.", "Balance your time between work (public) and home (private).", "Look for the middle ground in any family dispute.", "Strengthen your physical spine (Aj) through yoga or stretching.", "Recognize the 'other' as a necessary part of your own stability."], "title": "Balancing the Home", "content": "The duality of Tone 2 meets the stabilizing energy of Aj to create a day focused on 'Relationship within the Home.' 2 Aj asks us to look at the partnerships that support our domestic and community life. It is a day to balance the masculine and feminine energies within the household, or to find equilibrium between your public authority and your private self. The energy suggests that true strength comes from partnership—even the strongest pillar (Aj) needs a counterweight to hold the roof. You may find yourself navigating choices regarding family matters or community leadership. The lesson is that you don't have to carry the weight alone; share the burden with a partner. If there has been conflict in your personal space, today offers the mirror to see both sides and restore harmony through cooperation."}}	{"title": "The Diplomatic Pillar", "content": "To be born on 2 Aj is to be a peacemaker in the very center of the community. You are the 'Bridge of the Home'—someone who instinctively understands the dynamics between people and knows how to maintain harmony. You carry the authority of the Aj (the staff of power) but wield it with the gentleness and duality of the number 2. You are likely the person who mediates arguments in the family, seeing the validity of both sides. Your leadership style is partnership-oriented; you prefer to lead alongside others rather than from above.\\n\\nYour life path involves mastering the art of relationship within a structure. You deeply value stability and home, but you also need connection and interchange to feel alive. You may struggle at times with indecision, wanting to please everyone to keep the peace. Your challenge is to stand firm in your own integrity while remaining flexible enough to accommodate others. You are here to teach us that a home is built not just of walls, but of the relationships between the people inside them."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b4a468", "primary": "#14140f", "secondary": "#514228"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.775941	2026-04-25 14:38:01.293244
81	7	3	3	Aq'ab'al	You arrive at the lake before the sun does.\n\nThe world is made of outlines and guesses, shapes stacked in shades of deep blue and charcoal. The water is a dark mirror, holding the last of the night. For a moment, you wonder if you came too early, if there is anything here to see at all.\n\nThen the horizon inhales.\n\nA thin band of color appears where water meets sky, almost too subtle to trust. It is not full daylight, not yet, but it is no longer true night either. The in-between takes over, that fragile hour when everything is both and neither.\n\nYou sit on a flat stone near the shore and watch the light learn how to arrive. The first colors are small and shy, streaks of pale rose and soft gold slipping into the darkness. They do not erase the night. They braid themselves into it.\n\nThe lake responds in fragments. One part of the surface still reflects stars, sharp and cold. Another part catches the new light and turns it into liquid fire. Between them is a shifting seam where the two worlds touch. Nothing here is stable, yet nothing feels wrong.\n\nYou think of the places in your life that look like this seam: half old, half new. Habits loosening their grip but not yet gone. Stories you have outgrown but still repeat out of reflex. Possibilities that glow at the edge of your awareness but have not yet crossed into action.\n\nA bird calls from the trees behind you, tentative at first, then louder as if it has decided to trust the coming day. The sound ripples across the water, staining the silence with a note of certainty.\n\nYou do not stand up yet. You do not rush to move. Instead, you let yourself feel the wobble of this moment, the way your body leans toward change and shrinks from it at the same time. It is uncomfortable, but it is alive.\n\nAs the light grows, the seam between night and day becomes harder to see. The water looks simpler again, more familiar. But you remember what it looked like when everything was splitting and merging at once.\n\nWhen you finally rise, you know this much: you are allowed to be in transition. You are allowed to exist in the doorway without already knowing what waits on the other side.	You are not meant to have everything figured out today. You are meant to notice where the light is quietly starting to change.\n\nThis is a threshold kind of day, the kind where part of you is still holding hands with an old pattern while another part reaches toward something new. Instead of judging the tension, try listening to it. Where does your body lean when you imagine doing things differently? Where does it tighten when you think about staying the same?\n\nYou do not have to make a dramatic move. Start with one small action that aligns with the version of you that feels more awake, even if it is as simple as telling the truth, changing a tiny habit, or saying yes to a possibility you usually ignore. Let yourself be awkward. Dawn is messy before it is beautiful.	I honor the in-between spaces in my life, and I allow myself to take small, imperfect steps toward the light that feels true.	If possible, sit where you can see a natural horizon—a window, a skyline, even a blank wall you can imagine as the edge between earth and sky. Close your eyes and picture the moment just before dawn over a body of water.\n\nImagine the darkness holding you like a quiet room. Then, slowly, let a thin band of light appear along the horizon in your mind. With each inhale, allow that light to grow a little wider. With each exhale, soften any tension around not knowing what comes next.\n\nNow bring to mind one area of your life that feels “in between.” See it resting in that twilight band where night and day meet. You do not have to force a decision. Just acknowledge it kindly and say, either out loud or silently, “It is okay to be in transition. I am allowed to arrive slowly.”\n\nOffer a moment of gratitude for the ancient watchers of dawn and keepers of thresholds—those who listened to the turning of light and time long before you. Take one more steady breath, then open your eyes and carry that gentleness into whatever comes next.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Dawn of Possibility", "content": "Aq'ab'al is the Nawal of the dawn, the dusk, and the transition between light and dark. It represents the moment of awakening and the potential of a new day. Aq'ab'al is the energy of duality, polarity, and the hope that comes after the long night. In human experience, it manifests as optimism, youthfulness, and the ability to see the solution in the problem. It is the bridge between dream and reality, urging us to bring our inner visions out into the light. When aligned, it brings clarity and new opportunities; when misaligned, it can lead to hesitation.", "keywords": ["Dawn", "Transition", "Hope", "Awakening", "Potential"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Action", "content": "The number Three introduces movement, rhythm, and flow into the equation. If One is the point and Two is the line, Three is the triangle that creates stability through dynamism. In Mayan numerology, Three represents the pulse of life—the heartbeat, the breath, and the natural oscillation of energy. It is active, sometimes restless, and pushes things forward. It is the energy of 'doing' rather than just 'being.' The shadow of Three can be scattered energy, but its light is the joy of unimpeded expression.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Expression", "Rhythm", "Energy", "Instability"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Wake up early and move your body at sunrise.", "Launch a small pilot of your idea; don't wait for perfection.", "Change a habit that has been keeping you in the dark.", "Express your hope and optimism to others; it is contagious.", "Bridge the gap between your dreams and your daily actions."], "title": "The Movement of Dawn", "content": "The active rhythm of Tone 3 meets the awakening light of Aq'ab'al to create a day of 'Dynamic Optimism.' 3 Aq'ab'al is the energy of the sun breaking over the horizon—it is movement toward the light. After the dreaming of Imox and the wind of Iq', today we begin to see the shape of what we are creating. This is a day to take the first visible steps toward your vision. The energy is hopeful, youthful, and vibrant. It asks you to stop planning and start moving. 'Dawn the idea'—bring the concept out of the darkroom of your mind and expose it to the light of day. You may feel a restless urge to change your routine or try something new. Follow that impulse. The transition from night to day is in full swing, and you are the runner carrying the torch."}}	{"title": "The Harbinger of Action", "content": "To be born on 3 Aq'ab'al is to be a person of dawn-like energy who is always in motion. You are the 'Active Optimist'—someone who believes in the promise of a new day and works tirelessly to bring it about. You have a restless, youthful spirit that refuses to stagnate. You are likely an early adopter, a trendsetter, or someone who sees solutions where others see only problems. Your life is a constant transition from good to better.\\n\\nYour life path is one of bringing light through movement. You are not one to sit and contemplate for too long; you learn by doing. The number 3 gives you a rhythmic, expressive nature, while Aq'ab'al provides the vision. Your challenge is to ensure that you don't burn out by chasing every new sunrise. Learn to appreciate the dusk and the rest it offers. You are here to show us that hope is an active verb."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b07e72", "primary": "#0e1517", "secondary": "#3b363f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.783824	2026-04-25 13:46:57.774127
97	8	6	6	Kej	You descend the tower and the cloud-floor thickens, turning into a lush, rolling landscape of moss and fog. Tall, slender trees with silver bark rise into the mist. You are in the Forest of Whispers.\n\nThe wind here is gentle, rustling the leaves. But if you listen closely, the rustling sounds like voices. The trees are talking.\n\nSuddenly, a Stag steps onto the path. It is magnificent—tall, with antlers made of driftwood and wind. It looks at you with deep, liquid eyes.\n\nKej is the Deer, the keeper of the four directions, the spirit of the wilderness. The number 6 is Flow. Today, the struggle of the tower is over. You are in the flow of nature.\n\nThe Stag turns and walks. You follow. It moves with a grace that seems impossible, stepping over roots and stones without breaking its stride. It teaches you that the path doesn’t have to be a struggle. You can navigate the obstacles with elegance.\n\nThe Stag leads you to a clearing where the four winds meet. You feel the North wind (wisdom), the South wind (abundance), the East wind (beginnings), and the West wind (transformation). They swirl together, not fighting, but dancing.\n\nYou stand in the center. You feel your own body aligning with the four directions. You are not just a mind floating in the sky; you are a creature of the earth, connected to the cardinal points.\n\nThe wind blows through you, and you do not brace against it. You let it pass. You are hollow, like a reed, allowing the song of the universe to play through you.\n\nThe Stag bows its head and vanishes into the mist. You are left standing in the center of your own life, perfectly balanced, perfectly flowing.	Stop pushing so hard. The river is flowing; just get in the boat. The energy of 6 Kej is about grace, balance, and natural strength. You don’t need to force the door open; you just need to turn the handle.\n\nConnect with nature today. Even five minutes of fresh air will reset your nervous system. Your body knows the way forward better than your mind does right now. Follow your feet.	I move through my life with grace, strength, and natural balance.	Stand up. Face East. Breathe in new beginnings. Face South. Breathe in vitality. Face West. Breathe in release. Face North. Breathe in wisdom.\n\nFeel yourself anchored in the center of these four winds. You are the axis. You are safe. You are held.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Guardian of Nature", "content": "Kej is the Nawal of the Deer, the four cardinal directions, and the balance of nature. It represents strength, agility, and the connection between the physical and spiritual worlds. Kej is the guardian of the forest and the energy of leadership based on natural law. In human experience, Kej manifests as a love for the outdoors, a strong physical presence, and a need for autonomy. It is the shaman who walks between worlds. When aligned, Kej brings grounding and authority; when misaligned, it can lead to stubbornness.", "keywords": ["Nature", "Balance", "Strength", "Four Directions", "Leadership"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Harmony", "content": "The number Six represents the first point of true stability and flow in the cycle. It is the energy of the cube with a center, or the four directions plus the Above and Below. In Mayan cosmology, Six is the number of organic life and vital flow. Experientially, this energy feels gentle, rhythmic, and stabilizing. It is a day where things begin to click into place, and the struggle of the Five yields to a sustainable pace. The shadow of Six can be complacency, but its light is the grace of harmony. Today, the universe breathes easy.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Flow", "Stability", "Growth", "Rhythm"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Take a long walk in nature; let the forest heal you.", "Stand barefoot on the earth to ground your electromagnetic field.", "Observe the animals and plants; they are your teachers today.", "Practice 'gentle strength' in your interactions with others.", "Align your daily schedule with the sun and the natural light."], "title": "Natural Harmony", "content": "The stabilizing flow of Tone 6 meets the grounded nature of Kej to create a day of 'Forest Flow.' 6 Kej is the energy of the ecosystem in perfect balance. It is one of the best days for connecting with the natural world. The energy is strong yet gentle, like a deer moving silently through the trees. It supports finding your own rhythm and aligning it with the rhythm of the Earth. If you have been feeling out of sync, 6 Kej will gently pull you back into alignment. It is also a day for 'natural leadership'—leading by example and with grace rather than force. The four directions are stable, and the path is clear. Use this day to ground yourself, to breathe fresh air, and to remember that you are a biological being who needs rest, water, and connection to the soil."}}	{"title": "The Harmonious Guardian", "content": "To be born on 6 Kej is to be a steward of the earth and a pillar of strength. You are the 'Flowing Deer'—a soul who embodies the grace and power of the natural world. You have a calm, stabilizing presence that makes others feel safe. You are likely very connected to the environment and may feel a calling to protect it. You are a natural leader who prefers consensus and harmony over dominance. You move through life with a sure-footed rhythm, rarely losing your balance.\\n\\nYour life path is one of living in harmony with natural law. The number 6 gives you a love for family and community, which you integrate with the independence of the Deer. You are the person who brings the outdoors in, or who takes the family out. Your challenge is to ensure that your desire for harmony doesn't stop you from standing your ground when necessary. You are here to remind us that we are not separate from nature, but a vital part of its flow."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c6b78a", "primary": "#101917", "secondary": "#48483a"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#a18c68", "primary": "#1c2315", "secondary": "#564f32"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#a6a18c", "primary": "#5a6c58", "secondary": "#677f69"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#b5bebd", "primary": "#30362a", "secondary": "#6f7974"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.797273	2026-04-25 13:46:57.831673
249	20	2	2	Ajmaq	You climb higher. The air grows darker, turning a deep, velvety indigo. You have entered the Shadow of the Spire.\n\nThis is not a bad place; it is a quiet place. The wind dies down. You are walking along a ledge that overlooks a canyon filled with purple mist.\n\nAhead of you, blocking the path, sits a massive Owl. Its feathers are the color of smoke and ash. It blinks slowly, its large eyes reflecting the duality of the cosmos.\n\n2 is Duality. Ajmaq is the Ancestor, the Sinner, the Forgiver.\n\nThe Owl speaks, not with a voice, but inside your head. *To fly high, you must be light. What stones are you carrying?*\n\nYou think you are carrying nothing. But then you feel the weight in your boots. You reach down and find them filled with heavy, grey stones. You pull one out. It is labeled "Guilt." You pull out another. "Shame." Another. "Regret."\n\nYou realize you have been dragging these up the mountain, thinking they were part of you. They are not. They are just rocks.\n\nThe Owl watches. It does not judge. It offers the medicine of 2 Ajmaq: Reconciliation. To move forward, you must make peace with what is behind.\n\nYou hold the stone of Guilt over the ledge. It feels terrifying to let it go—it has been a companion for so long. But the Owl nods.\n\nYou drop it. It falls into the mist. You wait for the crash, but there is no sound. It simply vanishes.\n\nYou empty your boots. With every stone you drop, you feel a physical lift in your body, as if gravity is losing its hold on you.\n\nThe Owl spreads its wings and takes flight, silent as a thought. The path opens. You step forward, lighter, quieter, forgiven.	You cannot fly if you are weighed down by yesterday’s stones. The energy of 2 Ajmaq asks you to look at the guilt or regret you are carrying. Is it helping you? Or is it just heavy?\n\nForgiveness is not about condoning what happened; it’s about untying the rope that binds you to it. Be gentle with yourself today. You did the best you could with what you knew. Drop the rock. The sky is waiting.	I forgive myself and others, releasing the weight of the past to fly free.	Visualize yourself holding a heavy sack. It is full of your "mistakes." You are standing at the edge of a beautiful cliff.\n\nOpen the sack. Instead of rocks, butterflies fly out. Your mistakes have transformed into wisdom. Watch them fly away. Feel the lightness in your shoulders.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Owl of Forgiveness", "content": "Ajmaq is the nawal of the owl, the ancestors, and the sinner/saint. It represents the human condition in all its flaw and glory. Ajmaq is the energy of forgiveness, reconciliation, and the wisdom that comes from making mistakes. Associated with the element of earth and the spirit world, it carries a soft, solemn, and deeply compassionate energy. It is the archetype of the elder who looks back on life with understanding rather than judgment. In daily life, Ajmaq manifests as curiosity, the questioning of authority, and the healing of ancestral lines. Its shadow aspect can be guilt, shame, or the refusal to learn from the past. Ajmaq teaches us that our imperfections are the cracks where the light enters.", "keywords": ["Forgiveness", "Ancestors", "Wisdom", "Redemption", "Curiosity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "Tone 2 introduces the concept of the 'other.' It is the energy of polarity, partnership, and the dynamic tension between opposites. If Tone 1 is the solitary point, Tone 2 is the line connecting two points, creating relationship. This number governs the mysteries of duality: light and dark, masculine and feminine, inner and outer. Experientially, Tone 2 often brings choices or presents situations where you must weigh two sides of a coin. It is a day of reflection, where the world acts as a mirror to your internal state. While it can bring the challenge of indecision or conflict, its higher expression is balance and cooperation. It teaches that separation is an illusion and that opposing forces are actually complementary halves of a greater whole.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Reflection", "Connection", "Balance", "Choice"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Reach out to someone you have been estranged from.", "Practice 'Ho'oponopono' or another forgiveness ritual.", "Look at a conflict from the other person's perspective.", "Honor the duality of your ancestors (both their gifts and their flaws).", "Choose compassion over being 'right' in an argument."], "title": "The Choice to Forgive", "content": "When the duality of Tone 2 meets the redemptive energy of Ajmaq, we encounter a day of 'Relational Healing.' 2 Ajmaq is the decision to forgive. It highlights the dynamic between two people—the 'sinner' and the 'saint,' the hurt and the healer. Today, the mirror of relationship reflects our deepest wounds and our capacity for grace. It is a powerful day to reconcile differences, whether with a partner, a friend, or an ancestor. The energy asks us to see both sides of the story. Can we hold space for the imperfection in others? Can we accept it in ourselves? 2 Ajmaq supports bridging the gap between past and present, resolving old karmic debts through the simple act of understanding. The challenge is to avoid the trap of dualistic judgment (good/bad). The opportunity is to find the wholeness that exists when we embrace our shared humanity."}}	{"title": "The Partner of Redemption", "content": "To be born on 2 Ajmaq is to be a natural counselor and a bridge-builder in relationships. You possess a soul that understands the complexities of human nature. Tone 2 gives you a relational focus, while Ajmaq grants you deep empathy and the wisdom of the Owl. You are the person people turn to when they have made a mistake, knowing they will find understanding rather than judgment. You see the light and the dark in everyone, and you love them for the whole package.\\n\\nYour life path is one of reconciliation. You are here to heal rifts—between individuals, within families, or even within communities. You have a talent for diplomacy, able to navigate sensitive emotional terrain with grace. You may be drawn to psychology, mediation, or history, seeking to understand the roots of human behavior. You are a loyal partner, often helping your loved ones to process their past and find peace.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 2 Ajmaq soul is boundaries. You may become the 'sin-eater' for your relationships, absorbing the guilt or shame of others until it weighs you down. You might struggle with indecision, seeing so many sides to a story that you cannot take a stand. There is a risk of staying in toxic relationships because you believe you can 'heal' them. Your lesson is to remember that forgiveness does not mean lack of consequences. When you balance your compassion with self-respect, you become a true agent of healing."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a690b8", "primary": "#0d0f12", "secondary": "#3e3845"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#c1c1c1", "primary": "#7d7d7c", "secondary": "#a2a2a2"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#e5dded", "primary": "#9a8fad", "secondary": "#c1b7cf"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#6c6787", "primary": "#21212f", "secondary": "#46465d"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.881665	2026-04-25 13:46:58.078226
85	7	7	7	Kej	You take the path more slowly today, not out of hesitation but out of awareness. Every step feels deliberate, as if the ground itself is teaching you something about balance.\n\nWhen you reach the lake, the world is quiet — not the heavy quiet from earlier days, but a clear, resonant kind of stillness. The water reflects the sky so perfectly that the treeline seems to float upside down.\n\nBut something is different.\n\nAcross the surface of the lake, thin lines of light stretch between distant points like invisible bridges. They shift as you move, rearranging themselves in patterns you cannot quite decipher — constellations drawn too close to the ground.\n\nYou realize they are not random. They are pathways.\n\nSome lead toward the center of the lake, some toward the far shore, some upward into the reflection of the sky. The lines pulse with a faint, steady rhythm, neither beckoning nor warning — just showing what is possible from a higher vantage.\n\nA presence stirs at the edge of your awareness, and you turn to see the faint form of a great antlered figure standing among the trees. Not an animal, not exactly. More like a guardian shaped from bark and mist and memory. Its antlers branch like living maps, each tine pointing to a different direction your life could take.\n\nIt does not move toward you. It doesn’t need to.\n\nInstead, you feel yourself rise — not physically, but inwardly, like your perception has climbed a tree and now sees the forest instead of the ground. Everything widens. Everything sharpens. All the threads you have touched in the last few days weave themselves into something coherent.\n\nYou look back at the lake and the light-paths adjust again, revealing connections you hadn’t noticed: how your choices intersect, how your past supports your present, how your desires form patterns even when you pretend they don’t.\n\nYou lower yourself to sit at the edge of the water, letting the clarity settle into your bones. The antlered figure watches, silent and patient. You understand: this is a day not for movement, but for seeing.\n\nBefore you leave, the paths of light fade softly back into the water, but you carry their shape within you.\n\nFor the first time in a while, the way forward feels both mysterious and deeply, quietly right.	Your vision expands today. Not in a dramatic, lightning-strike way, but in a soft widening — the kind that lets you see both where you stand and where you are heading with more honesty.\n\nThis is a day for stillness, clarity, and quiet insight. Your intuition feels sharper, your senses more attuned. Patterns you’ve missed may emerge, or you may finally understand why certain experiences unfolded the way they did.\n\nYou don’t have to act on anything yet. Just pay attention. Listen to the subtle guidance of your own inner compass. Your path is becoming clearer.	I trust the quiet clarity that rises within me, and I allow my path to reveal itself with ease and truth.	Find a comfortable seated position. Close your eyes and imagine yourself standing at the top of a gentle hill above a wide, open landscape. The air is calm. The sky is clear.\n\nIn your mind’s eye, see lines of light stretching across this landscape — pathways, connections, choices. Some glow strongly. Others are faint. There is no right or wrong path, only different expressions of who you are becoming.\n\nAs you breathe slowly, let one path brighten slightly. Follow it with your awareness, not to its end, but just far enough to feel its energy. What does it evoke? Peace? Curiosity? Strength? Relief?\n\nWhen you return to center, offer gratitude to the great teachers of stability, direction, and nature. Then open your eyes gently, carrying that clarity into your day.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Guardian of Nature", "content": "Kej is the Nawal of the Deer, the four cardinal directions, and the balance of nature. It represents strength, agility, and the connection between the physical and spiritual worlds. Kej is the guardian of the forest and the energy of leadership based on natural law. In human experience, Kej manifests as a love for the outdoors, a strong physical presence, and a need for autonomy. It is the shaman who walks between worlds. When aligned, Kej brings grounding and authority; when misaligned, it can lead to stubbornness or being dominating.", "keywords": ["Nature", "Balance", "Strength", "Four Directions", "Leadership"]}, "number": {"title": "The Summit of Reflection", "content": "The number Seven represents the midpoint of the trecena, the top of the pyramid, and the power of mystic vision. In Mayan cosmology, Seven is a number of great potential but also of suspension; it is the moment where we can look back at the climb (1-6) and forward to the descent (8-13). Experientially, this energy feels like a pause in the action—a time to assess, reflect, and gain perspective. It is neither a beginning nor an end, but a bridge. The shadow of Seven can be indecision, but its light is the clarity that comes from seeing the whole picture.", "keywords": ["Reflection", "Midpoint", "Vision", "Insight", "Clarity"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Spend time in the forest or a park; nature is your teacher today.", "Face the four directions and offer gratitude to each.", "Reflect on the balance in your life (work/rest, giving/receiving).", "Stand firm in your boundaries; the Deer is gentle but strong.", "Seek a higher perspective on a grounded problem."], "title": "Balancing the World", "content": "The reflective power of Tone 7 meets the grounding nature of Kej to create a day of 'Natural Equilibrium.' 7 Kej represents standing in the exact center of the four directions. It is the perfect day to orient yourself—physically, spiritually, and emotionally. The energy asks you to go into nature (Kej) to find your perspective (7). Stand with your feet on the earth and look at where you have come from and where you are going. This is a day of balance. If you have been too focused on work, go to the woods. If you have been too spiritual, eat a hearty meal. 7 Kej reminds us that we are part of a larger ecosystem. The Deer is vigilant and calm on the hilltop, surveying the landscape. Adopt this stance today. It is a powerful time for rituals that honor the Earth and for finding your own center of gravity."}}	{"title": "The Nature Mystic", "content": "To be born on 7 Kej is to be a guardian of the natural order. You are the 'Reflective Ranger'—a soul who feels most at home in the wilderness and who possesses an innate understanding of the Earth's rhythms. You stand at the center of the compass (7), able to see all directions clearly. You are likely a natural leader, but one who leads with quiet strength and dignity rather than force. People respect you because you are grounded and fair.\\n\\nYour life path is one of maintaining balance. You are the bridge between the civilized world and the wild, often serving as an advocate for nature or a guide for others seeking their path. The number 7 gives you a mystical, introspective quality; you don't just walk in the woods, you commune with them. Your challenge is to not become too isolated in your strength or too critical of the imbalance you see in the world. You are here to anchor the light of the spirit into the soil of the earth."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#cfc594", "primary": "#1e2118", "secondary": "#695c3f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.786719	2026-04-25 13:46:57.779509
76	6	11	11	Iq'	The Manifestation of the plaza gives way to a structure that defies gravity—the Tower of the Silent Breath. Built from thousands of hollow, white quills, the tower hums with a haunting melody as the winds of 11 Iq' pass through it. To find liberation, you must climb. At the summit, you are asked to exhale a single 'stagnant' story—a map you've clung to out of fear—into the indigo sky. As the wind carries the ink-clouds away, your path becomes unpredictable and whimsically light. The dissolution of your rigid plans is not a loss; it is the freedom to breathe with the spirit of the road itself.	The cosmos is exhaling today, and it’s a breath that can move mountains and unbind the most stubborn knots of the soul. You might feel a sharp, clean inspiration striking like lightning behind your ribs, clearing the air for a conversation or a release you’ve avoided for far too long. This is the day of the sacred Gale, where the energy of dissolution meets the divine messenger of the wind. You are being invited to stand in the center of your own life and let the high-frequency vibrations of change strip away the maps and blueprints that have become cages. There is a sacred turbulence in the atmosphere that supports the radical release of old baggage, turning your stale secrets into harmless gray ash that the wind carries into the indigo void. Do not mistake this chaos for destruction; it is the most profound form of purification available to a traveler. By letting go of the stories that have stagnated in your throat, you allow a fresh perspective to rush in—one that is as bright, unpredictable, and wide as the sky itself. You are being unpinned from the board of your own expectations, granted the weightlessness required to meander with the whimsy of a stray cloud. Trust the power of your own exhale today. When you stop holding your breath, you find that the universe has been waiting to fill your lungs with the scent of ozone and absolute freedom.	I release my need for a fixed destination, allowing the breath of the spirit to unbind my potential.	Sit comfortably and focus on your breath. As you inhale, feel the air as a fresh, unpredictable wind. As you exhale, imagine you are blowing away a stack of old, dusty papers that represent stale stories of who you are. Feel the space that opens up in your chest when you no longer have to hold onto a fixed destination.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, climb the Tower of the Silent Breath, built of thousands of humming white quills. Stand at the very peak as the Gale of Unbinding roars around you. Hold out an unwritten map and let the wind tear it from your hands. Watch as it dissolves into the indigo clouds, leaving you weightless and free to meander wherever the spirit of the wind leads.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Breath of Spirit", "content": "Iq' is the Nawal of the wind, the breath, and communication. It represents the vital spirit that animates all living things. Iq' is the energy of inspiration, ideas, and the power of the spoken word. It clears the air and brings change. In human experience, Iq' manifests as intellect, agility, and a need for freedom. It is the voice that speaks the truth. When aligned, Iq' brings clarity, effective communication, and a fresh perspective; when misaligned, it can lead to anger or fickleness. It is the wind that can fill the sails or break the branches.", "keywords": ["Wind", "Breath", "Communication", "Inspiration", "Change"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Change", "content": "The number Eleven represents dissonance, resolution through change, and the stripping away of the non-essential. In Mayan cosmology, Eleven is a high-frequency energy that shakes the foundation to test its strength. It is not necessarily negative, but it is turbulent. Experientially, this energy feels like a strong wind or a sudden shift in plans. It breaks the static perfection of Ten to allow for higher growth. The shadow of Eleven can be chaos, but its light is liberation and the clearing of the path. Today, the universe unbinds the knots.", "keywords": ["Change", "Liberation", "Dissonance", "Clearing", "Transformation"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Expect changes to your schedule and adapt quickly.", "Watch your words; communication is powerful and volatile today.", "Let go of an old idea or belief that no longer serves you.", "Go outside and feel the wind; let it cleanse your aura.", "Practice deep breathing to calm the nervous system."], "title": "The Winds of Change", "content": "The turbulent energy of Tone 11 combines with the windy nature of Iq' to create a day of 'Radical Shift.' 11 Iq' is the hurricane—powerful, unpredictable, and capable of changing the landscape in an instant. This energy comes to sweep away everything that is stagnant or false. It is a day of high-velocity communication; words may be spoken that cannot be taken back, but they needed to be said. The mind is racing, ideas are flying, and plans may change at the last minute. The advice is to be flexible. Like a tree in a storm, if you are rigid, you will break; if you bend, you will survive and grow stronger. This is a day of liberation. Let the wind blow through your life and carry away the debris. Expect the unexpected, and trust that the chaos is rearranging things for your highest good."}}	{"title": "The Stormy Liberator", "content": "To be born on 11 Iq' is to be a force of nature. You are the 'Wind of Change'—a soul who brings fresh air, new ideas, and sometimes necessary chaos wherever you go. You have a quick, brilliant mind and a tongue that can be sharp or inspiring, depending on the day. You are not here to follow the rules; you are here to rewrite them. Your life is likely a series of transformations, as you constantly shed old skins and seek new freedoms.\\n\\nYour life path is one of liberation. You challenge the status quo and push others to think differently. The number 11 gives you a high-voltage energy that can be intense for those around you, but it is this very intensity that breaks through stagnation. Your challenge is to master your own volatility—to learn to direct the wind rather than being blown about by it. When you are centered, you are a powerful communicator who can inspire movements and change minds. You are the breath of spirit in a stagnant world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#ccc2bd", "primary": "#141616", "secondary": "#4f4b4f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.779278	2026-04-25 14:38:01.302863
150	12	7	7	Tz'i'	The river of abundance ends at a high, suspended bridge made of white rope. It is narrow and sways in the wind. Standing in the middle of the bridge is a white Dog.\n\nThis is the Bridge of Fidelity.\n\n7 is the Reflection, the Mystic Center. Tz’i’ is the Dog, the Guide, the Law. Today, at the top of the trecena pyramid, you are asked to reflect on your loyalties.\n\nYou walk out onto the bridge. The Dog watches you. Its eyes are mirrors. You look into them and see your own reflection.\n\nThe Dog asks (without words): "To what are you tethered?"\n\nYou look at the net of your life. You see the connections you have kept. Are you loyal to your past, or your future? Are you loyal to your fear, or your potential? Are you loyal to people who drain you, or people who feed you?\n\nThe net of K’at gathers everything, but Tz’i’ sorts it with the law of love.\n\nYou realize that true loyalty is not blind adherence to an old promise. It is fidelity to the truth. If a connection is false, keeping it is a betrayal of yourself.\n\nYou stand on the bridge and make a choice. You renew your vows to your own soul. You promise to be the faithful companion to yourself first.\n\nThe Dog wags its tail. It turns and trots across the bridge, leading you to the other side. The ropes feel steadier now. You are walking in integrity.	Look in the mirror today. Who looks back? The energy of 7 Tz’i’ is a check-in point. It asks you to look at your loyalties. Are you staying in a situation out of habit or out of love?\n\nYou don’t have to be loyal to your suffering. You don’t have to be loyal to a version of you that doesn’t exist anymore. Be faithful to the person you are becoming. That is the highest law.	I am loyal to my truth and walk my path with integrity and love.	Visualize a cord of light connecting your heart to the things you love. See the cords that are bright and healthy. See the cords that are dark and frayed.\n\nImagine the dark cords dissolving. Imagine the bright cords glowing stronger. You are connected to what matters.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Guide of Law", "content": "Tz'i' is the energy of spiritual law, justice, and authority. It is the dog, the loyal companion, and the guide who leads the soul. Tz'i' represents fidelity, accuracy, and the instinct for truth. It points toward integrity and unconditional love. It asks us to be true to ourselves and to the laws of the universe.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Loyalty", "Truth", "Authority", "Guidance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Summit of Reflection", "content": "The number 7 represents the top of the pyramid, the midpoint of the cycle. It is a place of mystical power, equilibrium, and the ability to see both the past and future. 7 is a number of channeling and high magic. In the K'at trecena, 7 gives us a bird's eye view of the net we are weaving. It allows us to see the pattern of our connections and to align them with a higher purpose.", "keywords": ["Insight", "Clarity", "Reflection", "Mysticism", "Midpoint"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Meditate on your core values; are you living them?", "Seek counsel or guidance from a trusted mentor.", "Make a fair decision that benefits the whole, not just the self.", "Trust your intuition to sniff out dishonesty or misalignment.", "Commit to a path of integrity, regardless of the cost."], "title": "The Apex of Integrity", "content": "7 Tz'i' is a day of high spiritual authority and clear vision. Standing at the top of the pyramid, we are asked to judge our own lives with the eyes of unconditional love. The gathering theme of K'at is refined here: are we gathering truth? Are our connections aligned with divine law? It is a powerful day for legal matters, for making binding agreements, and for seeking justice. The energy is not harsh; it is elevated. We can see the 'right' path clearly. It is a day to align your personal will with the will of the cosmos, trusting that loyalty to the truth will always lead to abundance."}}	{"title": "The Mystic Judge", "content": "To be born on 7 Tz'i' is to carry the energy of a spiritual magistrate. You possess a profound sense of justice and a direct line to higher wisdom. You are the person who can see both sides of every story, yet you never lose sight of the ultimate truth. You are a natural channel for guidance, often knowing the right thing to do without knowing how you know. You are deeply loyal, protective, and committed to the concept of unconditional love.\\n\\nYour life path is one of seeking and upholding the truth. You may find yourself in roles of authority, mediation, or spiritual leadership. You have a mystic's heart and a lawyer's mind. You are here to help correct the imbalances in the world, not through force, but through the clarity of your vision. You are a faithful companion to those who earn your trust.\\n\\nYour challenge is the burden of knowing. Seeing the truth so clearly can sometimes be isolating or lead to cynicism when the world falls short of your standards. You may also struggle with indecision, as the 7 energy sees all possibilities. Your lesson is to act on your truth with compassion. When you marry your high standards with a forgiving heart, you become a beacon of divine justice, guiding others back to their own integrity."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c1c5c2", "primary": "#111a1b", "secondary": "#464c51"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.829324	2026-04-25 13:46:57.914189
162	13	6	6	K'at	By the time the caravan reaches solid ground again, the crossing has changed more than anyone says aloud. Water has a way of deciding what is worth carrying. A few packs are lighter now, though no one speaks of what was lost. A broken strap dangles from one wagon. A rolled blanket is missing from another. One traveler walks without the bundle they had kept pressed to their chest for days, and though their hands seem uncertain without it, their shoulders have lowered, as if some private argument has ended.\n\nThe caravan pauses in a grove of low trees where the rain falls in finer threads. There, people begin to sort through what remains. Wet cloth is wrung out and hung where branches will hold it. Supplies are counted. Food is redistributed. The work is practical, but beneath it runs something quieter and deeper. This is not merely an inventory of objects. It is a reckoning.\n\nYou kneel beside your own belongings and find that the act of touching them has changed. What seemed necessary yesterday now feels heavy. What once gave comfort now asks for energy you no longer want to spend. A traveler beside you unwraps a small packet of keepsakes that the water nearly claimed. They turn each thing over in their hands before setting half of it aside without ceremony. Another cuts loose a tangle of cord that had snagged beneath a wagon and holds it for a moment before leaving it in the mud.\n\nThe one who has walked beside the covered wagon moves among the group with quiet steadiness, helping where help is needed, saying little. Their presence makes the work feel less like loss and more like refinement. You begin to understand that release is not the opposite of care. Sometimes it is care in its clearest form.\n\nAs the caravan prepares to move again, the difference is subtle but unmistakable. The wagons roll more easily. The steps of the travelers fall into a smoother rhythm. Even the rain seems less like an obstacle and more like part of the process, rinsing away whatever no longer belongs.\n\nWhen you rise to continue, you carry less than before. The absence is strange at first, but as the caravan resumes its forward motion, you realize that what remains in your hands fits more honestly there.	There is a quiet sorting happening today, and it may not be entirely comfortable.\n\nAfter crossing a threshold, there is always a moment where you look around and realize you cannot carry everything forward. Not because you are lacking strength, but because something within you has changed its priorities. What once felt necessary may now feel heavy. What once gave you identity may now feel like resistance.\n\nThis is not loss.\n\nThis is refinement.\n\nYou may feel yourself evaluating things in a new way—habits, relationships, patterns of thinking, even parts of your own self-image. There may be a temptation to hold onto something simply because it has been with you for a long time. But longevity is not the same as alignment.\n\nAsk yourself gently: Does this still belong to who I am becoming?\n\nIf the answer is unclear, you don't need to force it. Just notice the weight. Your body is often more honest than your mind in these moments. What feels draining? What feels like effort without return? What feels like it's asking more of you than it gives?\n\nThere is wisdom in letting go before you are forced to.\n\nNot everything needs to be carried to the end of the journey.\n\nAnd what remains, when chosen consciously, becomes lighter. More true. More capable of moving forward with you.\n\nYou are not losing anything essential.\n\nYou are making space for what actually is.	I release what no longer supports me and carry forward what is true.	Close your eyes and take a deep breath in.\nAs you exhale, imagine releasing something you no longer need to carry.\nIt could be tension, a thought, or a feeling.\nYou don't need to force it—just allow it to drift away.\nRepeat this with each breath.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine strands of energy attached to you—some bright, some heavy. As rain begins to fall, the heavier strands dissolve and wash away, while the brighter ones remain and grow stronger. You realize you don't have to decide what stays and what goes—the storm knows.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Cosmic Net", "content": "K'at is the energy of the net, the harvest, and the gathering. It represents the principle of entanglement—both the abundance we gather and the traps that hold us back. K'at is the lizard and the spider, asking us to look at what we are carrying. It governs community, abundance, and the clearing of debts.", "keywords": ["Gathering", "Net", "Abundance", "Release", "Community"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Stability", "content": "The number 6 represents ultimate stability, flow, and vitality. It brings balance to the work of the 5, facilitating responsiveness and organic growth. It is associated with the heart of the sky and earth in alignment. In the Kawoq trecena, 6 brings a harmonious flow to the process of gathering resources for the new life.", "keywords": ["Flow", "Harmony", "Stability", "Vitality", "Balance"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Organize your physical space or finances with a sense of flow.", "Connect with a friend you haven't seen in a while.", "Donate items you no longer need; keep the flow moving.", "Visualize your life as a net catching only golden opportunities.", "Release a mental burden; drop it from your net."], "title": "The Flow of Gathering", "content": "6 K'at offers a day of fluid abundance and sorting. The stability of the 6 smooths out the tangles of K'at. Today, the storm has passed, and we are walking the beach to see what the tide has brought in. It is a day to gather what is useful and to release what is debris. The energy supports organization that feels organic rather than rigid. It is a time to connect with your community, to share resources, and to untangle any knots in your relationships with grace. The net is cast, and it comes back full, but the load is balanced and easy to carry."}}	{"title": "The Harmonious Connector", "content": "To be born on 6 K'at is to be a master of social and energetic weaving. You possess a natural charm and a gift for bringing people together. You are the spider who weaves a web of community that supports everyone. You are abundant by nature, often attracting resources and opportunities with ease. You are a stabilizer, someone who can walk into a chaotic room and organize it simply by your presence.\\n\\nYour life path is one of gathering and sharing. You are a collector—of friends, of experiences, of wisdom. However, unlike the hoarder, you understand that the net must remain open for the flow to continue. You are generous and likely the 'glue' that holds your family or friend group together.\\n\\nYour challenge is entanglement. You can become so connected that you feel trapped by the needs of others or by your own possessions. You may struggle to say no, fearing you will break the harmony. Your lesson is discernment. When you learn to fill your net only with what truly nourishes your soul, you become a conduit for infinite abundance, feeding the world without weighing yourself down."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d4a873", "primary": "#111210", "secondary": "#4f3d30"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.835922	2026-04-25 14:25:01.116962
135	11	5	5	Toj	The upward path is suddenly choked by the Fire-Vine Thicket—a dense, tangled wall of grey, thorny branches that feel cold and drained of life. To move higher, you cannot simply climb; you must work. You feel the heat of the Spire’s initiation gathering in your palms, a warm glow of empowerment that pulses in time with your heart. This is the labor of reciprocity. You begin to pull at the thorns, your hands glowing with a soft ember-light as you channel your internal fire to clear the obstruction. Each vine you remove is a physical prayer, a 'sacred sweat' offered to the Spire in exchange for the vitality it has granted you.\n\nAs you work, steam rises from the damp bark where your fingers touch the wood. The effort is intense, but it feels right—a necessary payment of energy to maintain the balance of the climb. You are not just a consumer of the Spire’s magic; you are a participant in its upkeep. The thorns do not tear your skin; they seem to yield to the sincerity of your effort. By the time the path is clear, you are breathing heavily, your muscles humming with a new kind of strength. You have paid your spiritual debt through honest toil, and the Spire responds by opening a wider, more luminous way forward, the steam of your labor lingering behind you like an incense offering.	The path ahead is thick with grey, thorny vines today, and the only way to the next level is with your sleeves rolled up. You can feel a physical fire gathering in your palms—not a flame that burns your skin, but a heat that empowers your muscles. This is the day of reciprocity, where the universe asks you to physically enact your gratitude through effort. You have been fed by the magic of the climb, and now it is time to offer your labor in return. \n\nEvery obstacle you clear and every burden you help lift for another traveler is a physical prayer that restores balance to your world. Don’t resent the weight of the task or the friction of the thorns; the 'sacred sweat' of today is exactly what turns your raw potential into a lasting, tempered wisdom. You are clearing the way not just for yourself, but for those who follow your scent. \n\nAs you work, notice the steam rising from your hands where they touch the cold, grey wood. That is the evaporation of your old limitations. The harder you work today, the more space you create for a wider, more luminous way forward. By the time the sun sets, your hands will be glowing with the evidence of your service, and the path will be wide open.	I act with reciprocity and gratitude, paying for my wisdom with the strength of my hands.	Close your eyes and focus on the warmth in your palms. Imagine this heat as a tool for clearing the obstacles in your life, fueled by your own willpower and dedication. \n\nOptionally, see yourself in a clearing of thorny grey vines, your hands glowing with ember-light as you work to restore balance to the forest through your sacred effort.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Fire", "content": "Toj is the energy of offering, payment, and reciprocity. It is the sacred fire that transmutes matter into spirit. Toj represents the law of cause and effect (karma) and the necessity of giving back to maintain universal balance. It is the day to pay spiritual debts, to offer gratitude, and to sacrifice the ego for the greater good. Toj reminds us that nothing is free; everything requires an exchange of energy.", "keywords": ["Offering", "Payment", "Reciprocity", "Fire", "Gratitude"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Empowerment", "content": "The number 5 represents empowerment, work, and the human hand (five fingers). It is the energy of doing, gathering, and applying will to the structures created by the 4. 5 breaks the stability of the 4 to put things into motion through effort. It is the center point of the single digits, representing a gathering of resources and the intelligent application of energy. It is a number of work, investigation, and the practical implementation of ideas.", "keywords": ["Empowerment", "Work", "Effort", "Gathering", "Investigation"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform an act of service without expecting anything in return.", "Pay a financial debt or resolve an outstanding obligation.", "Make a physical offering to the fire or the earth.", "Work hard on a project; put your 'back' into it.", "Say 'thank you' more times than usual today."], "title": "The Work of Reciprocity", "content": "5 Toj is a powerful day of active payment and service. The empowerment of the 5 drives us to physically enact the offerings of Toj. In the Kan trecena, this is where we 'pay for' the wisdom and power we are gaining. We acknowledge that our evolution is not just for us; it serves the whole. Today asks for effort. It is a day to work hard, to help others, and to clear any karmic debts that might be weighing you down. The energy is warm and active. It feels good to give today, to sweat a little, and to know that you are restoring balance to your life through your own actions."}}	{"title": "The Keeper of the Flame", "content": "To be born on 5 Toj is to be a tireless worker for the spiritual and physical well-being of your community. You carry a deep sense of responsibility and a natural understanding of the law of reciprocity. You are the one who ensures that the 'bill is paid'—energetically and literally. You are generous, hardworking, and often find yourself in service roles. You have a fire within you that drives you to correct imbalances and to help those who are in debt or distress.\\n\\nYour life path is one of balancing the scales. You are a natural investigator and a fixer. You are not afraid of hard work; in fact, you thrive on it. You likely have a strong connection to the element of fire and to ceremonial practices. You understand that true power (Kan) requires sacrifice (Toj), and you live this truth daily.\\n\\nYour challenge is burnout. You can be so focused on paying debts (yours and others') that you forget to receive. You may also struggle with a sense of never doing enough. Your soul's lesson is to realize that you are also worthy of the offering. When you learn to receive with the same grace that you give, you become a sustainable source of warmth and light, a true firekeeper who warms the world without consuming yourself."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c58b6f", "primary": "#0e100e", "secondary": "#40332d"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.809745	2026-04-25 14:38:01.311852
26	2	13	13	Q'anil					{"nawal": {"title": "The Golden Seed", "content": "Q'anil is the nawal of the seed, the rabbit, and the star. It represents the spark of life, fertility, and the potential for organic growth. Q'anil is the energy of the planter and the harvester. It is a joyful, abundant energy that governs biological life, agriculture, and artistic creation. Q'anil is the promise that 'what you plant, you will harvest.' In its shadow, Q'anil can manifest as impatience, problems with fertility/creativity, or a scattering of seeds on barren ground. Its highest expression is the blooming garden—the realization of potential into beautiful, living form.", "keywords": ["Seed", "Harvest", "Fertility", "Star", "Creation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Light of Ascension", "content": "Thirteen is the number of completion, ascension, and the spirit world. It is the final step in the trecena cycle, representing the return to the source but at a higher level of spiral. Thirteen is the number of the ancestors and the 'invisible army' of support. Experientially, a Thirteen day feels mystical, thin-veiled, and sometimes surreal. It is a day of wrapping up, letting go, and preparing for the new seed (which comes tomorrow). The shadow of Thirteen can be ungroundedness or a feeling of being 'checked out' of reality. It asks us to celebrate the journey and harvest the wisdom.", "keywords": ["Completion", "Ascension", "Spirit", "Ancestors", "Renewal"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Celebrate! Do something purely for joy—eat a good meal, dance, or play.", "Plant a physical seed or flower as a symbol of your intention for the next cycle.", "Write a list of 'harvests' (wins/lessons) from the last 13 days.", "Offer a toast to your ancestors, thanking them for guiding you through the Ajmaq work.", "Visualize your heart as a golden star radiating light in all directions."], "title": "The Harvest of Spirit", "content": "We reach the end of the Ajmaq trecena with 13 Q'anil—the 'Ascended Seed' or the 'Spiritual Harvest.' This is a beautiful, light-filled conclusion. The journey of forgiveness and reconciliation (Ajmaq) has led us here: to a place where we can plant a new, golden seed for the future. The Thirteen elevates the Q'anil energy, suggesting that what we are harvesting today is not just material, but spiritual abundance. It is a day of celebration, gratitude, and looking forward. The heavy lifting of the trecena is done. You may feel a sense of lightness, a 'cosmic wink,' or a deep appreciation for the beauty of life. Any seeds planted today (intentions, projects, relationships) are blessed with the highest frequency of the calendar. They carry the wisdom of the ancestors and the spark of the star. The challenge is simply to receive it. Do not rush to the next thing yet; pause to enjoy the fruit. This is the moment the flower opens fully to the sun."}}	{"title": "The Star of Destiny", "content": "To be born on 13 Q'anil is to be a cosmic gardener and a carrier of the golden light. You are a 'star seed' in the truest sense—someone who brings a high, refined frequency to the earth. The number Thirteen connects you directly to the spirit world and the ancestors, giving you a powerful intuition and a sense of divine protection. Q'anil makes you a creator, a lover of life, and a natural attracter of abundance. You are the person who always seems to land on their feet, the one who finds the four-leaf clover. Your presence brings joy and growth to those around you.\\n\\nYour life path is one of bringing heaven to earth. You are here to plant seeds of consciousness, beauty, and art. You may be drawn to agriculture, the arts, children, or spiritual teaching. You have a natural innocence and optimism that is rare, but it is backed by the ancient wisdom of the Thirteen. You understand that life is a cycle of planting and harvesting, and you are patient with the process.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is remaining grounded. With such high energy, you can sometimes float away into fantasy or spiritual bypassing. You may also struggle with the harshness of the world, as your soul is tuned to a frequency of harmony. Your lesson is to keep your hands in the dirt—to ensure that your beautiful visions are rooted in practical reality. You are here to show us that the Garden of Eden is not a place we left, but a place we can grow right here, right now."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d5bd89", "primary": "#131514", "secondary": "#4a4237"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.745378	2026-04-25 13:46:57.661078
10	1	10	10	Iq'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Breath of Spirit", "content": "Iq' is the wind, the breath of life, and the voice of the spirit. It represents communication, inspiration, and the vital force that animates all living things. Iq' is the messenger that carries the seeds of change. It governs the mind, the lungs, and the power of words. This nawal can be gentle like a breeze or destructive like a hurricane. It cleanses, purifies, and shifts energy rapidly. It asks us to speak our truth, to breathe deeply, and to be willing to change our minds when the wind shifts direction.", "keywords": ["Wind", "Breath", "Communication", "Change", "Inspiration"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Manifestation", "content": "The number Ten represents the two hands coming together—cooperation and the full realization of the form. It is the number of manifestation, responsibility, and community agreement. Ten takes the gestational energy of Nine and births it into the world. It is a solid, even number that brings things to a head. It represents the laws of society and the agreements we make with each other. On this day, the focus is on the concrete results of our actions and the legacy we are building. It is a day to shake hands and seal the deal.", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Community", "Agreement", "Creation"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Sign contracts or make verbal agreements with clear intent.", "Practice conscious breathwork to ground your nervous system.", "Speak a desire out loud to 'crystallize' it into the physical world.", "Clear the air in a misunderstanding; the wind supports resolution.", "Write a manifesto or mission statement for your life or project."], "title": "Manifesting Through the Word", "content": "10 Iq' brings the power of the spoken word into concrete reality. The manifesting energy of Ten combines with the communicative force of Iq' to create a day where 'abracadabra' (I create as I speak) is literally true. This is a powerful day for agreements, contracts, and public speaking. The wind is no longer just blowing aimlessly; it is being channeled into a structure (Ten) that can drive windmills or fill sails. It is a time to take responsibility for your communication—to ensure your words align with your actions. The energy supports clearing the air in relationships and establishing new, healthier agreements based on truth."}}	{"title": "The Voice of Change", "content": "To be born on 10 Iq' is to be a powerful communicator and a catalyst for social evolution. You have the gift of gab, but it is backed by the weight of responsibility (Ten). You do not just speak to hear your own voice; you speak to build, to connect, and to manifest. You are likely a writer, a speaker, or a negotiator—someone who understands how to use language to shape reality. The wind moves through you, bringing constant new ideas and a need for freedom.\\n\\nYour challenge is consistency. The wind can be fickle, and you may find yourself changing direction often or struggling to stick to the agreements you've made. Your words have immense power, so you must learn to wield them with care, avoiding gossip or harshness. Your soul's purpose is to be a breath of fresh air in stagnant situations, using your voice to bring people together and to inspire concrete, positive change in your community."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#adb2a9", "primary": "#1f221e", "secondary": "#51554f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.737371	2026-04-25 13:46:57.627014
129	10	12	12	No'j					{"nawal": {"title": "The Universal Mind", "content": "No'j is the energy of the brain, the intellect, and wisdom. It represents the power of thought to shape reality. No'j is the connection to the universal mind and the capacity for logic, science, and philosophy. It is the earth shaking with the power of an idea. No'j transforms raw information into usable knowledge. It asks us to think clearly, to plan, and to harmonize our human intelligence with the wisdom of the earth.", "keywords": ["Wisdom", "Intellect", "Knowledge", "Thought", "Earth"]}, "number": {"title": "The Crystal of Understanding", "content": "The number 12 represents understanding, the gathering of wisdom, and the bundling of life experience. It is the highest even number, representing a stable, complex wholeness. 12 is the energy of the council, the village, and the retrospective view. It brings the capacity to understand the 'why' of the journey. It is a day of synthesis, where the scattered lessons of the trecena come together into a coherent body of knowledge.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Wisdom", "Synthesis", "Community", "Review"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Journal your 'lessons learned' from the last 12 days.", "Share a complex idea with a group; the energy supports understanding.", "Solve a puzzle or plan a strategy for a future project.", "Meditate on the connection between your mind and the Earth's mind.", "Thank the teachers and sources of wisdom in your life."], "title": "Synthesizing the Wisdom", "content": "12 No'j is the day of the Sage. As we near the end of the Kame trecena, we are asked to understand the transformation we have undergone. This is not just intellectual understanding; it is the deep, cellular wisdom that comes from experience. 12 No'j bundles the lessons of death and rebirth into a coherent philosophy. It is a day of great mental clarity and community wisdom. The 'new self' now has a new mind. It is a time to share what you have learned, to solve problems that seemed impossible before, and to integrate your spiritual insights into a practical plan for the future."}}	{"title": "The Keeper of Wisdom", "content": "To be born on 12 No'j is to be a library of the universe in human form. You possess a formidable intellect and a deep capacity for understanding complex systems. You are the scholar, the scientist, the philosopher, and the sage. But your wisdom is not just academic; the 12 energy connects you to the community and the totality of experience. You understand people as well as you understand concepts. You are a natural synthesizer, able to take disparate pieces of information and bundle them into a unified truth.\\n\\nYour life path is one of learning and teaching. You are here to bring clarity where there is confusion. You likely have a 'busy' mind that is always processing, and you may find peace in nature, which grounds the electrical energy of No'j. People come to you for advice because you can see the logic in the chaos. You are a problem-solver of the highest order.\\n\\nYour challenge is overthinking or becoming detached from your heart. The brilliance of your mind can sometimes isolate you or make you impatient with those who learn slower. Your soul's task is to bring your wisdom down from the mountain and use it to serve the village. When you marry your intellect with compassion, you become a true luminary, helping humanity understand its own evolution."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c3d0d7", "primary": "#101312", "secondary": "#48474c"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.80793	2026-04-25 13:46:57.870606
12	1	12	12	K'at					{"nawal": {"title": "The Net of Abundance", "content": "K'at is the net, the spiderweb, and the gathering bag. It represents the principle of connection—how we are all tied together in the web of life. K'at is the energy of abundance, gathering resources, and holding space. However, it also represents the trap; the net can catch food, or it can tangle us. This nawal governs memories, debts, and the baggage we carry. It asks us to sort through our net, keeping what nurtures us and releasing what weighs us down. It is an energy of organization, burning the chaff to reveal the grain.", "keywords": ["Net", "Gathering", "Abundance", "Release", "Connection"]}, "number": {"title": "The Crystal of Understanding", "content": "The number Twelve represents the grouping together of all parts to form a coherent whole. It is the number of understanding, retrospection, and the 'village council.' Twelve takes the chaotic expansion of Eleven and integrates it into wisdom. It is a stable, complex vibration that looks back at the entire cycle and makes sense of the journey. This energy is communal and cooperative, recognizing that the sum is greater than its parts. It asks us to synthesize our experiences and to find the common thread that binds them.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Integration", "Community", "Wisdom", "Retrospection"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Review your finances or resources; organize your physical assets.", "Release a mental burden or 'old story' that is cluttering your mind.", "Gather with your community to share resources or wisdom.", " untangle a complex problem by looking at how the parts relate to the whole.", "Donate physical items you no longer need to clear space for the new."], "title": "Gathering the Wisdom of the Cycle", "content": "12 K'at is a day of great accumulation and sorting. The integrating energy of Twelve combines with the gathering power of K'at to create a massive 'harvest' of experience. This is the time to look at everything you have collected—physically, emotionally, and spiritually—during this trecena. What is gold, and what is dross? The energy supports a comprehensive review of your life's 'net.' It is a day to bundle your wisdom, to pay off debts, and to untangle the knots in your relationships. You have the understanding now to see how everything is connected. Use this day to organize your abundance so it serves you rather than enslaves you."}}	{"title": "The Keeper of the Web", "content": "To be born on 12 K'at is to be a master connector and a storehouse of memory. You have a mind that naturally sorts and categorizes experiences, seeing the hidden threads that link people and events. The number Twelve gives you a deep desire for understanding and community, while K'at provides you with the ability to gather resources and people together. You are likely the 'glue' in your social circle, the archivist, or the one who holds space for everyone else. You carry an abundance of talent and potential.\\n\\nYour challenge is hoarding—whether it is physical clutter, emotional baggage, or too many responsibilities. You may feel trapped by your own net, unable to move because you are carrying so much. Your soul's path is to learn the art of release. You must constantly curate your life, understanding that true abundance requires flow, not stagnation. You are here to teach the world that we are all connected, but that we must remain free within the web."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c89c53", "primary": "#1d1c16", "secondary": "#50442f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.738452	2026-04-25 13:46:57.63171
138	11	8	8	E'	The Spire’s ascent reaches a plateau of profound harmony. You enter the Grove of Turning Leaves, where every broad, silver-veined leaf rotates slowly on its stem to track your movement through the canopy. The energy here is whole, reflecting the octave of the journey; you have returned to the note of the beginning, but on a higher level. You find a shallow pool of liquid starlight gathered in the crook of a massive root. Remembering the long miles behind you—the shed skins, the rhythmic drums, and the sacred sweat—you sit and bathe your feet in the cool, luminescent water. It is a ceremony of acknowledgment.\n\nYou realize that the road was not a means to an end, but the teacher itself. The 'obstacles' were merely the friction needed to spark your evolution. In this moment of resonance, your inner compass aligns perfectly with the vertical path of the Spire. You bless the road you have walked and the road yet to come, understanding that you are exactly where you are meant to be. The struggle of the climb has softened into a rhythmic, purposeful walk. As you stand and step out of the starlight pool, your footprints glow with a soft, steady gold, marking you as a sacred traveler who carries the wisdom of the road in every step.	The road under your feet has finally begun to harmonize with your heartbeat. You’ve reached a high plateau where the air is sweet and every silver-veined leaf turns slowly on its stem to track your light. Take a moment to sit and look back at the winding path below. Every mile you’ve walked—especially the ones that were steep, muddy, and exhausting—has provided the exact friction needed to make your spirit shine this bright today. \n\nThis is a ceremony of wholeness. Bathe your feet in a pool of liquid starlight and thank the journey for what it has carved into you. You aren't just wandering aimlessly; you are exactly where you are meant to be in the grand design. All the twists, turns, and 'wrong' directions were just part of the rhythm. \n\nAs you stand to continue, you’ll notice that your footprints are now glowing with a soft, steady gold that refuses to fade. You are leaving a trail of light for those who follow, even when you aren't trying to. Your journey is now a blessing to the world around you. Walk with the quiet confidence of someone who knows that the destination is just a story we tell to keep us moving on the beautiful road.	I am a sacred traveler, and I harmonize the wisdom of the road with every step I take.	Breathe into the soles of your feet and feel their connection to the earth. Trust that you are exactly where you are meant to be in your grand design. \n\nOptionally, walk through a grove where silver-veined leaves rotate to track your light, leaving footprints of steady gold on the dark moss behind you.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Path of Destiny", "content": "E' is the energy of the road, the journey, and the path of life. It is the tooth that bites through obstacles and the feet that walk the miles. E' governs travel, exploration, and the spiritual quest. It represents the experience of the journey itself, rather than the destination. It is the guide who protects travelers and the restless spirit that seeks new horizons. It asks us to trust the road and gain wisdom through experience.", "keywords": ["Path", "Journey", "Exploration", "Destiny", "Experience"]}, "number": {"title": "The Harmonic Resonance", "content": "The number 8 represents the octave, the return to the note of the beginning but on a higher level. It is the number of wholeness, wrapping up the bundle of the previous seven days. 8 is the number of male spirituality and the energy of the fabric of life. It brings a certain organic closure and a resonance of harmony. It is often the day of the 'party' or the ceremonial celebration of the work done so far.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Wholeness", "Resonance", "Ceremony", "Fabric"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Bless your feet or your shoes; thank them for carrying you.", "Take a trip, even a short one, with a sacred intention.", "Reflect on the 'obstacles' of the past and see how they guided you.", "Share a story of your journey with a friend.", "Trust that you are exactly where you are meant to be."], "title": "Harmonizing the Journey", "content": "8 E' is a day of wholeness on the path. It represents a moment where the journey makes sense. All the twists and turns, the obstacles and the open roads, come together into a coherent story. In the Kan trecena, this is the day we realize that the wisdom we sought was in the walking itself. It is a day to bless the road you are on. The energy is supportive and ceremonial. It is a perfect day to start a trip, to bless a vehicle, or to honor the spiritual path you have chosen. The struggle of the climb softens into the rhythm of the walk."}}	{"title": "The Sacred Traveler", "content": "To be born on 8 E' is to be a pilgrim of life. You carry an aura of completeness and purpose as you move through the world. You are not just wandering; you are on a quest, and you know it. You possess a deep inner compass and a resilience that allows you to overcome any obstacle. You are a natural guide for others, helping them find their own way when they are lost. Your life is likely filled with travel, both physical and spiritual, and you gather wisdom from every mile.\\n\\nYour life path is about the integration of experience. You are a collector of stories and a bridge between cultures or ideas. You have a harmonious energy that makes you a welcome guest wherever you go. You understand that the destination is an illusion and that the true gold is found on the road. You are a diplomat of the path, smoothing the way for those who follow.\\n\\nYour challenge is restlessness. You may find it hard to settle down or to commit to one place or person. You may also struggle with the feeling that the 'real life' is always over the next hill. Your lesson is to find the journey within. When you realize that the longest road is the one from the head to the heart, you become a master of the inner landscape, guiding others not just across the earth, but toward their own souls."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#add2cd", "primary": "#0e1a19", "secondary": "#354e4a"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.810912	2026-04-25 14:38:01.314114
226	18	5	5	Aj	The bridge of bones leaves you on a high plateau, but the terrain here is different. The open fire is gone, replaced by a dense, surreal forest. But these are not trees. They are towering stalks of obsidian cane, growing thick and wild, their sharp leaves clacking together like knives in the wind.\n\nThere is no path here. The dense thicket blocks every direction. You try to push through, but the stalks are iron-hard and unyielding. You feel a surge of frustration. After the flow of the thread and the stability of the bridge, you are stuck again.\n\nBut the energy in your hands—the same energy that held the ember—begins to thrum. You realize that you cannot just walk through this; you have to *work* for it.\n\nYou find a loose stalk, slightly separated from the rest. It is heavy, solid black glass, humming with a deep, grounding resonance. You grip it with both hands. It resists. You pull, engaging your back, your legs, your will. It is a struggle. It requires sweat. It requires force applied with intention.\n\nWith a sharp *crack*, the cane breaks free.\n\nIn your hands, it is no longer an obstacle. It is a tool. A staff. You strike the ground with it, and the sound rings out clear and authoritative. The forest seems to listen. The tangled wall of cane ahead shivers and parts slightly, acknowledging your right to be here.\n\nYou are not just a wanderer anymore. You are a pilgrim with a support. You have claimed your authority.\n\nYou step forward, using the staff to push aside the heavy leaves, clearing your own way. The work is hard, but it feels good. It feels like building a home, one step at a time.	You need to back yourself today. Don’t look around for permission—it isn’t coming from the outside. Stand tall like a pillar. If you want a sanctuary, you have to build it with your own actions.\n\nYour energy is a house; don’t leave the door open for just anyone to walk in. Do the work to protect your peace. Build the fence. Set the boundary. Sometimes the most spiritual thing you can do is say "no" and mean it.	I stand tall in my truth and protect my inner home.	Sit with a straight spine. Visualize your backbone as a column of golden light, extending deep into the earth and high into the sky. You are the bridge between heaven and earth.\n\nWith every inhale, breathe strength into your vertebrae. Feel yourself growing taller, more solid. You are a pillar of integrity. Nothing can knock you over.\n\nVisualize a roof of light forming over your head, supported by this pillar. You are safe. You are sheltered. You are home.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Pillar of Community", "content": "Aj is the nawal of the cane, the reed, and the home. It represents the spine, the pillar of the family, and the authority that comes from integrity. Aj is the energy of resurrection and flexibility—like the corn stalk that bends in the wind but does not break. Associated with the element of earth and the color brown or yellow, it carries a gentle, protective, and paternal/maternal energy. It is the archetype of the rightful leader who serves the community. In daily life, Aj manifests as domestic harmony, questions of authority, and the strength of one's inner convictions. Its shadow aspect can be rigidity, authoritarianism, or problems within the home/family structure. Aj teaches us that true strength lies in flexibility and service.", "keywords": ["Home", "Leadership", "Harmony", "Integrity", "Authority"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Power", "content": "Tone 5 is the energy of empowerment, work, and the center. In Mayan numerology, it represents the hand (five fingers) and the ability to grasp, shape, and work with materials. It breaks the stability of the 4 to add a new dimension of agency and action. Tone 5 is the central pivot point of the single-digit numbers (1-9), representing the core or the heart of the matter. Experientially, it feels energetic, capable, and sometimes demanding. It is a day to gather resources and apply effort. While it empowers us to get things done, its shadow can manifest as over-exertion, grasping for control, or losing sight of the spiritual in favor of the material work. It is the number of the worker who makes the vision real.", "keywords": ["Action", "Discipline", "Work", "Empowerment", "Center"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Do physical work to improve your home environment.", "Take charge of a family situation that needs leadership.", "Strengthen your physical spine through exercise or posture work.", "Set clear, firm boundaries with those you live with.", "Work on a project that benefits your local community."], "title": "Empowering the Foundation", "content": "When the working hand of Tone 5 meets the stabilizing force of Aj, we encounter a day of 'Active Stewardship.' 5 Aj is the energy of the Homebuilder and the Community Leader. It is a day to put effort into harmony in home and community. The energy is not passive; it requires us to work for the peace and stability we desire. It feels like the satisfaction of fixing a broken fence or cooking a meal for a large gathering. 5 Aj empowers us to take authority in our own lives, standing tall like the Corn. It supports leadership that is hands-on and practical. If there is disharmony in your household, today is the day to actively address it—not with aggression, but with firm, loving effort. The challenge is to avoid becoming a dictator in your own domain. The opportunity is to be the strong center around which others can thrive."}}	{"title": "The Strong Pillar of Community", "content": "To be born on 5 Aj is to be a person of immense capability and integrity. You act as the backbone of your family or organization. Tone 5 gives you a hard-working, action-oriented nature, while Aj provides you with a love for home, tradition, and order. You are the 'hand that holds the staff'—a natural leader who leads by doing. You don't just talk about community; you build it. You are likely the one who organizes the events, fixes the problems, and ensures that everyone is taken care of.\\n\\nYour life path is one of responsible leadership. You are here to provide stability and protection for others. You have a practical wisdom that is highly valued, and people often turn to you for advice on earthly matters. You may be drawn to construction, politics, administration, or parenting—any role where you can nurture growth through structure. You have a resilience that is admirable; like the reed, you can withstand great pressure without snapping, always bouncing back to your upright position.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 5 Aj soul is the potential for being overbearing or rigid. Because you work so hard to maintain order, you may become frustrated when others don't follow your rules. You might struggle to delegate, believing that if you want it done right, you must do it yourself. This can lead to exhaustion or resentment. Your lesson is to learn the true nature of authority, which is service. When you lead with flexibility and empower others to stand on their own, your strength becomes a shelter rather than a cage."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c59d4d", "primary": "#14120b", "secondary": "#54442f"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#baac9f", "primary": "#1c1d29", "secondary": "#595255"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#c4ae5e", "primary": "#4b4f2e", "secondary": "#8d8243"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#90848a", "primary": "#14151b", "secondary": "#41424a"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.867657	2026-04-25 13:46:58.034404
88	7	10	10	Tz'i'	The air feels clearer today.\n\nYou walk the path to the lake with a steadiness that surprises you—not confidence exactly, but alignment. Your steps fall naturally, as if they have finally found their rhythm on this land.\n\nWhen you reach the shoreline, the lake is calm in a new way. Not still like the first day, not glowing like yesterday, not breathing like before. This calm feels… trustworthy. The kind of quiet that comes from having nothing to hide.\n\nThe water reflects the sky with such precision that for a moment it feels like you are standing at the edge of two identical worlds: one above, one below. The reflection is flawless—no distortion, no ripple, no blur.\n\nYou step closer, and the mirror changes.\n\nPatterns appear across the water—thin, luminous lines forming gentle arcs, circles, and straight paths. They shift and reorganize, settling into something that looks like the beginning of a map. Not the kind made of roads or cities, but of choices. Of consequences. Of truths that want to be acknowledged.\n\nNear the far end of the lake, something moves.\n\nA tall, slender silhouette steps into view. It is not a person—not exactly—but a figure shaped from shimmering lines of light, like a constellation held together by invisible threads. Its form is simple, upright, balanced. Where a face would be, there is only a soft glow.\n\nYou do not feel fear. What rises instead is honesty.\n\nNot confession, not apology—just the quiet willingness to stand as yourself, without mask or embellishment.\n\nThe figure raises one hand. Instantly, the map on the lake sharpens. Some pathways brighten. Others dim. You understand: this is not judgment. It is clarity.\n\nYou think of the ways you’ve acted out of fear. The times you’ve avoided speaking the truth because the truth was inconvenient. The moments you bent your integrity to keep the peace, or stayed silent when your voice could have mattered.\n\nThe lake does not accuse you. It simply reflects.\n\nYou kneel and let your fingers hover just above the water. A ripple moves outward—but instead of distorting the image, the ripple makes the patterns clearer, as if honesty improves things rather than disrupts them.\n\nSomething in your chest loosens.\n\nYou realize that truth is not a weapon. It is a stabilizer. A grounding force. The thing that holds bridges up and keeps foundations from cracking.\n\nThe shimmering figure lowers its hand and the map slowly dissolves back into the quiet reflection. Before fading completely, the figure tilts its head in a gesture that feels like approval—not for perfection, but for willingness.\n\nYou stand, taller than when you arrived.\n\nThe path home feels straighter today. Not easier, but straighter.\n\nYou leave the lake with a clear, steady sense of who you are becoming: someone whose truth is not sharp or defensive, but clean, grounded, and kind.	Today brings a clear, grounded truthfulness. You may feel a strong instinct to straighten your posture, tidy your space, clarify your intentions, or speak honestly in a way you’ve been avoiding.\n\nThis is not a day for dramatic confessions. It is a day for alignment. For removing the small lies you tell yourself out of convenience or habit. For choosing the path that is clean over the one that is merely easy.\n\nWhen you act from integrity today, things fall into place with surprising ease. Trust the part of you that knows what’s right—not morally, but energetically. Truth feels steady. Let it guide you.	I stand in my truth with clarity and kindness, and I let my actions reflect the person I choose to be.	Sit or stand with a long spine. Close your eyes and imagine the lake before you, perfectly reflective.\n\nOn the surface, see lines of light forming a simple map—paths, arcs, intersections. Let the image shift until one path brightens. Follow it gently in your mind. Notice how it feels in your body: does it bring steadiness, calm, relief?\n\nNow place a hand on your heart and ask inwardly: “What truth wants to be lived today?”\n\nYou don’t need a sentence. Even a sensation or a single word is enough.\n\nOffer a quiet thanks to the keepers of truth, justice, and integrity. Then open your eyes and take one grounded step into the day with that guidance in mind.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Guide of Law", "content": "Tz'i' is the Nawal of the dog, the law, justice, and loyalty. It represents the principle of divine order and the faithful guide who leads the soul through the darkness. Tz'i' is the energy of authority, protection, and unconditional love. In human experience, Tz'i' manifests as a strong sense of right and wrong, a desire for justice, and deep loyalty to friends and family. It is the secretary who keeps the records straight. When aligned, Tz'i' brings legal success and spiritual guidance; when misaligned, it can lead to judgment, addiction, or blind obedience.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Loyalty", "Law", "Faith", "Protection"]}, "number": {"title": "The Peak of Manifestation", "content": "The number Ten represents the manifestation of the intent. It is the two hands coming together (5+5) to finalize the creation. In Mayan cosmology, Ten is the energy of community agreement, collaboration, and the realization of the project. Experientially, this energy feels solid, accomplished, and social. It is the moment when the house is built and we invite the neighbors in. The shadow of Ten can be over-responsibility, but its light is the satisfaction of seeing your dreams take physical form. Today, the universe says: 'It is done.'", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Collaboration", "Realization", "Mastery"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Review contracts or legal documents with a clear eye.", "Stand up for a friend or a cause; show your loyalty.", "Bring a project to completion that involves rules or structure.", "Trust your moral compass; it is pointing true north today.", "Collaborate with others to create a fairer system."], "title": "Manifested Justice", "content": "When the manifesting power of Tone 10 meets the legal authority of Tz'i', we experience a day of 'Community Law.' 10 Tz'i' is the energy of justice being served in the village square. It is a day where truth comes to light and order is restored through collaboration. If you have legal matters pending, this is a powerful day for resolution. The energy supports fairness, loyalty, and the upholding of agreements. It is also a day to manifest your own internal code of ethics—to walk your talk in a way that others can see. The dog (Tz'i') protects the community (10). Be a loyal friend today; stand up for those who cannot stand up for themselves. The energy is solid and reliable. It reminds us that spiritual law is not abstract; it is manifested in how we treat each other every single day."}}	{"title": "The Loyal Leader", "content": "To be born on 10 Tz'i' is to be a pillar of justice and a faithful companion. You are the 'Manifested Guide'—someone who embodies the law of love and loyalty in a tangible way. You have a strong sense of responsibility to your community and are likely the person everyone trusts to do the right thing. You are a natural leader, not through force, but through your unwavering reliability. People know that if you say you will do something, it is as good as done (10).\\n\\nYour life path is one of upholding the truth. You may be drawn to law, administration, or social justice work. You have a 'detective' mind that seeks to uncover the facts and restore order. Your challenge is to ensure that your love for the law does not turn into rigidity or judgment of those who are less disciplined. Remember that the highest law is unconditional love. You are here to protect the pack and guide us toward the light."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#caccbd", "primary": "#101818", "secondary": "#3f4540"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.790411	2026-04-25 13:46:57.769409
227	18	6	6	Ix	With the staff in your hand, the dense forest becomes navigable. You find a rhythm—step, push, clear. Step, push, clear. The physical effort grounds you, quieting your mind.\n\nGradually, the sharp crystal canes give way to softer forms. The ground beneath your boots changes from crunching ash to something spongy and alive. You look down and see moss. But it isn’t green. It is a deep, velvety purple, glowing with faint, ultraviolet veins.\n\nThe air cools rapidly. A thick mist rolls in, smelling of rain and ozone. It swirls around your legs, moving with a deliberate intelligence.\n\nYou stop. The silence here is different. It isn’t the silence of emptiness; it is the silence of someone holding their breath.\n\nAhead, in a clearing of the glowing moss, the mist thickens and takes form. A shape coalesces—low to the ground, muscular, prowling. A jaguar. But it is not made of flesh and fur. It is made of the mist itself, lit from within by starlight.\n\nIt turns its massive head toward you. Its eyes are pools of infinite depth. It does not growl. It simply watches, pulsing with a slow, rhythmic light that matches the beating of your own heart.\n\nYou realize the garden is aware of you. The moss, the mist, the stone—it is all one nervous system, and you are standing inside it.\n\nThe jaguar turns and walks away into the fog, looking back once to ensure you are following. It is not a guide you can leash. It is a flow you must join.\n\nYou abandon the straight line. You step where the moss glows brightest. You move with the mist. You trust the invisible current that pulls you forward.\n\nMagic is not a spell you cast. It is a path you walk.	Stop pushing. The more you force things today, the harder they will get. The magic is in the pause. You are being helped by forces you can’t see.\n\nPay attention to "coincidences" today. The universe is whispering to you, but you have to be quiet to hear it. Trust your gut—the inner jaguar knows the way through the dark better than your mind does. Follow the flow, even if it doesn’t make sense yet.	I walk with the silent confidence of the jaguar.	Close your eyes. Imagine you are in a dark, ancient forest. You are not afraid. You drop down onto all fours and become a jaguar. Feel the strength in your shoulders, the softness of your paws on the earth.\n\nMove through the forest with silent grace. You can see in the dark. You can sense the heartbeat of the trees. Feel the earth pulsing beneath you, sending energy up into your limbs.\n\nYou are connected to everything. You are the magic. Breathe in the power of the earth.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Jaguar of Earth Magic", "content": "Ix is the nawal of the jaguar, the shaman, and the magic of the earth. It represents the feminine mysteries, high magic, and the connection to nature spirits. Ix is the energy of the night seer who walks without fear in the darkness. Associated with the element of earth and the spirit, it carries a stealthy, potent, and highly intuitive energy. It is the archetype of the healer who uses nature's tools to transform reality. In daily life, Ix manifests as intuition, synchronicity, and a deep pull toward the mysteries of life. Its shadow aspect can be the misuse of power, black magic, or becoming reclusive and disconnected from the human world. Ix teaches us that the earth is alive.", "keywords": ["Magic", "Intuition", "Nature", "Jaguar", "Mystery"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Harmony", "content": "Tone 6 is the energy of flow, rhythm, and responsiveness. After the exertion of the 5, the 6 allows the energy to stabilize and find its natural groove. It is the number of ultimate balance in motion—like a surfer riding a wave or a heart beating in time. In Mayan cosmology, it is associated with the six directions (East, West, North, South, Up, Down), representing a spatial wholeness. Experientially, Tone 6 feels fluid and harmonious. It is a day where things often 'click' into place without force. While it fosters growth and family connection, its shadow can be passivity or a tendency to drift with the current rather than steering. It is the breath that connects the effort to the result.", "keywords": ["Rhythm", "Harmony", "Flow", "Balance", "Growth"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Spend time in nature, simply observing the flow of life.", "Visit a sacred site or a place of natural beauty.", "Practice intuitive movement or dance to connect with your body.", "Trust the 'coincidences' that happen today; they are messages.", "Perform a small act of service for the Earth (pick up trash, plant a seed)."], "title": "The Flow of Earth Magic", "content": "When the harmonious flow of Tone 6 meets the magical intuition of Ix, we enter a day of 'Natural Mysticism.' 6 Ix is the Jaguar moving gracefully through the jungle. The energy today is not about forcing magic to happen, but about stepping into the stream where magic already exists. It is a day of service to the Earth and sacred sites. Synchronicities flow easily today; the right people and the right information appear without effort. It feels like being in the right place at the right time. 6 Ix supports healing work that involves nature or the feminine principle. It encourages us to trust our bodies and our instincts. The challenge is to remain grounded while navigating the subtle realms. The opportunity is to realize that the separation between the physical and the spiritual is an illusion."}}	{"title": "The Intuitive Harmonizer of Nature", "content": "To be born on 6 Ix is to be a bridge between the human world and the intelligence of nature. You possess a sensitive, intuitive soul that feels the rhythms of the earth. Tone 6 gives you a harmonious, easy-going nature, while Ix grants you the deep wisdom of the Jaguar. You are likely the person who can walk into a room and instantly read the energy, or walk into a forest and feel at home. You have a natural healing ability, often just through your presence or touch. You flow through life with a certain grace, trusting your instincts to guide you.\\n\\nYour life path is one of integrating magic into the everyday. You are not a recluse; you bring the mysteries of the feminine and the earth into your relationships and community. You may be drawn to herbalism, alternative healing, ecology, or the arts—ways to express the beauty and magic you perceive. You are a natural diplomat for the planet, helping others to see the sacredness of the physical world. Your spirituality is not rigid; it is fluid, evolving, and deeply felt.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 6 Ix soul is the potential for passivity or ungroundedness. You may prefer to drift in the magical realms rather than deal with the harsh realities of life. You might struggle to set boundaries, absorbing the energies of others until you are overwhelmed. There is also a risk of using your intuition to escape rather than to engage. Your lesson is to bring your magic down to earth—to use your sensitivity to solve real problems and to create harmony in the here and now. When you do, you become a powerful healer who reminds the world of its own soul."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#7fb76f", "primary": "#090e0a", "secondary": "#466e3b"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#5186d4", "primary": "#0f1929", "secondary": "#273a7e"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#ba9ddf", "primary": "#252c55", "secondary": "#7867af"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#8684b0", "primary": "#131728", "secondary": "#373962"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.868203	2026-04-25 13:46:58.036222
14	2	1	1	Ajmaq					{"nawal": {"title": "The Owl of Forgiveness", "content": "Ajmaq is the nawal of pardon, redemption, and the profoundly human experience of fallibility. Represented by the owl and the bee, it governs the sweetness of life that returns after we have reconciled with our errors. It is the energy of the ancestors, carrying the wisdom of the lineage and the ability to clear karmic debts through genuine acknowledgment and forgiveness. Ajmaq is not about perfection; it is about the grace found in admitting we are imperfect. It teaches us that wisdom often comes from the 'mistake,' not the success. In its shadow aspect, Ajmaq can lead to wallowing in guilt, hiding from one's actions, or repeating patterns without learning. However, when aligned, it offers the deepest form of liberation: the ability to forgive oneself and others, restoring harmony to the web of life. It is the soft darkness that holds us while we heal.", "keywords": ["Forgiveness", "Ancestors", "Redemption", "Sweetness", "Reconciliation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Fire", "content": "One is the beginning, the primordial spark from which all creation unfurls. It is the seed that contains the entire blueprint of the forest within its humble shell. In the Mayan cosmology, the number One represents unity, potential, and the focused initiation of a new cycle. It is not merely a starting line but a concentrated point of power where intention is most fertile. Experientially, this energy feels like a sudden clarity or an urge to plant something new—whether a project, a relationship, or a habit. The shadow of One can manifest as isolation or a lack of momentum if the seed is not watered with action. It asks you to stand firmly in your individuality while recognizing that you are the origin point of the ripple you are about to create. Today, the universe holds its breath, waiting for you to make the first move.", "keywords": ["Unity", "Potential", "Initiation", "Focus", "Seed"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Identify one past mistake you are ready to stop punishing yourself for.", "Light a candle for your ancestors and ask for their guidance in clearing old patterns.", "Write down a grievance on a piece of paper and safely burn it to symbolize release.", "Practice the phrase 'I am learning' instead of 'I failed' throughout the day.", "Sit in silence and visualize a seed of golden light planted in your heart center."], "title": "Seeding the Path of Reconciliation", "content": "The convergence of the number One with the nawal Ajmaq creates a powerful opening for self-forgiveness and a new chapter of emotional freedom. While One brings the energy of new beginnings and singular focus, Ajmaq softens this drive with the wisdom of the ancestors and the acceptance of human imperfection. This day is not about launching a business or building a physical structure; it is about initiating a new relationship with your own past. It is the 'Seed of Forgiveness.' You are being asked to look at where you have been harsh with yourself or others and to plant a seed of mercy in that wound. The energy feels tender, quiet, and profound—like the first light of dawn touching a dark forest. The challenge today is to avoid the trap of shame which might try to stifle this new beginning. Instead, use the focused power of the One to cut through the noise of guilt and declare a new standard of gentleness for your life. This is the day to set the intention that your journey forward will be lighter than the one behind you."}}	{"title": "The Initiator of Grace", "content": "To be born on 1 Ajmaq is to be a pioneer of forgiveness and a carrier of ancestral hope. You possess a unique soul signature that blends the initiating power of the number One with the deep, redemptive wisdom of Ajmaq. You are likely the person in your family or community who breaks the cycle—the one who decides that the trauma stops here. Your presence naturally invites others to drop their defenses and admit their vulnerabilities, for you carry an aura of non-judgmental acceptance. You are a 'first mover' in the realms of healing, often finding yourself in situations where you must lead by example in offering apology or amnesty.\\n\\nYour life path is one of discovering the strength in softness. While others may see forgiveness as weakness, you understand it as a potent force of creation. You have a natural affinity for history, lineage, and the hidden stories of the past, often feeling a strong connection to those who came before you. You are a listener, a keeper of secrets, and a weaver of reconciliation. The sweetness of life is your birthright, but you must claim it by refusing to carry burdens that do not belong to you.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is to ensure that your capacity for forgiveness does not turn into a lack of boundaries. The number One gives you a strong sense of self, but Ajmaq's desire to harmonize can sometimes lead you to absorb the emotions of others. Your growth lies in learning that you can love and forgive without losing your own center. You are here to teach the world that every new beginning starts with making peace with the end."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b376a5", "primary": "#131512", "secondary": "#4b383d"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.740589	2026-04-25 13:46:57.65219
175	14	6	6	E'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Path of Destiny", "content": "E' is the energy of the road, the journey, and the spiritual path. It is the tooth that bites through obstacles and the feet that walk the miles. E' governs travel, exploration, and the experience of the journey itself. It asks us to trust the road and gain wisdom through movement.", "keywords": ["Path", "Journey", "Exploration", "Destiny", "Guide"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Stability", "content": "The number 6 represents ultimate stability, flow, and vitality. It brings balance to the work of the 5, facilitating responsiveness and organic growth. It is associated with the heart of the sky and earth in alignment. In the Kej trecena, 6 brings a harmonious flow to the journey.", "keywords": ["Flow", "Harmony", "Stability", "Vitality", "Balance"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Take a trip or go for a long drive.", "Trust that the obstacles are being cleared for you.", "Practice 'walking meditation.'", "Ask for guidance on your life path.", "Enjoy the journey without worrying about the destination."], "title": "The Smooth Road", "content": "6 E' is a day of smooth, flowing travel. The stability of the 6 removes the obstacles from the path of E'. In the Kej trecena, this is a day where the walk through the wilderness feels effortless. We are in the flow of our destiny. It is an excellent day for travel, for moving forward with plans, and for trusting the direction you are heading. The energy supports a steady pace. We are not rushing, but we are moving with the certainty of a river. The road rises to meet our feet."}}	{"title": "The Steady Traveler", "content": "To be born on 6 E' is to be a soul on a blessed journey. You possess a natural flow and a sense of direction that others envy. You are not the frantic explorer; you are the steady pilgrim. You move through life with a calm assurance that you are on the right path. You are a natural diplomat and guide, smoothing the way for others. You have a talent for navigating different cultures and ideas with grace.\\n\\nYour life path is one of harmonious discovery. You learn through experience, but your lessons tend to be gentle rather than harsh. You are adaptable and responsive to the road. You are likely well-traveled and open-minded.\\n\\nYour challenge is complacency. Because the road is often smooth for you, you may avoid the steep climbs that lead to the best views. You may drift rather than drive. Your lesson is to choose a destination worthy of your journey. When you align your steady flow with a high purpose, you become a guide who can lead others safely through any terrain."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#accbd2", "primary": "#142021", "secondary": "#4b636b"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.842182	2026-04-25 13:46:57.9534
23	2	10	10	Kan					{"nawal": {"title": "The Serpent of Wisdom", "content": "Kan is the nawal of the serpent, the life force (kundalini), and evolution. It represents the inner fire that coils at the base of the spine and rises to bring enlightenment. Kan is the energy of DNA, the spiral, and the power of transformation through shedding skin. It governs sexuality, vitality, and justice. Kan is an intense, instinctual energy—it is the raw power of nature. In its shadow, Kan can be manipulative, seductive in a negative way, or prone to misuse of power. It represents the test of integrity. Its highest expression is the wise use of power to serve the evolution of consciousness, moving with the fluidity and strength of the snake.", "keywords": ["Serpent", "Vitality", "Evolution", "Wisdom", "Power"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Manifestation", "content": "Ten is the number of manifestation, responsibility, and the two hands clasping together. It represents the realization of the cycle—where the intention of One and the work of Five come to fruition. Ten is a number of community agreement, law, and the tangible results of our efforts. Experientially, a Ten day feels solid, accomplished, and sometimes heavy with expectation. It is a day where things 'land.' The shadow of Ten can be the burden of responsibility or the harshness of judgment if the results are not what was hoped for. It asks us to own our creations and stand by what we have built.", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Fruition", "Collaboration", "Authority"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in physical exercise like yoga or dance to move the energy in your spine.", "Take ownership of a situation where you have given your power away.", "Focus on 'grounding' your ideas; what is the practical step to make the vision real?", "Be mindful of your lower back and spine; stretch and breathe into these areas.", "Visualize a caduceus (staff with two snakes) representing your balanced power."], "title": "Manifesting Vitality", "content": "When the manifesting power of Ten combines with the evolutionary force of Kan, we have a day of 'Realized Power' or 'Materialized Wisdom.' This is a high-voltage day. The abstract potential of the serpent's energy is being grounded into tangible form by the Ten. It is an incredible day for physical healing, athletic pursuits, or taking a leadership role that requires charisma and strength. Things you have been working on may suddenly shed their old skins and reveal their true, shiny forms. The energy is authoritative and demands respect. The challenge is to handle this power with integrity. Ten Kan can be overwhelming if your nervous system isn't ready for the voltage. It can also tempt you to use your influence for control rather than service. The lesson is to be the 'wise container' for the energy—to let the power flow through you into the world, creating structures (Ten) that support life and growth (Kan)."}}	{"title": "The Master of Life Force", "content": "To be born on 10 Kan is to be a powerhouse of energy and a natural leader of evolution. You possess a magnetism that is palpable; people are drawn to your vitality and your strength. The number Ten gives you a sense of authority and a drive to build tangible results, while Kan endows you with deep instinctual wisdom and a connection to the primal forces of life. You are likely very physical, intelligent, and possibly gifted in the healing arts or in fields that require high stamina and strategy. You are a 'manifestor'—when you put your mind to something, you have the sheer force of will to make it happen.\\n\\nYour life path is one of mastering your own power. You have a Ferrari engine, and you need to learn to drive it without crashing. You may face lessons around the use of influence, sexuality, or material wealth. You are a teacher of transformation, often by modeling it yourself—shedding skins publicly and emerging stronger each time. You have a deep sense of justice and will fight fiercely for what you believe is right.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is not to be consumed by your own fire. You can be intense, and sometimes this intensity can burn bridges or intimidate others. Your lesson is to channel your massive energy into service and to cultivate a 'cool head' to balance your 'hot blood.' When you align your will with higher wisdom, you become a force of nature that evolves not just yourself, but everyone around you."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a3a464", "primary": "#13140e", "secondary": "#47442c"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.744361	2026-04-25 13:46:57.655348
252	20	5	5	Kawoq	You have cut your tethers, but now you are exposed. The sky darkens rapidly. Clouds boil up from the valley, purple and bruised, moving with unnatural speed. The wind changes from a whisper to a scream.\n\nA storm is coming.\n\n5 is Empowerment and Work. Kawoq is the Storm and the Midwife. This is not a punishment; it is an initiation. The Vision must be tested.\n\nLightning strikes the Spire above you. Thunder shakes the plateau. You look for shelter. You see a cave opening, glowing with a warm, amber light.\n\nYou run for it. You dive inside just as the rain hits—a deluge that washes the world clean.\n\nInside the cave, it is dry and warm. But you are not alone. There are others here—shadowy figures, spirits of the mountain, maybe other travelers. They are sitting in a circle around a fire.\n\nThey make space for you. Someone hands you a blanket. Someone hands you a cup.\n\nYou realize that Kawoq is not just the storm outside; it is the community inside. It is the "turtle shell" that protects the soft life within. To handle the immense power of the storm, you need a container. You need a family.\n\nYou sit by the fire. You feel the heat (5) empowering you. The storm rages outside, battering the mountain, washing away the debris of your past cutting. But in here, you are safe.\n\nYou understand that abundance is not just having wings; it is having a nest. It is having a place to weather the storm.\n\nThe group begins to hum, a low resonant sound that matches the thunder. You join in. Your voice blends with theirs. You are gathering strength for the next ascent.	The weather might get a little intense today, emotionally or literally. The energy of 5 Kawoq is a storm, but it’s a cleansing one. Don’t stand out in the rain trying to be a hero. Find your shelter.\n\nConnect with your people. Your family, your friends, your community—they are your turtle shell. There is immense power in gathering together and waiting out the thunder. You will emerge from this washed clean and ready for the new.	I am safe in the storm, protected by love and the strength of my community.	Visualize a turtle shell. It is glowing with golden symbols. You are inside it. It is warm, soft, and comfortable. \n\nOutside, the rain pounds and the wind howls. But you are dry. Feel the safety of your boundaries. Feel the warmth of your own heart.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Compassionate Storm", "content": "Kawoq is the nawal of the storm, the turtle, and the midwife. It represents the community, the family bloodline, and the power of feminine cleansing. Kawoq is the energy of the rain that washes away the dust and nourishes the crops. Associated with the element of water and the color green/blue, it carries a fluid, emotional, and collective energy. It is the archetype of the caregiver who holds space for birth and rebirth. In daily life, Kawoq manifests as family gatherings, emotional release, and the protection of the vulnerable. Its shadow aspect can be emotional overwhelm, lack of boundaries, or 'smothering' care. Kawoq teaches us that we are all drops in the same ocean.", "keywords": ["Community", "Compassion", "Cleansing", "Rebirth", "Midwife"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Power", "content": "Tone 5 is the energy of empowerment, work, and the center. In Mayan numerology, it represents the hand (five fingers) and the ability to grasp, shape, and work with materials. It breaks the stability of the 4 to add a new dimension of agency and action. Tone 5 is the central pivot point of the single-digit numbers (1-9), representing the core or the heart of the matter. Experientially, it feels energetic, capable, and sometimes demanding. It is a day to gather resources and apply effort. While it empowers us to get things done, its shadow can manifest as over-exertion, grasping for control, or losing sight of the spiritual in favor of the material work. It is the number of the worker who makes the vision real.", "keywords": ["Action", "Discipline", "Work", "Empowerment", "Center"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Do a favor for a family member or neighbor.", "Volunteer your time for a community cause.", "Engage in a deep cleaning of your home (water cleansing).", "Facilitate a healing circle or support group.", "Work on a creative project that involves emotional expression."], "title": "Empowered Compassion", "content": "When the working hand of Tone 5 meets the storm energy of Kawoq, we experience a day of 'Active Caregiving.' 5 Kawoq is the energy of the Midwife at work. It is not a day for passive empathy, but for rolling up your sleeves and helping the community. The energy supports sustained effort in the realms of healing, family, and home. It feels like the busy, focused energy of preparing a meal for a large family or cleaning a house from top to bottom. 5 Kawoq asks us to put our compassion into action. It is a powerful day to serve others, to facilitate a gathering, or to work on healing ancestral patterns through decisive action. The challenge is the potential for burnout; the 5 wants to work, and Kawoq feels everything. The opportunity is to realize that service is a form of power, and that caring for others creates a center of gravity for the whole community."}}	{"title": "The Strong Guardian of the Family", "content": "To be born on 5 Kawoq is to be a pillar of strength and compassion for your community. You possess a soul that is both nurturing and incredibly capable. Tone 5 gives you a work ethic and a drive to take action, while Kawoq connects you to the heart of the family and the flow of emotions. You are the 'Midwife of Action'—the one who doesn't just hold the hand, but boils the water and catches the baby. You are a natural protector, willing to work hard to ensure the safety and well-being of those you love.\\n\\nYour life path is one of service through strength. You are here to build and maintain the community structure. You may be drawn to nursing, social work, parenting, or community organizing—roles where care is a verb. You have a resilience that allows you to weather emotional storms that would topple others. People rely on you because you get things done, but you do it with a heart full of love.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 5 Kawoq soul is over-functioning. You may become the martyr, doing everything for everyone until you collapse. You might struggle to let others help you, believing that you must be the strong one. There is a risk of becoming controlling in your care, smothering those you mean to protect. Your lesson is to empower others to care for themselves. When you learn to facilitate rather than fix, your strength becomes a renewable resource that nourishes the entire village."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#6ac2ba", "primary": "#10191a", "secondary": "#2b5151"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#93bcd5", "primary": "#184064", "secondary": "#457da7"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#cee3d5", "primary": "#938fab", "secondary": "#c6b6e2"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#388aa4", "primary": "#161a1f", "secondary": "#9c4f17"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.882636	2026-04-25 13:46:58.083027
250	20	3	3	No'j	The path changes again. It is no longer a natural trail; it is a staircase carved directly into the vertical face of the Spire. The steps are geometric, interlocking shapes that glow with a faint blue light.\n\nThis is the Ascent of the Mind.\n\n3 is Movement. No’j is Wisdom and Intellect. To climb this section, you cannot just use your feet; you must use your mind.\n\nYou step onto the first geometric block. It shifts under your weight, clicking into a new position. You realize the staircase is a puzzle. If you move without thinking, the path crumbles. If you move with intention, the path forms ahead of you.\n\nYou pause. You observe the pattern. It is a logic of nature—fractals, spirals, the geometry of a pinecone or a snowflake. You align your thoughts with the pattern.\n\n*Click.*\n\nThe next step rises to meet you.\n\nYou begin to climb, solving the mountain with every step. Your mind races—not with worry, but with calculation and insight. You see the solution to a problem that has plagued you for months. You see the structure of your next project. You see how A connects to B connects to C.\n\nThe air crackles with static electricity. Sparks fly from your fingertips as you touch the walls. You are channeling pure information.\n\nYou are moving fast now, leaping from logic to logic, riding the flow of intelligence. It is exhilarating. You realize that your mind is not a cage; it is a ladder. If you use it right, it can take you anywhere.\n\nYou reach a high plateau, breathless and buzzing. You look back at the staircase. It has locked into a solid, beautiful spiral. You have built your way up.	Your brain is on fire today—in a good way. The energy of 3 No’j is quick, sharp, and brilliant. You might find yourself connecting dots that have been separate for years.\n\nDon’t try to slow down the flow of ideas. Let them come. Scribble them on napkins, voice note them, share them. You are cracking the code of your own life. The solution you’ve been looking for is right there in the pattern. Look closer.	I trust my intelligence and allow my mind to flow with divine wisdom.	Imagine your brain is a beautiful, glowing network of blue light. Watch the impulses travel along the neural pathways. \n\nSee a block in the road—a worry or a confusion. Now watch the light route around it, dissolve it, and create a new, faster path. Feel your mind upgrading itself.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Crystal Mind of Wisdom", "content": "No'j is the nawal of the mind, knowledge, and the earth's brain. It represents the power of thought, logic, and the conversion of information into wisdom. No'j is the scholar, the scientist, and the planner. Associated with the element of earth and the color blue, it carries a cool, clear, and intellectual energy. It is the archetype of the sage who solves problems through clarity and innovation. In daily life, No'j manifests as study, brainstorming, and the spark of a good idea. Its shadow aspect can be overthinking, arrogance, or becoming trapped in mental loops. No'j teaches us that true intelligence is not just knowing facts, but knowing how to live in harmony with the cosmos.", "keywords": ["Wisdom", "Knowledge", "Thought", "Innovation", "Logic"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Movement", "content": "Tone 3 is the energy of movement, vibration, and communication. It breaks the static balance of the number 2, introducing flow and dynamism. If 1 is the point and 2 is the line, 3 is the triangle—the first geometric form that implies stability yet encourages motion. It represents the integration of the right brain, left brain, and the central nervous system, or the union of mind, body, and spirit. Experientially, Tone 3 feels busy, expressive, and sometimes restless. It is a day of 'doing,' where ideas seek to be spoken and energies seek to be circulated. While it fosters creativity and connection, its shadow can manifest as scattered energy, anxiety, or a lack of focus. It is the pulse that keeps the universe from standing still.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Expression", "Energy", "Instability", "Flow"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Brainstorm ideas for a project without censoring yourself.", "Write in a journal or start a blog post.", "Engage in a stimulating conversation or debate.", "Take a walk to help process your thoughts (movement aids No'j).", "Teach someone a skill or share a piece of knowledge."], "title": "The Active Mind", "content": "When the rhythmic movement of Tone 3 meets the intellectual power of No'j, we experience a day of 'Creative Intelligence.' 3 No'j is the brain in motion—synapses firing, ideas flowing, and communication happening. It is not a day for quiet contemplation, but for active brainstorming and discussion. The energy is quick, sharp, and innovative. It supports solving problems by looking at them from new angles. 3 No'j encourages us to speak our thoughts and to listen to the wisdom of others. It is an excellent day for writing, teaching, or engaging in debate. The challenge is the 'monkey mind'—thoughts moving so fast they become scattered or anxious. The opportunity is to channel this mental agility into a clear stream of expression, turning abstract wisdom into communicable truth."}}	{"title": "The Communicator of Wisdom", "content": "To be born on 3 No'j is to be a brilliant communicator and a quick thinker. You possess a mind that never stops moving. Tone 3 gives you a need for expression and rhythm, while No'j grants you the intellect of the scholar. You are the teacher who makes learning fun, the writer who turns complex ideas into accessible stories, the scientist who can explain the universe to a child. You have a restless curiosity and a wit that is both sharp and charming.\\n\\nYour life path is one of sharing knowledge. You are not meant to keep your wisdom to yourself. You thrive in environments where ideas are exchanged freely. You may be drawn to journalism, education, technology, or public speaking. You have a talent for connecting dots that others don't see, innovating solutions through your creative logic. You are a lifelong learner, always seeking the next piece of the puzzle.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 3 No'j soul is mental burnout. Your mind runs at such a high speed that you can suffer from anxiety or insomnia. You may struggle to focus on one thing for long, jumping from topic to topic. There is a risk of being 'all talk and no action,' loving the theory but avoiding the practice. Your lesson is to ground your mental energy. When you learn to focus your powerful mind on a singular purpose, your words become catalysts for profound change and understanding."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#cdcbe1", "primary": "#17191c", "secondary": "#474775"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#94c5e1", "primary": "#132645", "secondary": "#3e6898"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#f2eccc", "primary": "#a7b1ab", "secondary": "#d4e8eb"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#a1c1cd", "primary": "#4a7191", "secondary": "#41b2da"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.881945	2026-04-25 13:46:58.079907
15	2	2	2	No'j					{"nawal": {"title": "The Mind of the Earth", "content": "No'j is the nawal of wisdom, intellect, and the transmutation of knowledge into understanding. It represents the brain and the mind, but specifically the mind that is connected to the Earth—grounded, practical wisdom rather than abstract theory. No'j is the problem-solver, the planner, and the keeper of ancient science. It governs the movement of the earth (earthquakes) and the movement of the mind (ideas). In its aligned state, No'j brings brilliant clarity, innovative solutions, and a deep appreciation for learning. In its shadow, it can lead to overthinking, arrogance, or becoming trapped in one's own mental loops. No'j asks us to use our intelligence to serve the collective, turning raw data into nourishment for the community.", "keywords": ["Wisdom", "Intellect", "Solutions", "Knowledge", "Earthquake"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "Two is the energy of polarity, partnership, and the dynamic tension between opposites. In the Mayan worldview, nothing exists in isolation; everything has a counterpart. Two brings the awareness of the 'other'—light and dark, masculine and feminine, sun and moon. It is the number of relationships and choices. Experientially, a Two day often presents a fork in the road or a situation that requires you to weigh two sides of a coin. It is not necessarily a day of conflict, but one of comparison and reflection. The energy asks for balance and cooperation. Its shadow can manifest as indecision or seeing separation where there should be connection. It teaches us that duality is not a battle to be won, but a dance to be partnered with.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Partnership", "Balance", "Reflection", "Choice"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in a conversation with someone who holds a different perspective than you.", "Write down a pro/con list for a decision you have been avoiding.", "Read a book or article on a subject you know nothing about to stimulate new neural pathways.", "Practice active listening; listen to understand, not to reply.", "If you feel mentally scattered, walk barefoot on the earth to ground your thoughts."], "title": "Harmonizing the Dual Mind", "content": "When the polarizing energy of Two meets the intellectual force of No'j, we enter a day of 'Shared Wisdom' or 'Dialoguing Minds.' The energy today focuses on the relationship between ideas—how one thought balances or challenges another. It is an excellent day for collaboration, debate, and finding the middle ground between opposing viewpoints. You may find yourself playing the role of the diplomat or the synthesizer, taking two disparate concepts and weaving them into a coherent solution. The experience is one of mental activity and relational reflection. The challenge lies in the potential for mental conflict—indecision paralysis or an argument where two 'rights' clash. However, the opportunity is to see the other side of the argument with crystal clarity. It is a day to realize that wisdom is rarely a monologue; it is a conversation between the known and the unknown, the self and the other."}}	{"title": "The Diplomat of Wisdom", "content": "To be born on 2 No'j is to be a bridge between minds and a harmonizer of opposing truths. You carry the dual gift of high intellect and profound empathy for the 'other side.' Your mind works dialectically; you naturally see the thesis and the antithesis, and your life's work often involves finding the synthesis. You are the person friends come to when they need a fair, unbiased opinion, for you have an innate ability to detach from emotional bias and see the structural reality of a situation. You are a partner in thought, thriving in collaborations where ideas can be bounced back and forth like a game of tennis.\\n\\nYour intelligence is not cold or academic; it is relational. You understand that knowledge is most useful when it connects people. You may find yourself drawn to fields like law, counseling, diplomacy, or teaching, where the goal is to bridge gaps in understanding. You are a natural problem-solver who prefers to work in tandem rather than alone. The 'Two' energy gives you a charm and approachability that softens the sometimes intense mental energy of No'j, making you a relatable and beloved teacher or guide.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is the burden of over-analysis. Seeing both sides of everything can sometimes leave you stuck in the middle, unable to make a firm choice for yourself. You may also struggle with doubting your own wisdom if it isn't validated by a partner. Your evolution involves learning to trust your own inner counsel as much as you value the input of others. You are here to show that true wisdom is a cooperative act."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#6faab3", "primary": "#141513", "secondary": "#464848"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.741079	2026-04-25 13:46:57.662554
253	20	6	6	Ajpu	The storm breaks as dawn approaches. You step out of the cave. The air is scrubbed clean, shimmering with moisture. The sun crests the horizon, turning the wet quartz of the mountain into a blinding beacon of light.\n\n6 is Flow. Ajpu is the Sun, the Hero, the Divine Hunter.\n\nYou look up at the remaining ascent. Yesterday it looked impossible. Today, in the golden light of the sun, it looks like a playground.\n\nYou begin to climb. But you are not trudging anymore; you are flowing. Your feet find the holds before you look for them. Your breath is steady. You feel a golden energy moving through your veins, matching the sun above.\n\nYou realize that you are not just a pilgrim; you are the Hero of your own story. The doubts are gone. The heaviness is gone.\n\nA figure waits for you on a ridge—a Warrior made of sunlight, holding a blowgun. He smiles. He is not here to fight you; he is here to remind you of your aim.\n\nHe points the blowgun at a distant cloud. *Thwip.* The cloud disperses.\n\n*Focus,* he says without words. *The Hero does not struggle; the Hero aligns.*\n\nYou align your will with the mountain. You move with the grace of a jaguar and the vision of an eagle. You are in the Zone.\n\nYou climb past obstacles that would have stopped you days ago. You laugh as you pull yourself up a ledge. It feels good to be in your body. It feels good to be alive. It feels good to be winning.\n\nYou reach a high, sunny meadow near the peak. You stand in the light, absorbing it. You are glowing.	You are the main character today. The energy of 6 Ajpu is pure, flowing solar power. The obstacles are melting away, and the path is lighting up. \n\nWalk with your head high. You have earned this confidence. People will be drawn to your light today, so shine it brightly. Don’t shrink back. This is your moment to be the hero of your own life. Enjoy the glow.	I am the hero of my journey, walking in the light of my own divinity.	Visualize a golden sun above your head. Let it pour liquid gold light down into your body. \n\nFeel it filling your skull, your chest, your belly, your legs. You are becoming a being of light. You are radiant. You are unstoppable.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Hero of Light", "content": "Ajpu is the nawal of the sun, the blowgunner, and the hero. It represents the divine spark within the human, the mastery of self, and the triumph of light over darkness. Ajpu is the energy of the warrior who fights for beauty and truth. Associated with the element of fire and the sun, it carries a radiant, confident, and masculine energy. It is the archetype of the artist-warrior who walks the path of holiness in everyday life. In daily life, Ajpu manifests as clarity, leadership, overcoming challenges, and the recognition of one's own divinity. Its shadow aspect can be ego, arrogance, or the testing of one's integrity. Ajpu teaches us that we are the light of the world.", "keywords": ["Divinity", "Heroism", "Sun", "Purpose", "Mastery"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Harmony", "content": "Tone 6 is the energy of flow, rhythm, and responsiveness. After the exertion of the 5, the 6 allows the energy to stabilize and find its natural groove. It is the number of ultimate balance in motion—like a surfer riding a wave or a heart beating in time. In Mayan cosmology, it is associated with the six directions (East, West, North, South, Up, Down), representing a spatial wholeness. Experientially, Tone 6 feels fluid and harmonious. It is a day where things often 'click' into place without force. While it fosters growth and family connection, its shadow can be passivity or a tendency to drift with the current rather than steering. It is the breath that connects the effort to the result.", "keywords": ["Rhythm", "Harmony", "Flow", "Balance", "Growth"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Lead a project or group with a gentle hand.", "Engage in a creative activity that brings you joy.", "Spend time in the sun to harmonize your energy.", "Practice confidence; walk with your head held high.", "Resolve a conflict by taking the high road."], "title": "Harmonious Leadership", "content": "When the fluid energy of Tone 6 meets the solar power of Ajpu, we experience a day of 'Graceful Heroism.' 6 Ajpu is the energy of the benevolent king or queen who leads with ease. Today, we do not need to fight to prove our worth; we simply need to shine. The energy is stabilizing for the ego and the spirit. It feels like a sunny day with a gentle breeze—perfect conditions for growth. 6 Ajpu supports creative expression, leadership that inspires rather than commands, and the harmonization of masculine and feminine energies. It is a day to walk your path with confidence but without rigidity. The challenge is to not become complacent in your light. The opportunity is to embody the truth that true power is effortless when it is aligned with the divine flow."}}	{"title": "The Radiant Harmonizer", "content": "To be born on 6 Ajpu is to be a person of natural charisma and balanced power. You possess a soul that shines brightly but softly. Tone 6 gives you a rhythmic, flowing nature, while Ajpu grants you the presence of the Sun Hero. You are not the warrior who crashes through the door; you are the light that fills the room. People follow you because they feel good around you. You have a natural sense of justice and beauty, often expressing your divinity through the arts or through leadership that seeks consensus.\\n\\nYour life path is one of demonstrating the grace of power. You are here to show that you can be strong without being hard. You may be drawn to the performing arts, politics, or spiritual teaching—roles where you can embody high ideals. You have a knack for being in the right place at the right time, flowing with the currents of success. You are a natural stabilizer, bringing order to chaos simply by being your authentic self.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 6 Ajpu soul is vanity or passivity. You may rely too much on your charm and avoid the hard work of character building. You might struggle to take a stand when it disrupts the harmony, preferring to keep the peace even at the cost of truth. There is a risk of identifying too much with your public image. Your lesson is to cultivate inner substance to match your outer radiance. When you do, you become a true solar force, warming the world without burning it."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#e6c863", "primary": "#171613", "secondary": "#5b422c"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#dca947", "primary": "#782b0f", "secondary": "#b05d17"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#f9f5ea", "primary": "#d8b868", "secondary": "#ebdebb"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#dcba62", "primary": "#38393b", "secondary": "#7eadbb"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.884185	2026-04-25 13:46:58.08534
148	12	5	5	Q'anil	Leaving the stable trees, you walk onto a net that is finer, shimmering with a pearlescent sheen. It looks like spider silk, delicate but incredibly strong. Suspended in this net are thousands of glass spheres, like bubbles caught in a web.\n\nThis is the Seed Bank.\n\nQ’anil is the Seed, the Star, the Rabbit. The number 5 is Work and Empowerment. Today, the net is not catching debris; it is catching potential.\n\nYou walk gently, careful not to break the spheres. Inside each one is a glowing spark—a seed of light. These are the ideas you have had, the loves you have started, the projects you have dreamed of.\n\nSome are dim, neglected. Some are bright, ready to burst.\n\nA Rabbit made of soft white light hops across the net. It stops at a dim sphere and nudges it. The sphere glows brighter.\n\nYou understand the work of the day. You must tend the seeds. You cannot just collect them; you must empower them.\n\nYou find a sphere that holds a creative dream you abandoned. It is cold. You cup your hands around it. You pour your energy (5) into the seed (Q’anil). You imagine it growing, blooming, bearing fruit.\n\nThe sphere warms up. It turns from dull grey to brilliant gold. The light spreads, illuminating the path ahead.\n\nYou realize that your "collection" is not just past burdens; it is future gardens. But a garden in a net cannot grow without attention. You must choose which seeds to water.\n\nYou spend the time touching the spheres that matter to you, waking them up. The canyon begins to glow with the light of a thousand awakened stars.	Your dreams are hungry today. They need your attention. The energy of 5 Q’anil is fertile and hardworking. Don’t just wish for things to happen; put your hand to the plow.\n\nPick one seed—one project, one desire—and give it some real energy. Water it with your time. Feed it with your focus. You will be surprised at how quickly it responds. The universe is ready to grow whatever you are willing to tend.	I empower my dreams with action and watch them bloom into abundance.	Visualize a garden. It is your life. Look at the plants. Which ones are wilting? Which ones are thriving?\n\nImagine a golden watering can in your hand. The water is liquid light. Water the plants you want to keep. Watch them turn green and vibrant. Feel the satisfaction of the gardener.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Seed of Abundance", "content": "Q'anil is the energy of the seed, the star, and the ripening crop. It represents fertility, potential, and the inevitable unfolding of life. Q'anil is the promise that what is planted with intention will grow. It carries a gentle, golden energy of nourishment and organic development. It reminds us to tend the soil and trust the process of fruition.", "keywords": ["Seed", "Fertility", "Abundance", "Growth", "Ripening"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Power", "content": "The number 5 represents empowerment, work, and the human hand. It is the energy of doing, gathering, and applying will to the structures created by the 4. 5 breaks the stability to put things into motion through effort. In this trecena, 5 represents the work required to haul in the net. It is the effort of gathering, sorting, and utilizing the resources we have connected with.", "keywords": ["Action", "Work", "Effort", "Empowerment", "Clarity"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Put extra effort into a project that is in its early stages.", "Invest money or energy into something that will grow over time.", "Work with your hands—gardening, cooking, or crafting.", "Clarify your intentions for your 'seeds' (projects/children).", "Visualize your efforts as golden light feeding the roots of your life."], "title": "Working the Harvest", "content": "5 Q'anil brings a dynamic, industrious energy to the theme of abundance. It is the day of the 'active gardener.' The potential of the seed (Q'anil) meets the work of the hand (5). This is not a day to sit back and watch the grass grow; it is a day to weed, to water, and to harvest. The gathering energy of the K'at trecena is at its most productive here. We are empowered to put effort into our dreams, knowing that the work we do today directly contributes to the future harvest. It is a fortunate day for business, for starting new projects, and for putting energy into anything you wish to see multiply."}}	{"title": "The Active Cultivator", "content": "To be born on 5 Q'anil is to be a tireless worker for abundance and beauty. You possess a unique blend of optimism and practicality. You see the potential in everything—seeds, people, ideas—but you also understand the hard work required to bring that potential to fruition. You are not a dreamer who waits for luck; you are a doer who makes your own luck. You are likely blessed with a 'green thumb,' whether literally in the garden or metaphorically in business and relationships.\\n\\nYour life path is one of productive creation. You thrive when you are busy, when you are building, planting, or nurturing. You have a natural drive to improve things and to leave the world more beautiful than you found it. You are generous and often share the fruits of your labor with your community.\\n\\nYour challenge is impatience or overwork. The 5 energy wants results now, while the Q'anil energy needs time to ripen. You may become frustrated if your seeds don't sprout overnight, or you may burn yourself out trying to force growth. Your lesson is to trust the timing of nature. When you align your industrious spirit with the patience of the seasons, you become a master of manifestation, creating a legacy of abundance that feeds the world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c2bf7e", "primary": "#161b17", "secondary": "#524d33"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.828077	2026-04-25 13:46:57.912442
16	2	3	3	Tijax					{"nawal": {"title": "The Obsidian Blade", "content": "Tijax is the double-edged obsidian knife, the nawal of discrimination, healing, and cutting away what no longer serves. It is the archetype of the spiritual warrior and the surgeon. Tijax cuts to the truth, slicing through illusion, illness, and negativity. It is an intense energy that demands integrity and alignment. In the physical realm, it governs suffering and the healing of that suffering. Tijax people are often healers, doctors, or critics—those who can see exactly where the problem lies and have the courage to excise it. In its shadow, Tijax can be gossipy, harsh, or prone to accidents and conflict. However, its highest purpose is to refine reality, carving out the beautiful sculpture from the rough stone.", "keywords": ["Healing", "Discrimination", "Truth", "Cutting", "Obsidian"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Movement", "content": "Three is the number of vibration, rhythm, and the break from duality into motion. If One is a point and Two is a line, Three is a triangle—the first stable structure, yet also an energy of dynamism. It represents the flow of communication and the spark of creativity that arises when two opposites interact. Experientially, Three feels like a surge of energy, a need to express, or a shift in the wind. It is often associated with the arts, speech, and the nervous system. The shadow of Three can be scattered energy, anxiety, or a lack of focus, like a current that is too erratic to power a machine. It asks us to move, to speak, and to let the energy flow rather than stagnate.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Rhythm", "Communication", "Creativity", "Flow"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Identify a habit that drains your energy and take one concrete step to stop it today.", "Have an honest conversation that you have been avoiding, but keep your tone calm.", "Clean or reorganize a physical space in your home to get energy moving.", "Be mindful of handling sharp objects or driving; the energy can be accident-prone.", "Visualize cutting energetic cords that attach you to past negativity."], "title": "The Dance of Radical Truth", "content": "Today, the rhythmic motion of Three propels the sharp truth of Tijax into action. This is a day of 'Active Healing' or 'Communicating Truth.' The energy is fast-moving and decisive. It is not a day to ruminate; it is a day to cut the cord, speak the difficult truth, or make the change you have been hesitating on. The Three energy prevents the Tijax blade from staying in the sheath—it wants to move, to work, to create flow by removing blockages. You might feel a sudden urge to declutter your home, end a toxic conversation, or finally book that therapy appointment. The vibration is high and perhaps a bit jagged. The challenge is to wield this blade with rhythm and grace rather than erratic slashing. Words spoken today will be sharp and penetrate deeply, so ensure they are dipped in the medicine of healing, not just the poison of anger. It is a day to surgically remove the stagnation from your life and dance in the space that opens up."}}	{"title": "The Eloquent Healer", "content": "To be born on 3 Tijax is to be a voice for truth and an agent of rapid transformation. You possess a mind that is quick, sharp, and incisive, coupled with a communicative flair that makes you hard to ignore. You are the person who says what everyone else is thinking but is afraid to voice. Your words are your scalpel, and you have the potential to be a brilliant writer, speaker, or advocate who exposes injustice and promotes healing. The number Three gives you a restlessness and a need for variety; you are likely multitalented and easily bored by routine. You move through life with a certain velocity, often bringing change wherever you go.\\n\\nYour healing capacity comes from your ability to diagnose the root cause of an issue instantly. Whether it's a structural problem in a business or an emotional blockage in a friend, you see the crack in the foundation. You are not one to sugarcoat reality, and while this honesty is your greatest gift, it can also be your social stumbling block. You are a 'truth-cutter' who dances with the blade, finding a strange kind of joy in the precision of reality.\\n\\nThe challenge for you lies in the management of your own nervous energy and the sharpness of your tongue. You may be prone to anxiety or impulsive speech that wounds rather than heals. Your life lesson is to learn the timing of the surgeon—knowing exactly when to cut and when to bandage. When you master your own intensity, you become a powerful force for liberation, using your voice to set others free from their illusions."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c09e88", "primary": "#131412", "secondary": "#4f4135"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.741436	2026-04-25 13:46:57.66477
254	20	7	7	Imox	You climb above the meadow and find a crater lake near the summit. The water is perfectly still, reflecting the sky so accurately that you can’t tell where the water ends and the air begins.\n\nThis is the Mirror of the Deep.\n\n7 is the Reflection. Imox is the Water, the Dream, the Subconscious. You have climbed high to look deep.\n\nYou stand at the edge. The air is thin and silent. You look into the water. You don’t just see your face; you see your soul. You see the dream that birthed you.\n\nYou realize that the "Prosperity" of the Tz’ikin trecena is not just about gold coins. It is about the richness of your inner world. It is about the flow of creativity from the collective ocean.\n\nA water lily opens on the surface. Inside it is not a flower, but a vision of your future. It is fluid, shifting, beautiful. It shows you that you are not a fixed object; you are a river.\n\nYou dip your hand into the cold, clear water. You splash it on your face. You are baptizing yourself in your own essence.\n\nThe reflection changes. You see yourself not as the climber, but as the mountain. You see yourself as the sky.\n\nYou sit by the lake for a long time, integrating the sun of yesterday with the water of today. Hero and Dreamer. Action and Intuition.\n\nYou are becoming whole.	The surface is calm, but the waters are deep today. The energy of 7 Imox invites you to look into the mirror of your soul. What dreams are swimming down there?\n\nDon’t be afraid of your emotions. They are the source of your creativity. Today offers a rare chance to see your feelings clearly, without getting drowned in them. Look at the reflection. It’s beautiful. It’s you.	I trust the wisdom of my feelings and see my true reflection in the waters of life.	Visualize a lake at the top of a mountain. It is night. The moon is reflecting in the water.\n\nDive into the reflection. Swim through the stars in the water. Feel the cool, healing embrace of the cosmos. You are swimming in the mind of God.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Primordial Dreamer", "content": "Imox is the nawal of the dreamer, the mystic, and the primordial waters. It represents the collective consciousness, imagination, intuition, and the subconscious ocean where creation begins. Imox is the energy of the womb and the deep psychological currents that drive us. Associated with the element of water and the color blue, it carries a fluid, chaotic, and highly creative energy. It is the archetype of the artist who pulls visions from the ether. In daily life, Imox manifests as vivid dreams, emotional sensitivity, and 'crazy' ideas. Its shadow aspect can be emotional overwhelm, disconnection from reality, or getting lost in the delusion of the mind. Imox teaches us to navigate the depths without drowning.", "keywords": ["Intuition", "Dreams", "Imagination", "Emotion", "Psychic Flow"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mystic Prism", "content": "Tone 7 is the midpoint of the 13-day cycle, sitting at the very top of the energetic pyramid. It represents the point of maximum potential, reflection, and mystical power. Unlike the stability of 4 or the flow of 6, Tone 7 is a threshold energy—neither here nor there, but encompassing both the beginning and the end. It is a day of 'no time,' where the veil between worlds is thin. Experientially, Tone 7 feels contemplative, strange, and highly intuitive. It provides a 360-degree view of reality, allowing us to see the past and future simultaneously. While it offers profound insights and the ability to channel energy, its shadow can be indecision, confusion, or getting lost in the ether. It is the mirror at the top of the mountain.", "keywords": ["Insight", "Reflection", "Mysticism", "Threshold", "Vision"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Record your dreams; they are messages from the 7th dimension.", "Spend time near the ocean or a lake to connect with the energy.", "Practice fluid, intuitive art (watercolor, dance).", "Allow yourself to 'space out' and daydream.", "Trust your gut instinct over your rational mind."], "title": "The Mystic Ocean", "content": "When the mystical peak of Tone 7 meets the deep waters of Imox, we reach a threshold of 'Panoramic Intuition.' 7 Imox is a day of seeing the dream from the highest vantage point. Standing at the top of the pyramid, we gaze into the collective unconscious and see the patterns of creation. The energy is incredibly psychic, fluid, and non-linear. It is a day where logic fails and only feeling can guide us. 7 Imox supports deep diving into the mysteries of the mind, channeling art, or connecting with water spirits. It feels like being suspended in a floatation tank—weightless and infinite. The combination invites us to embrace the chaos of the imagination as a source of wisdom. The challenge is the potential for confusion or madness; the boundaries of reality are very blurry today. The opportunity is to bring back a pearl of wisdom from the depths of the soul."}}	{"title": "The Mystic Dreamer", "content": "To be born on 7 Imox is to be a soul who lives between the worlds. You possess a psychic sensitivity and an imagination that knows no bounds. Tone 7 places you at the mystical center of the calendar, while Imox connects you to the primordial source of all creation. You are a visionary, an artist, and a natural medium. You see the world not as it is, but as it could be—or as it is in the spirit realm. You are likely the 'weird' one in your family, the one who feels things too deeply and sees things others don't.\\n\\nYour life path is one of navigating the unseen. You are here to bridge the gap between the dream and the reality. You may be drawn to the arts, psychology, or metaphysics. You have a panoramic view of the human psyche, understanding the madness and the genius that lie within us all. You are a catalyst for creativity, inspiring others to open their minds to the impossible. You are fluid, adaptable, and often enigmatic.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 7 Imox soul is grounding. You can easily drift away into fantasy or get lost in the emotional currents of the collective. You may struggle with practical life, finding it boring or harsh. There is a risk of mental instability if you do not have a strong container for your psychic energy. Your lesson is to learn to swim. When you master your sensitivity, you become a diver who can bring up treasures from the deep without drowning, enriching the world with your unique vision."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#7bd2c4", "primary": "#0f1d1b", "secondary": "#305b54"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#8cb29f", "primary": "#14281f", "secondary": "#3c6852"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#cbe5ef", "primary": "#5285ae", "secondary": "#93b7cb"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#82bdcb", "primary": "#0a3862", "secondary": "#287da1"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.884443	2026-04-25 13:46:58.087062
29	3	3	3	Iq'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Breath", "content": "Iq' is the nawal of the wind, the breath of life, and the spirit. It represents the invisible force that animates matter. Iq' is the messenger, the carrier of words, and the power of inspiration. It governs the respiratory system and the mind's agility. Iq' energy is quick, purifying, and sometimes unpredictable—like a sudden gust that clears the air. In its shadow, Iq' can manifest as anger, erratic behavior, or empty speech. However, its highest expression is the clear channel of communication between the human and the divine. It is the breath that calms the mind and the wind that spreads the seeds of change.", "keywords": ["Wind", "Breath", "Spirit", "Communication", "Inspiration"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Breath", "content": "Three is the number of movement, rhythm, and the breaking of stagnation. If One is the point and Two is the line, Three is the triangle that brings stability through motion. It represents the flow of energy, communication, and the creative spark. Three is often associated with the nervous system and the wind. Experientially, a Three day feels active, buzzing, and potentially restless. It is a day where things want to move—ideas, bodies, conversations. The shadow of Three can be scattered energy, anxiety, or a lack of focus. It asks us to express ourselves and to let the energy circulate freely.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Communication", "Rhythm", "Flow", "Expression"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Practice deep, rhythmic breathing or Pranayama exercises.", "Write freely in a journal without editing; let the words flow.", "Open the windows in your home to physically change the air.", "Have that difficult conversation, but keep your tone measured.", "Go for a run or a walk to work off the excess nervous energy."], "title": "The Winds of Change", "content": "Today, the rhythmic movement of Three amplifies the windy nature of Iq', creating a day of high-velocity energy and 'Activated Spirit.' This is a double dose of movement and air. The energy is fast, communicative, and inspiring. It is an incredible day for brainstorming, writing, speaking, or traveling. The wind is not just blowing; it has a rhythm, a beat. You might feel a surge of creative ideas or a sudden urge to express something you've been holding back. The universe is speaking loudly today, likely through synchronicities, overheard conversations, or sudden insights. The challenge is the potential for chaos. 3 Iq' can feel like a hurricane if not grounded. Anxiety levels may be high, and words can be sharp or scattered. The key is to breathe. Conscious breathing aligns you with the rhythm of the day, turning the chaotic gale into a steady, propulsive wind. Let the old stale air be blown out of your life to make room for fresh inspiration."}}	{"title": "The Voice of the Spirit", "content": "To be born on 3 Iq' is to be a messenger of the winds and a catalyst for movement. You are a person of high vibration, quick wit, and boundless curiosity. The number Three gives you a need for variety and rhythm, while Iq' connects you to the world of ideas and communication. You are likely a gifted speaker, writer, or performer—someone who uses words to shift energy. You cannot stay still for long; your soul is like the breeze, always exploring new territories and perspectives.\\n\\nYour life path is one of expression and inspiration. You are here to circulate information and energy. You may be the person who connects different groups of people or who brings new, radical ideas into a stagnant system. You have a spiritual sensitivity that allows you to 'hear' the truth in the wind, giving you flashes of insight that others miss.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is focus and grounding. You can be prone to anxiety, inconsistency, or scattering your energy in too many directions. Like a storm, you can be destructive if your power isn't channeled. Your lesson is to learn to harness your breath and your words with intention. When you do, your voice becomes a powerful instrument of healing and transformation."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a8dddd", "primary": "#0e1b1b", "secondary": "#325052"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.747382	2026-04-25 13:46:57.686801
258	20	11	11	Kan	The harvest is gathered. Now comes the final push. The path turns vertical again, winding up the spire like a snake.\n\n11 is Dissonance and Power. Kan is the Serpent and the Lightning.\n\nThe air crackles with energy. You feel a pressure in your spine, a heat rising. It is the kundalini of the mountain waking up.\n\nYou climb. It is hard. The wind is whipping now, chaotic and wild. But you are not tired. You are electrified.\n\nA giant Serpent made of lightning arcs across the sky. It strikes the peak, grounding the energy of the heavens into the earth.\n\nYou realize that true vision requires power. You cannot just see the future; you have to have the voltage to build it.\n\nYou let the energy move through you. You shed the last of your smallness. You shed the identity of the "climber." You are becoming the energy itself.\n\nYou are moving fast, scrambling up the rock, driven by an instinct that is older than thought. You are the snake shedding its skin. You are the lightning finding the ground.\n\nYou burst onto the final plateau, panting, alive, buzzing with power. The summit is just ahead.	You are a lightning rod today. The energy of 11 Kan is electric, wild, and powerful. You might feel restless or intense. That’s good. You are shedding a skin.\n\nUse this surge to break through a wall you’ve been hitting. You have the power to change everything in a moment. Don’t be afraid of your own intensity. The world needs your fire.	I channel my power with purpose and shed what limits my growth.	Visualize your spine as a rod of white light. See lightning striking the top of your head and flowing down into the earth. \n\nFeel the buzz. You are a conduit for cosmic energy. You are alive. You are powerful.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Serpent of Vitality", "content": "Kan is the nawal of the serpent, the life force, and the kundalini. It represents life energy, movement, sexuality, and wisdom. Symbol of growth through transformation and mastery of instinct. Associated with the element of fire and the colors green and red, it carries a potent, instinctual, and evolving energy. It is the archetype of the lightning bolt that connects sky and earth. In daily life, Kan manifests as physical strength, sexual attraction, athletic ability, and the drive to evolve. Its shadow aspect can be manipulation, misuse of power, anger, or being consumed by desire. Kan teaches us that our body is the vessel for the divine fire.", "keywords": ["Vitality", "Power", "Sexuality", "Growth", "Transformation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Dissolution", "content": "Tone 11 is the energy of dissonance, stripping away, and liberation. Unlike the stability of the 10, the 11 introduces a chaotic variable to test the structure. It is the 'master number' of change. Experientially, Tone 11 feels turbulent, unpredictable, and intense. It is a day where things might fall apart, but only so that what is true can remain. It acts as a filter, discarding what is no longer needed before the final ascent of the cycle. While it can bring anxiety or disruption, its higher expression is freedom and the clearing of space. It is the wind that shakes the dead leaves from the tree.", "keywords": ["Change", "Liberation", "Release", "Dissonance", "Clearing"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Move your body vigorously to release excess energy.", "Practice safe and grounded Kundalini yoga or breathwork.", "Channel your passion into a creative project.", "Let go of a physical habit that is harming you.", "Allow yourself to feel your anger, then release it constructively."], "title": "The Liberating Fire", "content": "When the chaotic force of Tone 11 meets the raw power of Kan, we experience a day of 'Explosive Evolution.' 11 Kan is the energy of the serpent shedding its skin in a violent or sudden way. It is a day of intense transformation where the life force breaks through old restrictions. The energy is unpredictable, sexual, and electric. It feels like a lightning storm or a Kundalini awakening. 11 Kan challenges us to let go of the old forms that are constricting our growth. It is a powerful day for physical breakthroughs, breaking addictions, or releasing pent-up anger. The challenge is to handle this high voltage without burning out or hurting others. The opportunity is to use this surge of power to liberate yourself from stagnation, emerging renewed and more alive than ever."}}	{"title": "The Catalyst of Vitality", "content": "To be born on 11 Kan is to be a lightning rod for transformation. You possess a spirit that is intense, powerful, and constantly evolving. Tone 11 gives you a love for freedom and change, while Kan grants you the raw life force of the Serpent. You are not here to live a quiet life; you are here to shake things up. You have a magnetic presence and a high level of physical energy. You are a catalyst, sparking change in everyone you meet.\\n\\nYour life path is one of mastering your own power. You will likely go through many sudden shifts and shed many skins in your lifetime. You may be drawn to extreme sports, intense spiritual practices, or revolutionary movements. You have a deep wisdom about the body and the instincts, often knowing things without knowing how. You are a warrior for liberation, using your vitality to break chains.\\n\\nThe challenge for an 11 Kan soul is volatility. Your energy can be overwhelming, leading to burnout, aggression, or chaotic relationships. You may struggle to find stability, always seeking the next thrill or the next transformation. There is a risk of being consumed by your own fire. Your lesson is to ground your lightning. When you learn to channel your immense power into a steady current, you become a healer and a leader who can energize the world without destroying it."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a4773d", "primary": "#0d0b08", "secondary": "#473823"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#509fb8", "primary": "#2e2366", "secondary": "#ac58c9"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#f6f4cc", "primary": "#638bd3", "secondary": "#bed6e2"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#a2cfc7", "primary": "#36464f", "secondary": "#668690"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.887142	2026-04-25 13:46:58.07164
43	4	4	4	Kame	You climb back toward the surface, expecting the city to feel the same as you left it. It doesn’t.\n\nThe twilight has deepened, but not into night. The sky hangs low and heavy, a deep plum-grey that swallows sound. Buildings rise like monuments to forgotten stories. Windows glow with faint colors that don’t reach the street. For the first time, you notice the silence between the lights.\n\nA narrow avenue opens before you, flanked by tall structures whose edges blur, as if they are dissolving or remembering how to exist. Something in the air shifts. Cold brushes the back of your neck. The city seems to inhale.\n\nYou walk forward.\n\nShadows peel from the walls, not as threats but as echoes — outlines of former selves, former choices, former lives. They move with slow, deliberate rhythm, crossing the avenue like a procession. Their forms flicker: a bowed head heavy with grief, hands cupped around an extinguished flame, a figure carrying a burden you can almost name.\n\nYou do not flee.\n\nYou recognize them.\n\nThese are the versions of you that didn’t survive certain moments. The ones who stayed behind at old crossroads. The ones who held memories too heavy to carry further.\n\nOne shadow pauses in front of you. It holds out its hands. Within them lies a faint ember, the smallest glow, still warm. A remnant of a dream that died, or a hope you believed was lost.\n\nThe ember pulses once.\n\nYou feel a squeeze in your chest — the grief you never had time to process, the endings you rushed past, the goodbyes you softened with distraction. The city around you stills, giving you room to feel.\n\nWhen you reach out and cup the ember, the shadow dissolves, not erased but freed. You hold the glow carefully. It is fragile, yes, but it is also honest. It asks nothing from you except acknowledgment.\n\nFar down the avenue, other silhouettes fade through walls, leaving behind trails of cool violet light. You realize the city is not trying to haunt you. It is helping you carry your dead.\n\nNot the literal ones — the emotional endings, the identities shed, the pieces of you that served their purpose and now wait to be honored.\n\nYou close your hands around the ember. It brightens, a soft violet-gold pulse against your palms.\n\nFor the first time, you understand that grief is not meant to be a collapsing. It is a doorway.\n\nAnd today, the city lets you walk through it with the light of your own endings guiding the path ahead.	Something old rises today, not to haunt you but to be witnessed. You may feel memories surfacing, or emotions you thought were finished returning with new clarity. This is not regression. It is integration.\n\nWhen the past speaks, listen with compassion. Not everything needs to be fixed. Some things simply need to be acknowledged before they can settle into their rightful place.\n\nLet yourself grieve gently. Let yourself release gently. Allow something small — a memory, a dream, an old version of yourself — to be honored instead of ignored.\n\nThis is a day for courage, but not the loud kind. The quiet kind. The steady kind. The kind that lets you feel without falling apart.	I honor what has ended and let its light guide me toward renewed purpose.	Sit comfortably and close your eyes. Imagine you are standing in a quiet avenue of the twilight city. The buildings on either side appear slightly blurred, as if dissolving into memory.\n\nShadows begin to cross the street — gentle silhouettes of past versions of yourself. Notice how they move slowly, peacefully, carrying no threat. One approaches with hands extended, holding a small ember of soft violet-gold light.\n\nVisualize yourself cupping your hands beneath theirs. Feel the warmth of the ember settle into your palms. This ember represents an ending you never fully faced, a part of your story that deserves acknowledgment.\n\nHold it gently. Breathe. With each inhale, feel the ember brighten. With each exhale, feel the tension around that memory loosen.\n\nOffer quiet gratitude to the ancestors who walk with you through transformation. When you are ready, watch the remaining shadows fade through the buildings, leaving faint trails of violet light.\n\nOpen your eyes slowly, carrying the warmth of the ember with you.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Transformer", "content": "Kame is the nawal of death, rebirth, and the ancestors. It represents the dimensional door between worlds and the cycle of transformation. Kame is the compost that feeds the flower. It governs spiritual initiation, facing fears, and the peace of surrender. In its shadow, Kame can be fearful, morbid, or clinging to the past. Its highest expression is the courage to let go in order to be reborn.", "keywords": ["Death", "Rebirth", "Ancestors", "Transformation", "Surrender"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cube of Stability", "content": "Four is the number of stability, foundation, and the physical plane. It represents the four directions and the four pillars that uphold the sky. After the movement of Three, Four brings the energy back to earth to be grounded. It is the energy of structure, order, and definition. Experientially, a Four day feels solid and practical. It is a time to build and organize. The shadow of Four can be rigidity or stubbornness. It asks us to create a stable container for our lives.", "keywords": ["Stability", "Structure", "Foundation", "Order", "Grounding"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create or tend to an ancestor altar in your home.", "Reflect on the 'foundations' of your life—what needs to die to make them stronger?", "Visit a cemetery or a place of memory with gratitude, not fear.", "Clean the corners of your home to move stagnant energy.", "Meditate on the earth as the ultimate transformer of energy."], "title": "Stabilizing Transformation", "content": "When the structural stability of Four meets the transformative power of Kame, we have a day of 'Grounded Change' or 'Ancestral Foundation.' Transformation can often feel chaotic, but today offers a stable container for it. It is a day to build a relationship with the cycles of life and death in a practical way. The Four grounds the ethereal energy of Kame, making it safer to explore deep emotions or ancestral patterns. It is an excellent day for setting up an altar, organizing family records, or making a will—practical acts that honor the cycle of life. The energy is quiet, strong, and profound. The challenge is resistance; the Four can sometimes try to 'box in' the change that Kame demands. Don't build a wall to keep change out; build a hearth to welcome it in. Trust that the ground will hold you even as the form shifts."}}	{"title": "The Anchor of Spirit", "content": "To be born on 4 Kame is to be a stabilizer in times of crisis. You possess a rare ability to remain calm and grounded in the face of death, change, and transformation. The number Four gives you a love for structure and tradition, while Kame connects you to the deep mysteries of the soul. You are likely the 'rock' your family leans on during hard times. You have a natural respect for the past and may be the keeper of family history or lineage.\\n\\nYour life path involves bridging the physical and spiritual worlds in a practical way. You may be drawn to hospice work, psychology, history, or archaeology. You are not afraid of the dark; you understand that it is simply part of the foundation of life. Your challenge is to not become too rigid or heavy. You can carry the weight of the ancestors on your shoulders. Your lesson is to build structures that allow for flow, remembering that true stability comes from the ability to adapt to the inevitable changes of life."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d1c7c7", "primary": "#131a1b", "secondary": "#4c4a4f"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#a46e9d", "primary": "#20295f", "secondary": "#473d93"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#ca7866", "primary": "#130f3d", "secondary": "#5b2863"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#5a546b", "primary": "#1d202f", "secondary": "#313348"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.757186	2026-04-25 13:46:57.710273
149	12	6	6	Toj	The Seed Bank fades into a section of the canyon where the nets form a series of cascading waterfalls—not of water, but of coins, beads, and shells. They flow down the ropes with a tinkling, melodic sound, gathering in suspended pools before overflowing to the next level.\n\nThis is the River of Reciprocity.\n\n6 is Flow. Toj is Offering. The lesson here is circulation.\n\nYou watch the flow. The nets catch the abundance, hold it for a moment, and then release it to the net below. If a net tried to hold onto the coins forever, it would break under the weight.\n\nYou realize that the "Gathering" of K’at is not meant to be static. You gather so you can give.\n\nA figure stands by the flow—a woman woven from the water of the river. She holds a bowl. She dips it into the stream, drinks, and then pours the rest back in.\n\nShe looks at you. "The debt is paid," she whispers. "The flow is open."\n\nYou look at your own collection. You find a bundle of "Talent" you have been hoarding, afraid to share it. You find a bundle of "Love" you have been saving for the right moment.\n\nYou toss them into the river. They dissolve into the stream, increasing the flow. You feel a surge of joy. By giving, you have become part of the river.\n\nThe canyon sings with the sound of movement. You are no longer heavy. You are a conduit.	Let it flow. Money, love, energy, time—don’t hoard it today. The energy of 6 Toj is a river of reciprocity. If you hold on too tight, you block the fresh water from coming in.\n\nTrust that there is enough. Give freely, and receive freely. The universe loves a vacuum; if you empty your hands, they will be filled again. Be a conduit, not a dam.	I allow abundance to flow through me, giving and receiving with ease.	Visualize yourself as a riverbed. Water flows through you. It brings leaves, gold dust, and life.\n\nDon’t try to catch the water. Just feel it moving. Feel how it cleans you. Feel how it feeds the ocean. You are the channel.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Fire", "content": "Toj is the energy of offering, payment, and reciprocity. It is the sacred fire that transmutes matter into spirit. Toj represents the law of karma and the necessity of giving back to maintain balance. It is the day to pay spiritual debts and offer gratitude. It reminds us that everything we gather (K'at) requires an exchange.", "keywords": ["Offering", "Payment", "Reciprocity", "Gratitude", "Fire"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Stability", "content": "The number 6 represents ultimate stability, flow, and vitality. It brings balance to the work of the 5, facilitating responsiveness and organic growth. It is associated with the heart of the sky and earth in alignment. In the K'at trecena, 6 brings a harmonious flow to our connections. It eases the tension of the net, allowing resources to flow to us with grace rather than struggle.", "keywords": ["Flow", "Harmony", "Stability", "Vitality", "Balance"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Make an offering to the elements with a sense of joy, not obligation.", "Donate to a cause that helps restore balance in the world.", "Practice 'flow' in your finances; pay a bill with gratitude.", "Gather with family or community around a fire or a meal.", "Thank the universe for what you have gathered so far."], "title": "The Harmony of Giving", "content": "6 Toj is a day of beautiful, flowing reciprocity. The stability of the 6 combines with the offering energy of Toj to create a sense of ease in paying our debts. Today, the 'net' is balanced through gratitude. We realize that the more we give, the more we are able to receive. It is a day where offering doesn't feel like a sacrifice; it feels like a natural part of the cycle. Relationships are healed through mutual service, and old karmic knots are untied with the gentle hands of forgiveness. The energy is warm, fluid, and deeply healing for the heart."}}	{"title": "The Harmonious Giver", "content": "To be born on 6 Toj is to be a natural philanthropist of the spirit. You possess a warm, radiant energy that draws people to your hearth. You understand instinctively that life is a flow of giving and receiving, and you are often the one who keeps that flow moving in your family or community. You are not just generous with material things, but with your time, your attention, and your love. You are a stabilizer, someone who brings harmony to chaotic situations through the power of gratitude.\\n\\nYour life path is one of service and balance. You may be drawn to healing professions, social work, or any role where you can help others find equilibrium. You have a deep sense of duty, but it is carried lightly, with grace. You are likely very connected to family and tradition, understanding the importance of honoring those who came before.\\n\\nYour challenge is to ensure you are included in the circle of giving. You can sometimes give so much that you deplete your own vitality, or you may struggle to receive help when you need it. Your lesson is to treat yourself as a worthy recipient of the offering. When you balance your outpouring of love with self-care, you become a sustainable source of light, teaching others the true joy of reciprocity."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#bea380", "primary": "#111a19", "secondary": "#4f4941"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.828647	2026-04-25 13:46:57.913485
17	2	4	4	Kawoq					{"nawal": {"title": "The Storm of Compassion", "content": "Kawoq is the energy of the storm, the midwife, and the community. It represents the gathering of clouds, the thunder that precedes the rain, and the breaking of waters at birth. Kawoq is a feminine energy, powerful and cleansing, focused on the well-being of the collective and the family. It is the force that pushes us through the birth canal of transformation. While it can be turbulent, its intent is always to bring new life and abundance. Kawoq governs the home, the hearth, and the circle of community. In its shadow, it can manifest as emotional overwhelm, intrusiveness, or the chaos of a storm that destroys rather than waters. Its highest expression is the compassionate warmth of the heated stones in the sweat lodge.", "keywords": ["Storm", "Midwife", "Community", "Compassion", "Abundance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cube of Stability", "content": "Four is the number of stability, form, and the physical plane. It represents the four directions (East, West, North, South), the four elements, and the four pillars that hold up the sky. After the movement of Three, Four brings things back to earth to be grounded and tested. It is the energy of definition, boundaries, and foundation. Experientially, a Four day feels solid, reliable, and practical. It is a time to work, to build, and to organize. The shadow of Four can be rigidity, stubbornness, or a feeling of being 'boxed in.' It asks us to create a container for our spirit, ensuring that our dreams have a sturdy place to land.", "keywords": ["Stability", "Structure", "Foundation", "Four Directions", "Order"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Clean and declutter your living space to honor the energy of the home.", "Host a small gathering or dinner for close family or friends.", "Check on the 'foundations' of your life—finances, health, basic needs.", "Practice patience; allow processes to unfold within their own safe container.", "Visualize a golden cube of light protecting your home and loved ones."], "title": "Building the Sanctuary", "content": "When the structural stability of Four meets the compassionate storm of Kawoq, the result is an energy of 'Protected Transformation' or 'Sanctuary Building.' Today is about creating a safe, solid container for feelings, family, and community. It is the perfect day to work on your home, not just physically, but energetically—making it a fortress of peace. The Four stabilizes the volatility of the Kawoq storm, turning a potential flood into a well-managed irrigation system. This combination favors practical acts of care: cooking a meal for loved ones, fixing a leak, or organizing community resources. It suggests that true abundance requires a strong vessel to hold it. The challenge is to balance the need for order with the flow of emotion; do not build walls so thick that they keep love out. Instead, build a hearth where the fire can burn safely. Trust that the structures you reinforce today will support the new life that is trying to be born."}}	{"title": "The Guardian of the Hearth", "content": "To be born on 4 Kawoq is to be a pillar of the community and a builder of safe havens. You possess a nurturing spirit that is grounded in practical action. You are likely the 'rock' of your family, the one who provides both the shoulder to cry on and the roof over everyone's head. The number Four gives you a deep love for stability, tradition, and order, while Kawoq fills you with empathy and a drive to care for the collective. You are not a solitary creature; you thrive when you are responsible for the well-being of a group, whether that is a large family, a team, or a neighborhood.\\n\\nYour approach to life is maternal (regardless of gender) and architectural. You want to build systems of care that last. You might be drawn to professions in social work, housing, nursing, or community planning. You understand that love is not just a feeling, but a structure—it requires reliable presence and tangible support. People feel safe around you because you exude a sense of permanence and protection. You are the calm eye within the storm, capable of holding space for intense emotions without being toppled by them.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is the tendency to over-give or to become rigid in your role as the protector. You may struggle to let others take care of themselves, feeling that the roof will collapse if you aren't holding it up. Your lesson is to build structures that are flexible enough to allow for growth and to remember that you, too, deserve a place of sanctuary. You are here to demonstrate that the strongest foundation is one built on compassion."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#cbb4c2", "primary": "#1a1819", "secondary": "#735761"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.74226	2026-04-25 13:46:57.667595
19	2	6	6	Imox					{"nawal": {"title": "The Dream of the Waters", "content": "Imox is the nawal of the primordial ocean, the collective unconscious, and the dream world. It represents the water that connects all things—the rain, the rivers, the blood in our veins. Imox is the source of all creativity, but it is also the realm of madness and illusion. It is the energy of the 'crazies,' the visionaries, and the empaths. Imox governs the psyche and the hidden currents of emotion. In its aligned state, it is the fountain of artistic genius and psychic intuition. In its shadow, it can be a drowning pool of confusion, paranoia, or emotional instability. It asks us to navigate the depths without losing our breath.", "keywords": ["Water", "Dreams", "Intuition", "Collective", "Madness/Genius"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Harmony", "content": "Six is the number of flow, responsiveness, and organic stability. It represents the point where the initial effort stabilizes and begins to find its rhythm. In Mayan cosmology, Six is often associated with the Heart of the Sky and the Heart of the Earth connecting. It is a number of family, physical vitality, and the natural flow of life events. Experientially, a Six day feels smoother than the previous days; obstacles tend to dissolve if you stop pushing and start flowing. It is a time for acceptance and alignment. The shadow of Six can be passivity or a lack of direction, drifting too much with the current. It teaches us to trust the process and move with the Tao of the moment.", "keywords": ["Flow", "Harmony", "Vitality", "Responsiveness", "Connection"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Spend time near a body of water, or take a long mindful bath.", "Keep a dream journal next to your bed; messages are likely to come in sleep.", "Engage in free-flow creative activities like painting or dancing without a plan.", "Practice energetic shielding if you are in crowded places.", "Drink plenty of water to honor the element of the day."], "title": "Navigating the Emotional Tide", "content": "As the harmonious flow of Six meets the watery depths of Imox, we enter a day of 'Fluid Intuition' or 'Emotional Flow.' The energy today is incredibly psychic and permeable. The boundaries between you and the world, or between reality and dream, may feel thin. This is a beautiful energy for artists, healers, and lovers, as it allows for a deep, wordless connection. The Six helps to stabilize the potentially chaotic waters of Imox, making this a safer day than usual to explore your subconscious. You may feel a strong pull toward water, music, or meditation. The challenge is to not get swept away by the collective emotional tide. You might pick up on feelings that aren't yours. The key is to let them flow *through* you, not get stuck *in* you. Trust your gut feelings today; your logic may be foggy, but your intuition is flowing like a clear river."}}	{"title": "The Intuitive Flow", "content": "To be born on 6 Imox is to be a vessel for the collective dream and a master of emotional currents. You possess a soul that is deeply connected to the invisible realms. You are likely an empath, feeling the moods of a room the moment you walk in. The number Six gives you a natural grace and an ability to navigate these waters with relative stability, preventing you from drowning in the depths that might overwhelm others. You are a natural healer or therapist, intuitively knowing what others need before they speak it. Your creativity is boundless, often springing from a source you can't explain—you are a channel for the muse.\\n\\nYour life path is one of bringing the formless into form. You may struggle with the rigid structures of the 'real world'—schedules, deadlines, and dry logic are foreign languages to you. You thrive in environments that allow for fluidity and feeling. You are the friend who listens without judgment, the artist who paints the soul, the dreamer who reminds us that reality is malleable. People are drawn to your soothing, watery presence.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is maintaining your own boundaries. Because you are so porous, you can easily become a psychic sponge for the world's pain. You may also struggle with 'Imox madness'—a sense of confusion or ungroundedness when you lose touch with the shore. Your lesson is to learn to be the riverbed as well as the water—to contain your own flow so that it can be directed toward healing and creation rather than dissipation. You are here to teach the world to trust the unseen."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#80cebd", "primary": "#0e1c1a", "secondary": "#2c5752"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.742991	2026-04-25 13:46:57.670682
62	5	10	10	Ajpu					{"nawal": {"title": "The Solar Hero", "content": "Ajpu is the Nawal of the Sun, the blowgunner, and the spiritual warrior. It represents the divine spark within the human being—the light that conquers darkness. Ajpu is the energy of leadership, clarity, and the hero's journey. It governs the search for truth and the overcoming of obstacles through certainty and skill. In human experience, Ajpu manifests as confidence, artistic talent, and a connection to the divine. It is the face of the sun shining on the path. When aligned, Ajpu brings success, enlightenment, and the ability to lead by example; when misaligned, it can lead to ego, perfectionism, or judgment. It is the light that refuses to be hidden.", "keywords": ["Sun", "Hero", "Divinity", "Purpose", "Leadership"]}, "number": {"title": "The Peak of Manifestation", "content": "The number Ten represents the manifestation of the intent. It is the two hands coming together (5+5) to finalize the creation. In Mayan cosmology, Ten is the energy of community agreement, collaboration, and the realization of the project. Experientially, this energy feels solid, accomplished, and social. It is the moment when the house is built and we invite the neighbors in. The shadow of Ten can be over-responsibility or the burden of maintenance, but its light is the satisfaction of seeing your dreams take physical form. Today, the universe says: 'It is done.'", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Collaboration", "Realization", "Mastery"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Share your creative work or ideas publicly; the audience is receptive.", "Take a leadership role in a group setting.", "Connect with the sun (literally); feel its light on your face.", "Acknowledge your achievements; give yourself credit for how far you've come.", "Use your influence to uplift others; true heroes serve the whole."], "title": "Realized Divinity", "content": "The manifestation power of Tone 10 combines with the solar brilliance of Ajpu to create a day of 'Shining Achievement.' 10 Ajpu is a day of victory. It represents the moment the hero returns from the journey, transformed and ready to share their light with the community. The energy is bright, confident, and highly creative. It is an excellent day to showcase your work, perform, lead a meeting, or simply stand tall in your truth. The doubt of previous days burns away in the noon sun of 10 Ajpu. You are asked to own your gifts and to take responsibility for your role as a co-creator of reality. It is a day to walk with your head high, not in arrogance, but in the quiet knowledge of your own divinity. The world is looking for light today—be the one who provides it."}}	{"title": "The Manifested Light", "content": "To be born on 10 Ajpu is to walk the earth as a beacon of realized potential. You are the 'Solar Achiever'—someone who is destined to shine and to bring projects, ideas, and people into their highest form. You possess a natural magnetism and a confidence that seems to come from a deep, internal source. People look to you for direction and inspiration. You are not just a dreamer; with the energy of the number 10, you are a finisher. You have the grit to take the hero's journey all the way to the end.\\n\\nYour life path is one of overcoming challenges to prove the triumph of the spirit. You are likely artistic, athletic, or a leader in your field, driven by a desire for excellence. You hold yourself to high standards and expect the same from others. Your challenge is to ensure that your pursuit of perfection does not isolate you or turn into ego; remember that the sun shines on everyone equally. You are here to show us that the divine is not far away—it is right here, in the work of our hands and the light of our eyes."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d7c086", "primary": "#121916", "secondary": "#544a39"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.771396	2026-04-25 13:46:57.726718
27	3	1	1	Ajpu					{"nawal": {"title": "The Solar Hero", "content": "Ajpu is the nawal of the Sun, the blowgunner, and the spiritual warrior. It represents the light of divinity that resides within the human form and the quest for higher consciousness. Ajpu is the archetype of the hero twins from the Popol Vuh who descend into the underworld to defeat the lords of death through wit, art, and resilience. It governs leadership, performance, and the clarity of vision. Ajpu energy is radiant, confident, and triumphant—it is the hunter who aims true. In its shadow, Ajpu can manifest as arrogance, perfectionism, or a need for constant validation. However, its true essence is the humble recognition of one's own divinity and the courage to shine that light into the world.", "keywords": ["Sun", "Hero", "Divinity", "Purpose", "Courage"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Fire", "content": "One is the number of new beginnings, unity, and the initial spark of creation. It represents the potential of the seed that contains the entire forest within its shell. In the Mayan cosmology, One is the focused intent that precedes all action—the moment the arrow is notched but not yet released. It is a day of singularity, where the energy is concentrated and potent. Experientially, the number One feels like a fresh start or a sudden clarity of purpose. It is the 'I Am' presence, standing alone but connected to the source. The shadow of One can be isolation or a lack of momentum if the will is not engaged. It asks us to define our direction and plant the intention for the cycle ahead with absolute precision.", "keywords": ["Unity", "Beginnings", "Potential", "Focus", "Initiation"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Set a clear, noble intention for the 13-day cycle.", "Stand in the direct sunlight for a few minutes to absorb the solar code.", "Identify one area of your life where you have been playing small and decide to step up.", "Wear gold or yellow to align with the frequency of the sun.", "Meditate on the image of a hunter aiming at a target; what is your target?"], "title": "Initiating the Hero's Journey", "content": "The convergence of the initiating force of One with the solar power of Ajpu marks the beginning of the Hero's Journey. Today is the 'Seed of Divinity.' It is a day to remember who you really are—a spiritual being having a human experience—and to commit to walking your path with nobility and courage. The energy is vibrant, optimistic, and deeply empowering. It asks you to step into the center of your own life and claim your sovereignty. Unlike other beginnings that might be tentative, 1 Ajpu is bold; it is the sun rising over the horizon, chasing away the shadows of doubt. You are being asked to set a high intention for the next 13 days: What mountain are you ready to climb? What truth are you ready to embody? The challenge is to stand in this light without being blinded by your own ego. True heroism is service to the light, not ownership of it. Stand tall, aim high, and let the journey begin."}}	{"title": "The Solar Initiator", "content": "To be born on 1 Ajpu is to be a pioneer of light and a natural-born leader. You possess the concentrated power of the number One combined with the radiant charisma of the Sun. You are a self-starter, often preferring to forge your own path rather than follow others. Your soul carries the archetype of the 'First Hero'—the one who is willing to go first, to take the risk, and to light the way for others. You have a strong sense of personal destiny and a belief that you are here for a specific, higher purpose. People are drawn to your confidence and your innate nobility; you carry yourself with a dignity that commands respect.\\n\\nYour life path is one of self-discovery and the manifestation of your divine potential. You are likely drawn to the arts, athletics, or leadership roles where you can shine and inspire. However, your journey is not just about external success; it is about the internal victory over fear and darkness. You are a warrior of the spirit, constantly testing your own limits to see how high you can fly.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is the trap of the ego. Because you shine so brightly, you can sometimes become isolated or arrogant, believing you must do everything alone. Your lesson is to realize that true leadership is empowering others to find their own inner sun. You are here to remind the world that divinity is not something to be sought outside, but a flame to be kindled within."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d3b776", "primary": "#0f1615", "secondary": "#443e34"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.74675	2026-04-25 13:46:57.678001
36	3	10	10	Toj					{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Fire", "content": "Toj is the nawal of offering, payment, and the sacred fire. It represents the law of cause and effect (karma) and the need for balance through giving back. Toj is the energy of gratitude expressed through action. It governs the payment of spiritual and physical debts. In its shadow, Toj can manifest as suffering, sickness (the body demanding payment), or a victim mentality. Its highest expression is the joy of service—giving freely to the fire of life to maintain the equilibrium of the cosmos.", "keywords": ["Offering", "Payment", "Fire", "Gratitude", "Balance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Manifestation", "content": "Ten is the number of manifestation, responsibility, and community agreement. It represents the two hands clasping together—collaboration and results. Ten is where the intention of One and the work of Five come to fruition in the physical world. It is a solid, authoritative number. Experientially, a Ten day feels accomplished and 'real.' It is a day where things land. The shadow of Ten can be the burden of responsibility or judgment. It asks us to own our creations.", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Collaboration", "Fruition", "Authority"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Make a donation to a cause you believe in.", "Pay a bill with a feeling of gratitude for the service received.", "Light a fire or a candle and offer tobacco, sugar, or prayers.", "Do a favor for a neighbor or colleague without being asked.", "Reflect on what you are 'indebted' to (ancestors, earth) and say thank you."], "title": "Manifesting Gratitude", "content": "When the manifesting power of Ten meets the sacrificial fire of Toj, we have a day of 'Community Offering' or 'Tangible Gratitude.' This is a very strong day for settling debts—financial, energetic, or emotional. The Ten brings the capacity to actually pay what is owed and to see the results of that clearing. It is also a day where your service to others manifests visible rewards. If you have been giving without expectation, 10 Toj is often when the universe balances the books in your favor. The energy is communal and warm. It is a perfect day for a group ceremony, a charity event, or simply buying lunch for a friend. The challenge is to give from a place of power (Ten) rather than obligation. Do not martyr yourself. True offering strengthens the giver as much as the receiver. Make your life an offering today, and watch how the world responds with abundance."}}	{"title": "The Community Servant", "content": "To be born on 10 Toj is to be a pillar of generosity and a keeper of the balance. You have a deep sense of responsibility towards your community and a natural understanding of the law of reciprocity. The number Ten gives you the ability to organize and manifest, while Toj fills you with a desire to serve and to give back. You are likely the first to volunteer, the one who organizes the fundraiser, or the person who quietly takes care of the family's needs. You understand that true wealth circulates.\\n\\nYour life path is one of clearing karma—for yourself and your lineage. You may face challenges that feel like 'payments,' but your resilience turns them into offerings. You are a spiritual banker, instinctively knowing how to balance the energetic books. Your challenge is burnout. You can give until you are empty if you aren't careful. Your lesson is to learn that receiving is also part of the cycle. When you allow yourself to be supported, you become an even more powerful vessel for the sacred fire."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c69874", "primary": "#111413", "secondary": "#50403a"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.749808	2026-04-25 13:46:57.680081
39	3	13	13	E'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Path of Destiny", "content": "E' is the nawal of the path, the road, and the journey. It represents the tooth (wisdom) and the destination. E' is the energy of the traveler, the explorer, and the guide. It governs the physical road as well as the spiritual path (the Dao). E' energy is restless, curious, and forward-moving. In its shadow, E' can manifest as aimless wandering, inability to commit, or getting lost. Its highest expression is the conscious pilgrim who walks the path with purpose, knowing that the journey itself is the destination.", "keywords": ["Path", "Journey", "Road", "Exploration", "Destiny"]}, "number": {"title": "The Light of Ascension", "content": "Thirteen is the number of completion, ascension, and the spirit world. It represents the final step in the trecena cycle—the return to source at a higher level. Thirteen is the number of the ancestors and the 'invisible army' of support. Experientially, a Thirteen day feels mystical, thin-veiled, and sometimes surreal. It is a day of wrapping up and letting go. The shadow of Thirteen can be ungroundedness. It asks us to celebrate the journey and harvest the wisdom.", "keywords": ["Completion", "Ascension", "Spirit", "Ancestors", "Renewal"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Take a long, conscious walk without a destination.", "Visualize your life path as a golden road stretching into the stars.", "Thank your feet for carrying you this far; give them a massage.", "Ask your ancestors for a sign regarding your next step.", "Write a summary of the 'hero's journey' you have lived these last 13 days."], "title": "Ascending the Path", "content": "We reach the culmination of the Ajpu trecena with 13 E'—the 'Ascended Path' or the 'Spiritual Journey.' The hero's journey that began on 1 Ajpu now completes its cycle. We have walked the road, faced the challenges, and now we stand at the threshold of a new level. Today is a day of profound realization about your life's direction. You may feel a strong connection to your destiny—a sense that you are exactly where you are meant to be, even if the road has been rocky. The Thirteen brings the ancestors close to walk beside you. It is a perfect day for a pilgrimage, a long walk, or a meditation on your future path. The energy is light, expansive, and full of movement. The challenge is to not rush into the next thing too quickly. Pause at this milestone. Look back at how far you have come. Honor the road under your feet. You are not just walking; you are ascending."}}	{"title": "The Cosmic Traveler", "content": "To be born on 13 E' is to be a pilgrim of the stars. You possess a restless, adventurous spirit that is always seeking the next horizon. The number Thirteen connects you to the spirit world and the ancestors, making your journey feel guided by invisible hands. E' makes you a natural explorer—of lands, of ideas, and of consciousness. You are likely someone who cannot stay in one place (physically or mentally) for too long; you need movement to feel alive. You are a guide for others, helping them find their way when they are lost.\\n\\nYour life path is the path itself. You are not result-oriented; you are experience-oriented. You gather wisdom through your travels and trials. Your challenge is grounding. You can be so focused on the 'there' that you miss the 'here.' You may also struggle with commitment. Your lesson is to realize that the ultimate destination is within. When you find your internal compass, your external wandering becomes a sacred pilgrimage, and every step becomes a prayer."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c5d5be", "primary": "#101c1a", "secondary": "#3f5b54"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.751027	2026-04-25 13:46:57.683896
89	7	11	11	B'atz'	The path feels lighter today, almost playful.\n\nThere’s a quickness in your step that you didn’t choose—something in the air tugs at you with quiet excitement, as if the forest can hardly wait for you to arrive. Sunlight flickers through the leaves in weaving patterns, braiding shadow and glow into shifting designs that dance across your hands.\n\nBy the time you reach the lake, the world is already in motion.\n\nThreads of light rise from the water—hundreds of them, thin and shimmering, drifting upward like strands of silk caught in a rising breeze. Some spiral gently, some arc in sweeping curves, some twist together before drifting apart again.\n\nThey do not feel random.\n\nYou step closer, and the threads react, brightening, gathering, rearranging themselves around you like friendly, curious companions. The lake beneath them is calm, but the air above it is alive, pulsing with creative electricity.\n\nWithout thinking, you lift your hand.\n\nA thread drifts close and wraps softly around your fingers—warm, weightless, impossibly delicate. The moment it touches you, something inside you sharpens: a memory, a vision, a forgotten idea, a half-formed dream. Another thread drifts close, brushing your arm with a color you don’t have a name for. A dozen images flash behind your eyes: stories you’ve told, stories you’ve abandoned, stories you haven’t yet dared to imagine.\n\nThe threads begin weaving themselves.\n\nNot into fabric, not into rope—into a living tapestry suspended in the air: a shifting map of your experiences, your desires, your mistakes, your brilliance. Every moment of your life, even the ones you once thought meaningless, glimmer here as part of the pattern.\n\nFor a moment, you feel overwhelmed. The motion is chaotic, spiraling, unpredictable. But as you keep watching, a strange truth emerges:\n\nThe chaos has rhythm.\n\nThe randomness has intention.\n\nThe threads loop and braid and scatter, but somehow everything is connected. Your life has never been a straight line—it has always been a weave, and every thread has belonged.\n\nYou reach out again, gently.\n\nThis time, when your fingers brush the nearest strand, you feel something different—not memory or idea, but freedom. Permission to create without perfection. Permission to improvise. Permission to be unfinished.\n\nA laugh escapes you—small, surprised, real. The threads respond instantly, flaring with brighter color before spiraling upward into the sky like joyful sparks.\n\nWhen they fade, the air hums with quiet afterglow.\n\nYou understand: today is not about control. It is about creation. About trusting the threads that pull you. About letting your genius move without needing to justify itself.\n\nAs you leave the lake, you notice a single shimmering thread wrapped softly around your wrist. It dissolves the moment you look at it, but the warmth remains.\n\nYou walk back carrying a new, vibrant truth:\n\nYour path is not something you follow.\n\nIt is something you weave.	Today brings creative lightning.\n\nYou may feel restless, inspired, nostalgic, energized—sometimes all at once. This is not a day to force discipline or rigid plans. It is a day to follow the thread: the idea that sparks, the memory that glows, the small joy that wants your attention.\n\nLet your mind wander with purpose. Let your creativity be messy and true. Trust that the connections forming today are meaningful, even if they don’t make sense yet. A new pattern is weaving itself through your life.	I follow the thread of inspiration and allow my creativity to flow freely, joyfully, and without perfection.	Sit comfortably and imagine a single shimmering thread floating before you. With every inhale, see it brighten; with every exhale, see another thread join it. Let them form a small, shifting tapestry—your experiences woven into light.\n\nAsk yourself: “What thread wants my attention today?” Allow an image, word, or feeling to appear.\n\nHonor it. Follow it. Let it guide your steps.\n\nOffer thanks to the ancient weavers and artists who understood that life is created, not controlled.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Weaver of Time", "content": "B'atz' is the Nawal of the thread, the weaver, and the continuous unfolding of time itself. It represents the creative life force that spins the universe into existence. As the archetype of the artist and the organizer, B'atz' governs all forms of creative expression and the planning of time. In human experience, it manifests as the urge to create, to connect, and to celebrate. It is the thread of destiny. When aligned, B'atz' brings flow and beauty; when misaligned, it can lead to feeling tangled or anxious.", "keywords": ["Creativity", "Weaving", "Time", "Artistry", "Thread"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Change", "content": "The number Eleven represents dissonance, resolution through change, and the stripping away of the non-essential. In Mayan cosmology, Eleven is a high-frequency energy that shakes the foundation to test its strength. It is not necessarily negative, but it is turbulent. Experientially, this energy feels like a strong wind or a sudden shift in plans. It breaks the static perfection of Ten to allow for higher growth. The shadow of Eleven can be chaos, but its light is liberation and the clearing of the path.", "keywords": ["Change", "Liberation", "Dissonance", "Clearing", "Transformation"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Let go of your rigid schedule; allow spontaneity.", "Experiment with a new artistic medium or method.", "If a plan falls apart, look for the freedom in the rubble.", "Re-evaluate how you spend your time; cut out the non-essential.", "Trust the process of unweaving; it is part of creation."], "title": "Unraveling to Reweave", "content": "The turbulent energy of Tone 11 meets the weaving power of B'atz' to create a day of 'Creative Chaos.' 11 B'atz' is the energy of the artist who decides to scrap the painting and start over. It represents the unraveling of old patterns so that a new, more beautiful design can be woven. This can feel unsettling, as B'atz' usually likes order, but 11 demands change. Today, allow your plans to be disrupted. If a thread snaps, don't panic; it was meant to break. This is a powerful day for improvisation, for jazz, for art that breaks the rules. The energy asks you to be flexible with your time and your creativity. You are being liberated from a pattern that was too small for you. Let the design change. The new tapestry that emerges from this chaos will be far more vibrant than the one you planned."}}	{"title": "The Innovative Weaver", "content": "To be born on 11 B'atz' is to be a revolutionary artist of life. You are the 'Weaver of Change'—a soul who knows the rules of time and creation well enough to break them beautifully. You are likely highly creative, with a mind that sees connections others miss. You don't just follow the pattern handed down by tradition; you invent new knots, new colors, new designs. Your life is a work of art in constant flux.\\n\\nYour life path is one of liberation through creativity. You may struggle with restlessness or a sense that you don't fit into the standard timeline of society. The number 11 gives you a disruptive energy that challenges the status quo. Your challenge is to embrace your uniqueness and not fear the chaos of creation. You are here to show us that time is not a straight line, but a dance, and that we are free to change the steps whenever the music shifts."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#78cab4", "primary": "#0f1a1a", "secondary": "#2d4c47"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.791055	2026-04-25 13:46:57.770041
42	4	3	3	Kan	You take a different route through the city, hoping the paths will make more sense today. They don’t.\n\nThe buildings lean in stranger angles than before, as if they have been quietly rearranging themselves while you slept. Corridors stretch longer than they should. Stairwells descend into soft electric darkness. The air tastes metallic, charged, almost alive.\n\nThen you notice it.\n\nA faint flicker beneath a grated walkway, like something bright is trying to slither free. You kneel, listening. The ground hums faintly, not with the heavy static of dead wires, but with a low, rippling pulse. It reminds you of breath. Or a heartbeat.\n\nYou follow the sound down a stairwell that wasn’t there yesterday. Neon strips glow beneath broken rails, guiding you deeper. The temperature shifts. The air thickens. Colors sharpen into electric greens and golds. Here, in the underbelly of the city, the walls don’t stay still. They ripple subtly, like snakes shifting beneath old wallpaper.\n\nAt the base of the stairs, you find a narrow platform lit by a single green tube of light that buzzes like a living thing. The pulse grows stronger.\n\nSomething moves.\n\nFrom the darkness between the platform and the next corridor, a filament of glowing gold arcs outward like a serpent made of charged air. It does not threaten. It watches. Its movement is curious, instinctual, winding toward you with a shimmering intelligence.\n\nYou stand still and let your breath settle.\n\nThe energy-coil hovers near your chest as if reading you. Images spark behind your eyes — flashes of moments when you acted too quickly, times when you hesitated, impulses that never had a voice, truths you swallowed, power you dimmed because someone else might misunderstand.\n\nThe serpent-light coils tighter, and you feel a thrum of recognition.\n\nThis is not an enemy.\n\nIt is the part of you that acts before you think, the raw instinct you feared was reckless. In its shimmering curves, you see that instinct is not chaos. It is guidance waiting to be trusted.\n\nThe serpent-wisp brushes your arm and leaves a brief trail of warm gold. In that contact, you understand: your instinct has been whispering the whole time. You’ve just been too tangled, too tired, too burdened to listen.\n\nWhen you lift your head again, the energy-coil flickers, twists once, and slips back into the dark corridor, leaving behind a thin trail of gold that slowly fades into the air.\n\nYou take one step forward. Then another.\n\nThe ground beneath you feels steadier, as if your feet finally remember a rhythm older than fear.\n\nDeep in the city, far from the surface, you feel the first clean spark of your own power returning.	There is a spark moving under the surface today, and you feel it before you know why. Something in you wants to shift — not dramatically, not recklessly, but honestly.\n\nInstinct is speaking more clearly than usual. You might feel drawn toward a conversation you’ve avoided, a new idea, or a subtle boundary that wants to be placed. This is not impulse without wisdom. This is wisdom wearing the shape of impulse.\n\nLet your body speak. Your breath, your posture, the heat rising or settling in your chest — these are all messages. You are learning to trust the signals that don’t come from thought but from the deeper coil of knowing.\n\nMove gently, but don’t ignore the spark. It’s pointing somewhere real.	I listen to the quiet spark within me and let instinct guide my next small movement.	Find a calm place to sit. Close your eyes and imagine yourself descending a stairwell lit by soft green and gold light. The air thickens as you move deeper, growing warm and electric.\n\nAt the bottom, see a shimmering serpent-shaped energy coil emerging from the shadows. It approaches without threat, moving with curiosity. Let it pause in front of you, sensing your breath, your heartbeat, your truth.\n\nImagine this serpent is your intuition — the part of you that knows before words form. As it hovers near your chest, feel warmth spread outward, loosening doubt, softening hesitation.\n\nNow imagine placing your hand near the serpent’s glow. A pulse of warmth travels through your arm, into your ribs, your spine, your belly. Let that warmth gather into a single point of golden clarity.\n\nThank the ancient ones who honored instinct as sacred guidance. Take one final breath, then watch the serpent slip back into the corridor, leaving a soft trail of light.\n\nWhen you open your eyes, let your next action be guided by that quiet inner spark.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Serpent of Wisdom", "content": "Kan is the nawal of the serpent, the life force (kundalini), and evolution. It represents the inner fire that coils at the base of the spine and rises to bring enlightenment. Kan is the energy of DNA, sexuality, and transformation through shedding skin. It governs the nervous system and physical truth. Kan is an intense, instinctual energy. In its shadow, Kan can be manipulative or seductive. Its highest expression is the wise use of vitality to serve evolution.", "keywords": ["Serpent", "Vitality", "Evolution", "Power", "Wisdom"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Movement", "content": "Three is the number of vibration, rhythm, and the breaking of stagnation. If One is a point and Two is a line, Three is the triangle that brings stability through motion. Three represents communication, creativity, and the flow of energy. Experientially, a Three day feels active, buzzing, and potentially restless. It is a day where things want to move. The shadow of Three can be scattered energy or anxiety. It asks us to express ourselves and let the energy circulate.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Communication", "Rhythm", "Creativity", "Flow"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Dance! Put on music and let your body move intuitively.", "Practice Kundalini yoga or breathwork to move energy up the spine.", "Express a passionate truth to someone you trust.", "Be mindful of your nervous system; if you feel jittery, ground yourself.", "Create art that is visceral and bold."], "title": "The Dance of the Serpent", "content": "Today, the rhythmic movement of Three activates the serpentine power of Kan. This is a day of 'Moving Energy' or 'Vital Expression.' The life force (Kan) is being asked to flow, to dance, and to communicate (Three). It is an incredibly high-energy day, perfect for physical exercise, dance, or creative performance. Your body wants to move today; sitting still might feel impossible or cause anxiety. The energy supports the awakening of the nervous system and the clearing of energetic blockages. You may feel a surge of libido or creative passion. The challenge is to direct this flow constructively. Unchecked, 3 Kan can lead to nervous burnout or erratic behavior. Don't let the serpent run wild; give it a rhythm to dance to. Speak your truth with passion, move your body with intention, and let the old skins shed as you dance your way into a new form."}}	{"title": "The Charismatic Catalyst", "content": "To be born on 3 Kan is to be a dynamo of energy and expression. You possess a magnetic personality and a natural rhythm that draws people to you. The number Three gives you a gift for communication and performance, while Kan provides the raw power and vitality to back it up. You are likely an artist, a performer, or a teacher—someone who uses their body and voice to transmit energy. You are never boring; your life is a constant dance of evolution and change.\\n\\nYour life path is one of mastering your own intensity. You have a lot of 'voltage' running through you, and if you don't channel it into creativity or movement, it can turn into anxiety or chaos. You may struggle with restlessness or a need for constant stimulation. Your lesson is to learn to flow with your own power, to trust your instincts, and to use your charisma to uplift and heal others. You are here to show the world that life is meant to be lived with passion."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#7f998b", "primary": "#0d1717", "secondary": "#334440"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#cd8b33", "primary": "#1c1b20", "secondary": "#533e35"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#c58923", "primary": "#09161a", "secondary": "#524321"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#d3970f", "primary": "#03281c", "secondary": "#1a542f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.756208	2026-04-25 13:46:57.708434
202	16	7	7	Ix	You emerge from the Sanctuary rested, but the Veldt has changed. The indigo sky turns pitch black. The glowing plants dim and vanish. You are left in absolute, suffocating darkness. You cannot see your hand in front of your face.\n\nBut then, a prickle of heat starts behind your eyes. Your pupils dilate, expanding until they swallow the iris. Your vision shifts. Suddenly, the world flares back into existence—not in color, but in energy.\n\nYou see the Veldt as an X-ray. You see the white ghost-veins of roots running miles deep into the black earth. You see the faint heat signatures of sleeping Grazers. And far in the distance, you see a pulsing beacon of white fire—the destination. You have the Jaguar's sight now. You do not need the sun to know where to walk.	The world has just gone pitch black, but don't reach for a lantern. What you need today isn't more light—it’s a change in your vision. A prickle of heat is starting behind your eyes, dilating your pupils until they swallow the iris. You are gaining the sight of the night-seer. Suddenly, the darkness isn't an empty void; it’s a map of energy. You can see the ghost-veins of the world, the deep roots of old stories, and the faint heat signatures of possibilities that are still sleeping. This is the shaman’s stealth, the ability to walk through the shadows without fear because you can see the truth hidden beneath the surface.\n\nYou are standing at a mystical threshold where the veil between what you want and what is possible is paper-thin. Trust your wildly non-linear intuition over your logical brain. If your gut tells you there’s a path through the dark, follow the heat. You don't need a sun to tell you where to walk when you have the internal fire of your own magic to guide you. This is a 360-degree review of your soul’s hidden dimensions. Look at the people and projects in your life through this X-ray lens—who is truly rooted, and who is just a silhouette? The answers are whispers in the dark. Listen with your skin.	My intuition is my greatest power, and I walk fearlessly into the mysteries of life.	Keep your eyes closed and focus on the space between your eyebrows. Imagine you are listening to the ground beneath you rather than looking at it. Feel the vibrations of the earth’s hidden movements. Trust the silent 'knowing' that rises through your seat, bypassing your eyes and ears.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine the world around you fading into absolute darkness. Feel your pupils dilate until you can see the 'X-ray' of reality. Visualize the glowing veins of roots and the heat signatures of life miles away. You are the Jaguar, walking fearlessly through the mystery because you see the truth in the dark.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Jaguar of Earth Magic", "content": "Ix is the nawal of the jaguar, the shaman, and the magic of the earth. It represents the feminine mysteries, high magic, and the connection to nature spirits. Ix is the energy of the night seer who walks without fear in the darkness. Associated with the element of earth and the spirit, it carries a stealthy, potent, and highly intuitive energy. It is the archetype of the healer who uses nature's tools to transform reality. In daily life, Ix manifests as intuition, synchronicity, and a deep pull toward the mysteries of life. Its shadow aspect can be the misuse of power, black magic, or becoming reclusive and disconnected from the human world. Ix teaches us that the earth is alive and that we are in constant dialogue with her.", "keywords": ["Magic", "Intuition", "Nature", "Jaguar", "Mystery"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mystic Prism", "content": "Tone 7 is the midpoint of the 13-day cycle, sitting at the very top of the energetic pyramid. It represents the point of maximum potential, reflection, and mystical power. Unlike the stability of 4 or the flow of 6, Tone 7 is a threshold energy—neither here nor there, but encompassing both the beginning and the end. It is a day of 'no time,' where the veil between worlds is thin. Experientially, Tone 7 feels contemplative, strange, and highly intuitive. It provides a 360-degree view of reality, allowing us to see the past and future simultaneously. While it offers profound insights and the ability to channel energy, its shadow can be indecision, confusion, or getting lost in the ether. It is the mirror at the top of the mountain.", "keywords": ["Insight", "Reflection", "Mysticism", "Threshold", "Vision"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in divination, meditation, or dream work.", "Spend time in nature, specifically wild or wooded areas.", "Trust your gut feelings over your logical analysis today.", "Look for signs, symbols, and animal messengers.", "Pause and reflect on the first half of the trecena; adjust your course."], "title": "The Summit of Magic", "content": "7 Ix is one of the most mystical and powerful days in the entire Tzolk'in. When the threshold energy of Tone 7 combines with the earth magic of the Jaguar (Ix), we stand at the peak of spiritual receptivity. This is a day of 'High Magic'—not in a performative sense, but in the deep, quiet knowing that the material and spiritual worlds are one. The energy today is thick with potential; synchronicities are likely to be constant. It feels like standing in a deep jungle clearing where the air is humming with invisible life. 7 Ix invites us to pause at the top of the pyramid and look at our lives through the eyes of the Jaguar—seeing the truth in the dark. It is an ideal time for divination, meditation, or simply being in nature to listen. The logical mind may struggle today, as the answers coming through are non-linear and felt rather than thought. The opportunity is to trust your wildest intuition and to recognize the magic in the mundane."}}	{"title": "The Mystic Seer of Nature", "content": "To be born on 7 Ix is to carry the soul of a high priestess or a shaman within a modern existence. You are a person of deep mystery and profound intuition, naturally attuned to the subtle energies that others miss. Standing at the top of the pyramid (Tone 7) with the heart of the Jaguar (Ix), you have a panoramic view of reality that includes both the visible and invisible worlds. You are likely a natural healer, counselor, or artist, using your connection to the divine to bring transformative insights to those around you. People are drawn to your enigma; you don't reveal everything at once, and your silence often speaks louder than words.\\n\\nYour life path is one of bridging the gap between the mundane and the magical. You are not here to live a superficial life. You are compelled to dig for the truth, to explore the shadows, and to understand the secrets of nature. You may find yourself experiencing psychic phenomena or having a deep, unspoken bond with animals and plants. Tone 7 gives you a reflective nature; you need solitary time to process the vast amount of energetic information you receive. You are a catalyst for others' awakening, often simply by being your authentic, mysterious self.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 7 Ix soul is grounding. Because you live so comfortably in the ether and the abstract, the practical demands of the material world can sometimes feel harsh or boring. You may struggle with indecision or a feeling of being 'spaced out.' There is also a risk of isolation, as you may feel that few people truly understand your depth. Your lesson is to bring your magic down to earth—to use your vision not just to escape reality, but to enrich and heal it. When you integrate your spiritual sight with practical action, you become a powerful force for evolution."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#77c09d", "primary": "#0f1917", "secondary": "#3d453b"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.853746	2026-04-25 14:38:01.323046
30	3	4	4	Aq'ab'al					{"nawal": {"title": "The Dawn of Possibility", "content": "Aq'ab'al is the nawal of the dawn, the twilight, and the threshold between worlds. It represents the moment when the darkness gives way to the light, symbolizing hope, clarity, and new beginnings. Aq'ab'al is the energy of potential—the realization of a new day or a new concept. It governs the polarity of young and old, and the transition states. In its shadow, Aq'ab'al can manifest as duality, confusion, or deception—the trick of the half-light. However, its highest expression is the clear vision of the morning star, bringing the promise of renewal.", "keywords": ["Dawn", "Hope", "Transition", "Polarity", "Renewal"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cube of Stability", "content": "Four is the number of stability, foundation, and the physical plane. It represents the four directions (East, West, North, South) and the four elements that uphold the material world. After the movement of Three, Four brings the energy back to earth to be grounded and structured. It is the energy of the cube and the square—solid, reliable, and enduring. Experientially, a Four day feels steady and practical. It is a time to build, organize, and establish boundaries. The shadow of Four can be rigidity or stubbornness. It asks us to create a stable container for our lives.", "keywords": ["Stability", "Structure", "Foundation", "Four Directions", "Order"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create a physical plan or timeline for a new goal.", "Wake up at dawn and stand facing the East to honor the direction of new beginnings.", "Declutter your entryway to clear the path for new energy.", "Focus on 'foundational' self-care: sleep, hydration, and healthy food.", "Meditate on the image of a temple being built at sunrise."], "title": "Grounding the New Dawn", "content": "When the stabilizing force of Four meets the hopeful dawn of Aq'ab'al, we have a day of 'Manifested Hope' or 'Structural Renewal.' The fleeting inspiration of the previous days is now asking to be built into something real. Today is about taking a new idea (Aq'ab'al) and giving it legs to stand on (Four). It is an excellent day for starting a new routine, laying the foundation for a project, or physically cleaning your space to welcome new energy. The Four stabilizes the transition of Aq'ab'al, making the change feel less scary and more manageable. The energy is calm, optimistic, and industrious. The challenge is to not let the stability turn into stagnation; ensure that the walls you build have windows for the new light to enter. Use this day to anchor your dreams in reality. Don't just hope for a better tomorrow; build the structure that will support it."}}	{"title": "The Architect of Hope", "content": "To be born on 4 Aq'ab'al is to be a builder of new realities. You possess a unique blend of practical stability (Four) and visionary optimism (Aq'ab'al). You are not just a dreamer; you are someone who knows how to make dreams come true through hard work and planning. You likely have a talent for spotting potential—in people, in projects, or in properties—before anyone else does. You are the one who buys the 'fixer-upper' and turns it into a palace.\\n\\nYour life path involves bridging the gap between what is and what could be. You are comfortable in transition phases, often acting as a guide or stabilizer for others going through change. You have a youthful spirit that never quite ages, yet you carry the wisdom of an old soul. People rely on you because you are steady, but they are inspired by you because you are always looking toward the light.\\n\\nThe challenge for you is a tendency towards duality or hesitation. You may see so much potential that you struggle to commit to one path, or you may become too rigid in your methods. Your lesson is to trust that the dawn will come and to keep building the temple to receive it. You are here to show the world that hope is a solid thing."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c5a487", "primary": "#131919", "secondary": "#533f39"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.747683	2026-04-25 13:46:57.687729
46	4	7	7	Toj	You wake with the sense that the city has climbed higher around you.\n\nThe structures stretch upward today, rising in staggered terraces, as if the two overlapping worlds have begun to build a single spine from their fractured pieces. The twilight sky glows faintly gold near the horizon, the brightest you’ve seen since you arrived.\n\nAs you walk, the streets narrow into sloping pathways that spiral gently upward. The air becomes clearer. The hum of old cables softens. Even the broken signs seem steadier, like they’re remembering how to hold light.\n\nYou climb a long set of steps carved into the side of an old tower. The stone is cracked, but warm, as if absorbing light from somewhere deeper than the sun. At the top, the city opens into a wide platform — a rooftop that feels more like an altar.\n\nFrom this height, you can see both cities fully.\n\nThe shadow-city still clings to the edges, its signs flickering, its walls fractured. But the luminous city glows through it more clearly now — soft golds, pale blues, warm ambers, shimmering like a dream on the verge of becoming real.\n\nYou stand between them, suspended in the space where two realities overlap.\n\nAt the center of the rooftop lies a shallow stone basin. Inside it: ash, charcoal, fragments of old offerings long extinguished. You kneel beside it. The wind shifts. Something inside you recognizes this place.\n\nYou have climbed here to release something.\n\nYour hands hover over the basin, unsure at first what to offer. Some burdens are too heavy to name. Some debts you’ve carried so long they feel like parts of your ribs.\n\nBut as you breathe, a small warmth flickers in your palms — the ember from Day 4, the quiet seed of ending you accepted. You feel it pulse once, twice, asking for release.\n\nYou lower your hands. The ember drops into the ash.\n\nFor a moment, nothing happens. Then the ash glows faintly, ignited not by flame but by acknowledgment. A thin column of light rises from the basin, spiraling upward into the twilight sky. It is not fire. It is offering.\n\nAnd the city responds.\n\nThe fractured buildings below soften at the edges. Golden seams brighten. The luminous city grows clearer, as if the act of release opened a small window between the worlds. The rooftop vibrates gently under your feet — not with danger, but with gratitude.\n\nYou exhale. Something inside you unwinds.\n\nYou came here carrying more than you could hold. You leave with space for what comes next.	There is a clearing at the midpoint of this cycle — a moment when you can step back, look at your life from above, and feel the shape of what is unfolding.\n\nToday asks for release, not sacrifice. Let something go because it frees you, not because you owe anything. Offer up a thought, a memory, or a burden you’ve carried too tightly.\n\nAs you make space, clarity arrives. The path becomes easier to see. Light begins to filter into corners you didn’t realize had dimmed.\n\nThis is not a day for effort. It is a day for gratitude, forgiveness, and gentle perspective.	I release what weighs me down and allow clarity to rise in its place.	Find a quiet place to sit. Close your eyes and imagine climbing a long set of steps up the side of an old twilight tower. With each step, feel your body grow lighter.\n\nAt the top, envision a wide rooftop platform overlooking both the shadow-city and the luminous city. A shallow stone basin rests in the center.\n\nPicture yourself kneeling beside it. In your hands, a small ember glows softly — a symbol of something you’re ready to release.\n\nDrop the ember into the basin. Watch as the ash glows and a thin column of light rises into the sky. Feel the weight you’ve been carrying dissolve into that light.\n\nOffer quiet gratitude to the keepers of balance and reciprocity. Sit with the stillness for a few breaths. When you are ready, open your eyes, carrying renewed clarity with you.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Fire", "content": "Toj is the nawal of offering, payment, and the sacred fire. It represents the law of cause and effect (karma) and the need for balance through giving back. Toj is the energy of gratitude expressed through action. It governs the payment of debts and the restoration of equilibrium. In its shadow, Toj can manifest as suffering or a victim mentality. Its highest expression is the joy of service—giving freely to maintain the balance of life.", "keywords": ["Offering", "Payment", "Fire", "Gratitude", "Balance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Summit of Vision", "content": "Seven is the number of the midpoint, the top of the pyramid, and mystical alignment. It represents the ability to see both the past and the future simultaneously. Seven is a number of reflection, choice, and dynamic balance. It is a day where energy peaks and shifts. Experientially, a Seven day feels like reaching a lookout point—there is clarity and perspective. The shadow of Seven can be indecision born of seeing too many options. It asks us to look at the whole picture.", "keywords": ["Midpoint", "Reflection", "Perspective", "Mysticism", "Choice"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Make a physical offering (flowers, food, money) to a source of support.", "Write a list of things you are grateful for, looking at both past and future.", "Meditate on the flame of a candle as a symbol of transmutation.", "Forgive a debt someone owes you, if you are able.", "Reflect on the 'costs' of your choices and accept them with grace."], "title": "The Perspective of Gratitude", "content": "Today, we stand at the top of the pyramid (Seven) and make an offering to the fire (Toj). This is a day of 'Spiritual Payment' or 'Balanced Giving.' The Seven gives us the perspective to see *why* we need to give back. We can see the debts of the past and the potential of the future, and we understand that offering is the bridge between them. It is a powerful day for ceremony, for settling karmic accounts, and for expressing deep gratitude. The energy is high and spiritual. You may feel a strong desire to help others or to make a sacrifice for a higher cause. The challenge is to not give from a place of guilt, but from a place of vision. See the interconnectedness of all things. Realize that your offering is not a loss, but an investment in the flow of the universe. Clear the slate today so you can walk down the other side of the pyramid with a lighter step."}}	{"title": "The Visionary Giver", "content": "To be born on 7 Toj is to be a soul dedicated to service and spiritual balance. You occupy a mystical midpoint, acting as a mediator between the human and divine worlds through the act of offering. The number Seven gives you a deep, reflective nature and the ability to see the 'big picture' of karma, while Toj fills you with a desire to give back and restore harmony. You are likely the person who reminds others of the importance of gratitude. You may suffer if you do not find a way to serve; your soul needs to be useful to be at peace.\\n\\nYour life path is one of clearing debts—not just your own, but perhaps those of your lineage or community. You are a natural healer or ceremonialist. Your challenge is to not become a martyr. You can see so much need (Seven) and feel such a drive to help (Toj) that you can deplete yourself. Your lesson is to learn that you are also worthy of receiving. True balance requires that the flow goes both ways. When you master this, you become a powerful conduit for divine grace."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d5a681", "primary": "#101614", "secondary": "#45403b"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#9e6a9e", "primary": "#20285d", "secondary": "#433b8f"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#c77567", "primary": "#120f3d", "secondary": "#542661"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#645b70", "primary": "#212434", "secondary": "#3d3d54"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.759709	2026-04-25 13:46:57.71536
32	3	6	6	Kan					{"nawal": {"title": "The Serpent of Wisdom", "content": "Kan is the nawal of the serpent, the life force (kundalini), and evolution. It represents the inner fire that coils at the base of the spine and rises to bring enlightenment. Kan is the energy of DNA, sexuality, and the power of transformation through shedding skin. It governs the nervous system and physical truth. Kan is an intense, instinctual energy—it is the raw power of nature. In its shadow, Kan can be manipulative, seductive, or prone to misuse of power. However, its highest expression is the wise use of vitality to serve the evolution of consciousness.", "keywords": ["Serpent", "Vitality", "Evolution", "Power", "Wisdom"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Stability", "content": "Six is the number of flow, organic balance, and responsiveness. It represents the point where the initial effort of the 1-5 cycle stabilizes and finds its rhythm. Six is associated with the Heart of the Sky and Heart of the Earth, bringing a vertical alignment. Experientially, a Six day feels smoother and more harmonious. Obstacles tend to dissolve if you stop pushing and start flowing. It is a time for family, physical vitality, and acceptance. The shadow of Six can be passivity or drifting. It teaches us to trust the process and move with the current.", "keywords": ["Flow", "Harmony", "Vitality", "Responsiveness", "Alignment"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Do a yoga session focusing on the spine to awaken the Kan energy.", "Spend time in nature, specifically observing the movement of water or wind.", "Trust your gut instincts; your body is a truth-teller today.", "Engage in intimate connection with a partner or yourself.", "Drink plenty of water to help the energy flow through your system."], "title": "Flowing with Vitality", "content": "When the harmonious flow of Six meets the evolutionary power of Kan, we experience a day of 'Rhythmic Vitality' or 'Fluid Power.' The intense energy of the serpent is softened and guided by the flow of the Six, making it a day of graceful strength rather than explosive force. It is an incredible day for physical movement—yoga, dance, or Tai Chi—where you can connect with the wisdom of your body. The energy supports healing, especially of the nervous system. You may feel a sense of alignment between your physical desires and your spiritual path. The 'shedding of skin' happens naturally today, without the usual pain. The challenge is to stay present in your body. The energy is high, and if blocked, it can manifest as anxiety or restlessness. Let it move. Trust the intelligence of your life force; it knows exactly where it needs to go to heal and evolve you."}}	{"title": "The Graceful Serpent", "content": "To be born on 6 Kan is to be a master of fluid power and physical wisdom. You possess a natural grace and charisma that is undeniable. The number Six gives you a harmonious, responsive nature, smoothing out the often intense edges of the Kan serpent energy. You are likely very comfortable in your body—perhaps an athlete, a dancer, or a healer who works with somatic energy. You have an intuitive understanding of the cycles of life and death, knowing instinctively when it is time to shed a skin and move on.\\n\\nYour life path is one of embodied evolution. You are here to show that spiritual growth doesn't mean leaving the body, but fully inhabiting it. You may have a strong magnetic pull on others, and your challenge is to use this influence with integrity. You are a natural teacher of balance, demonstrating how to be strong without being rigid, and how to be powerful without being aggressive. You flow through life's changes with a serpentine elegance that inspires everyone around you."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#84ba88", "primary": "#131c18", "secondary": "#394c36"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.748285	2026-04-25 13:46:57.689704
144	12	1	1	K'at	You step tentatively onto the first woven walkway. The rope is thick, made of golden fibers that feel warm to the touch. Below you, the canyon floor is miles down, hidden in shadow. Around you, the nets are cluttered with debris.\n\nThis is the Net of Accumulation.\n\nBundles hang everywhere. Some are labeled with dates from years ago. Some pulse with anxiety. Some are heavy sacks of "Maybe someday" and "What if." The path forward is blocked by a massive, tangled knot of cables and cords, vibrating with a low, dissonant hum.\n\n1 is the number of Beginnings. K’at is the Net. Today, you must acknowledge the trap before you can find the treasure.\n\nYou realize that you have been hoarding energy. You have said "yes" when you meant "no." You have kept relationships on life support. You have stored resentments in the attic of your mind. The knot before you is the physical manifestation of your overwhelmed spirit.\n\nYou cannot cut it—that would sever the bridge. You must loosen it.\n\nYou reach into the tangle. The ropes are tight, pulling against each other. You find a single strand that feels distinct—a small worry you pick up every morning out of habit. You acknowledge it. "I am holding this," you whisper.\n\nThe moment you name it, the tension in that strand releases. It goes slack. The knot loosens, just a fraction.\n\nYou find another strand. "I am holding this old expectation." It relaxes.\n\nThis is the work of the first day: simple acknowledgment. You don’t have to fix the whole mess today. You just have to admit that you are carrying it. You have to stop pretending your hands are empty.\n\nAs the knot loosens, a gap opens in the path. It is just wide enough for you to squeeze through.\n\nYou step through the opening, leaving a little bit of the tightness behind. The net sways, adjusting to your lighter weight.	You might feel a bit weighed down today, as if you are carrying a backpack you forgot to take off. The energy of 1 K’at reveals the nets you are caught in.\n\nDon’t panic. The net is not a cage; it’s just a collection. Look at what’s inside. Are you carrying other people’s problems? Old guilts? Tasks that don’t matter? Simply acknowledging the load is the first step to setting it down. You are waking up to your own capacity.	I acknowledge what I am carrying, and I prepare to release what no longer serves me.	Visualize yourself standing in a golden net. All around you are objects caught in the mesh. Some are beautiful jewels (your gifts); some are heavy stones (your burdens).\n\nWalk around and inspect them. Don’t touch them yet. Just name them. "This is my job." "This is my worry about money." "This is my love for my family."\n\nSee the inventory clearly. You are the sorter.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Cosmic Net", "content": "K'at is the energy of the net, the harvest, and the gathering of resources. It represents the principle of entanglement—both the abundance that we gather into our lives and the traps that hold us back. K'at is the lizard and the spider, weavers of destiny who teach us about interdependence. It is a container energy, asking us to look at what we are carrying in our personal 'nets.' It governs community, abundance, and the clearing of debts or burdens that no longer serve us. It is the friction that creates the pearl.", "keywords": ["Gathering", "Release", "Abundance", "Community", "Entanglement"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Connection", "content": "The number 1 represents the spark of creation, the unity of all things, and the seed that contains the potential for the entire cycle. It is the beginning, the impulse to exist, and the singular focus required to start a new journey. In the K'at trecena, the 1 energy initiates a cycle of gathering, sorting, and untangling. It acts as the first knot in the net—the point of origin from which all other connections will flow. It asks for a clear intention regarding what you wish to harvest and what you are ready to release. It is the singular focus of the spider beginning its web.", "keywords": ["Unity", "Initiation", "Potential", "Seed", "Focus"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Set a clear intention for what you wish to manifest or 'catch' in this cycle.", "Identify one burden or debt (emotional or physical) to release.", "Reach out to a new contact or strengthen an existing network.", "Clean out a physical space (drawer, bag, room) to symbolize clearing your net.", "Visualize your life as a web; where are the knots too tight?"], "title": "Casting the First Thread", "content": "1 K'at initiates a 13-day cycle focused on the themes of connection, abundance, and release. Today is the day to cast your net with intention. The singular energy of the 1 combines with the gathering power of K'at to ask: What do you want to bring into your life, and what are you ready to cut loose? It is a day of seeding connections. Every interaction today has the potential to become a significant thread in your future tapestry. The energy is ripe for starting new collections—of ideas, resources, or allies. However, it also demands discernment. Be careful not to trap yourself in commitments or burdens that are too heavy to carry. The seed planted today is one of interdependence; ensure the soil is free of weeds before you sow."}}	{"title": "The Great Connector", "content": "To be born on 1 K'at is to be a master of connections and a weaver of community. You possess an innate ability to bring people, resources, and ideas together in meaningful ways. You are the spider at the center of the web, sensitive to the slightest vibration in your network. You are likely a natural organizer, a collector of wisdom, or someone who thrives in fields that require complex logistics. Your presence acts as a glue, binding disparate elements into a cohesive whole.\\n\\nYour life path is defined by the dual nature of the net: abundance and entanglement. You have a magnetic quality that draws experiences and people to you, often resulting in a life rich with variety. However, this same magnetism can lead to feeling burdened or trapped by your own success and commitments. You may struggle with saying no, fearing that you might miss out on a valuable resource or connection.\\n\\nYour challenge is to learn the art of release. The 1 K'at soul must constantly discern between what is worth carrying and what is merely dead weight. You are learning that true abundance requires open hands, not just a full net. When you master the balance of gathering and letting go, you become a powerful conduit for prosperity, ensuring that your web supports you rather than ensnares you."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#ccb682", "primary": "#101412", "secondary": "#483f33"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.816689	2026-04-25 13:46:57.901754
72	6	7	7	Tijax	At the peak of the 13-day mountain, the Bazaar of Maps suddenly drops away into a deep indigo void. Spanning the chasm is the Bridge of the Paper Cut—a razor-thin ribbon of parchment that vibrates with the energy of the Obsidian Blade. From this height, you can see every map you’ve ever carried. To cross, you must undergo the surgery of 7 Tijax. The road itself acts as a spiritual healer, its edges sharpening to cut away the excess baggage of false stories and heavy illusions. As you walk, you feel the 'cords' of old attachments being sliced clean. You reach the other side with nothing but the essential truth of your journey, your spirit refined and light enough to dance across the remaining miles of the road.	You have reached a high, silent ridge where the air is thin and the vision is absolute. From this peak, the universe is handing you a shard of polished obsidian—not to use as a weapon, but as a tool for profound spiritual surgery. You may feel a sudden, sharp clarity regarding a situation that has felt cluttered or confusing. Today is not about gentle adjustments; it is about the brave act of cutting away the illusions that have been weighing you down. The atmosphere smells of ozone and cold stone, a reminder that true healing often begins with a clean, honest break from the past. Don't be afraid of the "sharpness" of your own insight. You are being asked to distinguish between what is essential and what is merely noise. If you notice a cord or a pattern that no longer serves your growth, use this moment of peak perspective to release it once and for all. By refining your life through the power of discernment, you restore your natural balance and protection. You are a holy warrior of the truth today, and your greatest victory is the restoration of your own clarity. Walk back down into the valley light, unburdened and profoundly renewed.	I use the blade of my own truth to cut through illusions, refining my spirit at the peak of my vision.	Close your eyes and imagine a thin, razor-sharp line of violet light descending from the crown of your head to the base of your spine. As you breathe, let this light act as a blade of discernment, quietly severing any heavy cords or illusions that no longer serve you. Feel the lightness that comes when the excess is cut away, leaving only your essential truth.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, visualize yourself standing on the Bridge of the Paper Cut over a deep indigo void. Look down at the silver cords of old attachments trailing behind you. See an obsidian blade-tip touch these threads, causing them to dissolve into prismatic sparks. Feel the spiritual surgery of the bridge refining you, making you light enough to dance across the razor-thin ribbon of parchment toward your freedom.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Obsidian Blade", "content": "Tijax is the Nawal of the obsidian blade, the double-edged sword of truth. It represents the energy of the warrior and the healer—the one who cuts to cure. Tijax governs discernment, drastic changes, and the removal of negative energies or illnesses. In human experience, Tijax manifests as sharp wit, the courage to speak the truth, and a talent for cutting through illusion. It is the lightning strike that clears the air. When aligned, Tijax brings liberation and healing; when misaligned, it can lead to harshness or conflict. It is the surgeon's scalpel.", "keywords": ["Truth", "Healing", "Discernment", "Cutting", "Purification"]}, "number": {"title": "The Summit of Reflection", "content": "The number Seven represents the midpoint of the trecena, the top of the pyramid, and the power of mystic vision. In Mayan cosmology, Seven is a number of great potential but also of suspension; it is the moment where we can look back at the climb and forward to the descent. Experientially, this energy feels like a pause in the action—a time to assess, reflect, and gain perspective. It is neither a beginning nor an end, but a bridge. The shadow of Seven can be indecision, but its light is the clarity that comes from seeing the whole picture.", "keywords": ["Reflection", "Midpoint", "Vision", "Insight", "Clarity"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Reflect on what burden you have been carrying up the mountain; drop it now.", "Make a clear, final decision on a lingering issue.", "Use the 'sword' of your speech to define your boundaries clearly.", "Engage in a ritual of cutting ties (figuratively or literally with cords).", "Trust your discernment; you see the truth clearly today."], "title": "The Final Cut", "content": "The reflective power of Tone 7 combined with the cutting edge of Tijax creates a pivotal day of 'Decisive Healing.' 7 Tijax represents the top of the pyramid, where we have the clearest view of what is working and what is not. From this vantage point, the Obsidian Blade can be wielded with absolute precision. Today is the day to cut the last cord that holds you back. It is a day of profound release—a spiritual surgery that removes the obstacle blocking your path (E'). Because 7 is a number of vision, you can see exactly where the cut needs to be made. This is not a hacking frenzy; it is a single, clean severance. Use this energy to end a bad habit, leave a toxic situation, or simply let go of a limiting belief. The feeling is one of sudden lightness after the weight is dropped. The bridge is crossed; burn the ships."}}	{"title": "The Mystic Surgeon", "content": "To be born on 7 Tijax is to hold the scalpel of the divine. You are the 'Visionary Healer'—a soul who can see deep into the heart of a matter and knows exactly what needs to be removed to restore health. You possess a piercing intellect and a strong sense of right and wrong. Situated at the top of the pyramid (7), you have a detached, panoramic view of life that allows you to be objective, even when things are messy. You are a truth-teller, often saying what others are afraid to whisper.\\n\\nYour life path is one of purification and refinement. You are here to help yourself and others cut through illusions and get to the core of truth. You may be drawn to healing professions, surgery, or counseling—anywhere that requires sharp discernment. The danger for you is becoming too critical or cutting yourself off from others in your quest for perfection. Your lesson is to remember that the knife is a tool for healing, not for harm, and that true healing includes compassion. You are the lightning that clears the sky."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#af9a88", "primary": "#161613", "secondary": "#563a34"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.777613	2026-04-25 14:38:01.298384
50	4	11	11	Aj	The platform at the end of the bridge narrows into a quiet residential district—or what remains of one. The buildings here stand straighter. Their windows glow with soft, steady light, not flickering or fractured. Vines from the forest district curl along balconies, and patches of the luminous city shine through the walls like gentle lanterns.\n\nThe air feels different. Still, but full.\n\nAs you walk, you notice a repeating structure appearing at regular intervals: tall stone columns embedded into the streets and doorways. Some are cracked, others polished smooth by time, but each one hums with a grounding presence. The sound is subtle, a deep resonance that seems to settle your breath and lengthen your spine.\n\nYou approach one of the pillars.\n\nIts surface glows with faint etched patterns—lines that look like roots and constellations intertwined. When you place your hand on it, a pulse rises through your arm, warm and steady.\n\nSomething inside you responds.\n\nMemories of every place you’ve called home flicker through your mind: rooms you outgrew, corners where you hid, the one place you left too quickly, the places where you stayed too long. You feel the weight of all those temporary shelters, all the times you kept moving because stillness felt dangerous.\n\nThe column hums louder—not demanding, not summoning, but acknowledging.\n\nA gentle shift spreads through the district. The buildings straighten further. Doorframes realign. Even the air feels more centered. You understand now: these columns aren’t remnants.\n\nThey’re anchors.\n\nAs you continue walking, more columns appear in your path, each one supporting the quiet architecture of this shifting world. Some glow gold. Others emit soft blue or gentle violet. Each carries a unique rhythm, but all of them share one purpose: to hold the world steady.\n\nThen you reach the heart of the district.\n\nA circular plaza holds a massive pillar—wider than a tree trunk, tall enough to merge with the twilight sky. Its surface is smooth stone, but alive with light moving through faint carved pathways. You step closer and feel your body settle in a way you haven’t known for years.\n\nThis pillar feels like a spine.\n\nNot of a building or a city—of you.\n\nYou place both hands on it. The resonance deepens, spreading through your bones. Strength rises quietly, not in the form of power or confidence, but in simple presence. Your breath becomes slower, fuller. You feel your entire body align, rooted yet open.\n\nA truth moves through you:\n\nYou do not always have to travel.\n\nYou do not always have to run.\n\nThere is a home inside you that cannot be destroyed.\n\nFor the first time, the city is not just guiding you.\n\nIt is welcoming you.	Today asks you to root into yourself even as life moves in multiple directions. You may feel pulled toward different tasks, emotions, or choices—but underneath it all, there is a steady pulse guiding you.\n\nThis is a day for grounding, for choosing presence over speed, for remembering that your strength doesn’t come from doing everything perfectly. It comes from standing in your truth like a pillar.\n\nLet yourself slow down. Let yourself breathe. Let yourself feel the quiet stability rising inside you.\n\nFrom that center, you can handle anything.	I am rooted, steady, and supported by the quiet strength within me.	Sit comfortably and close your eyes. Imagine walking through a peaceful district of the twilight city where tall glowing pillars rise between buildings.\n\nSee yourself approach a central pillar—a massive structure of stone and light. Place your hands upon it. Feel the warm resonance travel into your palms, up your arms, and through your spine.\n\nWith each breath, feel your body align. Feel your energy settle. Imagine roots extending gently from your feet into the ground, anchoring you in calm strength.\n\nLet this pillar represent the home inside you—the place that cannot be shaken. Sit with its grounding presence for a few moments.\n\nWhen you are ready, open your eyes, carrying that steadiness forward.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Pillar of Home", "content": "Aj is the nawal of the cane, the home, and the spine. It represents authority, leadership, and the staff of power. Aj is the energy of stability, family, and community integrity. It governs the spinal column and the home environment. In its shadow, Aj can manifest as rigidity, authoritarianism, or family problems. Its highest expression is the upright leader who supports the people like a strong pillar.", "keywords": ["Home", "Authority", "Cane", "Spine", "Leadership"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Dissolution", "content": "Eleven is the number of dissonance, change, and the breaking of patterns. It is the energy that disrupts the status quo to clear the way for higher order. Eleven tests the structures we have built. Experientially, an Eleven day can feel chaotic or liberating. It is the loose brick in the wall. The shadow of Eleven is overwhelm. It asks us to be flexible and to find freedom in letting things fall apart.", "keywords": ["Change", "Dissonance", "Liberation", "Testing", "Clearing"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Check the physical structure of your home (spine) for issues.", "Have an honest conversation about family dynamics.", "Release a rigid belief about how life 'should' be.", "Stretch your spine; practice yoga for flexibility.", "Stand tall in your own truth, even if it shakes the room."], "title": "Shaking the Pillars", "content": "Today, the disruptive force of Eleven meets the stabilizing energy of Aj. This is a day of 'Structural Testing' or 'Family Realignment.' The Eleven shakes the pillars of the home and the community to see if they are truly sound. It is a day where family secrets may come out, or where rigid authority figures are challenged. The energy can feel uncomfortable, as our sources of security (Aj) are being tested (Eleven). However, this is necessary for growth. If a structure survives the shaking of the Eleven, you know it is true. Use this day to examine the 'rules' of your house or your life. Are they supporting you, or are they constraining you? Be willing to let go of outdated traditions or rigid power dynamics. The goal is a home that is flexible enough to withstand the storm, not a fortress that cracks under pressure."}}	{"title": "The Reformer of Tradition", "content": "To be born on 11 Aj is to be a challenger of the established order within the home and community. You have a deep love for family and tradition (Aj), but the number Eleven makes you a non-conformist who cannot abide by rules that don't make sense. You are the 'black sheep' who ends up healing the family line. You see where the cracks are in the foundation and you aren't afraid to point them out. You have a natural authority, but it is a revolutionary authority.\\n\\nYour life path is one of redefining what 'home' and 'leadership' mean. You may experience upheaval in your early life that forces you to build your own sense of stability from the inside out. Your challenge is to not simply destroy for the sake of destruction. Your lesson is to use your power to renovate, not demolish. You are here to build a new kind of home—one that is strong enough to hold the truth."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d3b87c", "primary": "#111615", "secondary": "#4a4038"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.764226	2026-04-25 13:46:57.700143
51	4	12	12	Ix	You leave the pillar district with a steadiness that feels new. The streets welcome you back with softer rhythms, the twilight gentler than before. As you walk, the boundaries between the two cities—the broken and the luminous—begin to blur more noticeably.\n\nCracks in the pavement glow faintly with green-gold light. Moss forms intricate spirals along the walls. Windows shimmer with reflections not your own: glimpses of forests, mountains, waterfalls, starfields. The city feels alive today, breathing in long, patient cycles.\n\nSoon, you enter a part of the city where the buildings melt seamlessly into nature. Tree roots braid into staircases. Stone merges with living bark. Ferns unfurl from between glowing tiles. Soft mist drifts through archways formed from intertwined branches and steel.\n\nYou sense a presence—not watching you, but observing the city through you.\n\nThe air thickens with a low, velvety hum. Light gathers at the edges of the path in subtle geometric patterns. For a moment, the world becomes quieter than quiet.\n\nThen you see it.\n\nA jaguar-shaped silhouette, made not of fur but of shifting twilight colors—deep indigo, soft gold, muted green—stepping from behind a massive root structure. Its body glows faintly, as if touched by starlight. Its eyes are luminous pools of calm intelligence.\n\nYou freeze, but the jaguar’s presence is not dangerous. It is ancient. Sacred. Protective.\n\nIt doesn’t approach. It simply walks beside you, mirroring your pace. Wherever it steps, the path brightens—small flowers opening in its footsteps, stones humming with soft resonance. The jaguar’s breath is slow, grounded, steady.\n\nYou feel your senses sharpen.\n\nYou hear the heartbeat of the city.\n\nYou smell distant rain.\n\nYou feel energy rising through the ground like warm, living current.\n\nFor a moment, you understand the city not as two fractured layers, but as a single living spirit—vast, interconnected, aware.\n\nThe jaguar pauses before a stone archway covered in vines. You step toward it, and the vines bloom instantly with pale, glowing flowers. The air shifts into stillness again.\n\nThe jaguar meets your gaze.\n\nNot threatening, not pleading—only revealing.\n\nAnd you understand:\n\nMagic didn’t arrive here today.\n\nIt was always present.\n\nYou’re only now clear enough to feel it.\n\nWhen you pass through the archway, the jaguar dissolves into drifting motes of gold and green that scatter into the twilight.\n\nThe city breathes with you.\n\nEvery corner feels enchanted. Every sound feels intentional. Every movement feels part of a pattern older than you, older than any city.\n\nYou belong here now, not as a wanderer—but as someone who can finally sense the unseen threads that hold the world together.	Today brings subtle revelations—the quiet kind that settle into your bones rather than flash in your mind. You may sense deeper meaning in ordinary moments, or feel more connected to your surroundings.\n\nThis is intuition waking fully. Earth magic rising. Inner clarity gathering strength.\n\nTrust what you feel, even if you can’t explain it. Notice the signs that appear around you. This is a day to walk gently, listen closely, and let the world speak to you in its own language.	I honor the unseen magic in my life and trust the wisdom rising within me.	Close your eyes and imagine stepping into a part of the twilight city where buildings and forest blend into one living landscape.\n\nSee a jaguar-shaped being made of twilight light walking beside you. Feel its steady presence, its grounded steps, its deep awareness.\n\nAs you walk together, watch flowers bloom where it steps. Feel your senses sharpen—every sound clearer, every color richer.\n\nThe jaguar stops at a vine-covered archway. You step through it. Behind you, the jaguar dissolves into golden-green light.\n\nStand in the stillness that follows. Feel the earth beneath you humming with quiet magic.\n\nWhen you are ready, open your eyes, carrying that subtle awareness forward.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Jaguar of Magic", "content": "Ix is the nawal of the jaguar, the earth, and high magic. It represents the feminine power of nature and the mysteries of the night. Ix is the energy of the shaman and the healer. It governs the shrines and the sacred places of the earth. Ix energy is stealthy, powerful, and intuitive. In its shadow, Ix can be manipulative or secretive. Its highest expression is the wise use of spiritual power to heal and protect.", "keywords": ["Jaguar", "Magic", "Earth", "Feminine", "Shrine"]}, "number": {"title": "The Crystal of Understanding", "content": "Twelve is the number of understanding, summation, and the gathering of scattered parts into a whole. It represents the family, the tribe, and complex stability. Twelve is the 'council' number—it holds space for all previous experiences to be integrated. Experientially, a Twelve day feels rich and cooperative. It is a time to look back and see the lesson. The shadow of Twelve can be heaviness. It asks us to find unity in diversity.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Integration", "Community", "Summation", "Wholeness"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Visit a sacred site or a place of natural beauty with friends.", "Perform a gratitude ceremony for Mother Earth.", "Trust your intuition in social situations; you can see the unseen.", "Reflect on the 'magic' of everyday life.", "Send healing energy to the planet."], "title": "The Council of Earth Magic", "content": "When the integrative understanding of Twelve meets the earth magic of Ix, we have a day of 'Collective Magic' or 'Deep Wisdom.' The scattered energies of the trecena are now gathered into a powerful, magical whole. This is a day where the veil is thin and the earth is alive. It is a perfect day for group ceremonies, healing circles, or connecting with nature on a deep level. The Twelve brings a sense of community to the solitary jaguar, suggesting that our magic is stronger when we share it. You may feel a deep sense of understanding about the mysteries of your life—why things happened the way they did. The energy is rich, feminine, and grounding. The challenge is to hold the complexity; life is not simple, but it is magical. Trust your intuition (the jaguar) and lean on your community (the twelve)."}}	{"title": "The Earth Wisdom Keeper", "content": "To be born on 12 Ix is to be a powerful conduit for earth magic and community healing. You possess a deep, intuitive wisdom (Ix) backed by a broad understanding of human nature (Twelve). You are likely a healer, a counselor, or an environmentalist—someone who works to restore the balance between people and the planet. You have a mysterious, magnetic quality that draws people to you, but you also love your solitude. You are the 'village witch' or the 'wise elder' archetype, regardless of your age.\\n\\nYour life path is one of integrating the spiritual and the social. You are not meant to practice your magic in a cave; you are meant to bring it into the council circle. Your challenge is to manage your sensitivity. You feel the pain of the earth and the people deeply. Your lesson is to use your magic not to escape reality, but to transform it. You are here to remind us that the earth is sacred and that we are all connected."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c7d3ad", "primary": "#111d1d", "secondary": "#435953"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.765201	2026-04-25 13:46:57.701433
52	4	13	13	Tz'ikin	You feel it before you see it.\n\nA widening inside your chest. A soft pressure behind your eyes. A sense that the city—both the broken version and the luminous one—has stretched itself to make room for something vast.\n\nYou follow an upward current in the air, a pull gentle but insistent. Staircases appear where none existed before, spiraling along the outside of tall structures. Walkways extend like invitations. Platforms open like petals.\n\nYou climb.\n\nWith every level, the horizon expands. The twilight sky brightens into soft gradients of rose and amber, the first true hint of something like dawn. The higher you rise, the more the two cities blend—cracked stone glowing with golden seams, luminous towers showing faint outlines of rust beneath their radiance.\n\nAt the top of the final staircase, you reach an open terrace.\n\nWind moves through it—not cold, not harsh, but clean. Clearing.\n\nThe terrace is empty except for a single structure at its edge: a tall, delicate lattice of metal and light shaped like an unfinished spire. Its geometric patterns shift slowly, catching the rising glow of the sky.\n\nYou approach it, sensing that this is the highest place in the city—the point where vision is possible.\n\nThe sky changes.\n\nA ripple of gold crosses the horizon. Then another. Feathers of light begin forming in the air, drifting gently until they spiral upward. They gather above the spire, weaving themselves into the shape of a great bird—vast, luminous, made of shifting gold and shimmering twilight blue.\n\nAn eagle.\n\nIt doesn’t fully manifest. It is half energy, half outline, wings made of living light. But its presence is unmistakable. You feel it in your bones.\n\nThe eagle doesn’t descend. It lifts.\n\nAnd when it rises, your vision rises with it.\n\nSuddenly you see everything:\n\nThe shadow-city with its broken structures and memory-haunted streets.\nThe luminous city with its soft gold, gentle lines, and living architecture.\nThe forest district, the weaving plaza, the glowing path, the rooftop altar.\nEvery place you walked.\n\nEvery step you took.\n\nEvery moment you thought you were lost.\n\nFrom above, nothing is broken.\n\nNothing is separate.\n\nEverything belongs.\n\nThe eagle arcs through the air, scattering feathers of gold that drift down like blessings. One lands near your feet and dissolves into light, sending a warm surge up your spine and into your chest. It feels like gratitude. Like recognition. Like release.\n\nWhen you look up again, the eagle has risen into the brightening sky.\n\nThe city exhales.\n\nYou realize the trecena has carried you from the first crack of light into full vision—not a final destination, but a perspective wide enough to see where you might go next.\n\nEverything feels possible.\n\nEverything feels open.\n\nAnd for the first time, you are ready for whatever the next dawn brings.	Today brings vision.\n\nNot the kind that solves every problem at once, but the kind that widens your inner horizon. You may see connections that were invisible before, feel new clarity about your direction, or experience a sudden lift in your spirit.\n\nThis is a day for perspective—rising above doubt, confusion, and the noise of daily life to glimpse what truly matters.\n\nLet yourself be inspired. Let yourself dream bigger. Let yourself see the world from a vantage point you’ve earned.	I rise into clarity and welcome the vision that opens the next chapter of my life.	Close your eyes and imagine standing on a high terrace in the twilight city. The horizon stretches wide, glowing with soft gold and deep blue.\n\nA structure of light and metal rises beside you—a spire catching the first rays of a new dawn. Above it, feathers of golden light gather into the shape of a great eagle.\n\nAs the eagle lifts, feel your awareness lift with it. See the whole city from above: the broken places, the luminous places, the paths you walked, the moments of healing.\n\nLet this wide vision settle into your heart.\n\nWhen the eagle disappears into the brightening sky, breathe deeply and open your eyes, carrying that clarity with you.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Eagle of Vision", "content": "Tz'ikin is the nawal of the bird, the eagle, and vision. It represents prosperity, freedom, and the ability to see the big picture. Tz'ikin is the messenger between earth and sky. It governs abundance and business. Tz'ikin energy is optimistic, expansive, and high-flying. In its shadow, it can be distracted or greedy. Its highest expression is the visionary who manifests spiritual abundance for all.", "keywords": ["Vision", "Prosperity", "Eagle", "Freedom", "Abundance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Light of Ascension", "content": "Thirteen is the number of completion, ascension, and the spirit world. It represents the final step in the trecena cycle—the return to source at a higher level. Thirteen is the number of the ancestors and the 'invisible army.' Experientially, a Thirteen day feels mystical and surreal. It is a day of wrapping up and letting go. The shadow of Thirteen can be ungroundedness. It asks us to celebrate the journey.", "keywords": ["Completion", "Ascension", "Spirit", "Ancestors", "Renewal"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Write down your vision for the next year; dream without limits.", "Make a donation or share your wealth in some way.", "Look at the sky; watch for birds as messengers.", "Celebrate! Have a feast or a party to honor the completion of the cycle.", "Say 'thank you' for everything—the light and the dark."], "title": "Ascending Vision", "content": "We reach the culmination of the Aq'ab'al trecena with 13 Tz'ikin—the 'Ascended Vision' or 'Spiritual Abundance.' The cycle that began with the dawn of hope now ends with the high-flying view of the eagle. Today, you can see the entire journey clearly. The fog has lifted. The Thirteen elevates the prosperity of Tz'ikin to a spiritual level—it is a day of harvesting not just wealth, but wisdom and freedom. The energy is ecstatic, light, and expansive. It is a perfect day to dream big for the future, to give thanks for the abundance in your life, and to connect with the spirit world. The ancestors are celebrating with you. The challenge is to stay grounded enough to enjoy it. Don't just fly away; bring that eagle vision down to earth. Share your abundance. Realize that the dawn you hoped for on Day 1 has now become the full, bright sun of Day 13."}}	{"title": "The Cosmic Visionary", "content": "To be born on 13 Tz'ikin is to be a master of manifestation and a seer of high destinies. You possess a limitless imagination (Tz'ikin) backed by the power of the spirit world (Thirteen). You are a person who can make things happen simply by envisioning them. You have a natural connection to abundance and often live a life of freedom and prosperity. People are drawn to your optimism and your ability to see the best in everyone.\\n\\nYour life path is one of soaring above the mundane. You are not meant for smallness; you are meant for the sky. You may be a visionary entrepreneur, a spiritual teacher, or a philanthropist. Your challenge is to not lose touch with the ground. You can be so focused on the horizon that you trip over the stone in front of you. Your lesson is to bring your vision down to earth—to use your abundance to uplift others. You are here to show us that we are all meant to fly."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#aecab7", "primary": "#0f1c1c", "secondary": "#3a5754"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.76622	2026-04-25 13:46:57.70285
74	6	9	9	Ajpu	The path unrolls into a quiet grove where the trees are tall quills and the leaves are small, wax-sealed scrolls. This is the ripening of 9 Ajpu—the stage where purpose reaches its full gestation. The scrolls are heavy, laden with the 'heroic' truths of your journey, but they cannot be forced open. You must wait with feminine patience as the Sun of the Bazaar, now a permanent golden disc of silk, slowly warms the orchard. As the heat melts the seals, the wisdom within spills out as liquid light. You realize that your ordinary steps were always a search for this divinity. By waiting for the right moment to shine, you allow your ripened purpose to illuminate the road for all who follow.	The sky above you has finally ripened into a permanent, golden silk disc, and the air is thick with the scent of blooming jasmine and success. Today, your personal "hero’s journey" is reaching a point of significant fruition. You may feel a warm glow in your chest—a realization that the small, ordinary tasks you’ve performed were actually the holy labor of your soul’s purpose. The universe is inviting you to step into the role of the "Sun Hero," acknowledging your own brilliance without a shred of sanctimony. This is a day of deep creative fulfillment and the "golden" clarity of the spirit. You don't need to chase the light today; you simply need to let it shine through your actions. There is a profound nurturing strength in the atmosphere, encouraging you to care for your goals as if they were a garden nearing harvest. If you feel a surge of courage, use it to speak your truth with the soft certainty of a ripening fruit. You are becoming the master of your own divinity, proving that the most heroic thing you can do is to be authentically yourself.	I shine my light with humble authority, acknowledging the holiness in every step I take.	Close your eyes and visualize a small, golden sun glowing in the center of your belly. Breathe deeply, feeling the warmth of this sun ripen your intentions and dreams. Imagine you are a fruit on a sacred tree, soaking up the light and growing heavy with the sweetness of your own purpose. There is no rush; there is only the ripening.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, enter the Orchard of Glowing Wax. See the quill-trees with their scroll-leaves sealed in violet wax. Sit beneath the silk sun of the bazaar and watch as its heat slowly melts the seals of your own story. As the liquid light spills out, realize that your ordinary journey has been a heroic search for this very divinity, now fully gestated and ready to shine.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Solar Hero", "content": "Ajpu is the Nawal of the Sun, the blowgunner, and the spiritual warrior. It represents the divine spark within the human being—the light that conquers darkness. Ajpu is the energy of leadership, clarity, and the hero's journey. It governs the search for truth and the overcoming of obstacles through certainty and skill. In human experience, Ajpu manifests as confidence, artistic talent, and a connection to the divine. It is the face of the sun shining on the path. When aligned, Ajpu brings success and enlightenment; when misaligned, it can lead to ego or judgment.", "keywords": ["Sun", "Hero", "Divinity", "Purpose", "Leadership"]}, "number": {"title": "The Womb of Patience", "content": "The number Nine represents the completion of the developmental cycle, the gestation period (9 months), and the energy of the feminine. In Mayan cosmology, Nine is associated with the 'Primordial Female' and the deep, dark soil where the seed transforms. Experientially, this energy feels introspective, creative, and sometimes slow. It is the patience of the mother waiting for the birth. It is a time for nurturing, refining details, and preparing for the final manifestation. The shadow of Nine can be isolation, but its light is the profound power of life generating life.", "keywords": ["Patience", "Gestation", "Feminine", "Completion", "Nurturing"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Connect with the feminine aspect of the divine.", "Nurture your creative talents in private; practice your art.", "Honor the women who have been heroes in your life.", "Spend time in the sun to recharge your spiritual battery.", "Trust that your time to shine is coming; today, just glow."], "title": "Hidden Divinity", "content": "The feminine, gestating energy of Tone 9 meets the masculine, solar power of Ajpu to create a day of 'Inner Light.' 9 Ajpu is the sun in the womb—the hidden potential of the hero. It represents the feminine aspect of leadership and the spiritual warrior who fights with compassion rather than force. The energy today is soft, warm, and deeply illuminating. It is a day to nurture your own divinity, to recognize the god/goddess within, and to prepare for a time when you will shine more brightly. It favors artistic projects, spiritual study, and connecting with the women in your life who embody strength. The hero is resting today, gathering strength and wisdom before the next battle. Use this time to polish your mirror so that when you do step out, you reflect the light perfectly. You are gold in the crucible."}}	{"title": "The Spiritual Artist", "content": "To be born on 9 Ajpu is to carry a light that is both brilliant and nurturing. You are the 'Goddess of the Sun'—a soul who blends the heroic qualities of Ajpu with the deep, feminine wisdom of the number 9. You are likely an artist, a healer, or a spiritual teacher, using your talents to uplift and inspire others. You have a quiet confidence; you don't need to shout to be heard. Your presence alone brings warmth and clarity to a room.\\n\\nYour life path is one of incubating the divine. You are here to bring new forms of light into the world—whether through art, children, or spiritual movements. You understand that true heroism involves patience and the ability to hold space for growth. Your challenge is to balance your high ideals with the messy reality of human life, and to ensure that you do not hide your light out of humility. You are the dawn that promises the day; let yourself rise."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d4b56c", "primary": "#1a140d", "secondary": "#633e1f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.778384	2026-04-25 14:38:01.300956
109	9	5	5	Tijax					{"nawal": {"title": "The Obsidian Blade", "content": "Tijax is the Nawal of the obsidian blade, the double-edged sword of truth. It represents the energy of the warrior and the healer—the one who cuts to cure. Tijax governs discernment, drastic changes, and the removal of negative energies or illnesses. In human experience, Tijax manifests as sharp wit, the courage to speak the truth, and a talent for cutting through illusion. It is the lightning strike that clears the air. When aligned, Tijax brings liberation and healing; when misaligned, it can lead to harshness, gossip, or conflict.", "keywords": ["Truth", "Healing", "Discernment", "Cutting", "Purification"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Action", "content": "The number Five represents the center point of the first wave of creation. It is the energy of the hand (five fingers) and the power to grasp, work, and manipulate reality. In Mayan cosmology, Five is the force of 'doing'; it breaks the static stability of Four and puts it into motion through effort. Experientially, this energy feels like a surge of willpower and a drive to get things done. It is the number of work, discipline, and the application of energy. The shadow of Five can be forcing things, but its light is the satisfaction of a job well done.", "keywords": ["Action", "Discipline", "Work", "Willpower", "Effort"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Actively remove clutter or 'dead weight' from your life.", "Engage in a detox or cleansing practice.", "Have a courageous conversation to clear up a misunderstanding.", "Work on a project that requires sharp focus and editing.", "Cut the cord of an addiction through sheer willpower."], "title": "The Work of Healing", "content": "When the hardworking energy of Tone 5 meets the cutting power of Tijax, we engage in the 'Discipline of Truth.' 5 Tijax is a day to work hard on your healing. It is not a passive process; it requires the effort of the surgeon. The energy asks you to actively cut away what is not working—bad habits, negative thoughts, or toxic relationships. It is a day of 'spiritual sweat.' You may feel a drive to clean, to purge, or to have the difficult conversations that clear the air. The obsidian blade is in your hand (5); use it with precision and effort. This is also a powerful day for physical healing that requires intervention or discipline, such as surgery, physical therapy, or a detox regimen. The energy is sharp and demanding, but ultimately liberating. Do the work of cutting the cords, and you will be free."}}	{"title": "The Disciplined Warrior", "content": "To be born on 5 Tijax is to be a warrior for truth and a tireless worker for healing. You are the 'Active Surgeon'—a soul who is not afraid to do the hard, messy work of fixing what is broken. You possess a sharp mind and a strong will. You are likely the person who steps in to solve the crisis while everyone else is panicking. You have a talent for discernment and can spot a lie or a flaw from a mile away.\\n\\nYour life path is one of purification through effort. You are here to refine reality, to cut away the excess and reveal the diamond underneath. The number 5 gives you the stamina to keep going when things get tough. Your challenge is to temper your blade with compassion; sometimes you work so hard to 'fix' things (or people) that you forget to be gentle. You are here to show us that healing is an active verb, and that the truth, while sharp, is the only thing that sets us free."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d1ad99", "primary": "#101210", "secondary": "#493832"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.803253	2026-04-25 13:46:57.858333
41	4	2	2	K'at	The door’s thin line of light stays behind you as you walk, a quiet reminder that not everything is sealed shut.\n\nThe street bends sooner than it should.\n\nYou take a turn, then another, and realize the city has begun to fold in on itself. Alleys loop back to where you started. Stairways spiral down only to rise again a block away. Overhead, cables sag between buildings in heavy curves, draped like nets that were thrown and never pulled back in.\n\nYou follow a narrow passage, convinced this one is new. A rusted fire escape leans against a wall. Old banners hang in strips, their colors eaten by time. Neon tubing snakes along the brick, sometimes lit, sometimes dead. At first it looks random.\n\nThen you notice the pattern.\n\nWherever you go, the same shapes repeat: arcs, loops, crossings. Wires braided together, then knotted around support beams. Streets that cross at odd angles, then double back. Reflections in dark windows that show you not where you are, but where you just came from.\n\nThe city is full of nets.\n\nYou pause beneath a junction where dozens of cables converge. Some are bright, pulsing softly with hidden power. Others are slack and lifeless, still tied into the bundle as if no one ever thought to cut them free.\n\nYou feel a tug in your chest.\n\nMemories rise without being invited. Old promises you made to keep the peace. Roles you stepped into so no one would be disappointed. Burdens you picked up because it seemed easier than watching someone else struggle.\n\nThey weave together inside you the way these cables do above your head.\n\nFor a moment you feel trapped, like one more strand in the knot. The air grows tight. The city seems to lean closer, waiting to see what you will do.\n\nYou reach out and touch one of the wires. It hums faintly, warm under your fingertips. Images flicker at the edge of your vision: faces, places, habits, timelines. Some carry a steady glow that feels like love, like genuine connection. Others buzz with a sharp, draining ache.\n\nYou realize you do not have to tear everything down.\n\nYou only have to decide what still belongs.\n\nGently, you imagine one dead cable loosening from the bundle. You picture it slipping free of the knot, sliding down the wall, coiling harmlessly at your feet. In your chest, a similar strand gives way, an old obligation softening, no longer fused to your sense of self.\n\nThe city does not transform all at once. The streets are still confusing, the wires still tangled. Yet in one small section of sky, the nets thin just enough that you can see a patch of softer light above, a hint of the other city shining through.\n\nYou stand beneath the crossing lines and breathe.\n\nYou are not required to carry every thread forever.	Today may highlight the invisible nets in your life: the promises, roles, and patterns that quietly decide how you move, often without your conscious consent.\n\nYou might notice where you say yes out of habit, where you feel responsible for holding everything together, or where your energy leaks away in situations that no longer fit who you are becoming.\n\nThis is not a call to burn every bridge or drop every duty. It is an invitation to look closer. Which threads in your life feel alive, reciprocal, and truthful? Which feel dead, heavy, or tangled with resentment and guilt?\n\nAllow yourself to loosen one strand. Step back from one obligation that has been tightening around your spirit. Create a little space in the weave of your days. The moment you do, light begins to filter through the gaps, and you remember that your worth is not measured by how much you carry, but by how honestly you choose.	I gently loosen the knots in my life and choose to carry only what truly nourishes my heart.	Sit comfortably and let your breath slow. Close your eyes and imagine yourself walking through the twilight city, following streets that keep looping back on themselves.\n\nAbove you, see cables and glowing threads strung between the buildings, crossing and knotting into dense nets. Let these strands represent all the roles, expectations, and obligations you have taken on.\n\nNow, imagine that some of the threads glow with a warm, steady light. These are the connections and commitments that truly feed you. Others look dull, frayed, or lifeless. These are the burdens you carry out of habit, fear, or old agreements.\n\nChoose one dim strand. In your mind, reach up and touch it. Feel any emotion that arises. Then visualize the knot in that strand slowly loosening. The thread slips free from the bundle and drifts down, dissolving into soft light at your feet.\n\nOffer quiet gratitude to the ancestors and lineages who understood the power of weaving and unweaving, of tying and releasing. Take three slow breaths, feeling a little more space in your chest each time. When you are ready, open your eyes and carry that sense of gentle release into the rest of your day.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Net of Abundance", "content": "K'at is the nawal of the net, the web, and the gathering. It represents the energy of connection, abundance, and the harvest. K'at is the lizard who carries the seed and the mesh bag that holds the corn. It governs the gathering of people and resources. However, the net can also represent entanglement—debts, burdens, and traps. In its shadow, K'at can manifest as feeling trapped or hoarding. Its highest expression is the ability to gather what nurtures and release what weighs us down.", "keywords": ["Net", "Gathering", "Abundance", "Entanglement", "Release"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "Two is the energy of polarity, partnership, and the interaction between opposites. It represents the separation of the One into two—masculine and feminine, light and dark. Two brings choices into focus and emphasizes relationships. Experientially, a Two day feels like a dialogue. It asks for balance and cooperation. The shadow of Two can be indecision or conflict. It teaches us that we define ourselves through our reflection in the other.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Balance", "Partnership", "Choice", "Reflection"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Sort through physical items (clothes, papers) and donate what you don't need.", "Evaluate a partnership: is the energy exchange balanced?", "Visualize cutting energetic cords to past burdens.", "Have a conversation with a partner about shared resources or debts.", "Practice the mantra: 'I release what binds me; I keep what frees me.'"], "title": "Choosing What to Carry", "content": "When the polarizing choice of Two meets the gathering net of K'at, we have a day of 'Selective Gathering' or 'Relationship Sorting.' Today asks you to look at your net—your relationships, your possessions, your commitments—and make a choice. What are you carrying that is truly yours? What are you carrying that belongs to someone else? The Two brings a mirror to your entanglements. It is a powerful day for decluttering, both physically and emotionally. You may find yourself at a crossroads in a partnership, deciding whether to weave your nets together or cut the cord. The energy supports cooperation, but only if it is balanced. The challenge is indecision; K'at wants to keep everything 'just in case,' while Two weighs the pros and cons. Use the discernment of the Two to lighten your load. Keep the connections that feed your soul; release the ones that trap your spirit."}}	{"title": "The Weaver of Relationships", "content": "To be born on 2 K'at is to be a master of connection and a weaver of community. You possess a natural charm and a talent for bringing people together. The number Two gives you a relational focus—you thrive in partnerships—while K'at gives you the ability to gather resources and opportunities. You are likely the 'hub' of your social circle, the one who connects friends, organizes events, and holds the group together. You have a gift for abundance and often find yourself surrounded by material and social wealth.\\n\\nYour life path involves learning the art of discernment in relationships. Because you attract so many people and possibilities, you can easily become entangled in drama or weighed down by the needs of others. You may struggle with saying no or with codependency. Your lesson is to learn that you cannot carry everyone in your net. You must choose your partners wisely. When you do, your ability to create abundance is amplified, and you become a powerful force for cooperative success."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b4b37a", "primary": "#121412", "secondary": "#474230"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#863b36", "primary": "#060b1a", "secondary": "#221938"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#887655", "primary": "#0e182b", "secondary": "#2c404d"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#32314b", "primary": "#020f22", "secondary": "#081b39"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.754531	2026-04-25 13:46:57.706643
44	4	5	5	Kej	You walk until the city thins into a fringe of broken structures. Something in the air shifts — a scent you haven’t smelled since before this strange place swallowed your sense of direction. Earth. Moss. Cold stone warmed by sunlight you can’t see.\n\nA narrow archway of crumbling concrete opens before you, cracked down the middle as if split by a growing tree. Light spills through the break, brighter than anything you’ve seen since arriving. You step toward it, expecting another illusion.\n\nBut when you cross the threshold, the ground changes.\n\nConcrete gives way to soil. Twilight becomes a muted forest glow. The dual cities fall silent behind you.\n\nYou stand in a wild sanctuary hidden inside the broken geometry of the urban world. Towering roots push through old pavement. Ferns drink the pale light. Ancient stone pillars rise between the trees like remnants of a forgotten temple, their surfaces carved with motifs worn soft by time.\n\nThe forest is quiet, but not empty.\n\nA subtle presence watches you — not with eyes, but with a steady, grounded intelligence that belongs to things that survive by being still. The sensation settles into your bones. You are being evaluated, not judged. Measured, not weighed.\n\nYou move slowly between the roots until you reach a clearing where four stone pillars form a square. Their tops glow faintly, each pulsing with the rhythm of a heartbeat. When you approach, the air thickens, and the ground seems to breathe.\n\nA shape emerges from the edge of the clearing. Not an animal, not a person — more like a silhouette woven from forest-light and dusk. It carries the outline of antlers, but they are made of fractured beams of soft gold. Its steps are silent. Its presence is calm.\n\nThe deer-shaped guardian stands before you, and the clearing steadies.\n\nEverything steadies.\n\nYour breath slows. Your thoughts loosen. The wild stillness enters you like a medicine you didn’t know you needed.\n\nIn this place, nothing demands. Nothing rushes. Nothing hides its truth.\n\nYou feel the weight of your body again, not as burden but as belonging. You feel your spine lengthen, your feet root into the earth, your heart settle into a rhythm older than fear.\n\nThe guardian tilts its luminous head, acknowledging your presence without expectation. Then, with a soft shimmer, it dissolves into drifting specks of gold that fade into the canopy.\n\nThe clearing remains.\n\nYou place your hand on one of the pillars. It hums gently beneath your palm, grounding you further. You realize the forest is not an escape from the city. It is part of it — a memory of balance waiting to rise through the cracks.\n\nYou close your eyes.\n\nFor the first time in a long while, you feel strong without forcing it.	Today brings strength, but the soft kind — the kind that doesn’t roar or push, the kind that steadies you from the inside out.\n\nYou may feel a quiet clarity rising, a desire to act from grounded truth instead of stress or habit. This is the power of the forest within you, the part that knows how to set a pace you can sustain.\n\nChoose one action that feels rooted rather than rushed. Let your decisions come from your spine, not your fear. A sense of sacred alignment is forming beneath the surface, guiding your steps with steadiness.\n\nTrust the choices that make your breath deepen, not the ones that make it quicken.	I move with grounded strength and let steady truth guide my actions.	Close your eyes and imagine stepping through a cracked concrete archway into a hidden forest growing inside the city. Feel the ground shift beneath your feet — soil instead of pavement, roots instead of wires.\n\nIn the center of this wild space, see four stone pillars forming a square of gentle light. Approach them slowly. Let your breath match the steady rhythm you feel in the air.\n\nA deer-shaped guardian appears at the forest’s edge, formed of golden dusk and soft-shadow light. It stands calmly, watching you without expectation. Feel its presence settle your body. Notice your spine lengthening, your breath deepening, your energy grounding.\n\nImagine placing your hand on one of the glowing pillars. A warm pulse travels up your arm and spreads through your chest, rooting you into the earth.\n\nThank the ancient nature guardians who held balance long before cities rose. When you are ready, step back into your body, carrying the forest’s steadiness with you.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Stag of the Wild", "content": "Kej is the nawal of the deer, the four directions, and the natural world. It represents the balance between the wild and the tame, the spiritual and the physical. Kej is the guardian of the forest and the conductor of natural harmony. It governs strength, agility, and the authority of the shaman. In its shadow, Kej can be dominating or stubborn. Its highest expression is the graceful leadership that respects the laws of nature.", "keywords": ["Deer", "Nature", "Strength", "Balance", "Wilderness"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Effort", "content": "Five is the number of work, empowerment, and the human hand. It represents the energy of applying will and effort to move things forward. Five is the center point that drives the four directions into action. It is an industrious, net-gathering energy. Experientially, a Five day asks for participation; it is not a day for passivity. The shadow of Five can be forcing things or overworking. It reminds us that we have the power to shape our reality.", "keywords": ["Work", "Action", "Effort", "Empowerment", "Center"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Spend time working in a garden or cleaning up a natural space.", "Go for a strong hike or walk to engage your legs (the deer's power).", "Take a leadership role in a project, but lead with grace.", "Use your voice to advocate for the environment.", "Stand in the center of a room and visualize connecting to the four directions."], "title": "Working with Nature", "content": "Today, the industrious energy of Five combines with the natural strength of Kej to create a day of 'Active Harmony' or 'Wild Effort.' The energy asks you to put your hands to work, but to do so in alignment with natural rhythms. It is not about forcing a result (which Five can sometimes do), but about working *with* the flow of nature (Kej). It is a perfect day for physical labor, gardening, hiking, or any activity that engages the body and the earth. You have extra strength and stamina today. The 'Four Directions' of Kej are activated by the 'Center' of the Five, creating a powerful vortex of stability and action. The challenge is to avoid dominance. Don't try to conquer nature or others; try to harmonize with them. Use your strength to protect, to build, and to serve the balance. Effort applied today with respect will yield a strong and lasting result."}}	{"title": "The Guardian of the Wild", "content": "To be born on 5 Kej is to be a force of nature and a tireless worker for harmony. You possess a unique blend of physical stamina (Five) and natural nobility (Kej). You are a person of action, not just words. When you see something out of balance—in your community or in the environment—you step in to fix it. You have a strong connection to the earth and may feel most at home in the wilderness. You are a natural leader who leads by example, often taking on the heavy lifting yourself.\\n\\nYour life path is one of service to the natural order. You may be drawn to environmentalism, animal welfare, or outdoor leadership. You have a 'shamanic' quality—an ability to sense the energies of the land and the people around you. Your challenge is stubbornness. You can be so sure of your path that you refuse to listen to others. Your lesson is to remain flexible like the deer, adapting your strength to the changing terrain. You are here to remind us that true power comes from working in harmony with life."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#7d8850", "primary": "#0e100e", "secondary": "#38392a"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#853b36", "primary": "#060b1a", "secondary": "#221938"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#8d7754", "primary": "#0e182b", "secondary": "#2e434f"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#6b444c", "primary": "#021023", "secondary": "#0d2040"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.757937	2026-04-25 13:46:57.712052
40	4	1	1	Aq'ab'al	You wake in a city that never quite reaches night and never fully arrives at day.\n\nThe sky above the towers is the color of old bruises and faded neon, a dim violet-grey that bleeds into every alley and window. Streetlights flicker without rhythm. Some stay lit with a stubborn, buzzing glow. Others blink on and off like they are trying to remember how to shine.\n\nYou are standing in the middle of an empty street.\n\nThe buildings around you lean in close, their glass cracked, their signs half-dead. Holoscreens loop old advertisements in colors that have forgotten how to be bright. Somewhere far off, a low hum trembles through the ground — power running through old cables, or something older moving beneath the foundation.\n\nYou do not remember how you came here, only that something inside you was too tired to keep pretending everything was fine.\n\nAs your eyes adjust, you notice that the darkness is not complete. Thin seams of light hide in the cracks: a glow beneath a rusted door, a soft line where two walls don’t quite meet, a faint shimmer tracing the outline of a stairwell leading somewhere you cannot see.\n\nFor a moment, you stand very still.\n\nYou feel the weight of something you have not wanted to face — a quiet ache buried under routines, distractions, and the mechanical motion of getting through the day. It lives in your chest like a room with the light turned off.\n\nThe city around you feels like that room.\n\nA stray breeze moves through the street, carrying the scent of metal, rain, and something almost sweet, like distant blossoms you cannot locate. A single sign above a doorway buzzes, flickers, and then steadies into a soft, unwavering glow.\n\nIt is nothing dramatic.\n\nJust one more light deciding, for now, not to go out.\n\nYou step toward it.\n\nAs you walk, you notice more details. A broken window filled with carefully arranged candles, some burned low, some barely touched. A balcony garden clinging to life despite cracked concrete and stale air, leaves tilted toward whatever faint light they can find. A mural peeling from a wall, its colors faded but its message still visible: a figure standing between night and day, holding a lantern.\n\nYou feel something shift inside you — not a sudden revelation, not a miracle, just the smallest willingness to look directly at what hurts.\n\nYou reach the doorway beneath the glowing sign and place your hand against the cool metal. For a breath, nothing happens. Then, somewhere deep within the building, a lock unclicks, a mechanism stirs, and a slender line of light appears along the frame.\n\nThe door does not open yet.\n\nBut it is no longer fully closed.\n\nYou exhale without realizing you were holding your breath. The city around you still looks broken, still looks tired. Yet in the thin glow of that almost-open door, you feel something fragile and persistent rise in your chest.\n\nIt isn’t certainty.\n\nIt is the first, quiet thought that maybe you are allowed to hope again.	Today is not about dramatic breakthroughs. It is about noticing the first cracks in the wall you built around your own heart.\n\nYou may find yourself seeing your life with slightly clearer eyes — recognizing a pattern you can’t ignore anymore, admitting a feeling you’ve been pushing away, or sensing that the numbness you’ve relied on is starting to thin.\n\nThis is the energy of the first door becoming slightly unstuck.\n\nYou don’t have to walk through it yet. You don’t have to have a plan. Just let yourself admit what you see. Honor the small, quiet part of you that wants more light, more truth, more real connection.\n\nThe city of your life may still look cracked and tired in places, but one sign is flickering back on. Pay attention.	I welcome the first cracks of light in my life and allow small, honest truths to guide my next step.	Find a place where you can sit quietly, even for a few minutes. Close your eyes and imagine yourself standing in a dim, quiet street in a city at perpetual twilight.\n\nSee the worn buildings, the flickering signs, the long shadows. Let this city gently represent the parts of your life that feel tired, stuck, or unresolved.\n\nNow, imagine one small sign above a doorway beginning to glow steadily. No drama, no fanfare — just one light deciding not to go out.\n\nBring your attention to your chest and ask softly, “Where is the first light returning in my life?” Do not force an answer. Let an image, a feeling, or a simple word arise.\n\nOffer a quiet thank you to the peoples and ancestors who honored the in-between times — dawn, dusk, thresholds — and treated them as sacred moments of turning. Take one more slow breath, then open your eyes, carrying that thin but real light with you.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Dawn of Possibility", "content": "Aq'ab'al is the nawal of the dawn, the twilight, and the threshold between night and day. It represents the bridge between the dream world and the waking world. Aq'ab'al is the energy of new hope, clarity, and the realization of potential. It governs the polarity of young and old, darkness and light. Experientially, Aq'ab'al feels like the first breath of morning air—full of promise but still holding the mystery of the night. In its shadow, it can manifest as hesitation, confusion, or the deception of the half-light. Its highest expression is the clear vision that emerges when the sun illuminates the darkness.", "keywords": ["Dawn", "Hope", "Threshold", "Duality", "Renewal"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Fire", "content": "One is the number of beginnings, unity, and the primordial spark. It represents the seed containing infinite potential—the point of creation before it expands into form. In the Mayan cosmology, One is the day of initiation and planting intentions. It is the 'I Am' energy, singular and focused. Experientially, a One day feels fresh, potent, and sometimes quiet, like the moment before a speech begins. It is the best day to start a new cycle or launch a new concept. The shadow of One can be isolation or a lack of momentum if the seed is not watered. It asks us to be the origin point of our own reality.", "keywords": ["Beginnings", "Unity", "Potential", "Seed", "Initiation"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Wake up before sunrise to witness the physical dawn and set your intention.", "Start a 'dream journal' to capture the wisdom of the night.", "Identify one area of your life that feels 'stuck in the dark' and ask for light.", "Light a candle to symbolize the return of the sun.", "Write down your main goal for this 13-day cycle."], "title": "Initiating the New Dawn", "content": "The convergence of the initiating force of One with the dawn energy of Aq'ab'al creates a powerful portal for new beginnings. Today is the 'Seed of Hope' or the 'First Light.' It marks the start of a 13-day cycle dedicated to clarity, transition, and bringing dreams into reality. The energy is incredibly fertile for conceiving new projects, relationships, or habits. You are standing on the threshold of a new chapter. The One gives you the focus to plant the seed, while Aq'ab'al provides the fertile soil of possibility. It is a day to be gentle with yourself, as new beginnings are often tender. The challenge is the fear of the unknown—stepping out of the comfortable dark and into the revealing light. Trust the transition. Initiate the change you wish to see, knowing that the dawn is inevitable."}}	{"title": "The Bringer of Dawn", "content": "To be born on 1 Aq'ab'al is to be a pioneer of hope and a catalyst for new beginnings. You carry the energy of the first light—optimistic, fresh, and full of potential. The number One gives you a strong sense of individuality and the drive to start things, while Aq'ab'al connects you to the mysteries of transition and duality. You are likely a person who is always looking forward, the one who spots the silver lining before anyone else. You have a youthful spirit that remains vibrant regardless of your age.\\n\\nYour life path is one of constant renewal. You may find yourself frequently starting over or reinventing yourself, not out of failure, but out of a desire for fresh experience. You are a natural bridge-builder, comfortable in the spaces between 'this' and 'that.' Your challenge is to follow through. You are great at the spark (One) and the dawn (Aq'ab'al), but you must learn to endure the heat of the midday sun. Your lesson is to trust that your light is enough to dispel any darkness you encounter. You are here to remind the world that it is never too late to begin again."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#bdac88", "primary": "#0d1615", "secondary": "#423d3a"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#6e4c36", "primary": "#0c1115", "secondary": "#202631"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#de984f", "primary": "#4e3a68", "secondary": "#806880"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#66636d", "primary": "#1b262f", "secondary": "#3f4247"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.753649	2026-04-25 13:46:57.697321
53	5	1	1	B'atz'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Weaver of Time", "content": "B'atz' is the Nawal of the thread, the weaver, and the continuous unfolding of time itself. It represents the creative life force that spins the universe into existence, connecting past, present, and future into a single, vibrant tapestry. As the archetype of the artist and the organizer, B'atz' governs all forms of creative expression, from the fine arts to the way we structure our days. In human experience, this energy manifests as the urge to create, to connect with others, and to celebrate the beauty of existence. It is the thread of destiny that links us to our ancestors and our future lineage. When aligned, B'atz' brings flow, beauty, and synchronization; when misaligned, it can lead to feeling tangled, overwhelmed by details, or anxious about time running out. It is the master artisan of reality.", "keywords": ["Creativity", "Weaving", "Time", "Artistry", "Initiation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Fire", "content": "The number One represents the primordial spark, the moment before explosion, and the unity of all things. It is the seed that contains the entire blueprint of the forest within its tiny shell. In the Mayan cosmology, One is the energy of initiation and firm beginnings; it is not merely a start, but a powerful concentration of potential that requires focus and intent. Experientially, this energy feels like a surge of inspiration or a sudden clarity of purpose—a 'yes' ringing out in the silence. It asks you to stand alone if necessary, to be the single point of origin for a new cycle. The shadow of One can be isolation or a failure to launch due to the overwhelming weight of potential, but its light is the unstoppable force of creation itself. Today, you are the origin point.", "keywords": ["Unity", "Potential", "Initiation", "Seed", "Focus"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Plant the seed of a new creative project today; the energy supports long-term growth.", "Set a clear intention for the next 260 days, as this day often initiates larger cycles.", "Engage in a small act of physical creation—drawing, writing, or building—to ground the energy.", "Trust your aesthetic intuition; if something feels beautiful, it is likely the right path.", "Do not rush the beginning; treat the start of this cycle as a sacred ceremony."], "title": "Initiating the Great Weave", "content": "When the initiating power of Tone 1 meets the creative mastery of B'atz', we enter a day of profound origin. Today is the beginning of the beginning—the moment the first thread is chosen for a new tapestry of time. This combined energy is electric with possibility; it is the ideal moment to start a creative project, launch a business, or set a new life pattern into motion. The energy feels like standing before a blank canvas with a brush full of paint, knowing that the first stroke will define the entire composition. It is a day to honor the sanctity of beginnings and to recognize that you are the weaver of your own reality. The challenge today lies in overcoming the inertia of the void; the blank page can be intimidating. However, the synthesis of One and B'atz' provides the spark needed to break the silence. You are being asked to pick up the thread and make the first knot. What you begin today carries the blessing of longevity and artistic grace."}}	{"title": "The Primal Artisan", "content": "To be born on 1 B'atz' is to be a divinely appointed initiator of beauty and culture. You carry the energy of the 'First Thread'—a person who does not just follow trends but starts them. Your soul is hardwired to weave people, ideas, and timelines together into cohesive, functioning wholes. You likely have a strong sense of destiny and a natural charisma that draws others into your orbit, often serving as the spark that gets community projects or artistic movements moving. You are the one who picks up the instrument first, who breaks the silence, who proposes the plan.\\n\\nYour life path is one of creative leadership. Unlike those who lead by force, you lead by fascination and rhythm. You have an innate understanding of cycles and timing, knowing exactly when to act and when to wait. People look to you to set the tempo. However, because you carry the energy of the 'seed' (1), you may sometimes feel the pressure of potential—the sense that you must constantly be birthing something new. Your challenge is to trust that the thread you spin is strong enough to hold, and that you don't need to restart constantly; you just need to keep weaving."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#dac48c", "primary": "#131613", "secondary": "#4e3e2d"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.768163	2026-04-25 13:46:57.724786
181	14	12	12	Tijax					{"nawal": {"title": "The Cosmic Knife", "content": "Tijax is the obsidian blade, the mirror, and the healer. It represents the power to cut away illness, illusion, and negativity. Tijax is the warrior for truth who removes what is dead to save the patient. It is the energy of the surgeon and the spark of the flint. It reveals the truth inside the stone.", "keywords": ["Healing", "Cutting", "Obsidian", "Truth", "Purification"]}, "number": {"title": "The Crystal of Understanding", "content": "The number 12 represents understanding, wisdom, and the bundling of experience. It is the highest even number, representing a stable, complex wholeness. 12 brings the capacity to understand the 'why' of the journey and to synthesize lessons. In the Kej trecena, 12 brings the healing power of understanding.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Wisdom", "Synthesis", "Community", "Review"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Identify the root cause of a recurring problem.", "Make a decisive cut to end a toxic pattern.", "Seek a healer who understands the whole system.", "Review your life and edit out the distractions.", "Thank the 'knife' for the clarity it brings."], "title": "The Wisdom of Healing", "content": "12 Tijax is a day of profound, comprehensive healing. The wisdom of the 12 guides the blade of Tijax. In the Kej trecena, this is where we understand *what* needs to be cut and *why*. It is a day of surgical precision applied with the compassion of a master healer. We can see the root cause of our imbalance. It is a day to edit our lives, to remove what is no longer healthy, and to do so with a sense of wholeness. The energy is sharp but stable. We cut to cure, not to wound."}}	{"title": "The Master Healer", "content": "To be born on 12 Tijax is to be a surgeon of the soul. You possess a sharp intellect and a deep, accumulated wisdom about healing. You are not a dabbler; you are a master. You see the truth instantly and have the courage to name it. You are here to help humanity cut away the illusions that cause suffering. You have a stable, authoritative presence that inspires trust in those who are broken.\\n\\nYour life path is one of refinement and restoration. You may be drawn to medicine, therapy, or critical analysis. You have a talent for seeing the diamond in the rough and cutting away the excess to reveal it. You understand that healing is a holistic process.\\n\\nYour challenge is harshness. Your truth is so sharp that it can wound if not delivered with care. You may also struggle with perfectionism. Your lesson is to wield the blade with love. When you combine your discernment with the wisdom of the heart, you become a miraculous healer, helping the world become whole again."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#caaa8f", "primary": "#111211", "secondary": "#503d35"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.844324	2026-04-25 13:46:57.946
63	5	11	11	Imox					{"nawal": {"title": "The Primordial Dreamer", "content": "Imox is the Nawal of the water, the lizard/crocodile, and the collective subconscious. It represents the primordial soup from which all things emerge. Imox is the energy of dreams, intuition, and the fluid, chaotic nature of the mind. In human experience, Imox manifests as wild creativity, psychic ability, and a connection to the 'crazy' wisdom of the universe. It is the ocean that can be a calm mirror or a raging storm. When aligned, Imox brings profound inspiration and adaptability; when misaligned, it can lead to emotional instability, confusion, or losing touch with reality. It is the dream that dreams us.", "keywords": ["Water", "Dreams", "Intuition", "Subconscious", "Creativity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Change", "content": "The number Eleven represents dissonance, resolution through change, and the stripping away of the non-essential. In Mayan cosmology, Eleven is a high-frequency energy that shakes the foundation to test its strength. It is not necessarily negative, but it is turbulent. Experientially, this energy feels like a strong wind or a sudden shift in plans. It breaks the static perfection of Ten to allow for higher growth. The shadow of Eleven can be chaos or confusion, but its light is liberation and the clearing of the path. Today, the universe unbinds the knots.", "keywords": ["Change", "Liberation", "Dissonance", "Clearing", "Transformation"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Write down your dreams immediately upon waking; they hold keys.", "Avoid making binding contracts or rigid plans; things are too fluid.", "Engage in free-form creativity (painting, dancing) to release the energy.", "If you feel overwhelmed, touch water (shower, swim, drink) to ground.", "Embrace the weirdness; normal rules do not apply today."], "title": "Dissolving into the Dream", "content": "The turbulent change of Tone 11 meets the watery chaos of Imox to create a day of 'Radical Fluidity.' 11 Imox is a day where the structures of logic may dissolve completely. The energy is wild, psychic, and unpredictable. It is a powerful time to break free from rigid mental patterns or to brainstorm ideas that are completely 'outside the box.' However, it can also feel emotionally overwhelming or confusing if you try to control it. The advice for today is to be like water—flow around obstacles, do not resist the changes, and trust your intuition over your intellect. The veil between the waking world and the dream world is very thin today. Pay attention to the strange coincidences, the sudden feelings, and the messages that come through the static. It is a day of liberation through surrender."}}	{"title": "The Dream Liberator", "content": "To be born on 11 Imox is to be a surfer of the cosmic tides. You are the 'Agent of Change'—a soul who is comfortable in the chaos and who brings innovation through intuition. You likely have a mind that works differently than others, making connections that seem illogical at first but prove to be brilliant. You are deeply sensitive and psychic, often picking up on the collective mood before anyone else does. Your presence shakes things up; you are not here to maintain the status quo.\\n\\nYour life path is one of mastering the waters of the subconscious. You may struggle with emotional stability or feeling 'crazy' because you perceive so much more than the physical eye can see. The number 11 gives you a restless, transformative energy that pushes you to constantly evolve. Your challenge is to find a vessel for your vast ocean—to channel your wild creativity into forms that others can understand without losing your unique spark. You are here to remind us that reality is just a collective dream we can rewrite."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#77bda7", "primary": "#0d1a19", "secondary": "#2f554f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.772588	2026-04-25 13:46:57.72826
58	5	6	6	Ajmaq					{"nawal": {"title": "The Owl of Forgiveness", "content": "Ajmaq is the Nawal of the Owl, the ancestors, and the concept of forgiveness. It represents the wisdom that comes from experience—specifically, the wisdom gained through making mistakes. Ajmaq is the energy of pardon, redemption, and the sweetness of life that returns when we release guilt. It governs the lineage and the unseen connection to those who came before. In human experience, Ajmaq manifests as curiosity, a probing mind, and a deep capacity for empathy. It is the 'sinner' and the saint wrapped in one. When aligned, Ajmaq brings deep healing, reconciliation, and ancestral support; when misaligned, it can lead to hiding the truth, repeating errors, or wallowing in shame. It is the gentle hand that wipes the slate clean.", "keywords": ["Forgiveness", "Ancestors", "Wisdom", "Curiosity", "Redemption"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Harmony", "content": "The number Six represents the first point of true stability and flow in the cycle. It is the energy of the cube with a center, or the four directions plus the Above and Below (Heart of Sky, Heart of Earth). In Mayan cosmology, Six is the number of organic life and vital flow. Experientially, this energy feels gentle, rhythmic, and stabilizing. It is a day where things begin to click into place, and the struggle of the Five yields to a sustainable pace. The shadow of Six can be complacency, but its light is the grace of harmony and family. Today, the universe breathes easy.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Flow", "Stability", "Growth", "Rhythm"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Reach out to family members you haven't spoken to in a while.", "Practice self-forgiveness; write down a regret and burn it safely.", "Visit a place of ancestry or look at old family photos with gratitude.", "Allow yourself to flow with the day; do not force rigid schedules.", "Accept the imperfections in others as part of their learning journey."], "title": "Harmonious Redemption", "content": "The gentle flow of Tone 6 combined with the forgiving nature of Ajmaq creates a day of 'Deep Healing.' 6 Ajmaq is one of the most compassionate days in the calendar. It offers a stable, supportive energy for addressing old wounds, family patterns, or personal regrets. The energy does not demand a harsh accounting; instead, it invites a rhythmic washing away of what no longer serves. It is an ideal day for family gatherings, visiting ancestors, or simply being kind to yourself. The atmosphere is thick with a quiet, unconditional love that says, 'It is okay to be human.' You may find that difficult conversations go smoother today, or that you finally find the grace to let go of a grudge. The owl watches over the family today, ensuring that the flow of love is restored across the generations."}}	{"title": "The Ancestral Peacemaker", "content": "To be born on 6 Ajmaq is to be a vessel of ancestral grace and family harmony. You are the 'Healer of the Lineage'—someone who intuitively understands the complexities of human nature and meets them with compassion rather than judgment. You likely serve as the emotional anchor in your family or friend group, the one people turn to when they have messed up and need acceptance. Your presence is soothing, stable, and deeply wise, carrying an 'old soul' quality that others recognize immediately.\\n\\nYour life path involves learning through trial and error and teaching others that mistakes are merely stepping stones to wisdom. You have a curious mind that wants to understand the 'why' behind human behavior. With the stabilizing influence of the number 6, you are able to hold space for deep emotional work without being swept away by it. Your challenge is to ensure that you do not carry the burdens of others (or your ancestors) as your own; your gift is forgiveness, not martyrdom. You are here to remind the world that every sunrise offers a fresh start."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#be9fc2", "primary": "#101718", "secondary": "#42384a"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.769993	2026-04-25 13:46:57.742676
164	13	8	8	Kame	That night, the caravan stops beside a ring of dark stones at the edge of an open field where the rain falls more softly, almost respectfully. No one announces what is happening, yet the mood shifts the moment the wagons come to rest. The travelers move with a different kind of intention now, slower and more inward. A space is cleared near the center of camp. Wet branches are gathered from beneath canvas coverings, and with great patience, a small fire is coaxed to life.\n\nIts flame flickers stubbornly against the damp air, then steadies. Around it, the travelers form a loose circle.\n\nThe one who has long walked beside the covered wagon kneels first. They place a hand over their heart, then toward the fire, and the gesture is echoed by others in their own way. A few bring objects: a strip of cloth, a carved bead, a broken buckle, a small pouch of herbs gone fragrant from the rain. One by one, these things are offered to the flame or laid beside it to be blessed by smoke and heat.\n\nYou feel it before you have words for it. The camp is no longer occupied only by the living. The presence that enters is subtle, carried in memory and breath rather than form, yet it is unmistakable. Ancestors. Teachers. The dead who remain threaded through the living by love, grief, unfinished blessings, and the stubborn continuity of blood and story.\n\nThe storm circles the camp but does not intrude. Rain hisses softly at the edges of the firelight, and the smoke rises in twisting ribbons, briefly taking on shapes that seem almost recognizable before dissolving again. The travelers do not look surprised. They bow their heads, and some close their eyes.\n\nWhen your turn comes, you step forward holding nothing visible. What you bring cannot be wrapped in cloth or placed in a palm. It is a burden you have carried so long it has felt like part of your body. A fear. A memory. A pattern. You do not name it aloud. You only let yourself feel its full shape one final time, then offer it inwardly to the fire.\n\nSomething in you loosens.\n\nThe release is not dramatic. There is no sudden cleansing, no instant freedom. But the part of you that has been bracing against an old ghost softens, and in that softening you feel transformation begin. Not as an idea, but as an irreversible turning.\n\nWhen you step back into the circle, the firelight warms your face, and for a moment you sense many lives at once converging in the storm-dark field. Those who came before, those who stand beside you now, and the one still waiting to enter the world. The ceremony does not erase sorrow. It makes room for it, and in doing so, turns sorrow into a doorway.	There is something sacred in the air today, even if it isn't immediately visible.\n\nYou may feel drawn inward, toward reflection, toward memory, toward something that carries more weight than the present moment alone. This is not nostalgia. This is connection.\n\nYou are being invited to acknowledge where you come from.\n\nNot just your history, but your influences, your patterns, the unseen threads that have shaped your path. There may be emotions tied to this—gratitude, grief, confusion, even resistance. All of it belongs.\n\nTransformation does not happen in isolation. It happens in relationship to what came before.\n\nToday is a moment of honoring.\n\nYou don't need a formal ritual. The act itself is enough. Pausing. Acknowledging. Letting something be seen fully for what it was and what it gave you, whether that gift was ease or challenge.\n\nThere is a release embedded in that recognition.\n\nSomething that has been held quietly in the background may shift. Not disappear, but transform into something that no longer needs to weigh on you in the same way.\n\nYou are not separate from your past.\n\nBut you are not bound by it either.\n\nThere is space here to carry forward what is true, and to let the rest return to where it belongs.	I honor where I come from and transform what I carry.	Close your eyes and take a slow breath.\nBring to mind something from your past that shaped you.\nNotice how it feels in your body.\nWithout judgment, simply acknowledge it.\nThen take a breath and soften around it.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine a small ceremonial fire in front of you. You gently place old memories into the fire—not to destroy them, but to transform them. As they burn, they release light instead of smoke. You feel gratitude—not for the pain, but for the strength it created.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Transformer", "content": "Kame is the energy of death, rebirth, and the ancestral realms. It represents the great transitions of life and the peace that follows necessary endings. Kame is the courage to face the unknown and the connection to those who came before. It is the owl seeing through the veil.", "keywords": ["Death", "Rebirth", "Ancestors", "Transformation", "Peace"]}, "number": {"title": "The Harmonic Resonance", "content": "The number 8 represents the octave, wholeness, and the fabric of life. It wraps up the bundle of the previous seven days, bringing organic closure and harmony. 8 is the number of male spirituality and resonance. In this trecena, 8 brings the storm cycle into a harmonious relationship with the ancestors.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Wholeness", "Resonance", "Fabric", "Ceremony"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create an altar for your ancestors with photos and candles.", "Visit a cemetery or a place of memory.", "Meditate on the cycle of life; accept your own mortality.", "Ask the ancestors to help heal a family wound.", "Celebrate the life that comes from death (compost, seeds)."], "title": "Harmonizing with the Ancestors", "content": "8 Kame is a day of profound ancestral connection and ceremonial wholeness. The storm has cleared the path, and now we stand at the gate of the ancestors to offer thanks. Today, the cycle of death and rebirth is felt not as a trauma, but as a harmonious part of the fabric of existence. It is the perfect day to honor those who have passed, to ask for their guidance, and to heal lineage patterns. The energy is quiet, respectful, and deep. We realize that we are the result of thousands of loves and thousands of storms, all woven together into the present moment."}}	{"title": "The Ancestral Bridge", "content": "To be born on 8 Kame is to be a guardian of the lineage and a bridge between the living and the dead. You possess an old soul and a natural comfort with the mysteries of life and death. You are the one who remembers the stories, who keeps the traditions, and who honors the past. You have a harmonious, calming presence that helps others navigate grief and transition. You are not afraid of the dark; you know it is where the roots grow.\\n\\nYour life path is one of spiritual integration. You are here to heal the wounds of your family line and to weave the wisdom of the past into the future. You are likely drawn to history, genealogy, or hospice work. You have a deep respect for the sacred cycles.\\n\\nYour challenge is heaviness. You can carry the grief of the ancestors so deeply that it weighs you down. You may struggle to let go of the past or to live fully in the present. Your lesson is to be the bridge, not the destination. When you allow the ancestral wisdom to flow through you without holding onto the pain, you become a beacon of peace, showing the world that love transcends death."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#beaabb", "primary": "#1b181d", "secondary": "#5b4657"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.836588	2026-04-25 14:25:01.120916
64	5	12	12	Iq'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Breath of Spirit", "content": "Iq' is the Nawal of the wind, the breath, and communication. It represents the vital spirit that animates all living things. Iq' is the energy of inspiration, ideas, and the power of the spoken word. It clears the air and brings change. In human experience, Iq' manifests as intellect, agility, and a need for freedom. It is the voice that speaks the truth. When aligned, Iq' brings clarity, effective communication, and a fresh perspective; when misaligned, it can lead to anger, fickleness, or destructive outbursts. It is the wind that can fill the sails or break the branches.", "keywords": ["Wind", "Breath", "Communication", "Inspiration", "Change"]}, "number": {"title": "The Crystal of Understanding", "content": "The number Twelve represents the grouping together, the village, and the understanding that comes from retrospection. In Mayan cosmology, Twelve is the energy of the 'Great Gathering.' It stabilizes the chaos of Eleven and integrates the lessons learned. Experientially, this energy feels inclusive, cooperative, and wise. It is a day to summarize, to discuss, and to connect the dots. The shadow of Twelve can be difficulty with individuality, but its light is the strength of the collective mind. Today, the universe holds a council.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Integration", "Cooperation", "Review", "Community"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Hold a meeting or a meaningful conversation; communication is favored.", "Write a summary of your recent experiences or a blog post.", "Practice breathwork to clear your mind and body.", "Open the windows and let fresh air into your space.", "Seek feedback from your community; 12 values the group perspective."], "title": "The Council of Winds", "content": "When the integrating understanding of Tone 12 meets the communicative power of Iq', we arrive at a day of 'Collective Wisdom.' 12 Iq' is the energy of the great dialogue. It is the perfect day to communicate complex ideas, to teach, or to bring a group together to discuss a shared vision. The chaos of yesterday settles into a clear, breathable atmosphere. The energy supports summing up the journey so far and articulating the lessons learned. You may find that your words carry extra weight today, or that you are able to understand a difficult concept that previously eluded you. It is a day of mental synthesis. The wind blows through the village, cleaning out the dust and leaving only clarity. Listen as much as you speak today; the wind carries messages from all directions."}}	{"title": "The Wise Messenger", "content": "To be born on 12 Iq' is to be a voice for the collective. You are the 'Communicator of Wisdom'—someone who has a gift for synthesizing complex information and delivering it with clarity and inspiration. You are likely a natural storyteller, teacher, or writer, with a mind that moves as fast as the wind. People are drawn to your ideas and your ability to articulate what everyone else is thinking but cannot say. You thrive in groups and often serve as the connector who keeps the information flowing.\\n\\nYour life path is one of understanding and expression. You are here to learn the power of the word and to use it to bring people together. The number 12 gives you a cooperative nature; you are not a lone wolf but a vital part of the pack. However, the wind can be changeable, and you may struggle with consistency or with a temper that flares up suddenly. Your challenge is to discipline your breath and your speech, ensuring that your winds build bridges rather than storms. You are the breath of fresh air the world needs."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#beb4b9", "primary": "#1b1f1a", "secondary": "#535254"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.773743	2026-04-25 13:46:57.736438
5	1	5	5	No'j					{"nawal": {"title": "The Cosmic Brain", "content": "No'j is the nawal of wisdom, intellect, and the sacred science of the mind. It represents the transformation of knowledge into wisdom. No'j is the energy of the earthquake—the sudden shift in the earth that releases pressure and realigns the landscape, just as a new idea shifts our perception. It governs clarity, logic, planning, and the power of thought. This nawal connects us to the universal mind, allowing us to download solutions and innovations. It asks us to use our intelligence not for manipulation, but for the collective good, turning raw data into meaningful understanding.", "keywords": ["Wisdom", "Intellect", "Ideas", "Logic", "Solution"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Action", "content": "The number Five represents the center point of the first wave of creation—the four directions plus the center. It is the energy of work, effort, and the human hand. Five breaks the static stability of Four and puts it into motion. It is the number of 'doing,' of gathering resources, and applying will to matter. This vibration carries a sense of urgency and agency; it is not enough to plan, one must now act. It creates a bridge between the intention and the result through the sweat of one's brow. Five empowers us to take the tools we have and put them to use.", "keywords": ["Action", "Work", "Effort", "Center", "Empowerment"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Tackle the most complex problem on your to-do list today.", "Organize your workspace or digital files to improve workflow.", "Put a theoretical plan into physical motion.", "Brainstorm with others to gather diverse solutions, then act on the best one.", "Use your hands to fix or build something that requires precision."], "title": "Implementing the Master Plan", "content": "5 No'j is a day of powerful, intelligent action. The working energy of Five combines with the intellectual brilliance of No'j to create a vibe of 'practical genius.' This is not a day for abstract theorizing, but for applying your best ideas to solve real-world problems. The energy supports tackling complex tasks, organizing systems, and doing the heavy lifting required to manifest a vision. It is a 'work smart AND hard' kind of day. You may find that solutions to lingering problems suddenly click into place, provided you are willing to put in the effort to implement them. The earthquake energy of No'j suggests that your actions today could significantly shift your landscape."}}	{"title": "The Architect of Reality", "content": "To be born on 5 No'j is to possess a restless, brilliant mind that yearns to be used. You are a natural problem-solver who is not content with simply understanding how things work—you want to improve them. The number Five gifts you with a strong work ethic and a need for physical engagement, while No'j provides you with a vast reservoir of knowledge and creativity. You are the engineer, the strategist, the one who can turn a vague concept into a working prototype.\\n\\nYour challenge may lie in an overactive mind that leads to anxiety or burnout. You might feel a constant pressure to be 'doing' and 'thinking' simultaneously. Your lesson is to learn to pace yourself, to allow the earthquake of your ideas to settle before rushing to build on the new ground. Your soul's purpose is to bridge the gap between the intellectual and the practical, showing the world that true wisdom is found in the application of knowledge."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#839cac", "primary": "#151815", "secondary": "#3e4246"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.733348	2026-04-25 13:46:57.641656
127	10	10	10	Tz'ikin					{"nawal": {"title": "The Visionary Eagle", "content": "Tz'ikin is the bird, the eagle, and the vision. It represents prosperity, freedom, and the ability to see the whole picture from above. Tz'ikin is the intermediary between heaven and earth, carrying prayers up and bringing abundance down. It governs business, wealth, and the clear vision required to manifest dreams. It is the joy of flight and the sharp eye that spots the opportunity in the landscape.", "keywords": ["Vision", "Prosperity", "Freedom", "Eagle", "Abundance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Wheel of Manifestation", "content": "The number 10 represents manifestation, responsibility, and the hands coming together (two hands = ten fingers). It signifies the agreement between two people or the community. 10 is the number where the intention takes its final form in the physical world before the cycle begins to dissolve back into spirit. It brings a sense of weight, solidity, and the requirement to own the results of one's creation.", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Community", "Agreement", "Form"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Write down your vision for the next year in concrete detail.", "Take a tangible step toward a financial goal.", "Look for opportunities that others might miss; your eyes are sharp today.", "Share your vision with a partner or team (the power of 10).", "Celebrate your freedom and your capacity to create wealth/value."], "title": "Manifesting the Vision", "content": "10 Tz'ikin is a powerhouse day for material and spiritual success. The grounding, manifesting energy of the 10 combines with the soaring, prosperous energy of the Eagle. In the Kame trecena, this represents the moment where the 'rebirth' becomes fully visible and functional in the world. The new self you have been birthing is now ready to fly. This is a day to launch projects, to make business deals, and to take responsibility for your own abundance. The transformation is no longer a painful process of death, but a joyful realization of new capacity. The view is clear, the wings are strong, and the reality is solid."}}	{"title": "The Master of Prosperity", "content": "To be born on 10 Tz'ikin is to be a visionary builder of abundance. You possess a rare combination: the eagle's ability to see the highest potential and the human hands' ability to build it in reality. You are likely drawn to business, leadership, or large-scale projects because you understand how to bring resources together. You are a natural manifestor; when you focus your intent, things happen. You carry an energy of optimism and success that uplifts those around you.\\n\\nYour life path involves learning to handle power and prosperity with responsibility. You are not meant to struggle in the mud; you are meant to fly. However, the 10 energy requires that you use your vision for the benefit of the community, not just yourself. You are a bridge between the spiritual realm of ideas and the physical realm of results. You likely have a strong magnetic personality that attracts opportunities.\\n\\nYour challenge is to not become obsessed with the material aspect of abundance or to lose patience with the details. The eagle can sometimes be arrogant or detached from the ground. Your soul's lesson is to remember that true prosperity includes spiritual wealth and the well-being of your relationships. When you ground your lofty visions in service to the collective, you become a great provider and a bringer of hope, proving that the spiritual and the material are one."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b2cbb4", "primary": "#131f1f", "secondary": "#445f5c"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.807524	2026-04-25 13:46:57.867171
69	6	4	4	Tz'ikin	The restless textures of the bazaar finally smooth out as you encounter a lighthouse built from compressed stacks of ancient, petrified maps. At the summit, a giant, rotating lens made of prismatic crystal projects 'possible futures' onto the blank vellum sky. This is the energy of 4 Tz'ikin—where the soaring vision of the bird meets the solid foundation of the earth. You are tasked with organizing these flickering light-projections into four specific windows, creating a stable frame for the abundance you seek. As you align the lenses, the shifting paper beneath you hardens into a sturdy stone plaza. By giving your vision a structure, the bazaar rewards you with a steady gold beacon that illuminates the path for miles ahead.	There is a strange, beautiful weight is settling into your spirit today, turning your flighty dreams into something you can actually touch. You may notice that your "big ideas" are no longer drifting away like smoke, but are instead seeking a place to land and grow roots. This is the energy of the visionary meeting the earth. It is a day to take the shimmering threads of your imagination and weave them into a sturdy net. You are being asked to create order out of the chaotic brilliance of your mind, turning your insights into a lasting legacy of abundance. The air feels solid and supportive, as if the four directions have finally agreed to hold you steady. This is an ideal time to look at your resources—not with anxiety, but with the eagle-eye precision of a master builder. Where can you add more structure to your daily rhythm? How can you use your voice to command a new level of prosperity? Today, the most "spiritual" thing you can do is to be practical. By building a nest for your vision, you ensure that when the winds of change blow, you are the one who stays upright. Trust the logic of the light. Your prosperity is ripening, and it requires a strong vessel to hold its weight.	I ground my highest visions into a sturdy reality, building a foundation for lasting prosperity.	Sit upright and imagine your spine is a solid pillar of stone. Close your eyes and visualize four windows of light opening around you—North, South, East, and West. Breathe in the expansive vision of the high sky, then exhale that light down into your base, grounding it into the earth. Feel the stability of a dream that has finally found its foundation.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, see yourself at the top of the Tower of the Glass Lens. Watch as a giant prismatic crystal lens rotates above you, projecting golden futures onto the vellum clouds. Reach out and adjust the lens until the light focuses into a single, steady gold beacon. Watch as the shifting paper streets below harden into a sturdy stone plaza, illuminated by your organized intent.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Visionary Bird", "content": "Tz'ikin is the Nawal of the Bird, the Eagle, and the Condor. It represents vision, freedom, and the ability to rise above the mundane to see the big picture. Tz'ikin is the energy of prosperity and abundance, reminding us that spiritual vision attracts material resources. It governs the eyes and the ability to 'see' opportunities. In human experience, Tz'ikin manifests as optimism, sociability, and a drive for success. It is the intermediary between Earth and Sky, carrying our prayers up and bringing blessings down. It is the wings that lift us toward the sun.", "keywords": ["Vision", "Prosperity", "Opportunity", "Freedom", "Abundance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cube of Stability", "content": "The number Four represents stability, definition, and the material world. It is the energy of the four cardinal directions, the four elements, and the four walls of a house. In Mayan cosmology, Four is the force that grounds spirit into form; it creates the container in which life can exist. Experientially, this energy feels solid, reliable, and sometimes a bit heavy. It is a day for building, organizing, and establishing boundaries. The shadow of Four can be rigidity, but its light is the comfort of a secure foundation.", "keywords": ["Structure", "Balance", "Grounding", "Manifestation", "Stability"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create a budget or a business plan; ground your finances.", "Define the next practical steps for your biggest dream.", "Look for opportunities that offer long-term stability, not just quick wins.", "Express gratitude for the physical abundance you already possess.", "Build a 'nest' for your ideas—write them down, organize them."], "title": "Grounding the Vision", "content": "The structural energy of Tone 4 combines with the expansive vision of Tz'ikin to create a day of 'Manifested Prosperity.' 4 Tz'ikin is the architect who not only dreams of the castle but lays the foundation for it. This is an incredibly powerful day for business, financial planning, and grounding your long-term goals in reality. The bird (Tz'ikin) sees the opportunity, and the number 4 captures it and builds a cage (a structure) to keep it safe. It is a day to ask: 'How can I make my vision sustainable?' The energy supports taking flight, but with a flight plan. It is also a day of physical abundance; you may find resources appearing to support your projects. Use this energy to stabilize your finances or to define the parameters of a new venture. The sky is the limit, but the ground is the launchpad."}}	{"title": "The Builder of Abundance", "content": "To be born on 4 Tz'ikin is to be a master of materializing vision. You are the 'Grounded Eagle'—someone who can soar high enough to see the future but who also knows how to land and build a life on earth. You likely have a talent for business or organization, combining an optimistic outlook with a practical, structural mind. People trust you because you deliver; you don't just promise the moon, you build a rocket to get there. You are a natural provider, often attracting wealth and resources to share with your community.\\n\\nYour life path is one of creating sustainable prosperity. You are not interested in fleeting success; you want to build something that lasts (4). The Tz'ikin energy gives you charisma and luck, while the 4 gives you the discipline to manage it. Your challenge is to avoid becoming too materialistic or rigid in your definition of success. Remember that true abundance includes the freedom of the spirit, not just the security of the bank account. You are here to show that spiritual vision and material stability can coexist perfectly."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#acc5ba", "primary": "#0f1a1b", "secondary": "#374c57"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.776623	2026-04-25 14:38:01.2953
77	6	12	12	Aq'ab'al	You reach a magnificent bridge where the environment splits in two: one half is bathed in the deep indigo ink of night, and the other glows with the gold leaf of an approaching dawn. This is the integration of 12 Aq'ab'al. As you walk across this liminal threshold, you undergo a life review of the Bazaar. You see how every paper cut, every ink stain, and every detour was a necessary stitch in the wisdom you now carry. The bridge acts as a mirror, revealing that the road and the traveler have become one. The revelation is clear: the dawn is not a destination you reach, but a state of being you have finally integrated.	You are standing on a magnificent bridge that spans the liminal space between the person you were and the hero you are becoming. One side of your world is bathed in the deep indigo ink of an integrated night, while the other glows with the shimmering gold leaf of a fast-approaching dawn. Today is a day of profound comprehension and spiritual integration, where the universe asks you to review the 'shadow-lessons' of your journey and see how they have become the very light of your current wisdom. You may feel a deep, resonant sense of peace as the contradictions of your life—the paper cuts and the peak views—finally begin to rhyme, forming a unified truth that you can wear like a cloak of stars. This is the energy of the Dawn-Bridge, where the secrets of the dark are revealed to be the necessary foundations of the day. You might feel a surge of cooperative spirit, a desire to share your integrated truth with those who are still navigating their own thresholds in the haze. By honoring both the velvet shadows and the prismatic light, you find the balance necessary to step across into your new cycle with a steady hand. The revelation of the day is clear: the dawn is not a destination you reach, but a state of being you have finally allowed yourself to inhabit. Trust the review; the wisdom you gather in this gilded twilight is the lantern that will light your way through all the cycles to come.	I honor the twilight of my transition, recognizing that every darkness was the foundation for my day.	Close your eyes and visualize a seam of golden light running down the center of your vision. To the left is a peaceful indigo shadow; to the right is a soft peach dawn. Breathe into the space where they meet, integrating your past lessons and your future potential into a single, unified moment of 'now.'\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, stand on the Bridge of the Gilded Twilight. Look back at the Bazaar of Maps and see the entire 12-day journey spread out behind you. See how every 'paper cut' and 'ink stain' has been woven into your wisdom. Hold a lantern that contains both a sun-spark and a nebula, and feel the revelation that you and the road have finally become one.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Dawn of Hope", "content": "Aq'ab'al is the Nawal of the dawn, the dusk, and the transition between light and dark. It represents the moment of awakening and the potential of a new day. Aq'ab'al is the energy of duality, polarity, and the hope that comes after the long night. In human experience, Aq'ab'al manifests as optimism, youthfulness, and the ability to see the solution in the problem. It is the bridge between the dream and the reality. When aligned, Aq'ab'al brings new opportunities, clarity, and a soft, hopeful light; when misaligned, it can lead to hesitation. It is the first ray of sun.", "keywords": ["Dawn", "Duality", "Transition", "Hope", "Awakening"]}, "number": {"title": "The Crystal of Understanding", "content": "The number Twelve represents the grouping together, the village, and the understanding that comes from retrospection. In Mayan cosmology, Twelve is the energy of the 'Great Gathering.' It stabilizes the chaos of Eleven and integrates the lessons learned. Experientially, this energy feels inclusive, cooperative, and wise. It is a day to summarize, to discuss, and to connect the dots. The shadow of Twelve can be difficulty with individuality, but its light is the strength of the collective mind. Today, the universe holds a council.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Integration", "Cooperation", "Review", "Community"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Share your hopes and dreams with your community.", "Discuss the 'new beginnings' emerging in your life with a friend.", "Look for the silver lining; optimism is powerful today.", "Plan a project that brings light to others.", "Acknowledge the darkness of the past without living in it."], "title": "Collective Awakening", "content": "The integrative energy of Tone 12 meets the dawning light of Aq'ab'al to create a day of 'Shared Hope.' 12 Aq'ab'al is the moment the village wakes up together. It represents a collective realization or a new beginning that affects everyone. After the storm of 11 Iq', this energy feels like the fresh, clean air of a new morning. It is a wonderful day for social gatherings, team meetings, or any event where people come together to look toward the future. The energy supports optimism and the sharing of new ideas. We are able to see the 'dawn' of a solution to our shared problems. It is a day to acknowledge the dualities of life—light and dark, old and new—and to understand how they fit together in the larger picture. The night is over; let's walk into the day together."}}	{"title": "The Bringer of New Days", "content": "To be born on 12 Aq'ab'al is to be a harbinger of hope for the many. You are the 'Collective Dawn'—a soul who radiates optimism and helps others see the light at the end of the tunnel. You have a youthful, vibrant energy that draws people to you. You are naturally cooperative and thrive in community settings, often serving as the one who introduces new concepts or rallies the group toward a brighter future. You bridge the gap between the old ways and the new, helping your tribe transition smoothly.\\n\\nYour life path is one of understanding duality. You see the potential in everything, even the darkest situations. The number 12 gives you a comprehensive view of life; you understand how all the parts fit together. Your challenge is to ensure that your optimism is grounded in reality and that you don't gloss over the necessary shadow work. You are here to remind us that no matter how long the night, the sun always rises, and we rise with it."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d8b177", "primary": "#111719", "secondary": "#4a3f3f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.779618	2026-04-25 14:38:01.303651
86	7	8	8	Q'anil	By now, the path to the lake feels like part of you.\n\nYour steps fall into an easy rhythm, guided less by memory and more by a quiet pull from somewhere behind your ribs. You know the way without needing to think about it. The forest seems to know you too. Branches lift instead of snagging; leaves shift to let more light through.\n\nWhen you reach the shore, the lake is neither stormy nor still. It glows.\n\nThe light does not come from above. It rises from beneath the surface, soft and scattered at first, like faint stars at the bottom of a night sky. As you watch, the points of light drift upward, gathering near the shallows until you see what they are.\n\nSeeds.\n\nNot the kind you plant in soil. These are made of light and color, tiny ovals and spheres that pulse gently as if they remember every heartbeat you have ever carried. Some are pale and new, barely formed. Others are bright, full, ready to open.\n\nThey float just below the surface, clustered in small constellations. As the water moves, they arrange themselves into simple shapes: a hand, an eye, a spiral, then break apart and reform into something else.\n\nYou kneel at the edge without being asked.\n\nA feeling rises in your chest — not longing this time, not ache, but something simpler and deeper. Gratitude. Not for any one outcome or achievement, but for the simple fact that these seeds exist at all, that your life has contained enough light for them to form.\n\nYou realize that each seed is a piece of you that kept glowing even when you weren’t looking.\n\nA small ceremony begins without anyone declaring it.\n\nYou place your hands over your heart and bow your head, not to the water as a separate thing, but to the exchange between you and it. To the way your quiet wishes, your half-formed ideas, your almost-forgotten joys have been collecting here, waiting for this moment.\n\nAs you breathe, a few of the brightest seeds rise fully to the surface. They open like slow-motion flowers — not into petals, but into ripples of color that spread outward, tinting the water with soft golds, blues, and greens.\n\nThe lake seems to exhale in response.\n\nYou do not reach in to grab anything. You do not try to decide which seed should bloom next. Instead, you let yourself feel the abundance already present — the projects you have begun, the healing you have allowed, the small daily choices that have been quietly growing roots beneath your awareness.\n\nA thought comes, clear and gentle: not everything needs to be pushed. Some things only need to be tended.\n\nYou whisper a thank you — to the water, to the seeds, to the parts of you that kept believing in something more even on the days you did not.\n\nWhen you finally stand, the seeds sink slowly back into the depths, their light dimming but not disappearing.\n\nYou leave the shore with a new understanding resting softly inside you: the future is not empty. It is already sprouting beneath the surface, waiting for your care, not your control.	Today, your inner garden is lit up.\n\nYou may suddenly notice how far you’ve actually come — not in dramatic milestones, but in the subtle ways your life feels different than it once did. Habits softened. Boundaries clarified. Dreams that no longer feel impossible.\n\nThis is a day to pause and acknowledge growth. To thank yourself for the quiet work you’ve been doing, even on the days that felt stagnant.\n\nWater what matters with your attention. Celebrate the small blooms. Trust that what you tend with care will continue to grow.	I honor the quiet seeds that have been growing within me, and I choose to tend my inner garden with gratitude and care.	Sit comfortably and close your eyes. Imagine the lake before you, its surface calm and gently glowing from beneath.\n\nSee tiny seeds of light floating just under the water — each one representing a part of your life that has been quietly growing: a healed wound, a new habit, a creative idea, a relationship, a boundary, a tender hope.\n\nWith each inhale, imagine one seed brightening. With each exhale, see it open into a soft ripple of color that spreads across the water.\n\nSilently repeat: “Thank you for growing, even when I wasn’t watching.”\n\nWhen you feel complete, offer a moment of gratitude to the unseen forces — ancestral, earthly, and inner — that help your seeds take root. Then open your eyes, carrying that sense of abundance into the rest of your day.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Seed of Life", "content": "Q'anil is the Nawal of the seed, the rabbit, and Venus. It represents the generative power of life, fertility, and the potential for abundance. Q'anil is the energy of planting, ripening, and harvesting. It governs the cycles of growth and the beauty of creation. In human experience, Q'anil manifests as artistic talent, a love for pleasure, and a connection to the biological rhythms of life. It is the spark of life in the soil. When aligned, Q'anil brings successful projects and joy; when misaligned, it can lead to impatience, vanity, or problems with alcohol/substances.", "keywords": ["Seed", "Fertility", "Abundance", "Growth", "Ripening"]}, "number": {"title": "The Harmony of Justice", "content": "The number Eight represents the octave, the return to power, and the weaving of the spiritual into the material. In Mayan cosmology, Eight is the number of the 'Primordial Male' energy, mirroring the 'Primordial Female' of Nine. It is often associated with ceremonies and the harmonization of energy. Experientially, this energy feels like a solid, resonant chord—it is balanced, organized, and powerful. It is a day to take the insights of Seven and begin to apply them with authority. The shadow of Eight can be rigidity, but its light is the strength of integrity.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Balance", "Ceremony", "Reciprocity", "Fairness"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a gratitude ceremony for the abundance in your life.", "Plant physical seeds or start a garden.", "Start a creative project with a clear intention of success.", "Share food and drink with friends; celebrate life.", "Trust the timing of your life; do not dig up the seed to see if it's growing."], "title": "Ceremony of Abundance", "content": "When the ceremonial power of Tone 8 meets the fertile energy of Q'anil, we celebrate a day of 'Sacred Planting.' 8 Q'anil is one of the most auspicious days for gratitude ceremonies, specifically those thanking the Earth for its abundance. The energy is rich, golden, and harmonious. It is the perfect time to plant intentions (seeds) that you want to grow into something lasting and beautiful. Because 8 is the number of justice and reciprocity, the day asks: What are you giving back to the soil that feeds you? It is a day to honor the cycle of give and take. If you have been working hard, 8 Q'anil invites you to enjoy the fruits of your labor—share a meal, create art, or simply bask in the beauty of life. It is a day to remember that every harvest begins with a seed and a prayer."}}	{"title": "The Artist of Life", "content": "To be born on 8 Q'anil is to be a gardener of the soul and a creator of beauty. You are the 'Ceremonial Planter'—someone who treats life as a sacred art form. You have a natural green thumb, whether with plants, projects, or people. You know how to nurture potential until it blossoms. The number 8 gives you a sense of structure and ritual, making you reliable and grounded in your creativity. You are likely drawn to the arts, agriculture, or healing—anything that affirms life.\\n\\nYour life path is one of harmonizing with the cycles of growth. You understand that everything has its season. Your presence brings joy and abundance to those around you; you are often the 'lucky charm' in a group. Your challenge is to guard against impatience and to ensure that you are nurturing yourself as much as you nurture the world. You are here to show us the beauty of fruition."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#dac38a", "primary": "#101917", "secondary": "#48453a"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.787506	2026-04-25 13:46:57.780216
133	11	3	3	Kej	The Spire demands a new tempo. You reach a section where the vines are stretched tight across the gaps between trunks, taut and resonant like the skin of a celestial drum. As you step onto them, your footfalls do not thud; they ring. The vibration travels upward through your soles, and suddenly, the frantic effort of the climb dissolves into a rhythmic dance. You find yourself moving with a sudden, wild agility, your body instinctively finding the 'bounce' in the living bark. This is the rhythm of Kej, the sovereign of the wilderness, and you are learning to pulse in time with it.\n\nWith every leap, the Spire responds. The forest is no longer a silent obstacle but a percussive partner. You hear the deep, thrumming heartbeat of the great trees echoing your own, a call-and-response that vibrates in your teeth. You are no longer just a traveler; you are a frequency moving through a living instrument. The restlessness of the number 3 becomes a fuel for your momentum, pushing you to bypass the easy path for the one that requires the most grace. You feel the strength of the deer in your thighs and the alertness of the guardian in your eyes. As you drum your way higher into the canopy, the Spire itself seems to sing, a roaring emerald symphony that welcomes your presence as part of its own wild music.	The ground beneath you has stopped being a stable, silent floor and has transformed into a vibrating, celestial drumhead. Every step you take today sends a visible ripple through the world, and the world is ringing back in a percussive call-and-response that vibrates in your very teeth. If you try to walk with your old, heavy caution or your practiced hesitation, you will find yourself stumbling. This energy demands a different kind of movement—it demands a dance. \n\nTrust the 'bounce' in your legs and the wild, agile rhythm rising in your blood like a tide. You are being asked to leap across the gaps of your own doubt, spanning the distances between who you are and who you want to be with the instinctive grace of a creature born for the wilderness. You don't need a map when the rhythm is this clear. \n\nLet your heartbeat set the tempo for your decisions today. The environment around you is singing a roaring, emerald symphony, and you are currently the soloist. Do not tiptoe through the opportunities that present themselves. Leap into the center of the music and let the vibration carry you higher than you ever thought possible. The air is thin, but your spirit is strong.	My vitality flows through the world, and I find my power in the dynamic dance of life.	Stand tall and close your eyes. Shift your weight from side to side, feeling the agility and strength in your legs. Inhale the scent of wild cedar and feel your senses sharpen. \n\nOptionally, imagine yourself standing on a vine stretched tight like a drumhead, your heartbeat syncing with the percussive thrum of the great trees around you.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Guardian of the Wild", "content": "Kej is the deer, the sovereign of the wilderness, and the keeper of the four directions. It represents strength, agility, and a deep, harmonious connection with the natural world. Kej carries the energy of authority that is earned through grace rather than force. It is the alert sensitivity of the deer, sensing shifts in the wind, and the sturdy legs that can climb the mountain. It asks us to stand tall and ground our energy.", "keywords": ["Nature", "Strength", "Balance", "Leadership", "Harmony"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Movement", "content": "The number 3 represents movement, flow, and the disruption of static balance. It is the energy of the child, the creative spark that refuses to sit still. 3 breaks the duality of 2 to create a dynamic triangle of flow. It is associated with communication, expression, and the rhythm of life. While it brings great creativity and change, it can also bring instability or scattered energy if not channeled.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Creativity", "Flow", "Rhythm", "Change"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Go for a hike or a long walk in a natural setting.", "Practice 'instinctive movement' or dance.", "Pay attention to the signs in the environment (wind, animals).", "Use your voice to express a truth you've been holding back.", "Break your routine; take a different path today."], "title": "Moving with Natural Grace", "content": "3 Kej brings a dynamic, flowing energy to the trecena. The strength of the Deer meets the movement of the number 3. This is a day to get outside, to move your body, and to let your instincts guide you. The transformation initiated by Kan is now finding its legs. You may feel a restless energy, a need to roam or to express yourself. It is a powerful day for creative projects that involve nature or the body. The lesson is to move with agility—not rushing blindly, but flowing around obstacles like water (or a deer in the woods). Trust your physical senses today; they are sharper than usual."}}	{"title": "The Agile Leader", "content": "To be born on 3 Kej is to be a force of nature—dynamic, expressive, and undeniably strong. You possess the grace of the deer combined with a restless, creative energy that keeps you constantly in motion. You are a natural leader, but not the kind who sits on a throne; you lead from the front, scouting the path and encouraging others to follow. You have a deep connection to the earth and the elements, and you likely need open spaces to feel sane.\\n\\nYour life path is one of movement and communication. You are an excellent orator, artist, or advocate for the natural world. You have a quick mind and sharp instincts. People are drawn to your vitality and your ability to navigate difficult terrain with ease. You are often the one who spots the danger before anyone else and knows exactly which way to run.\\n\\nYour challenge is focus. The 3 energy can make you scattered, and the deer energy can make you skittish. You may have a tendency to run away when things get too heavy or emotionally complex. Your soul's task is to learn to stand your ground when necessary. When you channel your boundless energy into a clear purpose, you become a powerful guardian of the wild and a voice for the voiceless, showing others how to move through life with both power and grace."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#7ead6e", "primary": "#0f1817", "secondary": "#354237"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.8094	2026-04-25 14:38:01.30831
115	9	11	11	K'at					{"nawal": {"title": "The Cosmic Net", "content": "K'at is the Nawal of the net, the spider web, and the gathering of abundance. It represents the principle of connection—how things are tied together. K'at is the energy that catches what we need (abundance) and what we don't need (entanglements). It governs the harvest, the storage of seeds, and the release of burdens. In human experience, K'at manifests as the ability to network, to organize, and to carry a load. It is the burning of the net to free the captive. When aligned, K'at brings fruitful connections; when misaligned, it can lead to feeling trapped.", "keywords": ["Gathering", "Release", "Abundance", "Net", "Entanglement"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Change", "content": "The number Eleven represents dissonance, resolution through change, and the stripping away of the non-essential. In Mayan cosmology, Eleven is a high-frequency energy that shakes the foundation to test its strength. It is not necessarily negative, but it is turbulent. Experientially, this energy feels like a strong wind or a sudden shift in plans. It breaks the static perfection of Ten to allow for higher growth. The shadow of Eleven can be chaos, but its light is liberation and the clearing of the path. Today, the universe unbinds the knots.", "keywords": ["Change", "Liberation", "Dissonance", "Clearing", "Transformation"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Throw away or donate things you no longer need; lighten your load.", "Cut an energetic cord with a toxic person or habit.", "Allow a plan to change; don't cling to the old structure.", "Review your commitments; release the ones that feel like traps.", "Feel the lightness of being untangled."], "title": "Untangling the Net", "content": "The turbulent change of Tone 11 meets the gathering energy of K'at to create a day of 'Radical Release.' 11 K'at is the energy of cutting the cords that bind you. If you have felt trapped, weighed down by clutter, or entangled in a situation that drains you, today is the day the net breaks open. This can feel chaotic, as the things you were holding onto (or that were holding onto you) suddenly fall away. But this is a divine liberation. The energy asks you to review what you are carrying. Is your net too full? 11 K'at shakes the web to see what sticks and what falls. Let the non-essential go. It is a powerful day to declutter your home, end a restrictive contract, or release a mental burden. You are being freed to gather something better. Trust the unraveling."}}	{"title": "The Liberator of Burdens", "content": "To be born on 11 K'at is to be a master of release and reorganization. You are the 'Chaos Weaver'—a soul who knows how to untangle the messiest knots of life. You likely have a restless spirit that resists being tied down. You are a catalyst for others, helping them to see where they are trapped and inspiring them to break free. You may have a life filled with sudden changes of fortune or direction, as the number 11 constantly shakes your net.\\n\\nYour life path is one of finding freedom through sorting. You are here to learn what is worth carrying and what is just dead weight. You have a gift for organization, but often in unconventional ways. Your challenge is to find a sense of stability within the flux, and to ensure that you don't cut cords that are actually lifelines. You are here to show us that true abundance requires the space to receive it."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#e2c681", "primary": "#121312", "secondary": "#5f4732"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.804463	2026-04-25 13:46:57.851791
125	10	8	8	Aj					{"nawal": {"title": "The Pillar of Community", "content": "Aj is the cane, the cornstalk, and the pillar. It represents the spine, the home, and the authority of the lineage. Aj is the energy of the benevolent leader who supports the family and the community. It signifies triumph, resurrection, and the ability to stand tall and flexible like the bamboo. It connects the earth to the sky and represents the sanctity of the home space. Aj is the protector of the tender shoots of life.", "keywords": ["Home", "Authority", "Spine", "Corn", "Resurrection"]}, "number": {"title": "The Harmonic Resonance", "content": "The number 8 represents the octave, the return to the note of the beginning but on a higher level. It is the number of wholeness, wrapping up the bundle of the previous seven days. 8 is the number of male spirituality and the energy of the fabric of life. It brings a certain organic closure and a resonance of harmony. It is often the day of the 'party' or the ceremonial celebration of the work done so far.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Wholeness", "Resonance", "Ceremony", "Fabric"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Hold a family gathering or a meal with close friends to celebrate connection.", "Bless the corners of your home with smoke or water.", "Check your posture; align your physical spine to align your spiritual authority.", "Meditate on the concept of 'flexible strength.'", "Plant a staff or a symbolic object in the ground to claim your space."], "title": "Resurrecting the Sanctuary", "content": "8 Aj is a day of profound wholeness and resurrection within the home and the self. Following the path-finding of 7 E', today we return to the center to establish a harmonious authority. The theme of the Kame trecena—rebirth—is powerfully enacted here as 'Resurrection.' The corn that died has been reborn as the strong stalk. This is a day to celebrate your survival, your strength, and your support systems. It is an excellent day to bless your home, to gather with family, and to stand tall in the knowledge that you have weathered the storm. The energy is gentle but unbreakable, like a green reed in the wind."}}	{"title": "The Pillar of Light", "content": "To be born on 8 Aj is to be a foundational stone for your people. You carry an aura of completeness, authority, and safety. You are the person others lean on, the one who holds the roof up when the walls are shaking. You possess a natural resonance with the divine masculine (regardless of gender)—a protective, providing, and stabilizing energy. Your life is deeply connected to the concepts of home, family, and community leadership.\\n\\nYou are a natural counselor and a figure of respect. People instinctively trust you. You have the ability to regenerate yourself and others; you are the living embodiment of resurrection. No matter how many times you are cut down, like the corn, you grow back stronger. You are meant to create sanctuaries—spaces where others can feel safe to grow.\\n\\nYour challenge is to remain flexible. The pillar that is too rigid will snap in the storm. You may also struggle with the weight of responsibility, feeling that you must carry everyone else's burdens. Your lesson is to emulate the bamboo—strong but yielding. When you lead with flexibility and allow others to find their own strength, you become a wise elder and a true king/queen of your domain, harmonizing the world from your own living room."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d5bf89", "primary": "#171c1a", "secondary": "#65523b"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.807112	2026-04-25 13:46:57.878424
134	11	4	4	Q'anil	The frantic music of the climb softens as you find an opening in the side of a gargantuan trunk. Inside is a hollow sanctuary, a cathedral of calm where the air is thick with the scent of damp loam and ripening nectar. Four massive pillars of solid, glowing light stand at the edges of this space, grounding the electric energy of the Spire into the floor of rich, black moss. This is the Star-Seed Sanctuary, a place where the vertical world pauses to remember the soil. After the movement of the previous days, the stability of this chamber feels like a gift.\n\nIn the center of the moss, a cluster of small, pulsing seed-stars rests in a bed of ferns. You realize this is the place to plant the intentions you brought into the Spire. As you kneel and press your hands into the cool earth, the four pillars hum in unison, a low frequency of manifestation that vibrates through your chest. You are building the foundation of your journey here, ensuring that your growth isn't just fast, but sustainable. The golden hue of the sanctuary suggests a harvest that is already guaranteed if you simply trust the process of the shed. You spend the night in the silence between the pillars, feeling your roots descend as surely as your spirit has ascended, becoming a bridge between the stars above and the deep heart of the earth.	After the frantic music of the climb, the universe pulls you into a quiet, hollow cathedral made of filtered light and damp earth. The walls here are humming with a frequency that demands you stop, breathe, and sink your roots into something real. You’ve been reaching so hard for the stars that you might have forgotten that even the brightest light needs a solid foundation to keep it from drifting away into the void. \n\nToday is about the sacred, steady work of grounding your electricity. Imagine four pillars of solid gold light standing at the corners of your life, holding the sky steady while you plant your intentions into the fertile dark of your inner self. There is no need to rush the harvest; growth is an inevitable, organic process when the foundation is this deep and well-tended. \n\nSpend the day being still, becoming the bridge between the earth that supports you and the heavens that inspire you. In this sanctuary, the air smells of rich loam and ripening nectar, reminding you that abundance starts in the shadows. Your dreams are safe here. Let them take root in the moss and wait for the natural moment when they are ready to break the surface as something solid and true.	I am grounded in my own sanctuary, providing a stable foundation for my dreams to bloom.	Close your eyes and imagine four pillars of light surrounding you, creating a square of absolute safety and stability. Breathe into the rich, damp earth beneath you and feel your intentions taking root. \n\nOptionally, enter the Star-Seed Sanctuary within the tree trunk, kneeling on iridescent black moss as you plant your dreams into the glowing soil.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Seed of Abundance", "content": "Q'anil is the energy of the seed, the star, and the ripening crop. It represents fertility, potential, and the inevitable unfolding of life when conditions are right. Q'anil is the promise that what is planted with intention will grow. It carries a gentle, golden energy of nourishment and organic development. It reminds us that we cannot force the flower to open; we can only tend the soil and trust the process.", "keywords": ["Seed", "Fertility", "Abundance", "Growth", "Ripening"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cube of Stability", "content": "The number 4 brings form, definition, and stability to the flow of creation. It represents the four directions, the four elements, and the solid foundation of the physical world. After the movement of 3, 4 grounds the energy, creating a container or a structure where life can reside. It is the energy of the builder, the organizer, and the stabilizer. It offers a pause to assess, measure, and establish a firm footing.", "keywords": ["Stability", "Structure", "Foundation", "Definition", "Four Directions"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Plant something physical or start a savings account.", "Create a plan or schedule for a creative project.", "Spend time with children or nurture a 'young' idea.", "Express gratitude for the abundance already in your life.", "Eat a meal with intention, honoring the earth that grew it."], "title": "Stabilizing the Harvest", "content": "4 Q'anil offers a beautiful, grounding energy. It is the 'Planter's Day.' Here, the wisdom of the Kan trecena finds a place to take root. The stability of the 4 provides the perfect garden bed for the seeds of Q'anil. This is a day to focus on the practical aspects of your dreams. It is not enough to just want to grow; you must build the trellis, water the soil, and ensure the conditions are right. Today brings a sense of calm assurance. If you do the work today, the results are guaranteed in time. It is a day of patience, gratitude, and the slow, steady work of creation."}}	{"title": "The Master Gardener", "content": "To be born on 4 Q'anil is to be a stable, nurturing force for growth in the world. You are the person who plants the trees under whose shade you may never sit. You possess a deep patience and a practical understanding of how things develop over time. You are not interested in flash-in-the-pan success; you are interested in legacy, sustainability, and true abundance. You are likely the rock of your family or community, the one who ensures that everyone is fed and that the future is secure.\\n\\nYour life path is one of cultivation. Whether you are raising children, building a business, or creating art, you approach it with the care of a master gardener. You understand cycles, seasons, and the importance of a strong foundation. You are generous and fertile in spirit, often surrounded by the fruits of your labor.\\n\\nYour challenge is to not become too rigid or overly cautious. The 4 energy can sometimes make you resistant to change, and you may struggle when storms threaten your carefully tended garden. Your lesson is to trust the resilience of life. When you balance your desire for stability with faith in the organic process, you become a creator of lasting beauty, proving that the most profound magic is simply helping things grow."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#bcbb7d", "primary": "#111514", "secondary": "#434234"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.80957	2026-04-25 14:38:01.310731
172	14	3	3	Toj					{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Fire", "content": "Toj is the energy of offering, payment, and reciprocity. It is the sacred fire that transmutes matter into spirit. Toj represents the law of karma and the necessity of giving back to maintain universal balance. It is the day to pay spiritual debts and offer gratitude. It reminds us that nature requires an exchange.", "keywords": ["Offering", "Payment", "Reciprocity", "Fire", "Gratitude"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Movement", "content": "The number 3 introduces movement, flow, and the disruption of static balance. It is the energy of communication, expression, and the creative spark. 3 breaks the deadlock of duality to create a dynamic flow. In this trecena, 3 sets the stable energy of the Deer into motion, asking for an active offering.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Expression", "Flow", "Rhythm", "Creativity"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Make an offering to the fire (candle or bonfire).", "Move your body in gratitude; dance for the earth.", "Pay a debt quickly and with a smile.", "Speak words of thanks to the elements.", "Let go of a burden by offering it to the flames."], "title": "The Flow of Gratitude", "content": "3 Toj is a day of active, moving gratitude. The rhythm of the 3 stirs the fire of Toj. In the Kej trecena, this reminds us that our connection to nature is maintained through reciprocity. We cannot just take from the earth; we must give back. Today is a day to make offerings in motion—a dance, a song, or an act of service. The energy is warm and fluid. It asks us to pay our debts not with heaviness, but with the joy of keeping the cycle moving. The fire is dancing today."}}	{"title": "The Fire Dancer", "content": "To be born on 3 Toj is to be a spark of divine gratitude in motion. You possess a dynamic, expressive energy that seeks to balance the world through joy and offering. You are not a silent payer of debts; you are a celebrant of the exchange. You understand that life is a dance of giving and receiving. You are likely artistic, musical, or drawn to ceremonial practices involving fire and movement.\\n\\nYour life path is one of active service. You pay your karmic debts through your creativity and your ability to inspire others. You have a warm, infectious spirit that warms those around you. However, the 3 energy can make you restless, and Toj can make you feel indebted.\\n\\nYour challenge is consistency. You may burn bright and hot, then burn out. You may struggle to stick with the mundane payments of life. Your lesson is to tend your inner fire steadily. When you channel your expressive energy into consistent acts of gratitude, you become a living offering, reminding the world that service is a form of joy."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#cb986c", "primary": "#101211", "secondary": "#423630"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.841185	2026-04-25 13:46:57.948501
136	11	6	6	Tz'i'	Above the clearing, the chaotic growth of the rainforest settles into a magnificent, rhythmic order. You look up to see a wolf-like creature made of pure, translucent starlight standing upon a branch of silver moss. This is the Guardian of Law, and its presence brings a sudden, stabilizing calm to the climb. It does not bark or growl; it simply watches you with eyes that reflect your own integrity. As you move, the Guardian follows, jumping effortlessly from vine to vine, its trail marked by paw-prints of cooling blue sparks. Its loyalty is not to you, but to the truth of the journey itself.\n\nFollowing the Guardian, you find that the ascent has become a flow. Your movements align with the natural geometry of the Spire, each handhold appearing exactly where your body needs it to be. There is no friction here, only the responsiveness of a world that recognizes your commitment to the path. The stability of the number 6 anchors the electric energy of the Kan trecena, turning raw power into a steady, vital current. You realize that justice in this world is simply the alignment of your will with the cosmic rhythm. As long as you walk with integrity, the Spire is your loyal companion. The Guardian pauses at the edge of a high canopy, bowing its head in a silent salute before dissolving into the morning mist, leaving you standing tall and centered in the flow of your own life force.	The chaos of the climb is settling into a magnificent, geometric order that feels both ancient and brand new. You aren't alone today; a noble, silent presence is moving alongside you, watching from the silver branches with eyes made of steady, unwavering light. This is the energy of absolute loyalty—not a loyalty to another person’s expectations, but a fierce fidelity to your own highest truth. \n\nWhen you act with integrity, the path through the forest suddenly becomes a frictionless flow. Handholds appear exactly where your hands need to reach, and the wind seems to push gently at your back. Today, your only job is to stay true to your 'internal north.' If a choice feels heavy or murky, it is a sign to stop. If it feels clear and bright, let it carry you upward. \n\nTrue authority doesn't need to shout; it simply exists as a steady vibration. You are being guided by the laws of the heart, which are far older than the laws of men. Trust the guardian that walks beside you in the shadows. As long as you maintain your alignment with what is right, the entire Spire is your loyal companion, ensuring you reach the canopy with your spirit intact.	I walk the path of integrity, and I am supported by the loyal flow of universal truth.	Close your eyes and find your 'true north'—the core truth that guides your heart. Imagine yourself walking along a path of light where every step feels aligned and effortless. \n\nOptionally, visualize a wolf-like spirit of starlight jump from vine to vine beside you, its blue spark-prints marking a trail of integrity through the geometric forest.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Guide of Law", "content": "Tz'i' is the energy of spiritual law, justice, and authority. It is the dog, the loyal companion, and the guide who leads the soul through the dark. Tz'i' represents fidelity, accuracy, and the instinct for truth. It is the scribe who records the deeds of life and the guardian who protects the natural order. It points toward integrity and unconditional love, acting as the compass for the soul.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Law", "Loyalty", "Truth", "Guidance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Stability", "content": "The number 6 represents ultimate stability, flow, and the physical vitality of the solar system. It is an even number that brings balance to the work of the 5. 6 is often associated with the heart of the sky and the heart of the earth in perfect alignment. It facilitates responsiveness and organic growth. It is a day where things come together with less friction, allowing for a harmonious expansion of the journey.", "keywords": ["Flow", "Stability", "Vitality", "Harmony", "Responsiveness"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Practice loyalty to a friend or partner.", "Trust your intuition to guide you in a moral dilemma.", "Review a contract or agreement with a clear eye.", "Let go of a grudge; let justice flow naturally.", "Write down your core values and see if you are living them."], "title": "Flowing with Integrity", "content": "6 Tz'i' brings a beautiful, harmonious alignment to the concept of justice. Unlike the rigid application of law, 6 Tz'i' represents the *flow* of truth—justice that is natural, organic, and compassionate. In the Kan trecena, this day asks us to align our personal power with universal law. It is a day where doing the right thing feels easy and natural. Relationships can be healed today through loyalty and honesty. The energy supports finding your 'true north' and following it without struggle. It is a day of trust—trusting yourself, trusting the law of karma, and trusting the path."}}	{"title": "The Compassionate Judge", "content": "To be born on 6 Tz'i' is to be a beacon of integrity and harmonious authority. You possess a natural sense of right and wrong, but it is tempered by a deep understanding of human nature (the 6 energy). You are not a harsh judge; you are a guide. People trust you implicitly because they sense your loyalty and your lack of hidden agendas. You are likely the peacemaker in your family, the one who resolves disputes not by force, but by helping everyone see the truth.\\n\\nYour life path involves the administration of justice in its highest form—which is love. You may work in law, counseling, or any field where accuracy and ethics are paramount. You have a 'nose' for the truth and can sniff out deception instantly. However, you approach errors with a desire to correct and heal rather than to punish. You are a faithful friend and partner.\\n\\nYour challenge is to not become entangled in the problems of others. Your desire to help and your loyalty can sometimes lead you to stay in toxic situations too long. Your lesson is to learn that sometimes the most loving thing you can do is to let others face their own consequences. When you maintain your own boundaries while radiating integrity, you become a pillar of light, showing the world that true justice is a form of harmony."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#98b3c0", "primary": "#10191c", "secondary": "#36464e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.810219	2026-04-25 14:38:01.312645
1	1	1	1	Aj					{"nawal": {"title": "The Pillar of Community", "content": "Aj is the energy of the Cane or Reed—the emblem of home, stability, and righteous authority. It represents the spinal column of the human body and the pillars that hold up the roof of the temple. Aj is the gentle but unyielding leader who serves the community not through force, but through integrity and flexible strength. Like the bamboo that sways in the wind but never breaks, Aj teaches the wisdom of resilience. It governs the sanctity of the home space and the protection of those we love. This nawal connects deeply to the Earth and the sky, acting as a conduit between the two, reminding us that true authority comes from being hollow enough to let spirit pass through.", "keywords": ["Home", "Authority", "Stability", "Integrity", "Resilience"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Authority", "content": "The number One represents the singularity of creation, the initial spark from which all subsequent patterns emerge. It is the seed containing the entire holographic blueprint of the trecena, vibrating with unity and focused potential. On this day, the energy is not about scattering your attention but about identifying the core essence of what you wish to cultivate. It brings a feeling of fresh resolve and the power to initiate new cycles. Like a heavy stone dropped into a still pond, the intentions set under this influence ripple outward to define the next thirteen days. It is a time for firmness, clarity, and the solitary strength required to stand upright before the world.", "keywords": ["Unity", "Initiation", "Potential", "Seed", "Focus"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Clarify your non-negotiable values and boundaries today.", "Physically clean or bless your home to anchor fresh energy.", "Initiate a project that requires long-term stability and patience.", "Stand tall in a situation where you have previously made yourself small.", "Connect with the earth to stabilize your nervous system and intent."], "title": "Planting the Staff of Power", "content": "When the initiating force of the number One meets the stabilizing energy of Aj, we encounter a profound moment of grounding. This day is about planting your staff in the earth and claiming your space—not just physical territory, but your spiritual sovereignty. It is the perfect energy for establishing a new order in your life, whether that means revitalizing your home environment, stepping into a leadership role, or simply committing to a personal code of ethics. The atmosphere feels dense with purpose yet supportive, like the strong walls of a sanctuary. You are being asked to define the foundations upon which you will build your future. This is not a day for flighty ideas, but for concrete, tangible commitments that will shelter you and your community for the long haul."}}	{"title": "The Guardian of the Hearth", "content": "To be born on 1 Aj is to be the seed of stability and the anchor for those around you. You carry a natural, quiet authority that does not need to shout to be heard; your presence alone commands respect. You are the architect of safe spaces, instinctively knowing how to build structures—whether they are families, organizations, or physical homes—that endure the tests of time. Your soul's purpose is intertwined with the concept of the 'good leader,' one who leads by example and serves as a pillar of integrity for the community.\\n\\nYou likely possess a deep love for family and tradition, finding strength in your roots. However, your challenge lies in the rigidity that can sometimes accompany such stability. Because you are the 'One,' the initiator, you may feel you must carry the weight of the world alone. Your growth comes from learning the lesson of the reed: to remain upright by being flexible, bending with the winds of change rather than breaking under the pressure of your own high standards."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b9a971", "primary": "#161816", "secondary": "#474735"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.725609	2026-04-25 13:46:57.622596
7	1	7	7	Kawoq					{"nawal": {"title": "The Storm of Compassion", "content": "Kawoq is the energy of the community, the turtle, and the gathering storm. It represents the collective family and the compassionate, sometimes overwhelming, force of the divine feminine. Kawoq is the midwife, bringing new life into the world through the intensity of labor. It governs abundance, fertility, and the cleansing power of rain. While it is nurturing, Kawoq can also be tempestuous, washing away what is not true to the heart of the community. It asks us to consider the welfare of the group over the individual and to prepare for the rebirth of our reality.", "keywords": ["Community", "Compassion", "Storm", "Midwife", "Abundance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Peak of Reflection", "content": "The number Seven stands at the top of the pyramid, the midpoint of the thirteen-day cycle. It represents the point of maximum visibility, where we can look back at where we started and forward to where we are going. Seven is a mystical number, representing the perfect balance between the spiritual and material worlds. It is an energy of pause, reflection, and calibration. Unlike the active numbers, Seven asks us to stop and assess. It creates a space for choices to be weighed without pressure. It is the breath at the top of the climb before the descent begins.", "keywords": ["Reflection", "Mysticism", "Balance", "Midpoint", "Assessment"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Take a pause from social media to assess your own feelings vs. the collective's.", "Reflect on a recent 'stormy' period in your life: what was born from it?", "Gather with a small, trusted group to share deep feelings.", "Visualize yourself as the eye of the storm—calm amidst chaos.", "Assess the health of your 'community'—who supports you, who do you support?"], "title": "The Eye of the Storm", "content": "7 Kawoq places us in the calm center of the swirling energies of life. The reflective nature of Seven pauses the intense, generative power of the Kawoq storm, allowing us to understand the deeper purpose of the changes we are experiencing. This is a day to look at your role within your family and community from a spiritual perspective. Are you being swept away by the collective drama, or are you anchoring the light? The energy supports a deep, compassionate review of your relationships and your contribution to the whole. It is a time to incubate your dreams in the safety of the shell, knowing that the storm outside is preparing the soil for your growth."}}	{"title": "The Compassionate Mystic", "content": "To be born on 7 Kawoq is to be a lightning rod for collective emotion and spiritual insight. You stand at the crossroads of the human family, feeling the joys and sorrows of those around you with intense clarity. The number Seven gives you a mystical, reflective nature, while Kawoq provides you with a heart big enough to hold the storm. You are likely a natural counselor, teacher, or community organizer—someone who can see the spiritual lesson within the worldly struggle.\\n\\nYour challenge is learning to manage the flood of empathy so you do not drown in it. You may struggle with boundaries, feeling responsible for healing everyone's pain. Your soul's lesson is to understand that you are the midwife, not the mother; you assist in the birthing process, but you cannot carry the labor for others. By maintaining your own spiritual balance (the Seven), you become a safe harbor for others in the storm."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#7c7cb9", "primary": "#15171b", "secondary": "#393a55"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.734998	2026-04-25 13:46:57.6441
87	7	9	9	Toj	The forest feels different before you even see the water.\n\nIt is not heavier, not lighter—just more aware. As if every leaf has turned its face toward you, listening.\n\nYou walk the familiar path, but today you are not empty-handed. In your pocket or your palm or pressed against your heart, you carry something that has been quietly asking to be acknowledged: an old regret, a name, a memory, a promise you did not keep. It is small and invisible to anyone else, but you can feel its weight.\n\nWhen you reach the lake, you stop.\n\nThe surface is calm, but not waiting in the way it did at the beginning. It feels like an equal presence now, not a silent mirror or a distant mystery. The light from beneath—those seed-glows from yesterday—is softer, deeper, settled further down as if they are rooting themselves.\n\nNear the shoreline, you notice something new.\n\nSmall bowls float on the water, each holding a single flame. They drift in slow, deliberate patterns, never colliding, never tipping, their light reflected twice: once in the air, once in the depths. Some bowls carry petals. Some carry tiny stones. Some seem to carry nothing at all and still burn.\n\nYou understand without being told: you are not the only one who has come here asking. Others—seen and unseen, past and present—have stood where you stand, felt what you feel, and offered something back.\n\nYou sit at the edge of the lake and hold your invisible burden in your hands. You think of all the ways you have received: guidance in the wind, clarity at dawn, strength from the forest, seeds of possibility glowing beneath the surface. You think of the ways you have paid attention, and also of the times you have taken without thanks, walked away without closing the loop.\n\nA warmth rises in your chest. Not shame. Not punishment. Just the simple, human ache of knowing you could have done better and still can.\n\nYou take a small, flat stone from the shore and press it between your palms. You do not need ink or carving. You let your breath, your memory, and your honest feeling imprint themselves into it.\n\nThen, with a slow exhale, you place the stone at the water’s edge.\n\nThe lake responds in its own language.\n\nOne of the floating bowls drifts closer, as if caught in a current that wasn’t there a moment ago. Its flame leans toward you, reflecting in your eyes. For a brief second, you see your own face in the water—not the one you show the world, but the one that remembers everything you’ve carried—and you do not look away.\n\n“Thank you,” you whisper, though you are not entirely sure whether you are speaking to the lake, to the past, or to yourself.\n\nAs the words leave your mouth, something loosens. The weight you brought with you does not vanish; it changes shape. It feels less like a stone and more like a story that has finally been placed where it belongs.\n\nThe bowl drifts back toward the others. The flames sway together in a slow, almost-breathing rhythm.\n\nYou rise from the shore feeling a quiet balance settle into your bones. You have asked. You have received. You have given something back.\n\nFor the first time, you do not feel like a visitor here.\n\nYou feel like part of the exchange.	Today, your heart remembers that you are part of a web.\n\nYou may feel called to make amends, to say thank you, to finally acknowledge a debt of care or kindness—whether to another person, to yourself, or to the unseen forces that have held you up when you thought you were alone.\n\nThis is not about punishment or keeping score. It is about balance. About choosing to participate in the flow of giving and receiving with more awareness.\n\nAsk yourself: where have I been supported? What can I offer back, even in a small way? A sincere apology, a message of gratitude, a moment of service, a promise to treat yourself with more respect—all of these are offerings.\n\nLet your actions today be a quiet flame on the water: small, steady, and full of meaning.	I honor the ways life has supported me, and I choose to give back with sincerity, gratitude, and care.	Sit comfortably with your feet on the ground and your hands resting over your heart or in your lap. Close your eyes and imagine the lake before you at dusk.\n\nSee small bowls of light floating on the surface—each one an offering from someone, somewhere, across time. Some represent gratitude. Some represent healing. Some represent apologies finally spoken.\n\nBring to mind one place in your life that feels like it needs balance: a relationship, a memory, a pattern, or a way you’ve treated yourself. Hold it gently in your awareness.\n\nOn your inhale, imagine drawing in warmth from one of the floating flames. On your exhale, silently offer something back: a promise, a thank you, a willingness to change, a simple “I’m sorry.”\n\nRepeat this for several breaths, letting the exchange feel real and mutual. When you feel complete, picture your own small bowl of light joining the others on the water.\n\nOffer a quiet gratitude to the keepers of sacred fire, reciprocity, and balance. Then open your eyes and carry that intention into one concrete action today.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Fire", "content": "Toj is the Nawal of the offering, the sacred fire, and the payment of debts. It represents the law of cause and effect (karma) and the need for reciprocity. Toj is the energy of giving back to the universe to maintain balance. It governs physical and spiritual health, reminding us that illness is often a sign of imbalance. In human experience, Toj manifests as a desire to serve, a sense of duty, and the warmth of the hearth. When aligned, Toj brings purification and release from debt; when misaligned, it can lead to feeling victimized or burdened by obligation.", "keywords": ["Offering", "Payment", "Fire", "Balance", "Reciprocity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Womb of Patience", "content": "The number Nine represents the completion of the developmental cycle, the gestation period (9 months), and the energy of the feminine. In Mayan cosmology, Nine is associated with the 'Primordial Female' and the deep, dark soil where the seed transforms. Experientially, this energy feels introspective, creative, and sometimes slow. It is the patience of the mother waiting for the birth. It is a time for nurturing, refining details, and preparing for the final manifestation. The shadow of Nine can be isolation, but its light is the profound power of life generating life.", "keywords": ["Patience", "Gestation", "Feminine", "Completion", "Nurturing"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Make an offering (candle, incense, charity) with deep intention.", "Tend to your physical health; listen to your body's needs.", "Pay a bill or debt with a feeling of gratitude rather than resentment.", "Help a woman or a mother in your life.", "Reflect on what you are 'cooking' in your life; give it warmth."], "title": "Gestating Gratitude", "content": "The nurturing patience of Tone 9 meets the offering energy of Toj to create a day of 'Feminine Service.' 9 Toj is the energy of the mother who tends the fire. It is a day to pay your debts—energetic, emotional, or financial—with patience and love. The energy is not transactional; it is devotional. It suggests that true giving comes from a deep, gestating place within the heart. Today is a powerful time for healing, particularly health issues related to the feminine or the emotions. The fire of Toj is gentle today, warming the womb of potential. It asks: What are you willing to sacrifice for the new life that is coming? Offer your pain, your fear, or your ego to the fire. Nurture the spirit of gratitude within you, and watch how it transforms your reality. Service to others is the highest form of magic today."}}	{"title": "The Nurturing Flame", "content": "To be born on 9 Toj is to be a keeper of the sacred hearth. You are the 'Compassionate Offering'—a soul dedicated to service, healing, and the restoration of balance. You have a warm, nurturing presence that draws people to you for comfort. The number 9 gives you great patience and feminine wisdom, while Toj drives you to give back to the world. You are likely the one who takes care of everyone else, the one who pays the check, the one who remembers to say thank you.\\n\\nYour life path is one of clearing debt—for yourself and your lineage. You may face health challenges or heavy responsibilities, but these are your teachers, showing you the power of reciprocity. Your challenge is to learn that you cannot pour from an empty cup; you must receive as well as give. You are here to remind us that gratitude is the fire that keeps the world warm."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#de9171", "primary": "#0f110f", "secondary": "#4b352e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.788136	2026-04-25 13:46:57.781741
4	1	4	4	Ajmaq					{"nawal": {"title": "The Owl of Forgiveness", "content": "Ajmaq is the owl, the nawal of deep introspection, forgiveness, and the wisdom of the ancestors. It represents the veil between the living and the dead, and the curiosity to peer behind it. Ajmaq governs the 'sweetness' of life that comes from making peace with our imperfections. It is the energy of pardon—pardoning ourselves for our mistakes and pardoning others. This nawal acknowledges the human condition with all its flaws and teaches that wisdom comes from experience, often through trial and error. It is a gentle, dark, and profound energy that heals the lineage.", "keywords": ["Forgiveness", "Ancestors", "Wisdom", "Curiosity", "Pardon"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cube of Stability", "content": "The number Four brings the restless energy of Three into form. It represents the four directions, the four elements, and the solid foundation of the physical world. Four is the energy of stability, definition, and boundaries. It is the cube, the square, the table leg that holds the weight. On this day, the focus shifts to establishing order, defining parameters, and creating a safe container for growth. It is a grounding vibration that asks for practicality and endurance. While it may feel less dynamic, it provides the essential structure needed for any lasting creation.", "keywords": ["Stability", "Structure", "Foundation", "Order", "Directions"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create a physical altar or space to honor your ancestors.", "Write a letter of forgiveness to yourself or someone else (burn it or keep it).", "Examine family patterns that need to be stopped or structured differently.", "Focus on the practical aspects of a mistake: what was learned, what changes now?", "Ground your emotions by physically connecting with the four directions."], "title": "Grounding the Lineage", "content": "4 Ajmaq offers a profound opportunity to stabilize your spiritual and emotional foundations through forgiveness. The structural energy of Four combines with the ancestral depth of Ajmaq to help you build a solid base of inner peace. This is a day to 'settle' debts—energetic, emotional, or karmic. The stability of the Four allows you to look at past mistakes or family patterns without being toppled by them. It is a time to establish a firm boundary against guilt and shame, replacing them with the structural integrity of wisdom learned. You are building a house of forgiveness that will shelter your future growth."}}	{"title": "The Anchor of Wisdom", "content": "To be born on 4 Ajmaq is to be a stabilizing force for your lineage. You carry the weight of ancestral wisdom with the practical strength to apply it in the modern world. You are likely a 'pattern breaker'—someone who sees the recurring themes in your family history and has the fortitude to resolve them. The number Four gives you a love for structure and safety, while the Owl gives you the curiosity to explore the shadowy, hidden realms of the human psyche. People likely come to you for advice because you offer judgment-free, grounded perspectives.\\n\\nYour challenge is a tendency to carry too much responsibility or to become rigid in your definitions of right and wrong. You may struggle with perfectionism, forgetting that Ajmaq is about the wisdom of the mistake. Your soul's path is to build a life structure that is flexible enough to include forgiveness—for others, but most importantly, for yourself. You are here to demonstrate that true stability comes from making peace with the past."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#7e7b79", "primary": "#141614", "secondary": "#3b3935"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.732548	2026-04-25 13:46:57.640149
103	8	12	12	Aj	The storm breaks as quickly as it started. You enter the Eye of the Hurricane.\n\nHere, the air is perfectly still. You are standing on a circular platform made of white cane. In the center is a house. It is simple, thatched, and warm. Light spills from the windows.\n\n12 is the number of Understanding. Aj is the Home.\n\nYou walk to the house. You open the door. Inside, there is a fire burning in the hearth. There is a table set for one.\n\nYou sit down. You eat the bread and drink the water. You feel a profound sense of arrival. \n\nYou realize that the "Home" you were looking for was never a place on the map. It was this feeling of alignment inside you. The wind can blow, the path can twist, the net can tangle—but this internal hearth remains.\n\nYou understand now. You traveled through the sky to find the ground. You learned to speak so you could listen to the silence.\n\nYou rest. You are safe. You are the master of your own house.	You’ve arrived. The frantic energy settles down into a deep, warm hum. The energy of 12 Aj is about coming home to yourself. You understand something today that you didn’t understand yesterday.\n\nWhatever was confusing you has straightened out. Stand in your authority. You have earned your place at the table. Enjoy the stability. You are safe.	I am at home in my body, my life, and my spirit.	Visualize your spine as a stalk of golden corn or a bamboo cane. It is flexible but strong. It roots you to the earth and reaches for the sky.\n\nBreathe up and down your spine. Feel the energy flowing freely. You are the conduit. You are home.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Pillar of Community", "content": "Aj is the Nawal of the home, the cane, and the spinal column. It represents the principle of authority, leadership, and the upright growth of the cornstalk. Aj is the energy that holds up the roof—strong yet flexible. It governs the home, the family, and the community, emphasizing harmony, ethics, and protection. In human experience, Aj manifests as the desire to build a safe container for life. It is the staff of power. When aligned, Aj brings peace and stability; when misaligned, it can lead to rigidity or authoritarianism.", "keywords": ["Home", "Leadership", "Harmony", "Community", "Integrity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Crystal of Understanding", "content": "The number Twelve represents the grouping together, the village, and the understanding that comes from retrospection. In Mayan cosmology, Twelve is the energy of the 'Great Gathering.' It stabilizes the chaos of Eleven and integrates the lessons learned. Experientially, this energy feels inclusive, cooperative, and wise. It is a day to summarize, to discuss, and to connect the dots. The shadow of Twelve can be difficulty with individuality, but its light is the strength of the collective mind. Today, the universe holds a council.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Integration", "Cooperation", "Review", "Community"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Host a family dinner or community meeting.", "Offer support to a leader or an elder.", "Strengthen the physical structure of your home.", "Seek consensus in a group decision.", "Celebrate the stability that comes from belonging."], "title": "Community Pillars", "content": "When the integrative energy of Tone 12 meets the stabilizing force of Aj, we arrive at a day of 'Collective Strength.' 12 Aj is the energy of the village council or the strong family gathering. It represents the understanding that we are stronger together. The energy supports building community, resolving family issues, and establishing authority that is based on consensus rather than force. It is a day to strengthen the 'pillars' of your life—your home, your ethics, and your support systems. The chaos of the 11 E' detour settles into a new, shared stability. We realize that our individual paths (E') are supported by the collective home (Aj). It is an excellent day for leadership that serves the whole. Stand tall, but stand together. The cornstalks in the field support each other against the wind."}}	{"title": "The Pillar of the People", "content": "To be born on 12 Aj is to be a cornerstone of your community. You are the 'Collective Authority'—a soul who naturally takes on the role of leader, protector, or elder. You have a deep love for home and tradition, but the number 12 makes you inclusive and expansive. You want everyone to have a seat at the table. People look to you for strength and guidance because you embody integrity and fairness.\\n\\nYour life path is one of building structures that support the many. You are a natural organizer and a harmonizer, able to bring different viewpoints together under one roof. Your challenge is to not let the weight of the community rest too heavily on your shoulders (spine). Remember that a true pillar is part of a larger structure; you don't have to hold up the roof alone. You are here to show us the power of unity."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a09f68", "primary": "#0d0e0d", "secondary": "#3c352b"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#eae3cf", "primary": "#b6a17c", "secondary": "#d2c3a1"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#f9e3cc", "primary": "#a25838", "secondary": "#cf8754"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#bda172", "primary": "#111d2d", "secondary": "#43505b"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.799965	2026-04-25 13:46:57.795018
104	8	13	13	Ix	You leave the house and walk to the edge of the platform. The storm has vanished. The sky is a deep, endless indigo filled with stars, even though it is day.\n\nYou are in the Starry Expanse.\n\nSuddenly, the stars begin to move. They swirl down and form the shape of a giant Jaguar. It is not the earthly jaguar of the forest; it is the Cosmic Jaguar, the Night Sun.\n\n13 is Ascension. Ix is the Shaman. The cycle is complete.\n\nThe Jaguar bows to you. You bow back. You realize that the wind you have been riding, the breath you have been breathing—it was all magic. You have become the magician.\n\nYou look down at the world below. It looks small, precious. You are ready to go back. But you are not going back as a sleepwalker. You are going back as an Awakener.\n\nYou take a step off the edge. You do not fall. You float. You are lighter than air.\n\nThe wind catches you, gentle and loving, and carries you home.	The journey is done. You have climbed the mountain and flown with the wind. The energy of 13 Ix is high magic. You might feel a bit ungrounded, floating in the ether. Enjoy it.\n\nYou have accessed a new level of intuition. Carry this magic with you as you start the next cycle. You are a wizard of your own life. Use your power wisely.	I am a being of magic, connected to the stars and the earth.	Visualize yourself turning into stardust. You expand until you fill the entire universe. You are the stars. You are the darkness between them.\n\nFeel the infinite peace of the cosmos. You are everywhere and nowhere. You are free.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Jaguar of Earth Magic", "content": "Ix is the Nawal of the Jaguar, the night, and the magic of the Earth. It represents the feminine mysteries, intuition, and the high magic of the shrines and altars. Ix is the energy that sees in the dark; it connects us to the subtle forces of nature and the wisdom of the mountains. As the archetype of the Shaman and the Healer, Ix governs our capacity to transform and to manifest through intent. In human experience, Ix brings a heightened sensitivity and a love for solitude. It is the velvet darkness that holds the stars.", "keywords": ["Earth Magic", "Intuition", "Jaguar", "Sacred Sites", "Manifestation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascension", "content": "The number Thirteen represents the completion of the cycle, the ascension to the next level, and the spirit world. In Mayan cosmology, Thirteen is the number of the ancestors and the highest vibration of time. It is the moment where the wave crashes onto the shore and recedes to become part of the ocean again. Experientially, this energy feels magical, heightened, and sometimes ungrounded. It is a day of 'déjà vu' and profound intuition. The shadow of Thirteen can be a disconnection from reality, but its light is the ultimate transformation.", "keywords": ["Completion", "Ascension", "Ancestors", "Transformation", "Spirit"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a closing ritual for the trecena; give thanks to the wind and the earth.", "Spend time in a wild place; listen to the silence.", "Trust your psychic hits; they are accurate today.", "Connect with the 'magic' in your life—art, love, nature.", "Celebrate the mystery; you don't need to understand everything to feel it."], "title": "Ascended Magic", "content": "The Iq' trecena concludes with the powerful magic of 13 Ix. Here, the ascension energy of Tone 13 meets the shamanic power of the Jaguar. This is a day of 'High Magic.' We have traveled through the wind of spirit (Iq'), and now we land in the heart of the Earth's mystery. 13 Ix is the energy of the sorcerer who has mastered the elements. It is a day of profound connection to nature and the invisible realms. The veil is nonexistent today. Your intuition is operating at its highest peak. Use this energy to close the cycle with a ritual or a prayer. Connect with the spirit of the Earth; ask for vision, healing, and transformation. The Jaguar walks fearlessly between the worlds today, and so can you. The wind has become breath, and the breath has become magic. You are the bridge between the sky and the soil."}}	{"title": "The Cosmic Shaman", "content": "To be born on 13 Ix is to be a soul of deep, ancient power. You are the 'Ascended Jaguar'—a mystic who walks between the worlds with ease. You possess a profound intuition and a natural connection to the magical arts, healing, and the forces of nature. The number 13 connects you to the spirit world and the ancestors, while Ix grounds that power in the Earth. You are a conduit for high-frequency energy.\\n\\nYour life path is one of spiritual mastery. You are here to bring the magic of the invisible world into the visible one. You may be drawn to shamanism, energy work, or environmental protection. Your presence is often intense and magnetic; people can feel that you 'know' things. Your challenge is to stay grounded in your body and not get lost in the spirit realms. You are here to remind us that the world is far more mysterious and beautiful than we dare to imagine."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#8dd3a0", "primary": "#0d1b18", "secondary": "#376047"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#5191ab", "primary": "#0a1a1f", "secondary": "#204b59"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#a292b7", "primary": "#453260", "secondary": "#6f5a88"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#8791bd", "primary": "#111745", "secondary": "#3c4584"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.800409	2026-04-25 13:46:57.807377
137	11	7	7	B'atz'	You reach the pyramid’s peak of the cycle—a broad, mossy platform that hangs in the center of the vertical abyss by seven silken threads. From here, you can see the entire tapestry of the Spire stretching above and below, a grand weaving of time and growth. But the Spire does not ask for solemnity today; it offers a long, iridescent vine that hangs over the void like a great pendulum. In this midpoint of equilibrium, you find the spirit of the Monkey. You grab the vine and leap, swinging out into the open air with a shout that echoes through the emerald cathedral.\n\nAs you swing, the 'seriousness' of the evolution dissolves into the joy of creation. You are the weaver and the thread, moving through the air in a playful arc that defies the heavy logic of the climb. Below you, the kaleidoscope of the forest floor shifts in vibrant patterns; above you, the stars beckon. The number 7 grants you the vision to see all your options at once, but B'atz' reminds you that the most powerful choice is to create beauty with a light heart. You are re-weaving your destiny in mid-air, picking up dropped stitches of joy and adding new colors to the design of your life. When you finally swing back to the platform, you are breathless and laughing, your spirit as flexible and bright as the silver threads that hold the world together.	You’ve reached a precarious midpoint where the view is dizzying and the logic of the climb begins to fail. The universe is dangling a single, iridescent silken thread over the vast abyss and daring you to grab it. Today, the 'seriousness' of your spiritual work is actually your biggest obstacle. The cosmos is a playful weaver, and it wants you to remember that growth shouldn't always feel like a chore. \n\nLet go of the heavy effort and embrace the trickster within. Laugh at the absurdity of the obstacles you’ve faced so far. When you move with a light heart and a mischievous grin, you find you can re-weave the design of your destiny in mid-air. The threads of time are flexible today, and beauty is born from play and improvisation, not just from grim determination. \n\nLeap into the open space. Swing across the gaps of your own fear. Shout your joy into the emerald cathedral and listen to the echo. The void isn't empty—it is full of the colors you haven't used yet. Today, you aren't just a traveler; you are the artist of the climb, and the sky is your canvas.	I am the master weaver of my own destiny, creating beauty from the threads of my experience.	Close your eyes and visualize a silver thread in your hands. Realize you have the power to pick up any dropped stitches of joy and re-weave your destiny. \n\nOptionally, stand on a mossy platform held by seven silken threads, watching a kaleidoscope of flower petals and light-particles swirl around you in a dance of equilibrium.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Weaver of Time", "content": "B'atz' is the thread of time, the artist, and the weaver of destiny. It represents the creative principle that organizes chaos into beauty. B'atz' is the monkey, the playful trickster who reminds us not to take the illusion too seriously, yet who holds the sacred calendar in its hands. It governs the arts, marriage, and the weaving together of community and purpose. It is the beginning of time and the continuity of life.", "keywords": ["Creativity", "Weaving", "Time", "Art", "Thread"]}, "number": {"title": "The Summit of Reflection", "content": "The number 7 represents the top of the pyramid, the midpoint of the 13-day cycle. It is a place of mystical power, equilibrium, and the ability to see both the past (1-6) and the future (8-13) simultaneously. 7 is a number of channeling, high magic, and the lack of definite polarity—it is the center point where all options are visible. It allows for a pause to integrate and align before the energy descends into manifestation.", "keywords": ["Equilibrium", "Mysticism", "Overview", "Midpoint", "Channeling"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in any form of artistic creation without judgment.", "Look for synchronicities; the 'weaver' is sending signs.", "Reflect on the timeline of your life from a higher perspective.", "Celebrate a partnership or a marriage.", "Laugh; do not take your spiritual path too seriously today."], "title": "Weaving the Mystical Pattern", "content": "7 B'atz' is a day of high magic and creative vision. Standing at the top of the pyramid, we see the thread of our life stretching backward and forward. In the Kan trecena, this is where we weave our newfound wisdom into the fabric of our destiny. It is a powerful day for artists, visionaries, and spiritual seekers. The energy is playful yet profound. It asks us to look at the patterns we are creating. Are they beautiful? Are they strong? Today you have the power to change the design, to pick up a dropped stitch, or to start a new color. It is a day to celebrate the sheer joy of existence."}}	{"title": "The Visionary Artist", "content": "To be born on 7 B'atz' is to be a soul who weaves magic into the mundane. You are the ultimate artist of life. You possess a unique perspective that allows you to see the connections between things that others miss. You are likely multi-talented, creative, and charming, with a touch of the mystic. You live your life as a work of art, constantly improvising and creating beauty from whatever materials are at hand. You are a natural conduit for divine inspiration.\\n\\nYour life path is one of expression and synthesis. You are here to show the world that time is not a straight line, but a tapestry. You may struggle with the mundane details of life because your head is often in the clouds (the 7 energy), but your creative output is profound. You are a gatherer of people and ideas, weaving them together into communities or projects.\\n\\nYour challenge is grounding. You can be so open to the flow of the universe that you have trouble finishing what you start. You may also be indecisive, seeing so many beautiful possibilities that you cannot choose one. Your lesson is to choose a thread and follow it. When you discipline your creative genius, you become a master weaver, creating works—whether art, families, or systems—that endure through time and inspire generations."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d19794", "primary": "#181514", "secondary": "#64393d"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.810598	2026-04-25 14:38:01.313637
194	15	12	12	Q'anil					{"nawal": {"title": "The Seed of Life", "content": "Q'anil is the seed, the rabbit, and the star Venus. It represents fertility, abundance, biological life, and the potential for a glorious harvest. Q'anil is the energy of the 'yellow'—the color of ripening corn. It governs genetics, pregnancy, and the planting of intentions. It is a gentle, joyful, and creative energy that loves to see things grow. In its shadow, Q'anil can manifest as drunkenness, wastefulness, or the refusal to grow up. But in its light, it is the eternal optimism of the gardener, the creator of beauty, and the promise that every ending contains a new beginning. It asks us to trust the slow, miraculous process of life unfolding.", "keywords": ["Seed", "Fertility", "Harvest", "Abundance", "Growth"]}, "number": {"title": "The Crystal of Understanding", "content": "Tone 12 represents the summing up, the gathering of wisdom, and the complex stability of the community. It is 4 x 3 (structure x movement). Tone 12 is the 'Village.' It governs the court of law, the council of elders, and the library of experience. After the disruption of the 11, the 12 reassembles the pieces into a new, higher understanding. It is a day of review, cooperation, and looking at the whole picture. It is not yet the final release (13), but the point where the lesson is fully comprehended. Tone 12 asks us to connect the dots and to share our realized wisdom with the group.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Cooperation", "Wisdom", "Review", "Wholeness"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Celebrate your achievements and growth with others.", "Share your wisdom or creative work with your community.", "Reflect on the 'harvest' of the last 12 days; what worked?", "Plant a metaphorical seed for the future with full understanding of its potential.", "Enjoy the abundance of life—eat good food, appreciate nature, be grateful."], "title": "The Ripening of Wisdom", "content": "12 Q'anil is a beautiful, abundant day representing the 'village harvest.' The comprehensive understanding of the 12 meets the fertile seed energy of Q'anil. It suggests that our wisdom has ripened and is ready to be shared. This is a day to celebrate the fruits of our labor—not just the material results, but the lessons learned along the way. The energy is communal and joyous; it supports gathering with friends, feasting, or collaborating on a creative project. We are asked to look at the seeds we planted at the beginning of the cycle and acknowledge how they have grown. It is a time to understand that every experience (12) is a seed (Q'anil) for the future. The struggle is over; now is the time to enjoy the beauty of what has been created and to carefully select the 'seeds' (ideas/intentions) we want to carry forward."}}	{"title": "The Keeper of the Garden", "content": "To be born on 12 Q'anil is to be a cultivator of life and a pillar of the community. You are the 'Wise Seed.' The number 12 gives you a complex, comprehensive mind that seeks to understand how everything fits together, while Q'anil fills you with creativity, optimism, and a love for growth. You are a natural teacher, parent, or mentor. You see the potential in everyone and everything, and you have the patience to help it blossom. Your life is a garden, and you are happiest when it is full of diverse, thriving plants (people/projects).\\n\\nYour life path is one of bringing things to fruition. You are not a starter who quits; you are a finisher who nurtures. You likely have a talent for bringing people together to cooperate (12) on something beautiful (Q'anil). You may be drawn to agriculture, education, the arts, or community planning. You understand that true abundance is not just money, but a richness of experience and connection. You are the one who reminds the group to stop and smell the flowers, to celebrate the wins, and to respect the cycles of nature.\\n\\nHowever, the challenge of 12 Q'anil is over-giving. You want so badly for everything to grow that you may deplete your own soil nurturing others. The complexity of the 12 can also make you prone to 'analysis paralysis'—wanting to understand every variable before planting the seed. Your shadow side might struggle with addiction or escapism if life feels too heavy. Your soul's growth lies in remembering that you are also a seed. You must nurture your own growth with the same love you pour into the world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c0b076", "primary": "#101817", "secondary": "#4a463a"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.850184	2026-04-25 13:46:57.964478
142	11	12	12	Ajmaq	The wind dies down, replaced by a heavy, golden silence. You enter a cloud of shimmering pollen that hangs like a curtain across the path. This is the Ancestor’s Breath, carrying the collective wisdom and soft whispers of every soul that has ever climbed the Spire. In this space of total understanding, the weight of your past 'mistakes' begins to dissolve. You see each stumble and doubt not as a failure, but as a necessary facet of the jewel you are becoming. The pardon of Ajmaq washes over you, a gentle frequency that reconciles your humanity with your divinity. You sit amidst the golden dust, bundling your 12 days of experience into a coherent body of knowledge. You forgive yourself for the struggle, realizing that the nectar of wisdom is only gathered by those who are willing to fall and rise again. You are at peace with your lineage, a wise counselor of your own soul, ready for the final step.	The wind has finally died down, leaving you in a heavy, golden silence filled with shimmering, iridescent dust. This is the 'Ancestor’s Breath'—the collected, synthesized wisdom of every soul that has walked before you and every experience you have ever endured. In this space of total understanding, there is no such thing as a mistake or a wasted moment. \n\nEvery stumble you’ve made, every wrong turn, and every heart-wrenching delay was actually the golden pollen needed to fertilize the profound wisdom you are carrying right now. Today is for radical, multidirectional forgiveness. Bundle your 12 days of effort and struggle with a ribbon of mercy and put them to rest. \n\nYou understand the 'why' of the journey now, seeing how the darkness was just as necessary as the light. You are at peace with the version of yourself that started this climb, recognizing their bravery and their innocence. This peace has turned your very being into a jewel of complex, ancestral light. Sit in the golden fog and let the reconciliation heal every crack in your soul.	I am at peace with my journey and my lineage, accepting the perfection of my human experience.	Sit in a golden, peaceful silence. Reflect on your 'mistakes' and wrap them in a blanket of total forgiveness, realizing they were the jewels needed for your wisdom. \n\nOptionally, enter a cloud of shimmering golden pollen that carries the soft whispers of your ancestors, reconciling your human path with your divine soul.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Owl of Forgiveness", "content": "Ajmaq is the energy of the owl, the ancestors, and the pardon. It represents the human experience—the sweetness of life, but also the inevitable mistakes and the need for forgiveness. Ajmaq is the curiosity to peer into the dark and the wisdom to accept imperfection. It is the day of reconciliation, of healing ancestral lines, and of making peace with one's own humanity. It reminds us that we are learning, and that stumbling is part of the walk.", "keywords": ["Forgiveness", "Curiosity", "Ancestors", "Wisdom", "Pardon"]}, "number": {"title": "The Crystal of Understanding", "content": "The number 12 represents understanding, the gathering of wisdom, and the bundling of life experience. It is the highest even number, representing a stable, complex wholeness. 12 is the energy of the council, the village, and the retrospective view. It brings the capacity to understand the 'why' of the journey. It is a day of synthesis, where the scattered lessons of the trecena come together into a coherent body of knowledge.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Wisdom", "Synthesis", "Community", "Review"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Reflect on your 'mistakes' and see the wisdom they gave you.", "Forgive yourself for not being perfect.", "Light a candle for the 'forgotten' ancestors.", "Share a vulnerable story with someone you trust.", "Accept a situation exactly as it is, without trying to fix it."], "title": "Understanding the Human Experience", "content": "12 Ajmaq is a day of profound wisdom and compassion. We gather the lessons of the Kan trecena and filter them through the lens of forgiveness. The understanding of the 12 meets the pardon of Ajmaq. This creates a space of total acceptance. We understand *why* we made mistakes; we understand the struggles of our ancestors; we understand our own humanity. It is a day to bundle up your past with love and put it to rest. The wisdom gained is not just intellectual; it is emotional and ancestral. The energy is soft, deep, and incredibly healing."}}	{"title": "The Wise Counselor", "content": "To be born on 12 Ajmaq is to be an old soul filled with compassion for the human condition. You possess a deep, accumulated wisdom that seems to span lifetimes. You are the confessor, the counselor, and the friend who listens without judgment. You understand that life is messy and that everyone is doing their best. You have a strong connection to the past and to your lineage, often acting as the one who heals the family karma.\\n\\nYour life path is one of synthesis and reconciliation. You are a gatherer of lost souls and lost wisdom. You have a curiosity that drives you to explore the hidden or taboo aspects of life, but you do so with a gentle heart. You are a bridge between the generations, honoring the old while welcoming the new.\\n\\nYour challenge is the weight of the past. You can sometimes get bogged down in nostalgia, regret, or the collective grief of the world. You may also struggle to forgive yourself, even as you forgive others. Your lesson is to use your understanding to liberate, not to bind. When you realize that every experience is a jewel in the bundle of life, you become a true sage, teaching the world the power of unconditional love."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#bb9bb2", "primary": "#101315", "secondary": "#473946"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.812175	2026-04-25 14:38:01.317704
120	10	3	3	Q'anil					{"nawal": {"title": "The Seed of Abundance", "content": "Q'anil is the energy of the seed, the star, and the ripening crop. It represents fertility, potential, and the inevitable unfolding of life when conditions are right. Q'anil is the promise that what is planted with intention will grow. It carries a gentle, golden energy of nourishment and organic development. It reminds us that we cannot force the flower to open; we can only tend the soil and trust the process. It is the Rabbit in the Moon, constantly regenerating life.", "keywords": ["Seed", "Fertility", "Abundance", "Growth", "Ripening"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Movement", "content": "The number 3 introduces movement, flow, and the disruption of static balance. It is the energy of the child, the creative spark that refuses to sit still. 3 breaks the duality of 2 to create a dynamic triangle of flow. It is associated with communication, expression, and the rhythm of life. While it brings great creativity and change, it can also bring instability or scattered energy if not channeled. It is the pulse of the drum and the wind in the sails.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Creativity", "Flow", "Rhythm", "Change"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Plant a physical seed or start a new creative draft today.", "Move your body to shift stagnant energy and encourage flow.", "Speak your intentions out loud to give them vibration and form.", "Trust the instability of new growth; wobbling is part of rising.", "Nurture a budding idea with time and attention, even if it seems small."], "title": "Germinating the New Life", "content": "3 Q'anil activates the seeds of rebirth that were planted on 1 Kame. The stillness of the seed is broken by the movement of sprouting. This is a day of dynamic growth and creative fertility. The transformation is no longer just an idea; it is beginning to show visible signs of movement. You may feel a restless urge to create, to start projects, or to express the new life bubbling up within you. It is a fortunate day for artists, gardeners, and anyone seeking to bring a dream into reality. The energy supports breaking through the soil of the old self to reach for the light."}}	{"title": "The Spreader of Seeds", "content": "To be born on 3 Q'anil is to be a vibrant catalyst for growth and abundance. You carry an infectious, dynamic energy that naturally inspires others to develop their potential. You are the wind that scatters the seeds, ensuring that life blooms in unexpected places. You are likely artistic, expressive, and deeply connected to the cycles of nature. Your presence brings a sense of optimism and possibility; you are the one who sees the harvest before the seeds have even been watered.\\n\\nYour modality is movement. You are not meant to be static. You thrive when you are communicating, traveling, or circulating ideas. You are a natural networker of organic life—connecting people to resources, or ideas to reality. Your creativity is prolific, though you may sometimes struggle to finish what you start because your mind is always jumping to the next fertile possibility.\\n\\nYour challenge is to cultivate patience and focus. The 3 energy can be scattered, and Q'anil requires time to ripen. You may feel frustrated if success doesn't happen overnight. Your soul's lesson is to trust the rhythm of your own growth, learning that true abundance is not a sprint but a season. When you learn to channel your boundless energy into sustained nurturing, you become a master gardener of life, leaving a legacy of beauty and fruition wherever you go."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#baaf7a", "primary": "#101918", "secondary": "#49483d"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.806276	2026-04-25 13:46:57.873234
11	1	11	11	Aq'ab'al					{"nawal": {"title": "The Dawn of Revelation", "content": "Aq'ab'al is the dawn, the twilight, the threshold between night and day. It represents the moment when the light conquers the darkness, bringing clarity and new beginnings. Aq'ab'al is the energy of potential, of the 'idea' becoming the 'reality.' It governs duality, polarization, and the sudden realization of truth. This nawal is optimistic but realistic; it knows the dark exists but chooses the light. It asks us to wake up, to wipe the sleep from our eyes, and to seize the opportunities that are emerging on the horizon.", "keywords": ["Dawn", "New Beginnings", "Polarity", "Potential", "Clarity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Dissolution", "content": "The number Eleven represents dissonance, trial, and the breaking of patterns. It is often seen as a challenging number, not because it is 'bad,' but because it forces us to shed what is no longer working. Eleven is the energy of the seed husk cracking open so the sprout can emerge. It brings a lack of balance that compels movement. This vibration asks us to let go of our rigid structures and expand. It is the necessary chaos that precedes a higher order. Eleven days are often intense, requiring flexibility and non-attachment.", "keywords": ["Change", "Dissonance", "Liberation", "Trial", "Expansion"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Embrace a sudden change of plans as a divine redirection.", "Wake up before sunrise to witness the physical dawn and set intentions.", "Identify a belief system that feels 'tight' and consciously break out of it.", "Look for the opportunity hidden within a challenge or conflict.", "Allow yourself to feel the tension of the threshold without rushing to resolve it."], "title": "Breaking Through to the Light", "content": "11 Aq'ab'al is a high-voltage day of breakthrough. The pattern-breaking energy of Eleven combines with the dawning light of Aq'ab'al to create a powerful moment of realization. This is a day where old structures may crumble, but the light that shines through the cracks is blindingly beautiful. You may experience a sudden shift in perspective, a 'waking up' from a long slumber. The energy can feel unstable, like the flickering light of a candle in the wind, but it is driving you toward a higher clarity. Don't cling to the night; let the dawn strip away your illusions. It is a time to reinvent yourself."}}	{"title": "The Harbinger of Dawn", "content": "To be born on 11 Aq'ab'al is to be a transformer, a person who lives on the edge of the new. You are comfortable in the liminal spaces where others feel anxious. The number Eleven gives you a restless, seeking spirit that is never satisfied with the status quo, while Aq'ab'al provides you with the optimism to see the potential for a new day in every ending. You are likely an innovator, a revolutionary, or a guide who helps others navigate transitions. Your life is a series of reinventions.\\n\\nYour challenge is that your life can feel like a rollercoaster. The instability of the Eleven means you may struggle to find a resting place. You might be prone to breaking things—relationships, jobs, habits—just to feel the rush of the new. Your soul's path is to learn that the dawn is a daily occurrence, not a crisis. You are here to show others that change is not something to be feared, but the very mechanism by which the light enters."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a4794e", "primary": "#111211", "secondary": "#463d34"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.737979	2026-04-25 13:46:57.628545
9	1	9	9	Imox					{"nawal": {"title": "The Primordial Ocean", "content": "Imox is the spirit of the water, the collective unconscious, and the source of all things. It represents the dream world, intuition, and the chaotic, creative soup from which reality emerges. Imox is the lizard, the crocodile that floats half-submerged. It governs our emotions, our sanity, and our connection to the telepathic web of life. This nawal is fluid, irrational, and deeply psychic. It can bring immense creativity or emotional overwhelm. It asks us to embrace the flow, to trust our gut feelings, and to recognize that we are not separate drops, but part of a vast ocean.", "keywords": ["Water", "Dreams", "Intuition", "Collective", "Chaos"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cycle of Gestation", "content": "The number Nine represents the feminine, the mysterious, and the completion of cycles. It is the number of life, associated with the nine months of human gestation. Nine brings an energy of patience, depth, and the quiet work that happens in the dark before birth. It is often linked to the ancestors and the 'Great Mystery.' This vibration is not about rushing to the finish line, but about ensuring that the creation is fully formed and viable. It asks for trust in the timing of the universe and a willingness to sit in the unknown.", "keywords": ["Gestation", "Feminine", "Mystery", "Patience", "Depth"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Pay close attention to your dreams; keep a journal by your bed.", "Spend time near a body of water (ocean, lake, river, or bath).", "Engage in free-flow writing or painting without a plan.", "Avoid crowded places if you feel psychically porous.", "Trust your 'crazy' ideas—they are seeds from the collective mind."], "title": "Dreaming the World into Being", "content": "9 Imox is a day of deep, submerged magic. The gestational energy of Nine combines with the watery depths of Imox to create a womb-like atmosphere. This is a day where the veil between the conscious and unconscious is incredibly thin. It is a time for dreaming, for artistic incubation, and for connecting with the feminine lineage. The energy is soft, nebulous, and highly psychic. You may feel more emotional or sensitive than usual; this is simply your antennae picking up the collective frequency. Do not try to force logic onto today's experiences. Instead, float in the mystery and let your intuition guide the ripening of your soul's desires."}}	{"title": "The Dreamer of the Deep", "content": "To be born on 9 Imox is to be a bridge between the dream world and waking reality. You are a deeply sensitive and intuitive soul, often feeling the emotions of others as if they were your own. The number Nine gives you a connection to the mysteries of life and death, while Imox grants you access to the collective unconscious. You are likely an artist, a visionary, or a healer who works with the psyche. You understand that reality is fluid and that imagination is the precursor to matter.\\n\\nYour challenge is staying grounded. The vastness of your internal ocean can sometimes lead to confusion, escapism, or difficulty distinguishing your feelings from the collective's. You may struggle with 'reality' in the conventional sense. Your soul's path is to learn to navigate these waters without drowning—to bring the pearls of wisdom from the deep up to the surface. You are here to remind the world of the power of the invisible."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#90d7c5", "primary": "#111f1e", "secondary": "#31605c"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.736718	2026-04-25 13:46:57.646552
139	11	9	9	Aj	The Spire invites you inward. You discover a hidden opening that leads into the Hollow of the Mother—a quiet, protected chamber deep within the primary trunk of the world-tree. The walls here are lined with soft, pulsing fibers that mimic the interior of a womb, and the air is heavy with the scent of sweet corn and ancient wood. This is a place of gestation, governed by the feminine principle of the number 9. You sit in the center of the hollow, focusing on your own spine—the internal pillar that has supported your climb. You feel it strengthening, becoming as resilient and flexible as the cane.\n\nIn the silence, you nurture the new authority that has begun to take shape within you. It is a leadership born not of command, but of integrity and the sanctity of the home. You are no longer just climbing; you are building a sanctuary within your own being. The power of Kan has transformed into a steady, internal structure. Like a tender shoot protected by the husk, your new self is ripening in the dark, gathering the ancestral strength needed to stand tall in the world above. You breathe with the slow, deep pulse of the Spire’s heart, recognizing that true resurrection happens first in the quiet, secret places of the soul.	The world asks you to step inside for a while, away from the noise of the wind and the glare of the sun. Deep within the protected hollow of your own being, there is a secret ripening happening today. You are building an internal pillar—a source of strength that is as flexible as bamboo but as unbreakable as ancient stone. This is the quiet gestation of your new authority. \n\nYou don't need to shout, prove your worth, or perform your power for anyone else right now. Like a tender shoot protected by a thick, golden husk, let your new self-worth grow in the nourishing dark. Feel your posture straighten naturally as your spine aligns with the vertical axis of the universe. \n\nThis is the strength of the home and the hearth, the power that supports the world without ever needing to demand applause. When you finally emerge from this internal sanctuary, you will find that you no longer need to seek permission to lead. Your presence alone will be enough to stabilize the rooms you enter. Trust the silence; it is the most fertile ground you have.	I am the sanctuary of my own growth, and I stand tall with the resilience of the ancient wood.	Close your eyes and imagine a tender shoot of green growing within a protective husk. Feel the patience and strength of the feminine principle nurturing your internal growth. \n\nOptionally, breathe with the slow, deep heartbeat of the Spire's trunk, becoming as resilient and flexible as the cane that stands tall against the wind.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Pillar of Community", "content": "Aj is the cane, the cornstalk, and the pillar. It represents the spine, the home, and the authority of the lineage. Aj is the energy of the benevolent leader who supports the family and the community. It signifies triumph, resurrection, and the ability to stand tall and flexible like the bamboo. It connects the earth to the sky and represents the sanctity of the home space. It is the protector of the tender shoots of life.", "keywords": ["Home", "Authority", "Spine", "Corn", "Resurrection"]}, "number": {"title": "The Circle of Life", "content": "The number 9 represents the feminine principle, gestation, and the circle of life. It is the number of the nine months of pregnancy and the nine lords of the night. 9 brings a quieter, more internal energy than the 8. It is about patience, stealth, and the slow, unseen development of life in the dark. It is a fortunate number for female spirituality and for projects that need to be nurtured in secret before they are born.", "keywords": ["Gestation", "Feminine", "Patience", "Depth", "Circle"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Spend time at home; cook, clean, or beautify your space.", "Nurture a child or a vulnerable part of yourself.", "Stand tall and breathe into your spine; feel your internal pillar.", "Keep your big plans to yourself for now; let them ripen.", "Connect with the feminine aspect of authority (nurturing strength)."], "title": "Gestating the New Authority", "content": "9 Aj is a day of deep, internal strengthening. It represents the gestation of a new kind of leadership—one that is rooted in the home, the heart, and the spine. In the Kan trecena, this is the day where the wisdom we have gained begins to form into a solid internal structure. It is a day for privacy, for tending to the home, and for nurturing the family. The energy is quiet, protective, and potent. Like the corn growing in the husk, something strong and vital is developing within you. It is a time to trust the unseen growth and to fortify your inner sanctuary."}}	{"title": "The Nurturing Pillar", "content": "To be born on 9 Aj is to be a source of profound, quiet strength for your loved ones. You are the heart of the home and the spine of the family. You possess a deep, nurturing energy that allows others to grow and flourish under your protection. You are a natural parent, mentor, or community leader, but you lead from behind or from within, rather than from a podium. You have a great capacity for patience and for holding space.\\n\\nYour life path involves the creation of safe containers. You are a builder of homes—not just physical houses, but emotional sanctuaries. You are deeply connected to the feminine mysteries of birth, growth, and resurrection. You have a resilience that is quiet but unbreakable; like the bamboo, you bend but do not break. You are a keeper of traditions and a protector of the vulnerable.\\n\\nYour challenge is to not lose yourself in the role of the caretaker. You can be so focused on gestating the lives of others that you forget to live your own. You may also struggle with being too private or holding things in. Your lesson is to let your own light shine. When you balance your nurturing instincts with your own need for growth, you become a pillar of light that supports the world without crumbling under the weight."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d6bb77", "primary": "#151715", "secondary": "#534636"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.811217	2026-04-25 14:38:01.314781
141	11	11	11	Tz'ikin	As you reach the highest reaches of the Spire, the humid air of the lower canopy is replaced by a fierce, high-altitude gale. This is the Force of Resolution, a vibration so thin and high it shakes the very structure of the forest. You watch as the wind strips away the remaining Ghost-Skins and false hopes that clung to the vines, leaving only the essential core of your journey. In this clearing, your vision shifts. You no longer see the Spire as a series of separate obstacles, but as a single, magnificent organism of infinite abundance. From this vantage point, you possess the eagle’s eye, spotting opportunities for prosperity that were invisible from the shadows below. The dissonance of the climb has served its purpose, refining your perspective until only the truth remains. You stand on a narrow, pulsing branch, your hair whipped by the wind, feeling the exhilaration of a vision that is finally, undeniably clear.	A fierce, high-altitude wind is blowing through your life today, and it hasn't come to destroy you—it has come to do you a massive favor. It is stripping away the 'ghost-skins' of old illusions, small-minded fears, and the petty anxieties that have been cluttering your field of vision. Don't fight the gale or try to hold onto the debris. Let the wind clear the air until only the essential truth remains. \n\nFrom this height, the problems that felt like insurmountable mountains just yesterday are revealed to be nothing more than tiny, harmless pebbles. You have the eagle’s eye now, spotting vast opportunities for prosperity and connection that were hidden in the shadows of your own doubt. \n\nLet go of the limited, 'ground-level' thinking that kept you feeling caged. The sky is wide open, your wings are strong, and the vision of your future is finally, undeniably clear. You can see the whole pattern now, the grand weaving of your life’s potential. Fly toward the light of your highest ambition; the wind is officially at your back.	I let go of limited thinking and soar toward the expansive opportunities of my true potential.	Close your eyes and imagine a fierce wind blowing through your mind, clearing away all cluttered thoughts and small-minded doubts. See the vast landscape of abundance stretching out before you. \n\nOptionally, stand on a narrow branch high in the Spire, watching the gale sweep away the last ghost-skins as you fly with the expansive vision of the eagle.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Visionary Eagle", "content": "Tz'ikin is the bird, the eagle, and the vision. It represents prosperity, freedom, and the ability to see the whole picture from above. Tz'ikin is the intermediary between heaven and earth, carrying prayers up and bringing abundance down. It governs business, wealth, and the clear vision required to manifest dreams. It is the joy of flight and the sharp eye that spots the opportunity in the landscape.", "keywords": ["Vision", "Prosperity", "Freedom", "Eagle", "Abundance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Resolution", "content": "The number 11 represents dissonance, clearing, and the testing of the structure. It has a high, thin vibration that can feel unsettling but is necessary to break up rigidity. 11 is the energy of 'sorting'—separating the grain from the chaff. It pushes the cycle toward its conclusion by shaking loose anything that is not essential. It is powerful, transformative, and often brings a unique, non-linear perspective.", "keywords": ["Dissonance", "Clearing", "Testing", "Resolution", "Change"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Review your finances or business plans and cut the dead weight.", "Ask for a 'higher perspective' on a problem that is stuck.", "Let go of a dream that is no longer true for you.", "Pay attention to birds today; they are messengers.", "Visualize yourself soaring above your life, detached and free."], "title": "Refining the Vision", "content": "11 Tz'ikin is a day of high-altitude clearing. The dissonance of the 11 challenges the vision of the Eagle, stripping away illusions and false hopes to reveal the core truth. In the Kan trecena, this is the day we refine our perspective. Are we seeing clearly? Are we chasing 'shiny objects' or true prosperity? The energy can feel restless or frantic, like a bird in a storm, but it serves to strengthen our wings. It is a day to let go of limited thinking and to allow a higher, more expansive vision to break through. The clutter is cleared so the true abundance can land."}}	{"title": "The Liberated Visionary", "content": "To be born on 11 Tz'ikin is to be a soul who refuses to be caged. You carry a wild, expansive energy that is constantly seeking freedom and higher truth. You have a brilliant, unique mind that sees possibilities where others see walls. You are a natural entrepreneur, inventor, or visionary artist. The 11 energy gives you a non-conformist edge; you do things your own way, often breaking the rules to create something better.\\n\\nYour life path is one of seeking and creating abundance—not just money, but richness of experience. You are generous and optimistic, believing that there is enough for everyone. However, your path is rarely smooth. You learn through trial and error, through the 'shake-ups' of the 11. You are here to challenge the status quo and to bring new visions to humanity.\\n\\nYour challenge is grounding and focus. You can be so high-flying that you lose touch with reality or become scattered. You may also struggle with the intensity of your own nervous system. Your lesson is to learn to land. When you anchor your brilliant visions in practical reality, you become a bringer of true prosperity, showing others how to break free from scarcity and fly."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#8bdbce", "primary": "#0f1b1a", "secondary": "#315753"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.811884	2026-04-25 14:38:01.316628
200	16	5	5	E'	The spiral path straightens out, stretching into the deep unknown of the Veldt. It looks clear, smooth, and inviting. But the moment you step onto it, the air thickens. It is not wind; it is gravity. The atmosphere turns viscous, pressing against your chest with the weight of deep water.\n\nEvery step becomes a supreme act of will. You are not fighting the plants anymore; you are fighting the inertia of the world itself. Your muscles burn, and your breath comes in ragged gasps. You lean forward, pressing your forehead against the invisible resistance, driving your legs like pistons.\n\nYou look back and see that where you have walked, the stone is glowing brighter. The pressure is not trying to stop you; it is trying to deepen your impact. You are leaving glowing craters with every step, stamping your intent permanently into the road.	The air has turned thick today, pressing against your chest with the weight of deep water. Forward motion feels like a supreme act of will, and every step requires a ragged, honest breath. You might feel like the world is trying to stop you, but you’ve misread the resistance. This gravity isn't a barrier; it's a tool for deepening your impact. The universe wants to see how much you mean it. By driving your legs through this viscous atmosphere, you are stamping your intent permanently into the road, leaving glowing craters where a lighter person would have left no mark at all.\n\nThis is the day of the trailblazer, the one who understands that raw willpower is the most powerful magic in the kit. The struggle is actually a form of calibration, ensuring that when you finally arrive, you have the strength to hold the destination. Don't look for a guide or wait for a sign—the friction you feel is the sign. Lean into the pressure, press your forehead against the invisible resistance, and keep moving. Your destiny is being built by your own hands and feet in this very moment. By the time the air clears, the road behind you will be a permanent landmark for anyone lost in the dark. You are carving a legacy into the stone. Don't stop now.	I embrace the resistance of the road, for it deepens the impact of my journey.	Close your eyes and imagine the air around you becoming thick and heavy, like clear honey. Feel the weight of it against your skin. Instead of fighting it, lean into it. Use your breath to create space, feeling the strength of your own muscles and the power of your will as you hold your position in the density.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, visualize yourself walking down a straight road in the Veldt. Every step is difficult and slow. As you lift your foot, see that you have left a glowing, deep crater in the obsidian ground. The resistance is not stopping you; it is ensuring your impact is permanent and undeniable.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Pathfinder of Destiny", "content": "E' is the nawal of the path, the road, and the journey. It represents the destiny that unfolds as we walk, the physical roads we travel, and the spiritual path of life. E' is the explorer, the guide, and the energy of movement toward a destination. Associated with the element of air (and sometimes earth) and the color white, it carries a forward-moving, adventurous energy. It is the archetype of the traveler who gains wisdom through experience. In daily life, E' manifests as travel, starting a new venture, or seeking a better way. Its shadow aspect can be aimlessness, restlessness, or the refusal to commit to a direction. E' teaches us that the destination is less important than the wisdom gathered along the way.", "keywords": ["Journey", "Path", "Exploration", "Guidance", "Destiny"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Power", "content": "Tone 5 is the energy of empowerment, work, and the center. In Mayan numerology, it represents the hand (five fingers) and the ability to grasp, shape, and work with materials. It breaks the stability of the 4 to add a new dimension of agency and action. Tone 5 is the central pivot point of the single-digit numbers (1-9), representing the core or the heart of the matter. Experientially, it feels energetic, capable, and sometimes demanding. It is a day to gather resources and apply effort. While it empowers us to get things done, its shadow can manifest as over-exertion, grasping for control, or losing sight of the spiritual in favor of the material work. It is the number of the worker who makes the vision real.", "keywords": ["Action", "Discipline", "Work", "Empowerment", "Center"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Take a physical trip or a long walk to clear your mind and ground your energy.", "Put extra effort into a project that feels aligned with your long-term purpose.", "Clear obstacles (physical or metaphorical) that are blocking your path.", "Trust your own agency; do not wait for a guide, become one.", "Focus on the 'how' of your journey—the practical steps needed to advance."], "title": "Empowering the Journey", "content": "When the working hand of Tone 5 meets the open road of E', we are gifted with the energy of 'practical exploration.' 5 E' is the day of the Trailblazer—the one who not only sees the path but has the strength and tools to clear it. This is a powerful day for taking decisive steps forward. The conceptual planning is over; now is the time to put boots on the ground. The energy supports hard work directed toward your destiny. If you have felt stuck or unsure of your direction, 5 E' provides the push to just start walking and trust that the work itself will reveal the way. It feels like the steady rhythm of a hike: effortful, grounding, but deeply satisfying. The combination emphasizes that your destiny is not something that happens to you, but something you build with your own hands and feet. The challenge is to not simply wander, but to walk with purpose and discipline."}}	{"title": "The Trailblazer of Practical Magic", "content": "To be born on 5 E' is to be a tireless seeker and a capable guide on the road of life. You possess a restless spirit that is always looking for the next horizon, combined with a remarkable work ethic that ensures you actually get there. You are not a dreamer who sits still; you are a doer who learns by moving. People look to you for direction because you seem to have an internal compass and the stamina to endure the journey. You are likely the one who organizes the trips, paves the way for others, or finds solutions where others see dead ends.\\n\\nYour life path is defined by 'action-oriented discovery.' You are here to explore the world—both physical and spiritual—and to work hard at understanding it. Tone 5 gives you a practical, hands-on approach to your destiny. You don't just want to read about the path; you want to walk it, feel the stones under your feet, and build bridges over the rivers. You may be drawn to careers in travel, logistics, research, or any field that allows for autonomy and exploration. You are a natural collector of experiences, and your wisdom comes from the dust on your boots.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 5 E' soul is the potential for exhaustion or a feeling of never arriving. Your drive to move and work can make it hard for you to rest or appreciate where you are right now. You may also struggle with a fear of being tied down, viewing commitment as a cage rather than a foundation. Your lesson is to realize that the path is not just about forward motion, but also about the depth of your presence in each step. When you learn to bring your full awareness to the 'now,' your journey becomes a sacred pilgrimage rather than a race."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c0e7e1", "primary": "#182524", "secondary": "#548380"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.853051	2026-04-25 14:38:01.321969
2	1	2	2	Ix					{"nawal": {"title": "The Jaguar of Earth Magic", "content": "Ix is the jaguar, the shaman of the night, and the keeper of earth magic. It represents the feminine mysteries, intuition, and the high magic of the shrines and altars. Ix is the energy that walks between worlds, seeing in the dark what others miss in the light. It governs our connection to nature spirits and the tangible, vibrating life force of the planet. This nawal is stealthy, powerful, and deeply creative, often associated with the ability to manifest reality through spiritual will. It asks us to honor the invisible forces that shape our physical existence and to treat the earth itself as a living, breathing partner.", "keywords": ["Magic", "Nature", "Intuition", "Jaguar", "Feminine"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "The number Two introduces the essential tension of polarity: the separation of the one into two, creating the dynamic of relationship. It is the energy of the mirror, reflecting the self back through the other. This vibration governs choices, partnerships, and the delicate balance between opposing forces—light and dark, masculine and feminine, inner and outer. It is not necessarily a day of conflict, but rather one of recognition, where we define ourselves by what we are not. The energy here is reactive and cooperative, asking us to consider the other side of the coin before proceeding.", "keywords": ["Duality", "Partnership", "Reflection", "Choice", "Balance"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Pay attention to signs and synchronicities in your interactions today.", "Seek balance between your logical mind and your intuitive gut feelings.", "Spend time in nature with a partner or friend to ground the connection.", "Notice where you are projecting your own shadow onto others.", "Perform a small ritual of gratitude for the relationships that sustain you."], "title": "Harmonizing the Polarities of Nature", "content": "2 Ix brings the mystical power of the Jaguar into the realm of relationship and duality. This is a day where the magic of connection is heightened, but so is the potential for projection. The combined energy asks you to look at your partnerships—romantic, business, or even your relationship with nature—and see the magic mirrored there. It is a time to balance your intuitive, wild self with your practical, social obligations. The atmosphere is charged with a stealthy potency; things left unsaid may communicate louder than words. You might feel a pull between the desire for solitude and the need for connection, and the lesson is to find the sacred ground where both can coexist."}}	{"title": "The Shaman of Relationships", "content": "To be born on 2 Ix is to walk the path of the mystical diplomat. You possess a natural affinity for the unseen world and a profound sensitivity to the energies between people. The number Two gifts you with a deep desire for connection and partnership, while the Jaguar grants you the intuition to see behind people's masks. You are likely drawn to healing arts, psychology, or spiritual practices that involve balancing energies. Your presence is magnetic and slightly mysterious, often drawing others to reveal their secrets to you.\\n\\nHowever, the duality of the Two can sometimes lead to indecision or a tendency to lose yourself in others. Your challenge is to maintain your own strong, magical center while navigating the complexities of relationships. You are learning to use your powerful intuition not just to understand others, but to create harmony between the spiritual and physical worlds. Your life is a dance of integrating the wild, instinctual wisdom of the Jaguar with the tender, reflective nature of the partner."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c2b174", "primary": "#191b18", "secondary": "#535239"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.729452	2026-04-25 13:46:57.636918
65	5	13	13	Aq'ab'al					{"nawal": {"title": "The Dawn Runner", "content": "Aq'ab'al is the Nawal of the dawn, the dusk, and the transition between light and dark. It represents the moment of awakening and the potential of a new day. Aq'ab'al is the energy of duality, polarity, and the hope that comes after the long night. In human experience, Aq'ab'al manifests as optimism, youthfulness, and the ability to see the solution in the problem. It is the bridge between the dream and the reality. When aligned, Aq'ab'al brings new opportunities, clarity, and a soft, hopeful light; when misaligned, it can lead to confusion, hesitation, or fear of the unknown. It is the first ray of sun that dispels the shadows.", "keywords": ["Dawn", "Duality", "Transition", "Hope", "Awakening"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascension", "content": "The number Thirteen represents the completion of the cycle, the ascension to the next level, and the spirit world. In Mayan cosmology, Thirteen is the number of the ancestors and the highest vibration of time. It is the moment where the wave crashes onto the shore and recedes to become part of the ocean again. Experientially, this energy feels magical, heightened, and sometimes ungrounded. It is a day of 'déjà vu' and profound intuition. The shadow of Thirteen can be a disconnection from reality, but its light is the ultimate transformation and the preparation for a new beginning. Today, the universe opens the gate.", "keywords": ["Completion", "Ascension", "Ancestors", "Transformation", "Spirit"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a closing ceremony for the projects or intentions you started on Day 1.", "Wake up early to watch the actual sunrise; the energy is potent at dawn.", "Look for signs and synchronicities; the spirit world is very close.", "Release any remaining heaviness to the night; step into the light.", "Celebrate the transition; you have completed a spiral of time."], "title": "Transcendent Dawn", "content": "The cycle of the B'atz' trecena concludes with the mystical energy of 13 Aq'ab'al. Here, the ascension power of Tone 13 meets the dawning light of Aq'ab'al. This is a day of 'Spiritual Awakening.' We have woven the thread (B'atz'), walked the path (E'), and done the work (Tz'ikin), and now we stand at the threshold of a completely new level of consciousness. 13 Aq'ab'al is the energy of the breakthrough. It is the moment when the confusion clears not just intellectually, but spiritually. The energy is soft, hopeful, and incredibly high-vibration. It suggests that the 'night' of the past 13 days is over, and a new, higher reality is emerging. It is a perfect day for gratitude, for closing the ceremony of the trecena, and for looking forward with optimism. The weaving is finished, and as we hold it up to the light of dawn, we see the pattern clearly for the first time."}}	{"title": "The Mystic of the Dawn", "content": "To be born on 13 Aq'ab'al is to be a soul who lives on the threshold of the divine. You are the 'Ascended Light'—someone who carries a vibration of hope and spiritual completion. You likely have a foot in both worlds—the practical reality and the mystical unknown—and you serve as a bridge for others. You are the eternal optimist, the one who knows that no matter how dark the night, the sun will always rise. Your presence brings a sense of possibility and renewal to those around you.\\n\\nYour life path is one of spiritual transformation. With the number 13, you have a powerful connection to the ancestors and the spirit world, perhaps manifesting as strong intuition or psychic gifts. Combined with Aq'ab'al, this makes you a guide for transitions—helping people be born, die, or change their lives. Your challenge is to stay grounded, as the high frequency of 13 can make the physical world feel harsh or heavy. You are here to remind us that every ending is just a prelude to a brighter beginning."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#baab8f", "primary": "#101818", "secondary": "#4e4c4b"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.774209	2026-04-25 13:46:57.737254
54	5	2	2	E'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Pathfinder", "content": "E' is the Nawal of the path, the road, and the journey—both the physical roads we travel and the spiritual destiny we walk. It represents the energy of exploration, trade, and the exchange of wisdom that happens when we leave our comfort zones. As the archetype of the Guide and the Traveler, E' governs the nervous system and the connections between things. It is the bridge between cultures and concepts. In human experience, E' brings a restlessness to move, to discover, and to learn through direct experience. It is the patron of entrepreneurs and diplomats. When aligned, E' brings clarity of direction and safe passage; when misaligned, it can manifest as aimless wandering or feeling lost in the wilderness of life. It is the road that rises to meet your feet.", "keywords": ["Journey", "Path", "Exploration", "Guidance", "Discovery"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "The number Two represents the fundamental principle of polarity: light and dark, male and female, self and other. It is the energy of relationship and the tension that exists between two points. In the Mayan cosmology, Two is not a point of separation, but of connection and reflection; it teaches us that we define ourselves through our interaction with the 'other.' Experientially, this energy brings choices into sharp focus and asks for balance. It is a day where partnerships are tested and strengthened, and where the mirror of reality reflects our inner state back to us. The shadow of Two is indecision or conflict, but its light is the profound harmony that arises when opposites dance together. Today asks you to look at the other side of the coin.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Reflection", "Connection", "Balance", "Choice"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Evaluate your current partnerships; are they supporting your life path?", "If faced with a decision between two directions, look for the middle way.", "Take a walk with a friend or partner to discuss the future; movement aids the conversation.", "Be open to a detour; the rigid path may not be the one that brings balance.", "Trust the 'other' to act as a guide today; you don't have to hold the map alone."], "title": "The Crossroads of Choice", "content": "The synthesis of Tone 2's duality with the traveling energy of E' creates a powerful dynamic of 'The Crossroads.' Today is a day of choosing which path to take. The energy highlights the relationships you have with your own life path—are you walking it alone, or are you in right relationship with your companions? This is a day to negotiate the route, to look at the map with a partner, and to decide on a direction that honors both sides of the equation. It feels like standing at a fork in the road where two viable options present themselves. The combined energy asks for diplomacy and compromise; it suggests that the journey is better shared. It is an excellent day for reconciling differences regarding future plans or for finding a middle way between two opposing directions. The path is not a straight line today; it is a dance."}}	{"title": "The Companion of the Way", "content": "To be born on 2 E' is to be the ultimate travel companion and a diplomat of the road. Your soul purpose is found in the intersection of relationship and journeying. You are rarely one to walk alone; you find your greatest wisdom and growth through your interactions with others as you explore the world. You have a natural gift for bridging gaps—between people, between cultures, and between ideas. You are the person who can translate the map for the group and ensure that everyone's needs are met before setting out. \\n\\nYour energy is dynamic yet receptive. You thrive on the exchange of ideas and experiences, and you likely feel a constant pull to explore, whether physically or intellectually. However, the duality of the number 2 can sometimes cause you to hesitate at crossroads, paralyzed by the validity of multiple options. Your challenge is to internalize the truth that the 'right' path is often the one where you can maintain the most authentic connection with yourself and your chosen companions. You are here to teach the world that the destination matters less than who you walk with."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#ccdfe7", "primary": "#0f191a", "secondary": "#39494d"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.768577	2026-04-25 13:46:57.738037
56	5	4	4	Ix					{"nawal": {"title": "The Jaguar of Earth Magic", "content": "Ix is the Nawal of the Jaguar, the night, and the magic of the Earth. It represents the feminine mysteries, intuition, and the high magic of the shrines and altars. Ix is the energy that sees in the dark; it connects us to the subtle forces of nature and the wisdom of the mountains. As the archetype of the Shaman and the Healer, Ix governs our capacity to transform and to manifest through intent. In human experience, Ix brings a heightened sensitivity, a love for solitude, and a deep connection to the natural world. It is the silent paw on the forest floor. When aligned, Ix brings spiritual power and profound insight; when misaligned, it can lead to being overwhelmed by psychic input or using power for selfish gain. It is the velvet darkness that holds the stars.", "keywords": ["Earth Magic", "Intuition", "Jaguar", "Sacred Sites", "Manifestation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cube of Stability", "content": "The number Four represents stability, definition, and the material world. It is the energy of the four cardinal directions, the four elements, and the four walls of a house. In Mayan cosmology, Four is the force that grounds spirit into form; it creates the container in which life can exist. Experientially, this energy feels solid, reliable, and sometimes a bit heavy. It is a day for building, organizing, and establishing boundaries. It asks us to define our position and to stand firm. The shadow of Four can be rigidity or stagnation, but its light is the comfort of a secure foundation. Today, the universe provides a platform for your efforts.", "keywords": ["Structure", "Balance", "Grounding", "Manifestation", "Stability"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create or tend to a physical altar; ground your prayers in the material world.", "Trust your intuition in business or practical matters; the Jaguar sees the unseen.", "Spend time in nature, specifically connecting with rocks, trees, or the soil.", "Establish boundaries around your time and energy; protect your magic.", "Use the stability of the number 4 to calm any anxiety or psychic overwhelm."], "title": "Grounding the Magic", "content": "The meeting of Tone 4's structural stability and Ix's high magic creates a day of 'Materialized Magic.' This is one of the most powerful days for bringing spiritual concepts down into physical reality. 4 Ix asks you to build a structure for your intuition—to create an altar, a ritual, or a tangible practice that houses your spiritual life. The energy is not flighty or abstract; it is deep, heavy, and resonant, like the heartbeat of the Earth itself. It is a day to trust your gut instincts about practical matters. You may find that solutions to physical problems come through sudden intuitive flashes. The Jaguar is resting on a square stone today, surveying its domain with absolute certainty. Use this energy to stabilize your sensitivity; if you have been feeling ungrounded or psychically open, 4 Ix offers the perfect energy to close the circle and find your footing."}}	{"title": "The Architect of the Sacred", "content": "To be born on 4 Ix is to be a builder of bridges between the visible and invisible worlds. You are the 'Grounded Mystic'—someone who possesses deep intuition and spiritual power but knows exactly how to apply it in the real world. You are not a daydreamer lost in the ether; you are a magician who builds solid structures. People often perceive you as mysterious yet deeply reliable. You likely have a natural affinity for nature, healing arts, or psychology, and you approach these subjects with a practical, systematic mind.\\n\\nYour soul's vibration is one of ancient wisdom. You carry the energy of the sacred sites and the stone temples—enduring, silent, and potent. You may find yourself drawn to create physical spaces for healing or community gathering. The challenge of 4 Ix is to avoid becoming too rigid in your spiritual beliefs or too closed off in your solitude. The Jaguar likes to walk alone, and the number 4 builds walls; remember to leave a door open for others to witness the magic you have cultivated."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a4af6f", "primary": "#1d1d19", "secondary": "#57492f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.769299	2026-04-25 13:46:57.739762
95	8	4	4	Kan	You leave the silver fields and the ground becomes solid earth—rich, dark soil floating in the sky. You have reached the Sky Garden.\n\nHere, the wind does not howl; it whispers. It caresses the rows of strange, luminous plants that grow here. They are not rooted in the ground; they float just above the soil, tethered by beams of green light.\n\nIn the center of the garden coils a giant Serpent made of wind and leaves. It is sleeping. Its scales are made of jade and emerald, shifting like the canopy of a forest.\n\nKan is the seed, the vitality, the sexual force. The number 4 is stability and the four directions. Here, the wild energy of the serpent is grounded.\n\nYou sit next to the sleeping serpent. You feel the immense power radiating from it—the power to grow, to change, to create life. In the human world, this power often feels chaotic or overwhelming. But here, it is held in the four directions.\n\nYou place your hands on the dark soil. You ground yourself. You realize that your inspiration (Iq’) needs a body (Kan) to live in. You cannot just be a head floating in the clouds. You must bring the wind down into your belly.\n\nThe serpent opens one eye. It is golden and vertical. It breathes on you. The breath smells of rich loam and crushed basil. It is the scent of life.\n\nYou breathe it in. You feel your own vitality stabilize. You are not just a thinker; you are a grower. You have the power to plant your words and watch them turn into realities.\n\nThe wind here is not just movement; it is nourishment.	Your ideas are great, but they need legs. The energy of 4 Kan asks you to ground your inspiration. If you’ve been living in your head, come back to your body. Feel your feet on the floor. Feel the blood in your veins.\n\nYou have a lot of power available to you today, but it needs a direction. Don’t scatter it. Pick one goal and pour your vitality into it. Grow something real.	I ground my inspiration in my body and use my vitality to create.	Imagine a cord of red light extending from the base of your spine deep into the earth. It wraps around the crystal core of the planet.\n\nNow, imagine a cord of white light extending from the crown of your head into the sky. You are the bridge. Feel the energy of the earth rising up to meet the energy of the sky in your heart. You are stable. You are alive.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Serpent's Fire", "content": "Kan is the Nawal of the Serpent, the vital life force (Kundalini), and wisdom. It represents the energy of evolution, sexuality, and the DNA spiral. Kan is the power that moves up the spine and brings enlightenment or transformation. In human experience, Kan manifests as charisma, physical strength, and a drive for justice and truth. It is the teacher and the student. When aligned, Kan brings vitality, passion, and deep wisdom; when misaligned, it can lead to manipulation, anger, or misuse of power. It is the fire in the blood.", "keywords": ["Vitality", "Power", "Wisdom", "Transformation", "Sexuality"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cube of Stability", "content": "The number Four represents stability, definition, and the material world. It is the energy of the four cardinal directions, the four elements, and the four walls of a house. In Mayan cosmology, Four is the force that grounds spirit into form; it creates the container in which life can exist. Experientially, this energy feels solid, reliable, and sometimes a bit heavy. It is a day for building, organizing, and establishing boundaries. The shadow of Four can be rigidity or stagnation, but its light is the comfort of a secure foundation.", "keywords": ["Structure", "Balance", "Grounding", "Manifestation", "Stability"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in grounding exercises (Yoga, Qigong) to stabilize your energy.", "Focus on your physical health and nutrition.", "Create a 'container' for your passion or creativity.", "Study the laws of nature or ancient wisdom.", "Respect the power of your own sexuality and life force."], "title": "Grounded Power", "content": "When the stable energy of Tone 4 meets the electric power of Kan, we experience a day of 'Contained Lightning.' 4 Kan is the energy of the serpent resting on the earth—potent, grounded, and ready. This is an incredibly powerful day for physical healing and bodywork. The number 4 provides a safe structure for the high-voltage energy of Kan to circulate without burning out the system. It is a day to build up your strength, to ground your wisdom, and to establish healthy boundaries around your vitality. If you have been feeling scattered or weak, 4 Kan offers the stability to recharge. It is also a day of 'material wisdom'—understanding the laws of the physical universe and using them to your advantage. The serpent is not coiling to strike today; it is coiling to build a foundation. Trust your body's intelligence."}}	{"title": "The Master of Vitality", "content": "To be born on 4 Kan is to be a powerhouse of grounded energy. You are the 'Stable Serpent'—a soul who possesses immense strength and charisma, but who keeps it under disciplined control. You are likely physically robust, with a natural talent for athletics, healing, or leadership. People are drawn to you because you radiate a sense of calm power; you don't need to show off because your presence speaks for itself. You are a builder of wisdom, someone who takes ancient truths and applies them to create a stable life.\\n\\nYour life path is one of mastering the physical and spiritual energies. You are here to learn how to hold high-frequency energy in a human body. The number 4 gives you a practical, earthy nature that grounds the fiery Kan. Your challenge is to ensure that you don't become too rigid or suppressed, allowing your fire to burn freely within the hearth you have built. You are here to show us that true power is not explosive, but enduring."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#5a5334", "primary": "#191918", "secondary": "#292a24"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.79547	2026-04-25 13:46:57.826249
33	3	7	7	Kame					{"nawal": {"title": "The Transformer", "content": "Kame is the nawal of death, rebirth, and the ancestors. It represents the dimensional door between worlds and the only certainty in life: change. Kame is the compost that feeds the flower—the ending that allows for the beginning. It governs spiritual initiation and the facing of fears. Kame is a peaceful, quiet energy, but it commands total respect. In its shadow, Kame can be morbid, fearful, or clinging to the past. Its highest expression is the profound peace of surrender—knowing that death is simply a transformation of energy.", "keywords": ["Death", "Rebirth", "Ancestors", "Transformation", "Surrender"]}, "number": {"title": "The Summit of Vision", "content": "Seven is the number of the midpoint, the top of the pyramid, and mystical alignment. It represents the ability to see the past (1-6) and the future (8-13) simultaneously. Seven is a number of reflection, choice, and equilibrium. Unlike the static balance of Two or Four, Seven is a dynamic, spiritual balance. It is a day where energy peaks and shifts. Experientially, a Seven day feels like reaching a lookout point—there is clarity, perspective, and a sense of potential. The shadow of Seven can be indecision born of seeing too many options. It asks us to look at the whole picture.", "keywords": ["Midpoint", "Reflection", "Perspective", "Mysticism", "Choice"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Light a candle for a loved one who has passed and ask for their blessing.", "Reflect on a past version of yourself and thank them for getting you here.", "Visit a place of high elevation or a sacred site if possible.", "Practice 'dying' to the moment—letting go of each breath fully.", "Journal about what 'rebirth' looks like for you in this current chapter."], "title": "The View from the Threshold", "content": "Today, we stand at the top of the pyramid (Seven) and look through the veil of worlds (Kame). This is a day of 'Mystical Transformation' or 'Ancestral Perspective.' It is the midpoint of the Ajpu trecena, a time to pause and evaluate the hero's journey. What needs to die for you to continue your ascent? The Seven gives you the detachment to see your own cycles of death and rebirth clearly, without fear. The veil between the living and the ancestors is incredibly thin today. It is a powerful day for mediumship, visiting graves, or simply asking your lineage for guidance. You may feel a sense of 'spiritual vertigo'—a realization of how vast and cyclical existence truly is. The challenge is to not get lost in the other side; keep your feet on the ground even as your head touches the sky. Use this day to make a conscious choice about what you are carrying forward into the second half of the cycle and what you are leaving here, at the summit, as an offering to the past."}}	{"title": "The Mystic Traveler", "content": "To be born on 7 Kame is to be a bridge between the worlds. You possess a soul that is deeply familiar with the mysteries of life and death. The number Seven gives you a philosophical, reflective nature, while Kame connects you to the ancestral realms and the power of transformation. You are likely an 'old soul' in the truest sense, carrying wisdom that seems to come from beyond your years. You may have a natural talent for divination, healing, or counseling, as you are not afraid of the dark or the unknown.\\n\\nYour life path is a series of deep internal shifts. You are constantly dying and being reborn, refining your spirit with each cycle. You are a guide for others during their times of crisis, able to offer a perspective that is both compassionate and detached. Your challenge is to stay grounded in the land of the living. You can sometimes drift too far into the mystical or the melancholic. Your lesson is to bring the wisdom of the 'other side' into this one, living fully and joyfully as a testament to the preciousness of life."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c4b7c4", "primary": "#171618", "secondary": "#534758"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.748602	2026-04-25 13:46:57.691337
204	16	9	9	Ajmaq	You descend from the mountain to find the seed you planted. It has transformed into a massive, swollen pod, heavy with life and glowing with a soft, internal pulse. But as you inspect it, you find a flaw—a jagged crack running down the side.\n\nPanic rises. You try to seal it, thinking you have failed to protect the harvest. But then you stop. A soft, golden light is leaking from the fissure. The Owl of Ajmaq lands nearby, watching with wide, knowing eyes. You realize the flaw is not a mistake; it is the opening. Perfection would keep the seed trapped forever. You touch the wound gently, forgiving the imperfection, and allow the light to bleed through. The wound is the door.	You have returned to the seed of your intent only to find a jagged crack running down its side. Your first instinct might be panic, a desperate urge to seal the flaw and hide the imperfection. Stop your hands. That crack isn't a failure; it’s the door. Perfection is a prison that keeps the light trapped forever, but the wound—the honest, jagged breakage—is where the internal pulse finally begins to bleed into the world. Today asks for the radical patience of the womb, the slow-moving power that understands the value of the dark before the final shatter.\n\nThe cosmos is leaning in with wide, owl-like eyes, watching how you handle your own vulnerability. Can you forgive the parts of yourself that didn't grow the way you planned? Can you heal the cracks in your own story with compassion rather than judgment? The energy today is heavy and emotional, pulling things from the deep to the surface. It’s a day for the 'feminine' power of gestation, where the most important work happens behind the scenes in the silence. Be incredibly gentle with your own heart. Your flaws are the precise locations where your light is finally starting to escape. Let the light bleed through. Redemption isn't a clean process; it’s a beautiful, messy birth. Trust the opening.	I forgive my imperfections, knowing they are the doors where my light enters.	Bring your awareness to a part of yourself that feels 'broken' or imperfect. Breathe into that space. Instead of trying to fix it, imagine a soft golden light glowing within the crack. See the flaw as a necessary opening, the place where your soul finally has room to breathe and expand.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, visualize yourself as a large seed pod in the dark soil. Feel the pressure of gestation, the slow and heavy pulse of growth. An Owl lands on your shoulder, whispering that your mistakes were the very things that prepared you to bloom. Forgive the process and trust the dark.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Owl of Forgiveness", "content": "Ajmaq is the nawal of the owl, the ancestors, and the sinner/saint. It represents the human condition in all its flaw and glory. Ajmaq is the energy of forgiveness, reconciliation, and the wisdom that comes from making mistakes. Associated with the element of earth and the spirit world, it carries a soft, solemn, and deeply compassionate energy. It is the archetype of the elder who looks back on life with understanding rather than judgment. In daily life, Ajmaq manifests as curiosity, the questioning of authority, and the healing of ancestral lines. Its shadow aspect can be guilt, shame, or the refusal to learn from the past. Ajmaq teaches us that our imperfections are the cracks where the light enters.", "keywords": ["Forgiveness", "Ancestors", "Wisdom", "Redemption", "Curiosity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Patience of Gestation", "content": "Tone 9 is the energy of patience, cycles, and the feminine. It represents the nine months of human gestation and the nine levels of the Mayan underworld (Xibalba). It is a number of deep, slow-moving power. Unlike the flash of the 1 or the action of the 5, Tone 9 is the energy of the seed swelling underground just before it breaks the surface. Experientially, it feels heavy, emotional, and sometimes secretive. It is a day for working behind the scenes, nurturing projects, and trusting the dark. While it fosters deep creativity and empathy, its shadow can be depression, lethargy, or getting stuck in the past. It is the womb that holds the future.", "keywords": ["Patience", "Gestation", "Feminine", "Completion", "Depth"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Practice radical self-forgiveness; release a specific guilt.", "Connect with your female ancestors through photos or meditation.", "Allow yourself to move slowly; do not rush the process today.", "Engage in a quiet activity like journaling or gentle yoga.", "Show compassion to someone who has made a mistake."], "title": "The Womb of Redemption", "content": "When the gestation energy of Tone 9 holds the forgiving nature of Ajmaq, we enter a profound space of healing and compassion. 9 Ajmaq is the 'Feminine Healer.' It is a day that asks us to be incredibly gentle with ourselves and others. The energy is slow, deep, and reflective, perfect for processing old wounds or finally letting go of long-held guilt. It feels like a long exhale or a warm embrace from a grandmother. Today, the focus is not on perfection, but on the beauty of the struggle. It is a powerful time to connect with female ancestors or to heal wounds related to the mother line. The combination supports the quiet, private work of self-acceptance. The challenge may be an upwelling of emotion or grief, as the 9 brings things from the deep to the surface. The opportunity is to nurture these feelings until they transform into wisdom, realizing that every mistake was a necessary step in your gestation."}}	{"title": "The Compassionate Keeper of Wisdom", "content": "To be born on 9 Ajmaq is to be an old soul, carrying the wisdom of many lifetimes and a deep well of compassion for the human experience. You possess a patient, nurturing presence that draws others to you for comfort and forgiveness. Tone 9 connects you deeply to the feminine mysteries, gestation, and the long cycles of time, while Ajmaq gives you the curiosity of the Owl and the ability to see in the dark. You are likely the person who holds the family secrets or the one who bridges the generational gaps, understanding both the ancestors and the youth.\\n\\nYour life path is one of healing through understanding. You are here to learn—and teach—that mistakes are not failures, but essential lessons in the school of life. You have a profound capacity for forgiveness, often seeing the wounded child inside the 'sinner.' This makes you an incredible therapist, historian, or healer. You are comfortable with the messy, complex, and grey areas of life, where rigid judgment fails. Your creativity is deep and often requires long periods of incubation before it is ready to be shared with the world.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 9 Ajmaq soul is often the weight of the past. You may struggle with your own guilt or carry the unresolved trauma of your lineage. Because you feel so deeply, you can be prone to melancholy or a sense of burden. You may also hide your true self, fearing judgment, even as you offer non-judgment to others. Your growth comes from applying your immense capacity for forgiveness to yourself. When you lighten your own load, your ability to guide others through the dark becomes a beacon of pure, redemptive love."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d2b3ce", "primary": "#191a20", "secondary": "#6e4f6f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.854746	2026-04-25 14:38:01.324488
60	5	8	8	Tijax					{"nawal": {"title": "The Obsidian Knife", "content": "Tijax is the Nawal of the obsidian blade, the double-edged sword of truth. It represents the energy of the warrior and the healer—the one who cuts to cure. Tijax governs discernment, drastic changes, and the removal of negative energies or illnesses. In human experience, Tijax manifests as sharp wit, the courage to speak the truth, and a talent for cutting through illusion. It is the lightning strike that clears the air. When aligned, Tijax brings liberation, healing, and divine protection; when misaligned, it can lead to gossip, harshness, or unnecessary conflict. It is the surgeon's scalpel, dangerous in clumsy hands but lifesaving in the hands of a master.", "keywords": ["Truth", "Healing", "Discernment", "Cutting", "Purification"]}, "number": {"title": "The Harmony of Justice", "content": "The number Eight represents the octave, the return to power, and the weaving of the spiritual into the material. In Mayan cosmology, Eight is the number of the 'Primordial Male' energy, mirroring the 'Primordial Female' of Nine. It is often associated with ceremonies and the harmonization of energy. Experientially, this energy feels like a solid, resonant chord—it is balanced, organized, and powerful. It is a day to take the insights of Seven and begin to apply them with authority. The shadow of Eight can be rigidity or an overpowering nature, but its light is the strength of integrity and justice. Today, the universe aligns the scales.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Balance", "Ceremony", "Reciprocity", "Fairness"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Identify one habit or thought pattern that drains you and choose to cut it today.", "Speak your truth clearly and directly, but without malice.", "Engage in a cleansing ritual (smudging, shower) to remove stagnant energy.", "Address a conflict directly; 8 Tijax supports fair resolution through honesty.", "Trust your discernment; if something feels 'off,' it probably is."], "title": "Healing Justice", "content": "The synthesis of Tone 8's harmonic balance and Tijax's cutting truth creates a day of 'Surgical Healing.' This is a powerful day for cutting away what is out of balance in your life to restore harmony. 8 Tijax is the energy of the benevolent warrior who fights for what is right. It is an excellent time to end a toxic habit, leave a draining situation, or speak a difficult truth that needs to be heard. The energy is sharp but stable; it does not cut recklessly. It asks you to perform a 'spiritual surgery' on your reality—to identify the infection and remove it so that health can return. While the energy can feel intense, the presence of the number 8 ensures that the outcome is one of greater balance and justice. Do not be afraid to say 'no' today; your boundaries are your medicine. Let the obsidian blade sever the cords that bind you to the past."}}	{"title": "The Just Warrior", "content": "To be born on 8 Tijax is to be a guardian of truth and a healer of imbalances. You are the 'Harmonic Sword'—someone who possesses a sharp mind and a fearless heart, dedicated to setting things right. You have an innate sense of justice and fairness, and you cannot stand to see deception or suffering. You are likely the person who speaks up when others are silent, the one who points out the elephant in the room. Your words are powerful tools; they can cut deeply, so learning to wield them with compassion is your life's work.\\n\\nYour path is one of purification—for yourself and for the world. You may be drawn to medicine, law, or any field where you can diagnose a problem and implement a cure. The number 8 gives you a ceremonial, dignified presence; you don't just hack away at problems, you solve them with ritual precision. Your challenge is to manage your own intensity and to remember that not everything needs to be cut; sometimes healing requires a softer touch. You are here to liberate us from our illusions."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#cd9883", "primary": "#0f1211", "secondary": "#463731"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.770657	2026-04-25 13:46:57.744932
98	8	7	7	Q'anil	The forest opens up into a vast, sunlit space where clouds act as soil. Growing out of the clouds are trees made of glass and gold, heavy with fruit that glows like lamps. This is the Floating Orchard.\n\nYou walk among the trees. The air smells of honey and ozone. You feel a sense of immense ripening.\n\nYou are at the midpoint of the trecena. The number 7 is the top of the pyramid. Q’anil is the Seed, the Star, the Rabbit. It is the energy of fertility and joy.\n\nYou realize that the words you spoke on Day 1, the choices you made on Day 2, the clearing you did on Day 3—they are all ripening here. Your breath has become fruit.\n\nYou approach a tree. Hanging from a branch is a golden sphere. You look closely. Inside the semi-transparent skin of the fruit, you see a scene moving. It is a vision of a project you want to start, or a relationship you want to heal.\n\nIt is almost ready. It just needs a little more time, a little more light.\n\nYou do not pluck it. You place your hands around it and send it warmth. You understand that creation cannot be rushed. You have done the work; now you must trust the gestation.\n\nThe wind blows gently through the orchard, chiming against the glass leaves. It sings a song of patience.\n\nYou sit under the tree and rest. You look out over the cloudscape, seeing how far you have come. You feel pregnant with possibility. The harvest is coming, and it will be sweet.	Something beautiful is growing in your life, even if you can’t see the sprouts yet. The energy of 7 Q’anil is fertile and joyous. It asks you to trust the process.\n\nYou have planted the seeds. You have watered the soil. Now, stand back and let the sun do its work. Stop worrying about the outcome and enjoy the garden. You are right on track.	I trust the seeds I have planted and wait with joy for the harvest.	Visualize a seed of light in your solar plexus (stomach area). Imagine it glowing brighter and brighter. It sends roots down into your legs and branches up into your chest.\n\nFeel the warmth of this inner sun. You are fertile ground. Everything you need is already inside you.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Seed of Life", "content": "Q'anil is the Nawal of the seed, the rabbit, and Venus. It represents the generative power of life, fertility, and the potential for abundance. Q'anil is the energy of planting, ripening, and harvesting. It governs the cycles of growth and the beauty of creation. In human experience, Q'anil manifests as artistic talent, a love for pleasure, and a connection to the biological rhythms of life. It is the spark of life in the soil. When aligned, Q'anil brings successful projects and joy; when misaligned, it can lead to impatience or vanity.", "keywords": ["Seed", "Fertility", "Abundance", "Growth", "Ripening"]}, "number": {"title": "The Summit of Reflection", "content": "The number Seven represents the midpoint of the trecena, the top of the pyramid, and the power of mystic vision. In Mayan cosmology, Seven is a number of great potential but also of suspension; it is the moment where we can look back at the climb and forward to the descent. Experientially, this energy feels like a pause in the action—a time to assess, reflect, and gain perspective. It is neither a beginning nor an end, but a bridge. The shadow of Seven can be indecision, but its light is the clarity that comes from seeing the whole picture.", "keywords": ["Reflection", "Midpoint", "Vision", "Insight", "Clarity"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Visualize the successful completion of your goals.", "Reflect on which projects are thriving and which are struggling.", "Spend time in a garden or with plants; observe their slow growth.", "Celebrate the 'seeds' of talent within yourself.", "Be patient; you are at the midpoint of the cycle, not the end."], "title": "Reflective Germination", "content": "The reflective power of Tone 7 meets the fertile energy of Q'anil to create a day of 'Visionary Growth.' 7 Q'anil is the moment the farmer stands in the middle of the field and surveys the crops. It is a day to check on the seeds you have planted in your life—are they growing? Do they need water? Or do they need to be pulled? The energy is paused but potent, like a seed just before it bursts open. It is a wonderful day to visualize your future harvest. Use the mystic vision of the 7 to see the end result of your projects clearly. This clarifies your intention and feeds the energy of the seed. It is also a day to appreciate the beauty of the process. Don't rush the growth; just observe it with gratitude. The rabbit is still today, listening to the earth. Follow its lead."}}	{"title": "The Visionary Planter", "content": "To be born on 7 Q'anil is to be a soul who sees the potential in everything. You are the 'Mystic Gardener'—someone who knows intuitively what seeds will grow and what they need to thrive. Situated at the top of the pyramid (7), you have a broad view of life's cycles, allowing you to plan for the future with uncanny accuracy. You are likely artistic, creative, and appreciative of beauty in all its forms. You carry a seed of genius within you that is destined to ripen.\\n\\nYour life path is one of cultivating abundance through vision. You are here to plant ideas, projects, or communities and watch them grow. The number 7 gives you a spiritual depth that prevents you from being purely materialistic. Your challenge is to trust the timing of the harvest and not to dig up the seeds out of anxiety. You are here to remind us that if we align with the vision of nature, abundance is inevitable."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#ece2af", "primary": "#1e221f", "secondary": "#a28757"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#b9c090", "primary": "#2f4753", "secondary": "#65887d"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#f8de9a", "primary": "#ca9048", "secondary": "#efbe6e"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#f4cfaa", "primary": "#b78476", "secondary": "#dfa48b"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.797528	2026-04-25 13:46:57.833308
91	7	13	13	Aj	The forest feels different today.\n\nNot brighter, not darker—just more itself. Every sound is clear, every scent distinct, every leaf holding its place with the quiet confidence of something that knows it belongs. As you walk, the path beneath your feet seems to steady you, as if matching your stride with its own.\n\nWhen you reach the lake, it is the calmest you have ever seen it.\n\nNo ripples,\nno mist,\nno shifting reflections—\nonly a surface so still it looks carved from polished stone. The sky rests on it comfortably, unbroken.\n\nAnd then you notice something else.\n\nAcross the ground near the water’s edge, tall shapes rise slowly from the earth—columns made of light and shadow, woven with faint threads of gold. They are not physical, but they feel solid in a way your body understands. Thirteen of them stand in a soft arc around the lake, each one humming with a tone too low to hear but easy to feel.\n\nYou step closer.\n\nAs you approach the first pillar, your chest lifts, and a quiet awareness fills you: this pillar carries the beginning, the first spark.\n\nThe next holds breath.\nThe next dawn.\nThe next the net.\nThe serpent.\nThe ancestors.\nThe guardian.\nThe seeds.\nThe offering.\nThe truth.\nThe thread.\nThe path.\n\nAnd the final pillar—the thirteenth—waits for you.\n\nIt is taller than the rest, luminous and warm, steady as an ancient tree. You feel its presence like a heartbeat outside your body. When you place your hand near it, the air thickens, not with intensity but with recognition.\n\nThis pillar is you.\nOr rather, it is the shape you have been growing toward: the version of yourself built not from fear or longing, but from the courage you’ve shown in the smallest moments.\n\nMemories rise, not as scenes but as sensations: the honesty of day two, the trembling of day three, the releasing of day four, the spark of day five, the relief of day six, the vision of day seven, the gratitude of day eight, the strength of day nine, the integrity of day ten, the creativity of day eleven, the perspective of day twelve.\n\nNone of these stand apart now.\nThey form a structure—an inner home.\n\nYou step into the center of the circle.\n\nThe pillars brighten, one by one, until the air around you glows like a sanctum built from every lesson you have lived. The lake reflects the pillars perfectly, doubling the image—above and below—like the spine of a world held in balance.\n\nYour breath settles. Your shoulders drop. Something inside you clicks into place, quiet and sure.\n\nYou feel…upright.\nAligned.\nTrue.\n\nThe pillars slowly dissolve back into the air, leaving no trace but a subtle warmth in the earth beneath your feet.\n\nThe lake remains still.\nBut you feel changed—not transformed into something new, but restored to something real.\n\nWhen you walk away from the shore for the final time in this cycle, the forest does not feel like a place you visited.\n\nIt feels like a place within you that you can now return to at will.\n\nAnd the lake, calm and silent behind you, remains—\nnot an ending, but a foundation.	Today brings completion—not as an ending, but as alignment. You may feel more centered, more grounded, or simply more aware of what truly matters.\n\nThis is a day to trust your inner structure. To act with dignity. To let truth shape your choices. You are standing on solid ground now.\n\nHonor your growth. You earned this steadiness.	I stand in my truth with clarity, dignity, and harmony. I honor the foundation I have built within myself.	Sit comfortably and imagine thirteen pillars of light forming a gentle circle around you. Each one represents a lesson, a moment of growth, or a truth you’ve reclaimed.\n\nLet them glow brighter, one by one, until you feel surrounded by a soft, steady sanctuary.\n\nPlace your hand on your heart and silently repeat:\n“I am held. I am centered. I am aligned.”\n\nOffer gratitude to the keepers of home, harmony, and sacred structure. Then let the pillars dissolve in your mind, leaving their steadiness in your body as you return to your day.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Pillar of Light", "content": "Aj is the Nawal of the home, the cane, and the spinal column. It represents the principle of authority, leadership, and the upright growth of the cornstalk. Aj is the energy that holds up the roof—strong yet flexible. It governs the home, the family, and the community, emphasizing harmony and ethics. In human experience, Aj manifests as the desire to build a safe container for life. It is the staff of power. When aligned, Aj brings peace and stability; when misaligned, it can lead to rigidity.", "keywords": ["Home", "Authority", "Pillar", "Integrity", "Spine"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascension", "content": "The number Thirteen represents the completion of the cycle, the ascension to the next level, and the spirit world. In Mayan cosmology, Thirteen is the number of the ancestors and the highest vibration of time. It is the moment where the wave crashes onto the shore and recedes to become part of the ocean again. Experientially, this energy feels magical, heightened, and sometimes ungrounded. It is a day of profound intuition. The shadow of Thirteen can be a disconnection from reality, but its light is the ultimate transformation.", "keywords": ["Completion", "Ascension", "Ancestors", "Transformation", "Spirit"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a house blessing or energetic clearing of your space.", "Connect with the 'spiritual pillar' within you (your spine/chakras).", "Honor the leaders and elders in your community.", "Celebrate the completion of the 13-day cycle with a family meal.", "Stand tall; feel your dignity and your connection to the divine."], "title": "Ascended Harmony", "content": "The Imox trecena concludes with the spiritual height of 13 Aj. Here, the ascension energy of Tone 13 meets the stabilizing pillar of Aj. This is a day of 'Spiritual Authority.' We have navigated the chaotic waters of Imox, and now we land on solid, holy ground. 13 Aj represents the ultimate home—the home within the spirit. It is a day to stand tall in your integrity, connected to both Heaven (13) and Earth (Aj). The energy is regal, peaceful, and complete. It suggests that true authority comes from spiritual alignment, not force. It is a perfect day to bless your home, to honor the 'elders' and ancestors, and to recognize the divine structure that supports your life. The dream of Imox has found its house. You have built a sanctuary in the storm. Stand in the doorway and welcome the light."}}	{"title": "The Spiritual Anchor", "content": "To be born on 13 Aj is to be a tower of spiritual strength. You are the 'Ascended Pillar'—a soul who brings the high frequency of the spirit world down into the very structure of earthly life. You have a commanding presence, yet you are gentle and flexible like the cornstalk. You are likely a natural leader, a spiritual teacher, or the rock of your family, someone who others lean on for support and wisdom. You embody the authority of the ancestors.\\n\\nYour life path is one of bringing heaven to home. You are here to build structures (families, organizations, communities) that are aligned with divine law. The number 13 gives you a psychic edge and a connection to the mysteries, while Aj keeps you rooted in tradition and ethics. Your challenge is to stay grounded enough to be accessible to others, as your energy can sometimes feel 'otherworldly.' You are the staff that connects the earth to the sky."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#aab88e", "primary": "#111917", "secondary": "#4c4d3d"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.792038	2026-04-25 13:46:57.771898
179	14	10	10	Ajmaq					{"nawal": {"title": "The Owl of Forgiveness", "content": "Ajmaq is the energy of the owl, the ancestors, and the pardon. It represents the human experience—the sweetness of life, the mistakes, and the need for forgiveness. Ajmaq is the wisdom to accept imperfection and the curiosity to peer into the dark. It is the day of reconciliation.", "keywords": ["Forgiveness", "Ancestors", "Wisdom", "Pardon", "Curiosity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Wheel of Manifestation", "content": "The number 10 represents manifestation, responsibility, and the hands coming together. It signifies the agreement of community and the crystallization of intention into form. 10 brings a sense of weight and solidity. In the Kej trecena, 10 is the day we take responsibility for our humanity.", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Community", "Agreement", "Results"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Apologize to someone you have hurt.", "Forgive a debt or a grudge publicly.", "Host a gathering to celebrate friendship and imperfection.", "Take responsibility for a past error without shame.", "Honor the ancestors for the life they gave you."], "title": "Manifesting Forgiveness", "content": "10 Ajmaq is a day of tangible healing and community forgiveness. The manifesting power of the 10 brings the pardon of Ajmaq down to earth. In the Kej trecena, this is where we balance our accounts with our fellow humans. It is a day to take responsibility for our mistakes and to offer forgiveness to others. The energy is sweet, heavy, and human. We realize that part of being in balance (Kej) is accepting our imperfections. It is a day to hug, to make amends, and to build a community based on mutual understanding."}}	{"title": "The Community Healer", "content": "To be born on 10 Ajmaq is to be a pillar of compassion for your community. You possess a deep understanding of the human condition and a heart big enough to hold everyone's flaws. You are the peacemaker, the confessor, and the one who reminds us that we are all in this together. You have a natural authority, but it is soft and approachable. You build community through vulnerability and forgiveness.\\n\\nYour life path is one of reconciliation. You are here to heal the rifts between people and to manifest a more compassionate world. You have a talent for seeing the wisdom in mistakes. You are a bridge between the generations, honoring the ancestors while supporting the youth.\\n\\nYour challenge is carrying the collective burden. You can feel responsible for everyone's pain. You may also struggle to forgive yourself even as you forgive others. Your lesson is that you are human too. When you embrace your own imperfections with the same love you give to others, you become a true saint of the everyday, teaching the world the power of grace."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#cdaeca", "primary": "#16161d", "secondary": "#614b63"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.84341	2026-04-25 13:46:57.944337
216	17	8	8	Kan					{"nawal": {"title": "The Serpent of Vitality", "content": "Kan is the nawal of the serpent, the life force, and the kundalini. It represents life energy, movement, sexuality, and wisdom. Symbol of growth through transformation and mastery of instinct. Associated with the element of fire and the colors green and red, it carries a potent, instinctual, and evolving energy. It is the archetype of the lightning bolt that connects sky and earth. In daily life, Kan manifests as physical strength, sexual attraction, athletic ability, and the drive to evolve. Its shadow aspect can be manipulation, misuse of power, anger, or being consumed by desire. Kan teaches us that our body is the vessel for the divine fire.", "keywords": ["Vitality", "Power", "Sexuality", "Growth", "Transformation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Harmonious Weaver", "content": "Tone 8 is the energy of resonance, justice, and the octave. Following the peak of the 7, the 8 represents the return to the material world but with a higher frequency. It is the number of the 'infinite loop' (infinity symbol), representing the continuous flow of spirit into matter and back again. Experientially, Tone 8 feels harmonious, balanced, and ceremonial. It is often associated with the male energy or the father, bringing structure that honors the spirit. It is a day of resonance, where actions echo loudly. While it fosters integrity and wholeness, its shadow can be rigidity or a dogmatic adherence to form over feeling. It is the weaver who tightens the threads to create a strong cloth.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Justice", "Resonance", "Infinity", "Ceremony"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in yoga, tai chi, or exercise to move stagnant energy.", "Practice gratitude for your physical health and body.", "Channel your passion into a creative or spiritual discipline.", "Ground yourself if you feel 'wired' or overly energetic.", "Meditate on the spine and the flow of light within it."], "title": "Harmonizing the Life Force", "content": "When the resonant structure of Tone 8 meets the raw power of Kan, we get a day of 'Sacred Vitality.' 8 Kan is the energy of Kundalini rising in a safe, ceremonial container. It is a day to honor the body and the electricity that runs through it. The energy is high, potent, but balanced. It feels like the hum of a well-tuned engine or the flow of a powerful river. Today, the wild instincts of the Serpent are guided by the justice of the 8, making it an excellent time for physical healing, tantric practices, or martial arts—anything that channels power with discipline. This combination supports the harmonization of our sexual and spiritual energies. The challenge is to not suppress the fire, nor to let it burn out of control, but to circulate it. The opportunity is to feel the infinite loop of energy that sustains your life and to offer gratitude for your vitality."}}	{"title": "The Master of Vital Energy", "content": "To be born on 8 Kan is to be a powerhouse of vital energy and a natural healer. You possess a physical and spiritual strength that is palpable to others. You are the 'Serpent of Light,' carrying the wisdom of the body and the fire of transformation. Tone 8 gives you a sense of balance, justice, and authority, allowing you to handle the intense energy of Kan without burning out. You are likely drawn to physical disciplines—athletics, yoga, dance—or the healing arts, where you can use your hands to transmit energy. People are attracted to your magnetism; you have a charisma that is both grounded and electric.\\n\\nYour life path is one of mastering the life force. You are here to learn how to channel power responsibly. You understand instinctively that the body is a temple and that sexuality and spirituality are linked. You may serve as a teacher or a guide, helping others to wake up their own dormant potential. You have a strong sense of ethics (8) that guides your use of power (Kan), making you a protector of the innocent and a champion of justice.\\n\\nThe challenge for an 8 Kan soul is the intensity of your own drives. You may struggle with anger, desire, or a need for control. If you do not have a physical outlet for your energy, it can turn into anxiety or aggression. You may also be prone to rigid thinking, believing that your way is the only way. Your growth comes from fluidity—learning to flow like the serpent rather than striking. When you surrender your power to a higher purpose, you become a conduit for the infinite energy of the cosmos, healing yourself and the world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b8b676", "primary": "#1a1e15", "secondary": "#524a30"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.860254	2026-04-25 13:46:58.01351
59	5	7	7	No'j					{"nawal": {"title": "The Earth's Intellect", "content": "No'j is the Nawal of the mind, knowledge, and the sacred science. It represents the intellect of the Earth—the patterns, the logic, and the wisdom that structures reality. No'j is the energy of the scholar, the planner, and the problem-solver. It transforms raw information into usable wisdom. In human experience, No'j manifests as clarity of thought, good ideas, and the urge to learn. It is the 'Aha!' moment. When aligned, No'j brings brilliant solutions, noble thoughts, and a connection to the cosmic mind; when misaligned, it can lead to overthinking, arrogance, or being trapped in one's own head. It is the thought that precedes the action.", "keywords": ["Wisdom", "Intellect", "Knowledge", "Planning", "Solutions"]}, "number": {"title": "The Summit of Reflection", "content": "The number Seven represents the midpoint of the trecena, the top of the pyramid, and the power of mystic vision. In Mayan cosmology, Seven is a number of great potential but also of suspension; it is the moment where we can look back at the climb (1-6) and forward to the descent (8-13). Experientially, this energy feels like a pause in the action—a time to assess, reflect, and gain perspective. It is neither a beginning nor an end, but a bridge. The shadow of Seven can be indecision or feeling stuck 'in between,' but its light is the clarity that comes from seeing the whole picture. Today, the universe hands you a telescope.", "keywords": ["Reflection", "Midpoint", "Vision", "Insight", "Clarity"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Dedicate time to study, reading, or learning something complex.", "Journal your thoughts; the connection between mind and page is strong.", "Review your progress over the last 6 days and adjust your course.", "Meditate on a specific question; the answer is likely to arrive.", "Avoid making impulsive moves; today is for strategy, tomorrow is for action."], "title": "The Clarity of the Center", "content": "When the reflective height of Tone 7 meets the intellectual brilliance of No'j, we arrive at a day of 'Supreme Insight.' 7 No'j is considered one of the most powerful days for seeking wisdom and answers. The energy allows you to see all sides of a problem with detached clarity. It is like standing on a mountain peak (7) with a detailed map in your hand (No'j). This is the ideal day for strategic planning, deep study, or making decisions that require a long-term view. The confusion of previous days lifts, replaced by a cool, crystalline understanding of what needs to be done. However, because 7 is a midpoint, the energy is more about 'seeing' than 'doing.' It is a day to formulate the plan, not necessarily to execute it. Trust your mental faculties today; your mind is tuned to a higher frequency. If you have been wrestling with a dilemma, 7 No'j often delivers the solution in a sudden flash of knowing."}}	{"title": "The Sage of Balance", "content": "To be born on 7 No'j is to carry the mind of a visionary strategist. You are the 'Central Intelligence'—a person who stands in the middle of chaos and sees the order within it. You possess a brilliant, probing intellect that is naturally balanced; you rarely take sides without understanding the whole picture. People seek you out for advice because you can see the past and the future simultaneously, offering solutions that are both practical and wise. You are a lifelong learner, likely accumulating books and knowledge like treasures.\\n\\nYour life path is one of synthesizing information into wisdom. You are the bridge builder between opposing viewpoints, using your logic to find common ground. With the number 7, you may sometimes feel a sense of detachment, observing life from a distance rather than diving into the fray. Your challenge is to bring your brilliant ideas down from the mountain top and share them with the world. You are here to solve the puzzles that stump everyone else, reminding us that every problem has a solution if you look from the right perspective."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a3c3c8", "primary": "#121d1e", "secondary": "#3f555d"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.770326	2026-04-25 13:46:57.743793
61	5	9	9	Kawoq					{"nawal": {"title": "The Storm Midwife", "content": "Kawoq is the Nawal of the storm, the turtle, and the midwife. It represents the family unit, community, and the chaotic but necessary energy that brings new life. Kawoq is the rain that nourishes the crops and the thunder that wakes us up. In human experience, Kawoq manifests as compassion, the drive to care for others, and the ability to weather emotional storms. It is the energy of the 'group' rather than the individual. When aligned, Kawoq brings abundance, renewal, and deep emotional cleansing; when misaligned, it can lead to codependency, overwhelming drama, or getting lost in the collective emotions. It is the water breaking before the birth.", "keywords": ["Community", "Storm", "Compassion", "Rebirth", "Cleansing"]}, "number": {"title": "The Womb of Patience", "content": "The number Nine represents the completion of the developmental cycle, the gestation period (9 months), and the energy of the feminine. In Mayan cosmology, Nine is associated with the 'Primordial Female' and the deep, dark soil where the seed transforms. Experientially, this energy feels introspective, creative, and sometimes slow. It is the patience of the mother waiting for the birth. It is a time for nurturing, refining details, and preparing for the final manifestation. The shadow of Nine can be isolation or emotional heaviness, but its light is the profound power of life generating life. Today, the universe holds you in its embrace.", "keywords": ["Patience", "Gestation", "Feminine", "Completion", "Nurturing"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Focus on self-care and nurturing your physical body.", "Spend time with family or your chosen community; strengthen the bonds.", "Allow your emotions to flow without judgment; crying can be cleansing.", "Work on creative projects that are near completion but need final polish.", "Trust the timing of your life; do not force a flower to open."], "title": "Gestating the New World", "content": "When the nurturing patience of Tone 9 meets the stormy, birthing energy of Kawoq, we experience a day of 'Feminine Power.' 9 Kawoq is the archetype of the Great Mother who is ready to birth a new reality. The energy is thick, emotional, and profoundly creative. It is not a day for rushing; it is a day for preparing the nest. The storm may be gathering outside, but inside the shell of the turtle (Kawoq), there is safety and growth. This combination favors all activities related to family, home, and community care. It is a powerful time to heal maternal wounds or to work on projects that benefit the collective. You may feel a heightened emotional sensitivity today—let it flow like rain. The 9 asks you to wait for the right moment, while Kawoq promises that the renewal is coming. You are in the delivery room of the spirit; breathe and trust the process."}}	{"title": "The Nurturing Storm", "content": "To be born on 9 Kawoq is to be a powerhouse of compassionate creativity. You are the 'Cosmic Midwife'—a soul dedicated to helping others birth their dreams, their truths, and their best selves. You possess a deep, reservoir of emotional strength and feminine wisdom (regardless of gender). You are likely the person who holds the family together, the one who creates a sense of home wherever you go. Your energy is warm, enveloping, and sometimes intense, like a tropical rainstorm that brings life to the jungle.\\n\\nYour life path is centered on community and the collective good. You feel the emotions of those around you acutely and are driven to alleviate suffering. With the gestation energy of the number 9, you are a master of patience and long-term development; you understand that good things take time. Your challenge is to establish boundaries so that you do not drown in the emotional tides of others. You are here to teach us that vulnerability is a strength and that we are all part of the same family."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#82d8c9", "primary": "#11201f", "secondary": "#377269"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.77098	2026-04-25 13:46:57.745642
99	8	8	8	Toj	You leave the orchard and the path turns to white marble steps leading down into a canyon of mist. At the bottom lies the Altar of Mist.\n\nIt is a simple stone slab, smooth and ancient. Surrounding it are bowls of water, incense burners releasing copal smoke, and piles of feathers.\n\nToj is Offering. The number 8 is Wholeness and Harmony. Today is the day of payment.\n\nYou approach the altar. You realize that you have received so much on this journey—inspiration, clarity, stability, power, flow, vision. The universe has poured energy into you. Now, you must pour some back to keep the balance.\n\nBut what do you have to give? You have no money, no goods.\n\nYou have your breath.\n\nYou stand before the altar. You think of everything you are grateful for. You gather that gratitude in your heart until it feels like it might burst.\n\nYou lean forward and breathe that gratitude onto the stone. You pour your love into the altar. You promise to use the gifts you’ve been given to help others.\n\nThe mist swirls around you, forming shapes of hands receiving your gift. The stone glows warmly. You feel lighter. The transaction is complete.\n\nYou realize that payment isn’t a loss; it’s a connection. By giving back, you prove you are part of the loop. You are not a consumer; you are a participant.	Gratitude is the currency of the universe today. If you want more flow in your life, you have to give something back. The energy of 8 Toj asks for a small offering.\n\nIt doesn’t have to be big. Pay for the coffee of the person behind you. Send a thank-you text. Leave a flower on a rock. Show the universe you are paying attention, and the universe will show you its generosity.	I give with a glad heart, knowing that generosity restores the balance of my life.	Imagine you are breathing in light and breathing out love. \n\nInhale: I receive the gift of life.\nExhale: I offer my love to the world.\n\nFeel the loop. You are a conduit. Keep the energy moving.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Fire", "content": "Toj is the Nawal of the offering, the sacred fire, and the payment of debts. It represents the law of cause and effect (karma) and the need for reciprocity. Toj is the energy of giving back to the universe to maintain balance. It governs physical and spiritual health, reminding us that illness is often a sign of imbalance. In human experience, Toj manifests as a desire to serve, a sense of duty, and the warmth of the hearth. When aligned, Toj brings purification and release from debt; when misaligned, it can lead to feeling victimized.", "keywords": ["Offering", "Payment", "Fire", "Balance", "Reciprocity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Harmony of Justice", "content": "The number Eight represents the octave, the return to power, and the weaving of the spiritual into the material. In Mayan cosmology, Eight is the number of the 'Primordial Male' energy, mirroring the 'Primordial Female' of Nine. It is often associated with ceremonies and the harmonization of energy. Experientially, this energy feels like a solid, resonant chord—it is balanced, organized, and powerful. It is a day to take the insights of Seven and begin to apply them with authority. The shadow of Eight can be rigidity, but its light is the strength of integrity.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Balance", "Ceremony", "Reciprocity", "Fairness"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a fire ceremony or light a candle to pay karmic debts.", "Donate money or time to a cause; restore the flow.", "Address any imbalances in your relationships (give/take).", "Express gratitude for your health and vitality.", "Step into a role of service or leadership in your community."], "title": "Ceremonial Balance", "content": "When the harmonic power of Tone 8 meets the offering energy of Toj, we arrive at a day of 'Sacred Reciprocity.' 8 Toj is the quintessential day for ceremony and payment. The energy is perfectly aligned for settling debts—karmic, financial, or emotional. It is a day to bring the scales back to center. If you have been taking more than you give, offer something back today. If you have been giving too much, allow yourself to receive. The fire of Toj is bright and stable under the influence of the 8. It burns away the old patterns and purifies the spirit. This is a day of service, but service performed with dignity and strength, not servitude. Light a candle, make a donation, or simply say 'thank you' to the universe. The echo of your offering will return to you as a blessing. Balance is the key."}}	{"title": "The Keeper of the Flame", "content": "To be born on 8 Toj is to be a ceremonial guardian of the balance. You are the 'Sacred Official'—a soul who instinctively understands the laws of karma and reciprocity. You have a dignified, authoritative presence and a deep desire to be of service. You are likely the person who organizes the rituals, manages the funds, or ensures that everyone is treated fairly. You carry a heavy load at times, as Toj often involves paying the debts of the lineage, but the strength of the number 8 gives you the power to carry it with grace.\\n\\nYour life path is one of restoring harmony through offering. You are a natural healer, often working through heat, fire, or blood (the life force). Your challenge is to ensure that you do not become a martyr, giving until you have nothing left. You must learn to receive as well as you give. You are here to keep the sacred fire burning for all of us."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d7896d", "primary": "#160f0d", "secondary": "#493029"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#e5d1a7", "primary": "#8b653c", "secondary": "#bc9b6b"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#f4ebd5", "primary": "#bc5d44", "secondary": "#d0a975"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#c3c2bc", "primary": "#6d6b69", "secondary": "#979793"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.798708	2026-04-25 13:46:57.834693
233	18	12	12	Ajpu	The rain stops as suddenly as it began. You push open the heavy door of the steam lodge and step out into the cool, clean air. The world has been scrubbed. The black rock glistens, and the sky is a brilliant, washed-out azure.\n\nStanding on the ridge above you is a figure. They are glowing with intense, golden light, so bright you have to squint. It is the Solar Hero.\n\nThey do not speak. They simply hold out a weapon—a blowgun, or perhaps a bow, made of pure light. You climb the ridge and take it. It feels weightless in your hands, yet humming with power.\n\nYou look out over the garden. In the distance, the sun is rising, cresting over the jagged horizon. The Hero points to it.\n\nYou understand. You aren’t hunting animals. You are hunting *destiny*.\n\nYou raise the weapon. You aim at the center of the rising sun. You realize that the arrow you are about to fire is not wood or metal. It is your own intent. It is the sum of everything you have learned in the fire, the cave, and the storm.\n\nYou draw back the string. You feel the strength in your arms—the strength you built pulling the cane. You feel the clarity in your mind—the clarity from the puzzle. You feel the lightness in your heart—the release from the amber cave.\n\nYou release.\n\nThe arrow of light streaks across the sky, singing as it flies. It hits the center of the sun.\n\nA pulse of golden light explodes outward, washing over the garden. Where it touches the wet, black earth, life erupts. Not just moss or ferns, but massive, bioluminescent sunflowers, turning their heads not toward the sky, but toward *you*.\n\nYou realize you are the light source they are following.\n\nThe Hero on the ridge fades, smiling. You look at your reflection in a pool of rainwater. You see the face of the one you were waiting for. You are wearing a crown of light.	Stop looking for the hero outside yourself. The cavalry isn’t coming because *you* are the cavalry. Today, own your light. Don’t dim it to make others comfortable.\n\nYou understand now. The struggle wasn’t a punishment; it was training. Every challenge was carving out more space for this light to inhabit. Wear your scars like gold medals. You have earned your sovereignty. Stand tall.	I honor the light within me and shine without apology.	Stand with your feet wide, hands on your hips (Power Pose). Close your eyes. Visualize a miniature sun glowing in your solar plexus (the area below your ribs).\n\nWith every breath, the sun grows brighter and hotter. It burns away insecurity. It radiates golden light that fills your entire body, pushing out through your skin.\n\nFeel this light expanding until it fills the room. You are a source of energy. You are radiant. You are the sun.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Hero of Light", "content": "Ajpu is the nawal of the sun, the blowgunner, and the hero. It represents the divine spark within the human, the mastery of self, and the triumph of light over darkness. Ajpu is the energy of the warrior who fights for beauty and truth. Associated with the element of fire and the sun, it carries a radiant, confident, and masculine energy. It is the archetype of the artist-warrior who walks the path of holiness in everyday life. In daily life, Ajpu manifests as clarity, leadership, overcoming challenges, and the recognition of one's own divinity. Its shadow aspect can be ego, arrogance, or the testing of one's integrity. Ajpu teaches us that we are the light.", "keywords": ["Divinity", "Heroism", "Sun", "Purpose", "Mastery"]}, "number": {"title": "The Understanding of the Whole", "content": "Tone 12 is the energy of understanding, gathering, and the retrospective view. It represents the summation of the cycle's lessons before the final transcendence. It is the number of the 'crystal clear' comprehension that comes after the storm of the 11. Experientially, Tone 12 feels communal, settled, and wise. It is a day to gather the scattered pieces and make sense of them. It fosters cooperation and the ability to summarize complex experiences. While it is generally a positive energy, its shadow can be a refusal to move on or looking backward for too long. It is the librarian who organizes the stories.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Unity", "Cooperation", "Summary", "Review"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Share your story of overcoming a challenge to inspire others.", "Gather with a group to celebrate a shared success.", "Reflect on the 'villains' in your life and see them as teachers.", "Connect with the sun energy to recharge your solar plexus.", "Acknowledge the hero within yourself and within a friend."], "title": "The Gathering of Light", "content": "The synthesizing wisdom of Tone 12 meets the solar brilliance of Ajpu to create a day of 'Collective Enlightenment.' 12 Ajpu is the review of the hero's journey. It is a day to gather all the challenges, victories, and lessons of the past and see them as a unified path of light. The energy feels clear, noble, and expansive. It suggests that our individual heroism is part of a larger, collective story of awakening. 12 Ajpu supports group leadership and the sharing of spiritual truths. It is a time to recognize the divinity in everyone around you. The storm of yesterday has cleared, and the sun is shining on the whole village. The challenge is to avoid spiritual pride; the 12 reminds us that we are all in this together. The opportunity is to stand in the light and invite others to stand with you."}}	{"title": "The Hero of the Collective", "content": "To be born on 12 Ajpu is to be a leader who shines for the benefit of all. You possess a radiant spirit and a deep understanding of the human journey. Tone 12 gives you a collaborative, inclusive nature, while Ajpu grants you the courage and charisma of the sun. You are not a solitary hero; you are a captain of the team, a leader who empowers others to find their own light. You have a natural ability to bring people together around a higher purpose. You are likely drawn to coaching, teaching, performing, or activism—roles where you can be a visible example of integrity.\\n\\nYour life path is one of demonstrating shared divinity. You are here to show that we are all heroes in our own stories. You have a wisdom that comes from experience; you understand the trials of life and can summarize them into lessons that help others. You are a 'sun' in your community, providing warmth and illumination. People flock to you because you make them feel seen and capable.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 12 Ajpu soul is the weight of expectation. You may feel that you always have to be 'on,' always strong, always the leader. This can lead to masking your vulnerabilities. You might also struggle with the complexity of group dynamics, feeling responsible for the harmony of the whole. Your lesson is to remember that the sun also sets. When you allow yourself to be human and vulnerable, your light becomes even more relatable and inspiring, fostering true unity rather than just admiration."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d5b957", "primary": "#171710", "secondary": "#5e4d31"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#dbba7d", "primary": "#162743", "secondary": "#5a5659"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#e4e7d8", "primary": "#619bc6", "secondary": "#a7cce0"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#e5a84a", "primary": "#12131b", "secondary": "#3e91df"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.873962	2026-04-25 13:46:58.024211
66	6	1	1	E'	You emerge into a plaza that feels like the center of a dream. Above, the sky is a vast, blank title page, and at your feet, the ground is a textured vellum that hums with the vibration of a thousand untold stories. In the center of the square, a fountain carved from obsidian sprays iridescent, glowing ink into the air. The droplets don't fall as water; they crystallize into tiny, detailed maps of places that defy logic—islands of clocks, forests made of mirrors, and cities that float on the breath of giants. \n\nTo move forward, you must catch the potential before it hits the ground. You reach out, your palm stained with the scent of ozone and cedar, and catch a falling map. The moment the ink touches your skin, a silver needle-vane erupts from the center of the plaza, spinning wildly before pointing toward a distant, indigo horizon. The blank vellum beneath your feet suddenly groans and begins to unroll in that direction, sketching out a winding ribbon of street, shop-fronts, and lantern-light as you take your first step. This is 1 E'—the seed of the road has been planted, and the bazaar is unspooling specifically for you.	The universe is handing you a silver quill, but it isn't asking you to write a poem; it’s asking you to sketch the very ground you intend to stand on. Today, the horizon isn't a fixed line—it’s a loose thread on a grand, unspooling silk scroll. You might feel a strange, electric restlessness in your heels, a humming in the bones that whispers of distant plazas and neon-inked alleyways. This is the seed of a journey that hasn't yet found its shape. Do not worry about the destination or the weight of the baggage you think you need to carry. Instead, focus on the first drop of ink. As you step into the marketplace of your own potential, notice how the environment reacts to your curiosity. The air smells of cedar and old paper, thick with the scent of things about to happen. You are the architect of the road now. Every choice you make, every glance toward a flickering light, causes the world to unroll a few inches further. It is a day for bold initiations and the quiet bravery of being a beginner. If you feel lost, remember that in a world made of maps, being lost just means you’ve found a page that hasn’t been drawn yet. Let the silver needle of your intent point you toward the most interesting contradiction you can find, and walk toward it with an open heart.	I am the architect of my direction, and I begin my discovery with a single, bold step.	Sit comfortably and close your eyes. Imagine you are standing at the edge of a great, unrolled scroll of white silk that stretches to the horizon. Breathe deeply, and with every exhale, feel your feet becoming heavy and connected to this path. See a single drop of iridescent ink fall from the sky and land just before you, marking the very first step of a new journey. Focus on the stillness of this beginning.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, visualize the Fountain of Infinite Ink spraying a fine mist over you. Feel the droplets settle on your skin like cooling stardust, each one containing a map of a different possibility. Allow your internal needle-vane to spin wildly until it clicks into place, pointing toward the indigo light of your true North.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Pathfinder", "content": "E' is the Nawal of the path, the road, and the journey of life. It represents the energy of movement, exploration, and the exchange of wisdom that comes from travel. E' governs the physical roads we walk as well as the spiritual destiny we are carving out. In human experience, it manifests as curiosity, restlessness, and a desire to see what lies beyond the horizon. It is the archetype of the Guide and the Diplomat who bridges cultures. When aligned, E' brings clarity of direction and safe passage; when misaligned, it can lead to aimless wandering or feeling lost. It is the road that rises to meet your feet.", "keywords": ["Journey", "Path", "Exploration", "Guidance", "Discovery"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Motion", "content": "The number One represents the unity of all things and the initial spark of creation. It is the seed that holds the potential for the entire forest. In Mayan cosmology, One is the energy of firm beginnings, resolve, and the single-pointed focus required to start a new cycle. Experientially, this energy feels like a surge of newness—a clear, singular impulse to move. It asks you to stand alone if necessary and to plant your intention with absolute clarity. The shadow of One can be isolation or fear of the first step, but its light is the unstoppable power of initiation. Today, you are the origin point of a new journey.", "keywords": ["Beginnings", "Unity", "Potential", "Seed", "Focus"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Take the first physical step toward a goal you have been planning.", "Set a clear intention for where you want to be in 13 days.", "Go for a walk in a place you have never been before.", "Bless your feet and your shoes; they are your primary tools today.", "Trust the impulse to move; stagnation is the only enemy today."], "title": "Initiating the Great Journey", "content": "When the initiating spark of Tone 1 meets the traveling energy of E', we stand at the true beginning of a quest. Today is the first step of a 13-day journey that emphasizes exploration, discovery, and the courage to leave the known for the unknown. The combined energy is restless and propulsive; it feels like the moment you lock the front door, turn around, and face the open road. It is the perfect day to start a trip, launch a new venture, or simply take a new route to work to invite fresh energy. The universe is asking you to set your internal compass. Where do you want to go? 1 E' is not just about physical travel; it is about initiating a new timeline in your life. The path is open, and the lights are green. Trust that the road will provide what you need, even if you cannot see the destination from here."}}	{"title": "The Pioneer of Destiny", "content": "To be born on 1 E' is to be a trailblazer in the truest sense. You carry the energy of the 'First Step'—the brave soul who is willing to venture where no one else has gone. You are the initiator of journeys, both for yourself and for those around you. Your life is likely characterized by a series of new beginnings and explorations; you are not meant to stay in one place for too long, either physically or spiritually. You possess a natural independence and a singular focus that allows you to cut through confusion and find the way forward.\\n\\nYour soul purpose is to discover new paths and to serve as a guide for others. You have an innate internal compass that rarely steers you wrong, provided you trust it over the advice of others. While you may sometimes feel the loneliness of the pioneer (the energy of the number 1), your solitude is often your greatest strength, allowing you to commune with the road itself. You are here to show the world that the unknown is not to be feared, but to be walked."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#bfd0d7", "primary": "#0f1315", "secondary": "#404a4f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.775591	2026-04-25 14:38:01.291591
83	7	5	5	Kan	You feel the pull of the lake before you see it.\n\nThe path seems shorter today, or maybe your feet are simply more certain. The air is warmer, carrying a faint metallic tang, like the scent in the air before lightning. Every step feels charged, as if the ground is humming under your soles.\n\nWhen you reach the shore, the water is no longer just a mirror.\n\nBeneath the surface, something moves with purpose. Not a fish, not a drifting branch, but a long, sinuous shape of light and shadow coiling in slow arcs. It never fully reveals itself. You see only sections — a curve here, a glint there — but the presence is unmistakable. The lake has a spine today.\n\nYou stand very still, unsure if you are being invited or tested.\n\nThe shape turns, and for a heartbeat it feels as though it is looking directly at you. Not with eyes, but with awareness. Your skin prickles. Old stories rise in your mind about what power is supposed to look like — loud, forceful, always in control. Yet this thing beneath the water is none of that. It is patient. It is coiled potential.\n\nYou notice how your body responds. A flicker of excitement. A curl of fear. A restless urge to move, to change something, to finally act on the quiet truths you have been circling around. The presence in the water seems to amplify everything: your desire, your anger, your hunger for a life that feels fully lived.\n\nYou crouch and place your hand just above the surface, close enough to feel the cool rising from below. Your fingers tingle, not from contact, but from proximity to something alive and immense. A thought comes, clear and simple: what you touch, you shape.\n\nYou think about the ways you have used your energy — the times you have scattered it, the times you have turned it inward against yourself, the rare moments you have directed it cleanly toward what you love. The shape beneath the water shifts again, looping in a slow spiral, as if tracing a path you could follow.\n\nYou do not reach into the lake. Not today. Instead, you make a quiet decision on the shore: to treat your own vitality as something sacred, not reckless; as a current to be aimed, not spilled.\n\nWhen you step away, the humming in your body remains. It is not agitation. It is readiness. The sense that your life is not a static pool, but a river that has been waiting for you to choose a direction.	There is a charge in the air around you today, the kind that makes it hard to sit completely still. Your body is speaking — through restlessness, attraction, irritation, or sudden bursts of inspiration. Instead of trying to shut it down, try listening.\n\nThis is not about forcing yourself to do everything. It is about choosing where your power goes. Ask yourself what you are truly hungry for right now: more aliveness, more honesty, more creative risk, more embodied joy. Then take one concrete action that feeds that hunger instead of numbing it.\n\nYou are not fragile decoration in your own life. You are a living current. Let your movements, your words, and your choices reflect that truth.	I honor my life-force as sacred and choose to direct my energy toward what is honest, alive, and aligned with my growth.	Sit or stand in a position where you can feel your feet firmly connected to the ground. Close your eyes and imagine a gentle, glowing current coiled at the base of your spine or deep in your belly.\n\nWith each inhale, see that current brighten slightly, as if you are greeting your own life-force. With each exhale, imagine it stretching a little longer through your body — up your spine, into your chest, down your arms, into your hands, and through your legs into your feet.\n\nOnce you can feel this imagined current flowing through you, quietly ask: “Where do I choose to direct this energy today?” Let an image, word, or feeling arise without forcing it. You do not need a full plan, only a clear direction.\n\nBefore you open your eyes, offer thanks to the wisdom of the body and to the ancient keepers of earth and fire, who understood that power is not just what you have, but how you use it. Take one steady breath and step back into your day with intention.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Serpent's Fire", "content": "Kan is the Nawal of the Serpent, the vital life force (Kundalini), and wisdom. It represents the energy of evolution, sexuality, and the DNA spiral. Kan is the power that moves up the spine and brings enlightenment or transformation. In human experience, Kan manifests as charisma, physical strength, and a drive for justice and truth. It is the teacher and the student. When aligned, Kan brings vitality, passion, and deep wisdom; when misaligned, it can lead to manipulation, anger, or misuse of power. It is the fire in the blood.", "keywords": ["Vitality", "Power", "Wisdom", "Transformation", "Sexuality"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Action", "content": "The number Five represents the center point of the first wave of creation. It is the energy of the hand (five fingers) and the power to grasp, work, and manipulate reality. In Mayan cosmology, Five is the force of 'doing'; it breaks the static stability of Four and puts it into motion through effort. Experientially, this energy feels like a surge of willpower and a drive to get things done. It is the number of work, discipline, and the application of energy. The shadow of Five can be forcing things, but its light is the satisfaction of a job well done.", "keywords": ["Action", "Discipline", "Work", "Willpower", "Effort"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in intense physical exercise to move the energy.", "Apply yourself to a difficult task; you have the stamina today.", "Channel sexual energy into a creative project.", "Stand up for a cause you believe in with passion.", "Study or teach something that requires deep focus."], "title": "Empowered Effort", "content": "When the hardworking energy of Tone 5 meets the potent life force of Kan, we get a day of 'Kundalini in Action.' 5 Kan is a powerhouse day. It represents the application of your deepest vital energy toward a goal. It is not a day for half-measures; whatever you do today, put your whole back (and spine) into it. The energy supports physical training, hard work, and the pursuit of wisdom through discipline. You may feel a surge of charisma or sexual energy; channel this into your creative or professional projects. 5 Kan asks you to 'empower your life'—to stop waiting for things to happen and to make them happen through the sheer force of your will and vitality. It is also a day of justice; use your power to stand up for what is right. The serpent is awake and working today."}}	{"title": "The Energetic Master", "content": "To be born on 5 Kan is to be a dynamo of energy and wisdom. You are the 'Active Serpent'—a soul who possesses immense vitality and the discipline to direct it. You are likely very charismatic, physically strong, or intellectually brilliant, with a presence that commands attention. You are a worker, a doer, and a natural leader who leads by example. You don't just possess wisdom (Kan); you apply it (5) to the real world.\\n\\nYour life path is one of mastering your own power. You have a high-voltage system that needs to be grounded through work, exercise, or service. If you do not channel your energy, it can turn into frustration or aggression. Your challenge is to use your power responsibly, serving the light rather than the ego. You are here to show us what it looks like when human potential is fully activated and applied."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#88b493", "primary": "#131a18", "secondary": "#3a493d"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.785301	2026-04-25 13:46:57.777763
118	10	1	1	Kame					{"nawal": {"title": "The Transformer", "content": "Kame is the energy of death, rebirth, and the ancestral realms. It is the great equalizer and the peace that follows necessary endings. Far from being frightening, Kame is the benevolent force that clears away stagnation so that life can renew itself. It connects us to the wisdom of those who walked before us and offers the spiritual protection needed to traverse dark passages. It is the owl that sees in the dark, the silence of the cocoon, and the courage to release what has already died so that the future can breathe.", "keywords": ["Rebirth", "Ancestors", "Transformation", "Endings", "Courage"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Transformation", "content": "The number 1 represents the spark of creation, the unity of all things, and the seed that contains the potential for the entire cycle. It is the beginning, the impulse to exist, and the singular focus required to start a new journey. In the context of this trecena, the 1 energy initiates a profound cycle of letting go and beginning again. It is not a gentle push but a decisive ignition. It asks for total presence and the willingness to stand at the threshold of the unknown, holding the intention for what is to be born from the ashes of the old.", "keywords": ["Unity", "Initiation", "Potential", "Seed", "Focus"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Identify one habit or fear that is ready to be released.", "Light a candle to honor your ancestors and ask for their guidance.", "Sit in silence and visualize a doorway; step through it mentally.", "Write down your intention for this 13-day cycle of transformation.", "Treat every ending today as a necessary clearing for new growth."], "title": "Initiating the Cycle of Rebirth", "content": "Today, the seed of transformation is planted. 1 Kame brings the powerful, singular intent to begin a process of deep renewal. This is a day to acknowledge what is ending in your life—not with fear, but with the reverence due to a closing chapter. The energy is quiet but intense, like the moment before a thunderstorm breaks. It invites you to step into the void of the unknown with trust, knowing that the ancestors stand as guardians at the gate. It is a time to set the intention for your own rebirth, asking yourself what part of your history you are ready to metabolize into wisdom and what new version of yourself is waiting to be born."}}	{"title": "The Initiator of New Worlds", "content": "To be born on 1 Kame is to be a soul intimately acquainted with the cycles of life and death. You carry the energy of the 'first breath' after a long silence. You are a natural initiator, someone who is not afraid to walk into the dark because you know that is where the light is born. Your presence often signals change for those around you; you are a catalyst who helps others release their old skins simply by being near them. You possess a quiet, ancient dignity and a connection to lineage that allows you to draw strength from the past to forge the future.\\n\\nYour path is one of constant reinvention. You may find that your life moves in distinct chapters, each one requiring you to completely let go of who you were to become who you are. While others may cling to security, you understand that security is an illusion and that true safety lies in fluidity and trust. You are a bridge between the visible and invisible worlds, often gifted with deep intuition or mediumship abilities.\\n\\nYour challenge is to not fear the power of your own transformation. The intensity of 1 Kame can sometimes feel isolating, as you perceive the impermanence of things more acutely than most. However, when you embrace your role as a guardian of thresholds, you become a powerful healer and guide. You teach the world that every end is a beginning, and that death is simply a change of clothes for the soul."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#dad2d8", "primary": "#101719", "secondary": "#3f3e45"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.805768	2026-04-25 13:46:57.866324
130	10	13	13	Tijax					{"nawal": {"title": "The Cosmic Knife", "content": "Tijax is the obsidian blade, the mirror, and the healer. It represents the power to cut away illness, illusion, and negativity. Tijax is the warrior for truth who is not afraid to sever what is dead to save the patient. It is the energy of the surgeon and the spark of the thunder flint. While it can be sharp and abrupt, its ultimate purpose is healing and purification. It reveals the shiny truth hidden inside the rough stone.", "keywords": ["Healing", "Cutting", "Obsidian", "Truth", "Purification"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascension of Spirit", "content": "The number 13 represents completion, ascension, and the spirit world. It is the final step of the wave, where the energy transcends the physical form and returns to the source. 13 is a number of great power, sensitivity, and psychic expansion. It is not just an ending, but an elevation. It allows us to see the entire cycle from the perspective of the ancestors. It brings the unexpected, the miraculous, and the touch of the divine.", "keywords": ["Ascension", "Completion", "Spirit", "Ancestors", "Renewal"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a cord-cutting visualization to release a past attachment definitively.", "Declutter a space ruthlessly; if it doesn't serve the new you, it goes.", "Visit a healer or perform a self-healing ritual.", "Look in the mirror and ask to see the absolute truth of your being.", "Celebrate the completion of your transformation; step into the new light."], "title": "The Ultimate Healing", "content": "13 Tijax is the grand finale of the Kame trecena. The journey of death and rebirth concludes with a powerful, transcendent healing. The obsidian blade of Tijax, wielded with the spiritual mastery of the 13, cuts the final cord that binds us to the old reality. This is not a painful cut, but a liberating one—like cutting the umbilical cord of a newborn. Today is a day of radical purification and sudden enlightenment. The energy is high, sharp, and decisive. We ascend out of the cycle of transformation, leaving behind the heavy skins we have shed, ready to walk into the new world healed, whole, and free."}}	{"title": "The Cosmic Surgeon", "content": "To be born on 13 Tijax is to be a high-frequency agent of evolution. You are a powerful healer and a warrior for truth, operating with the elevated perspective of the number 13. You have an uncanny ability to see straight to the heart of any matter, cutting through lies, excuses, and illusions with laser-like precision. You are not here to comfort people with comfortable lies; you are here to heal them with the sharp truth. Your presence can be intense, but it is always transformative.\\n\\nYour life path is one of constant refinement and ascension. You are likely intuitive, psychic, or deeply connected to the spirit world. You may find yourself in roles where you are 'fixing' things that others have given up on—whether bodies, systems, or souls. You have a double-edged sword: you can heal with a word, or you can wound. Because you see the flaws in everything, you are a perfectionist who seeks to reveal the divine spark in all matter.\\n\\nYour challenge is to wield your blade with compassion. The 13 energy makes you extremely sensitive, and you may react defensively if you feel threatened. Your lesson is to remember that the goal of the cut is to heal, not to harm. When you use your discernment to liberate rather than judge, you become a divine surgeon, helping the world cut away the darkness to reveal the light within."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d0b593", "primary": "#131312", "secondary": "#523931"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.808136	2026-04-25 13:46:57.871454
255	20	8	8	Iq'	You leave the lake and climb to the highest ridge, where the rock narrows to a knife-edge. On either side, the drop is infinite. But you are not walking; you are balancing on the air itself.\n\nThis is the Currents of the Sky.\n\n8 is Harmony and Wholeness. Iq’ is the Wind, the Breath, the Spirit. You have reached the element of the Eagle.\n\nThe wind here is not chaotic. It is a steady, powerful stream, like a river of air. You can lean into it, and it holds you.\n\nYou realize that to be a visionary, you cannot be rigid. You must be aerodynamic. You must move with the currents of the universe, not against them.\n\nYou spread your arms. You feel the wind rushing through your fingers. You are learning the art of the glide.\n\nProsperity is not about grabbing; it is about positioning your wings so the lift takes you higher. It is about least effort and maximum altitude.\n\nYou breathe in the high, pure air. It clears out the last of the dust from the valley. You are breathing the same air as the stars.\n\nYou feel a profound sense of harmony. The wind inside you (your breath) matches the wind outside you (the spirit). You are one with the flow.\n\nYou look ahead. The summit is close now. But you are not rushing. You are riding the updraft.	The wind is at your back today. The energy of 8 Iq’ is a harmonious gale that wants to lift you up. Stop flapping so hard and just glide.\n\nCommunication flows easily today. It’s a great day to speak your truth, share your ideas, or just take a deep breath and let the stress blow away. The universe is breathing with you. Get in sync.	I breathe in the harmony of the universe and speak my truth with love.	Visualize yourself as a feather floating in the sky. You have no weight. The wind carries you gently. Up, down, spiraling.\n\nFeel the absolute freedom of surrender. You don’t have to steer. The wind knows where you are going.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Breath of Spirit", "content": "Iq' is the nawal of the wind, the breath, and the messenger. It represents communication, clarity, and the breath of life. Governs inspiration, change, and purification. Can stir sudden transformation or anger when misaligned. Associated with the element of air and the color white, it carries a swift, changeable, and inspiring energy. It is the archetype of the divine messenger who whispers truth in our ears. In daily life, Iq' manifests as conversation, the internet, travel, and the sudden shifting of circumstances. Its shadow aspect can be impulsiveness, harsh words, or chaos. Iq' teaches us to listen to the spirit and to keep our own energy moving.", "keywords": ["Breath", "Words", "Clarity", "Change", "Communication"]}, "number": {"title": "The Harmonious Weaver", "content": "Tone 8 is the energy of resonance, justice, and the octave. Following the peak of the 7, the 8 represents the return to the material world but with a higher frequency. It is the number of the 'infinite loop' (infinity symbol), representing the continuous flow of spirit into matter and back again. Experientially, Tone 8 feels harmonious, balanced, and ceremonial. It is often associated with the male energy or the father, bringing structure that honors the spirit. It is a day of resonance, where actions echo loudly. While it fosters integrity and wholeness, its shadow can be rigidity or a dogmatic adherence to form over feeling. It is the weaver who tightens the threads to create a strong cloth.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Justice", "Resonance", "Infinity", "Ceremony"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Practice breathing exercises to balance your nervous system.", "Sing or chant to resonate your vocal cords.", "Write a letter or speak to someone to clear the air.", "Perform a ceremony with incense or smoke (air element).", "Listen deeply to the wind in the trees."], "title": "The Resonant Breath", "content": "When the resonant structure of Tone 8 meets the wind of Iq', we experience a day of 'Sacred Communication.' 8 Iq' is the energy of the Hummingbird ritual. It is a day to harmonize with the breath of life and to speak words of power. The energy is clear, vibrant, and ceremonial. It supports using the voice to heal and to create balance. 8 Iq' asks us to pay attention to the air we breathe and the words we speak—are they bringing life or death? It is an excellent day for chanting, singing, or having a conversation that restores harmony to a relationship. The energy feels like a pure, high note held in a cathedral. The challenge is to not let the wind scatter your focus; the 8 demands alignment. The opportunity is to become a hollow bone through which the spirit can blow a song of beauty."}}	{"title": "The Resonant Messenger", "content": "To be born on 8 Iq' is to be a voice for the divine and a bringer of harmony through communication. You possess a soul that vibrates with the breath of spirit. Tone 8 gives you a sense of balance and ceremonial structure, while Iq' grants you the power of the word and the inspiration of the wind. You are the poet, the singer, the orator who can move crowds with your voice. You understand that words are energy, and you use them to weave spells of healing and connection.\\n\\nYour life path is one of resonant expression. You are here to speak the truths that bring people back into alignment. You may be drawn to music, writing, media, or spiritual teaching. You have a quick mind and a restless spirit, always seeking the next current of inspiration. You are a natural connector, using communication to bridge gaps and restore justice. People listen to you because your words ring true.\\n\\nThe challenge for an 8 Iq' soul is inconsistency. You can be as changeable as the weather, blowing hot and cold. You may struggle with anger or sharp words when you are out of balance. There is a risk of talking too much and listening too little. Your lesson is to harmonize your breath. When you learn to speak from the center of the infinity loop—where spirit meets matter—your voice becomes a tool of sacred geometry, restructuring the world with every word."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#cfc7ca", "primary": "#181a1a", "secondary": "#5d555e"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#cac9ce", "primary": "#343a37", "secondary": "#8d9698"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#e8f2f9", "primary": "#a2b3c6", "secondary": "#d2e3f1"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#d2f2f5", "primary": "#1c8cba", "secondary": "#2bd5e8"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.884703	2026-04-25 13:46:58.08873
100	8	9	9	Tz'i'	From the altar, you enter a long, echoing corridor formed by clouds that have hardened into stone. This is the Hall of Echoes.\n\nYour footsteps ring out sharp and clear. *Click. Click. Click.*\n\nTz’i’ is the Dog, the Guardian of Law, the Guide. The number 9 is the energy of gestation and patience. Today, you are being tested on your consistency.\n\nA shadow-dog walks beside you. It does not look at you; it just matches your pace. It is checking your integrity. Are you the same person in the dark as you are in the light?\n\nThe walls of the hall reflect your thoughts back to you as whispers. You hear your own doubts, your own judgments. They are loud here.\n\nYou realize that the "Law" isn’t a rulebook written by someone else. It is the law of your own conscience. You know when you are out of alignment. You feel it in your gut.\n\nThe shadow-dog nudges your hand. It is a reminder: You don’t have to be perfect, but you have to be loyal. Loyal to yourself. Loyal to your path.\n\nYou straighten your back. You walk with more intention. The whispers on the walls change. They stop sounding like doubts and start sounding like prayers.\n\nYou reach the end of the hall. The dog sits and watches you pass. You have passed the test. You are walking your truth.	Your integrity is your superpower today. The energy of 9 Tz’i’ asks you to be faithful to who you are, even if no one is watching. Do the right thing, not the easy thing.\n\nThere is a quiet strength available to you. It’s not flashy, but it’s unbreakable. Trust your gut instincts. If a situation feels wrong, walk away. If it feels right, stay loyal to it. You are your own best guide.	I am loyal to my own soul, walking my path with patience and integrity.	Visualize a white dog sitting at your feet. It is your protector. Feel its unconditional love and loyalty.\n\nAsk it: "Where do I need to be more true to myself?"\n\nListen for the answer. Pet the dog. Feel safe.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Guide of Law", "content": "Tz'i' is the Nawal of the dog, the law, justice, and loyalty. It represents the principle of divine order and the faithful guide who leads the soul through the darkness. Tz'i' is the energy of authority, protection, and unconditional love. In human experience, Tz'i' manifests as a strong sense of right and wrong, a desire for justice, and deep loyalty to friends and family. It is the secretary who keeps the records straight. When aligned, Tz'i' brings legal success and spiritual guidance; when misaligned, it can lead to judgment or blind obedience.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Loyalty", "Law", "Faith", "Protection"]}, "number": {"title": "The Womb of Patience", "content": "The number Nine represents the completion of the developmental cycle, the gestation period (9 months), and the energy of the feminine. In Mayan cosmology, Nine is associated with the 'Primordial Female' and the deep, dark soil where the seed transforms. Experientially, this energy feels introspective, creative, and sometimes slow. It is the patience of the mother waiting for the birth. It is a time for nurturing, refining details, and preparing for the final manifestation. The shadow of Nine can be isolation, but its light is the profound power of life generating life.", "keywords": ["Patience", "Gestation", "Feminine", "Completion", "Nurturing"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Practice patience in any legal or bureaucratic matters.", "Show loyalty to a friend who is going through a hard time.", "Reflect on your own moral code; is it growing and evolving?", "Nurture your 'inner authority'—be a kind parent to yourself.", "Trust the process; justice is ripening."], "title": "Gestating Justice", "content": "The patient, feminine energy of Tone 9 meets the loyal, legal energy of Tz'i' to create a day of 'Compassionate Law.' 9 Tz'i' is the energy of the mother wolf—fiercely protective yet deeply nurturing. It is a day where justice is tempered with mercy and patience. If you are working on legal matters or seeking truth, this energy supports a long-term, careful approach. It is not about a quick verdict, but about the slow gestation of what is right. The energy asks you to be loyal to your own creative process and to your own truth. Don't rush to judgment—of yourself or others. Let the evidence gestate. 9 Tz'i' also highlights the 'law of love'—the idea that true justice cares for the whole. It is a beautiful day to nurture your relationships through acts of loyalty and faithfulness. Trust that the truth will be born in its own time."}}	{"title": "The Compassionate Guardian", "content": "To be born on 9 Tz'i' is to be a protector of the vulnerable and a keeper of the heart's law. You are the 'Nurturing Guide'—a soul who combines a fierce sense of justice with deep, feminine compassion. You are likely the person who rescues stray animals (literally or metaphorically) and fights for the underdog. You have a patient, enduring nature; you don't give up on people easily. Your loyalty is legendary, but it is not blind—you see the truth, yet you choose to love anyway.\\n\\nYour life path is one of evolving the concept of justice. You are here to show that the law is not just cold rules, but a living structure meant to protect life. The number 9 gives you a creative, gestating energy, making you a wonderful mentor or parent. Your challenge is to ensure that your loyalty doesn't keep you trapped in situations that have outlived their purpose. You are here to teach us that love is the highest law."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c8c8c0", "primary": "#131615", "secondary": "#51504b"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#c2774f", "primary": "#36100d", "secondary": "#7f3223"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#f7f7f5", "primary": "#dac99d", "secondary": "#ece8da"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#7f8da1", "primary": "#2c3343", "secondary": "#555f72"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.798964	2026-04-25 13:46:57.836654
105	9	1	1	Ix					{"nawal": {"title": "The Jaguar of Earth Magic", "content": "Ix is the Nawal of the Jaguar, the night, and the magic of the Earth. It represents the feminine mysteries, intuition, and the high magic of the shrines and altars. Ix is the energy that sees in the dark; it connects us to the subtle forces of nature and the wisdom of the mountains. As the archetype of the Shaman and the Healer, Ix governs our capacity to transform and to manifest through intent. In human experience, Ix brings a heightened sensitivity, a love for solitude, and a deep connection to the natural world. It is the velvet darkness that holds the stars. When aligned, Ix brings spiritual power and profound insight; when misaligned, it can lead to being overwhelmed by psychic input.", "keywords": ["Earth Magic", "Intuition", "Jaguar", "Sacred Sites", "Manifestation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Magic", "content": "The number One represents the primordial spark, the moment of inception, and the unity of all things. It is the seed that contains the entire blueprint of the future within its tiny shell. In Mayan cosmology, One is the energy of initiation and firm beginnings; it is not merely a start, but a powerful concentration of potential that requires focus and intent. Experientially, this energy feels like a surge of inspiration or a sudden clarity of purpose. It asks you to stand alone if necessary, to be the single point of origin for a new cycle. The shadow of One can be isolation or a failure to launch due to the overwhelming weight of potential, but its light is the unstoppable force of creation itself. Today, you are the origin point.", "keywords": ["Beginnings", "Unity", "Seed", "Potential", "Focus"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Set a clear intention for your spiritual practice for the next 13 days.", "Spend time in nature, listening to the wind and the earth.", "Create a small altar or designated sacred space in your home.", "Trust your gut feelings; your intuition is highly activated.", "Honor the feminine forces in your life and in the world."], "title": "Initiating the Magic", "content": "When the initiating spark of Tone 1 meets the deep, mystical energy of Ix, we stand at the threshold of a magical journey. 1 Ix is the 'Seed of Magic.' Today is the perfect day to plant an intention related to your spiritual growth, your intuition, or your connection to nature. This trecena will take you deep into the mysteries of the Earth and your own psyche. The energy is quiet, potent, and feline. It asks you to move silently and observe the subtle energies around you. You may feel a pull to visit a sacred place in nature or to create a small altar in your home. The Jaguar is waking up today, stretching its limbs, and preparing to walk the path of the heart. Trust your instincts completely; the logical mind is not the captain of this ship. Today, magic is not a fantasy; it is the seed of reality."}}	{"title": "The Mystic Initiator", "content": "To be born on 1 Ix is to be a natural-born shaman and a pioneer of the spirit. You are the 'First Jaguar'—a soul who carries the raw, unadulterated magic of the Earth. You likely have a profound connection to nature and animals, often feeling more at home in the woods than in the city. You possess a powerful intuition that operates almost instantly; you 'know' things without needing to have them explained. Your presence is often mysterious and magnetic, drawing others to you who are seeking depth.\\n\\nYour life path is one of initiating others into the mysteries of life. With the number 1, you are independent and perhaps a bit solitary, preferring to walk your own path rather than follow the herd. Ix gives you the ability to see in the dark, making you an excellent guide for those going through difficult times. Your challenge is to trust your own power and not to hide your magic to fit in. You are here to remind the world that the Earth is alive and that we are all connected to her spirit."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c1be80", "primary": "#161b15", "secondary": "#534b32"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.801713	2026-04-25 13:46:57.850099
163	13	7	7	Kan	The seventh day opens with a strange brightness beneath the clouds. The storm has not passed, yet something in the air feels charged, as if the whole sky is breathing through a different set of lungs. The rain glitters in brief flashes when lightning murmurs far off behind the hills, and the road ahead curves upward along a ridge that offers a wider view than any you have had since joining the caravan.\n\nAs the climb steepens, you feel the effort in your body with unusual clarity. Your calves burn. Your breath deepens. A pulse rises through you, not uncomfortable, but insistent, like a current waking inside your spine. It travels upward in slow, deliberate waves, and with it comes a heightened awareness of everything around you. The slickness of mud beneath your boots, the weight of your soaked clothes, the smell of wet earth and iron-rich stone, the sound of rain striking canvas, wood, skin.\n\nWhen the caravan finally reaches the ridge, the view opens in every direction. Valleys fold into one another under veils of mist. Dark rivers glint below like moving threads. The road behind you appears and disappears through the storm, and for the first time you can see the shape of your journey instead of only the next few steps.\n\nThe travelers spread out for a few moments, each taking in the view in their own way. The restless one stands very still, their usual agitation replaced by something closer to wonder. The one who so often carries heaviness lifts their face to the rain as if letting it strike them clean. Even the covered wagon seems changed here, framed against the wide horizon like a vessel carrying more than one life at once.\n\nYou feel the caravan differently now. Not as separate people moving through the same weather, but as a single living system, each part influencing the others. The energy running through you is not yours alone. It is shared, passed hand to hand, breath to breath, choice to choice. The storm itself seems to know this, curling around the ridge in long, serpentine sheets that move as if guided by an intelligence older than fear.\n\nStanding there, with the whole wet world spread beneath you, you understand that perspective is not distance from life. It is deeper entry into it. The current inside you does not ask you to dominate what you see. It asks you to feel your place within it.\n\nWhen the caravan begins to descend the far side of the ridge, you go with it carrying a new steadiness, as though something vital has risen and taken its rightful place within you.	Something in you is waking up, and it may not ask for permission.\n\nThere is an energy moving through today that feels alive, not in a chaotic sense, but in a deeply intelligent way. You may notice a heightened awareness of your body, your instincts, your reactions. Things feel more immediate. More present. Less filtered.\n\nThis is not something to control.\n\nThis is something to feel.\n\nYou may find that your perspective widens suddenly. Situations that once felt small or isolated now appear as part of a larger pattern. You begin to see connections—between people, between choices, between moments that once seemed unrelated.\n\nThis can feel empowering.\n\nIt can also feel overwhelming.\n\nThe key is not to grasp at the clarity too tightly. Let it move through you. Let it inform you without needing to define everything all at once.\n\nThere is a natural intelligence in your system that knows how to process this kind of expansion. Your role is not to manage it, but to stay present within it.\n\nGround yourself in your body when needed. Breathe. Feel your feet. Let the energy move rather than stagnate.\n\nYou are not becoming something new.\n\nYou are becoming more aware of what has been there all along.\n\nAnd that awareness changes everything.	I allow my energy to rise and move freely through me.	Sit still and close your eyes.\nBring your awareness to the base of your spine.\nAs you inhale, imagine energy gently rising upward through your body.\nAs you exhale, let it settle and integrate.\nMove slowly, without forcing anything.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine a luminous current rising through you like a spiral of light. It moves naturally, not aggressively. As it rises, it clears pathways within you, illuminating areas that were once hidden. You are not pushing this energy—it is awakening on its own.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Vital Force", "content": "Kan is the energy of the serpent, the kundalini, and the life force. It represents wisdom, sexuality, and the power of evolution. Kan is the teacher who shows us that true power comes from within and often requires shedding old skins. It is the spark of biology and the intelligence of the body.", "keywords": ["Vitality", "Power", "Sexuality", "Wisdom", "Transformation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Summit of Reflection", "content": "The number 7 represents the top of the pyramid, the midpoint of the cycle. It is a place of mystical power, equilibrium, and the ability to see both the past and future. 7 is a number of channeling and high magic. In the Kawoq trecena, 7 gives us a panoramic view of the life force that has been awakened by the storm.", "keywords": ["Insight", "Clarity", "Reflection", "Mysticism", "Midpoint"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Practice yoga or meditation to move energy up the spine.", "Connect with your sexual energy as a sacred creative force.", "Ask for wisdom regarding a health issue.", "Look at your life from a higher perspective; what skin needs shedding?", "Feel the pulse of the earth and align your heartbeat with it."], "title": "The Mystical Serpent", "content": "7 Kan is a day of high spiritual voltage. Standing at the top of the pyramid, we connect with the raw power of the Serpent. The storm of Kawoq has watered the earth, and now the life force (Kan) rises to meet the sun. This is a day of powerful healing and energetic activation. The energy is not just physical; it is mystical. We can see the patterns of our own evolution. It is a day to honor your body as a temple and to channel your passion into spiritual growth. The lightning of the storm meets the lightning in the spine. Evolution accelerates today."}}	{"title": "The Mystic of Life Force", "content": "To be born on 7 Kan is to be a vessel of potent spiritual and physical energy. You are a mystic who experiences the divine through the body. You possess a high vibration that can be intense for others; you naturally catalyze change just by being in the room. You have a deep, intuitive wisdom about the cycles of life and evolution. You are likely drawn to healing arts, tantra, or any path that integrates the spirit and the flesh.\\n\\nYour life path is one of mastering your own power. You stand at the midpoint between the instinctual and the divine, constantly working to integrate the two. You have a regal presence and a natural authority. You are a teacher of transformation, showing others that the path to enlightenment goes *through* the body, not away from it.\\n\\nYour challenge is balance. The 7 Kan energy is electric and can lead to burnout or nervous system overload if not grounded. You may also struggle with the intensity of your own desires. Your lesson is to become a hollow bone for the energy to flow through. When you align your personal will with the cosmic current, you become a powerful healer and a living example of the divine human potential."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d1a175", "primary": "#131a18", "secondary": "#54483c"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.836242	2026-04-25 14:25:01.118997
114	9	10	10	Aq'ab'al					{"nawal": {"title": "The Dawn of Possibility", "content": "Aq'ab'al is the Nawal of the dawn, the dusk, and the transition between light and dark. It represents the moment of awakening and the potential of a new day. Aq'ab'al is the energy of duality, polarity, and the hope that comes after the long night. In human experience, it manifests as optimism, youthfulness, and the ability to see the solution in the problem. It is the bridge between the dream and the reality. When aligned, Aq'ab'al brings new opportunities and clarity; when misaligned, it can lead to hesitation.", "keywords": ["Dawn", "Transition", "Hope", "Awakening", "Potential"]}, "number": {"title": "The Peak of Manifestation", "content": "The number Ten represents the manifestation of the intent. It is the two hands coming together (5+5) to finalize the creation. In Mayan cosmology, Ten is the energy of community agreement, collaboration, and the realization of the project. Experientially, this energy feels solid, accomplished, and social. It is the moment when the house is built and we invite the neighbors in. The shadow of Ten can be over-responsibility, but its light is the satisfaction of seeing your dreams take physical form. Today, the universe says: 'It is done.'", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Collaboration", "Realization", "Mastery"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Launch a project that has been in the planning phase.", "Celebrate a new chapter with your community or team.", "Acknowledge how past challenges (darkness) helped create this success (light).", "Look for tangible signs of hope in your environment.", "Collaborate to bring a new vision to life."], "title": "Manifested Hope", "content": "When the solid manifestation power of Tone 10 meets the dawning light of Aq'ab'al, we get a day of 'Realized Potential.' 10 Aq'ab'al is the day the sun fully rises on your project. The hope and potential that were just glimmers are now solid, visible realities. It is a day of community celebration for a new beginning. The energy supports bringing a concept out of the 'twilight' stage and fully into the material world, with the support of your tribe. It is a day to say, 'Look, we made it through the night.' The duality of Aq'ab'al is stabilized by the 10, allowing us to see how the dark and light work together to create the whole picture. It is a wonderful day to launch a community initiative, start a family project, or simply enjoy the clarity of a new day with friends."}}	{"title": "The Dawn Bringer", "content": "To be born on 10 Aq'ab'al is to be a leader of new beginnings. You are the 'Manifested Dawn'—someone who has the power to turn hope into reality. You are likely optimistic, energetic, and socially gifted, with a knack for rallying people around a vision of the future. You don't just dream of a better day; you build it (10). You are the person who finds the solution when everyone else sees only problems.\\n\\nYour life path is one of realizing potential. You are a bridge-builder, connecting people and ideas to create something new. The number 10 gives you a sense of responsibility to your community; you want your success to lift everyone up. Your challenge is to maintain your optimism when the 'night' seems long, and to remember that you have the power to bring the light. You are here to wake the world up."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c5977f", "primary": "#111819", "secondary": "#4f444a"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.804301	2026-04-25 13:46:57.85106
108	9	4	4	No'j					{"nawal": {"title": "The Earth's Intellect", "content": "No'j is the Nawal of the mind, knowledge, and the sacred science. It represents the intellect of the Earth—the patterns, the logic, and the wisdom that structures reality. No'j is the energy of the scholar, the planner, and the problem-solver. It transforms raw information into usable wisdom. In human experience, No'j manifests as clarity of thought, good ideas, and the urge to learn. It is the 'Aha!' moment. When aligned, No'j brings brilliant solutions and noble thoughts; when misaligned, it can lead to overthinking or arrogance.", "keywords": ["Wisdom", "Intellect", "Knowledge", "Planning", "Solutions"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cube of Stability", "content": "The number Four represents stability, definition, and the material world. It is the energy of the four cardinal directions, the four elements, and the four walls of a house. In Mayan cosmology, Four is the force that grounds spirit into form; it creates the container in which life can exist. Experientially, this energy feels solid, reliable, and sometimes a bit heavy. It is a day for building, organizing, and establishing boundaries. The shadow of Four can be rigidity or stagnation, but its light is the comfort of a secure foundation.", "keywords": ["Structure", "Balance", "Grounding", "Manifestation", "Stability"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create a detailed plan or schedule for a project.", "Organize your workspace or your files.", "Study a subject that requires logical structure (math, science, language).", "Solve a practical problem that has been bothering you.", "Ground your ideas by writing them down; make them physical."], "title": "The Architecture of Thought", "content": "When the structural stability of Tone 4 meets the intellectual power of No'j, we get a day of 'Grounded Wisdom.' 4 No'j is the architect. It is the energy of taking a brilliant idea and creating a solid blueprint for it. This is an exceptional day for planning, studying, or solving complex structural problems. The mind is sharp, logical, and practical. It is not a day for flighty fantasies; it is a day for concrete answers. If you have been struggling to understand how to make a dream reality, 4 No'j provides the mental framework to do it. The energy supports organizing your thoughts, your schedule, and your environment. It asks: Is your thinking sound? Is your plan stable? Use this day to build a foundation of knowledge that will support you for years to come. The earth's brain is open to you."}}	{"title": "The Practical Sage", "content": "To be born on 4 No'j is to be a builder of systems and a keeper of knowledge. You are the 'Stable Mind'—a soul who possesses a brilliant intellect that is firmly rooted in reality. You are not one for abstract theories unless they have a practical application. You love to learn how things work and to create structures that improve life. You are likely very organized, reliable, and the person others turn to when they need a logical solution to a chaotic problem.\\n\\nYour life path is one of materializing wisdom. You are here to take the great ideas of the cosmos (No'j) and build four walls around them (4) so they can live on earth. You may be drawn to architecture, engineering, teaching, or writing. Your challenge is to avoid becoming too rigid in your thinking or dismissing things that cannot be logically explained. You are here to show us that wisdom is the most solid foundation we can build upon."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a7b3cc", "primary": "#0d1216", "secondary": "#323a45"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.802285	2026-04-25 13:46:57.857262
110	9	6	6	Kawoq					{"nawal": {"title": "The Storm of Compassion", "content": "Kawoq is the Nawal of the storm, the turtle, and the midwife. It represents the family unit, community, and the chaotic but necessary energy that brings new life. Kawoq is the rain that nourishes the crops and the thunder that wakes us up. In human experience, Kawoq manifests as compassion, the drive to care for others, and the ability to weather emotional storms. It is the energy of the 'group' rather than the individual. When aligned, Kawoq brings abundance, renewal, and deep emotional cleansing; when misaligned, it can lead to overwhelm.", "keywords": ["Community", "Storm", "Compassion", "Rebirth", "Cleansing"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Harmony", "content": "The number Six represents the first point of true stability and flow in the cycle. It is the energy of the cube with a center, or the four directions plus the Above and Below. In Mayan cosmology, Six is the number of organic life and vital flow. Experientially, this energy feels gentle, rhythmic, and stabilizing. It is a day where things begin to click into place, and the struggle of the Five yields to a sustainable pace. The shadow of Six can be complacency, but its light is the grace of harmony.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Flow", "Stability", "Growth", "Rhythm"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Gather with your family or 'tribe' for a meal.", "Allow your emotions to flow without resistance.", "Support someone who is going through a 'rebirth' or transition.", "Create a safe, cozy space in your home (the turtle shell).", "Practice compassion for yourself and others; let go of judgment."], "title": "Flowing Compassion", "content": "The harmonious flow of Tone 6 meets the communal storm of Kawoq to create a day of 'Gentle Rain.' 6 Kawoq is the energy of the storm that has settled into a nourishing shower. It is a day of emotional stability within the family and community. The energy supports gathering together, sharing feelings, and supporting each other through changes. The 'midwife' energy of Kawoq is very strong but gentle today; it is a good day to birth a new idea or project, knowing that the environment is safe and supportive. If there has been turbulence in your relationships, 6 Kawoq offers the rhythm to smooth it out. It asks you to flow with the group, to be the calm center in the storm, and to offer your compassion freely. The turtle feels safe in its shell today. Let the rain wash away the dust."}}	{"title": "The Gentle Midwife", "content": "To be born on 6 Kawoq is to be a sanctuary in the storm. You are the 'Harmonious Guardian'—a soul who possesses a deep well of compassion and the stability to hold space for others. You are likely the glue that holds your family or community together. People flock to you when they are in crisis because you offer a calm, non-judgmental presence. You understand the chaos of birth and rebirth, but you meet it with the rhythmic grace of the number 6.\\n\\nYour life path is one of nurturing the collective. You are a natural caregiver, healer, or community organizer. You have the ability to take the intense energy of the storm (Kawoq) and channel it into a flow that nourishes rather than destroys. Your challenge is to maintain your own boundaries so that you don't get swept away by the needs of others. You are here to show us that even in the midst of change, there is a center of peace."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#74c9bd", "primary": "#101d1b", "secondary": "#355b56"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.803509	2026-04-25 13:46:57.859053
176	14	7	7	Aj					{"nawal": {"title": "The Pillar of Community", "content": "Aj is the cane, the cornstalk, and the pillar. It represents the spine, the home, and the authority of the lineage. Aj is the energy of the benevolent leader who supports the family and community. It signifies triumph and resurrection. It connects the earth to the sky.", "keywords": ["Home", "Authority", "Spine", "Corn", "Resurrection"]}, "number": {"title": "The Summit of Reflection", "content": "The number 7 represents the top of the pyramid, the midpoint of the cycle. It is a place of mystical power, equilibrium, and the ability to see both the past and future. 7 is a number of channeling and high magic. In the Kej trecena, 7 gives us a panoramic view of our home and our authority.", "keywords": ["Insight", "Clarity", "Reflection", "Mysticism", "Midpoint"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create a sacred space in your home.", "Meditate on your spine as a channel of light.", "Take a leadership role in your family with spiritual intent.", "Balance your work life and home life.", "Ask for flexibility in a rigid situation."], "title": "The Mystical Pillar", "content": "7 Aj is a day of high spiritual authority rooted in the home. Standing at the top of the pyramid, we connect with the cosmic pillar. In the Kej trecena, this represents the balance between our wild nature and our domestic life. It is a day to bring the sacred into the home. The energy is strong, flexible, and mystical. It asks us to be the spiritual leaders of our families and communities. We see the 'spine' of our life clearly—what holds us up? It is a day to align our earthly authority with divine will."}}	{"title": "The Spiritual Leader", "content": "To be born on 7 Aj is to be a conduit of divine authority. You possess a regal, upright energy that commands respect. You are the spiritual head of your household or community, whether you chose the role or not. You have a direct line to higher wisdom and a talent for bringing that wisdom down to earth. You are a pillar of strength, but you are also a mystic who understands the unseen worlds.\\n\\nYour life path is one of balancing power and service. You are here to support others, but you do so from a place of high alignment. You have a natural dignity and a strong sense of ethics. You are likely drawn to roles where you can protect and guide.\\n\\nYour challenge is the weight of the crown. You can feel responsible for everyone's spiritual well-being. You may also struggle with being too 'high up' to relate to everyday problems. Your lesson is to remain flexible like the reed. When you bend with the wind while keeping your roots deep, you become a bridge between heaven and earth, sheltering all who gather under your branches."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#cab070", "primary": "#111918", "secondary": "#45433a"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.842528	2026-04-25 13:46:57.954431
113	9	9	9	Iq'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Wind of Spirit", "content": "Iq' is the Nawal of the wind, the breath, and communication. It represents the vital spirit that animates all living things and the power of the spoken word. Iq' is the energy of inspiration, ideas, and the mind's agility. It clears the air, brings change, and carries messages from the divine. In human experience, Iq' manifests as intellect, curiosity, and a need for freedom. It is the voice that speaks the truth. When aligned, Iq' brings clarity and effective communication; when misaligned, it can lead to anger or fickleness.", "keywords": ["Breath", "Communication", "Wind", "Inspiration", "Change"]}, "number": {"title": "The Womb of Patience", "content": "The number Nine represents the completion of the developmental cycle, the gestation period (9 months), and the energy of the feminine. In Mayan cosmology, Nine is associated with the 'Primordial Female' and the deep, dark soil where the seed transforms. Experientially, this energy feels introspective, creative, and sometimes slow. It is the patience of the mother waiting for the birth. It is a time for nurturing, refining details, and preparing for the final manifestation. The shadow of Nine can be isolation, but its light is the profound power of life generating life.", "keywords": ["Patience", "Gestation", "Feminine", "Completion", "Nurturing"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Journal your inner thoughts; let them flow onto the page.", "Practice gentle breathwork to calm the mind.", "Have a heart-to-heart conversation with a female friend.", "Nurture a new idea; don't expose it to harsh criticism yet.", "Listen to the wind; it carries soft secrets today."], "title": "Gestating Inspiration", "content": "The feminine, nurturing energy of Tone 9 meets the windy spirit of Iq' to create a day of 'Whispered Wisdom.' 9 Iq' is the breath in the womb—the quiet inspiration that grows before it is spoken. It is a day to nurture your ideas and your words. The energy is not about shouting from the rooftops (that's more 1 or 8), but about the intimate, heartfelt communication that heals. It is a perfect day for writing, poetry, or having deep, soulful conversations with women or feminine figures in your life. The wind is gentle today, like a lullaby. It is a time to listen to the small, still voice within. If you have been working on a message or a creative project, let it incubate a little longer. Breathe life into it slowly. The spirit is moving, but it is moving with the patience of the earth."}}	{"title": "The Nurturing Voice", "content": "To be born on 9 Iq' is to be a keeper of sacred stories and a voice for the soul. You are the 'Patient Messenger'—someone who understands that true communication requires listening as much as speaking. You have a gift for words, but you use them to heal and nurture rather than to dominate. You are likely a writer, a poet, or a counselor, able to articulate the deepest feelings of the human heart. The number 9 gives you a feminine, gestating quality; you let ideas ripen before you share them.\\n\\nYour life path is one of breathing life into the world through your spirit. You may be more introverted than other Iq' signs, preferring deep one-on-one connections to large crowds. Your challenge is to trust your voice and not let your introspection silence you. The world needs the wisdom you have been growing in the quiet. You are the gentle breeze that brings the rain of new life."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d0c5d3", "primary": "#191f23", "secondary": "#5a5462"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.804147	2026-04-25 13:46:57.862823
84	7	6	6	Kame	The lake feels softer today.\n\nNot weak, not faded — simply softened, as if the edges of the world have rounded themselves. The path that brought you here feels smoother too, familiar beneath your feet. There is a rhythm to your steps, an ease that was not there before.\n\nWhen you reach the water, the surface is moving in slow, steady pulses. Not ripples. Not waves. Something deeper — as though the lake itself is breathing.\n\nYou watch the rise and fall of it, the gentle swell that expands outward and pulls back in. There is no urgency in it. No strain. Everything moves because movement is natural.\n\nA mist hangs low, drifting in a quiet spiral above the water. In the shifting air, you see faint shapes forming and dissolving — silhouettes of moments you’ve survived, choices that changed you, versions of yourself that no longer exist. They appear like shadows behind a curtain, soft and distant.\n\nYou do not feel fear. Only recognition.\n\nOne shape in particular draws your attention. It stands near the treeline, barely visible, its outline flickering like a candle behind frosted glass. You sense that it is not here to haunt you but to accompany you — one of the many selves you’ve been on your way to becoming.\n\nYou breathe in. The shape brightens. You breathe out. It recedes. Every rise and fall of your breath matches the slow rhythm of the lake.\n\nYou understand the message without hearing any words: nothing you’ve been through is wasted. Every ending has shaped you. Every loss has carved space for something new to live. The difficult chapters did not destroy you — they refined you.\n\nYou sit near the water and let your body settle into its own subtle tide. Thoughts that once felt heavy begin to move again, drifting without clinging. Emotions that once felt sharp soften at the edges.\n\nThe shape at the treeline tilts, almost like a nod, and then dissolves into the mist. Not gone — just integrated.\n\nYou rise slowly, feeling a quiet alignment in your bones. You are not finished changing, but some part of you has finally found its rhythm.	You are finding your rhythm today, whether you realize it or not. What once felt heavy now moves with a little more ease. What once felt tangled begins to loosen on its own. This is a day for letting things flow instead of forcing them.\n\nYour past may rise in small flashes — old memories, old versions of you, old fears — but only to show you how far you have come. You don’t need to relive anything or fix anything. Just notice the quiet shift from resistance to acceptance.\n\nLet your breath guide you. Let your steps be slow and deliberate. Let your energy organize itself around what feels true now, not what used to define you.	I move with the rhythm of my life, allowing old versions of myself to dissolve and new harmony to form.	Sit comfortably with your spine relaxed and your feet grounded. Close your eyes and imagine your breath as a soft tide rolling in and out.\n\nWith each inhale, see a gentle wave of light rise within you. With each exhale, let the wave fall, smoothing out tension in your body. As you breathe, picture faint silhouettes of past versions of yourself appearing in the mist — not to judge you, but to acknowledge how they shaped who you are.\n\nLet each silhouette dissolve on an exhale, leaving behind only the wisdom they carried. When you feel a steady rhythm inside you, offer a brief gratitude to the ancestors and elders who understood transformation as part of life’s ongoing flow.\n\nTake one more slow inhale and let the exhale guide you back into your day.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Transformer", "content": "Kame is the Nawal of death, rebirth, and the ancestors. It represents the only certainty in life: change. Kame is the energy that closes one door so another can open. It governs spiritual initiation, mediumship, and the courage to face the unknown. In human experience, Kame manifests as a connection to the spirit world, a talent for helping others through transitions, and deep inner strength. It is the peaceful rest after the struggle. When aligned, Kame brings profound transformation and ancestral protection; when misaligned, it can lead to fear of change or holding onto the past.", "keywords": ["Death", "Rebirth", "Ancestors", "Transformation", "Courage"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Harmony", "content": "The number Six represents the first point of true stability and flow in the cycle. It is the energy of the cube with a center, or the four directions plus the Above and Below. In Mayan cosmology, Six is the number of organic life and vital flow. Experientially, this energy feels gentle, rhythmic, and stabilizing. It is a day where things begin to click into place, and the struggle of the Five yields to a sustainable pace. The shadow of Six can be complacency, but its light is the grace of harmony.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Flow", "Stability", "Growth", "Rhythm"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Visit an ancestor's grave or light a candle for them.", "Accept a change that is happening in your life with grace.", "Practice 'ego death' through meditation or service.", "Allow your emotions to flow; do not dam the river.", "Trust that every ending is a necessary part of the harmony."], "title": "Flowing Transformation", "content": "The harmonious flow of Tone 6 meets the transformative power of Kame to create a day of 'Peaceful Change.' 6 Kame is the soft side of death/rebirth. It suggests that transformation does not have to be a violent struggle; it can be a natural, rhythmic process, like leaves falling in autumn. Today is an excellent day to connect with your ancestors and ask for their guidance in your life's transitions. The energy is supportive of letting go. Whatever is dying in your life—a habit, a relationship, a belief—let it go gently today. The number 6 provides a stable container for this process, ensuring you feel safe even as you change. It is a day to trust the cycle of life. Share your grief or your growth with family; the energy favors collective processing of the mysteries. Death is just a breath between lives."}}	{"title": "The Ancestral Bridge", "content": "To be born on 6 Kame is to be a gentle guide through the mysteries of life and death. You are the 'Harmonic Transformer'—a soul who understands that change is the natural rhythm of the universe. You likely have a strong connection to your ancestors and may possess mediumistic abilities or a deep intuition about the spirit world. People feel safe with you during their darkest times because you carry an air of peaceful acceptance. You are the calm presence at the funeral and the joyful midwfe at the birth.\\n\\nYour life path is one of facilitating transitions. You help people (and yourself) move from one state of being to another with grace. The number 6 gives you a loving, family-oriented nature, softening the sometimes stark energy of Kame. Your challenge is to ensure that you do not become absorbed by the grief of others, but rather serve as a stable bridge for them to cross. You are here to teach us that death is not the opposite of life, but a part of it."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d7ceae", "primary": "#1e1e17", "secondary": "#705c42"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.786149	2026-04-25 13:46:57.778825
92	8	1	1	Iq'	You stand on the first floating island, a small disc of white stone hovering in the blue. The air is still, but charged with potential, like the moment before a conductor raises a baton.\n\nIn the center of the platform stands a single, crystalline wind chime, taller than you. It hangs from nothing, suspended in the air. Its tubes are made of glass so clear they are almost invisible, etched with symbols that seem to shift when you look away.\n\nIt is silent.\n\nYou approach it, feeling the static electricity prickle on your skin. You understand that this chime is the tuning fork for the entire trecena. It cannot ring itself. It needs a catalyst.\n\nIt needs breath.\n\nYou stand before the chime. You realize how shallow your breathing usually is—short sips of air, just enough to survive. Here, that is not enough. To move the glass, you must breathe from the root of your being.\n\nYou inhale. You pull the air down past your throat, past your chest, into your belly. You feel your lungs expand, pushing against your ribs. You hold it for a second, feeling the oxygen race through your blood.\n\nThen, you exhale. You blow a steady, focused stream of air toward the chime.\n\nThe glass shivers. Slowly, one tube swings and strikes another.\n\n*Cling.*\n\nThe sound is pure and piercing. It vibrates through the platform, through the soles of your feet, and straight into the center of your skull. It clears the fog in your mind instantly.\n\nThe vibration triggers a chain reaction. A breeze kicks up from nowhere, swirling around the platform. The mist clears, revealing a path of floating stones stretching out into the clouds.\n\nYou have initiated the cycle. You have proven that your breath has power.\n\nThe wind is awake now. It tugs at your clothes, playful and insistent. It wants to show you where the sound goes.	The air is electric today. Can you feel it? A new idea or a fresh perspective is trying to get your attention. It might come as a whisper, or it might come as a sudden gust that messes up your hair.\n\nDon’t close the window. The energy of 1 Iq’ is pure inspiration. If you have been feeling stale or stuck, today is the day to breathe. Speak up. Your voice has a magical quality to it right now—use it to call in what you want.	I breathe in inspiration and breathe out my truth with clarity.	Sit comfortably. Close your eyes. Focus entirely on the tip of your nose. Feel the cool air entering. Feel the warm air leaving.\n\nVisualize the air as bright blue light. Inhale the light; let it fill your head, clearing away grey thoughts. Exhale the grey smoke. Do this until your mind feels as clear as a blue sky.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Wind of Life", "content": "Iq' is the Nawal of the wind, the breath, and communication. It represents the vital spirit that animates all living things and the power of the spoken word. Iq' is the energy of inspiration, ideas, and the mind's agility. It clears the air, brings change, and carries messages from the divine. In human experience, Iq' manifests as intellect, curiosity, and a need for freedom. It is the voice that speaks the truth. When aligned, Iq' brings clarity and effective communication; when misaligned, it can lead to anger, fickleness, or destructive outbursts. It is the breath that sustains us, the invisible force that moves the trees.", "keywords": ["Breath", "Communication", "Wind", "Inspiration", "Change"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Spirit", "content": "The number One represents the primordial spark, the moment of inception, and the unity of all things. It is the seed that contains the entire blueprint of the future within its tiny shell. In Mayan cosmology, One is the energy of initiation and firm beginnings; it is not merely a start, but a powerful concentration of potential that requires focus and intent. Experientially, this energy feels like a surge of inspiration or a sudden clarity of purpose. It asks you to stand alone if necessary, to be the single point of origin for a new cycle. The shadow of One can be isolation or a failure to launch due to the overwhelming weight of potential, but its light is the unstoppable force of creation itself. Today, you are the breath that starts the song.", "keywords": ["Beginnings", "Unity", "Seed", "Potential", "Focus"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Start a journal or blog; put your words into the world.", "Practice deep breathing exercises to center your spirit.", "Initiate a conversation you have been waiting to have.", "Set an intention for how you want to communicate in this cycle.", "Allow yourself to change your mind; the wind is never static."], "title": "Initiating the Breath", "content": "When the initiating spark of Tone 1 meets the communicative power of Iq', we stand at the beginning of a cycle of inspiration. 1 Iq' is the 'First Breath' of creation. It is the ideal day to launch a new idea, start a conversation, or breathe life into a project that has been stagnant. The energy is fresh, airy, and full of potential. Unlike the heavy water of Imox, Iq' is swift and mental. You may feel a rush of new thoughts or a sudden urge to speak your truth. This trecena will focus on communication, spirit, and connection, and today sets the tone. Be mindful of the words you speak today, as they carry the weight of a seed; what you say now will grow over the next 13 days. It is a day to clear your mind, open the windows, and let the spirit move through you. The wind is at your back; lift your sails."}}	{"title": "The Inspired Messenger", "content": "To be born on 1 Iq' is to be a voice for the spirit. You are the 'Primal Breath'—a soul who embodies the raw power of inspiration and communication. You likely have a quick mind and a restless spirit, always seeking new ideas and fresh perspectives. You are a natural initiator, often the first to speak up or the first to try a new path. Your presence is like a fresh breeze that wakes people up and clears the cobwebs from their minds.\\n\\nYour life path is one of mastering the power of the word. With the number 1, you have a strong sense of individuality and purpose. You are not here to echo others; you are here to say something new. However, the volatility of the wind can sometimes make you fickle or prone to sudden changes of heart. Your challenge is to ground your inspiration so that it doesn't just blow away. You are here to breathe life into the world, reminding us that spirit is always moving, always speaking."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#e2d9e4", "primary": "#13191b", "secondary": "#48434d"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#99b8c6", "primary": "#0a1224", "secondary": "#395775"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#e2eff4", "primary": "#93c2db", "secondary": "#bfdde9"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#a0ced7", "primary": "#072f46", "secondary": "#29748e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.794172	2026-04-25 13:46:57.785984
116	9	12	12	Kan					{"nawal": {"title": "The Serpent's Fire", "content": "Kan is the Nawal of the Serpent, the vital life force (Kundalini), and wisdom. It represents the energy of evolution, sexuality, and the DNA spiral. Kan is the power that moves up the spine and brings enlightenment or transformation. In human experience, Kan manifests as charisma, physical strength, and a drive for justice and truth. It is the teacher and the student. When aligned, Kan brings vitality, passion, and deep wisdom; when misaligned, it can lead to manipulation or misuse of power. It is the fire in the blood.", "keywords": ["Vitality", "Power", "Wisdom", "Transformation", "Sexuality"]}, "number": {"title": "The Crystal of Understanding", "content": "The number Twelve represents the grouping together, the village, and the understanding that comes from retrospection. In Mayan cosmology, Twelve is the energy of the 'Great Gathering.' It stabilizes the chaos of Eleven and integrates the lessons learned. Experientially, this energy feels inclusive, cooperative, and wise. It is a day to summarize, to discuss, and to connect the dots. The shadow of Twelve can be difficulty with individuality, but its light is the strength of the collective mind. Today, the universe holds a council.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Integration", "Cooperation", "Review", "Community"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Attend a class, workshop, or group discussion.", "Share a life lesson or a piece of wisdom with friends.", "Engage in physical activity with others to raise the collective energy.", "Reflect on the teachers who have shaped your path.", "Honor the 'body' of your community."], "title": "Collective Wisdom", "content": "When the integrative understanding of Tone 12 meets the potent wisdom of Kan, we arrive at a day of 'Shared Power.' 12 Kan is the gathering of the teachers. It represents the wisdom that is held not by one individual, but by the community. It is a day to share knowledge, to teach and to learn, and to pool our vital resources. The energy is electric but contained, like a circle of people holding hands. It supports discussions about justice, truth, and the evolution of the group. If you have been learning a lesson alone, today is the day to bring it to the village. The serpent of wisdom weaves through the collective, connecting us all. It is also a powerful day for group physical activities—yoga classes, team sports, or dance. Feel the strength of the many. We are evolving together."}}	{"title": "The Wise Teacher", "content": "To be born on 12 Kan is to be a keeper of the collective fire. You are the 'Village Sage'—a soul who possesses deep wisdom and vitality, and who feels a responsibility to share it with others. You are likely a natural teacher, mentor, or coach, with a charisma that draws people in. You understand that true power is not about dominance, but about empowering the whole. You have a strong sense of justice and will stand up for the community when it is threatened.\\n\\nYour life path is one of integrating knowledge and experience. The number 12 gives you a cooperative nature; you don't want to be the guru on the mountain, you want to be in the circle. Your challenge is to manage your intense energy so that it warms the village without burning it down. You are here to remind us that we are all students and we are all teachers, linked by the same life force."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c8a08d", "primary": "#121a19", "secondary": "#584642"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.804616	2026-04-25 13:46:57.852817
121	10	4	4	Toj					{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Fire", "content": "Toj is the energy of offering, payment, and reciprocity. It is the sacred fire that transmutes matter into spirit. Toj represents the law of cause and effect (karma) and the necessity of giving back to maintain universal balance. It is the day to pay spiritual debts, to offer gratitude, and to sacrifice the ego for the greater good. Toj reminds us that nothing is free; everything requires an exchange of energy. It is the warmth of the hearth and the heat of the fever that burns away illness.", "keywords": ["Offering", "Payment", "Reciprocity", "Fire", "Gratitude"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cube of Stability", "content": "The number 4 brings form, definition, and stability to the flow of creation. It represents the four directions, the four elements, and the solid foundation of the physical world. After the movement of 3, 4 grounds the energy, creating a container or a structure where life can reside. It is the energy of the builder, the organizer, and the stabilizer. It offers a pause to assess, measure, and establish a firm footing before moving forward.", "keywords": ["Stability", "Structure", "Four Directions", "Foundation", "Definition"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Build or clean your physical altar today.", "Make a donation or offer service to balance a past kindness.", "Sit facing the four directions and offer gratitude to each.", "Burn a list of old grievances safely, letting the fire transmute them.", "Create a stable routine for your spiritual practice."], "title": "Grounding the Offering", "content": "4 Toj establishes a stable foundation for our transformation through the act of gratitude. In the Kame trecena, where we are navigating death and rebirth, 4 Toj teaches us that the new life must be built on a foundation of reciprocity. We cannot simply take the new; we must pay for it by releasing the old and offering thanks. Today is a day to stabilize your spiritual debts. It is a time to create a physical altar, to make a concrete gesture of thanks, and to ground your prayers in the physical world. The stability of the 4 combined with the fire of Toj creates a 'hearth' energy—a safe place to burn away what is no longer needed."}}	{"title": "The Keeper of the Hearth", "content": "To be born on 4 Toj is to be a pillar of spiritual and emotional stability for your community. You carry the energy of the sacred fire contained within a well-built hearth. You are naturally generous, understanding implicitly that life is a cycle of giving and receiving. People are drawn to you for your warmth and your grounded presence; you are the one who remembers the birthdays, who organizes the gatherings, and who ensures that everyone is fed and cared for.\\n\\nYour life is often dedicated to service or the balancing of accounts—whether financial, emotional, or karmic. You have a strong sense of duty and a deep need to feel that you are 'square' with the house of life. You may find yourself in roles where you are managing resources or facilitating healing for others. You possess a great endurance and the ability to sustain effort over long periods, much like a fire that is well-tended.\\n\\nYour challenge lies in the potential for martyrdom or feeling overburdened by the debts of others. Because you are so willing to give, you must learn the boundary of the 4—to create structures that protect your own energy. You cannot pay everyone's way. Your highest evolution comes when you realize that your own well-being is also an offering to the divine. When you balance your giving with receiving, you become a stable, warming light that sustains the world without burning yourself out."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d4b48d", "primary": "#121615", "secondary": "#514138"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.806448	2026-04-25 13:46:57.874588
143	11	13	13	No'j	The Spire reaches its ultimate conclusion. You climb the final, translucent vine until it dissolves into pure, shimmering thought. There is no more bark to grip, no more moss to tread; you have ascended into the Crown of the Spire, where the physical world merges with the Universal Mind. The serpent power—the raw, electric Kan energy that started at the base of your spine—reaches the top of your skull and opens its wings. In an explosion of visionary clarity, the puzzle of your life is solved. You understand the master plan, seeing the logic and philosophy that binds the stars to the roots. Your human intelligence harmonizes with the divine mind of the earth, transforming information into eternal wisdom. You are no longer the traveler; you are the knowledge itself. The cycle is complete, the ascension is total, and your thoughts go out like prayers of light into the infinite sky.	The climb is finally over, and the physical world has begun to dissolve into pure, shimmering thought at the very crown of the universe. The serpent power that started as a low pulse in your blood thirteen days ago has finally reached the peak of your skull and opened its wings of light. You are standing in the cosmic library today, a place where your individual story merges with the infinite intelligence of the stars. \n\nThe puzzle of your life is solved, and the master plan is visible in all its terrifying beauty. You aren't just learning wisdom anymore; you have become the wisdom itself. The logic that binds the roots to the galaxies is coursing through your mind, turning every bit of information you’ve gathered into eternal, usable knowledge. \n\nLet your thoughts go out into the infinite sky like prayers of light, blessing the world you left below. You have ascended beyond the need for handholds. You are complete, you are illuminated, and you are home. The stars have been waiting for you to arrive and remember your true name among the constellations.	My serpent power has taken flight, transforming my vital force into pure, soaring intelligence.	Close your eyes and imagine the energy at the base of your spine rising all the way to the top of your head. Feel your mind expand to connect with the infinite intelligence of the universe. \n\nOptionally, stand at the Crown of the Spire as the last vine dissolves into pure white and ultraviolet thought, your serpent power opening its wings of cosmic wisdom.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Universal Mind", "content": "No'j is the energy of the brain, the intellect, and wisdom. It represents the power of thought to shape reality. No'j is the connection to the universal mind and the capacity for logic, science, and philosophy. It is the earth shaking with the power of an idea. No'j transforms raw information into usable knowledge. It asks us to think clearly, to plan, and to harmonize our human intelligence with the wisdom of the earth.", "keywords": ["Wisdom", "Intellect", "Knowledge", "Thought", "Earth"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascension of Spirit", "content": "The number 13 represents completion, ascension, and the spirit world. It is the final step of the wave, where the energy transcends the physical form and returns to the source. 13 is a number of great power, sensitivity, and psychic expansion. It is not just an ending, but an elevation. It allows us to see the entire cycle from the perspective of the ancestors. It brings the unexpected, the miraculous, and the touch of the divine.", "keywords": ["Ascension", "Completion", "Spirit", "Ancestors", "Renewal"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Meditate on a question you have been struggling with; the answer is near.", "Write down your 'thesis statement' for your life right now.", "Connect with the element of air and the vastness of the sky.", "Thank your mind for its service, but let it rest in the heart.", "Celebrate the completion of the cycle with a moment of silence."], "title": "Ascending into Universal Wisdom", "content": "13 No'j is the grand culmination of the Kan trecena. The cycle of vital force and evolution leads us here: to the expansion of the mind into cosmic consciousness. Today, our human intelligence connects with the divine mind. It is a day of breakthroughs, epiphanies, and visionary clarity. The power we have cultivated (Kan) has transformed into wisdom (No'j). We see the solution to the puzzle. We understand the master plan. It is a day to honor the intellect as a sacred tool and to send our thoughts out as prayers for the collective evolution. The serpent has coiled all the way up the spine and opened the wings of the mind."}}	{"title": "The Cosmic Philosopher", "content": "To be born on 13 No'j is to be a keeper of the cosmic library. You possess an intellect that is not just sharp, but transcendent. You are connected to the universal mind, often receiving downloads of information or ideas that are ahead of your time. You are a visionary thinker, a scientist of the soul, and a natural teacher. You have the ability to understand the most complex systems of the universe and translate them into language that others can understand.\\n\\nYour life path is one of expanding human consciousness. You are here to bridge the gap between science and spirituality, between logic and intuition. You are a problem-solver on a global or even cosmic scale. You carry the energy of the ancestors' wisdom raised to its highest octave. You are likely drawn to philosophy, technology, or ancient wisdom traditions.\\n\\nYour challenge is to stay connected to the human experience. You can live so much in your head or in the spirit world that you forget to eat, sleep, or relate to people on an emotional level. You may also feel overwhelmed by the noise of the world's thoughts. Your lesson is to ground your cosmic wisdom in the earth. When you use your brilliant mind to serve the heart of humanity, you become a true luminary, lighting the way for the collective evolution."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b2c3ce", "primary": "#0f181c", "secondary": "#3b454d"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.812623	2026-04-25 14:38:01.318449
132	11	2	2	Kame	As the climb becomes steeper, the air grows thin and cool, smelling of rain and ancient dust. Hanging from the spiraling branches above are the Ghost-Skins—translucent, hollow husks left behind by the Spire’s previous inhabitants, and perhaps, by versions of yourself you no longer recognize. They sway in the updrafts like tattered silken banners, whistling a low, mournful tune as the wind passes through their empty chest cavities. To move higher, you must navigate this vertical graveyard, your fingers brushing against the brittle remains of old identities.\n\nEach skin you touch sparks a flicker of memory: a fear you once held, a name you no longer answer to, a path you chose not to take. Kame demands a reckoning with duality—the tension between the living pulse in your veins and the necessary deaths that paved your way. You do not climb alone; you climb upon the shed layers of your own history. Instead of recoiling, you find a strange peace in the silence of these husks. They are not failures; they are the evidence of your evolution. You realize that in the Spire, nothing is truly lost, only transformed into the scaffolding for the next ascent. With a breath of gratitude for the 'you' that died so the 'you' of today could live, you pull yourself onto a higher ledge, leaving the rattling chorus of the past below.	Today, you find yourself walking through a gallery of your own echoes, where the walls are draped with the translucent, silken skins of the people you used to be. It might feel like a graveyard at first glance, but if you listen closely, it is actually a library of profound growth. These hollow husks are whistling a low, melodic song of gratitude as you pass, thanking you for having the courage to finally outgrow them. \n\nDo not turn away from the versions of yourself that had to wither or 'die' to make this current journey possible. They are not failures or embarrassments to be hidden; they are the essential scaffolding of your soul, the rungs of a ladder you’ve already climbed. There is a deep peace in acknowledging that you can no longer fit back into those old shapes. \n\nReach out in your mind and touch the memory of a former fear—something that used to keep you awake at night. Notice how thin, brittle, and harmless it has become in the light of your current power. Today is about the beauty of the shedding process. You are lighter now, more agile, and ready for the next level. Honor the hulls you’ve left behind, then keep moving upward into the light that waits above the canopy.	I honor the wisdom of my ancestors and release the old stories that no longer serve my growth.	Find a quiet space and close your eyes. Reflect on a part of your life that is coming to an end, holding it with gentleness and gratitude. Breathe into the space that remains, trusting that every ending is fertile ground for new growth. \n\nOptionally, visualize yourself walking through a forest of hanging ghost-skins, hearing the wind whistle through the empty silken husks of your past versions.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Transformer", "content": "Kame is the energy of death, rebirth, and the ancestral realms. It is the great equalizer and the peace that follows necessary endings. Far from being frightening, Kame is the benevolent force that clears away stagnation so that life can renew itself. It connects us to the wisdom of those who walked before us and offers the spiritual protection needed to traverse dark passages. It is the owl that sees in the dark.", "keywords": ["Rebirth", "Ancestors", "Transformation", "Endings", "Courage"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "The number 2 represents polarity, relationship, and the dynamic tension between opposites. It is the separation of the one into the many, creating the space for interaction. This energy governs partnerships, choices, and the reflection we see in others. It brings the challenge of balance—navigating between light and dark, male and female, self and other. In the cycle of 13, it is the reaction to the initial impulse, where the seed meets the soil.", "keywords": ["Duality", "Partnership", "Reflection", "Choice", "Balance"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Light a candle for a loved one who has passed.", "Reflect on a relationship that needs to change or end.", "Find the balance between grief and gratitude.", "Ask your ancestors for guidance on a difficult choice.", "Declutter a physical space to invite new energy."], "title": "Balancing Life and Death", "content": "2 Kame brings the theme of relationship into the realm of deep transformation. Following the vital spark of 1 Kan, today we encounter the necessity of letting go to make room for that growth. The energy is about the balance between holding on and releasing. It asks us to look at our relationships with the ancestors and with the cycles of change. Are you resisting the natural endings in your life? Today offers a gentle but firm hand to help you release what is dead. It is a day to find harmony in the impermanence of things, understanding that every death nurtures a new life."}}	{"title": "The Bridge Between Worlds", "content": "To be born on 2 Kame is to be a diplomat of the soul, standing comfortably between the visible and invisible worlds. You possess a sensitive, dual nature that understands both the joy of life and the sanctity of death. You are a natural medium, counselor, or bridge-builder, able to help others navigate their own transitions with grace. Your presence is calming; you are the one people call during a crisis because you do not fear the dark.\\n\\nYour life path involves mastering the art of letting go. You may find that your relationships are the primary arena for your spiritual growth. You learn deeply through partnership, and you often attract people who are going through profound transformations. You are a 'midwife' for the soul, helping to birth new versions of people and projects. You have a deep respect for history and lineage, often carrying on the work of your ancestors.\\n\\nYour challenge is to not get stuck in the grief or the heaviness of others. Because you feel the duality of life so keenly, you can sometimes struggle with decision-making or mood fluctuations. Your lesson is to trust that the cycle always turns toward the light. When you balance your sensitivity with your inner strength, you become a powerful healer who teaches the world that death is not an end, but a necessary and beautiful part of the eternal dance."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b5a7ac", "primary": "#111312", "secondary": "#423d3f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.809234	2026-04-25 14:38:01.307552
55	5	3	3	Aj					{"nawal": {"title": "The Pillar of Integrity", "content": "Aj is the Nawal of the home, the cane, and the spinal column. It represents the principle of authority, leadership, and the upright growth of the cornstalk. Aj is the energy of the pillar that holds up the roof—it is strong, yet flexible enough to bend in the wind without breaking. It governs the home, the family, and the community, emphasizing harmony, ethics, and protection. In human experience, Aj manifests as the desire to build a safe container for life to flourish. It is the archetype of the benevolent leader or the wise parent. When aligned, Aj brings peace, stability, and a deep sense of belonging; when misaligned, it can lead to rigidity, authoritarianism, or a refusal to adapt. It is the staff of life that supports the weary.", "keywords": ["Home", "Leadership", "Harmony", "Community", "Integrity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Movement", "content": "The number Three introduces movement, rhythm, and flow into the equation. If One is the point and Two is the line, Three is the triangle that creates stability through dynamism. In Mayan numerology, Three represents the pulse of life—the heartbeat, the breath, and the natural oscillation of energy. It is associated with the arts, communication, and the visible expression of inner reality. Experientially, this energy feels active and sometimes restless; it pushes things forward and breaks stagnation. It is the energy of 'doing' rather than just 'being.' The shadow of Three can be scattered energy or instability, but its light is the joy of unimpeded expression. Today, the universe is humming, and it asks you to move with it.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Expression", "Energy", "Rhythm", "Instability"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in physical activity that focuses on the spine and posture (yoga, pilates).", "Take active steps to improve your home environment or family relationships.", "Express your authority gently but firmly; leading by example is favored today.", "If tension arises, be the flexible cane—bend rather than break.", "Communicate your boundaries clearly; 3 gives voice to the structure of Aj."], "title": "Active Leadership", "content": "The combination of Tone 3's movement with the stabilizing energy of Aj creates a day of 'Dynamic Stability.' This is not a day for sitting still in the house; it is a day for actively working on the home, the community, or your own internal structure. The energy supports putting your authority into motion—walking your talk and demonstrating your values through action. It is an excellent time for renovations, both literal and metaphorical. You might feel a drive to reorganize your living space or to address a family dynamic that has become stagnant. 3 Aj suggests that true stability comes from flexibility and rhythm, like a bamboo forest swaying in the wind. The leadership required today is not about issuing commands from a throne, but about circulating among the people (or the parts of yourself) to ensure harmony is maintained through connection. Move your body to strengthen your spine; move your furniture to clear the energy."}}	{"title": "The Dynamic Pillar", "content": "To be born on 3 Aj is to be a source of strength that is never static. You are the 'Dancing Pillar'—someone who upholds tradition and family values but expresses them with unique flair and adaptability. You likely have a strong presence in your community or family, serving as a hub of activity and support. Unlike the stoic silence often associated with authority, your leadership style is communicative, expressive, and full of life. You are the parent who plays on the floor with the kids, or the boss who works alongside the team.\\n\\nYour gift is the ability to bring stability to chaotic situations through your own rhythmic adaptability. You intuitively understand that a home or a system needs to breathe and move to survive. However, the restlessness of the number 3 can sometimes conflict with the desire for settlement inherent in Aj, leading to a feeling of being torn between adventure and domesticity. Your soul's task is to find the adventure within the foundation—to build a life that is solid enough to hold you but spacious enough to let you dance."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a9ac6c", "primary": "#0f1816", "secondary": "#3d4536"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.76895	2026-04-25 13:46:57.738827
153	12	10	10	Aj	The spiral path lands you on the floor of the canyon. Here, the ground is flat and fertile. The nets above filter the sunlight into a golden cathedral light.\n\nIn the center of the valley stands a village of silos. They are tall, woven structures shaped like cornstalks, filled with the "harvest" that fell through the nets above. But this is not debris. This is compost. This is grain.\n\n10 is Manifestation and Community. Aj is the Staff and the Home. Today, the gathering finds a home.\n\nYou walk among the silos. You see people (or spirits) working together. They are taking the fallen bundles—the old dreams, the broken promises, the finished lessons—and grinding them down. They are turning them into soil.\n\nYou realize that K’at is not just about catching things; it is about gathering resources to build a home. The "clutter" of your life is actually the bricks and mortar of your wisdom.\n\nYou find a spot in the village. You plant your staff (Aj) into the ground. It takes root instantly. Walls rise up around it—not walls of stone, but walls of woven light.\n\nYou have built a home in the middle of the canyon. You are no longer just a traveler passing through the net; you are the keeper of the abundance.\n\nYou sit in your new house. It is filled with the things you decided to keep on Day 1. But now they are organized. They are honored. They are yours.\n\nYou are stable. You are abundant. You are home.	You are building something lasting today. The energy of 10 Aj is about stability, home, and legacy. All the sorting and gathering you’ve been doing is finally taking shape.\n\nLook around your life. Who is your village? What is your foundation? Strengthen those things today. You have gathered enough wisdom to build a house that will stand the test of time. Be the pillar.	I build my life on a foundation of wisdom, supported by my community.	Visualize yourself building a house. But the bricks are made of golden light (your wisdom). \n\nSee the walls rising. See the roof providing shelter. Invite your loved ones inside. Feel the warmth of the hearth. You are safe and supported.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Pillar of Community", "content": "Aj is the cane, the cornstalk, and the pillar. It represents the spine, the home, and the authority of the lineage. Aj is the energy of the benevolent leader who supports the family and community. It signifies triumph and resurrection. It connects the earth to the sky and represents the sanctity of the home space.", "keywords": ["Home", "Authority", "Spine", "Corn", "Resurrection"]}, "number": {"title": "The Wheel of Manifestation", "content": "The number 10 represents manifestation, responsibility, and the hands coming together. It signifies the agreement of community and the crystallization of intention into form. 10 brings a sense of weight and solidity. In the K'at trecena, 10 is the day the net is full. The harvest is brought in, measured, and made real. It is the realization of abundance in the physical world.", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Community", "Agreement", "Results"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Host a community gathering or a family dinner.", "Make a physical improvement to your home.", "Take on a leadership role with responsibility and grace.", "Stand tall; align your spine with the axis of the earth.", "Acknowledge the support system that allows you to thrive."], "title": "Manifesting the Sanctuary", "content": "10 Aj is a day of solid, tangible achievement within the community and home. The manifesting power of the 10 combines with the authority of Aj to create a pillar of strength. Today, the abundance of the K'at trecena is brought home. It is a day to celebrate the harvest with your family, to strengthen the foundations of your house, and to take responsibility for your role in the community. The energy is stable, authoritative, and protective. We realize that our connections (K'at) have built a home (Aj). It is a time to stand tall in your accomplishments and to share your corn with those you love."}}	{"title": "The Manifest Leader", "content": "To be born on 10 Aj is to be a cornerstone of society. You possess a natural authority and a gift for building lasting structures—whether families, businesses, or communities. You are the person who gets things done, who ensures that the corn grows and the roof holds. You have a strong sense of duty and a deep connection to tradition. People look to you for stability and direction because you embody the values you preach.\\n\\nYour life path is one of responsible leadership. You are a manifestor; your ideas don't stay in your head, they become brick and mortar. You are deeply connected to the home and may find your greatest joy in cultivating a sanctuary for others. You are resilient, able to rise again and again like the corn.\\n\\nYour challenge is rigidity. You can be so focused on maintaining the structure that you lose flexibility. You may also carry the weight of the world on your shoulders. Your lesson is to lead with a gentle hand. When you combine your strength with the flexibility of the reed, you become a truly great leader—one who supports the world without controlling it."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d7bd79", "primary": "#1d1a16", "secondary": "#775734"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.830916	2026-04-25 13:46:57.903109
122	10	5	5	Tz'i'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Guide of Law", "content": "Tz'i' is the energy of spiritual law, justice, and authority. It is the dog, the loyal companion, and the guide who leads the soul through the dark. Tz'i' represents fidelity, accuracy, and the instinct for truth. It is the scribe who records the deeds of life and the guardian who protects the natural order. While it can be associated with courts and legal matters, its deeper meaning is the internal compass that points toward integrity and unconditional love.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Law", "Loyalty", "Truth", "Guidance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Power", "content": "The number 5 represents empowerment, work, and the human hand (five fingers). It is the energy of doing, gathering, and applying will to the structures created by the 4. 5 breaks the stability of the 4 to put things into motion through effort. It is the center point of the single digits (1-9), representing a gathering of resources and the intelligent application of energy. It is a number of work, investigation, and the practical implementation of ideas.", "keywords": ["Empowerment", "Work", "Effort", "Center", "Investigation"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Review your personal 'laws' or rules for living; do they still serve you?", "Take concrete action on a legal or bureaucratic matter.", "Practice discipline in a small area of life (diet, schedule, speech).", "Show loyalty to a friend or cause through a tangible act of service.", "Investigate a truth you have been avoiding; shine the light on it."], "title": "Empowering the Truth", "content": "5 Tz'i' brings a surge of energy to the quest for truth and justice. In the cycle of transformation, this day asks us to do the work of aligning with our integrity. It is not enough to simply wish for a new life; we must actively lay down the law of our own existence. Today supports the investigation of our habits and the application of discipline to correct our course. It is a powerful day to stand up for what is right, to work on legal or administrative matters, and to let your loyalty to your soul's path override the temptation to stray. The 'death' of the old self requires the hard work of building a new code of conduct."}}	{"title": "The Worker of Justice", "content": "To be born on 5 Tz'i' is to be a tireless champion of truth and a diligent worker for the greater good. You possess a powerful combination of high ideals and the practical drive to implement them. You are not satisfied with abstract concepts of justice; you want to see them enacted in the real world. You are likely the person who rolls up their sleeves to fix the problem while others are still discussing it. Your loyalty is fierce, and once you commit to a person or a cause, you are unwavering.\\n\\nYour life path is often marked by a search for authority—first external, then internal. You may find yourself in roles involving law, administration, writing, or guidance. You have a natural instinct for order and a sharp eye for inaccuracy or dishonesty. You are a 'fixer' of broken systems and a faithful guide for those who are lost. Your energy is investigative; you love to dig until you find the core of the matter.\\n\\nYour challenge is to avoid becoming rigid or overly critical. The desire for perfection (the Law) combined with the drive to work (the 5) can lead to judgment of self and others. You must learn that true justice includes mercy. When you soften your approach and lead with the unconditional love that is the higher octave of Tz'i', you become a beacon of integrity who empowers others to trust their own moral compass."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#aabecc", "primary": "#111b1c", "secondary": "#394751"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.806616	2026-04-25 13:46:57.875762
152	12	9	9	E'	You exit the cavern and find a Path carved into the side of the cliff. It winds downwards, spiraling toward the canyon floor. The amber light is softer here, filtered through the layers of nets above.\n\nThis is the Spiral of Destiny.\n\n9 is Gestation and the Feminine. E’ is the Path. Today, the journey goes inward.\n\nYou walk the path. It is not a straight road; it curves, circles back, and descends. You realize that you are not just walking across the canyon; you are walking down into the history of your own gathering.\n\nAs you descend, you pass layers of the canyon wall. Each layer holds fossils of your past—old versions of you trapped in the stone. You see the child who gathered stones. The teenager who gathered secrets. The adult who gathered responsibilities.\n\nYou look at them with compassion. They were doing their best to build a net that would catch happiness.\n\nThe path hums with a low vibration. It is the song of the road. It tells you that you are not lost. The spiral is a shape of growth. You circle the same mountains, but at a different level each time.\n\nYou reach a resting point halfway down. A small shrine is cut into the rock. Inside is a footprint carved in jade. You place your foot in it. It fits.\n\nYou realize this path was made for you. You are not wandering aimlessly through the clutter. You are on a pilgrimage to the center of your own abundance.	You are on the right path, even if it feels like you are going in circles. The energy of 9 E’ is a spiral. You are revisiting old lessons, but from a higher perspective. \n\nBe patient with yourself. You are birthing a new version of your life, and that takes time. Trust the road. It knows the way, even when you don’t.	I trust the spiral of my journey, knowing every step leads me closer to my truth.	Visualize a spiral staircase going down into a beautiful, warm cave. Walk down it slowly.\n\nWith each step, you go deeper into yourself. Past the noise, past the worry. At the bottom is a glowing jade stone. Stand on it. Feel the grounding energy of your destiny.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Path of Destiny", "content": "E' is the energy of the road, the journey, and the spiritual path. It is the tooth that bites through obstacles and the feet that walk the miles. E' governs travel, exploration, and the experience of the journey itself. It asks us to trust the road, even when it is foggy, and to gain wisdom through movement.", "keywords": ["Path", "Journey", "Exploration", "Destiny", "Guide"]}, "number": {"title": "The Circle of Life", "content": "The number 9 represents the feminine principle, gestation, and the circle of life. It is the number of the nine months of pregnancy and the deep, internal nurturing of the dark. 9 brings patience and stealth. In the K'at trecena, 9 represents the gestation of the harvest. It is the quiet time when the gathered resources are stored and allowed to ripen. It asks us to trust the dark and the unseen growth.", "keywords": ["Gestation", "Feminine", "Patience", "Depth", "Mystery"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Plan a future trip or project in detail, but don't act yet.", "Meditate on the 'path of the heart.'", "Connect with female guides or mentors.", "Trust the delays; they are part of the gestation.", "Visualize your destiny unfolding like a map in the dark."], "title": "Gestating the Journey", "content": "9 E' brings a quiet, internal focus to the concept of the path. It is the 'journey within.' Today, the net we have woven becomes a womb for a new direction. It is a day of feminine guidance on the road of life. The energy is not about rushing forward, but about preparing for the next leg of the trip. It supports planning, introspection, and the silent accumulation of wisdom. You may feel a pull to explore your inner landscape or to nurture a dream of travel. It is a day to trust that you are on the right path, even if you are standing still. The road is growing inside you."}}	{"title": "The Deep Explorer", "content": "To be born on 9 E' is to be a traveler of the inner and outer worlds. You possess a quiet, mysterious depth and a profound connection to the feminine aspect of the journey. You are not a tourist in life; you are a pilgrim. You explore the hidden paths, the secrets, and the mysteries that others overlook. You have a great capacity for patience and for holding space for the journeys of others. You are a natural guide for those walking through the dark nights of the soul.\\n\\nYour life path is one of gestation and discovery. You may be a late bloomer, or your projects may take a long time to mature, but the results are always profound. You are likely drawn to psychology, mysticism, or long-distance travel. You navigate by intuition and feeling rather than by a map.\\n\\nYour challenge is isolation. The combination of the solitary path (E') and the internal 9 can make you reclusive. You may struggle to share your discoveries with the world. Your lesson is to bring your treasures back from the deep. When you share the wisdom of your inner journey, you become a lantern for the world, proving that the most important destination is the one we find inside ourselves."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#aaafaf", "primary": "#0e1818", "secondary": "#3d4548"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.830297	2026-04-25 13:46:57.916086
124	10	7	7	E'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Path of Destiny", "content": "E' is the energy of the road, the journey, and the path of life. It is the tooth that bites through obstacles and the feet that walk the miles. E' governs travel, exploration, and the spiritual quest. It represents the experience of the journey itself, rather than the destination. It is the guide who protects travelers and the restless spirit that seeks new horizons. E' asks us to trust the road, even when it is foggy, and to gain wisdom through experience.", "keywords": ["Path", "Journey", "Exploration", "Destiny", "Experience"]}, "number": {"title": "The Summit of Reflection", "content": "The number 7 represents the top of the pyramid, the midpoint of the 13-day cycle. It is a place of mystical power, equilibrium, and the ability to see both the past (1-6) and the future (8-13) simultaneously. 7 is a number of channeling, high magic, and the lack of definite polarity—it is the center point where all options are visible. It can feel suspended in time, offering a moment of pure potential and deep insight before the descent into manifestation begins.", "keywords": ["Equilibrium", "Mysticism", "Overview", "Midpoint", "Channeling"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Take a different route today to invite new energy.", "Reflect on the 'forks in the road' of your past with gratitude.", "Ask for a sign regarding your future direction; watch for it.", "Visualize your life path stretching out clearly before you.", "Stand at a physical crossroads and set a mental intention."], "title": "The View from the Crossroads", "content": "7 E' brings us to the high spiritual vantage point of our journey. We are halfway through the transformation of the Kame trecena. Today, we stand on the summit of the path and look at how far we have come and where we are going. The energy is mystical and expansive. It is a day where the destination matters less than the clarity of the direction. The 'death' we have experienced has cleared the road; now, 7 E' asks us to choose our next steps with the wisdom of the eagle. It is a day of powerful synchronicities and signs on the path. The road is open, and the choices made today resonate with the power of the center."}}	{"title": "The Mystic Traveler", "content": "To be born on 7 E' is to be a soul on a perpetual, high-frequency quest. You are the ultimate explorer, not just of the physical world but of the spiritual dimensions. You carry a restless, energetic spirit that is constantly seeking the 'middle way' or the higher truth. You are a natural mediator and a bridge-builder, able to see all sides of an issue because you view life from the top of the pyramid. Your life is likely filled with travel, movement, and a series of diverse experiences that others might find dizzying.\\n\\nYour path is one of gathering wisdom through motion. You are not meant to stay in one place—physically or mentally—for too long. You learn by doing, by walking the path, by biting into life. You have a gift for guidance; people often ask you for directions, both literal and metaphorical. You possess a mystical intuition that allows you to navigate the unknown with surprising confidence.\\n\\nYour challenge is indecision or the fear of committing to a single path. With the view of the 7, all roads look interesting, and you may hesitate to choose. You may also struggle with feeling ungrounded. Your growth comes when you realize that the path is not outside of you—you *are* the path. When you trust your internal compass, your wandering becomes a sacred pilgrimage, and you lead others toward their own destiny simply by walking yours."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d0c49b", "primary": "#1a1b19", "secondary": "#6f604c"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.806943	2026-04-25 13:46:57.877385
126	10	9	9	Ix					{"nawal": {"title": "The Jaguar's Magic", "content": "Ix is the jaguar, the shaman, and the energy of the night. It represents the magic of the earth, the shrines in the mountains, and the deep feminine intuition. Ix is the power to see in the dark and the ability to transform negativity into wisdom. It is independent, stealthy, and profoundly connected to the mysteries of nature. Ix asks us to trust our gut, to honor the invisible forces, and to walk with the velvet power of the great cat.", "keywords": ["Magic", "Jaguar", "Intuition", "Earth", "Stealth"]}, "number": {"title": "The Circle of Life", "content": "The number 9 represents the feminine principle, gestation, and the circle of life. It is the number of the nine months of pregnancy and the nine lords of the night. 9 brings a quieter, more internal energy than the 8. It is about patience, stealth, and the slow, unseen development of life in the dark. It is a fortunate number for female spirituality and for projects that need to be nurtured in secret before they are born.", "keywords": ["Gestation", "Feminine", "Patience", "Depth", "Circle"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Trust your intuition completely today; if it feels off, it is.", "Spend time alone in the dark or in nature to recharge.", "Work with crystals, herbs, or earth-based healing tools.", "Keep your plans secret for now; let them gather strength in the silence.", "Honor the women in your life and the feminine aspect of your soul."], "title": "Gestating the Magic", "content": "9 Ix is one of the most mystical and feminine days in the calendar. It combines the gestation energy of the 9 with the earth magic of the Jaguar. In the trecena of transformation (Kame), this day represents the deep, dark womb where the new self is being knit together. It is a day of profound intuition and subtle power. The energy is not out in the open; it is prowling in the shadows, protecting the new life that is forming. It is a powerful day for women, for healers, and for anyone doing deep psychological or magical work. The transformation today is silent, deep, and irreversible."}}	{"title": "The Shaman of the Deep", "content": "To be born on 9 Ix is to be a vessel of ancient, earth-based wisdom. You are a natural healer, a mystic, and a guardian of the mysteries. You carry the energy of the jaguar—regal, private, and possessed of a power that does not need to shout to be felt. You are deeply intuitive, often knowing things before they happen or sensing the emotional undercurrents of a room the moment you walk in. You are comfortable in the dark, both literal and metaphorical, and you are often the one who helps others navigate their shadow sides.\\n\\nYour life path is one of spiritual gestation and magic. You move at your own rhythm, which is often slower and more circular than the linear world expects. You nurture things—ideas, people, projects—with a fierce, protective love. You have a special connection to nature, particularly to wild places and high places (shrines). You are a weaver of subtle energies.\\n\\nYour challenge is isolation or becoming lost in the inner worlds. The jaguar walks alone, and you may struggle to let people in or to translate your profound insights into language others can understand. You may also be prone to absorbing the emotions of others. Your growth comes from learning to use your magic in service to the community while maintaining your boundaries. When you embrace your role as a bridge between the earth and the spirit, you become a powerful healer who helps the world birth its new reality."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#9bac8f", "primary": "#101b1a", "secondary": "#3f4f4b"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.807305	2026-04-25 13:46:57.87928
192	15	10	10	Kame					{"nawal": {"title": "The Transformer", "content": "Kame (or Cimi) is the energy of death, rebirth, and the ancestors. It is the nawal of the owl and the dimension beyond the physical. While the word 'Death' can be frightening, Kame is truly the 'Liberator'—the force that ends one cycle so the next can begin. It governs peace, silence, and the profound transformation that occurs when we let go. Kame is the connection to the lineage; it is the telephone line to those who have passed. In its shadow, Kame brings grief, fear of change, and a clinging to the past. But in its light, it is the fearless acceptance of impermanence, the courage to forgive, and the inner peace that comes from knowing the spirit is eternal. It teaches us to die to the old self daily.", "keywords": ["Death", "Rebirth", "Ancestors", "Transformation", "Peace"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Manifestation", "content": "Tone 10 represents the principle of manifestation, collaboration, and the two hands clasping together. It is two 5s (two hands/bars) meeting. Tone 10 is the number of community, agreement, and the concrete realization of plans. It brings the energy of the previous 9 days into a tangible form. It is the law of cause and effect solidified. On a 10 day, things happen. Projects are finished, deals are struck, and the results of our intentions become visible. It is a grounded, responsible energy that asks us to refine our creation and share it with the tribe. It represents the authority that comes from experience and the obligation to act with integrity.", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Collaboration", "Responsibility", "Agreement", "Result"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Bring a project or phase of your life to a respectful close.", "Connect with your ancestors; ask for their help in 'manifesting' your path.", "Face a fear of change and take a concrete step through it.", "Cleanse your home or workspace to physically manifest a fresh start.", "Accept that an ending is necessary for the new result you desire."], "title": "Manifesting Transformation", "content": "10 Kame is a powerful day where the transformation of Death (Kame) becomes manifest in the physical world (10). It is the 'materialization of change.' This is not a theoretical shifting of gears; it is the moment the butterfly actually breaks the chrysalis. The combined energy supports bringing closure to old cycles, finalizing divorces or separations, or completing a phase of deep internal work. It is also a day of profound ancestral collaboration—the 'two hands' of the 10 can be seen as one hand of the living grasping the hand of the ancestor. We are asked to take responsibility for our own rebirth. We cannot wait for change to happen *to* us; we must manifest it with our own actions. The energy is serious but deeply peaceful, offering the stability needed to face life's inevitable endings and beginnings with grace."}}	{"title": "The Bridge Between Worlds", "content": "To be born on 10 Kame is to be a stabilizing force in the face of the unknown. You are the 'Manifest Transformer.' The number 10 gives you a grounded, community-oriented nature and a knack for getting things done, while Kame gives you a deep connection to the spiritual realms and the cycles of life and death. You are not afraid of the dark; in fact, you are the one holding the flashlight for everyone else. You have a unique ability to make the topic of death or transformation feel safe and approachable. You bring the mystical down to earth.\\n\\nYour life path often involves helping others navigate major life transitions. You might be drawn to hospice work, estate planning, grief counseling, or historical preservation (connecting with the past). You are a natural medium, often feeling the presence of ancestors or guides as a tangible reality in your daily life. Unlike the drifty medium, however, you are practical. You use your connection to the other side to improve life here and now. You are the one who ensures the legacy is honored and the inheritance is managed correctly.\\n\\nHowever, the challenge of 10 Kame is heaviness. Carrying the weight of the ancestors and the awareness of mortality can sometimes make you overly serious or melancholic. You may struggle to let go of control (10), wanting to manage the uncontrollable process of change (Kame). Your soul's growth lies in learning to celebrate life as much as you honor death. Learn to laugh, to play, and to realize that your stability is meant to support the living, not just the dead."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#cbb9cc", "primary": "#12181b", "secondary": "#494450"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.849324	2026-04-25 13:46:57.963036
101	8	10	10	B'atz'	You emerge from the hall into a blindingly bright space. You are at the base of the Weaver’s Spire.\n\nIt is a tower made not of stone, but of interwoven beams of light—gold, silver, copper, and blue. They spiral upwards, crossing and recrossing in a complex, beautiful pattern.\n\n10 is the number of Manifestation. B’atz’ is the Weaver. Today, the threads you untangled on Day 3 are ready to be rewoven into a masterpiece.\n\nYou touch the spire. It feels solid. Your ideas have become reality. Your breath has become form.\n\nYou begin to climb the lattice of light. It is easy; your hands find the holds naturally. As you climb, you see other threads joining yours—the people you have met, the lessons you have learned. You realize that your life is not a solo project; it is a collaboration with the universe.\n\nYou reach a platform halfway up. There is a loom here, waiting for you. But it is a loom of reality.\n\nYou sit down. You pick up the shuttle. You start to weave. You weave in the joy of the orchard, the strength of the pillar, the silence of the tower. You create a pattern that is uniquely yours.\n\nThis is the art of your life. It is not random. It is designed by you, in real-time.\n\nYou look at the fabric you have created. It is strong. It is beautiful. It is ready to be worn.	Your life is a work of art today. The energy of 10 B’atz’ puts the brush in your hand. What do you want to paint? What do you want to weave?\n\nThis is a great day for collaboration. Reach out to your community. Your thread is strong, but it’s even stronger when it’s woven with others. Create something beautiful, something tangible. Make it real.	I weave my dreams into reality, creating a tapestry of beauty and connection.	Visualize your life as a tapestry. See the colors of your past. Now, look at the empty threads of your future.\n\nImagine yourself weaving gold and silver threads into that future. You are choosing the pattern. Make it bright. Make it bold.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Weaver of Time", "content": "B'atz' is the Nawal of the thread, the weaver, and the continuous unfolding of time itself. It represents the creative life force that spins the universe into existence. As the archetype of the artist and the organizer, B'atz' governs all forms of creative expression and the planning of time. In human experience, it manifests as the urge to create, to connect, and to celebrate. It is the thread of destiny. When aligned, B'atz' brings flow and beauty; when misaligned, it can lead to feeling tangled or anxious about time running out.", "keywords": ["Creativity", "Weaving", "Time", "Artistry", "Thread"]}, "number": {"title": "The Peak of Manifestation", "content": "The number Ten represents the manifestation of the intent. It is the two hands coming together (5+5) to finalize the creation. In Mayan cosmology, Ten is the energy of community agreement, collaboration, and the realization of the project. Experientially, this energy feels solid, accomplished, and social. It is the moment when the house is built and we invite the neighbors in. The shadow of Ten can be over-responsibility, but its light is the satisfaction of seeing your dreams take physical form. Today, the universe says: 'It is done.'", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Collaboration", "Realization", "Mastery"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Launch a creative project or share your art publicly.", "Host a celebration or get-together; connect the threads of your community.", "Organize your schedule; create a plan that flows.", "Collaborate with others; the energy favors group creativity.", "Celebrate the beauty of your life's design."], "title": "Manifested Tapestry", "content": "When the manifesting power of Tone 10 meets the creative weaving of B'atz', we get a day of 'Community Creation.' 10 B'atz' is the day the tapestry is finished and displayed. It represents the successful materialization of a creative project or a plan. The energy is social, artistic, and celebratory. It is a perfect day for weddings, partnerships, or launching a collaborative venture. The energy supports bringing people together to weave their threads into a larger design. If you have been working on a project, today is the day to make it real and share it with the world. The monkey (B'atz') is happy today, playing with the tangible results of its work. It is also a day of 'time mastery'—being able to manage your schedule and your life with grace and efficiency. Weave your reality with intention; the threads are strong today."}}	{"title": "The Master Weaver", "content": "To be born on 10 B'atz' is to be a master of destiny and a creator of community. You are the 'Manifested Artist'—someone who has the talent not only to dream up beautiful designs but to bring them into physical reality. You are likely very charismatic, social, and talented in the arts or organization. People are drawn to you because you make life feel like a celebration. You have a gift for bringing people together and weaving them into a cohesive group.\\n\\nYour life path is one of tangible creation. You are not a starving artist; you are a successful one (10). You understand how to work within the structures of reality to manifest your vision. Your challenge is to manage the many threads you hold without getting tangled in over-responsibility. Remember that you don't have to weave the whole world, just your part of it. You are here to show us that life is a work of art."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#8dbfa4", "primary": "#0d1918", "secondary": "#35514a"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#957941", "primary": "#0a0904", "secondary": "#44351b"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#f1f8f7", "primary": "#a68d9e", "secondary": "#d5cccb"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#9c9c99", "primary": "#2a3c57", "secondary": "#5a698a"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.799239	2026-04-25 13:46:57.789872
173	14	4	4	Tz'i'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Guide of Law", "content": "Tz'i' is the energy of spiritual law, justice, and authority. It is the dog, the loyal companion, and the guide who leads the soul. Tz'i' represents fidelity, accuracy, and the instinct for truth. It points toward integrity and unconditional love. It asks us to align with the natural order.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Law", "Loyalty", "Truth", "Guidance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cube of Stability", "content": "The number 4 brings form, definition, and stability. It represents the four directions, the four elements, and the solid foundation of the physical world. 4 grounds the energy, creating a container where life can reside. In the Kej trecena, 4 is the foundation of the law. It stabilizes the wild energy of the Deer with structure and justice.", "keywords": ["Stability", "Structure", "Foundation", "Definition", "Four Directions"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Establish a clear boundary in a relationship.", "Review legal documents or agreements for accuracy.", "Commit to a discipline or a code of ethics.", "Practice loyalty to your own values.", "Ask for justice in a situation where there has been imbalance."], "title": "Grounding the Law", "content": "4 Tz'i' is a day of profound stability and justice. The structural energy of the 4 aligns perfectly with the legal authority of Tz'i'. In the Kej trecena, this represents the 'Law of Nature.' It is a day to ground yourself in integrity and to establish clear, fair boundaries. The energy is reliable, loyal, and just. It supports legal matters, contracts, and the restoration of order. We are reminded that true freedom (the wild) relies on a foundation of natural law. It is a day to stand firm in your truth."}}	{"title": "The Pillar of Justice", "content": "To be born on 4 Tz'i' is to be a bedrock of integrity for your community. You possess an unshakable sense of right and wrong and a deep commitment to fairness. You are the reliable friend, the loyal partner, and the trustworthy guide. You build your life on a solid foundation of ethics. You are likely drawn to law, administration, or any role where you can uphold the structure of society.\\n\\nYour life path is one of maintaining order. You are a stabilizer. People come to you when their lives are chaotic because you offer a clear, grounded perspective. You have an instinct for truth that cuts through confusion.\\n\\nYour challenge is rigidity. The double stability of 4 and Tz'i' can make you inflexible or overly judgmental. You may struggle to forgive mistakes or to adapt to change. Your lesson is that justice must be tempered with mercy. When you learn to apply the law with a soft heart, you become a true pillar of the community, upholding the right without crushing the human spirit."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#82c0c4", "primary": "#17211e", "secondary": "#345d60"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.841486	2026-04-25 13:46:57.950824
193	15	11	11	Kej					{"nawal": {"title": "The Guardian of the Wild", "content": "Kej (or Manik) is the deer, the four directions, and the staff of authority. It represents the connection to the natural world and the raw, elegant strength of the wilderness. Kej is the guardian of the forest, representing balance, sure-footedness, and vigilance. It governs the shamanic path and the relationship between the human and the elemental. In its shadow, Kej can be dominant, demanding, or manipulative, using its strength to overpower others. But in its light, it is the noble leader who serves the natural law. Kej represents the physical body as a temple and the ability to stand one's ground with grace. It asks us to walk softly but carry a big presence.", "keywords": ["Nature", "Strength", "Balance", "Authority", "Wilderness"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Resolution", "content": "Tone 11 is the energy of dissonance, change, and refinement. It is neither the beginning nor the end, but the chaotic shake-up before the final resolution. Tone 11 is often called the 'spiritual test.' It asks us to shed whatever is redundant, heavy, or false. It is a high-frequency vibration that can feel unsettling, like a loose wheel on a cart. However, this shaking is purposeful—it separates the wheat from the chaff. Tone 11 liberates us from rigid patterns. It is the number of the mountain top where the air is thin and the view is clear but disorienting. It demands simplicity and truth.", "keywords": ["Change", "Dissonance", "Refinement", "Liberation", "Test"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Spend time in nature to ground the chaotic 11 energy.", "Simplify your life; shed the 'civilized' masks that suffocate you.", "Stand your ground in a conflict, but remain graceful.", "Listen to your body's signals; it knows the truth today.", "Embrace the 'shake-up' as a way to find a stronger balance."], "title": "The Wild Refinement", "content": "11 Kej is a day of spiritual testing within the physical realm. The refining, chaotic energy of the 11 meets the strong, earthy stability of Kej. This creates a friction—like a storm in the forest—that tests our strength and balance. We are asked: 'Can you stand tall like the stag when the ground is shaking?' This day challenges our connection to nature and our own physical bodies. It is an opportunity to shed artificial layers (11) and return to our wild, authentic self (Kej). We may feel a strong urge to break free from societal constraints and run to the woods. The lesson is to find your center amidst the dissonance. By stripping away the non-essential, we discover a primal, elegant strength that cannot be shaken. It is a day to re-wild your spirit and trust your animal instincts to navigate the change."}}	{"title": "The Shaman of Change", "content": "To be born on 11 Kej is to be a powerful agent of spiritual and physical evolution. You are the 'Liberated Stag.' The number 11 makes you a non-conformist, someone who is constantly refining and shedding the old, while Kej connects you deeply to the earth and the ancient laws of nature. You are not here to follow the beaten path; you are here to blaze a new trail through the wilderness. You have a restless, high-frequency energy that can be intimidating to others, but it is driven by a desire for truth and freedom.\\n\\nYour life path is the shamanic journey. You are likely drawn to holistic health, environmental activism, or spiritual leadership that breaks tradition. You challenge the status quo simply by existing. You have a deep bond with animals and the outdoors, often finding more peace in the forest than in the city. You are a 'breaker of chains,' helping others to release the societal conditioning that keeps them tame and unhappy. You lead by example, showing that true strength comes from being wild and authentic.\\n\\nHowever, the challenge of 11 Kej is finding peace. The constant dissonance of the 11 combined with the vigilance of the deer can make you hyper-alert and prone to stress or anxiety. You may be too hard on yourself, constantly testing your own limits. Your shadow side can be domineering, pushing others to change before they are ready. Your soul's growth lies in learning that nature has rhythms of rest, not just activity. Learn to graze peacefully in the meadow you have fought so hard to protect."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#9bc699", "primary": "#0e1a19", "secondary": "#3d5549"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.849761	2026-04-25 13:46:57.963894
93	8	2	2	Aq'ab'al	You follow the floating stones away from the chime. The bright, uniform light of the first day begins to change. The sky splits into two colors: a deep, velvety indigo on your left, and a warm, rising gold on your right.\n\nYou are walking on the Bridge of Twilight.\n\nThe bridge is made of glass, suspended over a sea of clouds that are half-shadow, half-fire. The wind here is different—it pulls you in two directions at once. It whispers doubts in one ear and hopes in the other.\n\nIn the middle of the bridge, you encounter a mirror. But it is not a solid object; it is a vertical sheet of polished fog.\n\nYou look into it. You see yourself, but the image is split. One version of you is shadowed, eyes downcast, carrying old hurts. The other version is luminous, looking upward, ready to fly.\n\nAq’ab’al is the dawn—the separation of night and day. But the number 2 is the challenge of duality. The mirror asks: Which one is you?\n\nYou realize the trap. If you pick the light and reject the shadow, you become fake. If you pick the shadow and reject the light, you become heavy.\n\nYou stand on the bridge, the wind buffeting you. You make a choice. You do not choose one side. You choose the middle. You choose the dawn itself—the place where the dark feeds the light.\n\nYou step *through* the fog mirror. It feels cold, then warm.\n\nThe two images merge inside you. You are not just the hope; you are also the survival. You are the whole sky.\n\nThe bridge stabilizes. The wind stops pulling and starts pushing, a steady tailwind urging you forward.	You might feel of two minds today. Part of you wants to stay safe in the cave; part of you wants to run into the sun. This tension is not a problem; it is a creative force.\n\nThe energy of 2 Aq’ab’al asks you to embrace the contrast. You don’t have to be all happy or all sad. You can be complex. In your relationships, look for the middle ground. The truth is usually found in the dawn, right between the night and the day.	I embrace both my shadow and my light, knowing they create the dawn of my wholeness.	Visualize a horizon. Below it is the dark, starry night. Above it is the bright blue day. Watch the line where they meet—the beautiful gradient of purple, pink, and gold.\n\nImagine you are breathing in that gradient. You are inhaling the beauty of transition. You are the sky that holds it all.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Dawn of Possibility", "content": "Aq'ab'al is the Nawal of the dawn, the dusk, and the transition between light and dark. It represents the moment of awakening and the potential of a new day. Aq'ab'al is the energy of duality, polarity, and the hope that comes after the long night. In human experience, it manifests as optimism, youthfulness, and the ability to see the solution in the problem. It is the bridge between the dream and the reality. When aligned, Aq'ab'al brings new opportunities and clarity; when misaligned, it can lead to hesitation or fear of the unknown. It is the first ray of sun that dispels the shadows.", "keywords": ["Dawn", "Transition", "Hope", "Awakening", "Potential"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "The number Two represents the fundamental principle of polarity: light and dark, male and female, self and other. It is the energy of relationship and the tension that exists between two points. In the Mayan cosmology, Two is not a point of separation, but of connection and reflection; it teaches us that we define ourselves through our interaction with the 'other.' Experientially, this energy brings choices into sharp focus and asks for balance. It is a day where partnerships are tested and strengthened. The shadow of Two is indecision, but its light is the profound harmony that arises when opposites dance together.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Reflection", "Connection", "Balance", "Choice"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Reflect on the 'light' and 'shadow' within your closest relationship.", "Wake up at dawn to meditate on a difficult choice.", "Look for the middle ground between two opposing ideas.", "Acknowledge your fears (shadows) so they can be transformed.", "Be the bridge for someone else who is struggling to decide."], "title": "The Dual Dawn", "content": "When the polarizing energy of Tone 2 meets the transitional nature of Aq'ab'al, we experience a day of 'Reflected Hope.' 2 Aq'ab'al highlights the contrast between light and dark in our relationships and choices. It is a day to look at the 'dawn' of a partnership or a new direction and weigh the options. The energy is soft but revealing; it shows you both the promise and the shadow. You may find yourself standing at a crossroads, seeing two very different futures. This is not a bad thing; Aq'ab'al loves the in-between spaces. Use the mirror of the number 2 to reflect on your true desires. Are you moving toward the light, or are you just running from the dark? The energy supports seeing the potential in others and finding balance in the transition. It is a day to embrace the twilight, knowing that the sun is inevitable."}}	{"title": "The Twilight Diplomat", "content": "To be born on 2 Aq'ab'al is to be a master of transitions and a keeper of the balance between worlds. You are the 'Bridge of Dawn'—a soul who understands that life is not black and white, but a spectrum of color. You have a natural gift for seeing both sides of every situation, making you an excellent mediator and counselor. You are optimistic yet realistic, holding the hope of the dawn with the wisdom of the dusk.\\n\\nYour life path is one of navigating duality. You thrive in partnerships and often find your greatest growth through your reflection in others. However, the double-dose of duality (2 and Aq'ab'al) can sometimes lead to chronic indecision or a feeling of being split in two. Your challenge is to integrate your own light and shadow so that you can stand whole in the center. You are here to show us that the transition is not something to fear, but the very place where magic happens."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b19686", "primary": "#0f1717", "secondary": "#433e3f"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#d8b191", "primary": "#1e1c36", "secondary": "#735b73"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#d0a167", "primary": "#362448", "secondary": "#6f5479"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#e0ca9f", "primary": "#13213c", "secondary": "#938f8b"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.794714	2026-04-25 13:46:57.820052
188	15	6	6	Iq'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Breath of Spirit", "content": "Iq' is the wind, the breath of life, and the sacred word. It represents the element of air and the power of communication. Iq' is the animating force that moves through all things—the spirit that fills the lungs and the ideas that fill the mind. It governs inspiration, change, and the swiftness of thought. Iq' is also the purifier; like a strong gale, it blows away the stale dust of the past. In its shadow, Iq' can be fickle, angry, or prone to gossip and harsh words. But in its light, it is the divine messenger, the clarity of a crystal, and the breath that connects us to the Creator. It reminds us that while our bodies are earth, our essence is air—invisible, free, and eternal.", "keywords": ["Wind", "Breath", "Communication", "Inspiration", "Change"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Stability", "content": "Tone 6 represents the ultimate stability in motion. It is associated with the six directions (North, South, East, West, Heart of Sky, Heart of Earth). 6 is the energy of flow, rhythm, and balance. It is often called the number of 'Heart of the Sky' because it connects the material plane to the spiritual axis. Unlike the static stability of the 4, the 6 is organic—it breathes. It is the point where the initial effort (1-5) finds its groove and begins to sustain itself. Tone 6 brings harmony to family and relationships; it smooths out the rough edges. It is a day to accept things as they are, to trust the unfolding process, and to find the equilibrium between doing and being.", "keywords": ["Flow", "Harmony", "Balance", "Heart", "Sustain"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Focus on your breath; use pranayama or meditation to center yourself.", "Communicate with grace; your words have the power to harmonize today.", "Allow change to happen naturally; flow like the wind rather than resisting.", "Connect with nature by spending time in the fresh air.", "Listen as much as you speak; the wind carries messages from spirit."], "title": "The Harmony of Communication", "content": "6 Iq' is a day of beautiful, rhythmic flow in communication. The harmonizing energy of the 6 smooths the erratic nature of the wind (Iq'), creating a breeze that is gentle, constant, and life-affirming. This is the 'breath of balance.' It is one of the best days for resolving conflicts through words, for writing poetry, or for speaking your truth with grace rather than force. The combined energy asks us to align our breath with the Heart of the Sky and the Heart of the Earth. It suggests that true inspiration comes when we are centered, not when we are frantic. We are invited to let the winds of change blow through our lives, trusting that they will only remove what is no longer in harmony with our growth. It is a day to breathe deeply, speak clearly, and let the spirit move through you without resistance."}}	{"title": "The Voice of Harmony", "content": "To be born on 6 Iq' is to be a messenger of divine balance. You are the 'Harmonious Wind.' While Iq' gives you a quick mind and a gift for communication, the number 6 grounds that energy, giving you a stability and rhythm that many other air signs lack. You are not a hurricane; you are the trade wind that sailors trust to carry them home. You have a natural talent for mediation and diplomacy. You can walk into a room filled with tension and, with a few well-chosen words, bring everyone back to center. Your presence feels like a breath of fresh air—vitalizing yet soothing.\\n\\nYour life path is deeply connected to the power of the word. You may find fulfillment in writing, singing, teaching, or counseling. You understand that communication is not just about exchanging data; it is about exchanging spirit (breath). You are likely very connected to your physical environment, needing open spaces and fresh air to think clearly. You move through life with a natural grace, trusting the flow of events rather than trying to force them. You are a conduit for inspiration, often receiving ideas that feel like they were whispered directly from the cosmos.\\n\\nHowever, the challenge of 6 Iq' is to maintain your own equilibrium when the winds around you get rough. You are sensitive to disharmony and can become ill or anxious in toxic environments. Your shadow side may manifest as passivity—going 'wherever the wind blows' to avoid conflict, rather than standing firm in your truth. Your soul's lesson is to learn that your voice is a sacred instrument of the Heart of the Sky. Speak up, even when it shakes the boat, for your truth is meant to restore the balance, not just keep the peace."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d0c7d0", "primary": "#111212", "secondary": "#483f46"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.847677	2026-04-25 13:46:57.971756
106	9	2	2	Tz'ikin					{"nawal": {"title": "The Visionary Bird", "content": "Tz'ikin is the Nawal of the Bird, the Eagle, and the Condor. It represents vision, freedom, and the ability to rise above the mundane to see the big picture. Tz'ikin is the energy of prosperity and abundance, reminding us that spiritual vision attracts material resources. It governs the eyes and the ability to 'see' opportunities. In human experience, Tz'ikin manifests as optimism, sociability, and a drive for success. It is the intermediary between Earth and Sky. When aligned, Tz'ikin brings financial flow and good luck; when misaligned, it can lead to greed or superficiality.", "keywords": ["Vision", "Prosperity", "Opportunity", "Freedom", "Abundance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "The number Two represents the fundamental principle of polarity: light and dark, male and female, self and other. It is the energy of relationship and the tension that exists between two points. In the Mayan cosmology, Two is not a point of separation, but of connection and reflection; it teaches us that we define ourselves through our interaction with the 'other.' Experientially, this energy brings choices into sharp focus and asks for balance. It is a day where partnerships are tested and strengthened. The shadow of Two is indecision, but its light is the profound harmony that arises when opposites dance together.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Reflection", "Connection", "Balance", "Choice"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Discuss financial goals or business plans with a partner.", "Look for 'win-win' opportunities; avoid zero-sum thinking.", "Share your vision with someone you trust; get their perspective.", "Practice generosity; give to receive.", "Balance your budget (2) with your dreams (Tz'ikin)."], "title": "Shared Vision", "content": "When the polarizing energy of Tone 2 meets the expansive vision of Tz'ikin, we experience a day of 'Relational Prosperity.' 2 Tz'ikin asks us to look at how we share our vision and our abundance with others. It is a powerful day for business partnerships, romantic relationships, and any collaboration where resources are shared. The energy suggests that true prosperity comes from connection—two eyes see better than one. You may face a choice today regarding money or opportunity; use the mirror of the 2 to see the situation from your partner's perspective. It is also a day to balance the material and the spiritual—to keep your feet on the ground (2) while your eyes look to the sky (Tz'ikin). If you have been trying to fly solo, the universe invites you to find a wingman. Abundance flows when the circuit is complete."}}	{"title": "The Visionary Partner", "content": "To be born on 2 Tz'ikin is to be a magnet for shared abundance. You are the 'Prosperous Diplomat'—someone who intuitively understands that success is a team sport. You have a gift for seeing opportunities that others miss, and you know exactly who to partner with to make them a reality. You are likely very social, charming, and persuasive, with a natural ability to bridge the gap between people and resources. You are not a solitary eagle; you are one who flies in formation.\\n\\nYour life path is one of creating wealth and freedom through relationship. You thrive when you have a counterpart to bounce ideas off of. The number 2 gives you a sensitivity to the needs of others, while Tz'ikin provides the drive for success. Your challenge is to ensure that your partnerships are truly balanced and that you do not become dependent on others for your sense of worth. You are here to show us that when we lift each other up, we all fly higher."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a2be9e", "primary": "#0f1b1a", "secondary": "#365250"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.80191	2026-04-25 13:46:57.854755
111	9	7	7	Ajpu					{"nawal": {"title": "The Solar Hero", "content": "Ajpu is the Nawal of the Sun, the blowgunner, and the spiritual warrior. It represents the divine spark within the human being—the light that conquers darkness. Ajpu is the energy of leadership, clarity, and the hero's journey. It governs the search for truth and the overcoming of obstacles through certainty and skill. In human experience, Ajpu manifests as confidence, artistic talent, and a connection to the divine. It is the face of the sun shining on the path. When aligned, Ajpu brings success and enlightenment; when misaligned, it can lead to ego.", "keywords": ["Sun", "Hero", "Divinity", "Purpose", "Leadership"]}, "number": {"title": "The Summit of Reflection", "content": "The number Seven represents the midpoint of the trecena, the top of the pyramid, and the power of mystic vision. In Mayan cosmology, Seven is a number of great potential but also of suspension; it is the moment where we can look back at the climb and forward to the descent. Experientially, this energy feels like a pause in the action—a time to assess, reflect, and gain perspective. It is neither a beginning nor an end, but a bridge. The shadow of Seven can be indecision, but its light is the clarity that comes from seeing the whole picture.", "keywords": ["Reflection", "Midpoint", "Vision", "Insight", "Clarity"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Meditate on your life's purpose; the vision is clear today.", "Stand in the sun and feel its power filling you.", "Reflect on the 'hero's journey' you have traveled so far.", "Honor your own divinity; treat yourself with deep respect.", "Look for the light in a difficult situation; it is there."], "title": "The Reflective Warrior", "content": "The reflective power of Tone 7 meets the solar brilliance of Ajpu to create a day of 'Spiritual Clarity.' 7 Ajpu represents the hero standing on the mountaintop, looking back at the trials overcome and forward to the destiny that awaits. It is a day of profound vision regarding your life's purpose. The sun illuminates everything from this high vantage point—the shadows have nowhere to hide. It is a perfect day to ask: Who am I? What is my mission? The energy is noble, bright, and certain. You may receive a clear sign or insight about your spiritual path. It is a day to honor the divinity within yourself and others, seeing the 'god spark' clearly. Use the balance of the 7 to integrate your human ego with your divine soul. You are the light of the world, suspended in a moment of perfect realization."}}	{"title": "The Spiritual Beacon", "content": "To be born on 7 Ajpu is to be a lighthouse for the soul. You are the 'Mystic Hero'—someone who shines with a light that seems to come from another world. Situated at the top of the pyramid (7), you have a perspective that is both human and divine. You are a natural leader, not because you crave power, but because you see the path so clearly that others naturally follow you. You are likely artistic, spiritual, and confident in your truth.\\n\\nYour life path is one of self-realization. You are here to discover the god-force within yourself and to help others do the same. You may struggle with the weight of expectation or the 'hero complex,' feeling you must save everyone. Your challenge is to remember that you can only show the way; you cannot walk it for others. You are here to remind us that we are all children of the sun, capable of infinite light."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d5b55f", "primary": "#1b1c19", "secondary": "#494136"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.803702	2026-04-25 13:46:57.860989
161	13	5	5	Aq'ab'al	By midday, the path ahead disappears beneath a wide stretch of water. The caravan slows, then comes to a halt at the edge of it. The surface reflects the storm in muted tones, giving no clear indication of what lies beneath.\n\nFor a moment, there is hesitation. The way forward is not obvious.\n\nThe traveler who has remained beside the covered wagon steps forward first. Their movement is neither hurried nor cautious, but deliberate. They step into the water, feeling for the ground beneath the surface, their balance adjusting with each step.\n\nOthers follow.\n\nYou stand at the edge for a moment longer, looking at the reflection staring back at you. It would be easy to wait, to let others determine the safety of the crossing. But something within you recognizes that this moment is not about certainty.\n\nIt is about effort.\n\nYou step forward.\n\nThe water is cold and unfamiliar, the ground beneath it uneven. Each step requires attention, awareness, a willingness to move without knowing exactly what comes next. And yet, with each step, the path reveals itself just enough to continue.	You are standing at the edge of something that cannot be fully understood from where you are.\n\nIt may not look dramatic. It may not even look like a clear decision point. But something in your life is asking you to move forward without the comfort of certainty. And that can feel unsettling in a very specific way—the kind that makes you want to pause, to wait, to gather more information before taking the next step.\n\nBut today is not about perfect clarity.\n\nIt is about willingness.\n\nYou are not being asked to leap blindly. You are being asked to engage. To step into the unknown with enough awareness to feel your way through it, rather than trying to solve it from the outside.\n\nThere is a subtle shift that happens when you do this. The path does not reveal itself all at once. It reveals itself in response to your movement.\n\nOne step.\n\nThen another.\n\nWhat felt unclear begins to take shape—not because the world changed, but because you did.\n\nTrust that you have enough to begin.\n\nNot enough to control the outcome.\n\nBut enough to meet it.\n\nAnd sometimes, that is the only kind of knowing that truly matters.	I step forward with trust, even when the path is not fully visible.	Sit comfortably and close your eyes.\nBring awareness to your body where it touches the ground.\nFeel the support beneath you.\nTake a slow breath in, and as you exhale, imagine taking a small step forward—not physically, but internally.\nYou don't need to know where it leads. Just feel the movement.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine a path forming in front of you, one step at a time. Each step appears only after you commit to moving forward. The space ahead is unclear, but it is not empty—it is waiting. The storm above you lights the path briefly with flashes of illumination, just enough to guide you.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Dawn Bringer", "content": "Aq'ab'al is the energy of the dawn, the twilight, and the threshold. It represents the transition from dark to light, the moment of awakening, and the duality of hope and uncertainty. Aq'ab'al is the new day breaking, bringing clarity and new opportunities. It asks us to leave the comfort of the night and step into the potential of the morning.", "keywords": ["Dawn", "Hope", "Transition", "Clarity", "New Beginnings"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Empowerment", "content": "The number 5 represents empowerment, work, and the human hand. It is the energy of doing, gathering, and applying will to the structures created by the 4. 5 breaks the stability to put things into motion through effort. In this trecena, 5 represents the work required to cross the threshold of rebirth. It is the push of the midwife.", "keywords": ["Action", "Work", "Effort", "Empowerment", "Clarity"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Wake up before dawn and set an intention as the sun rises.", "Take the first concrete step on a new project.", "Change a habit that belongs to your 'night' self.", "Clean a doorway or threshold in your home.", "Apply effort to clear up a misunderstanding; bring it to light."], "title": "Working the Threshold", "content": "5 Aq'ab'al is a day of active transition. The empowerment of the 5 drives us to push through the twilight of Aq'ab'al. The cleansing storm of Kawoq has prepared us, and now we must do the work to step into the new light. This is the moment of labor where the effort is greatest just before the birth. It is a day to take action on your new beginnings. Don't just wait for the sun to rise; climb the hill to meet it. The energy is hopeful but demanding. It asks us to leave behind the shadows of the past and to physically enact the change we wish to see."}}	{"title": "The Worker of the Dawn", "content": "To be born on 5 Aq'ab'al is to be a pioneer of new realities. You are the one who wakes up the village. You possess a restless, optimistic energy that is always looking for the next opportunity, the next horizon. You are not afraid of change; in fact, you work hard to create it. You are a natural innovator, often seeing the potential in things (and people) that others have given up on. You bridge the gap between what was and what could be.\\n\\nYour life path is one of active awakening. You may find yourself constantly starting over or initiating new phases of life. You are a hard worker, driven by the hope of a brighter future. You have a talent for bringing clarity to confusing situations, acting as a light in the dark places.\\n\\nYour challenge is patience. You live so much in the dawn that you may struggle with the long, hot day of maintenance or the dark night of rest. You can be impulsive, jumping into the new before finishing the old. Your lesson is to honor the transition. When you learn that the dawn cannot be rushed, you become a master of timing, helping others navigate their own darkness to find the light."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c3ad95", "primary": "#17191b", "secondary": "#49454c"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.835576	2026-04-25 14:25:01.115864
171	14	2	2	Q'anil					{"nawal": {"title": "The Seed of Abundance", "content": "Q'anil is the energy of the seed, the star, and the ripening crop. It represents fertility, potential, and the inevitable unfolding of life when conditions are right. Q'anil is the promise that what is planted with intention will grow. It carries a gentle, golden energy of nourishment and organic development. It reminds us that we cannot force the flower to open; we can only tend the soil.", "keywords": ["Seed", "Fertility", "Abundance", "Growth", "Ripening"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "The number 2 represents polarity, relationship, and the dynamic tension between opposites. It is the interaction between the self and the other, the masculine and the feminine. 2 brings choices and mirrors into focus. In the Kej trecena, it asks us to find balance in our relationships through the lens of growth and fertility.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Reflection", "Connection", "Balance", "Duality"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Plant a physical seed with a partner or friend.", "Discuss the future growth of a relationship.", "Nurture a shared dream with patience.", "Balance your 'doing' (Kej) with 'being' (Q'anil).", "Offer gratitude for the people who help you ripen."], "title": "Balancing the Seeds", "content": "2 Q'anil brings a gentle, fertile energy to the robust trecena of Kej. The strength of the Deer meets the softness of the Seed. Today, we look at the partnerships that help us grow. The 2 brings relationship into focus: who is watering your seeds? Are you nurturing the potential in your partner? It is a day for planting intentions within relationships—seeds of love, collaboration, or shared projects. The energy is organic and hopeful. It reminds us that balance (Kej) is necessary for growth (Q'anil). We cannot just push; we must also nurture."}}	{"title": "The Fertile Partner", "content": "To be born on 2 Q'anil is to be a nurturer of potential in others. You possess a warm, generative energy that makes things grow. You thrive in one-on-one relationships where you can pour your golden light into another person. You are patient, optimistic, and deeply connected to the cycles of life. You understand that relationship is a garden that needs constant tending.\\n\\nYour life path is one of shared abundance. You are not a solitary grower; you need a co-gardener. You are likely drawn to parenting, teaching, or collaborative arts. You have a natural talent for spotting talent or potential in others and helping to bring it out.\\n\\nYour challenge is dependency. You can become so focused on the other's growth that you neglect your own garden. You may also struggle with conflict, preferring to keep the peace even at a cost. Your lesson is that healthy plants need space. When you balance your nurturing instinct with healthy boundaries, you create relationships that are truly abundant and mutually sustaining."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b5bd8e", "primary": "#0f1918", "secondary": "#40493e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.840845	2026-04-25 13:46:57.947781
178	14	9	9	Tz'ikin					{"nawal": {"title": "The Visionary Eagle", "content": "Tz'ikin is the bird, the eagle, and the vision. It represents prosperity, freedom, and the ability to see the whole picture. Tz'ikin is the intermediary between heaven and earth, carrying prayers up and bringing abundance down. It governs business and the clear vision required to manifest dreams.", "keywords": ["Vision", "Prosperity", "Freedom", "Eagle", "Abundance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Circle of Life", "content": "The number 9 represents the feminine principle, gestation, and the circle of life. It is the number of the nine months of pregnancy and the deep, internal nurturing of the dark. 9 brings patience and stealth. In the Kej trecena, 9 represents the gestation of a higher vision.", "keywords": ["Gestation", "Feminine", "Patience", "Depth", "Mystery"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Visualize your highest future in detail.", "Nurture a business idea or creative project in private.", "Ask for a vision that benefits the whole community.", "Trust the timing of your success.", "Look for signs of abundance in the natural world."], "title": "Gestating the Vision", "content": "9 Tz'ikin is a day of incubating a grand vision. The gestation energy of the 9 holds the expansive vision of the Eagle. In the Kej trecena, this is the 'dream of the forest.' We are nurturing a vision of prosperity and freedom that is in harmony with nature. It is a day to look inward at your dreams. Are they ripe? Are they big enough? The energy is quiet but pregnant with possibility. It asks us to trust the process of developing our vision before we launch it. The Eagle is in the egg, gathering strength."}}	{"title": "The Nurturing Visionary", "content": "To be born on 9 Tz'ikin is to be a dreamer who births new realities. You possess a vast, soaring imagination and the patience to bring it to life. You are a natural entrepreneur or artist, but your approach is feminine and organic. You understand that great things take time to grow. You have a gift for seeing the potential in people and situations and helping them ripen.\\n\\nYour life path is one of bringing abundance into the world. You are a bridge between the spiritual vision and the physical manifestation. You are generous and nurturing, often sharing your prosperity with others. You have a deep trust in the universe's ability to provide.\\n\\nYour challenge is impatience with the process. Even though you have the 9 energy, the Eagle wants to fly *now*. You may struggle when the gestation period feels too long. Your lesson is to trust the egg. When you allow your visions to fully mature before launching them, you create success that is sustainable and deeply nourishing for the world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a0cbba", "primary": "#101d1c", "secondary": "#465f55"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.843145	2026-04-25 13:46:57.956915
112	9	8	8	Imox					{"nawal": {"title": "The Primordial Ocean", "content": "Imox is the Nawal of water, the collective subconscious, and the primordial dream from which reality emerges. It represents the feminine aspect of creation—the womb, the intuition, and the fluid chaos of imagination. Imox is the energy that connects us all telepathically and emotionally; it is the 'dream that dreams us.' In human experience, Imox manifests as wild creativity, psychic sensitivity, and sometimes 'crazy wisdom.' When aligned, it brings profound inspiration; when misaligned, it can lead to emotional overwhelm or confusion.", "keywords": ["Intuition", "Dreams", "Water", "Subconscious", "Creativity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Harmony of Justice", "content": "The number Eight represents the octave, the return to power, and the weaving of the spiritual into the material. In Mayan cosmology, Eight is the number of the 'Primordial Male' energy, mirroring the 'Primordial Female' of Nine. It is often associated with ceremonies and the harmonization of energy. Experientially, this energy feels like a solid, resonant chord—it is balanced, organized, and powerful. It is a day to take the insights of Seven and begin to apply them with authority. The shadow of Eight can be rigidity, but its light is the strength of integrity.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Balance", "Ceremony", "Reciprocity", "Fairness"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a water ceremony (bless your water before drinking).", "Take a ritual bath to cleanse your energy.", "Pay attention to your dreams; they have a message of balance.", "Create art that flows (watercolor, dance, music).", "Offer gratitude to the waters of the Earth."], "title": "Ceremonial Water", "content": "When the ceremonial balance of Tone 8 meets the watery depths of Imox, we enter a day of 'Sacred Flow.' 8 Imox is the energy of the holy water used in ritual. It is a day to harmonize the emotions and the subconscious mind. The structure of the 8 provides a safe container for the wildness of Imox, allowing us to access our intuition without drowning in it. This is a powerful day for water ceremonies, dream work, or artistic expression that heals. The energy asks: Are your emotions in balance? Are you honoring your intuition? It is a day to pay respect to the feminine principle and the collective soul. If you have been feeling mentally chaotic, 8 Imox offers the chance to organize the chaos into a beautiful pattern. Let the water wash over you and restore your equilibrium."}}	{"title": "The Harmonious Dreamer", "content": "To be born on 8 Imox is to be a master of the subconscious realms. You are the 'Ceremonial Mystic'—a soul who can navigate the chaotic waters of emotion and intuition with grace and balance. You have a profound psychic sensitivity, yet the number 8 gives you a strength and authority that keeps you grounded. You are likely an artist, a healer, or a counselor, able to help others make sense of their confusing feelings. You understand the hidden patterns of the universe.\\n\\nYour life path is one of bringing order to the dream. You are here to show that intuition is not 'crazy,' but a valid and powerful form of intelligence. You may struggle at times with the intensity of your own emotions or the collective energy you pick up, but your gift is the ability to channel that flow into something beautiful and healing. You are the vessel that holds the sacred water."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#81d0be", "primary": "#0e1a1a", "secondary": "#305a53"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.803986	2026-04-25 13:46:57.861868
128	10	11	11	Ajmaq					{"nawal": {"title": "The Owl of Forgiveness", "content": "Ajmaq is the energy of the owl, the ancestors, and the pardon. It represents the human experience—the sweetness of life, but also the inevitable mistakes and the need for forgiveness. Ajmaq is the curiosity to peer into the dark and the wisdom to accept imperfection. It is the day of reconciliation, of healing ancestral lines, and of making peace with one's own humanity. It reminds us that we are learning, and that stumbling is part of the walk.", "keywords": ["Forgiveness", "Curiosity", "Ancestors", "Wisdom", "Pardon"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Resolution", "content": "The number 11 represents dissonance, clearing, and the testing of the structure. It has a high, thin vibration that can feel unsettling but is necessary to break up rigidity. 11 is the energy of 'sorting'—separating the grain from the chaff. It pushes the cycle toward its conclusion by shaking loose anything that is not essential. It is powerful, transformative, and often brings a unique, non-linear perspective.", "keywords": ["Dissonance", "Clearing", "Testing", "Resolution", "Change"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Say 'I forgive you' to yourself or someone else, and mean it.", "Investigate a repeating family pattern and choose to end it today.", "Allow yourself to make a mistake without spiraling into shame.", "Clear out physical clutter; it often holds energetic stagnation.", "Ask the ancestors for help in releasing what you cannot release alone."], "title": "Clearing the Karmic Slate", "content": "11 Ajmaq is a day of powerful, perhaps turbulent, clearing and forgiveness. The dissonance of the 11 shakes up our history, bringing old grievances or hidden guilts to the surface so that the gentle energy of Ajmaq can forgive and release them. In the rebirth process of the Kame trecena, this is the final emotional detox. It is a day to let go of the idea of perfection. You may feel a strong urge to apologize, to forgive someone who hurt you, or to release a burden you have carried for your lineage. The energy is liberating but requires the courage to look at the 'messy' parts of life without judgment."}}	{"title": "The Redeemer", "content": "To be born on 11 Ajmaq is to carry the complex and beautiful burden of being a cosmic cleaner. You are a soul who has come to heal long-standing wounds, often those of your family line or even the collective. You possess a unique, slightly eccentric wisdom (the 11 influence) that sees beyond societal norms to the core human truth. You are deeply curious, unafraid of the dark corners of the human psyche, and possessed of a profound capacity for empathy and forgiveness.\\n\\nYour life path is rarely a straight line. You learn through trial and error, through experiencing the full spectrum of life's sweetness and bitterness. You may feel like the 'black sheep' or the one who is different, but this is your strength. You are here to question the established structures and to offer a new way of being that includes acceptance of imperfection. You are a natural counselor for the broken, as you do not judge.\\n\\nYour challenge is to not get lost in the 'sins' of the world or to carry guilt that does not belong to you. The 11 energy can make you feel ungrounded or mentally restless. Your lesson is to apply the forgiveness of Ajmaq to yourself first. When you accept your own unique, non-linear nature, you become a powerful agent of liberation, showing others that it is our cracks that let the light in."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#ccaec3", "primary": "#171417", "secondary": "#6d4c67"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.807698	2026-04-25 13:46:57.868152
131	11	1	1	Kan	You stand at the base of a vertical vine so wide it could support a village, its surface textured like the hide of a prehistoric creature. The electric hum from the gateway still vibrates in your marrow, but here, in the deepening green of the Spire, it finds a rhythm. From beneath a broad, heart-shaped leaf, an iridescent serpent emerges. It does not strike or flee; instead, it coils slowly around a smaller shoot, its scales refracting the lime-colored light into a thousand tiny rainbows. It watches you with eyes that contain the history of the forest.\n\nAs the serpent moves, you feel a corresponding ripple in your own body. A latent heat begins to stir at the base of your tailbone, a coiling sensation that mirrors the guardian before you. This is not a thought, but a physical awakening of the wisdom stored in your DNA. The serpent’s presence acts as a tuning fork for your nervous system, pulling your posture upright and aligning your breath with the pulsing veins of the vine. You realize the Spire isn't just something you climb; it is a mirror for the power rising within you. The iridescent guide flickers its tongue once, a silent acknowledgement of the fire you’ve sparked, and vanishes into the canopy. You reach out, your fingers finding the first hold on the living bark. The climb is no longer a concept—it is a pulse in your blood.	The air around you begins to pulse with a low, rhythmic heat, as if the earth itself just found its heartbeat under your feet. You can feel a spark—ancient, coiled, and undeniably alive—starting to stir at the very base of your spine. This isn't a loud or sudden change that demands your immediate attention with a crash; instead, it is the slow, inevitable awakening of an instinct you’ve ignored for far too long while you navigated the flat, predictable plains of your daily routine. \n\nThe rigid, horizontal logic of your current life is starting to melt away like wax near a flame, replaced by a vertical hunger to grow, to shed, and to reach for something electric. You might feel a strange pressure in your marrow, a quiet buzzing in your ears that sounds like a storm gathering miles away. This is your potential finally announcing itself. It doesn't ask for permission to arrive; it simply begins to rise. \n\nToday, your body knows the way before your mind can even formulate a single question or a doubt. You are being re-tuned to a higher frequency of existence. Trust the heat that is currently blooming behind your ribs. Trust the rise of the energy that makes your posture straighter and your gaze sharper. The evolution has begun, and it starts with this single, deep breath of raw, unrefined potential. Move as if you are the lightning and the cloud all at once.	My power is a sacred fire, and I trust the wisdom growing within my spine today.	Sit comfortably and close your eyes. Inhale deeply, imagining a spark of warmth at the very base of your spine. As you exhale, let that warmth settle into a steady, pulsing glow, aligning your posture with the upright strength of a great tree. \n\nOptionally, visualize the iridescent serpent from the Spire's gate coiling slowly around your spine, its scales refracting light that awakens the ancient wisdom stored within your DNA.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Vital Force", "content": "Kan is the energy of the serpent, the kundalini, and the life force that runs through the spine. It represents wisdom, sexuality, evolution, and the power of transformation. Kan is the teacher who shows us that true power comes from within. It is the energy of DNA and the spark of life itself. It asks us to shed our old skins to grow and to master our instincts so they serve our higher purpose.", "keywords": ["Vitality", "Wisdom", "Serpent", "Transformation", "Power"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Power", "content": "The number 1 represents the spark of creation, unity, and the seed potential of the entire cycle. It is the beginning, the singular focus, and the impulse that sets everything in motion. In the Kan trecena, the 1 energy initiates a cycle of vital force, wisdom, and evolution. It is the lightning strike that ignites the fire. It asks for a clear intention regarding how you wish to grow and how you will use your personal power over the next 13 days.", "keywords": ["Unity", "Initiation", "Seed", "Potential", "Spark"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in physical movement or yoga to wake up your body's energy.", "Set a clear intention for what wisdom you wish to gain this cycle.", "Visualize shedding a skin that is too tight for you.", "Study a piece of sacred knowledge or read a wisdom text.", "Connect with your spine and your posture; stand tall."], "title": "Igniting the Sacred Fire", "content": "1 Kan initiates the 13-day cycle with a surge of raw, vital energy. Today is the day the seed of wisdom is planted in the fertile soil of your being. The combination of the 1 (beginning) and Kan (evolution) creates a powerful momentum for personal growth. It is a day to set intentions around your physical health, your spiritual studies, or your creative projects. The energy is electric and alive; it wakes you up. It asks you to look at where you are stagnating and to invite the fire of transformation to burn away the old shell. This is the first breath of a new, more powerful version of yourself."}}	{"title": "The Initiator of Evolution", "content": "To be born on 1 Kan is to be a spark of evolutionary fire in human form. You carry the potent energy of the 'first serpent'—the initial impulse of life to grow, learn, and ascend. You are a natural leader, not necessarily through command, but through the sheer force of your vitality and presence. You have a deep, instinctive wisdom that often seems beyond your years, and you are driven by a constant need to transform and shed old versions of yourself. You are the person who starts the revolution, whether it is in a community, a field of study, or within a family dynamic.\\n\\nYour life path is one of mastering your own power. You are likely gifted with high energy, charisma, and a strong physical constitution. You may be drawn to the healing arts, athletics, or spiritual teaching—anywhere that allows you to channel your intense life force. You are a teacher by nature, but you teach through example; people watch how you navigate your own transformations and are inspired to do the same.\\n\\nYour challenge is to manage the intensity of your energy. The 1 Kan vibration can be overwhelming if not grounded, leading to impulsiveness or a tendency to burn out. You may also struggle with the patience required for slow growth, wanting to evolve instantly. Your soul's lesson is to trust the process of the shed. When you learn to channel your fire with discipline and compassion, you become a powerful catalyst for the evolution of consciousness, helping others ignite their own inner light."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#99a781", "primary": "#0e110f", "secondary": "#3b3a2f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.80906	2026-04-25 14:38:01.305914
195	15	13	13	Toj					{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Offering", "content": "Toj (or Muluc) is the fire, the payment, and the law of cause and effect. It represents the sacred exchange required to maintain balance in the universe. Toj is the energy of gratitude, sacrifice, and the clearing of debts. It is associated with the element of water (tears/rain) and fire (ceremony). Toj asks: 'What are you willing to give to receive?' It governs our karmic ledger. In its shadow, Toj can represent suffering, victimhood, or the feeling that life is exacting a heavy toll. But in its light, it is the joy of giving, the relief of forgiveness, and the power of the ceremonial fire to transmute heavy energy into light. It teaches us that everything has a cost, but that payment can be made with love.", "keywords": ["Offering", "Payment", "Balance", "Fire", "Gratitude"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascension of the Cycle", "content": "Tone 13 represents the completion, the ascension, and the return to the source. It is the highest frequency in the calendar. 13 is the number of the spirit world, the ancestors, and the universal consciousness. It signifies the end of the growth cycle and the preparation for a new beginning. Tone 13 is not a 'death' but a transcendence; it is the fruit becoming the seed. It allows us to see the entire journey from a place of detached love. On a 13 day, our intuition is at its peak. We are urged to wrap things up, to offer gratitude, and to let go of the form so we can keep the essence. It is the vibration of total alignment.", "keywords": ["Completion", "Ascension", "Spirit", "Ancestors", "Renewal"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Make a physical or energetic offering (candle, incense, charity).", "Express deep gratitude for the lessons of the last 13 days.", "Release any lingering guilt or 'debt'—forgive yourself and others.", "Connect with the spirit world; the veil is non-existent today.", "Prepare for the new cycle by emptying your cup completely."], "title": "The Ultimate Offering", "content": "13 Toj is the culmination of the trecena, a day of profound spiritual payment and release. The transcending energy of the 13 elevates the offering of Toj to the highest level. This is the 'Cosmic Receipt.' It is the day to settle all accounts—spiritual, emotional, and physical—so we can ascend to the next cycle light as a feather. The combined energy is intensely ceremonial. It asks us to offer up our struggles, our lessons, and our gratitude to the fire of creation. It is a day of deep liberation; by paying what is owed (gratitude/apology/service), we free ourselves from the past. The 13 connects us to the ancestors who stand ready to receive this offering. We realize that the ultimate currency of the universe is not money, but the open heart. As we close the book on this 13-day journey, we say 'Thank you' to everything—the pain and the joy alike."}}	{"title": "The Cosmic Equalizer", "content": "To be born on 13 Toj is to be a soul dedicated to the restoration of universal balance. You are the 'Ascended Offering.' The number 13 vibrates with the highest spiritual frequency, giving you a foot in the other world and a deep connection to the ancestors, while Toj grounds you in the law of karma and exchange. You are a natural clearer of energy. You walk into a room and instinctively know what is out of balance and what needs to be 'paid' to fix it. You are a generous spirit, often giving of yourself to help others clear their burdens.\\n\\nYour life path is one of service and ceremony. You may feel a lifelong calling to 'pay back' a debt—not out of guilt, but out of a deep sense of cosmic responsibility. You are drawn to philanthropy, healing, environmental restoration, or spiritual priesthood. You understand that everything is connected and that taking without giving creates sickness. You are the one who remembers to say thank you, who remembers the old ways, and who keeps the fire burning for the tribe. You are a bridge for the ancestors to do their work in the modern world.\\n\\nHowever, the challenge of 13 Toj is the tendency to over-sacrifice. You may feel like the 'sin-eater' for your family or community, taking on their debts and suffering as your own. The 13 can make you ungrounded, and Toj can make you feel like you perpetually owe something. Your soul's growth lies in realizing that you are worthy of receiving, not just giving. True balance requires that the scale tips both ways. Your existence is not a debt to be paid, but a gift to be enjoyed."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#be957a", "primary": "#0f1616", "secondary": "#443b37"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.850533	2026-04-25 13:46:57.965016
228	18	7	7	Tz'ikin	You follow the jaguar-mist until the ground begins to rise. The soft moss gives way to hard, vertical rock. You are climbing now, pulling yourself up ledges of black glass, your breath coming in short, sharp gasps.\n\nThe mist clears as you ascend, revealing the sky for the first time in days. It is a deep, bruised purple, streaked with veins of gold.\n\nYou reach the summit—a needle-like spire of obsidian that towers over the entire landscape. You pull yourself onto the narrow peak and look down.\n\nThe view steals your breath.\n\nFrom down in the canyon, the lava flows looked like random chaos. But from up here, you see the truth. The rivers of fire form a pattern. They are the glowing lines of a massive mandala, a sacred geometry burning into the crust of the world.\n\nYou see where you fell. You see the bridge of bones. You see the forest of cane. You see how every twist and turn was necessary to bring you to this exact point.\n\nThe wind here is fierce and clean. It strips away the last of the ash from your clothes. Above you, the clouds part, and a beam of pure sunlight hits the peak. It feels like a crown.\n\nYou realize that your suffering was just a matter of perspective. When you are in the fire, it burns. When you are above it, it illuminates.\n\nYou open your arms to the wind. You are halfway through the journey. You can see where you have been, and you can see the horizon of where you are going.\n\nIt is all one picture. And it is beautiful.	You are at the halfway point. Lift your head. Stop looking at the obstacle in front of your nose and look at the horizon. The confusion clears when you change your altitude.\n\nVision creates reality. Today, if you can see it in your mind, you can call it in. The universe is waiting for you to place your order. Dream big, then double it. The only limit on your abundance today is how far you are willing to look.	I rise above the noise and see my path with crystal clarity.	Sit comfortably. Imagine you are sitting at the very top of a high mountain. The air is thin and crisp. Below you, the world is spread out like a map.\n\nLook up. The sky is a perfect mirror. See your own reflection in the heavens—vast, unlimited, and filled with light. You are not the small figure struggling on the path; you are the sky itself.\n\nFeel your vision expanding. You can see the past, present, and future as one unbroken line. Rest in this clarity.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Visionary Bird of Prosperity", "content": "Tz'ikin is the nawal of the bird, the eagle/condor, and vision. It represents the ability to see the big picture, rising above the details to perceive the interconnectedness of all things. Tz'ikin is the energy of prosperity, abundance, and the freedom of the spirit. Associated with the element of air and the sky, it carries a light, expansive, and high-frequency energy. It is the archetype of the visionary who brings messages from the divine to the earth. In daily life, Tz'ikin manifests as financial luck, good news, dreaming, and artistic inspiration. Its shadow aspect can be spacing out, greed, or becoming distracted by 'shiny objects' without grounding. Tz'ikin teaches us that abundance is a natural state.", "keywords": ["Vision", "Prosperity", "Freedom", "Abundance", "Perspective"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mystic Prism", "content": "Tone 7 is the midpoint of the 13-day cycle, sitting at the very top of the energetic pyramid. It represents the point of maximum potential, reflection, and mystical power. Unlike the stability of 4 or the flow of 6, Tone 7 is a threshold energy—neither here nor there, but encompassing both the beginning and the end. It is a day of 'no time,' where the veil between worlds is thin. Experientially, Tone 7 feels contemplative, strange, and highly intuitive. It provides a 360-degree view of reality, allowing us to see the past and future simultaneously. While it offers profound insights and the ability to channel energy, its shadow can be indecision, confusion, or getting lost in the ether. It is the mirror at the top of the mountain.", "keywords": ["Insight", "Reflection", "Mysticism", "Threshold", "Vision"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in a visualization meditation to see your future self.", "Ask for guidance on a major life decision.", "Look for signs in the sky or from birds.", "Open yourself to receive abundance in unexpected forms.", "Take a 'bird's eye view' of a situation that is troubling you."], "title": "The Summit of Vision", "content": "When the mystical peak of Tone 7 meets the soaring vision of Tz'ikin, we reach the 'Apex of Insight.' 7 Tz'ikin is a day of tuning long-term vision. Standing at the top of the pyramid, with the eyes of the Eagle, we can see forever. This is the most powerful day for visualization and setting long-term goals. The energy is expansive, almost overwhelming in its possibility. It feels like standing on a mountaintop with the wind in your face. 7 Tz'ikin invites us to look beyond our immediate problems and see the larger pattern of our lives. It is a day of high magic for prosperity and spiritual connection. The veil is thin, and messages from the divine come through clearly. The challenge is to not get lost in the clouds; the vision must eventually be brought down to earth. The opportunity is to align your personal dream with the dream of the universe."}}	{"title": "The Seer of Infinite Possibility", "content": "To be born on 7 Tz'ikin is to be a visionary of the highest order. You possess a mind that naturally ascends to the highest vantage point, seeing patterns, potentials, and futures that others cannot imagine. Tone 7 places you at the mystical center, the threshold between worlds, while Tz'ikin gives you the wings to fly in both. You are a dreamer, a mystic, and a magnet for prosperity. People are drawn to you because you radiate a sense of freedom and limitless possibility. You likely have strong psychic abilities or a powerful intuition that guides your business and personal life.\\n\\nYour life path is one of spiritual mediation. You bring the vision of heaven down to earth. You are not here to get bogged down in the details; you are here to set the course. You may be drawn to entrepreneurship, the arts, spirituality, or any field where you can innovate and inspire. You have a natural luck, often finding that the universe provides exactly what you need when you need it. You understand that true prosperity is a spiritual vibration.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 7 Tz'ikin soul is grounding. You can be so high-flying that you lose touch with physical reality. You may struggle with indecision, seeing so many paths that you cannot choose one. There is also a risk of spiritual bypassing—using your high vision to avoid dealing with messy human emotions. Your lesson is to remember that the Eagle must eventually land. When you anchor your incredible vision in practical action, you become a powerful manifestor who can change the world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#bedbd8", "primary": "#181a15", "secondary": "#555e57"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#c4b27f", "primary": "#21273b", "secondary": "#565a5d"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#d2d8cc", "primary": "#507694", "secondary": "#93aab0"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#556f7b", "primary": "#20242f", "secondary": "#753025"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.868954	2026-04-25 13:46:58.037589
154	12	11	11	Ix	Night falls in the canyon. The amber light fades to a deep, mysterious indigo. The village goes quiet. But the air is not still; it is vibrating.\n\n11 is Dissonance and Chaos. Ix is the Jaguar and the Magician. Today, the gathered energy transforms.\n\nYou step out of your house. The silos are glowing. The nets above are shimmering like the Milky Way. A Jaguar made of starlight prowls between the structures. It is not walking on the ground; it is walking on the energy lines of the valley.\n\nIt approaches you. It opens its mouth, but instead of a roar, a wind comes out—a wind that smells of incense and ozone.\n\nThe Jaguar touches the silos. The "compost" inside them begins to change. The old memories, the heavy lessons—they spontaneously combust into pure magic. They turn into potential.\n\nYou realize that the chaos of the number 11 is not destructive; it is catalytic. It is the chemistry of the soul changing states.\n\nThe Jaguar invites you to run with it. You run through the canyon, your feet barely touching the ground. You feel the magic in your veins. You are not just a gatherer; you are a sorcerer. You can take the raw material of your life and alchemize it into anything you want.\n\nThe nets above dissolve into pure light. The boundaries are gone. There is only the magic of the night.	Expect the unexpected today. The energy of 11 Ix is wild and magical. Plans might change, things might get weird, but it is all for a higher purpose.\n\nYou have the power to transform a situation just by looking at it differently. Use your intuition. Use your magic. Don’t be afraid of the dark; that’s where the jaguar hunts. There is a miracle hiding in the mess.	I embrace the magic of transformation and trust the power of my intuition.	Visualize a purple flame. Throw your worries into it. Watch them burn. They don’t turn to ash; they turn to butterflies made of light.\n\nCatch the butterflies. They are your new power. Feel the magic tingling in your hands.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Jaguar's Magic", "content": "Ix is the jaguar, the shaman, and the energy of the night. It represents earth magic, shrines, and deep feminine intuition. Ix is the power to see in the dark and to transform negativity into wisdom. It is independent, stealthy, and connected to the mysteries of nature. It asks us to trust the invisible forces.", "keywords": ["Magic", "Jaguar", "Intuition", "Earth", "Stealth"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Resolution", "content": "The number 11 represents dissonance, clearing, and the testing of the structure. It has a high, thin vibration that shakes loose the non-essential. 11 is the energy of 'sorting'—separating the grain from the chaff. In the K'at trecena, 11 tests the net. It shakes the web to see if it is strong enough to hold the catch, or to break away the threads that are rotted.", "keywords": ["Dissonance", "Clearing", "Testing", "Resolution", "Change"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a ritual to clear negative energy from your life.", "Spend time alone in nature; listen to the wind.", "Trust the 'weird' or unexplainable feelings you have today.", "Let go of a friendship or habit that feels 'heavy' or false.", "Embrace the chaos; it is rearranging things for your benefit."], "title": "Clearing with Magic", "content": "11 Ix is a day of powerful, perhaps turbulent, spiritual clearing. The dissonance of the 11 meets the high magic of the Jaguar. Today, the K'at trecena asks us to cut the cords that bind us to low-vibration energies. The net is being purified. You may feel a strong urge to be alone, to visit wild places, or to perform a ritual of release. The energy is wild and unpredictable. It strips away the superficial layers to reveal the raw magic underneath. It is a day to trust your intuition over your logic, and to let the Jaguar guide you through the chaos of transformation."}}	{"title": "The Magical Catalyst", "content": "To be born on 11 Ix is to be a lightning rod for spiritual energy. You possess a high-frequency, unconventional magic that disrupts the status quo. You are a natural shaman, seeing the world through a lens of energy and spirit that others often miss. You are independent, fierce, and deeply intuitive. You are here to shake things up, to challenge established norms, and to clear the way for new realities.\\n\\nYour life path is one of purification and magic. You likely have a turbulent life story, full of sudden changes and profound insights. You are a catalyst; when you enter a room, the energy shifts. You have a special connection to the earth and its mysteries, but you engage with them in your own unique, non-traditional way.\\n\\nYour challenge is grounding. The 11 energy can be unbalancing, and the Ix energy can be solitary. You may feel misunderstood or like an alien in the mundane world. Your lesson is to channel your voltage. When you learn to ground your high-frequency magic in service to the earth, you become a powerful healer, clearing the collective shadow and restoring the sacred to everyday life."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a4d09e", "primary": "#111b1a", "secondary": "#3d5848"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.831436	2026-04-25 13:46:57.904889
156	12	13	13	Ajmaq	The eagle leaves you on the mesa. The sun sets, and the twilight returns, but it is different now. It is the violet light of deep peace.\n\nAn Owl lands on a branch of a twisted pine tree near you. It hoots softly. 13 is Ascension. Ajmaq is Forgiveness and the Ancestors.\n\nYou look back at the canyon one last time. You think of all the things you gathered in your net. You think of the things you released.\n\nThe Owl asks: "Is there anything left?"\n\nYou search your heart. There is one small stone left in your pocket. It is the judgment you hold against yourself for gathering the "wrong" things, for wasting time, for getting tangled.\n\nYou take the stone out. It feels heavy.\n\nAjmaq offers you the sweetness of pardon. It tells you that there were no mistakes. The tangle was the lesson. The burden was the muscle-building.\n\nYou toss the stone over the edge of the mesa. It falls, silent, into the dark.\n\nA wave of sweetness washes over you. You are forgiven. You are whole. You are free.\n\nThe net is gone. The canyon is gone. You are standing in the void of potential, ready for the next creation.\n\nYou have harvested your soul.	It is finished. The cycle is complete. The energy of 13 Ajmaq is a warm blanket of forgiveness. Whatever you think you did wrong—let it go. It’s over.\n\nYou have done the work. You have sorted the net. Now, rest. Listen to the wisdom of the ancestors whispering that you are enough, just as you are. The slate is clean.	I am forgiven, I am whole, and I am free to begin again.	Visualize yourself floating in a pool of honey-colored light. It is warm and sweet. It dissolves all your guilt, all your shame, all your tension.\n\nFloat in the sweetness. You are loved beyond measure. There is nothing to do but receive.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Owl of Forgiveness", "content": "Ajmaq is the energy of the owl, the ancestors, and the pardon. It represents the human experience—the sweetness of life, the mistakes, and the need for forgiveness. Ajmaq is the wisdom to accept imperfection and the curiosity to peer into the dark. It is the day of reconciliation and healing ancestral lines.", "keywords": ["Forgiveness", "Ancestors", "Wisdom", "Pardon", "Curiosity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascension of Spirit", "content": "The number 13 represents completion, ascension, and the spirit world. It is the final step where energy transcends physical form. 13 is a number of great power, sensitivity, and psychic expansion. It brings the cycle to a close and offers a connection to the ancestors. In the K'at trecena, 13 is the moment the net is lifted to the heavens. The harvest is offered up, and we are released from the entanglement of the process.", "keywords": ["Ascension", "Completion", "Spirit", "Ancestors", "Release"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a ritual of total forgiveness for yourself and others.", "Connect with your ancestors and ask for their blessing.", "Release a long-held guilt; put it down forever.", "Celebrate the 'sweetness' of being human, flaws and all.", "Close the cycle with a prayer of gratitude for the lessons of the net."], "title": "The Great Release", "content": "13 Ajmaq is the transcendent conclusion of the K'at trecena. The journey of gathering and entanglement ends with a profound act of forgiveness. The 13 elevates the pardon of Ajmaq to a cosmic level. Today, we release all debts, all grudges, and all the 'knots' in our net that we could not untie. We offer them to the ancestors and the spirit world. It is a day of total absolution. We realize that we are human, that we got tangled, and that it is okay. The energy is soft, mystical, and deeply liberating. We ascend from the web of karma into the freedom of spirit."}}	{"title": "The Cosmic Redeemer", "content": "To be born on 13 Ajmaq is to be a soul of infinite compassion and ancestral depth. You carry the energy of the final pardon. You are here to heal the timelines, to forgive the unforgivable, and to close the cycles of trauma for your lineage. You possess a psychic sensitivity that connects you to the spirit world and the voices of the past. You are a natural medium, healer, or spiritual teacher who works with the shadow to find the light.\\n\\nYour life path is one of redemption and ascension. You walk a path that is often solitary or misunderstood, as you are operating on a frequency of 13—the edge of the known world. You have a profound curiosity about the human condition and a lack of judgment that makes you a safe harbor for sinners and saints alike.\\n\\nYour challenge is to not drown in the collective ocean. Your sensitivity is so high that you must learn strong psychic boundaries. You may also struggle with a sense of not belonging to this earth. Your lesson is to embody forgiveness here and now. When you accept your role as a bridge between the ancestors and the living, you become a cosmic cleaner, washing the world in the healing waters of unconditional love."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c5a9b9", "primary": "#171c1f", "secondary": "#6b5668"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.832636	2026-04-25 13:46:57.907413
230	18	9	9	No'j	You leave the amber cave feeling weightless, as if gravity has loosened its grip on you. The path winds out of the canyon and into a valley where the black rock has been ground down into fine, fertile sand.\n\nBut the way forward is blocked.\n\nFloating in the air above the path is a massive, complex mandala made of blue laser light. It rotates slowly, its geometric patterns shifting and interlocking like the tumblers of a cosmic lock. It hums with a sound that you feel in the center of your forehead.\n\nYou try to walk around it, but the light expands to block you. You try to push through, but it is solid as stone. This is not an obstacle of force; it is an obstacle of mind.\n\nYou realize you cannot fight this puzzle. You have to solve it.\n\nYou sit down in the sand and watch the spinning lights. At first, it is dizzying. Your mind tries to analyze the pattern, to find the logic, to force a solution. But the more you think, the faster it spins.\n\nThen, you remember the lesson of the Amber Cave: release. You stop trying to figure it out. You simply breathe.\n\nYou sync your breath with the pulsing of the blue light. Inhale... Exhale... You let your mind become as empty and clear as the desert sky.\n\nIn that silence, a thought blooms. Not a frantic, worried thought, but a clear, fully formed idea. It rises from the depths of your consciousness like a bubble surfacing in a dark pond. It is the key.\n\nAs soon as the idea clicks into place in your mind, the mandala slows. The blue lights align, locking into a perfect, stable shape. The hum changes to a harmonious chord.\n\nThe puzzle dissolves, leaving behind a shower of blue sparks that drift down and settle into your hair like stardust. The path is clear.\n\nYou stand up, touching your forehead. You realize that the answer was never "out there." It was waiting for you to be quiet enough to hear it.	Your mind is a fertile garden, not a storage unit. Today, plant one clear solution. Don’t overthink the "how"—just clarify the "what."\n\nThe idea needs time to gestate. You want the answer *now*, but wisdom operates on its own timeline. Stop digging up the seed to check if it’s growing. Trust the incubation process. The breakthrough happens when you finally stop making noise.	I trust my inner wisdom to reveal the perfect solution in perfect time.	Sit with a straight spine. Close your eyes. Visualize your mind as a perfect, clear crystal sphere. It is silent and still.\n\nThoughts come and go like clouds reflecting on the surface, but they do not enter the crystal. Watch them pass without attaching to them.\n\nIn the center of the crystal, see a small blue flame. This is your pure intelligence. Focus on the flame. Let it burn away confusion. Rest in the clarity of your own mind.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Crystal Mind of Wisdom", "content": "No'j is the nawal of the mind, knowledge, and the earth's brain. It represents the power of thought, logic, and the conversion of information into wisdom. No'j is the scholar, the scientist, and the planner. Associated with the element of earth and the color blue, it carries a cool, clear, and intellectual energy. It is the archetype of the sage who solves problems through clarity and innovation. In daily life, No'j manifests as study, brainstorming, and the spark of a good idea. Its shadow aspect can be overthinking, arrogance, or becoming trapped in mental loops. No'j teaches us that true intelligence is not just knowing facts, but knowing how to live in harmony.", "keywords": ["Wisdom", "Knowledge", "Thought", "Innovation", "Logic"]}, "number": {"title": "The Patience of Gestation", "content": "Tone 9 is the energy of patience, cycles, and the feminine. It represents the nine months of human gestation and the nine levels of the Mayan underworld (Xibalba). It is a number of deep, slow-moving power. Unlike the flash of the 1 or the action of the 5, Tone 9 is the energy of the seed swelling underground just before it breaks the surface. Experientially, it feels heavy, emotional, and sometimes secretive. It is a day for working behind the scenes, nurturing projects, and trusting the dark. While it fosters deep creativity and empathy, its shadow can be depression, lethargy, or getting stuck in the past. It is the womb that holds the future.", "keywords": ["Patience", "Gestation", "Feminine", "Completion", "Depth"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Spend time alone to think and journal.", "Research a topic that you are passionate about.", "Meditate to quiet the chatter and access deeper wisdom.", "Be patient with a problem; the answer is gestating.", "Trust the 'knowing' that comes from your gut as well as your head."], "title": "The Gestation of Great Ideas", "content": "When the deep patience of Tone 9 meets the intellectual power of No'j, we enter the 'Cave of Wisdom.' 9 No'j is a day of balancing intuition and logic. It is the energy of the philosopher deeply contemplating the nature of reality. Today is not for quick decisions; it is for letting ideas ripen. The energy supports deep study, research, and long-term planning. It feels like the quiet hum of a supercomputer processing vast amounts of data. 9 No'j asks us to go inward and find the solution that honors the whole cycle. It is a day where ancient wisdom can surface to solve modern problems. The challenge is the tendency to get lost in thought, to analyze until we are paralyzed. The opportunity is to birth a concept that has the power to endure and transform."}}	{"title": "The Scholar of Deep Time", "content": "To be born on 9 No'j is to be a keeper of profound wisdom and a patient seeker of truth. You possess a mind that is both logical and intuitive, capable of understanding complex systems and deep mysteries. Tone 9 gives you a connection to the long cycles of time and the feminine principle of gestation, while No'j grants you the intellect of the sage. You are not interested in superficial answers; you want to know the 'why' and the 'how' at the deepest level. You are likely a lifelong learner, drawn to philosophy, science, history, or ancient wisdom traditions.\\n\\nYour life path is one of synthesizing knowledge into wisdom. You are here to think the thoughts that take time to mature. You may be a writer, a researcher, or a strategist—someone who works behind the scenes to create plans that benefit the future. You have a quiet, contemplative nature, often preferring the company of books or your own thoughts to loud crowds. You understand that true innovation comes from a deep understanding of the past.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 9 No'j soul is the burden of overthinking. You can get stuck in your own head, spinning in loops of analysis without ever taking action. You may struggle with depression or a sense of isolation, feeling that no one else understands the depth of your thoughts. There is a risk of becoming cynical if your ideals are not met. Your lesson is to share your wisdom. When you bring your ideas out of the cave and into the light, you help the world to evolve and understand itself better."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#72b1c1", "primary": "#0e1417", "secondary": "#344655"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#95a1a5", "primary": "#0e1536", "secondary": "#4a5373"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#dbbfb5", "primary": "#5d3a37", "secondary": "#9b705e"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#6061c6", "primary": "#191131", "secondary": "#3c317f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.870127	2026-04-25 13:46:58.0412
190	15	8	8	K'at					{"nawal": {"title": "The Net of Abundance", "content": "K'at is the energy of the net, the spiderweb, and the harvest. It represents the gathering of resources, people, and ideas. K'at is the force that pulls things together—it is gravity, magnetism, and the biological impulse to bond. It governs abundance, fertility, and the 'fullness' of the granary. However, the net has a double meaning: it can catch food, or it can become a trap. In its shadow, K'at represents entanglement, debts, hoarding, and the feeling of being burdened by one's possessions or obligations. K'at asks us to examine what we are carrying. Are we hauling a golden harvest, or are we tangled in old knots? It teaches the lesson of release—to cut the cords that bind us so we can enjoy the abundance we have gathered.", "keywords": ["Net", "Gathering", "Entanglement", "Release", "Abundance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Weaver of Justice", "content": "Tone 8 represents the energy of return, harmony, and the infinite loop. After the peak of the 7, the 8 brings the energy back down toward the earth, but in a more refined form. It is the number of the male principle (Solar) just as 9 is the female. Tone 8 is the 'octave,' representing a new level of order. It governs justice, balance, and physical energy. It is traditionally the number of the calendar keepers and the daykeepers. 8 asks us to organize the spiritual insights of the 7 into a coherent pattern. It is a day of ceremony, of weaving threads together, and of ensuring that all debts—energetic and physical—are paid. It carries a vibration of wholeness and resilience.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Harmony", "Weaving", "Return", "Ceremony"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Organize your physical space; clear clutter to clear your mind.", "Pay debts (financial or emotional) to restore energetic balance.", "Release an old burden or obligation that is no longer yours to carry.", "Gather with others; the net is strong for community building today.", "Perform a simple ceremony of gratitude for the abundance in your life."], "title": "The Harmonious Harvest", "content": "8 K'at is a day of powerful ceremonial unbinding and gathering. The harmonizing justice of the 8 meets the net of K'at, creating an energy that seeks to untangle the knots of our lives. This is perhaps the best day in the calendar to clear 'karmic debt' or to reorganize your physical and emotional load. The 8 brings a sense of sacred order to the chaos of the K'at net. It is a day to ask: 'What do I need to release to return to balance?' and 'What abundance am I ready to receive?' The energy supports organizing your finances, your home, or your community connections. It is a day of reciprocity; if you have been caught in a trap of your own making, the 8 offers the key to unlock it through right action and ceremony. We weave a new pattern today, one that holds plenty without holding us back."}}	{"title": "The Weaver of Community", "content": "To be born on 8 K'at is to be a master builder of connections and a keeper of abundance. You are the 'Harmonious Net.' The number 8 gives you a strong sense of justice, leadership, and organic rhythm, while K'at endows you with a magnetic ability to gather people and resources. You are the center of the spiderweb, keenly aware of every vibration on the strands. You are likely the person who brings the friend group together, organizes the event, or manages the complex logistics of a project. You have a natural talent for accumulation—whether it be knowledge, friends, or material wealth—and you know how to weave these things into a structure that benefits everyone.\\n\\nYour life path is one of disentanglement and liberation. You are often born into complex family webs or karmic situations that you are destined to unravel. You have a keen mind for sorting; you can look at a mess (literal or figurative) and immediately see how to organize it. People come to you when they feel trapped, knowing you have the patience to pick apart the knots. You are a generous soul, often sharing your harvest freely, as the 8 drives you toward reciprocity and balance.\\n\\nHowever, the challenge of 8 K'at is knowing when to let go. You can become a hoarder of emotions, responsibilities, or things, fearing that if you release anything, the net will break. You may get dragged down by the weight of others' problems, feeling responsible for carrying them. Your shadow side is 'burnout by entanglement.' Your soul's growth lies in learning that true abundance requires flow—you must empty the net occasionally to catch the fresh blessings. Your justice (8) must include justice for yourself."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d2ac77", "primary": "#131614", "secondary": "#5d4133"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.8484	2026-04-25 13:46:57.974352
212	17	4	4	Imox					{"nawal": {"title": "The Primordial Dreamer", "content": "Imox is the nawal of the dreamer, the mystic, and the primordial waters. It represents the collective consciousness, imagination, intuition, and the subconscious ocean where creation begins. Can bring inspiration or confusion. Imox is the energy of the womb and the deep psychological currents that drive us. Associated with the element of water and the color blue, it carries a fluid, chaotic, and highly creative energy. It is the archetype of the artist who pulls visions from the ether. In daily life, Imox manifests as vivid dreams, emotional sensitivity, and 'crazy' ideas. Its shadow aspect can be emotional overwhelm, disconnection from reality, or getting lost in the delusion of the mind. Imox teaches us to navigate the depths without drowning.", "keywords": ["Intuition", "Dreams", "Imagination", "Emotion", "Psychic Flow"]}, "number": {"title": "The Foundation of Form", "content": "Tone 4 is the energy of stability, structure, and definition. After the movement of 3, the 4 establishes a base, like the four walls of a house or the four legs of a table. It represents the four directions (East, West, North, South) and the four elements (Earth, Air, Fire, Water), grounding spiritual energy into physical reality. Experientially, Tone 4 feels calm, ordered, and reliable. It is a day for planning, organizing, and establishing boundaries. It brings the vague potential of the earlier numbers into concrete form. While it offers safety and predictability, its shadow can be rigidity, stagnation, or being 'boxed in.' It is the number of the builder who lays the cornerstone.", "keywords": ["Structure", "Balance", "Grounding", "Manifestation", "Stability"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create a physical container for your creativity (a sketchbook, a studio space).", "Write down your dreams immediately upon waking.", "Establish emotional boundaries to protect your sensitivity.", "Work on a project that requires both imagination and discipline.", "Spend time near a contained body of water (a pool, a lake, a bath)."], "title": "Structuring the Dream", "content": "The stabilizing force of Tone 4 meets the chaotic waters of Imox to create a day of 'Contained Imagination.' 4 Imox is the energy of the Reservoir. Without the 4, Imox can be a flood; without Imox, the 4 can be dry and rigid. Together, they create a perfect vessel for capturing and using creative flow. Today is the best day to give form to your wildest ideas. It is a day to write the book, paint the canvas, or build the structure that will hold your dreams. The energy supports taking the abstract and making it concrete. It feels like waking from a dream and being able to write it down in perfect detail. 4 Imox helps to stabilize emotions, allowing us to feel deeply without being swept away. The challenge is to trust that the structure will not kill the magic, but preserve it. The opportunity is to manifest the impossible by giving it a place to live in the physical world."}}	{"title": "The Architect of Dreams", "content": "To be born on 4 Imox is to be a master of manifesting the imaginary. You possess a unique mind that is comfortable in the deepest waters of the subconscious but also capable of building solid structures on land. You are the artist who actually finishes the painting, the visionary who builds the company, the mystic who can pay the bills. Tone 4 gives you a love for order and stability, which acts as a necessary anchor for the wild, swirling energy of Imox. You are likely a person of few words but deep feelings, often communicating through symbols or art rather than direct speech.\\n\\nYour life path is one of bridging the dream world and the waking world. You are here to show that intuition and logic can coexist. You may be drawn to psychology, the arts, architecture, or any field where you can give form to the formless. You have a natural gift for understanding the collective mind, sensing trends and feelings before they become mainstream. People feel safe with you because you are not afraid of their emotions; you provide a stable container for their chaos.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 4 Imox soul is the tension between your need for safety and your pull toward the unknown. You may struggle with anxiety, fearing that if you let go of control, you will drown in your own sensitivity. Or, you may become too rigid, suppressing your intuition to fit into a 'normal' life. Your growth comes from trusting your internal reservoir. When you learn to build structures that are flexible enough to hold your vast imagination, you become a powerful creator who can turn the stuff of dreams into reality."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#6cc3b6", "primary": "#0d1a19", "secondary": "#2b4f4a"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.858714	2026-04-25 13:46:58.009995
151	12	8	8	B'atz'	You cross the bridge and enter a cavern carved into the canyon wall. But it is not dark. It is hung with tapestries of incredible color and complexity. Looms stand in rows, weaving by themselves, driven by the wind.\n\nThis is the Weaver’s Archive.\n\n8 is Harmony and Wholeness. B’atz’ is the Thread and the Artist. Today, the net becomes Art.\n\nYou look at the tapestries. They are woven from the threads of the nets outside. You see the strands of "worry" woven into dark, contrasting backgrounds that make the bright colors pop. You see the "lost dreams" woven into borders of gold.\n\nYou realize that nothing in the net was wasted. Even the junk, even the pain, even the delays—it is all raw material for the weaver.\n\nA Monkey Spirit hangs from the ceiling, laughing. It grabs a handful of loose threads and spins them into a rope, then swings from it. It reminds you that life is not just about sorting and tidying; it is about playing.\n\nYou sit at a loom. You take the threads of your own journey—the K’at gathering, the Kan vitality, the Kame death, the Kej stability—and you start to weave.\n\nYou make a pattern. It is chaotic, yes, but it is yours. It is beautiful because it is whole.\n\nThe lesson of 8 B’atz’ is that the net is not a trap; it is a tapestry. You are not caught in it; you are the one weaving it.	Your life is a masterpiece in progress. The energy of 8 B’atz’ invites you to step back and look at the pattern. Even the dark threads add depth. Even the knots add texture.\n\nStop judging your life and start weaving it. If you dropped a stitch yesterday, pick it up today and make it into a design feature. Be creative. Be playful. The universe is handing you the thread; what will you make?	I weave every experience of my life into a tapestry of beauty and wholeness.	Visualize a loom. See the threads of your life—red for passion, blue for sadness, yellow for joy, black for loss. \n\nWatch as the shuttle moves back and forth, weaving them all together. See the fabric forming. It is strong. It is vibrant. It is you.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Weaver of Time", "content": "B'atz' is the thread of time, the artist, and the weaver of destiny. It represents creativity, the arts, and the beginning of new cycles. B'atz' is the monkey, the playful trickster who holds the sacred calendar. It governs the weaving together of community and purpose. It reminds us that we are the artists of our own lives.", "keywords": ["Creativity", "Weaving", "Time", "Art", "Joy"]}, "number": {"title": "The Harmonic Resonance", "content": "The number 8 represents the octave, wholeness, and the fabric of life. It wraps up the bundle of the previous seven days, bringing organic closure and harmony. 8 is the number of male spirituality and resonance. In this trecena, 8 weaves all the gathered threads into a coherent whole. It is the celebration of the net itself—the beauty of the connections we have made.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Wholeness", "Resonance", "Fabric", "Ceremony"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create something beautiful—art, food, or music.", "Celebrate a marriage or a long-term partnership.", "Weave disparate parts of your life (work, play, spirit) together.", "Thank the 'weavers' in your life (artists, organizers, mothers).", "Laugh at the cosmic joke; enjoy the play of time."], "title": "The Masterpiece of Connection", "content": "8 B'atz' is one of the most auspicious and creative days in the calendar. The wholeness of the 8 meets the weaving power of B'atz'. Today, the K'at trecena reaches a point of beautiful integration. We see the net not as a trap, but as a tapestry. It is a day to celebrate the connections that sustain us, the art we have created, and the time we have been given. The energy is joyful, artistic, and ceremonial. It is the perfect day for weddings, for initiating creative projects, and for gathering the community to celebrate the weave of life. The struggle of gathering softens into the joy of having."}}	{"title": "The Master Weaver", "content": "To be born on 8 B'atz' is to be a soul wrapped in the golden thread of destiny. You are a creator, a unifier, and a bringer of joy. You possess a natural wholeness and a talent for making life beautiful. You are the artist who sees the pattern in the chaos, the organizer who brings the community together, and the magician who can spin straw into gold. You are deeply connected to time and tradition, yet you approach life with a playful, monkey-like curiosity.\\n\\nYour life path is one of creative mastery. Whether you are an artist, a scientist, or a parent, you approach your work as a craft. You have a magnetic personality and are often the center of social circles. You are here to remind others that life is a creative act. You have the ability to initiate new cycles for yourself and others with grace and ease.\\n\\nYour challenge is to not get tangles in your own thread. You can be so multi-talented that you become scattered, or you may take on too much responsibility for weaving everyone else's lives. Your lesson is to focus on your own masterpiece. When you align your creative power with a sense of sacred purpose, you weave a legacy that endures, showing the world the exquisite beauty of the divine plan."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d290ad", "primary": "#141314", "secondary": "#4c383c"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.829824	2026-04-25 13:46:57.915053
213	17	5	5	Iq'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Breath of Spirit", "content": "Iq' is the nawal of the wind, the breath, and the messenger. It represents communication, clarity, and the breath of life. Governs inspiration, change, and purification. Can stir sudden transformation or anger when misaligned. Associated with the element of air and the color white, it carries a swift, changeable, and inspiring energy. It is the archetype of the divine messenger who whispers truth in our ears. In daily life, Iq' manifests as conversation, the internet, travel, and the sudden shifting of circumstances. Its shadow aspect can be impulsiveness, harsh words, or chaos—the hurricane rather than the breeze. Iq' teaches us to listen to the spirit and to keep our own energy moving.", "keywords": ["Breath", "Words", "Clarity", "Change", "Communication"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Power", "content": "Tone 5 is the energy of empowerment, work, and the center. In Mayan numerology, it represents the hand (five fingers) and the ability to grasp, shape, and work with materials. It breaks the stability of the 4 to add a new dimension of agency and action. Tone 5 is the central pivot point of the single-digit numbers (1-9), representing the core or the heart of the matter. Experientially, it feels energetic, capable, and sometimes demanding. It is a day to gather resources and apply effort. While it empowers us to get things done, its shadow can manifest as over-exertion, grasping for control, or losing sight of the spiritual in favor of the material work. It is the number of the worker who makes the vision real.", "keywords": ["Action", "Discipline", "Work", "Empowerment", "Center"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Write an important email or letter that requires clarity and strength.", "Engage in breathwork to energize your physical body.", "Speak up about a cause or project you are working on.", "Clear the air in a relationship through honest dialogue.", "Organize your digital files or communication channels."], "title": "Empowered Communication", "content": "When the working hand of Tone 5 meets the wind of Iq', we experience a day of 'Active Inspiration.' 5 Iq' is the energy of the Orator or the Messenger who commands attention. It is a powerful day to put your words to work. The energy supports taking action on your ideas and communicating them with force and clarity. This is not a day for idle chatter; it is a day for speeches, manifestos, and decisive conversations. 5 Iq' gives the wind direction and purpose. It feels like a strong, steady gale that fills the sails and pushes the ship forward. The combination allows us to 'grasp' the ethereal concepts of the spirit and mold them into understandable language. The challenge is to ensure that your words are not too forceful or damaging, as the 5 can add a heavy hand to the delicate air. The opportunity is to use your voice as a tool for empowerment and change."}}	{"title": "The Powerful Voice of Change", "content": "To be born on 5 Iq' is to be a force of nature, gifted with the power of the spoken word and the drive to use it. You possess a dynamic, energetic presence that stirs things up wherever you go. Tone 5 gives you a practical, work-oriented nature, while Iq' grants you the inspiration of the wind and a quick, agile mind. You are the person who not only has the great idea but also the charisma to sell it to the room. You are likely drawn to communications, media, teaching, or politics—any field where your voice can influence the material world.\\n\\nYour life path is one of empowerment through communication. You are here to speak for those who cannot speak, to clear the fog of confusion with your clarity, and to initiate change through your ideas. You are a natural networker, weaving people and concepts together with ease. Unlike the dreamer, you want your words to have a tangible impact; you want to see the results of your message. You have a restless energy that needs to be channeled into work, or else it can turn into anxiety.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 5 Iq' soul is the potential for volatility. Your words carry weight, and you can cause damage if you speak in anger or without thinking. You may also struggle with inconsistency, blowing hot and cold like the wind. There is a risk of becoming a workaholic, driven by a nervous energy that never lets you rest. Your lesson is to master your breath—to pause before you speak and to listen as much as you talk. When you align your powerful voice with the stillness of the center, your words become spells that can reshape reality."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d0c8cd", "primary": "#101210", "secondary": "#333334"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.859081	2026-04-25 13:46:58.010693
168	13	12	12	Tz'i'	On the twelfth day, nothing can remain vague.\n\nThe storm has stripped away too much for that. The road behind you, the things released, the ceremony, the forest, the offerings—all of it has brought the caravan to a place where truth stands plainly among you. Not as accusation, and not as abstract virtue, but as something practical and necessary.\n\nThe laboring traveler is no longer simply someone being cared for. Their struggle has become the central truth around which everyone's choices now revolve. Either the caravan will meet this moment in love, or it will fail it. There is no middle ground left.\n\nYou see the truth of each person more clearly now. The restless one, who once seemed ruled only by impatience, reveals a fierce loyalty when asked to remain. The traveler who carried heaviness reveals a tenderness sharpened by suffering. The one who has held space from the beginning reveals not control, but devotion. Their calm has never been distance. It has been love disciplined into service.\n\nAnd you see yourself as well.\n\nYou are no longer a witness moving safely along the edge of other people's lives. You are implicated now, woven into the consequences of every gesture, every hesitation, every act of courage. The truth is simple and immense: to love something is to become responsible to it.\n\nThis realization does not crush you. It steadies you.\n\nWhen the one guiding the labor asks for something, you do not wait to be certain of yourself before moving. You act. You hold. You listen. Around you, the caravan does the same, and in that shared responsiveness there is a form of justice more ancient than rules. Each person giving what they can. Each person protecting what is vulnerable. Each person answering truth with presence.\n\nThe storm continues, but it no longer feels like a force outside the circle. It has become witness. The rain falls in long, even strands, and the whole night seems suspended on the edge of revelation.	There is a clarity available today that may feel both grounding and confronting.\n\nAfter everything you've moved through, the truth is no longer abstract. It is present in your choices, in your actions, in the way you show up for yourself and others. You can see more clearly what matters, what aligns, and what does not.\n\nAnd with that clarity comes responsibility.\n\nYou may find yourself in a moment where hesitation is no longer neutral. Where waiting, avoiding, or staying on the edge is no longer an option that feels aligned. Something is asking you to step forward—not perfectly, but honestly.\n\nThere may be a brief moment of tension here. A choice that reveals itself as more significant than it first appeared. You may feel the pull to retreat into uncertainty, to give yourself more time.\n\nBut you already know.\n\nNot everything.\n\nBut enough.\n\nTruth today is not about being right. It is about being real.\n\nAbout allowing your actions to reflect what you understand, even if that understanding is still evolving.\n\nThere is strength in that kind of integrity.\n\nAnd once you move from it, something within you settles into place.	I act in alignment with what I know to be true.	Close your eyes and bring your awareness to your body.\nNotice where you feel aligned and where you feel tension.\nTake a breath into those areas.\nAsk yourself quietly, "What feels true right now?"\nListen without forcing an answer.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine a clear beam of light moving through you, illuminating everything in its path. It does not judge—it simply reveals. As it moves, anything misaligned gently shifts or falls away. What remains feels simple and solid.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Guide of Law", "content": "Tz'i' is the energy of spiritual law, justice, and authority. It is the dog, the loyal companion, and the guide who leads the soul. Tz'i' represents fidelity, accuracy, and the instinct for truth. It points toward integrity and unconditional love. It acts as the compass for the soul.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Law", "Loyalty", "Truth", "Guidance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Crystal of Understanding", "content": "The number 12 represents understanding, wisdom, and the bundling of experience. It is the highest even number, representing a stable, complex wholeness. 12 brings the capacity to understand the 'why' of the journey and to synthesize lessons. In the Kawoq trecena, 12 helps us understand the purpose of the storm. We see the justice in the cleansing.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Wisdom", "Synthesis", "Community", "Review"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Reflect on the 'rules' you live by; are they true for you?", "Seek legal or spiritual counsel.", "Practice loyalty to your own soul.", "Meditate on the concept of 'divine justice' vs. human judgment.", "Trust your instinct to guide you to the right path."], "title": "The Wisdom of Justice", "content": "12 Tz'i' is a day of profound clarity regarding the laws of life. The wisdom of the 12 meets the justice of Tz'i'. Today, we understand that the storm was not a punishment, but a correction. We see the love behind the law. It is a day to align our lives with our highest integrity, not out of fear, but out of understanding. The energy is supportive, loyal, and wise. It is a time to review our path and to commit to walking in truth. We are guided by a deep, internal compass that knows the way home."}}	{"title": "The Wise Judge", "content": "To be born on 12 Tz'i' is to be a pillar of wisdom and integrity. You possess a deep understanding of human nature and the laws that govern it. You are the wise judge, the counselor, the one who can see the truth in a tangle of lies. But your justice is tempered with the compassion of the 12; you seek to understand the 'why' behind the crime. You are loyal to a fault and deeply committed to the people and causes you love.\\n\\nYour life path is one of upholding the truth. You are here to bring order out of chaos and to guide others toward their own integrity. You may work in law, administration, or spiritual guidance. You have a scholarly mind and a faithful heart.\\n\\nYour challenge is judgment. You have such high standards that you can be hard on yourself and others. You may struggle to forgive betrayal. Your lesson is unconditional love. When you realize that we are all learning the law of love, you become a true guide, leading with a lantern instead of a gavel."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a1d1c6", "primary": "#121e1e", "secondary": "#335c60"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.83791	2026-04-25 14:25:01.125504
158	13	2	2	Ajpu	As the hours pass, the figures around you begin to take shape, no longer just silhouettes in the rain but distinct presences moving within it.\n\nThere is one who walks with restless energy, their gaze always searching ahead, as though the horizon might offer an escape if only they could reach it. Their movements are quick, almost impatient, cutting against the steady rhythm of the caravan. Not far from them, another traveler struggles beneath an invisible weight, their posture slightly collapsed, their breath uneven, as though the storm has settled within them rather than around them.\n\nAt first, you see only the contrast between them—the urgency of one, the heaviness of the other. But as the storm continues, something changes.\n\nA soft glow spreads through the clouds, not quite lightning, not quite sunlight. For a brief moment, the rain catches the light in a way that transforms it, each drop turning warm and luminous as it falls. In that glow, the travelers around you shift in your perception.\n\nThey do not appear broken or incomplete.\n\nThey appear human in the fullest sense—carrying weight, yes, but also carrying something steady beneath it.\n\nThe restless traveler pauses for just a moment, their expression softening as they look toward someone beside them. The one who struggles lifts their head slightly, meeting another's gaze, and in that quiet exchange, something unspoken passes between them.\n\nYou feel it too, a recognition that what you are witnessing is not simply contrast, but connection. Each person holds both strain and strength, shadow and light, and the storm reveals both without preference.\n\nAs the glow fades and the rain returns to its muted rhythm, you continue walking, seeing them differently than before.	There is a quiet mirror moving through your life today, and it is not subtle.\n\nYou may find yourself noticing the contrast in others more sharply—their contradictions, their strengths, their struggles, the ways they shine and the ways they falter. It might be tempting to sort these observations quickly, to decide what is admirable and what is not, what aligns with you and what doesn't.\n\nBut something deeper is happening beneath that instinct.\n\nWhat you are seeing is not just them.\n\nIt is the full spectrum of what it means to be human, reflected back at you in motion.\n\nToday carries a kind of golden illumination—not loud or blinding, but steady and revealing. It doesn't erase imperfection. It highlights the coexistence of everything. The light doesn't cancel the shadow. It lives beside it, within it, through it.\n\nYou may feel pulled between two ways of being. One that seeks clarity, direction, forward motion. Another that asks you to slow down, to feel, to remain present with what is not resolved. Neither is wrong. Neither needs to win.\n\nBalance today is not about choosing one side.\n\nIt is about allowing both to exist without collapsing into conflict.\n\nIn your relationships, this may look like softening your certainty. Listening longer than usual. Letting someone be more than the role you've unconsciously assigned them.\n\nAnd with yourself, it may look like something even simpler.\n\nLet yourself be both unfinished and whole at the same time.\n\nThere is a quiet kind of divinity in that.	I honor both my strength and my softness as parts of my wholeness.	Close your eyes and bring awareness to your breath.\nInhale slowly, noticing where your body expands.\nExhale gently, noticing where it softens.\nNow bring attention to two parts of yourself—one that feels strong, and one that feels tender.\nYou don't need to fix either one. Just allow them both to exist.\nLet your breath move between them, connecting them.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine two currents of water flowing in opposite directions within you—one warm, one cool. Instead of clashing, they begin to spiral together, forming a calm, balanced flow. You stand at the center of this movement, steady and aware. The storm above you pauses, as if honoring your ability to hold both forces without breaking.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Solar Hero", "content": "Ajpu is the energy of the Sun, the hero, and the blowgunner. It represents the divine light within humanity and the quest for spiritual truth. Ajpu is the warrior of the light who overcomes darkness through courage and clarity. It reminds us of our own divinity and our connection to the source. It is the certainty of the sunrise after the long night.", "keywords": ["Sun", "Hero", "Divinity", "Light", "Purpose"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "The number 2 represents polarity, relationship, and the dynamic tension between opposites. It is the interaction between the self and the other, the masculine and the feminine. 2 brings choices and mirrors into focus. In the Kawoq trecena, it asks us to find the balance within the storm. It is the lightning and the thunder, the rain and the earth, interacting to create life.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Reflection", "Connection", "Balance", "Duality"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Look someone in the eyes and silently acknowledge their divinity.", "Seek balance between your spiritual ideals and your human reality.", "Collaborate on a creative project; two suns shine brighter.", "Stand in the sunlight and feel it recharging your solar plexus.", "Practice 'noble speech'—words that uplift and clarify."], "title": "The Golden Duality", "content": "2 Ajpu brings a brilliant light to the cleansing process. The storm of the previous day clears the air for the Sun to shine. Today, the theme is seeing the divine in the other. It is a day to balance our human relationships with spiritual truth. The 2 brings partnership, and Ajpu brings holiness. This combination asks: Can you see the god or goddess in your partner? Can you hold your own light while honoring the light in another? It is a powerful day for clarity in relationships, where the 'storm' of emotion settles into a golden understanding of mutual purpose."}}	{"title": "The Partner of Light", "content": "To be born on 2 Ajpu is to be a mirror of the divine for everyone you meet. You possess a radiant warmth and a natural nobility that inspires others to be their best selves. You understand the duality of the human experience—that we are both mud and starlight—and you navigate this paradox with grace. You are a natural partner, thriving in one-on-one connections where you can shine your light on another and have it reflected back.\\n\\nYour life path is one of spiritual partnership and the search for truth. You are a 'hunter' of wisdom, using your clarity to cut through confusion. You are likely drawn to the arts, performance, or leadership roles where you can embody the hero archetype. However, you are not a solo hero; you need a co-pilot, a muse, or a dedicated team to fully activate your power.\\n\\nYour challenge is expectation. You hold yourself and others to very high standards, which can lead to disappointment when the messy reality of life intervenes. Your lesson is to find the holiness in the imperfection. When you learn to love the human as much as the divine, you become a true luminary, teaching the world that every relationship is a sacred encounter."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#ead294", "primary": "#171a18", "secondary": "#614635"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#bea6b1", "primary": "#1d1c2b", "secondary": "#5a5170"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#bba4a4", "primary": "#1e1a3d", "secondary": "#56497d"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#e3ad89", "primary": "#1e1723", "secondary": "#6d4a53"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.834433	2026-04-25 14:25:01.112223
206	16	11	11	Tijax	The Crystal Mind is awake, pulsating with blue light. But its clarity reveals a hard truth: half the plants in your Veldt are weeds. Beautiful, glowing, but parasitic vines are choking the true growth. You have been nurturing *everything*, but not everything belongs.\n\nYou pick up a shard of obsidian—the blade of Tijax. It is heavy and cold. You walk into the garden and begin to cut. It feels like a massacre. You slash through thick, glowing vines that hiss as they fall. You pile the debris high. It is ruthless work, but necessary. As the parasites fall, the true plants seem to inhale, standing taller and brighter now that the suffocation is gone. You have edited the world to save it.	The clarity of your success has revealed a hard truth: your garden is full of parasites. Beautiful, glowing, but ultimately suffocating vines are choking the true growth you’ve worked so hard to foster. You’ve been trying to nurture everything, but today the universe hands you a shard of cold obsidian and tells you to cut. This isn't cruelty; it’s a surgery of the spirit. Truth hurts, then it frees. If you want the masterpiece to survive, you have to massacre the illusions that are draining its energy. \n\nThis is a day of 'Cosmic Surgery,' a master-number moment of liberation. Whatever is not aligned with your highest good—be it a toxic habit, a stagnant belief, or a relationship that has become a parasite—needs to be excised. It will feel like a storm that clears the air, leaving everything sharp and bright. Don't believe the lies your ego tells you about 'holding on.' The soul rejoices in the freedom that comes after a necessary ending. Discernment is your blade. Use it with precision. As the debris falls away, you’ll feel the true plants in your life finally exhale, standing taller and brighter now that the suffocation is gone. Edit your world to save it. The lightness on the other side is your reward.	I release the old to make room for the true, finding liberation in every ending.	Sit with your eyes closed and identify one specific thought, habit, or attachment that feels like it is choking your growth. As you inhale, visualize a shard of sharp obsidian in your hand. As you exhale, use the 'blade' of your breath to sharply cut the cord. Feel the immediate lightness as the parasite falls away.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine walking through your inner garden. The air is cold and clear. Use your obsidian shard to ruthlessly edit the glowing vines, leaving only what is true. Hear the hiss of the debris as it falls, and feel the true plants of your soul inhale deeply, finally free to touch the light.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Obsidian Blade of Truth", "content": "Tijax is the nawal of the obsidian blade, the mirror, and the healer. It represents the double-edged sword of truth that cuts away illness and illusion. Tijax is the warrior for the light, the surgeon, and the spark of divinity. Associated with the element of fire and the mineral obsidian, it carries a sharp, decisive, and purifying energy. It is the archetype of the spiritual warrior who is willing to suffer to uncover the truth. In daily life, Tijax manifests as discernment, ending relationships or habits, and sudden healing crises. Its shadow aspect can be cruelty, gossip, or a tongue that cuts too deep. Tijax teaches us that sometimes we must wound in order to heal.", "keywords": ["Healing", "Truth", "Cutting", "Discernment", "Purification"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Dissolution", "content": "Tone 11 is the energy of dissonance, stripping away, and liberation. Unlike the stability of the 10, the 11 introduces a chaotic variable to test the structure. It is the 'master number' of change. Experientially, Tone 11 feels turbulent, unpredictable, and intense. It is a day where things might fall apart, but only so that what is true can remain. It acts as a filter, discarding what is no longer needed before the final ascent of the cycle. While it can bring anxiety or disruption, its higher expression is freedom and the clearing of space. It is the wind that shakes the dead leaves from the tree.", "keywords": ["Change", "Liberation", "Release", "Dissonance", "Clearing"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Identify one thing you need to release and actively cut it loose.", "Clean your physical space; throw away broken or useless items.", "Have the difficult conversation you've been avoiding (with care).", "Practice discernment; don't believe everything you think.", "Allow strong emotions to surface and release without judgment."], "title": "The Great Liberation", "content": "When the dissolving force of Tone 11 meets the cutting blade of Tijax, we experience a day of radical purification. 11 Tijax is the 'Cosmic Surgery.' The energy today is intense, uncompromising, and ultimately liberating. It is not a day for holding on; it is a day for letting go. Whatever is not aligned with your highest good—be it a habit, a belief, or a relationship—is likely to be challenged or cut away today. It feels like a storm that clears the air, leaving everything sharp and bright. While this can feel disruptive or painful to the ego, the soul rejoices in the freedom. This combination offers the power to break addictions and sever karmic cords that have held you back for lifetimes. The challenge is to surrender to the cut, knowing that Tijax only removes what is festering. The opportunity is to step out of the debris of the old self, lighter and more true than before."}}	{"title": "The Liberating Healer", "content": "To be born on 11 Tijax is to be a powerful agent of transformation and a seeker of ultimate truth. You possess a sharp, penetrating mind and a spirit that refuses to be caged. You are the breaker of chains, the one who comes into a stagnant system and shakes it up to reveal what is real. Tone 11 gives you a non-conformist, sometimes rebellious edge, while Tijax gifts you with the discernment of the surgeon—you know exactly where to cut to excise the rot. You are likely drawn to the healing arts, social activism, or any path that involves revealing the truth beneath the surface.\\n\\nYour life path is one of liberation—for yourself and others. You are not here to maintain the status quo. You are here to question it, test it, and if it is false, destroy it so that something better can be built. This can make you an intense presence; people either love your honesty or fear it. You have a unique ability to help people break through their own illusions and addictions. You are a mirror, reflecting back to the world both its beauty and its ugliness without filter.\\n\\nThe challenge for an 11 Tijax soul is the intensity of your own energy. You can be prone to conflict, restlessness, or being overly critical. The blade you carry can hurt others if not wielded with compassion. You may also experience a life of many changes and upheavals, as you are constantly shedding your own skins. Your growth comes from learning that the ultimate healing is love, not just surgery. When you soften your approach and use your blade to carve space for light rather than just to attack the dark, you become a holy warrior of the highest order."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d1b496", "primary": "#101110", "secondary": "#49362f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.855484	2026-04-25 14:38:01.325628
210	17	2	2	Kawoq					{"nawal": {"title": "The Compassionate Storm", "content": "Kawoq is the nawal of the storm, the turtle, and the midwife. It represents the community, the family bloodline, and the power of feminine cleansing. Kawoq is the energy of the rain that washes away the dust and nourishes the crops. Associated with the element of water and the color green/blue, it carries a fluid, emotional, and collective energy. It is the archetype of the caregiver who holds space for birth and rebirth. In daily life, Kawoq manifests as family gatherings, emotional release, and the protection of the vulnerable. Its shadow aspect can be emotional overwhelm, lack of boundaries, or 'smothering' care. Kawoq teaches us that we are all drops in the same ocean.", "keywords": ["Community", "Compassion", "Cleansing", "Rebirth", "Midwife"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "Tone 2 introduces the concept of the 'other.' It is the energy of polarity, partnership, and the dynamic tension between opposites. If Tone 1 is the solitary point, Tone 2 is the line connecting two points, creating relationship. This number governs the mysteries of duality: light and dark, masculine and feminine, inner and outer. Experientially, Tone 2 often brings choices or presents situations where you must weigh two sides of a coin. It is a day of reflection, where the world acts as a mirror to your internal state. While it can bring the challenge of indecision or conflict, its higher expression is balance and cooperation. It teaches that separation is an illusion and that opposing forces are actually complementary halves of a greater whole.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Reflection", "Connection", "Balance", "Choice"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Check in deeply with your partner or a close family member about their emotional state.", "Create a safe container for a difficult conversation to take place.", "Allow yourself to be vulnerable; let the 'storm' of your feelings be seen.", "Practice active listening; be the midwife for someone else's truth.", "Cleanse your shared living spaces with water or smoke."], "title": "The Shared Storm of Rebirth", "content": "When the duality of Tone 2 meets the storm energy of Kawoq, we encounter a day of relational cleansing. 2 Kawoq is the 'Partnership in the Storm.' The energy today highlights the emotional dynamics within our closest relationships and families. It is a time when hidden feelings may bubble to the surface like a geyser, demanding to be seen and washed away. This is not a gentle rain; it is a collaborative purification. Relationships are tested today, but also deepened. If you can navigate the storm together, the bond becomes stronger. It is a powerful day for couples or families to address shared traumas or to support each other through a birthing process—be it of a child, a project, or a new way of being. The challenge is to not drown in the emotional deluge of the other person. The opportunity is to be the anchor for each other while the waters of change wash through."}}	{"title": "The Compassionate Partner of Renewal", "content": "To be born on 2 Kawoq is to be a soul deeply deeply attuned to the emotional currents of relationships and the family unit. You are the ultimate partner in times of crisis, the one who stays steady when the storm hits. Tone 2 gives you a natural inclination toward duality and connection; you understand yourself best when in relationship with another. Kawoq gifts you with the empathy of the midwife and the protective instinct of the turtle. You are likely the person who mediates family disputes or provides a shoulder to cry on, instinctively knowing how to help others navigate their emotional rebirths.\\n\\nYour life path is one of balancing your own needs with the needs of the collective. You are a natural caregiver, but unlike the solitary healer, you do your best work in tandem with others. You may be drawn to couples therapy, midwifery, community building, or any field where you can help pairs or groups find harmony. You have a talent for washing away old resentments and bringing fresh energy into stagnant relationships. Your presence is soothing yet powerful, like a rainstorm that clears the humidity.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 2 Kawoq soul is the tendency to become enmeshed. You feel the emotions of your partner or family so intensely that you may lose track of where they end and you begin. You might attract chaotic partners because your soul seeks to 'heal' or 'birth' them into their potential. Your lesson is to learn that you can support someone without carrying their storm for them. When you establish healthy boundaries, your capacity for compassion becomes a true gift rather than a burden, allowing you to be a lighthouse in the rain."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#8bbbb4", "primary": "#101c1a", "secondary": "#374f4e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.857718	2026-04-25 13:46:58.007178
170	14	1	1	Kej					{"nawal": {"title": "The Guardian of the Wild", "content": "Kej is the energy of the deer, the sovereign of the wilderness, and the keeper of the four directions. It represents strength, agility, and a deep, harmonious connection with the natural world. Kej carries the energy of authority that is earned through grace rather than force. It is the alert sensitivity of the deer, sensing shifts in the wind, and the sturdy legs that can climb the mountain. It asks us to stand tall, ground our energy, and find our rightful place within the ecosystem of life.", "keywords": ["Nature", "Strength", "Balance", "Leadership", "Harmony"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of the Wild", "content": "The number 1 represents the spark of creation, the unity of all things, and the seed that contains the potential for the entire cycle. It is the beginning, the impulse to exist, and the singular focus required to start a new journey. In the Kej trecena, the 1 energy initiates a cycle of grounding, balance, and reclaiming our wild sovereignty. It is the first hoofprint on the trail. It asks for a clear intention regarding how you wish to walk on the earth and how you will balance the four directions of your life.", "keywords": ["Unity", "Initiation", "Potential", "Seed", "Focus"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Go into nature and introduce yourself to the land.", "Stand barefoot on the earth to initiate a ground connection.", "Set an intention for balance in the four areas of your life.", "Move your body with strength and grace; do yoga or hike.", "Claim your authority in a situation where you have been passive."], "title": "Initiating the Path of Balance", "content": "1 Kej initiates a 13-day cycle of strength, balance, and deep connection to nature. Today, the seed of authority is planted. The singular focus of the 1 combines with the stabilizing power of the Deer. It is a day to reclaim your personal sovereignty and to stand firmly on your own two feet. The energy is wild but graceful. It asks you to step out of the artificial cages of modern life and remember your wild nature. It is a time to set intentions for physical health, leadership, and harmony with the earth. The Deer invites us to walk a path of beauty and strength."}}	{"title": "The Sovereign of Nature", "content": "To be born on 1 Kej is to be a natural leader with a wild heart. You carry the energy of the 'first deer,' the pioneer of the forest. You possess a strong physical presence and a natural authority that commands respect without needing to shout. You are deeply connected to the earth and the four directions, often feeling a need to be outdoors to feel like yourself. You are a guardian of the natural order, with an instinct for balance and harmony.\\n\\nYour life path is one of reclaiming sovereignty. You are independent and may struggle with authority figures because you answer to a higher, more natural law. You have a sensitive nervous system, alert to the slightest change in your environment. You are here to lead by example, showing others how to walk with strength and grace.\\n\\nYour challenge is dominance vs. grace. The strong energy of the 1 combined with the power of Kej can sometimes make you forceful or stubborn. You may struggle to compromise. Your lesson is to lead with the gentleness of the deer, not just the strength of the stag. When you balance your power with sensitivity, you become a majestic leader who protects the wild and the vulnerable."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#798257", "primary": "#0e1511", "secondary": "#36392c"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.840529	2026-04-25 13:46:57.941831
180	14	11	11	No'j					{"nawal": {"title": "The Universal Mind", "content": "No'j is the energy of the brain, the intellect, and wisdom. It represents the power of thought to shape reality. No'j is the connection to the universal mind and the capacity for logic, science, and philosophy. It is the earth shaking with the power of an idea. It asks us to harmonize our human intelligence with the wisdom of the earth.", "keywords": ["Wisdom", "Intellect", "Knowledge", "Thought", "Earth"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Resolution", "content": "The number 11 represents dissonance, clearing, and the testing of the structure. It has a high, thin vibration that shakes loose the non-essential. 11 is the energy of 'sorting'—separating the grain from the chaff. In the Kej trecena, 11 challenges our intellect to find a higher wisdom.", "keywords": ["Dissonance", "Clearing", "Testing", "Resolution", "Change"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Challenge a long-held belief.", "Brainstorm without limits; write down every idea.", "Let go of 'being right' in favor of learning.", "Spend time in nature to ground your racing thoughts.", "Seek knowledge that disrupts your current worldview."], "title": "Clearing the Mind", "content": "11 No'j is a day of intense mental clearing. The dissonance of the 11 shakes the mind of No'j. In the Kej trecena, this is a day to break through limited thinking patterns. It is a day of 'brainstorms'—sudden flashes of insight that can be disruptive but clarifying. The energy asks us to let go of old ideas, rigid beliefs, and mental clutter. It is a powerful day for problem-solving, provided you are willing to look at things from a radically different angle. The mind expands to encompass the wild wisdom of nature."}}	{"title": "The Radical Thinker", "content": "To be born on 11 No'j is to be a revolutionary of the mind. You possess a brilliant, restless intellect that is constantly questioning the status quo. You are not satisfied with easy answers; you want to know the truth, even if it shakes the foundations. You are a natural innovator, scientist, or philosopher who sees the world differently. You have a high-frequency mental energy that can be both genius and chaotic.\\n\\nYour life path is one of expanding human knowledge. You are here to break the molds of conventional thinking. You learn through dissonance, often finding your greatest insights in the midst of confusion. You have a deep connection to the earth's wisdom, but you process it through a highly active mind.\\n\\nYour challenge is mental overload. Your brain never stops, which can lead to anxiety or burnout. You may also be misunderstood by those who prefer linear thinking. Your lesson is to ground your brilliance. When you connect your high-flying ideas with the practical needs of the earth, you become a visionary sage, solving the problems of the future with the wisdom of the ages."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c5dbd9", "primary": "#1a2324", "secondary": "#577583"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.843947	2026-04-25 13:46:57.945228
225	18	4	4	E'	You follow the golden vein through the dark for what feels like hours. The shaking of the ground subsides, replaced by a deep, resonant stillness.\n\nThe path ends abruptly at the edge of a vast chasm. Below, a river of magma churns, silent and heavy, too wide to jump and too hot to approach.\n\nBut spanning the gap is a structure that defies the chaos around it. It is a bridge, but not made of stone or metal. It is constructed of smooth, white, interlocking struts that look organically grown—like ivory, or bone.\n\nIt looks fragile against the backdrop of fire. The struts are thin, forming a geometric lattice that seems too delicate to hold a traveler’s weight. There are no handrails. Just a narrow spine of white bone hovering over the abyss.\n\nYou hesitate. Your mind—still racing from the twitching energy of the slate fields—screams that this is unsafe. That you need something thicker, heavier, more armored.\n\nBut the golden vein you’ve been following flows right up to the bridge and merges into it, turning the white bone translucent and humming with light.\n\nYou realize that in this world, strength isn’t about bulk. It’s about alignment. The bridge stands because every piece is perfectly placed, every angle calculated to distribute the load. It is pure structure. Pure intent.\n\nYou place one foot on the bridge. It does not sway. It feels solid, rooted, as if it is an extension of the earth’s core. You take another step. Then another.\n\nHalfway across, you stop. Suspended over the fire, you feel a sudden, profound sense of stability. The chaos is below you, but you are not *in* it. You are held by a structure that knows exactly what it is.\n\nYou look at your feet. They are steady. You look ahead. The path continues, straight and clear, cutting through the smoke.\n\nYou breathe out, and for the first time since you fell, your shoulders drop. You are safe. You are supported. You are walking the road.	Today brings the medicine of gravity. If your mind feels like a balloon floating away, look at your feet. Wiggle your toes. The road appears only when you decide to walk it.\n\nYou might be waiting for a sign, or for the fear to vanish. Stop waiting. Just take the next step. It doesn’t have to be a leap; it just has to be real. Grounding isn’t about stopping; it’s about moving with traction.	I am safe, supported, and guided on my journey.	Stand comfortably. Imagine you are standing in the center of a great square. Turn your attention to the East—the direction of new beginnings. Breathe in red light. Turn your attention to the West—the direction of transformation. Breathe in black or blue light.\n\nTurn to the South—the direction of the harvest. Breathe in yellow light. Turn to the North—the direction of wisdom. Breathe in white light.\n\nFeel these four pillars of light surrounding you, holding you in a perfect, protective cube. You are the center. You are the axis. You are stable.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Pathfinder of Destiny", "content": "E' is the nawal of the path, the road, and the journey. It represents the destiny that unfolds as we walk, the physical roads we travel, and the spiritual path of life. E' is the explorer, the guide, and the energy of movement toward a destination. Associated with the element of air (and sometimes earth) and the color white, it carries a forward-moving, adventurous energy. It is the archetype of the traveler who gains wisdom through experience. In daily life, E' manifests as travel, starting a new venture, or seeking a better way. Its shadow aspect can be aimlessness, restlessness, or the refusal to commit to a direction. E' teaches us that the destination is less important than the wisdom gathered along the way.", "keywords": ["Journey", "Path", "Exploration", "Guidance", "Destiny"]}, "number": {"title": "The Foundation of Form", "content": "Tone 4 is the energy of stability, structure, and definition. After the movement of 3, the 4 establishes a base, like the four walls of a house or the four legs of a table. It represents the four directions (East, West, North, South) and the four elements (Earth, Air, Fire, Water), grounding spiritual energy into physical reality. Experientially, Tone 4 feels calm, ordered, and reliable. It is a day for planning, organizing, and establishing boundaries. It brings the vague potential of the earlier numbers into concrete form. While it offers safety and predictability, its shadow can be rigidity, stagnation, or being 'boxed in.' It is the number of the builder who lays the cornerstone.", "keywords": ["Structure", "Balance", "Grounding", "Manifestation", "Stability"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Map out your goals for the next month with concrete steps.", "Take a walk in a structured environment (a park, a labyrinth).", "Commit to a specific direction in your life.", "Prepare the logistics for an upcoming trip or project.", "Reflect on the 'foundation' of your life path; is it stable?"], "title": "Grounding the Journey", "content": "When the stabilizing force of Tone 4 meets the traveling energy of E', we experience a day of 'Solid Progress.' 4 E' is the paved road. It is not the wild, overgrown trail; it is the structured path that leads surely to the destination. Today is about grounding your path and exploring within a container. The energy supports planning a trip, mapping out a career move, or establishing the steps needed to reach a goal. It feels reliable and purposeful. 4 E' reminds us that freedom (E') requires a certain amount of discipline (4). If we want to travel far, we need a map and supplies. This is an excellent day to check your compass and ensure you are heading in the right direction. The challenge is to not let the planning replace the journeying. The opportunity is to build a road that others can follow."}}	{"title": "The Builder of the Road", "content": "To be born on 4 E' is to be a pragmatic explorer and a reliable guide. You possess a soul that loves the journey but also respects the map. Tone 4 gives you a need for security, structure, and order, while E' calls you to explore the world and seek your destiny. You are the person who doesn't just wander aimlessly; you build the roads, bridges, and waystations that make travel possible for everyone else. You are methodical in your progress, taking one solid step at a time.\\n\\nYour life path is one of disciplined discovery. You are not a risk-taker in the reckless sense; you take calculated risks. You may be drawn to logistics, urban planning, tour guiding, or research—fields where you can explore the unknown within a structured framework. People trust you to lead them because you are prepared. You always have the backup plan, the supplies, and the knowledge of the terrain. You find comfort in the rhythm of the road, the steady putting of one foot in front of the other.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 4 E' soul is the tension between safety and adventure. You may become too rigid in your plans, refusing to take a detour even when the spirit calls. You might struggle with the unpredictable nature of life, wanting a guarantee before you take the first step. There is a risk of staying on the 'known road' and missing the magic of the wilderness. Your lesson is to trust that your internal compass is stable enough to handle the unknown. When you allow for spontaneity within your structure, your journey becomes a true adventure of the soul."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#7ccabe", "primary": "#101613", "secondary": "#38554c"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#a68a6e", "primary": "#16182c", "secondary": "#38384a"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#b5c6ca", "primary": "#396477", "secondary": "#618594"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#a79597", "primary": "#32151c", "secondary": "#653f48"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.866832	2026-04-25 13:46:58.032053
229	18	8	8	Ajmaq	The descent from the spire is easier than the climb. Gravity feels like a friend now, guiding you down the far side of the mountain. The air grows warmer again, but it has lost the sharp, sulfuric bite of the early days. Now, it smells sweet—like burning copal and warm honey.\n\nAt the base of the spire, you find a hidden entrance in the rock. It isn’t a dark hole; it glows with a soft, amber light. You step inside.\n\nYou are in a cavern, but the walls are not made of stone. They are coated in layers of ancient, fossilized resin—amber as tall as a cathedral. The light from outside filters through it, turning the entire space into a golden sanctuary.\n\nAnd you are not alone.\n\nDrifting through the golden air are translucent, smoky shapes. They look like you. There is the version of you that made that mistake three years ago. There is the version of you that stayed silent when you should have spoken. There is the version of you that hurt someone you loved.\n\nThey do not look at you with malice. They look tired. They are waiting.\n\nYou realize they are ghosts of your own making—the debts you thought you had to carry forever. But in this light, you see them for what they are: lessons that have already been learned.\n\nA deep peace settles over you. You understand that you don’t have to punish yourself to be a good person. The debt is paid not by suffering, but by release.\n\nYou stand in the center of the amber cave and speak a single word of forgiveness. It resonates in the warm air like a bell.\n\nOne by one, the smoky shapes dissolve into the light. They are not erased; they are integrated. They become part of the glow that lights your way.\n\nYou leave the cave lighter than you have ever been. The backpack of rocks you didn’t know you were wearing is gone.	You are carrying a backpack of rocks called "guilt." Today, the universe gives you permission to put it down. You don’t need to carry the past to honor it.\n\nThe energy today is sweet, like honey on a wound. It asks you to stop judging your own history so harshly. You did the best you could with what you knew. Let that be enough. To forgive yourself is the most powerful magic there is.	I forgive myself for the past and step into the harmony of the present.	Sit quietly. Visualize a cord connecting you to a past version of yourself—one who is hurting or holding onto guilt. See this cord clearly.\n\nImagine a pair of golden scissors in your hand. With a gentle snip, cut the cord. Watch as the ends retract and dissolve into light.\n\nSee that past version of yourself smile and fade away, free. Feel the space that opens up in your own energy field. You are free.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Owl of Forgiveness", "content": "Ajmaq is the nawal of the owl, the ancestors, and the sinner/saint. It represents the human condition in all its flaw and glory. Ajmaq is the energy of forgiveness, reconciliation, and the wisdom that comes from making mistakes. Associated with the element of earth and the spirit world, it carries a soft, solemn, and deeply compassionate energy. It is the archetype of the elder who looks back on life with understanding rather than judgment. In daily life, Ajmaq manifests as curiosity, the questioning of authority, and the healing of ancestral lines. Its shadow aspect can be guilt, shame, or the refusal to learn from the past. Ajmaq teaches us that our imperfections are the cracks where the light enters.", "keywords": ["Forgiveness", "Ancestors", "Wisdom", "Redemption", "Curiosity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Harmonious Weaver", "content": "Tone 8 is the energy of resonance, justice, and the octave. Following the peak of the 7, the 8 represents the return to the material world but with a higher frequency. It is the number of the 'infinite loop' (infinity symbol), representing the continuous flow of spirit into matter and back again. Experientially, Tone 8 feels harmonious, balanced, and ceremonial. It is often associated with the male energy or the father, bringing structure that honors the spirit. It is a day of resonance, where actions echo loudly. While it fosters integrity and wholeness, its shadow can be rigidity or a dogmatic adherence to form over feeling. It is the weaver who tightens the threads to create a strong cloth.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Justice", "Resonance", "Infinity", "Ceremony"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a ceremony to honor your ancestors.", "Write a letter of forgiveness to yourself or someone else.", "Reflect on the 'mistakes' of your life and what they taught you.", "Clear the energy in your home to welcome ancestral blessings.", "Practice 'Kintsugi' of the soul—honoring your broken places with gold."], "title": "Harmonizing the Past", "content": "When the resonant structure of Tone 8 meets the forgiving nature of Ajmaq, we encounter a day of 'Ancestral Harmony.' 8 Ajmaq is the energy of acceptance and forgiveness. It is a powerful day for healing the family line and making peace with the past. The energy feels like a ceremonial pardon—a formal release of old debts and grudges. 8 Ajmaq supports us in seeing the wisdom in our mistakes and weaving them into the tapestry of our lives. It is a day to honor the ancestors, not with fear, but with gratitude for the lessons they passed down. The energy is gentle yet structured, providing a safe container for vulnerability. The challenge is to face the shame or guilt that may surface. The opportunity is to transform that lead into gold, finding the wholeness (8) that comes from accepting our humanity (Ajmaq)."}}	{"title": "The Weaver of Ancestral Wisdom", "content": "To be born on 8 Ajmaq is to be a keeper of the lineage and a harmonizer of the past. You possess an old soul that carries the weight and the wisdom of those who came before you. Tone 8 gives you a sense of balance, justice, and ceremonial structure, while Ajmaq grants you deep compassion and a connection to the mysteries of the owl. You are the one who remembers the stories, who heals the family rifts, and who understands that life is a complex weave of light and dark. You are likely a natural counselor, historian, or healer, drawn to understanding the human condition.\\n\\nYour life path is one of redemption and integration. You are here to heal the wounds of the past—both your own and your ancestors'. You have a resonant presence that puts others at ease, allowing them to confess their burdens to you. You understand that forgiveness is not a weakness, but a powerful act of spiritual justice. You weave the lessons of the past into a beautiful future. You are often protected by unseen forces and have a knack for landing on your feet.\\n\\nThe challenge for an 8 Ajmaq soul is the tendency to get stuck in the loop of guilt or analysis. You may overthink your actions or carry a sense of responsibility for things that are not yours. You might be prone to secrecy, hiding your true self for fear of judgment. Your lesson is to practice radical self-forgiveness. When you accept your own humanity completely, you become a beacon of grace, showing the world that wholeness includes the broken pieces."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d8b66e", "primary": "#1d1e18", "secondary": "#5e4d35"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#e4c180", "primary": "#613c26", "secondary": "#aa774a"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#dd9355", "primary": "#7b454c", "secondary": "#ac604a"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#c89a5b", "primary": "#402c30", "secondary": "#8f5f3f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.869469	2026-04-25 13:46:58.038792
182	14	13	13	Kawoq					{"nawal": {"title": "The Compassionate Storm", "content": "Kawoq is the energy of the rainstorm, the midwife, and the turtle. It represents the duality of the storm—the force that cleanses and the water that brings life. Kawoq is the energy of the family, the community, and the compassionate cleansing that clears the path for rebirth. It asks us to value the collective.", "keywords": ["Storm", "Midwife", "Compassion", "Community", "Cleansing"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascension of Spirit", "content": "The number 13 represents completion, ascension, and the spirit world. It is the final step where energy transcends physical form. 13 is a number of great power, sensitivity, and psychic expansion. It brings the cycle to a close and offers a connection to the ancestors. In the Kej trecena, 13 brings the rebirth of the community.", "keywords": ["Ascension", "Completion", "Spirit", "Ancestors", "Renewal"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Celebrate the end of the cycle with your 'tribe.'", "Allow yourself to feel the full range of your emotions.", "Offer a prayer for the healing of the world.", "Visualize a protective shell of light around your loved ones.", "Step into the rain and feel the blessing of the spirit."], "title": "Ascending in the Storm", "content": "13 Kawoq is the powerful conclusion to the Kej trecena. The journey of balance and wildness ends in a transcendent storm of compassion. The 13 elevates the energy of Kawoq to a cosmic level. Today, we are washed clean by the spirit world. It is a day of collective rebirth. We realize that our individual strength (Kej) finds its ultimate purpose in the shelter of the community (Kawoq). The energy is intense, emotional, and purifying. We ascend out of the cycle refreshed, connected, and ready to protect the new life that has been born."}}	{"title": "The Cosmic Midwife", "content": "To be born on 13 Kawoq is to be a guardian of collective evolution. You possess a powerful, storm-like energy that is tempered by infinite compassion. You are here to help birth a new world. You are a natural community leader, a healer, and a protector of the vulnerable. You have a psychic connection to the spirit world and the ability to channel vast amounts of energy.\\n\\nYour life path is one of transformation through love. You are the eye of the storm, holding a space of peace while the world changes around you. You are deeply connected to the feminine mysteries and the power of the family. You are a catalyst for healing on a massive scale.\\n\\nYour challenge is overwhelm. You feel the pain of the world as your own. You may struggle to separate your energy from the collective. Your lesson is to be the turtle. When you carry your own sanctuary within you, you can navigate any storm, guiding humanity safely to the other side."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#81cdb5", "primary": "#101d1b", "secondary": "#30605a"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.844731	2026-04-25 13:46:57.946965
244	19	10	10	Kawoq					{"nawal": {"title": "The Compassionate Storm", "content": "Kawoq is the nawal of the storm, the turtle, and the midwife. It represents the community, the family bloodline, and the power of feminine cleansing. Kawoq is the energy of the rain that washes away the dust and nourishes the crops. Associated with the element of water and the color green/blue, it carries a fluid, emotional, and collective energy. It is the archetype of the caregiver who holds space for birth and rebirth. In daily life, Kawoq manifests as family gatherings, emotional release, and the protection of the vulnerable. Its shadow aspect can be emotional overwhelm, lack of boundaries, or 'smothering' care. Kawoq teaches us that we are all drops in the same ocean.", "keywords": ["Community", "Compassion", "Cleansing", "Rebirth", "Midwife"]}, "number": {"title": "The Manifestation of Responsibility", "content": "Tone 10 is the energy of manifestation, collaboration, and the two hands coming together. It represents the realization of the intention set in Tone 1. In the cycle, 10 is where the work hits the physical plane in a concrete way. It is a number of community, agreement, and the solidity of creation. Experientially, Tone 10 feels grounded, productive, and social. It is a day to shake hands, sign contracts, and see the tangible results of your efforts. While it fosters achievement and connection, its shadow can be the heavy weight of responsibility or the pressure to perform for the group. It is the number of the builder who sees the walls rise.", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Collaboration", "Result", "Community"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Host a family dinner or community gathering.", "Engage in a group cleansing ritual.", "Support a friend who is going through a 'birth' process.", "Work on a project that benefits the emotional health of your community.", "Allow yourself to feel the support of your 'turtle shell' (home/family)."], "title": "Manifesting Renewal", "content": "When the manifesting power of Tone 10 meets the storm energy of Kawoq, we experience a day of 'Community Rebirth.' 10 Kawoq is the cleansing rain that brings peaceful renewal to the village. It is a day where the emotional work of the group manifests in a tangible shift. The energy is powerful, fluid, and restorative. 10 Kawoq supports gathering with family or community to heal, to celebrate, or to weather a storm together. It is an excellent day for group therapy, family reunions, or community service that involves cleaning or caring. The energy feels like the fresh smell of ozone after a thunderstorm. The challenge is to navigate the collective emotions without drowning in them. The opportunity is to build a stronger, cleaner, more compassionate community structure."}}	{"title": "The Manifestor of Compassion", "content": "To be born on 10 Kawoq is to be a pillar of emotional strength and a builder of community. You possess a soul that is both nurturing and capable. Tone 10 gives you the ability to manifest results and work well with others, while Kawoq connects you to the deep waters of empathy and the family line. You are the 'Midwife of the Community,' the one who helps birth new projects, new families, and new ways of being. You are the person everyone turns to when they are in crisis because you know how to handle the storm.\\n\\nYour life path is one of creating compassionate structures. You are not just a feeler; you are a doer. You may be drawn to social work, healthcare, community organizing, or education. You have a natural authority when it comes to emotional matters. You build families—biological or chosen—that are strong, resilient, and loving. You are a protector of the vulnerable, using your strength to shield those who cannot shield themselves.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 10 Kawoq soul is the weight of the world's emotions. You can take on too much responsibility for others' feelings, becoming the 'fixer' who burns out. You might struggle to distinguish your own needs from the needs of the group. There is a risk of becoming over-protective or smothering. Your lesson is to learn that you can facilitate healing without doing it *for* others. When you empower people to navigate their own storms, you create a community of strength rather than dependency."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#5ba68c", "primary": "#0d1616", "secondary": "#254446"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.878949	2026-04-25 13:46:58.048763
245	19	11	11	Ajpu					{"nawal": {"title": "The Hero of Light", "content": "Ajpu is the nawal of the sun, the blowgunner, and the hero. It represents the divine spark within the human, the mastery of self, and the triumph of light over darkness. Ajpu is the energy of the warrior who fights for beauty and truth. Associated with the element of fire and the sun, it carries a radiant, confident, and masculine energy. It is the archetype of the artist-warrior who walks the path of holiness in everyday life. In daily life, Ajpu manifests as clarity, leadership, overcoming challenges, and the recognition of one's own divinity. Its shadow aspect can be ego, arrogance, or the testing of one's integrity. Ajpu teaches us that we are the light.", "keywords": ["Divinity", "Heroism", "Sun", "Purpose", "Mastery"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Dissolution", "content": "Tone 11 is the energy of dissonance, stripping away, and liberation. Unlike the stability of the 10, the 11 introduces a chaotic variable to test the structure. It is the 'master number' of change. Experientially, Tone 11 feels turbulent, unpredictable, and intense. It is a day where things might fall apart, but only so that what is true can remain. It acts as a filter, discarding what is no longer needed before the final ascent of the cycle. While it can bring anxiety or disruption, its higher expression is freedom and the clearing of space. It is the wind that shakes the dead leaves from the tree.", "keywords": ["Change", "Liberation", "Release", "Dissonance", "Clearing"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Do something spontaneous and out of character.", "Face a fear head-on and watch it dissolve.", "Let go of a title or role that defines you too narrowly.", "Stand in the sun and ask for clarity.", "Practice 'crazy wisdom'—laugh at the absurdity of life."], "title": "The Liberating Light", "content": "When the dissolving force of Tone 11 meets the solar power of Ajpu, we experience a day of 'Spontaneous Illumination.' 11 Ajpu is the light of the sun breaking through the clouds. The energy is intense, liberating, and unpredictable. It challenges our ego structures and asks us to stand in our true, naked divinity. Today, false masks are stripped away by the brilliance of the light. It is a day where the 'hero' is tested, not by a dragon, but by the chaos of change. The energy supports breaking free from old identities, outdated roles, or the need for approval. It feels like a sudden burst of clarity that changes everything. The challenge is to not be blinded by the intensity or to react with arrogance. The opportunity is to let the light dissolve everything that is not you, leaving only the pure gold of your spirit."}}	{"title": "The Liberated Hero", "content": "To be born on 11 Ajpu is to be a rebel with a divine cause. You possess a spirit that is fierce, free, and radiantly alive. Tone 11 gives you a non-conformist nature and a love for freedom, while Ajpu grants you the charisma and purpose of the Sun Hero. You are here to challenge the status quo, to break the rules, and to show the world what true authenticity looks like. You are not afraid to shine, even if your light makes others uncomfortable. You are a natural leader, but your leadership style is unconventional and transformative.\\n\\nYour life path is one of shedding skins to reveal the light within. You will likely go through many changes in your life, constantly reinventing yourself as you move closer to your core truth. You are an artist of life, using your existence as a canvas for divine expression. You inspire others to break their own chains and to claim their sovereignty. You are a warrior for freedom—spiritual, artistic, and personal.\\n\\nThe challenge for an 11 Ajpu soul is stability. You can be so focused on breaking free that you never build anything lasting. You may struggle with ego, believing that you are above the laws of the common world. There is a risk of burning out, consuming your own fuel in a blaze of glory. Your lesson is to find the sun's steady burn. When you anchor your liberation in a deep sense of purpose, your chaotic light focuses into a laser beam that cuts through darkness and illuminates the path for all."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d8b45d", "primary": "#1b1d1d", "secondary": "#664935"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.879154	2026-04-25 13:46:58.051054
209	17	1	1	Tijax					{"nawal": {"title": "The Obsidian Blade of Truth", "content": "Tijax is the nawal of the obsidian blade, the mirror, and the healer. It represents the double-edged sword of truth that cuts away illness and illusion. Tijax is the warrior for the light, the surgeon, and the spark of divinity. Associated with the element of fire and the mineral obsidian, it carries a sharp, decisive, and purifying energy. It is the archetype of the spiritual warrior who is willing to suffer to uncover the truth. In daily life, Tijax manifests as discernment, ending relationships or habits, and sudden healing crises. Its shadow aspect can be cruelty, gossip, or a tongue that cuts too deep. Tijax teaches us that sometimes we must wound in order to heal.", "keywords": ["Healing", "Truth", "Cutting", "Discernment", "Purification"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Fire", "content": "Tone 1 represents the initial spark of creation, the singularity from which all potential unfolds. It is the number of unity, beginnings, and the pure, unadulterated impulse to exist. Like a seed lying in the dark earth, Tone 1 contains the blueprint for the entire cycle that follows, holding immense power in a concentrated form. Experientially, this energy feels like a sudden clarity or a surge of new intent—a moment where the past falls away and only the future's possibility remains. It is a day of initiation, where your thoughts and actions plant the vibrations that will ripple through the next thirteen days. In its shadow aspect, Tone 1 can feel isolating or overwhelming, a blinding light with no direction. However, when embraced, it offers the profound gift of focus and the authority to define a new narrative.", "keywords": ["Beginnings", "Unity", "Potential", "Initiation", "Focus"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Identify the single biggest energetic drain in your life and decide to remove it.", "Cleanse your physical space of sharp objects or broken glass to honor the blade.", "Write down a truth you have been afraid to admit to yourself.", "Schedule a medical or therapeutic appointment to address a lingering issue.", "Visualize an obsidian knife severing the cords that bind you to old fears."], "title": "Initiating the Sacred Cut", "content": "When the initiating force of Tone 1 meets the cutting power of Tijax, we enter a day of radical surgery for the soul. 1 Tijax is the moment the scalpel touches the skin—the precise beginning of the healing process. This is not a day for hesitation or gentle measures; it is a day to identify exactly what is festering in your life and make the decision to cut it out. The energy is sharp, clear, and uncompromising. It feels like waking up with a sudden realization of what is true and what is false. This combination supports bold moves to sever cords, end toxic patterns, or speak a difficult truth that sets a new cycle in motion. The pain of the cut is real, but it is the pain of liberation, not injury. The challenge is to wield this blade with a steady hand, ensuring that the cut is clean and purposeful, not jagged and reactive. The opportunity is to carve a new path, free from the infections of the past."}}	{"title": "The Warrior of Radical Truth", "content": "To be born on 1 Tijax is to be a living catalyst for truth and transformation. You possess a piercing intellect and a spirit that cannot abide illusion. Like the obsidian blade that symbolizes your sign, you are sharp, precise, and capable of cutting through layers of deception to reach the core of any matter. You are the initiator of healing, often entering people's lives at moments of crisis to help them sever what no longer serves them. Your presence can be intense, as you naturally reflect back the things others try to hide, but your intention is always to heal, never to harm.\\n\\nYour life path is one of purification and spiritual surgery. You are here to clear the way, both for yourself and for your community. Tone 1 gives you a strong sense of independence and leadership; you are often the first to speak up or the first to take action. You may be drawn to professions in medicine, surgery, therapy, or social justice—anywhere that requires a steady hand and a commitment to the truth. You are a warrior for the light, willing to face the darkness that others avoid. While you may walk a solitary path at times, your courage inspires others to face their own shadows.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 1 Tijax soul is learning to sheath the blade. Your honesty can sometimes be brutal, and you may struggle with diplomacy. You might also turn the blade inward, being overly critical or harsh with yourself. It is essential for you to learn that healing also requires softness and recovery time. Your lesson is to balance your capacity for cutting with the capacity for mending. When you learn to wield your truth with compassion, you become not just a warrior, but a holy healer who restores wholeness to the world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a3695d", "primary": "#0d0f0d", "secondary": "#372e28"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.857395	2026-04-25 13:46:57.998344
223	18	2	2	Tz'i'	The ember in your hand is warm, a steady weight that anchors you as you navigate the sharp ridges of the obsidian field. The air here vibrates with a low-frequency growl, the sound of stone grinding against stone deep below the surface.\n\nThe path narrows, squeezed between two rising walls of cooling lava rock. Ahead, the route is blocked.\n\nTwo massive silhouettes stand guard. At first, they look like statues carved from the volcanic rock itself—jagged, dark, and motionless. But as you step closer, veins of blue fire ignite within their chests. They are alive.\n\nGuardians.\n\nThey resemble great, ancient dogs, but made of hardened ash and subterranean heat. One stands to the left, its eyes glowing with a fierce, judging light. It growls, and the sound resonates in your teeth—the vibration of every fear you’ve ever felt, every time you told yourself you weren’t enough.\n\nThe other stands to the right, its posture calm, its eyes holding a steady, golden warmth. It does not growl. It watches. It feels like the truth you ignore when you are too busy being afraid.\n\nYou stop. The heat of the ember in your palm intensifies.\n\nYou realize this isn’t a battle. You cannot fight the rock, and you cannot outrun the fear. This is a choice.\n\nThe guardian on the left snaps its jaws, a warning. *Go back.* The guardian on the right tilts its head, waiting. *Come forward.*\n\nLoyalty splits here. You can stay loyal to your fear—the safety of the known, the comfort of your old debts. Or you can be loyal to the path.\n\nYou take a breath, inhaling the sulfur and the strange, sharp clarity of the air. You turn your gaze away from the growling shadow and fix it on the silent, golden-eyed watcher.\n\n"I am not turning back," you whisper.\n\nYou raise the ember. Its red light reflects in the calm guardian’s eyes. The massive stone head dips in a slow nod. The tension in the air snaps, and the growling guardian on the left stiffens, then crumbles into harmless drifts of ash.\n\nThe path opens.\n\nYou step through the gate of ash and stone, heart pounding but lighter. You have chosen your alliance.	Relationships are mirrors today, reflecting the laws you secretly live by. If the reflection looks distorted, don’t break the glass—adjust your stance.\n\nYou are being asked to choose where your loyalty truly lies. Are you faithful to your potential, or are you devoted to your comfort zone? The energy is sharp but loving. Be fair to others, but be firm with yourself.\n\nLove is not about enabling old patterns. It’s about holding the standard of truth so high that only the real can survive in its presence.	I choose the path of love over the path of fear.	Sit with your spine straight. Close your eyes and bring your awareness to the two sides of your body. Feel the left side, then the right. Imagine one side holds your history, and the other holds your potential.\n\nBreathe into the center channel of your spine. With every inhale, imagine weaving these two sides together. You are not split. You are the bridge between what was and what will be.\n\nVisualize a golden thread of light running from the base of your spine to the crown of your head. This is your inner law. Your truth. Rest in this center line, balanced and whole.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Faithful Guide of Law", "content": "Tz'i' is the nawal of law, justice, and the dog. It represents the principle of divine order and the instinctual guidance that keeps us on the path of truth. Tz'i' is the faithful companion who guards the threshold, ensuring that we remain loyal to our highest purpose and to our community. Associated with the element of fire and the concept of authority, it carries a protective and corrective energy. It is the archetype of the judge, the lawyer, and the loyal friend. In daily life, Tz'i' manifests as questions of ethics, fidelity, and the right use of power. Its shadow aspect can be judgmentality, rigidity, or the corruption of authority. Tz'i' teaches us that true justice is not about rules, but about alignment with cosmic love.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Loyalty", "Faith", "Guidance", "Protection"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "Tone 2 introduces the concept of the 'other.' It is the energy of polarity, partnership, and the dynamic tension between opposites. If Tone 1 is the solitary point, Tone 2 is the line connecting two points, creating relationship. This number governs the mysteries of duality: light and dark, masculine and feminine, inner and outer. Experientially, Tone 2 often brings choices or presents situations where you must weigh two sides of a coin. It is a day of reflection, where the world acts as a mirror to your internal state. While it can bring the challenge of indecision or conflict, its higher expression is balance and cooperation. It teaches that separation is an illusion and that opposing forces are actually complementary halves of a greater whole.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Reflection", "Connection", "Balance", "Choice"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Examine a conflict from the other person's perspective.", "Check your boundaries; are they too loose or too rigid?", "Practice loyalty to a friend who needs support.", "Release a judgment you have been holding against a partner.", " seek to restore balance in a situation that feels unfair."], "title": "The Balance of Justice", "content": "When the duality of Tone 2 meets the law of Tz'i', we encounter a day of 'Relational Justice.' 2 Tz'i' is the energy of the scales weighing the heart. Today, the focus is on fairness within our partnerships and close connections. It challenges 'us vs them' thinking. The energy asks: Are we loyal to our partners? Are we loyal to our own truth within the relationship? It is a day where conflicts may arise, but only to reveal where the balance has been lost. The Dog (Tz'i') is a faithful guide, and paired with the 2, it encourages us to be a faithful mirror to others. This is an excellent day for mediation, legal agreements, or simply having an honest conversation about boundaries. The challenge is to seek justice without being judgmental. The opportunity is to find the sweet spot where loyalty to self and loyalty to other coexist in harmony."}}	{"title": "The Loyal Partner of Truth", "content": "To be born on 2 Tz'i' is to be a person of profound loyalty and a natural seeker of justice within relationships. You possess a binary mind that is constantly weighing right and wrong, fair and unfair. Tone 2 makes you deeply relational; you understand yourself best through your connection to others. Tz'i' gives you a protective, faithful nature that makes you an incredible friend and partner. You are the one who sticks by your loved ones when the world turns against them, provided they are in alignment with your moral code.\\n\\nYour life path is one of balancing the scales. You are drawn to situations where you can mediate, correct injustices, or advocate for the underdog. You may find success in law, counseling, or human resources—any field where human dynamics intersect with rules and ethics. You have a sharp instinct for detecting betrayal or dishonesty. However, you are also capable of great tenderness, offering a safe harbor for those you trust. Your love is not blind; it is eyes-wide-open loyalty.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 2 Tz'i' soul is the tendency to see the world in black and white. You may struggle with the grey areas of human behavior, becoming judgmental or unforgiving when someone makes a mistake. You might also become dependent on a partner, defining your worth by your loyalty to them. Your lesson is to internalize the law of love. When you realize that true justice includes compassion and that everyone is fighting their own battle, your rigidity softens into a powerful, guiding wisdom."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#e6d6be", "primary": "#161510", "secondary": "#64503b"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#d6d3dc", "primary": "#1a1e36", "secondary": "#575a7b"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#d5b0bd", "primary": "#6f6e7f", "secondary": "#9ba4b8"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#996353", "primary": "#1a151a", "secondary": "#42363f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.865257	2026-04-25 13:46:58.028076
247	19	13	13	Iq'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Breath of Spirit", "content": "Iq' is the nawal of the wind, the breath, and the messenger. It represents communication, clarity, and the breath of life. Governs inspiration, change, and purification. Can stir sudden transformation or anger when misaligned. Associated with the element of air and the color white, it carries a swift, changeable, and inspiring energy. It is the archetype of the divine messenger who whispers truth in our ears. In daily life, Iq' manifests as conversation, the internet, travel, and the sudden shifting of circumstances. Its shadow aspect can be impulsiveness, harsh words, or chaos. Iq' teaches us to listen to the spirit.", "keywords": ["Breath", "Words", "Clarity", "Change", "Communication"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascended Renewal", "content": "Tone 13 is the energy of completion, transcendence, and the spirit realm. It is the final step of the cycle, where the energy transforms into a new octave. It represents the ancestors, the universal movement, and the unseen forces. Experientially, Tone 13 feels light, magical, and sometimes ungrounded. It is a day where the rules of the physical world feel less rigid. It marks the end of the trecena, wrapping up the lessons and preparing the seed for the next cycle. While it offers spiritual connection and a sense of accomplishment, its shadow can be spaciness or a feeling of being 'done' before the work is truly finished. It is the spirit rising from the body.", "keywords": ["Completion", "Ascension", "Transformation", "Ancestors", "Spirit"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Practice conscious breathwork or pranayama.", "Send a message you have been afraid to send.", "Allow yourself to change your mind about a major decision.", "Listen to the wind; see what messages it brings.", "Sing, chant, or use your voice to shift your vibration."], "title": "The Ascended Breath", "content": "The transcendent energy of Tone 13 culminates in the wind of Iq', creating a day of 'Ultimate Communication.' 13 Iq' is the winds of change blowing through the spirit gate. The trecena of Tz'i' (Law) ends here, carrying the message of justice to the heavens. The energy is fast, high-frequency, and transformative. It is a day where inspiration strikes like lightning. Words spoken today have the power to alter reality. 13 Iq' connects us to the breath of the ancestors and the voice of the divine. It is a powerful time for prayer, chanting, or delivering a message that needs to be heard. The challenge is the unpredictability; the wind blows where it lists. The opportunity is to let the spirit breathe through you, clearing out the old stagnant air and filling your lungs with the oxygen of a new life."}}	{"title": "The Spirit Messenger", "content": "To be born on 13 Iq' is to be a voice for the spirit world. You possess a mind that is quick, agile, and connected to the divine source. Tone 13 places you at the end of the cycle, giving you a foot in the unseen realms, while Iq' grants you the power of communication and the breath of life. You are a messenger, a catalyst, a bringer of change. You often speak truths that come from 'somewhere else,' surprising even yourself with your wisdom. You are here to circulate energy, ideas, and inspiration.\\n\\nYour life path is one of spiritual transmission. You are not meant to hold onto things; you are meant to let them flow through you. You may be drawn to writing, speaking, media, or travel—ways to spread the word. You have a restless spirit that craves freedom and novelty. You are a natural innovator, always catching the next wave before anyone else sees it. Your presence is like a fresh breeze, clearing the air and waking people up.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 13 Iq' soul is grounding. You can be so ethereal and changeable that you struggle to maintain relationships or finish projects. You may be prone to anxiety, as your nervous system is highly sensitive to the 'winds' of the collective. There is a risk of speaking without thinking, causing chaos with your words. Your lesson is to anchor your breath. When you connect your high-flying inspiration with the stability of the earth, your voice becomes a powerful instrument of divine will, capable of healing and transforming the world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d7c6c8", "primary": "#1b1b18", "secondary": "#5d4b45"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.879482	2026-04-25 13:46:58.053734
259	20	12	12	Kame	The lightning fades. The wind settles. You stand on the penultimate ridge, looking down at the world below. It is so far away.\n\n12 is Understanding. Kame is Death.\n\nYou look down at the valley where you started 12 days ago. You see the fog. You see the scarcity. You see the person you used to be.\n\nYou realize that person had to die for you to be here.\n\nThe climb was a funeral procession for your small self. Every step was a burial of fear. Every breath was a release of the old story.\n\nA ghostly figure stands beside you—translucent, peaceful. It is the Ancestor spirit. It points to the horizon.\n\n*Death is not the end,* it whispers. *It is the elevator.* \n\nYou understand now. Transformation is the mechanism of prosperity. You cannot have the gold if you hold onto the lead. You cannot have the wings if you hold onto the shell.\n\nYou bow to the valley. You thank your old self for surviving. You thank the struggle for pushing you up the mountain.\n\nYou turn your back on the descent. You face the final peak.\n\nYou are ready to ascend.	You are looking back today, but not with sadness. You are looking back with wisdom. The energy of 12 Kame allows you to see the beauty in the endings. You understand why things had to change.\n\nYou have shed a lot of layers to get here. Honor that process. You are lighter now. The past is a foundation, not a residence. Thank it, and turn your face to the future.	I honor the cycles of my life and embrace the wisdom of transformation.	Visualize a beautiful autumn tree. The leaves are gold and red. They fall gently to the ground.\n\nSee the bare branches against the sky. They are strong. They are ready for the winter rest and the spring bloom. Trust the cycle.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Transformer of Worlds", "content": "Kame is the nawal of death, rebirth, and the ancestors. It represents the eternal cycle of transformation and the dimensional gates between worlds. Symbolizes spiritual initiation, death, and rebirth. Associated with the element of spirit and the color yellow or white (bone), it carries a peaceful, absolute, and transcendent energy. It is the archetype of the guide who leads souls through the transition. In daily life, Kame manifests as endings, major life changes, contact with the spirit world, and the need for surrender. Its shadow aspect can be fear of change, morbidity, or clinging to the past. Kame teaches us that death is not the opposite of life, but a part of it.", "keywords": ["Death", "Rebirth", "Transformation", "Courage", "Ancestors"]}, "number": {"title": "The Understanding of the Whole", "content": "Tone 12 is the energy of understanding, gathering, and the retrospective view. It represents the summation of the cycle's lessons before the final transcendence. It is the number of the 'crystal clear' comprehension that comes after the storm of the 11. Experientially, Tone 12 feels communal, settled, and wise. It is a day to gather the scattered pieces and make sense of them. It fosters cooperation and the ability to summarize complex experiences. While it is generally a positive energy, its shadow can be a refusal to move on or looking backward for too long. It is the librarian who organizes the stories.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Unity", "Cooperation", "Summary", "Review"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Visit a place that honors the dead (memorial, cemetery).", "Reflect on the 'deaths' of this trecena and what they taught you.", "Support someone who is grieving.", "Contemplate the cycle of nature; everything changes.", "Offer gratitude for the life you have right now."], "title": "The Collective Transformation", "content": "The synthesizing wisdom of Tone 12 meets the transformative power of Kame to create a day of 'Universal Rebirth.' 12 Kame is the energy of understanding the great cycle of life and death. It is a day to gather the lessons of our losses and see them as part of a greater whole. The energy is peaceful, profound, and communal. It supports collective mourning, honoring the ancestors, and making peace with the impermanence of life. 12 Kame asks us to look at what has died in our lives with gratitude rather than fear. It is a time to close chapters together and to prepare for the new beginning. The challenge is the weight of the collective grief. The opportunity is to feel the deep, interconnected web of souls that supports us through every transition."}}	{"title": "The Wise Transformer", "content": "To be born on 12 Kame is to be a soul guide and a keeper of the mysteries. You possess a wisdom that seems to come from another world. Tone 12 gives you a wide, inclusive perspective, while Kame connects you to the cycles of death and rebirth. You are the one who helps others understand the painful transitions of life. You have a calming presence, often finding yourself at the bedside of the dying or the birthing. You understand that everything is connected and that nothing is ever truly lost.\\n\\nYour life path is one of spiritual midwifery. You are here to help the collective move through its changes. You may be drawn to hospice work, counseling, history, or spirituality. You have a deep respect for the ancestors and may feel called to heal lineage trauma. You are a bridge between the past and the future, helping to summarize the lessons of history so they can be released.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 12 Kame soul is melancholy. You feel the impermanence of life so acutely that it can be hard to engage with the joys of the present. You might struggle to let go, wanting to hold onto the past or the people you have lost. There is a risk of becoming passive, waiting for life to happen to you. Your lesson is to embrace the vitality of the moment. When you accept death as a natural part of life, you become a fearless guide who teaches others how to live fully."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d2c3ba", "primary": "#141516", "secondary": "#514848"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#9fa4a9", "primary": "#1e2226", "secondary": "#5a6065"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#f6f2e5", "primary": "#9c6035", "secondary": "#d2c0a8"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#d4dcdd", "primary": "#545c60", "secondary": "#97a0a3"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.887654	2026-04-25 13:46:58.073355
183	15	1	1	No'j					{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Mind of Earth", "content": "No'j is the archetype of the Earth's intellect, the sacred logic that governs the unfolding of seasons, tectonic shifts, and the migration of birds. It is not merely human intelligence, but 'cosmic wisdom' grounded in physical reality. No'j represents the brain, knowledge, memory, and the ability to convert abstract inspiration into practical solutions. It is the energy of the problem-solver, the scientist, and the sage who understands that true wisdom serves the collective. When aligned, No'j brings clarity, innovative ideas, and a deep connection to ancestral knowing. However, its shadow can lead to overthinking, paralysis by analysis, or the arrogance of believing one's mind is separate from the heart of the world. No'j asks us to harmonize our thoughts with the rhythms of nature, reminding us that the most brilliant ideas are those that support life rather than dominate it.", "keywords": ["Wisdom", "Intellect", "Solutions", "Earth", "Memory"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Unified Thought", "content": "Tone 1 represents the primordial spark, the single point of unity from which all creation unfurls. It is the number of beginnings, initiation, and the concentrated potential of the seed before it breaks the soil. On this day, energy is not yet scattered or complex; it is singular, focused, and profoundly potent. The First Tone asks us to stand in the center of our own existence and recognize the power of a fresh start. It is a vibration of pure intent, where the separation between the dreamer and the dream has not yet occurred. While this energy offers immense creative power, it can also feel overwhelming in its solitude or intensity. It requires a steady hand to plant this seed correctly, for whatever is initiated under the influence of the One will carry the blueprint of its origin throughout the entire cycle. It is the breath before the song, the silence before the word.", "keywords": ["Unity", "Beginnings", "Potential", "Focus", "Initiation"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Plant the seed of a long-term intellectual or creative project today.", "Take time to silence the noise and listen to the single clearest thought arising within you.", "Honor your teachers and the lineage of wisdom that supports your understanding.", "Avoid scattering your mental energy; focus on one core problem to solve.", "Trust that a new cycle of clarity is beginning, even if you cannot see the full path yet."], "title": "The Genesis of Wisdom", "content": "When the initiating power of Tone 1 merges with the intellectual depth of No'j, we experience the genesis of a new consciousness. This is the 'Big Bang' of an idea—a day where a profound insight or solution suddenly crystallizes from the void. 1 No'j is the perfect energy for conceiving a master plan, setting a new educational path, or committing to a discipline of study. The energy here is not about the final product, but about the quality of the intention behind the thought. It is a day to ask: 'What seed of wisdom do I wish to plant for the future?' The combination invites us to unify our logic with our intuition, creating a 'thinking heart' capable of navigating complex challenges. It is a time to honor the ancestors who preserved knowledge for us, and to accept the mantle of responsibility for carrying that wisdom forward. While the mind may race with possibilities today, the lesson is to choose the one thought that resonates with the Earth itself."}}	{"title": "The Architect of New Reality", "content": "To be born on 1 No'j is to be a pioneer of thought, a soul carrying the blueprint for new ways of understanding the world. You possess a mind that is both unified and expansive, capable of seeing the root cause of any situation instantly. As a 1, you are a natural initiator, often preferring to work alone or lead the way rather than follow the crowd. Your life path is dedicated to birthing new systems of knowledge or practical solutions that have never been seen before. You are the spark of genius that ignites the collective mind.\\n\\nYour intelligence is not just abstract; it is deeply practical and earthy. You have a unique ability to take high-concept spiritual or scientific truths and ground them into usable tools for humanity. Whether through science, philosophy, or the arts, you translate the ineffable into the understandable. People are drawn to your clarity and your ability to cut through confusion with a single, well-placed word. You are a natural scholar, a keeper of records, and often a bridge between ancient wisdom and modern innovation.\\n\\nHowever, the weight of the number 1 can sometimes lead to feelings of isolation or the burden of 'knowing too much.' Your challenge is to learn that wisdom is meant to be shared, not hoarded in solitude. You may struggle with overthinking or becoming rigid in your new ideas. Your growth lies in remaining flexible and realizing that your brilliant mind is an instrument of the Earth, meant to serve the community rather than separate you from it."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#abbfd8", "primary": "#0d161a", "secondary": "#313b45"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.845849	2026-04-25 13:46:57.960743
215	17	7	7	K'at					{"nawal": {"title": "The Weaver of Abundance", "content": "K'at is the nawal of the net, the spider web, and the harvest. It represents gathering, community, and entanglement. Brings both abundance and the reminder to release what no longer serves. Associated with the element of fire and the color yellow, it carries a magnetic, accumulating, and sometimes heavy energy. It is the archetype of the fisherman who casts his net to see what he can catch. In daily life, K'at manifests as networking, hoarding, debt, and the 'sticky' situations we get ourselves into. Its shadow aspect can be greed, entrapment, holding on to old baggage, or feeling weighed down by obligations. K'at teaches us that to catch the new, we must untangle ourselves from the old.", "keywords": ["Gathering", "Release", "Abundance", "Community", "Traps"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mystic Prism", "content": "Tone 7 is the midpoint of the 13-day cycle, sitting at the very top of the energetic pyramid. It represents the point of maximum potential, reflection, and mystical power. Unlike the stability of 4 or the flow of 6, Tone 7 is a threshold energy—neither here nor there, but encompassing both the beginning and the end. It is a day of 'no time,' where the veil between worlds is thin. Experientially, Tone 7 feels contemplative, strange, and highly intuitive. It provides a 360-degree view of reality, allowing us to see the past and future simultaneously. While it offers profound insights and the ability to channel energy, its shadow can be indecision, confusion, or getting lost in the ether. It is the mirror at the top of the mountain.", "keywords": ["Insight", "Reflection", "Mysticism", "Threshold", "Vision"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Visualize cutting the energetic cords that drain you.", "Declutter a specific area of your home (the physical net).", "Reflect on your relationships: which ones feel like a trap?", "Gather your scattered energy back into your center through meditation.", "Donate items you no longer need to clear the flow of abundance."], "title": "The Mystic Net", "content": "When the high-frequency energy of Tone 7 meets the gathering power of K'at, we reach a critical point of 'Spiritual Sorting.' 7 K'at is the day to stand at the top of the pyramid and look at what is in your net. What have you gathered in your life? What connections, possessions, and beliefs are you carrying? Tone 7 provides the mystical clarity to see which of these things are treasures and which are traps. This is a powerful day for releasing karma and cutting energetic cords. It feels like a pause in the journey where we lighten our load before the descent. The energy supports a deep review of our attachments. Are we bound by love, or by fear? The combination invites us to cast our net into the spiritual realms, gathering insights rather than material things. The challenge is the potential for overwhelm, seeing all our entanglements at once. The opportunity is to cut the strings that bind us and keep only what truly feeds the soul."}}	{"title": "The Mystic Weaver of Connections", "content": "To be born on 7 K'at is to be a soul who stands at the crossroads of many worlds, holding the threads that connect them all. You possess a complex, brilliant mind that naturally sees patterns and interdependencies. Tone 7 gives you a mystical, reflective nature, while K'at makes you a gatherer of people, ideas, and experiences. You are the ultimate networker, but your purpose goes deeper than social climbing; you are here to weave a net of consciousness. You likely have a vast and eclectic circle of friends, and you are often the one who brings disparate groups together.\\n\\nYour life path is one of sorting and discernment. You attract much into your life—opportunities, people, resources—and your lesson is to know what to keep and what to release. You are a natural psychologist, able to see the traps and entanglements in others' lives and help them find freedom. Because you stand at the midpoint (7), you often feel pulled in many directions, acting as a bridge between opposing forces. You have a magnetic quality that draws abundance to you, but you must be careful not to become burdened by it.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 7 K'at soul is the feeling of being trapped by your own creation. You may say 'yes' to too many things, accumulating obligations until you feel suffocated. Your net can become a tangled mess if you do not regularly practice the art of release. You may also struggle with indecision, seeing so many possibilities that you freeze. Your growth comes from learning that true abundance requires empty space. When you learn to travel light, keeping only the threads that resonate with your highest truth, you become a master weaver of a liberated reality."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#dcb67b", "primary": "#101716", "secondary": "#453f39"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.85987	2026-04-25 13:46:58.012704
236	19	2	2	B'atz'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Weaver of Time", "content": "B'atz' is the nawal of the thread, the monkey, and the weaver. It represents the creative life force that spins the fabric of time and reality. B'atz' is the artist, the trickster, and the initiator of new cycles. Associated with the element of fire and the arts, it carries a playful, clever, and masterful energy. It is the archetype of the artisan who weaves scattered threads into a beautiful tapestry. In daily life, B'atz' manifests as artistic expression, marriage, scheduling, and the unfolding of destiny. Its shadow aspect can be arrogance, manipulation, or becoming tangled in one's own complexities. B'atz' reminds us that we are the weavers of our own lives.", "keywords": ["Creativity", "Weaving", "Time", "Artistry", "Initiation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "Tone 2 introduces the concept of the 'other.' It is the energy of polarity, partnership, and the dynamic tension between opposites. If Tone 1 is the solitary point, Tone 2 is the line connecting two points, creating relationship. This number governs the mysteries of duality: light and dark, masculine and feminine, inner and outer. Experientially, Tone 2 often brings choices or presents situations where you must weigh two sides of a coin. It is a day of reflection, where the world acts as a mirror to your internal state. While it can bring the challenge of indecision or conflict, its higher expression is balance and cooperation. It teaches that separation is an illusion and that opposing forces are actually complementary halves of a greater whole.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Reflection", "Connection", "Balance", "Choice"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Do something creative with a partner (paint, cook, dance).", "Discuss the 'pattern' of your relationship and how to improve it.", "Make a choice between two creative paths.", "Weave a physical symbol of connection (braid, knot, bracelet).", "Approach a conflict with curiosity and humor rather than rigidity."], "title": "Weaving the Partnership", "content": "When the duality of Tone 2 meets the creative weaving of B'atz', we experience a day of 'Relationship Artistry.' 2 B'atz' is creativity in relationship and the crossroads of choice. The energy supports weaving two distinct threads into a stronger cord. It is a powerful day for marriage, partnership contracts, or collaborative art projects. The Monkey (B'atz') brings a sense of play to the serious work of relating (2). Today, we are asked to look at our connections not as static obligations, but as living tapestries that we are constantly co-creating. It is a time to choose which threads to add to your shared design. The challenge is to ensure that both weavers are in rhythm; if one pulls too tight, the pattern distorts. The opportunity is to create a relationship that is a work of art—complex, beautiful, and enduring."}}	{"title": "The Weaver of Shared Destiny", "content": "To be born on 2 B'atz' is to be a master of connection and a creative diplomat. You possess a soul that thrives on interaction and artistic expression. Tone 2 gives you a deep understanding of duality and partnership, while B'atz' gifts you with the skills of the weaver and the charm of the monkey. You are likely the person who connects people, weaving social circles together with ease. You view relationships as an art form, constantly adjusting the threads to create harmony and beauty.\\n\\nYour life path is one of co-creation. You are not meant to weave alone. Your greatest works—whether they are businesses, families, or art—will come from collaboration. You have a talent for seeing the potential in others and helping them weave their destiny into yours. You may be drawn to wedding planning, matchmaking, collaborative arts, or counseling. You are a natural mediator, able to see both sides of the pattern and find the thread that unites them.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 2 B'atz' soul is the potential for entanglement. You may become so wrapped up in others' lives that you lose the thread of your own story. You might also struggle with indecision, seeing the beauty in every option and fearing to choose one. There is a risk of using your charm to manipulate relationships rather than to nurture them. Your lesson is to maintain your own center while weaving with others. When you honor your own creative sovereignty, your partnerships become a dance of two wholes rather than a merging of two halves."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#ca9681", "primary": "#131716", "secondary": "#4c3b38"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.877033	2026-04-25 13:46:58.054553
238	19	4	4	Aj					{"nawal": {"title": "The Pillar of Community", "content": "Aj is the nawal of the cane, the reed, and the home. It represents the spine, the pillar of the family, and the authority that comes from integrity. Aj is the energy of resurrection and flexibility—like the corn stalk that bends in the wind but does not break. Associated with the element of earth and the color brown or yellow, it carries a gentle, protective, and paternal/maternal energy. It is the archetype of the rightful leader who serves the community. In daily life, Aj manifests as domestic harmony, questions of authority, and the strength of one's inner convictions. Its shadow aspect can be rigidity, authoritarianism, or problems within the home/family structure. Aj teaches us that true strength lies in flexibility and service.", "keywords": ["Home", "Leadership", "Harmony", "Integrity", "Authority"]}, "number": {"title": "The Foundation of Form", "content": "Tone 4 is the energy of stability, structure, and definition. After the movement of 3, the 4 establishes a base, like the four walls of a house or the four legs of a table. It represents the four directions (East, West, North, South) and the four elements (Earth, Air, Fire, Water), grounding spiritual energy into physical reality. Experientially, Tone 4 feels calm, ordered, and reliable. It is a day for planning, organizing, and establishing boundaries. It brings the vague potential of the earlier numbers into concrete form. While it offers safety and predictability, its shadow can be rigidity, stagnation, or being 'boxed in.' It is the number of the builder who lays the cornerstone.", "keywords": ["Structure", "Balance", "Grounding", "Manifestation", "Stability"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Inspect the physical structure of your home for repairs.", "Establish a new family tradition or rule that creates stability.", "Focus on posture and spinal alignment exercises.", "Spend time at home, simply enjoying the safety of your space.", "Clarify your boundaries with family members or roommates."], "title": "The Solid Foundation of Home", "content": "When the structural stability of Tone 4 meets the domestic pillar of Aj, we experience a day of 'Deep Grounding.' 4 Aj is the energy of the foundation of the house itself. It is the day to ground home and community. The energy is incredibly stable, supportive, and protective. It feels like the safety of four solid walls and a roof over your head. 4 Aj asks us to attend to the structures that support our lives—our physical homes, our bodies (the spine), and our family agreements. This is the best day for construction, renovation, or establishing house rules. It creates a container where life can flourish safely. The challenge is to not become too rigid or insular; the walls should protect, not imprison. The opportunity is to build a sanctuary that is strong enough to weather any storm."}}	{"title": "The Architect of Sanctuary", "content": "To be born on 4 Aj is to be a person of immense stability and a builder of safe havens. You possess a soul that craves order, tradition, and a place to belong. Tone 4 gives you a love for structure and the four directions, while Aj connects you to the home and the community. You are the rock of your family, the one who keeps the traditions alive and ensures that everyone has a roof over their head. You are likely drawn to architecture, real estate, interior design, or community planning—any field where you can create containers for life.\\n\\nYour life path is one of establishing roots. You are not a wanderer; you build your castle and invite others in. You have a quiet authority that comes from your reliability. People trust you because you are consistent and fair. You understand that freedom requires a strong foundation, and you work hard to provide that for yourself and your loved ones. You are the spine of your community, upright and unbreaking.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 4 Aj soul is rigidity. You can be so focused on the structure that you forget the life inside it. You may struggle with change, viewing it as a threat to your carefully built security. You might also become authoritarian, imposing your rules on others 'for their own good.' Your lesson is to learn the flexibility of the reed. When you allow your structures to breathe and adapt, your sanctuary becomes a living, growing space rather than a fortress."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d2ba73", "primary": "#171b16", "secondary": "#5d4c30"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.8776	2026-04-25 13:46:58.056404
232	18	11	11	Kawoq	You step out of the Hall of Mirrors, and the stillness shatters. The sky, which had been a stark white above the mirrors, turns a bruised, swirling indigo. The heat that has defined this garden for ten days finally breaks.\n\nA drop of rain hits your cheek. Then another. Then the heavens open.\n\nIt isn’t a gentle shower. It is a deluge. Sheets of glowing, torrential rain hammer the obsidian ground, instantly flashing into steam where the earth is still hot. The dry channels of the valley fill with rushing water, sweeping away the ash and the "shavings" left behind by the mirrors.\n\nYou cannot stand still in this downpour. You run for shelter, spotting a circular stone dome rising from the steam ahead. It looks ancient, like a natural blister in the rock that has cooled and hardened.\n\nYou duck inside. It is a natural steam lodge, heated by the earth and fed by the storm.\n\nInside, it is dark, hot, and humid. The air is thick with the scent of wet stone and sage. You are safe from the violence of the wind, but you are not escaping the intensity. Here, the heat is different—it is moist, penetrating, womb-like.\n\nYou sit in the darkness, sweating. You realize this is the final cleanse. The fire burned away your debts. The mirrors cut away your illusions. Now, the storm is washing away the residue.\n\nYou breathe in the steam. It fills your lungs, loosening the last tightness in your chest. You are being unmade, softened, and prepared.\n\nOutside, the thunder shakes the ground. Inside, you are held in the warm, wet center of the change. You entered this lodge as a warrior of truth; you will crawl out as something new.	The room is being rearranged while you’re still standing in it. It feels messy, but it’s necessary. Don’t try to organize the tornado. Let the storm wash away what you detached yesterday.\n\nThis is the midwife energy. It might hurt a little, like birth pains, but it’s bringing something new. Be gentle with yourself. You are in the fragile state between "no longer" and "not yet." Stay in the shelter until the rain stops.	I am safe in the center of the change.	Visualize yourself standing in a warm, torrential rain. The water is glowing with soft light. As it hits your skin, it washes away grey soot and dust—the debris of the past ten days.\n\nWatch the grey water flow off you and into the earth, where it is neutralized. You are not cold; you are invigorated.\n\nFeel the rain cleansing your aura, your thoughts, and your heart. When the rain stops, you are standing fresh and new in the clear air.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Compassionate Storm", "content": "Kawoq is the nawal of the storm, the turtle, and the midwife. It represents the community, the family bloodline, and the power of feminine cleansing. Kawoq is the energy of the rain that washes away the dust and nourishes the crops. Associated with the element of water and the color green/blue, it carries a fluid, emotional, and collective energy. It is the archetype of the caregiver who holds space for birth and rebirth. In daily life, Kawoq manifests as family gatherings, emotional release, and the protection of the vulnerable. Its shadow aspect can be emotional overwhelm, lack of boundaries, or 'smothering' care. Kawoq teaches us that we are all drops in the same ocean.", "keywords": ["Community", "Compassion", "Cleansing", "Rebirth", "Midwife"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Dissolution", "content": "Tone 11 is the energy of dissonance, stripping away, and liberation. Unlike the stability of the 10, the 11 introduces a chaotic variable to test the structure. It is the 'master number' of change. Experientially, Tone 11 feels turbulent, unpredictable, and intense. It is a day where things might fall apart, but only so that what is true can remain. It acts as a filter, discarding what is no longer needed before the final ascent of the cycle. While it can bring anxiety or disruption, its higher expression is freedom and the clearing of space. It is the wind that shakes the dead leaves from the tree.", "keywords": ["Change", "Liberation", "Release", "Dissonance", "Clearing"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Allow yourself a good cry to release pent-up emotion.", "Take a long bath or shower to cleanse your energy field.", "Let go of a family expectation that feels suffocating.", "Support someone who is going through a difficult transition.", "Trust that the chaos is temporary and necessary for rebirth."], "title": "The Liberating Storm", "content": "When the chaotic force of Tone 11 meets the emotional power of Kawoq, we experience a day of 'Radical Rebirth.' 11 Kawoq is the breaking of the waters. It is the moment in birth where the intensity peaks and the old world dissolves to make way for the new. The energy is turbulent, emotional, and cleansing. It feels like a heavy thunderstorm that breaks a long drought. 11 Kawoq shakes up the family dynamics and the community structures, revealing what is solid and what washes away. It is a powerful day for releasing ancestral trauma and emotional baggage. The turtle shell may crack, but only so the spirit can expand. The challenge is to surrender to the storm without fear. The opportunity is to be washed clean, emerging from the chaos with a renewed sense of compassion and lightness."}}	{"title": "The Catalyst of Emotional Renewal", "content": "To be born on 11 Kawoq is to be a person of intense feeling and a catalyst for family and community transformation. You possess a soul that is like a storm—powerful, cleansing, and unpredictable. Tone 11 gives you a liberating, non-conformist nature, while Kawoq connects you to the deep waters of emotion and ancestry. You are the 'black sheep' who heals the flock, the one who refuses to carry the old patterns and forces the family to evolve. You are a natural midwife, unafraid of the messiness of birth and change.\\n\\nYour life path is one of breaking open to let the light in. You are here to challenge the status quo of your community, not out of malice, but out of a fierce compassion. You understand that sometimes things must fall apart to be rebuilt better. You may be drawn to crisis management, intense therapeutic work, or social revolution. You have a huge heart, but you express your love through freedom rather than control.\\n\\nThe challenge for an 11 Kawoq soul is overwhelm. You feel everything so deeply that you can become flooded by the emotions of the world. You may struggle with stability, creating storms in your own life just to feel alive. There is a risk of being misunderstood as chaotic or destructive when your true intent is healing. Your lesson is to find your own eye of the storm. When you anchor yourself in the turtle wisdom—slow, patient, protected—you can channel your immense energy into washing the world clean without drowning in the process."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b988d5", "primary": "#16151c", "secondary": "#48316f"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#b28e6e", "primary": "#1d2a38", "secondary": "#454a51"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#81b1a0", "primary": "#2d483c", "secondary": "#587c61"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#679bb7", "primary": "#11182d", "secondary": "#314c70"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.871443	2026-04-25 13:46:58.022887
220	17	12	12	Toj					{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Fire of Exchange", "content": "Toj is the nawal of offering, payment, and the sacred fire. It represents the universal law of reciprocity—the understanding that in order to receive, one must give. Toj is the energy of clearing karmic debts and restoring balance through sacrifice and gratitude. Associated with the element of fire and the color red, it carries a warm, purifying, and sometimes intense energy. It is the archetype of the ritualist who tends the hearth and ensures that the exchange between the human and spiritual worlds is honored. In daily life, Toj manifests as the need to pay bills, help others, or offer thanks. Its shadow aspect involves feeling burdened by debt, martyrdom, or the feeling that one is always giving without return. Toj reminds us that gratitude is the currency of the universe.", "keywords": ["Gratitude", "Offering", "Balance", "Purification", "Reciprocity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Understanding of the Whole", "content": "Tone 12 is the energy of understanding, gathering, and the retrospective view. It represents the summation of the cycle's lessons before the final transcendence. It is the number of the 'crystal clear' comprehension that comes after the storm of the 11. Experientially, Tone 12 feels communal, settled, and wise. It is a day to gather the scattered pieces and make sense of them. It fosters cooperation and the ability to summarize complex experiences. While it is generally a positive energy, its shadow can be a refusal to move on or looking backward for too long. It is the librarian who organizes the stories.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Unity", "Cooperation", "Summary", "Review"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Host a gratitude circle or dinner with friends.", "Make a donation to a cause that helps the community.", "Reflect on what you have received lately and how you can pay it forward.", "Burn a list of old grievances in a fire ceremony.", "Offer your time or skills to help someone in need."], "title": "The Universal Offering", "content": "The synthesizing wisdom of Tone 12 meets the sacrificial fire of Toj to create a day of 'Communal Gratitude.' 12 Toj is the Great Ceremony. It is a day where we understand, on a deep level, that everything is a gift and everything has a price. The energy is ripe for settling spiritual and physical debts, not as a burden, but as a way to restore harmony to the whole. It feels like a potluck dinner where everyone brings a dish—the abundance comes from the sharing. 12 Toj supports collective healing through offering. It is a time to look back at the trecena and give thanks for the cuts, the storms, and the growth. The challenge is to give without attachment to the outcome. The opportunity is to feel the lightness that comes when the ledger is balanced and the heart is open."}}	{"title": "The Keeper of the Sacred Balance", "content": "To be born on 12 Toj is to be a soul dedicated to the restoration of harmony through service and gratitude. You possess a deep understanding of the law of reciprocity; you know that life is a circle of giving and receiving. Tone 12 gives you a wide, inclusive perspective, allowing you to see the needs of the community, while Toj drives you to meet those needs through offering. You are the philanthropist, the volunteer, the one who always remembers to say 'thank you.' You carry a heavy karmic load, but you do so with grace, often clearing debts for your lineage or your people.\\n\\nYour life path is one of energetic accounting. You are here to balance the books, ensuring that fairness and gratitude prevail. You may be drawn to social work, finance, or spiritual leadership—roles where you can facilitate exchange. You have a natural warmth (fire) that draws people to you, and you are often the heart of your social circle. You understand that true wealth is not what you keep, but what you circulate.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 12 Toj soul is the potential for martyrdom. You may give until you are empty, believing that you must pay for everyone else's mistakes. You might struggle to receive, feeling that you are unworthy or that you will owe something in return. Your lesson is to include yourself in the circle of offering. When you realize that you are also a divine vessel worthy of support, your giving becomes a joyful celebration rather than a payment of debt."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#caa870", "primary": "#141512", "secondary": "#5f3f30"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.861597	2026-04-25 13:46:58.004723
242	19	8	8	No'j					{"nawal": {"title": "The Crystal Mind of Wisdom", "content": "No'j is the nawal of the mind, knowledge, and the earth's brain. It represents the power of thought, logic, and the conversion of information into wisdom. No'j is the scholar, the scientist, and the planner. Associated with the element of earth and the color blue, it carries a cool, clear, and intellectual energy. It is the archetype of the sage who solves problems through clarity and innovation. In daily life, No'j manifests as study, brainstorming, and the spark of a good idea. Its shadow aspect can be overthinking, arrogance, or becoming trapped in mental loops. No'j teaches us that true intelligence is not just knowing facts, but knowing how to live in harmony with the cosmos.", "keywords": ["Wisdom", "Knowledge", "Thought", "Innovation", "Logic"]}, "number": {"title": "The Harmonious Weaver", "content": "Tone 8 is the energy of resonance, justice, and the octave. Following the peak of the 7, the 8 represents the return to the material world but with a higher frequency. It is the number of the 'infinite loop' (infinity symbol), representing the continuous flow of spirit into matter and back again. Experientially, Tone 8 feels harmonious, balanced, and ceremonial. It is often associated with the male energy or the father, bringing structure that honors the spirit. It is a day of resonance, where actions echo loudly. While it fosters integrity and wholeness, its shadow can be rigidity or a dogmatic adherence to form over feeling. It is the weaver who tightens the threads to create a strong cloth.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Justice", "Resonance", "Infinity", "Ceremony"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in a study session or attend a lecture.", "Write down your thoughts to structure them.", "Perform a ceremony to honor wisdom keepers or teachers.", "Solve a conflict using logic and fairness.", "Meditate on the connection between your mind and the Earth's mind."], "title": "Harmonizing the Mind", "content": "When the resonant structure of Tone 8 meets the intellectual clarity of No'j, we experience a day of 'Sacred Wisdom.' 8 No'j is a day to celebrate the intellect and perform ceremony for the mind. The energy is balanced, clear, and highly conducive to learning and problem-solving. It feels like the satisfying click of a puzzle piece falling into place. 8 No'j asks us to bring our thoughts into harmony with our higher purpose. It is a day to use logic not as a weapon, but as a tool for justice and healing. The energy supports making plans that are both practical and ethically sound. The challenge is to not become rigid in our thinking or intellectualize our feelings. The opportunity is to resonate with the Universal Mind, downloading ideas that can bring harmony to our lives and the world."}}	{"title": "The Resonant Sage", "content": "To be born on 8 No'j is to be a person of brilliant intellect and deep integrity. You possess a mind that is structured, harmonious, and capable of grasping complex systems. Tone 8 gives you a love for balance and justice, while No'j grants you the wisdom of the scholar and the innovator. You are not just smart; you are wise. You use your knowledge to create harmony and to solve problems in a way that benefits the whole. You are likely drawn to science, law, philosophy, or education—fields where you can bring order to chaos through thought.\\n\\nYour life path is one of intellectual mastery. You are here to demonstrate the proper use of the mind. You have a resonant voice (8) and your words carry weight. People listen to you because your ideas are sound and your logic is impeccable. You are a lifelong student and a natural teacher. You understand that true knowledge is not just about facts, but about the interrelationship of all things.\\n\\nThe challenge for an 8 No'j soul is arrogance or rigidity. You may become so attached to your own ideas that you cannot see other perspectives. You might struggle to connect with your emotions, preferring to live in the safe tower of the intellect. There is a risk of becoming dogmatic, believing that your logic is the only truth. Your lesson is to keep your mind open and fluid. When you unite your head with your heart, your wisdom becomes a resonant force that heals and harmonizes the world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#bdbfd6", "primary": "#121b20", "secondary": "#41466d"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.87844	2026-04-25 13:46:58.061832
257	20	10	10	K'at	The sun breaks the horizon. The light hits the Spire, and suddenly, the mountain is not just rock; it is a treasure house.\n\nYou find yourself walking through a hanging valley filled with golden nets—similar to the ones in the K’at trecena, but these are not for catching burdens. These are for catching stars.\n\n10 is Manifestation. K’at is the Net and the Harvest. Today, the vision becomes tangible.\n\nThe nets are filled with the fruits of your climb. Not literal fruit, but crystallized forms of energy. You see a crystal of "Confidence." A gem of "Clarity." A woven bundle of "New Connections."\n\nYou realize that the "Prosperity" of Tz’ikin is not something you chase; it is something you catch when you are in the right place.\n\nYou walk through the harvest. You gather what you need. You put the gems in your pocket—not to hoard them, but to use them.\n\nA Lizard made of emeralds scuttles across the path. It stops and looks at you. It represents the abundance of the earth.\n\nYou understand that you have manifested this reality. By climbing the mountain, by clearing your mind, by healing your wounds, you have woven a net that can catch the blessings of the universe.\n\nYou are rich. Not just in things, but in capacity.\n\nYou take a moment to give thanks for the harvest. Then you keep climbing. The summit is near.	Open your hands. The universe is trying to give you something. The energy of 10 K’at is a full net. Your hard work, your intentions, your visions—they are all landing today.\n\nDon’t deflect the praise or the reward. Accept it. You earned it. This is a day of harvest. Look around at the abundance in your life, both material and spiritual. You are richer than you think.	I open my arms to receive the abundance and blessings I have manifested.	Visualize a golden net stretching across the sky. It catches shooting stars. The stars turn into coins, hearts, and flowers.\n\nThe net lowers them gently to you. Gather them up. Feel the weight of the blessings. Say "Thank you."	{"nawal": {"title": "The Weaver of Abundance", "content": "K'at is the nawal of the net, the spider web, and the harvest. It represents gathering, community, and entanglement. Brings both abundance and the reminder to release what no longer serves. Associated with the element of fire and the color yellow, it carries a magnetic, accumulating, and sometimes heavy energy. It is the archetype of the fisherman who casts his net to see what he can catch. In daily life, K'at manifests as networking, hoarding, debt, and the 'sticky' situations we get ourselves into. Its shadow aspect can be greed, entrapment, holding on to old baggage, or feeling weighed down by obligations. K'at teaches us that to catch the new, we must untangle ourselves from the old.", "keywords": ["Gathering", "Release", "Abundance", "Community", "Traps"]}, "number": {"title": "The Manifestation of Responsibility", "content": "Tone 10 is the energy of manifestation, collaboration, and the two hands coming together. It represents the realization of the intention set in Tone 1. In the cycle, 10 is where the work hits the physical plane in a concrete way. It is a number of community, agreement, and the solidity of creation. Experientially, Tone 10 feels grounded, productive, and social. It is a day to shake hands, sign contracts, and see the tangible results of your efforts. While it fosters achievement and connection, its shadow can be the heavy weight of responsibility or the pressure to perform for the group. It is the number of the builder who sees the walls rise.", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Collaboration", "Result", "Community"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Host a potluck or community gathering.", "Review your resources and share with those in need.", "Organize your physical belongings; store or donate.", "Network with people who can help manifest your vision.", "Release a debt or obligation that is weighing you down."], "title": "Manifesting the Harvest", "content": "When the manifesting power of Tone 10 meets the gathering net of K'at, we experience a day of 'Tangible Abundance.' 10 K'at is the day the net is pulled in, full of fish. It is a time of realizing the harvest of the trecena. The energy supports community gatherings, networking events, and the sharing of resources. It is a powerful day to manifest abundance through collaboration. 10 K'at asks us to look at what we have gathered—both the treasures and the trash. It is a day to share the wealth and to release the burdens we no longer need to carry. The energy feels heavy with potential and connection. The challenge is the risk of entanglement; the net can catch us if we are not careful. The opportunity is to use our connections to build a web of support that feeds everyone."}}	{"title": "The Manifestor of Freedom", "content": "To be born on 10 K'at is to be a weaver of community and a manifestor of abundance. You possess a soul that is magnetic and capable. Tone 10 gives you a drive to see results and to work with others, while K'at grants you the ability to gather resources and connect people. You are the ultimate networker, the person who knows everyone and can get things done. You are likely drawn to business, community organizing, or event planning—roles where you can bring people and things together.\\n\\nYour life path is one of managing abundance. You attract much into your life, and your lesson is to keep it flowing. You are a natural provider, often taking responsibility for the material well-being of your group. You have a talent for untangling complex problems, seeing the knots that others miss. You are a builder of safety nets, ensuring that no one falls through the cracks.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 10 K'at soul is the burden of accumulation. You can become weighed down by your own success, your possessions, or the emotional baggage of those you help. You might struggle to say no, getting caught in webs of obligation. There is a risk of losing your freedom to the very structures you built. Your lesson is to learn the art of release. When you keep your net clean and your hands open, you become a channel for infinite abundance, manifesting a world where everyone is supported and free."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#e9ce72", "primary": "#1c1613", "secondary": "#7c4529"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#d6a941", "primary": "#482f0d", "secondary": "#92641e"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#f8f0d7", "primary": "#8f8f48", "secondary": "#cbbb72"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#d8cc91", "primary": "#403a1a", "secondary": "#947f3b"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.886451	2026-04-25 13:46:58.069461
231	18	10	10	Tijax	The puzzle of light has vanished, and the valley opens up into a vast, silent plain. But this is not empty space. It is a Hall of Mirrors.\n\nRising from the ground are colossal slabs of polished silver obsidian, standing like monoliths. They are razor-sharp at the edges, and their surfaces are flawless. You have to walk between them.\n\nAs you step into the corridor, you look into the first mirror. You expect to see your reflection. Instead, you see a version of yourself wreathed in dark smoke—the doubts, the lies you tell yourself, the "nice" masks you wear to keep the peace.\n\nThen, a beam of light strikes the mirror. It slices through the reflection like a scalpel.\n\nYou feel a physical sensation—a sudden lightness, a shedding. The mirror has cut away the shadow. You look again, and the reflection is clearer, sharper.\n\nYou keep walking. Each mirror shows you a different truth, and each one performs a surgery. One slices away your fear of failure. Another cuts out your need for validation. Another excises the stories that don’t belong to you.\n\nIt is intense. It is uncomfortable. You feel naked, exposed under the glare of absolute truth. But you also feel incredibly clean.\n\nBy the time you reach the end of the hall, you look into the final mirror. The figure staring back at you is not the person who fell into this world ten days ago. That person was blurry, weighed down by a coat of debts.\n\nThe person in the mirror is crystalline. Sharp. Defined. There is no fluff left. There is only the diamond core of who you are.\n\nYou step out of the Hall of Mirrors, feeling the cool wind on your skin. You are smaller now, perhaps. But you are denser. You are real.	You have the raw material; now you need to carve it. Today is about editing. Cut the fluff. Cut the excuses. Cut the "maybe." Excellence isn’t about adding more; it’s about removing everything that isn’t true.\n\nHealing isn’t always a bubble bath; sometimes it’s a surgery. If something is removed from your life today, let it go. It was blocking your circulation. What remains will be sharper, clearer, and infinitely more powerful.	I am the sculptor of my own life, refining my path with truth.	Lie down and close your eyes. Visualize a beam of pure, white light descending from the stars. It looks like a laser or a blade of light.\n\nAllow this light to scan your body and your energy field. Wherever it finds heavy, dark, or stagnant energy, watch as it gently cuts it away. It does not hurt; it feels like a relief.\n\nSee the heavy energy falling away like dead leaves. You are left glowing, pristine, and sharp. You are a diamond that has been cut to reflect the light.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Obsidian Blade of Truth", "content": "Tijax is the nawal of the obsidian blade, the mirror, and the healer. It represents the double-edged sword of truth that cuts away illness and illusion. Tijax is the warrior for the light, the surgeon, and the spark of divinity. Associated with the element of fire and the mineral obsidian, it carries a sharp, decisive, and purifying energy. It is the archetype of the spiritual warrior who is willing to suffer to uncover the truth. In daily life, Tijax manifests as discernment, ending relationships or habits, and sudden healing crises. Its shadow aspect can be cruelty, gossip, or a tongue that cuts too deep. Tijax teaches us that sometimes we must wound in order to heal.", "keywords": ["Healing", "Truth", "Cutting", "Discernment", "Purification"]}, "number": {"title": "The Manifestation of Responsibility", "content": "Tone 10 is the energy of manifestation, collaboration, and the two hands coming together. It represents the realization of the intention set in Tone 1. In the cycle, 10 is where the work hits the physical plane in a concrete way. It is a number of community, agreement, and the solidity of creation. Experientially, Tone 10 feels grounded, productive, and social. It is a day to shake hands, sign contracts, and see the tangible results of your efforts. While it fosters achievement and connection, its shadow can be the heavy weight of responsibility or the pressure to perform for the group. It is the number of the builder who sees the walls rise.", "keywords": ["Manifestation", "Responsibility", "Collaboration", "Result", "Community"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in a group healing activity or support group.", "Cut ties with a habit that is harming your community or family.", "Have a 'clear the air' meeting to resolve a conflict.", "Declutter your digital or physical space with a friend.", "Commit to a truth that you will uphold together."], "title": "Manifesting the Cure", "content": "When the manifesting power of Tone 10 meets the cutting truth of Tijax, we experience a day of 'Community Healing.' 10 Tijax is the energy of the Surgeon in the operating room, supported by a team. It is a day to release patterns together. The energy supports taking decisive, collaborative action to fix what is broken. It is an excellent day for group therapy, clearing clutter from a shared space, or addressing a toxic dynamic in a community. The cut of Tijax today is grounded and purposeful, aiming for a tangible result. It feels like the relief of finally removing a splinter. The combination suggests that healing is not a solitary act; we need each other to hold the mirror and to bandage the wound. The challenge is to handle the blade with care, ensuring that the intervention is constructive, not destructive. The opportunity is to manifest a cleaner, truer reality for everyone."}}	{"title": "The Manifestor of Radical Truth", "content": "To be born on 10 Tijax is to be a powerful agent of change and a builder of a new, truer reality. You possess a sharp intellect and a collaborative spirit. Tone 10 gives you the ability to work well with others and to manifest results, while Tijax grants you the discernment of the obsidian blade. You are the one who sees the flaw in the system and has the practical skills to fix it. You are not just a critic; you are a reformer. You are likely drawn to medicine, social justice, editing, or any field where you can refine and improve the world.\\n\\nYour life path is one of healing through action. You are here to cut away the unnecessary and the false, leaving only what is essential and true. You have a strong sense of responsibility to your community, often taking on the role of the protector or the one who speaks the hard truths that no one else dares to say. People respect you because your actions align with your words. You build trust by being transparent and effective.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 10 Tijax soul is to avoid becoming too sharp or too heavy-handed. You may be prone to perfectionism, cutting yourself and others down for minor flaws. The weight of 'fixing' everything can lead to burnout. You might also struggle with collaboration if you feel others are not as committed to the truth as you are. Your lesson is to use your blade with love. When you manifest healing that is inclusive and compassionate, you become a master builder of a healthy, vibrant world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#dbd8cd", "primary": "#191c1b", "secondary": "#514f49"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#c2c8ba", "primary": "#092e35", "secondary": "#3b7072"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#dad9a6", "primary": "#365326", "secondary": "#8f9b4c"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#dadfe2", "primary": "#11161d", "secondary": "#69696b"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.870603	2026-04-25 13:46:58.020913
184	15	2	2	Tijax					{"nawal": {"title": "The Obsidian Knife of Truth", "content": "Tijax is the double-edged obsidian blade, the archetype of the spiritual warrior and the healer. It represents the power to cut away illness, negative energy, and illusion to reveal the healthy truth underneath. Tijax is the spark of flint and the lightning strike—sudden, sharp, and purifying. It governs the medical arts, surgery, and courageous conversations that sever toxic cords. In its shadow, Tijax can be gossipy, harsh, or prone to conflict, using its sharp tongue to wound rather than heal. But in its light, it is the 'Liberator,' the energy that fearlessly enters the darkest places to excise the rot. It reminds us that healing often requires a momentary pain—the prick of the needle or the cut of the scalpel—to restore wholeness. It is discernment in its sharpest form.", "keywords": ["Healing", "Discernment", "Cutting", "Truth", "Purification"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "Tone 2 introduces the concept of the 'Other.' It is the separation of the One into the Two—light and dark, masculine and feminine, self and partner. This number governs relationships, choices, and the dynamic tension that causes movement. Without the Two, the One would remain static and unmanifest. This day brings duality into sharp focus, asking us to look at the reflections in our lives. It is a day of cooperation, but also of challenge, as we must navigate the space between opposing forces. The energy of 2 is never solitary; it always demands a reaction or a relationship. It teaches us about balance, reciprocity, and the necessity of shadows to define the light. While it can bring conflict or indecision, its higher purpose is harmony—the beautiful dance of two distinct energies learning to move as one.", "keywords": ["Duality", "Relationships", "Balance", "Reflection", "Choice"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Examine your close relationships and gently cut away toxic patterns.", "Use discernment in your choices today; not every option is healthy for you.", "A conversation may be sharp, but it can lead to necessary healing.", "Practice the art of 'editing' your life—remove clutter, bad habits, or old grudges.", "Seek balance between being critical and being compassionate."], "title": "The Relationship of Healing", "content": "2 Tijax brings the sharp discernment of the obsidian blade into the realm of relationships and duality. This is a day where connections are tested, pruned, and ultimately healed. The combined energy asks: 'Which relationships feed my spirit, and which are draining my life force?' It is a powerful day to cut the cords of codependency or to have the difficult conversation that clears the air between partners. The 'Two' emphasizes that healing is often a collaborative act—doctor and patient, counselor and client, or two lovers resolving a conflict. We are asked to look in the mirror (2) and use the knife of truth (Tijax) to edit our own behaviors. While the energy can feel edgy or reactive, it offers the profound gift of liberation. By separating what is true from what is false within our connections, we make space for healthier, more authentic unions to flourish."}}	{"title": "The Mirror of Radical Truth", "content": "To be born on 2 Tijax is to be a healer of relationships and a mirror for the world's truth. You carry a dual nature—one part of you is the gentle diplomat seeking connection (2), and the other is the fierce warrior ready to cut through lies (Tijax). This makes you an incredibly potent friend and partner; you love deeply, but you have zero tolerance for inauthenticity. You are the person who will tell a loved one the hard truth they need to hear because you know it will save them in the long run. Your life path involves navigating the tension between keeping the peace and shattering illusions.\\n\\nYour healing abilities are often triggered through one-on-one interactions. You may find yourself in careers involving therapy, surgery, acupuncture, or any field where precise intervention is needed to restore balance. You have a knack for seeing both sides of a coin and knowing exactly where the 'infection' lies in a dynamic. People trust you to be the arbiter, the one who can slice through the confusion of a dispute and find the core issue. You are a surgeon of the soul, using your sharp intellect to excise pain.\\n\\nHowever, the challenge of 2 Tijax is to not turn the knife on yourself or those you love when you are frustrated. Your words are weapons, and in moments of imbalance, you can be cutting and critical. Your soul's lesson is to temper your obsidian edge with the softness of the number 2. Learn that not everything needs to be dissected; sometimes, the greatest healing comes from simply holding space for the duality of life without trying to fix it immediately."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d1a59c", "primary": "#0f100f", "secondary": "#44342e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.846197	2026-04-25 13:46:57.966904
185	15	3	3	Kawoq					{"nawal": {"title": "The Storm of Compassion", "content": "Kawoq is the energy of the storm, the midwife, and the community. It represents the breaking of waters that precedes birth—a powerful, sometimes chaotic force that clears the way for new life. Kawoq is associated with the turtle (slow, ancient wisdom) and the thunder (sudden, cleansing power). It is the archetype of the compassionate caregiver who is strong enough to hold space for intense transformation. Kawoq governs the home, the hearth, and the collective well-being of the 'tribe.' In its shadow, it can manifest as emotional overwhelm, intrusiveness, or the destructive fury of a hurricane. But in its light, it is the ultimate abundance, the rain that feeds the crops and the fierce love that protects the vulnerable. It teaches us that true tenderness often requires the strength of a storm.", "keywords": ["Storm", "Midwife", "Community", "Cleansing", "Compassion"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Movement", "content": "Tone 3 is the vibration of activation, movement, and rhythm. If 1 is the point and 2 is the line, 3 is the triangle that creates stability and form. It represents the integration of the previous two energies into a flow. This is the number of communication, artistic expression, and the restless energy that pushes growth forward. 3 breaks the stalemate of duality; it introduces a third element that allows for a new direction. It is associated with the heartbeat, the drum, and the natural oscillation of life. On a 3 day, things begin to happen—ideas are voiced, bodies move, and stagnation is shaken off. However, this dynamism can also lead to scattered energy or instability if not grounded. It is the playful, erratic, and vital pulse of creation in motion.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Rhythm", "Communication", "Flow", "Expression"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Allow your emotions to flow freely; do not dam the river today.", "Reach out to your community or family; there is strength in gathering.", "Express your compassion through action, not just silent feeling.", "Be the 'midwife' for someone else's idea or struggle—help them birth it.", "Trust that any turbulence today is clearing the air for new growth."], "title": "The Flow of Collective Healing", "content": "3 Kawoq is a day of dynamic emotional flow and communal regeneration. The movement of the 3 stirs up the waters of the Kawoq storm, creating a powerful current of feeling and expression. This is not a day to hold things in; it is a day to let the rain fall and the rivers run. The combined energy supports communicating deep emotional needs within the family or community. It is the 'midwife in motion,' actively working to birth a new state of being for the collective. We may feel a restlessness to fix things in our home or to rally our tribe around a cause. The lesson here is to trust the rhythm of the storm—to understand that the chaos of the 3 is necessary to rearrange the pieces into a more compassionate order. It is an excellent day for group therapy, family gatherings, or artistic expression that releases pent-up emotion."}}	{"title": "The Voice of the Tribe", "content": "To be born on 3 Kawoq is to be a dynamic force for community healing and expression. You are the storm that gets things moving. You possess a restless, vibrant spirit that cannot sit still when there is work to be done for the collective. As a 3, you are naturally expressive and communicative, and combined with the Kawoq energy of the family and tribe, you become the spokesperson for the group. You are often the one who verbalizes what everyone else is feeling but is afraid to say. You bring the rain that relieves the drought of silence.\\n\\nYour life is likely centered around groups, families, or communities. You have a 'midwife' quality, but you are an active, busy midwife—constantly running between people, weaving connections, and ensuring that everyone is taken care of. You might find yourself in roles like social work, community organizing, or the arts, where you can channel the collective emotional experience into something tangible. You are a natural nurturer, but your nurturing is active; you don't just hug, you build the house, cook the meal, and organize the festival. You are the heartbeat of your circle.\\n\\nHowever, the challenge of 3 Kawoq is learning to manage your own emotional tides. The combination of the unstable 3 and the watery Kawoq can make you prone to emotional storms or taking on too much of others' burdens. You may struggle with boundaries, feeling like you must be the flow for everyone. Your growth comes from learning that you can support the birthing process without drowning in the fluids. Learn to ground your lightning so that your presence brings warmth and rain, rather than a flood."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#57b6af", "primary": "#0b1717", "secondary": "#2c4c49"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.84661	2026-04-25 13:46:57.968126
186	15	4	4	Ajpu					{"nawal": {"title": "The Solar Hero", "content": "Ajpu is the nawal of the Sun, the blowgunner, and the spiritual warrior. It represents the divine spark within the human form—the capacity for heroism, artistry, and enlightenment. Ajpu is the hunter who seeks the highest truth with unwavering aim. It is the energy of the performer, the leader, and the one who overcomes the darkness of Xibalba (the underworld) through wit and courage, just as the Hero Twins did in the Popol Vuh. Ajpu governs the light of consciousness and the clarity of purpose. In its shadow, it can be ego-driven, arrogant, or overly perfectionistic. But in its light, it is the golden warmth that uplifts the community, the certainty of one's divinity, and the mastery of life's challenges. It is the realization that we are light made solid.", "keywords": ["Divinity", "Heroism", "Sun", "Purpose", "Mastery"]}, "number": {"title": "The Cube of Stability", "content": "Tone 4 is the energy of stability, definition, and material form. It represents the four directions, the four elements, and the four walls of a house. After the movement of the 3, the 4 arrives to ground that energy into a tangible reality. It is the number of foundations, planning, and bringing dreams down to earth. 4 offers a sense of calm reliability; it is the square upon which we can build. It asks us to organize, measure, and define the boundaries of our creation. While it lacks the speed of other numbers, it possesses an endurance that they do not. It is the solid earth under our feet, the reliable rhythm of the seasons, and the discipline required to turn a sketch into a masterpiece.", "keywords": ["Stability", "Foundation", "Structure", "Four Directions", "Definition"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create a physical altar or space to honor your spiritual connection.", "Bring discipline to your artistic or creative practice.", "Stand firm in your truth; be a stable light for others.", "Align your daily physical actions with your higher purpose.", "Recognize the divinity in the structure of the natural world."], "title": "Grounding the Divine Light", "content": "4 Ajpu is a day of profound spiritual solidity. It represents the grounding of the highest divine light into the physical plane. If Ajpu is the Sun, 4 is the temple built to honor it. This combination asks us to bring our spiritual ideals and heroic aspirations into a structured, livable reality. It is not enough to simply *feel* divine today; we must *act* with divine integrity in the material world. This is an excellent day for leadership that is steady and reliable, or for artistic projects that require both inspiration and discipline. The energy supports building the foundations of a life that honors your true purpose. We are reminded that the body itself (4) is the vessel for the spirit (Ajpu). By stabilizing our connection to the divine, we become pillars of light for those around us, standing firm against the shadows."}}	{"title": "The Pillar of Light", "content": "To be born on 4 Ajpu is to be a builder of spiritual realities. You are a 'Solar Architect,' someone who possesses the vision of the hero (Ajpu) backed by the unshakable stability of the four directions (4). You do not just dream of a better world; you have the practical skills and the discipline to build it brick by brick. Your presence is reassuring and regal; people look to you as a natural leader because you radiate a calm, grounded certainty. You embody the concept that spirituality is not an escape from the world, but a way to structure it beautifully.\\n\\nYour path is one of mastery and demonstration. You are likely drawn to roles where you can shine while providing structure—such as a benevolent boss, a dedicated artist, a spiritual teacher who emphasizes practice over theory, or a community pillar. You have a hunter's focus; when you set your sights on a goal, you pursue it with the relentless, steady pace of the sun crossing the sky. You are the one who ensures that the ceremony is done correctly, that the rules of the game are fair, and that the light is honored in daily life. You are a bridge between the heavens and the earth.\\n\\nHowever, the challenge for a 4 Ajpu is to avoid becoming rigid or dogmatic in your righteousness. The stability of the 4 can sometimes turn into stubbornness, and the pride of Ajpu can lead to a belief that your way is the *only* way. You may struggle with perfectionism, judging yourself and others harshly for falling short of the ideal. Your soul's growth lies in keeping your structure flexible enough to let the light breathe. Remember that a true hero empowers others to find their own light, rather than just blinding them with yours."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#ddc289", "primary": "#101110", "secondary": "#473b2f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.846967	2026-04-25 13:46:57.969347
240	19	6	6	Tz'ikin					{"nawal": {"title": "The Visionary Bird of Prosperity", "content": "Tz'ikin is the nawal of the bird, the eagle/condor, and vision. It represents the ability to see the big picture, rising above the details to perceive the interconnectedness of all things. Tz'ikin is the energy of prosperity, abundance, and the freedom of the spirit. Associated with the element of air and the sky, it carries a light, expansive, and high-frequency energy. It is the archetype of the visionary who brings messages from the divine to the earth. In daily life, Tz'ikin manifests as financial luck, good news, dreaming, and artistic inspiration. Its shadow aspect can be spacing out, greed, or becoming distracted by 'shiny objects' without grounding. Tz'ikin teaches us that abundance is a natural state.", "keywords": ["Vision", "Prosperity", "Freedom", "Abundance", "Perspective"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Harmony", "content": "Tone 6 is the energy of flow, rhythm, and responsiveness. After the exertion of the 5, the 6 allows the energy to stabilize and find its natural groove. It is the number of ultimate balance in motion—like a surfer riding a wave or a heart beating in time. In Mayan cosmology, it is associated with the six directions (East, West, North, South, Up, Down), representing a spatial wholeness. Experientially, Tone 6 feels fluid and harmonious. It is a day where things often 'click' into place without force. While it fosters growth and family connection, its shadow can be passivity or a tendency to drift with the current rather than steering. It is the breath that connects the effort to the result.", "keywords": ["Rhythm", "Harmony", "Flow", "Balance", "Growth"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Visualize money and resources flowing into your life like water.", "Share your vision with others; communication flows easily today.", "Take a risk on an opportunity that feels expansive.", "Practice gratitude for the abundance already present.", "Look at your problems from a higher altitude to find the harmonious solution."], "title": "The Flow of Abundance", "content": "When the harmonious flow of Tone 6 meets the expansive vision of Tz'ikin, we experience a day of 'Effortless Prosperity.' 6 Tz'ikin is the energy of stabilizing the highest vision. It is a day where abundance flows naturally, like a river finding its course. The struggle of the previous days relaxes into a state of receptivity. The energy supports financial growth, artistic breakthroughs, and seeing the 'big picture' of your life with clarity and ease. It feels like catching a thermal current and gliding without flapping your wings. 6 Tz'ikin asks us to trust that the universe wants to support us. It is an excellent day to ask for what you need and to be open to receiving it in unexpected ways. The challenge is to not block the flow with doubt or unworthiness. The opportunity is to align your vibration with the frequency of joy and plenty."}}	{"title": "The Harmonious Visionary", "content": "To be born on 6 Tz'ikin is to be a magnet for luck and a bringer of good news. You possess a naturally optimistic and expansive soul. Tone 6 gives you a rhythmic, easy-going nature, while Tz'ikin grants you the vision of the Eagle and the Midas touch. You are likely the person who always lands on their feet, who finds the parking spot, who gets the job. You flow through life with a sense of trust that the universe will provide. You are a visionary who can see the potential in people and situations that others miss.\\n\\nYour life path is one of demonstrating flow and abundance. You are here to show that life does not have to be a struggle. You may be drawn to business, the arts, philanthropy, or motivational speaking. You inspire others simply by your presence, lifting their spirits and helping them see a brighter future. You are a natural networker, connecting people and resources in a way that benefits everyone. Your generosity is a key part of your flow.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 6 Tz'ikin soul is discipline. Because things often come easily to you, you may lack the grit to push through when times get tough. You might be prone to laziness or superficiality, skimming the surface of life rather than diving deep. There is a risk of becoming addicted to the 'high' of new opportunities and failing to follow through. Your lesson is to ground your vision. When you combine your natural luck with steady effort, you can manifest a reality that is not only prosperous for you but uplifting for the whole world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b7cec6", "primary": "#131718", "secondary": "#425154"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.878033	2026-04-25 13:46:58.05989
38	3	12	12	B'atz'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Weaver of Time", "content": "B'atz' is the nawal of the thread, the monkey, and the artist. It represents the beginning and the creative process itself. B'atz' is the weaver who spins the thread of time and reality. It governs the arts, marriage, and the weaving of destiny. B'atz' energy is playful, clever, and masterfully creative. It is the spark that starts the fire. In its shadow, B'atz' can manifest as superficiality, inability to finish what is started, or getting tangled in one's own threads. Its highest expression is the Master Weaver who creates beauty and connection out of the raw material of life.", "keywords": ["Weaving", "Creativity", "Thread", "Monkey", "Art"]}, "number": {"title": "The Crystal of Understanding", "content": "Twelve is the number of understanding, summation, and the gathering of scattered parts into a whole. It represents the family, the tribe, and the complex stability that comes after the disruption of Eleven. Twelve is the 'council' number—it holds space for all previous experiences to be integrated. Experientially, a Twelve day feels rich, cooperative, and reflective. It is a time to look back at the journey and see the lesson. The shadow of Twelve can be heaviness or difficulty managing too many moving parts. It asks us to find the unity in diversity.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Integration", "Community", "Summation", "Wholeness"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in a craft: knitting, painting, writing, or cooking.", "Look at old photos or journals to see the patterns in your life.", "Connect with your 'tribe' or family for a shared activity.", "Visualize your life as a tapestry; what color thread do you want to add next?", "Laugh! B'atz' loves humor as a form of wisdom."], "title": "Weaving the Whole Picture", "content": "When the integrative power of Twelve meets the creative weaving of B'atz', we have a day of 'Masterful Integration' or 'The Great Tapestry.' Today, the scattered threads of the past 11 days are gathered into a coherent, beautiful design. The Twelve brings the understanding of how everything fits together, while B'atz' provides the skill to weave it. It is a wonderful day for artistic completion, family gatherings, or understanding the 'story arc' of your life. The monkey energy adds a touch of playfulness to the heavy Twelve, making it a day of joyful collaboration. You may see the 'red thread' that connects your diverse experiences. The challenge is complexity—there is a lot going on today. Do not get overwhelmed by the details. Step back and look at the pattern. Trust that every knot and every color has its place in the masterpiece you are creating."}}	{"title": "The Master Weaver", "content": "To be born on 12 B'atz' is to be a visionary artist and a unifier of people. You possess a dazzling creativity backed by a deep understanding of human complexity. The number Twelve gives you the ability to hold many different strands of reality at once, while B'atz' gives you the talent to weave them into something beautiful. You are likely the 'glue' in your family or community, the one who remembers the history and tells the stories. You have a playful, charming nature that draws people in, but beneath the humor lies a profound wisdom.\\n\\nYour life path is one of creative synthesis. You are here to show how things connect—how the past relates to the future, how science relates to art, how you relate to me. You may be a historian, an artist, a community organizer, or a storyteller. Your challenge is focus; you have so many threads in your hands that you can sometimes get tangled. Your lesson is to trust your own design and to keep weaving, knowing that your life is a work of art in progress."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d49dbe", "primary": "#14191b", "secondary": "#543f4e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.750653	2026-04-25 13:46:57.682529
189	15	7	7	Aq'ab'al					{"nawal": {"title": "The Dawn of Revelation", "content": "Aq'ab'al is the energy of the dawn and the dusk—the twilight times. It represents the transition from darkness to light, the moment when the sun has not yet risen but the night has ended. It is the nawal of new beginnings, hope, and the renewal of the self. Aq'ab'al governs the concept of 'light inside the darkness' and the potential for clarity to emerge from confusion. It is often associated with the polarity of youth and old age, or the conscious and subconscious. In its shadow, Aq'ab'al can bring uncertainty, a fear of the light, or a tendency to mask one's true self. But in its light, it is the glorious promise of a new day, the revelation of secrets, and the gentle warmth that wakes the world.", "keywords": ["Dawn", "Transition", "Hope", "Duality", "Renewal"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mystic at the Crossroads", "content": "Tone 7 represents the top of the pyramid, the midpoint of the 13-day cycle. It is a place of high perspective, equilibrium, and mystical power. Unlike the 6, which is stable flow, the 7 is a pause—a moment of stillness where we can look back at where we came from (1-6) and forward to where we are going (8-13). It is the number of 'mystical death' or the void, where potential is limitless. On a 7 day, the veil between worlds is thin. We are given the capacity to see both sides of any duality without choosing. It is a day of reflection, channeling, and making choices from a place of higher vision. However, this lack of direction can sometimes feel indecisive or ungrounded. It is pure potential energy hovering at the peak.", "keywords": ["Midpoint", "Reflection", "Mysticism", "Perspective", "Equilibrium"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Stand in the 'in-between' spaces; do not rush to define things today.", "Reflect on your past 6 days; what is ready to be illuminated?", "Embrace your shadow side; see the light hidden within your darkness.", "Look for signs and clarity at dawn or dusk.", "Use this high perspective to gain objectivity on a confusing situation."], "title": "The Threshold of Vision", "content": "7 Aq'ab'al is a profoundly mystical day, representing the ultimate threshold. We have the 'midpoint' energy of the 7 combined with the 'transition' energy of Aq'ab'al. This creates a double layer of liminality—we are at the center of the cycle, standing in the doorway of the dawn. It is a day of high vision where we can clearly see the contrast between our past (the night) and our potential future (the day). The energy is balanced perfectly between light and dark, allowing us to integrate our shadow selves with compassion. It is an excellent day for deep meditation, for realizing that 'problems' are just dawn breaking on a new understanding. The 7 asks us not to rush through the door, but to stand on the threshold and observe the beauty of the change. It is a moment of suspended time where the impossible feels reachable."}}	{"title": "The Keeper of the Twilight", "content": "To be born on 7 Aq'ab'al is to be a soul who walks between worlds. You are the 'Mystic of the Dawn.' The number 7 places you at the top of the pyramid, giving you a natural detachment and a panoramic view of life, while Aq'ab'al gives you dominion over the shifting sands of transition. You are never fully 'this' or 'that'; you are the bridge. You understand that light and dark are not enemies, but partners in the dance of creation. People are drawn to you because you hold a space of non-judgment; you can see the validity in opposing viewpoints and the hope in hopeless situations.\\n\\nYour life path is one of constant renewal. You may reinvent yourself many times, shedding skins like a snake or rising like the sun. You have a gift for helping others through their own transitions—birth, death, career changes, or spiritual awakenings. You are a way-shower, holding the lantern at the crossroads so others can find their path. Your intuition is powerful, often bordering on psychic, as the 7 connects you directly to the spirit world. You see the potential in people long before they see it in themselves.\\n\\nHowever, the challenge of 7 Aq'ab'al is finding solid ground. Living in the 'in-between' can be exhausting, and you may struggle with indecision or a feeling of never truly landing. The 7 can make you aloof, and Aq'ab'al can make you hide your true feelings behind a mask of optimism. Your soul's growth lies in learning to bring the vision of the dawn down into the practical day. You must learn that while you are a bridge, you are also allowed to cross over and inhabit the new world you have helped to birth."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c69283", "primary": "#0f1617", "secondary": "#413b3f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.848049	2026-04-25 13:46:57.972635
187	15	5	5	Imox					{"nawal": {"title": "The Primordial Dreamer", "content": "Imox is the spirit of the water—the ocean, the rain, and the fluid depths of the collective unconscious. It represents the left hemisphere of the brain, the intuitive, the crazy, and the creative. Imox is the primordial soup from which all things emerge; it is the chaos of potential before it is ordered. It governs dreams, psychic abilities, and the subtle undercurrents of emotion. In its light, Imox is the source of boundless creativity and empathy, the nurturer who connects to the oneness of all things. In its shadow, it can bring confusion, madness, or emotional drowning. It is the 'lizard' or 'crocodile' consciousness—ancient, instinctual, and submerged. Imox asks us to trust our feelings over our logic and to flow with the strange tides of the universe.", "keywords": ["Water", "Intuition", "Dreams", "Chaos", "Collective"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Empowerment", "content": "Tone 5 represents the energy of 'gathering' and work. It is associated with the human hand (five fingers) and the ability to grasp, shape, and utilize resources. After the foundation of the 4 is set, the 5 adds a center point—making a pyramid. It is the energy of empowerment, action, and the application of will. Tone 5 breaks the static stability of the 4 to get things done. It is dynamic, intelligent, and influential. This tone asks us to take the materials we have gathered and put them to use. It is a day of work, but work that is aligned and effective. It creates a net that captures energy and directs it toward a goal. 5 is the central pillar of the number cycle (1-9), representing the core strength required to push through obstacles.", "keywords": ["Empowerment", "Work", "Action", "Center", "Grasp"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Put effort into a creative or artistic project; make the dream tangible.", "Trust your intuition as a practical tool for decision making today.", "Be mindful of the 'collective mood'; do not absorb what isn't yours.", "Work with water—baths, rivers, or rain—to cleanse your energy field.", "Channel any feelings of chaos into a disciplined practice (yoga, writing, dance)."], "title": "Empowering the Dream", "content": "5 Imox is a day of working with the invisible. It brings the active, grasping energy of Tone 5 into the fluid, dreamlike realm of Imox. This creates a powerful opportunity to 'capture' a dream and begin to give it form. It is the work of the artist who pulls a vision from the ether and wrestles it onto the canvas. The energy today is dense with psychic potential; our ability to influence the collective emotional field is heightened. We are asked to put effort into our intuition—to not just passively feel, but to actively *use* our sensitivity as a tool. However, this combination can also feel eccentric or overwhelming, as the work required is internal and psychological. It is a day to empower your creative madness, to trust your gut instincts, and to realize that the 'unseen' is just as workable as clay or wood."}}	{"title": "The Practical Mystic", "content": "To be born on 5 Imox is to be a bridge between the dream world and the working world. You possess the rare ability to grasp the intangible. While Imox is often lost in the clouds or the depths of the ocean, the number 5 gives you hands to hold onto those visions and put them to work. You are a 'Practical Mystic'—someone who can navigate the chaos of the collective unconscious and bring back pearls of wisdom that are actually useful. You may be drawn to professions that require deep intuition applied with discipline, such as psychology, creative arts, or spiritual healing.\\n\\nYour energy is magnetic and sometimes enigmatic. People sense that you are connected to a deeper current, yet you are not drifty; you are surprisingly capable and hardworking. You have a natural talent for 'gathering'—whether it is gathering people into a community or gathering scattered ideas into a cohesive whole. You feel the emotions of others deeply, often acting as a psychic sponge, but your 5 energy gives you the strength to wring that sponge out and use the water to nourish your own garden. You are an agent of change, using your sensitivity to empower others.\\n\\nHowever, the challenge of 5 Imox is managing the volume of input you receive. The work of the 5 combined with the sensitivity of Imox can lead to burnout or 'compassion fatigue.' You may struggle to distinguish your own feelings from the collective ocean around you. Your shadow side might drift into eccentricity or paranoia if you do not stay grounded. Your soul's lesson is to keep your 'hands' busy with the work of creation, using the physical world as an anchor for your vast, watery spirit."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#6cc7b8", "primary": "#0d1a18", "secondary": "#2b534e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.847344	2026-04-25 13:46:57.970576
241	19	7	7	Ajmaq					{"nawal": {"title": "The Owl of Forgiveness", "content": "Ajmaq is the nawal of the owl, the ancestors, and the sinner/saint. It represents the human condition in all its flaw and glory. Ajmaq is the energy of forgiveness, reconciliation, and the wisdom that comes from making mistakes. Associated with the element of earth and the spirit world, it carries a soft, solemn, and deeply compassionate energy. It is the archetype of the elder who looks back on life with understanding rather than judgment. In daily life, Ajmaq manifests as curiosity, the questioning of authority, and the healing of ancestral lines. Its shadow aspect can be guilt, shame, or the refusal to learn from the past. Ajmaq teaches us that our imperfections are the cracks where the light enters.", "keywords": ["Forgiveness", "Ancestors", "Wisdom", "Redemption", "Curiosity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mystic Prism", "content": "Tone 7 is the midpoint of the 13-day cycle, sitting at the very top of the energetic pyramid. It represents the point of maximum potential, reflection, and mystical power. Unlike the stability of 4 or the flow of 6, Tone 7 is a threshold energy—neither here nor there, but encompassing both the beginning and the end. It is a day of 'no time,' where the veil between worlds is thin. Experientially, Tone 7 feels contemplative, strange, and highly intuitive. It provides a 360-degree view of reality, allowing us to see the past and future simultaneously. While it offers profound insights and the ability to channel energy, its shadow can be indecision, confusion, or getting lost in the ether. It is the mirror at the top of the mountain.", "keywords": ["Insight", "Reflection", "Mysticism", "Threshold", "Vision"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Light a candle for your ancestors and ask for their blessing.", "Forgive yourself for a past mistake; see it as a necessary lesson.", "Visit a cemetery or a place of historical significance.", "Meditate on the concept of 'wholeness' including your shadows.", "Use divination to ask about a karmic pattern in your life."], "title": "The Mystic Forgiveness", "content": "When the mystical peak of Tone 7 meets the redemptive power of Ajmaq, we reach a threshold of 'Ancestral Healing.' 7 Ajmaq is the day to end and begin with ancestral wisdom. Standing at the top of the pyramid, we can look back at the lineage that created us—all the triumphs and all the mistakes. Tone 7 allows us to see the entire pattern without judgment, while Ajmaq provides the compassion to forgive it. This is a powerful day for clearing karma and releasing generational trauma. The energy is quiet, profound, and deeply internal. It feels like a moment of silence where the ghosts of the past are finally laid to rest. 7 Ajmaq invites us to embrace our own humanity, accepting that we are a mix of light and dark. The challenge is to not get lost in the past or overwhelmed by the collective grief. The opportunity is to use this threshold to choose a new path, free from the weight of history."}}	{"title": "The Mystic of Reconciliation", "content": "To be born on 7 Ajmaq is to be a bridge between the past and the future, the human and the divine. You possess a soul that is deeply reflective and compassionate. Tone 7 places you at the center of the mystery, giving you a 360-degree perspective on life, while Ajmaq connects you to the wisdom of the ancestors and the power of forgiveness. You are the one who understands the 'why' behind human behavior. You do not judge; you observe, you understand, and you heal. You are likely a natural counselor, medium, or historian.\\n\\nYour life path is one of spiritual integration. You are here to reconcile opposites—to find the light in the dark, the saint in the sinner. You have a profound curiosity about the hidden side of life. You may experience strong intuition or psychic flashes, as the veil is thin for you. You are a peacemaker, not by avoiding conflict, but by understanding the deep roots of it. You help others to accept their imperfections and to find grace in their struggles.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 7 Ajmaq soul is the weight of the collective unconscious. You feel the pain of the world and the unresolved issues of your lineage as if they were your own. You may struggle with a sense of unworthiness or existential guilt. There is a risk of getting lost in the 'other world,' dissociating from the present moment. Your lesson is to use your mystical sight to bring healing to the here and now. When you ground your compassion in the present, you become a powerful agent of redemption, helping the world to forgive itself and move forward."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#afa9bc", "primary": "#151b1e", "secondary": "#4a4857"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.878233	2026-04-25 13:46:58.061029
196	16	1	1	Q'anil	You walk out into the black expanse, the soil yielding softly under your weight like memory foam. With every step, faint rings of violet light ripple out from your heels, fading into the dark. You find a spot that feels magnetic, a place where the thrumming from below is strongest. You kneel.\n\nThe earth here is warm. As you dig your hands into the soil to make a furrow, you are startled—it is wet and moves against your fingers. It feels less like dirt and more like the side of a great, sleeping animal. You are not just digging a hole; you are waking something up.\n\nYou place the amber seed into the small cradle you have made. For a second, nothing happens. Then, the soil *contracts*. It closes over the seed of its own accord, gripping it tight. A jolt of energy shoots up your arms, shaking your teeth. You pull your hands back just as the ground splits open.\n\nA single, vertical beam of golden light erupts from the planting spot. It solidifies into a thick, translucent stalk that shoots upward, growing feet by the second. It casts long, sharp shadows across the Veldt, illuminating the frightened grass around you. You have broken the seal. The growth has begun, and it is violent, beautiful, and unstoppable.	The universe is clearing its throat today, and the silence it leaves behind is a vast, velvet-black invitation. You are standing on the edge of a world that hasn't been born yet, holding a single, glowing seed of intent that feels heavy with the weight of stars. This isn't the time for half-hearted wishes or looking back at the gardens you’ve already left behind. The soil beneath your feet is hungry for your presence, and the air is thick with the sweet, ozone-rich scent of impending lightning. \n\nYou might feel a strange, magnetic pull toward the unknown, a flicker of 'weird light' crawling up your spine. Do not ignore it. The cosmos is leaning in close, whispering that your wildest ideas aren't just fantasies—they are blueprints. When you step forward, notice how the ground ripples in violet rings around your heels. You are not just walking; you are waking up the ancient, dormant heart of your own potential. If the darkness feels overwhelming, remember that the deepest black makes the brightest neon pop. Plant your dream with a firm hand and watch how the horizon shifts just to get a better look at you. The growth beginning now is violent, beautiful, and absolutely unstoppable. Say yes before your logic remembers how to doubt.	I am the spark that ignites the dark, and I trust the power of my first step.	Sit comfortably with your back straight and eyes closed. Visualize a single, tiny amber spark in the center of your chest. With every inhale, imagine this spark breathing with you, expanding slightly. With every exhale, feel it becoming more concentrated and hot. This is the seed of your thirteen-day journey, containing every victory you have yet to claim.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, imagine the Veldt stretching out around you in total darkness. Feel the thrumming of the earth beneath your seat. Visualize yourself leaning down and pressing that spark into the soil. Watch as a thin vertical beam of golden light erupts from the ground, connecting the earth to the sky and illuminating the path ahead.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Golden Seed of Life", "content": "Q'anil is the nawal of the seed, the star, and the generative power of life itself. It represents fertility, not just of the soil, but of the mind and spirit—the capacity for ideas, projects, and relationships to take root and flourish. Associated with the color yellow and the element of earth, Q'anil carries a gentle, organic energy that trusts in the slow, inevitable process of growth. It is the archetype of the gardener who knows that the harvest is assured if the planting is done with love. In human experience, Q'anil manifests as creativity, abundance, and a deep appreciation for beauty and biological rhythms. Its shadow side can appear as impatience, frustration with the slowness of maturation, or a vanity that seeks the flower without tending the roots. Ultimately, Q'anil teaches us that every moment is a planting for a future harvest.", "keywords": ["Growth", "Fertility", "Creativity", "Beauty", "Fruition"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Fire", "content": "Tone 1 represents the initial spark of creation, the singularity from which all potential unfolds. It is the number of unity, beginnings, and the pure, unadulterated impulse to exist. Like a seed lying in the dark earth, Tone 1 contains the blueprint for the entire cycle that follows, holding immense power in a concentrated form. Experientially, this energy feels like a sudden clarity or a surge of new intent—a moment where the past falls away and only the future's possibility remains. It is a day of initiation, where your thoughts and actions plant the vibrations that will ripple through the next thirteen days. In its shadow aspect, Tone 1 can feel isolating or overwhelming, a blinding light with no direction. However, when embraced, it offers the profound gift of focus and the authority to define a new narrative.", "keywords": ["Beginnings", "Unity", "Potential", "Initiation", "Focus"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Plant a physical or metaphorical seed today to anchor your thirteen-day intention.", "Review your current projects and decide which ones deserve your vital energy.", "Avoid rushing the process; trust that the cycle has its own perfect timing.", "Connect with nature or soil to ground your abstract ideas into the physical realm.", "Speak your goals aloud, as Q'anil responds to the vibration of life-affirming sound."], "title": "Planting the Star-Seed of Intention", "content": "When the initiating spark of Tone 1 meets the fertile potential of Q'anil, we enter a day of profound creative inception. 1 Q'anil is the quintessential 'planting day' of the Mayan calendar—a moment where the universe is exceptionally receptive to your intentions. The energy here is not about forceful action, but about the precise and reverent placement of your dreams into the fabric of reality. It feels like standing in a sunlit garden with a handful of seeds, knowing that what you choose to bury today will inevitably become your reality in the days to come. This combination invites you to clarify exactly what you wish to grow in your life. Are you planting seeds of joy, prosperity, and connection, or are you unconsciously sowing doubt? The synthesis of these energies creates a portal for conscious manifestation, where the gap between thought and form is bridged by the act of beginning. It is a time to trust the biological and spiritual cycles of life, knowing that the beginning contains the end, and the seed contains the fruit."}}	{"title": "The Planter of Living Stars", "content": "To be born on 1 Q'anil is to be a true initiator of growth and a carrier of infinite potential. You possess a soul that is naturally attuned to the cycles of creation, instinctively knowing when to start new ventures and how to nurture them into existence. You are the gardener of the community, the one who brings the spark of life to dormant situations. Your presence alone often acts as a catalyst, inspiring others to believe in their own ability to bloom. There is a radiant, star-like quality to your spirit; you carry a natural optimism and a belief in the abundance of the universe that is infectious.\\n\\nYour life path is one of planting and initiating. Unlike those who are meant to maintain or harvest, your greatest power lies in the beginning of things—the conception of ideas, the start of relationships, and the founding of movements. You are gifted with a fertile mind that is constantly generating new possibilities. However, because you carry the energy of the 'Seed,' you may sometimes feel vulnerable or delicate, needing the right environment to thrive. It is essential for you to surround yourself with supportive conditions and people who protect your growth rather than stifle it.\\n\\nChallenges for you may arise in the form of impatience or a fear that your efforts will not yield results. Because you stand at the very beginning of the cycle (Tone 1), you may sometimes feel the weight of having to do it all alone. Remember that your role is to provide the initial impulse and the fertile ground; you do not have to force the flower to open. Trust in the organic unfolding of your life, for you are the living evidence that even the smallest seed contains a galaxy of potential."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#a4a97f", "primary": "#111918", "secondary": "#3f4338"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.851661	2026-04-25 14:38:01.319839
197	16	2	2	Toj	The stalk you planted yesterday has become a beacon. It towers over you now, a pillar of amber light humming with energy. But as you admire the height, you notice the ground at its base is disturbed. The soil churns, and a second shape twists its way out of the earth.\n\nIt is not made of light. It is a gnarled, obsidian root, thick as your arm and covered in thorns. It wraps itself around the base of your golden stalk, looking like a parasite strangling its host. Your instinct screams to cut it away, to protect the purity of the light.\n\nYou reach for a sharp stone, but a sound stops you. Thump. Thump. The Grazer is watching from the edge of the light. It shakes its head—a blur of starlight—and looks pointedly at your water skin. You hesitate, then look closer at the plant. The golden stalk is swaying dangerously in a sudden wind; it is too tall, too top-heavy. The dark root is not strangling it; it is anchoring it.\n\nUnderstanding floods you. You uncork your water skin. You do not pour it on the beautiful flower. You pour the precious water onto the ugly, black root. It hisses as it drinks, expanding, digging deeper, locking the light into the earth. The swaying stops. The duality is struck. The shadow supports the light.	Beauty is only half the story today. While you’ve been busy admiring the glowing stalk of your latest success, something gnarled and obsidian is twisting its way out of the earth at your feet. Your first instinct might be to pull away, to view this dark, thorny interloper as a threat to your light. But look closer. That shadow isn't here to strangle your joy; it’s here to anchor it. The most brilliant heights require the deepest roots, and today asks you to feed the parts of your life that feel 'ugly' or difficult with the same devotion you give to your highlights.\n\nThe air is hissing with the energy of a sacred exchange. If a choice feels hot, cool it with a breath. If a relationship feels lopsided, check the ledger of your heart. Are you pouring your precious energy into things that actually stabilize you, or are you just chasing the glow? True power is found in the duality of the root and the bloom. Embrace the grit. Pour your gratitude onto the difficult soil, and watch how it locks your brilliance into the earth, making you unshakeable even when the sudden winds of change start to howl. The cosmos has a mischievous grin today, daring you to find the holiness in the thorns. Balance is not a static state; it’s a living, breathing sacrifice. Honor the anchor.	Every gift I receive is a seed I return with thanks, keeping the circle of life in motion.	Close your eyes and bring your attention to your breath. As you inhale, feel the air as a gift of light entering your lungs. As you exhale, release the breath as an offering of gratitude back to the world. Feel the natural reciprocity of this exchange, restoring balance to your internal rhythm.\n\nOptionally, if you wish to go deeper, visualize your spine as a glowing pillar of amber light reaching for the stars. Simultaneously, feel thick, gnarled obsidian roots growing from your base deep into the dark earth. Feel how the 'ugly' strength of the roots provides the necessary anchor for your light to stand tall against the wind.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Fire of Exchange", "content": "Toj is the nawal of offering, payment, and the sacred fire. It represents the universal law of reciprocity—the understanding that in order to receive, one must give. Toj is the energy of clearing karmic debts and restoring balance through sacrifice and gratitude. Associated with the element of fire and the color red, it carries a warm, purifying, and sometimes intense energy. It is the archetype of the ritualist who tends the hearth and ensures that the exchange between the human and spiritual worlds is honored. In daily life, Toj manifests as the need to pay bills, help others, or offer thanks. Its shadow aspect involves feeling burdened by debt, martyrdom, or the feeling that one is always giving without return. Toj reminds us that gratitude is the currency of the universe.", "keywords": ["Gratitude", "Offering", "Balance", "Purification", "Reciprocity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Mirror of Duality", "content": "Tone 2 introduces the concept of the 'other.' It is the energy of polarity, partnership, and the dynamic tension between opposites. If Tone 1 is the solitary point, Tone 2 is the line connecting two points, creating relationship. This number governs the mysteries of duality: light and dark, masculine and feminine, inner and outer. Experientially, Tone 2 often brings choices or presents situations where you must weigh two sides of a coin. It is a day of reflection, where the world acts as a mirror to your internal state. While it can bring the challenge of indecision or conflict, its higher expression is balance and cooperation. It teaches that separation is an illusion and that opposing forces are actually complementary halves of a greater whole.", "keywords": ["Polarity", "Reflection", "Connection", "Balance", "Choice"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Evaluate the give-and-take dynamic in your close relationships.", "Make a physical or energetic offering to clear stagnant energy.", "Pay a financial debt or resolve an emotional obligation to free your mind.", "Practice gratitude specifically for the people who challenge you.", "Light a candle to honor the balance between your needs and the needs of others."], "title": "Balancing the Scales of Reciprocity", "content": "The pairing of Tone 2's duality with Toj's law of exchange creates a powerful day for harmonizing relationships through giving and receiving. 2 Toj asks us to look at the 'ledger' of our connections. Are we giving too much and receiving too little? Or are we taking without offering gratitude in return? The energy today is like a gentle fire that warms but also illuminates imbalances in our partnerships. It is an auspicious time to settle debts—whether financial, emotional, or spiritual—and to do so with a partner or a witness. This combined energy suggests that true balance (2) is achieved not by holding on, but by the fluid circulation of energy (Toj). It encourages us to see our partners not as separate entities, but as collaborators in the sacred act of living. The challenge today may be facing the transactional nature of some interactions, but the opportunity is to transform those transactions into sacred offerings."}}	{"title": "The Partner of Sacred Balance", "content": "To be born on 2 Toj is to be a natural harmonizer and a bridge between worlds. You carry the energy of the sacred fire within a vessel of partnership, making you deeply sensitive to the dynamics of exchange and reciprocity. You are likely the person in your family or friend group who ensures that everyone is treated fairly and that no debt—emotional or physical—goes unpaid. Your soul instinctively understands the law of karma: that every action has a reaction, and every gift requires gratitude. This makes you a generous and attentive partner, always seeking to balance the scales of love and support.\\n\\nYour life path is woven with the themes of duality and offering. You flourish in one-on-one relationships where you can practice the art of giving and receiving. You may find yourself drawn to professions involving healing, counseling, or financial balancing, where you can help others restore equilibrium to their lives. The number 2 gifts you with the ability to see multiple perspectives, while Toj drives you to find a resolution that honors all parties. You are a diplomat of the spirit, using gratitude as your primary tool for negotiation.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 2 Toj soul often lies in the shadow of 'over-giving' or becoming a martyr for the sake of peace. You may struggle with setting boundaries, feeling that you owe the world more than you actually do. It is crucial for you to learn that you cannot pour from an empty cup. Your lesson is to include yourself in the circle of gratitude and to realize that receiving is also a spiritual act. When you balance your own needs with your desire to serve, you become a powerful conduit for the universe's abundance."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d19a66", "primary": "#1c1917", "secondary": "#6c3c29"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.851992	2026-04-25 14:38:01.32044
260	20	13	13	Kej	You take the final steps. The rock turns to pure crystal. You step onto the summit.\n\nThere is nothing higher than this. You are surrounded by 360 degrees of sky. The sun is a blazing diamond above you.\n\nStanding at the very peak is the Guardian of the Zenith—a Stag made of clouds and starlight. Its antlers stretch out to hold the four corners of the sky.\n\n13 is Ascension. Kej is the Deer, the Nature Spirit, the King of the Wild.\n\nThe Stag lowers its head. You touch its nose. A jolt of pure connection runs through you. You are connected to the North, South, East, and West. You are connected to the Earth below and the Sky above.\n\nYou realize that the "Vision" of Tz’ikin was never about seeing something *out there*. It was about seeing yourself as the center of the mandala. You are the connection point.\n\nProsperity is not something you gather; it is something you ARE when you are in your natural place, standing tall, balanced, and free.\n\nYou stand with the Stag. You look out at the infinite horizon. You feel the wind, the sun, the silence.\n\nYou have arrived.\n\nYou spread your arms. You are not just a climber anymore. You are the Spire. You are the Vision.\n\nYou are the Eagle flying in the shape of a Human.	You made it. The view from here is incredible. The energy of 13 Kej is the King of the Mountain. You have climbed the spire of vision, and now you can see everything clearly.\n\nStand tall today. Feel the strength in your legs and the spirit in your heart. You are balanced, powerful, and free. Take a moment to just breathe in the rare air of success. You are exactly where you are supposed to be.	I stand at the summit of my life, strong, balanced, and free.	Visualize yourself as a mountain. Your roots go deep into the earth. Your peak touches the stars. \n\nClouds float around your waist. Eagles fly around your head. You are ancient, stable, and majestic. Nothing can shake you.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Guardian of the Wild", "content": "Kej is the nawal of the deer, the four directions, and the wilderness. It represents harmony with nature and balance between the physical and spiritual worlds. Protector of the forests and sacred paths. Associated with the element of earth and the color brown or green, it carries a strong, majestic, and grounded energy. It is the archetype of the spiritual leader who stands on four legs, stable and alert. In daily life, Kej manifests as connection to nature, physical strength, and the authority that comes from walking one's talk. Its shadow aspect can be stubbornness, dominance, or being overly demanding. Kej teaches us to stand our ground with grace.", "keywords": ["Nature", "Grounding", "Balance", "Strength", "Grace"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascended Renewal", "content": "Tone 13 is the energy of completion, transcendence, and the spirit realm. It is the final step of the cycle, where the energy transforms into a new octave. It represents the ancestors, the universal movement, and the unseen forces. Experientially, Tone 13 feels light, magical, and sometimes ungrounded. It is a day where the rules of the physical world feel less rigid. It marks the end of the trecena, wrapping up the lessons and preparing the seed for the next cycle. While it offers spiritual connection and a sense of accomplishment, its shadow can be spaciness or a feeling of being 'done' before the work is truly finished. It is the spirit rising from the body.", "keywords": ["Completion", "Ascension", "Transformation", "Ancestors", "Spirit"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Go into the wilderness and offer a prayer of thanks.", "Connect with the four directions in a closing ceremony.", "Stand barefoot on the earth and feel the energy rising.", "Reflect on how your vision (Tz'ikin) has grounded into reality (Kej).", "Ask the spirits of nature for guidance on your next cycle."], "title": "The Ascended Guardian", "content": "The transcendent energy of Tone 13 culminates in the natural majesty of Kej, creating a day of 'Spiritual Sovereignty.' 13 Kej is the Lord of the Forest ascending to the spirit realm. The Tz'ikin trecena began with a vision, and it ends with the realization of that vision in the natural world. The energy is strong, noble, and deeply connected to the elements. It is a day to commune with the wilderness and to feel the divinity in nature. 13 Kej asks us to stand tall in our spiritual authority, balanced between heaven and earth. It is a powerful time for shamanic work, connecting with the four directions, or simply being in awe of creation. The challenge is to remain grounded while reaching for the sky. The opportunity is to embody the grace of the Deer and the power of the Spirit, closing the cycle with strength and beauty."}}	{"title": "The Spirit Guardian of Nature", "content": "To be born on 13 Kej is to be a powerful shamanic presence and a guardian of the wild. You possess a soul that is deeply connected to the earth and the spirit world simultaneously. Tone 13 gives you a transcendent, magical quality, while Kej grounds you in the strength of the Deer and the wisdom of the forest. You are a natural leader, but your authority comes from a higher source. You are here to protect the sacred balance of nature and to remind humans of their place in the web of life.\\n\\nYour life path is one of spiritual ecology. You are a bridge between the civilized and the wild, the human and the divine. You may be drawn to environmentalism, shamanism, outdoor leadership, or healing. You have a majestic presence that commands respect. You are sensitive to the subtle energies of the land and can often 'hear' what nature is saying. You are a warrior for the earth, standing strong against anything that threatens the balance.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 13 Kej soul is finding your place in the modern world. You may feel like an alien in the city, longing for the silence of the woods. You might struggle with the rigidity of human rules, preferring the laws of nature. There is a risk of becoming ungrounded or escaping into spiritual realms to avoid physical reality. Your lesson is to bring the wild into the world. When you embody the spirit of the forest in your daily life, you become a living testament to the sacredness of all creation."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#afbd8a", "primary": "#121812", "secondary": "#404734"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#b2b18e", "primary": "#1a293d", "secondary": "#4c656e"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#e4eff4", "primary": "#7292be", "secondary": "#aac3da"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#bcc8d2", "primary": "#0e62aa", "secondary": "#7192b3"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.888212	2026-04-25 13:46:58.076408
219	17	11	11	Q'anil					{"nawal": {"title": "The Golden Seed of Life", "content": "Q'anil is the nawal of the seed, the star, and the generative power of life itself. It represents fertility, not just of the soil, but of the mind and spirit—the capacity for ideas, projects, and relationships to take root and flourish. Associated with the color yellow and the element of earth, Q'anil carries a gentle, organic energy that trusts in the slow, inevitable process of growth. It is the archetype of the gardener who knows that the harvest is assured if the planting is done with love. In human experience, Q'anil manifests as creativity, abundance, and a deep appreciation for beauty and biological rhythms. Its shadow side can appear as impatience, frustration with the slowness of maturation, or a vanity that seeks the flower without tending the roots. Q'anil teaches us that every moment is a planting for a future harvest.", "keywords": ["Growth", "Fertility", "Creativity", "Beauty", "Fruition"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Dissolution", "content": "Tone 11 is the energy of dissonance, stripping away, and liberation. Unlike the stability of the 10, the 11 introduces a chaotic variable to test the structure. It is the 'master number' of change. Experientially, Tone 11 feels turbulent, unpredictable, and intense. It is a day where things might fall apart, but only so that what is true can remain. It acts as a filter, discarding what is no longer needed before the final ascent of the cycle. While it can bring anxiety or disruption, its higher expression is freedom and the clearing of space. It is the wind that shakes the dead leaves from the tree.", "keywords": ["Change", "Liberation", "Release", "Dissonance", "Clearing"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Let go of a project or idea that has become stagnant.", "Prune your plants or clean up your garden (literally or metaphorically).", "Allow your creative process to be messy and non-linear.", "Release the need for perfection; growth is often chaotic.", "Trust that a breakdown is leading to a breakthrough."], "title": "The Ripening of Release", "content": "When the liberating chaos of Tone 11 meets the fertile seed of Q'anil, we experience a day of 'Evolutionary Growth.' 11 Q'anil is the cracking of the seed coat. For the sprout to emerge, the protective shell must be destroyed. Today's energy is about the uncomfortable but necessary changes that allow for new life. It is a day where old forms of creativity or old projects may fall away to make room for a higher expression. It feels like the growing pains of adolescence or the pruning of a tree. The energy can be turbulent, as the 11 challenges the slow patience of Q'anil. But this friction is what generates the heat for germination. The challenge is to not mourn the shell that is breaking. The opportunity is to focus on the life that is pushing through. Trust that the dissolution is actually a sign of vitality."}}	{"title": "The Catalyst of Organic Growth", "content": "To be born on 11 Q'anil is to be a person of dynamic, evolutionary creativity. You possess a fertile mind that is constantly generating new ideas, but you also carry the restless energy of change. You are the gardener who is not afraid to prune back the roses to ensure they bloom brighter next year. Tone 11 gives you a non-conformist streak and a desire for freedom, while Q'anil grounds you in the love of life and beauty. You are here to shake up the status quo of how things grow, introducing new methods, new seeds, and new ways of being.\\n\\nYour life path is one of constant reinvention. You are not meant to stay the same. You bloom, you shed your petals, and you bloom again in a different form. This can make your life feel unstable at times, but your instability is the source of your genius. You may be drawn to the arts, permaculture, or social innovation—fields where you can experiment with the laws of creation. You have a unique ability to find the potential in the 'waste' or the 'chaos' that others discard.\\n\\nThe challenge for an 11 Q'anil soul is impatience. You want the forest to grow overnight, and you may tear things up before they have had a chance to take root. You can be hard on yourself and others when growth doesn't happen fast enough. There is also a risk of scattering your seeds—starting too many things and finishing none. Your lesson is to trust the wisdom of the cycle. When you learn to work with the seasons of your life rather than fighting them, your chaotic energy transforms into a powerful, regenerative force."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d3ce8a", "primary": "#131f19", "secondary": "#525d3f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.861292	2026-04-25 13:46:58.001167
221	17	13	13	Tz'i'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Faithful Guide of Law", "content": "Tz'i' is the nawal of law, justice, and the dog. It represents the principle of divine order and the instinctual guidance that keeps us on the path of truth. Tz'i' is the faithful companion who guards the threshold, ensuring that we remain loyal to our highest purpose and to our community. Associated with the element of fire and the concept of authority, it brings a protective and corrective energy. It is the archetype of the judge, the lawyer, and the loyal friend. In daily life, Tz'i' manifests as questions of ethics, fidelity, and the right use of power. Its shadow aspect can be judgmentality, rigidity, or the corruption of authority. Tz'i' teaches us that true justice is not about rules, but about alignment with cosmic love.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Loyalty", "Faith", "Guidance", "Protection"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascended Renewal", "content": "Tone 13 is the energy of completion, transcendence, and the spirit realm. It is the final step of the cycle, where the energy transforms into a new octave. It represents the ancestors, the universal movement, and the unseen forces. Experientially, Tone 13 feels light, magical, and sometimes ungrounded. It is a day where the rules of the physical world feel less rigid. It marks the end of the trecena, wrapping up the lessons and preparing the seed for the next cycle. While it offers spiritual connection and a sense of accomplishment, its shadow can be spaciness or a feeling of being 'done' before the work is truly finished. It is the spirit rising from the body.", "keywords": ["Completion", "Ascension", "Transformation", "Ancestors", "Spirit"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Meditate on the concept of Divine Justice versus human justice.", "Review the last 13 days; see how the 'cuts' led to this order.", "Renew a vow or a commitment to yourself or a partner.", "Ask for guidance from your spirit guides or higher self.", "Trust that what has left your life was meant to leave; release it fully."], "title": "The Ascended Justice", "content": "The transcendent energy of Tone 13 culminates in the faithful law of Tz'i', creating a day of 'Divine Order.' 13 Tz'i' is the final judgment, not in a punitive sense, but in the sense of everything falling into its rightful place. The trecena of Tijax began with a cut; it ends with the law that heals. Today, we see the higher purpose behind the severance. The energy feels authoritative, absolute, and deeply spiritual. It is a day to trust that the universe is just and that your path is protected. 13 Tz'i' connects us to the Cosmic Law that supersedes human rules. It is an ideal time for legal matters, making vows, or committing to a spiritual path. The challenge is to let go of your own limited ideas of 'fairness' and surrender to the divine plan. The opportunity is to walk through the gate of the next cycle with absolute faith."}}	{"title": "The High Priest of Divine Law", "content": "To be born on 13 Tz'i' is to be a custodian of cosmic order and a channel for divine authority. You possess a presence that is both commanding and mystical. Tone 13 connects you to the spirit world and the ancestors, while Tz'i' grounds you in the principles of loyalty and justice. You are not interested in petty rules; you are interested in the Truth with a capital T. You are likely a natural leader, judge, or spiritual teacher—someone who can see the energetic laws behind physical reality.\\n\\nYour life path is one of aligning the human world with the divine will. You are here to correct imbalances, to protect the sacred, and to guide others back to the path of integrity. You have a powerful intuition that acts as an internal lie detector; you can sense dishonesty or misalignment instantly. People respect you because you walk your talk. You are a loyal friend and a fierce protector of those you love, often serving as the 'spiritual lawyer' for your community.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 13 Tz'i' soul is the potential for fanaticism or being overly judgmental. You may struggle to accept human frailty, expecting everyone (including yourself) to live up to impossible standards of perfection. You might also feel ungrounded, as if you don't quite belong to this world. Your lesson is to temper justice with mercy. When you remember that love is the highest law of the universe, your authority transforms from a gavel into a guiding light, leading others home to their own truth."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#aececd", "primary": "#111d1f", "secondary": "#3d5c6c"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.8619	2026-04-25 13:46:58.005965
211	17	3	3	Ajpu					{"nawal": {"title": "The Hero of Light", "content": "Ajpu is the nawal of the sun, the blowgunner, and the hero. It represents the divine spark within the human, the mastery of self, and the triumph of light over darkness. Ajpu is the energy of the warrior who fights for beauty and truth. Associated with the element of fire and the sun, it carries a radiant, confident, and masculine energy. It is the archetype of the artist-warrior who walks the path of holiness in everyday life. In daily life, Ajpu manifests as clarity, leadership, overcoming challenges, and the recognition of one's own divinity. Its shadow aspect can be ego, arrogance, or the testing of one's integrity. Ajpu teaches us that we are the light of the world.", "keywords": ["Divinity", "Heroism", "Sun", "Purpose", "Mastery"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Movement", "content": "Tone 3 is the energy of movement, vibration, and communication. It breaks the static balance of the number 2, introducing flow and dynamism. If 1 is the point and 2 is the line, 3 is the triangle—the first geometric form that implies stability yet encourages motion. It represents the integration of the right brain, left brain, and the central nervous system, or the union of mind, body, and spirit. Experientially, Tone 3 feels busy, expressive, and sometimes restless. It is a day of 'doing,' where ideas seek to be spoken and energies seek to be circulated. While it fosters creativity and connection, its shadow can manifest as scattered energy, anxiety, or a lack of focus. It is the pulse that keeps the universe from standing still.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Expression", "Energy", "Instability", "Flow"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in physical exercise or dance to move the solar energy through your body.", "Take a leadership role in a meeting or group activity.", "Work on a creative project that allows you to shine.", "Confront a challenge head-on with the confidence of a warrior.", "Speak your truth publicly or share your work with an audience."], "title": "The Active Hero's Journey", "content": "When the dynamic movement of Tone 3 combines with the solar power of Ajpu, we get a day of 'Action in the Light.' 3 Ajpu is the energy of the Hero in motion. It is not a day for contemplation; it is a day for demonstration. The divine spark within you wants to express itself through movement, creativity, and leadership. This is the energy of the performer taking the stage or the athlete entering the arena. It feels vibrant, electric, and unstoppable. 3 Ajpu supports overcoming obstacles through sheer vitality and confidence. If you have been hiding your light, today it will burst forth. It is an excellent day for public speaking, artistic performance, or taking a bold step toward your life's purpose. The challenge is to manage the ego, which may become inflated by the rush of attention and energy. The opportunity is to let your actions be a testament to the spirit that moves through you."}}	{"title": "The Radiant Messenger of Spirit", "content": "To be born on 3 Ajpu is to be a beacon of light in motion. You possess a charismatic, energetic personality that naturally draws attention. You are the Solar Hero who cannot sit still—you must be doing, creating, and expressing. Tone 3 gives you a communicative gift and a rhythmic nature; you likely have a talent for music, dance, or public speaking. Ajpu fills you with a sense of divine purpose and the confidence to pursue it. You are here to show the world what it looks like when a human being is fully alive and aligned with their spirit.\\n\\nYour life path is one of creative expression and spiritual leadership. You are not a monk on a mountain; you are a mystic in the marketplace. You teach through your actions and your art. You may find yourself in the spotlight often, whether you seek it or not, because your energy is simply too bright to ignore. You have a warrior's spirit when it comes to defending the truth, but your weapon of choice is your voice or your craft. You are a natural motivator, inspiring others to find their own inner sun.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 3 Ajpu soul is the potential for burnout or scattering your immense energy. You may take on too many battles or try to shine in too many directions at once. There is also the risk of the 'performer's trap'—needing external validation to feel worthy. Your ego can be your greatest enemy if you forget that you are the channel, not the source. Your lesson is to cultivate an inner stillness that anchors your movement. When you move from a place of centered divinity rather than restless ego, your light becomes a steady, warming sun rather than a flickering flame."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#decb92", "primary": "#171b18", "secondary": "#644e34"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.858317	2026-04-25 13:46:58.009127
214	17	6	6	Aq'ab'al					{"nawal": {"title": "The Dawn of Possibility", "content": "Aq'ab'al is the nawal of the dawn, the twilight, and the new day. It represents the bridge between night and day, dream and reality. Symbolizes new beginnings, awakening, and creative potential being born. Associated with the colors red and black (dawn/dusk), it carries a hopeful, transitional, and clarifying energy. It is the archetype of the early riser who witnesses the first light. In daily life, Aq'ab'al manifests as sudden realizations, the start of new relationships, and the shifting of polarity. Its shadow aspect can be fear of the unknown, hesitation, or getting stuck in the 'grey area' between choices. Aq'ab'al teaches us that every ending is a new beginning.", "keywords": ["Beginnings", "Potential", "Revelation", "Transition", "Dawn"]}, "number": {"title": "The Flow of Harmony", "content": "Tone 6 is the energy of flow, rhythm, and responsiveness. After the exertion of the 5, the 6 allows the energy to stabilize and find its natural groove. It is the number of ultimate balance in motion—like a surfer riding a wave or a heart beating in time. In Mayan cosmology, it is associated with the six directions (East, West, North, South, Up, Down), representing a spatial wholeness. Experientially, Tone 6 feels fluid and harmonious. It is a day where things often 'click' into place without force. While it fosters growth and family connection, its shadow can be passivity or a tendency to drift with the current rather than steering. It is the breath that connects the effort to the result.", "keywords": ["Rhythm", "Harmony", "Flow", "Balance", "Growth"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Wake up early to watch the sunrise and set an intention.", "Start a new habit or routine in a gentle, sustainable way.", "Reflect on a recent change and find the harmony in it.", "Address a conflict by seeking a fresh perspective (a new dawn).", "Allow yourself to be in the 'in-between' phase without anxiety."], "title": "The Harmonious Dawn", "content": "The fluid energy of Tone 6 combines with the hopeful light of Aq'ab'al to create a day of 'Gentle Awakening.' 6 Aq'ab'al is the energy of the sunrise that comes softly, without jarring the sleeper. It is a day where new realizations flow into our consciousness with grace and ease. The energy supports transitions of all kinds, helping us move from one state to another without friction. If you have been struggling to start something new, 6 Aq'ab'al provides the rhythmic momentum to get it going. It feels like the fresh, cool air of the morning—full of promise and peace. This combination encourages us to trust the timing of our lives. The sun does not rush to rise, yet it is never late. Today, allow your changes to unfold naturally. The challenge is to remain present in the transition and not rush to the destination. The opportunity is to bring the harmony of the dream world into the waking life."}}	{"title": "The Bringer of Gentle Light", "content": "To be born on 6 Aq'ab'al is to be a person of eternal optimism and harmonious change. You carry the energy of the dawn in your soul, always looking toward the new possibility, the fresh start, the silver lining. Tone 6 gives you a relaxed, flowing nature that puts others at ease, while Aq'ab'al grants you the gift of revelation and the ability to see potential where others see darkness. You are likely the person who brings hope to a situation, the one who says, 'Tomorrow is another day' and truly believes it.\\n\\nYour life path is one of facilitating transitions. You are a bridge-builder, helping people move from the old to the new, from confusion to clarity. You may be drawn to counseling, design, innovation, or working with youth—any field that involves the birthing of new concepts. You have a natural sense of timing and rhythm; you know when to act and when to wait. Your presence is often described as refreshing or revitalizing. You are comfortable in the liminal spaces, the grey areas of life where binary thinking fails.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 6 Aq'ab'al soul is the tendency to avoid the 'night.' You may focus so much on the light and the positive that you bypass the necessary work of the shadow. You might struggle with deeper, darker emotions, preferring to skim the surface where it is bright. There is also a risk of indecision, of staying in the eternal dawn without ever fully stepping into the day. Your growth comes from integrating the dark into your light. When you accept that the night is the mother of the dawn, your optimism deepens into a profound, unshakable wisdom."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d2875f", "primary": "#141519", "secondary": "#783738"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.859466	2026-04-25 13:46:58.011546
217	17	9	9	Kame					{"nawal": {"title": "The Transformer of Worlds", "content": "Kame is the nawal of death, rebirth, and the ancestors. It represents the eternal cycle of transformation and the dimensional gates between worlds. Symbolizes spiritual initiation, death, and rebirth. Associated with the element of spirit and the color yellow or white (bone), it carries a peaceful, absolute, and transcendent energy. It is the archetype of the guide who leads souls through the transition. In daily life, Kame manifests as endings, major life changes, contact with the spirit world, and the need for surrender. Its shadow aspect can be fear of change, morbidity, or clinging to the past. Kame teaches us that death is not the opposite of life, but a part of it.", "keywords": ["Death", "Rebirth", "Transformation", "Courage", "Ancestors"]}, "number": {"title": "The Patience of Gestation", "content": "Tone 9 is the energy of patience, cycles, and the feminine. It represents the nine months of human gestation and the nine levels of the Mayan underworld (Xibalba). It is a number of deep, slow-moving power. Unlike the flash of the 1 or the action of the 5, Tone 9 is the energy of the seed swelling underground just before it breaks the surface. Experientially, it feels heavy, emotional, and sometimes secretive. It is a day for working behind the scenes, nurturing projects, and trusting the dark. While it fosters deep creativity and empathy, its shadow can be depression, lethargy, or getting stuck in the past. It is the womb that holds the future.", "keywords": ["Patience", "Gestation", "Feminine", "Completion", "Depth"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create an altar for your ancestors and light a candle.", "Practice surrender; let go of something you can no longer control.", "Journal about the 'deaths' you have experienced and what they birthed.", "Rest deeply; allow your body to integrate changes.", "Connect with the feminine aspect of divinity or the earth."], "title": "The Gestation of Rebirth", "content": "When the feminine depth of Tone 9 holds the transformative power of Kame, we enter the 'Womb of Rebirth.' 9 Kame is a day of profound, quiet transition. It is the energy of the chrysalis—the state where the caterpillar has dissolved but the butterfly has not yet emerged. Today, the veil between the living and the dead is incredibly thin, but soft. It is a day of gestation for the soul. The energy supports deep psychological work, mediumship, and the honoring of ancestors, especially the grandmothers. It feels like a holy silence. Something is dying in order to be born, and 9 Kame asks us to sit by the bedside and hold its hand. The challenge is the heaviness of the energy; it may bring up grief or a sense of limitation. The opportunity is to realize that this darkness is not a tomb, but a womb. Trust the process of becoming."}}	{"title": "The Midwife of the Soul", "content": "To be born on 9 Kame is to be a guardian of the mysteries of life and death. You possess an old, wise soul that is comfortable with the cycles of ending and beginning. Tone 9 connects you to the deep, feminine power of gestation, while Kame gives you access to the ancestral realms and the transformative power of death. You are not afraid of the dark; in fact, you often find your greatest peace there. You are likely a natural medium, hospice worker, or counselor—someone who helps others navigate the most difficult transitions of their lives.\\n\\nYour life path is one of spiritual alchemy. You are here to demonstrate that nothing is ever truly lost, only transformed. You have a quiet, calming presence that soothes those in grief or pain. You are deeply connected to your lineage and may feel a responsibility to heal ancestral trauma. Unlike those who rush to the light, you understand the value of the waiting period, the time in the cocoon. You are a patient gardener of the soul, knowing that the most beautiful blooms take the longest to open.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 9 Kame soul is a tendency toward melancholy or passivity. You may feel the weight of the world's suffering or the presence of spirits so intensely that you withdraw. You might struggle to let go of the past, living in a state of perpetual nostalgia or grief. Your lesson is to remember that you are also a creature of life. While you honor the ancestors and the endings, you must also participate in the present moment and the joy of living. When you balance your depth with vitality, you become a bridge that helps the world understand the beauty of the eternal cycle."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#cbc0c2", "primary": "#141a1c", "secondary": "#4b4850"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.860638	2026-04-25 13:46:58.014333
222	18	1	1	Toj	The eruption settles into a low, rhythmic thrumming, like the heartbeat of a giant sleeping beneath the rock.\n\nYou are standing on a ridge of cooling obsidian, the heat radiating through the soles of your shoes. The air is filled with drifting sparks, tiny fireflies of pure energy that vanish as soon as they touch the ground.\n\nYou unclench your fist. You don’t remember grabbing anything when you fell, yet there it is—resting in the center of your palm.\n\nA single, glowing ember.\n\nIt pulses with a deep, ruby-red light, hot to the look but strangely cool to the touch. It doesn’t burn your skin. Instead, it hums, vibrating against your lifeline. It feels dense, heavy for its size, as if a mountain of energy has been compressed into a seed small enough to carry.\n\nA wisp of smoke curls up from the ember, twisting into a shape that looks almost like a question mark, then a spiral. A thought enters your mind, not in words, but in a sudden flash of understanding: *This is the seed of the debt. This is the seed of the gift.*\n\nYou look out at the landscape. The magma rivers are impassable. The sharp glass cliffs are unclimbable. There is no clear way forward. But when you hold the ember up, its light catches a glint on the far side of the chasm—a faint reflection, a target.\n\nYou realize you cannot stay here. The rock beneath you is already beginning to melt again, turning soft and treacherous. You have to move. And you have to take this burning seed with you.\n\nIt feels risky to carry fire in your hand. It feels like holding a live wire. But as you close your fingers around it, the trembling in your legs stops. The fear recedes, replaced by a sharp, crystalline focus.\n\nThe fire is not just around you. It is now in your hand.\n\nYou take the first step onto the jagged path, the ember lighting the way with its red glow. You have accepted the offering. The transaction has begun.	A seed of fire is planted today. It might arrive as a sudden bill, an emotional realization, or a moment where you understand exactly what something costs. Don’t turn away from the heat.\n\nThis isn’t about losing something; it’s about investment. The universe is asking for a down payment on the future you say you want. Look at what you are holding onto tightly—fear, resentment, an old story—and consider offering it to the fire.\n\nWhen you give freely, the weight lifts. The payment is your freedom.	I am the seed of gratitude, planting peace with every payment.	Sit comfortably and close your eyes. Visualize your breath as a cycle of heat. As you inhale, imagine drawing in cool, clear possibilities. As you exhale, imagine breathing out smoke—releasing old debts, heavy memories, and stagnant energy.\n\nSee a small, glowing ember in the center of your chest. With every breath, the ember glows brighter, not burning you, but warming you from the inside out. This is your hearth. This is your center.\n\nFeel the warmth spread to your hands and feet. You are the vessel of the sacred fire. You are safe in the heat. When you are ready, open your eyes, keeping that inner warmth alive.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Fire of Exchange", "content": "Toj is the nawal of offering, payment, and the sacred fire. It represents the universal law of reciprocity—the understanding that in order to receive, one must give. Toj is the energy of clearing karmic debts and restoring balance through sacrifice and gratitude. Associated with the element of fire and the color red, it carries a warm, purifying, and sometimes intense energy. It is the archetype of the ritualist who tends the hearth and ensures that the exchange between the human and spiritual worlds is honored. In daily life, Toj manifests as the need to pay bills, help others, or offer thanks. Its shadow aspect involves feeling burdened by debt, martyrdom, or the feeling that one is always giving without return. Toj reminds us that gratitude is the currency of the universe.", "keywords": ["Gratitude", "Offering", "Balance", "Purification", "Reciprocity"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Fire", "content": "Tone 1 represents the initial spark of creation, the singularity from which all potential unfolds. It is the number of unity, beginnings, and the pure, unadulterated impulse to exist. Like a seed lying in the dark earth, Tone 1 contains the blueprint for the entire cycle that follows, holding immense power in a concentrated form. Experientially, this energy feels like a sudden clarity or a surge of new intent—a moment where the past falls away and only the future's possibility remains. It is a day of initiation, where your thoughts and actions plant the vibrations that will ripple through the next thirteen days. In its shadow aspect, Tone 1 can feel isolating or overwhelming, a blinding light with no direction. However, when embraced, it offers the profound gift of focus and the authority to define a new narrative.", "keywords": ["Beginnings", "Unity", "Potential", "Initiation", "Focus"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Make a physical offering (flowers, candle, food) to start the trecena.", "Write a list of things you are grateful for to seed the cycle.", "Pay a bill or a debt immediately to clear the energy.", "Set an intention to be of service to your community.", "Light a fire or a candle and focus on what you are ready to give back."], "title": "Initiating the Cycle of Giving", "content": "When the initiating spark of Tone 1 meets the sacred fire of Toj, we begin a cycle dedicated to balance and reciprocity. 1 Toj is the 'Seed of Offering.' It is the moment we light the fire that will burn for the next thirteen days. This energy asks us to set an intention of gratitude. Before we ask the universe for anything new, we must first say thank you for what is already here. It is a day to acknowledge our debts—spiritual, emotional, and physical—and to make the first move toward clearing them. The feeling is one of humble power; the recognition that we are part of a vast web of exchange. Today, you are the fire-keeper. What fuel will you add to the hearth? The challenge is to give freely without calculating the return immediately. The opportunity is to align yourself with the flow of abundance by becoming an open channel of generosity."}}	{"title": "The Initiator of Sacred Exchange", "content": "To be born on 1 Toj is to be a fire-starter of gratitude and a natural balancer of karma. You possess a spirit that is deeply attuned to the laws of cause and effect. As a Tone 1, you are a leader and an initiator, often the first to step forward to pay the check, offer help, or make the sacrifice that the group needs. Combined with Toj, this makes you a powerful force for clearing debts and restoring equilibrium. You do not wait for others to act; you instinctively know that balance begins with you.\\n\\nYour life path is one of service and offering. You are here to remind the world that nothing is free, but that the price of life is simply gratitude. You may find yourself in roles where you manage resources, facilitate exchanges, or work in healing professions where you help people release their burdens. You have a warm, fiery presence that comforts others, like a hearth in winter. However, because you are the 'first' offering, you may sometimes feel that you give more than anyone else.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 1 Toj soul is to avoid the trap of transactional relationships. You may feel resentful if your generosity is not immediately reciprocated. It is crucial for you to learn that your offering is to the universe, not just to the individual. Your lesson is to give from a place of fullness rather than obligation. When you master the art of unconditional offering, you become a magnet for abundance, proving that the more you give, the more the fire grows."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#376c66", "primary": "#050a09", "secondary": "#203432"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#a87e51", "primary": "#070c17", "secondary": "#2a3d3c"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#e6d2bd", "primary": "#3a2e4f", "secondary": "#a77375"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#984249", "primary": "#1a1119", "secondary": "#462838"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.864579	2026-04-25 13:46:58.018296
34	3	8	8	Kej					{"nawal": {"title": "The Stag of the Wild", "content": "Kej is the nawal of the deer, the four directions, and the natural world. It represents the balance between the wild and the tame, the physical and the spiritual. Kej is the guardian of the forest and the conductor of natural harmony. It governs strength, agility, and the authority of the shaman. Kej energy is noble and sensitive. In its shadow, Kej can be dominating, stubborn, or fearful. Its highest expression is the graceful leadership that respects the laws of nature and protects the sanctity of the earth.", "keywords": ["Deer", "Nature", "Strength", "Balance", "Wilderness"]}, "number": {"title": "The Weaver of Harmony", "content": "Eight is the number of wholeness, justice, and the octave. It represents the completion of a harmonic cycle and the energy of the masculine. Eight is the number of the weaver, bringing together threads to create a pattern. It is considered a lucky and ceremonial number, often used for weddings and day-keeping rituals. Experientially, an Eight day feels balanced, potent, and organized. It is a time of return and reciprocity. The shadow of Eight can be rigidity or a feeling of being caught in a loop. It asks us to weave the threads of our lives with integrity.", "keywords": ["Harmony", "Justice", "Wholeness", "Weaving", "Ceremony"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a ceremony in nature (even just pouring water on the earth).", "Stand barefoot on the grass to ground your electromagnetic field.", "Meditate on the four directions: East, West, North, South.", "Practice 'noble silence' for an hour to listen to the world around you.", "Eat plant-based foods to honor the deer's diet."], "title": "Harmonizing with Nature", "content": "When the harmonic wholeness of Eight meets the natural strength of Kej, we enter a day of 'Ceremonial Nature' or 'Wild Balance.' This is a very powerful day for connecting with the earth and aligning yourself with natural law. The Eight brings a sense of order and ceremony to the wild energy of the deer. It is the perfect day for an outdoor ritual, a hike, or simply sitting under a tree to regain your center. The energy is robust, noble, and stabilizing. It supports leadership that is rooted in service and balance. You may find that conflicts resolve easily today if approached with fairness and a 'wide' perspective. The challenge is to respect the wildness within and without—do not try to over-domesticate yourself or others. Let the deer run free within the sacred container of the Eight. Find the harmony between your civilized self and your animal soul."}}	{"title": "The Guardian of Harmony", "content": "To be born on 8 Kej is to be a pillar of the community and a protector of the sacred balance. You possess a strength that is both gentle and unyielding. The number Eight gives you a love for harmony, ritual, and justice, while Kej connects you to the deep wisdom of the natural world. You are likely a natural leader, perhaps in a spiritual or environmental context. People respect you because you walk your talk; you have an integrity that is felt rather than announced. You are the 'shaman-priest' archetype, capable of mediating between the human world and the wild.\\n\\nYour life path is one of maintaining equilibrium. You are sensitive to dissonance—in music, in relationships, or in the environment—and you have a drive to restore harmony. You may be drawn to healing arts, ecology, or the arts. Your challenge is to not become too rigid in your definition of 'right.' The deer must be free to move. Your lesson is to lead with the heart and to remember that true authority comes from serving the whole circle of life."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#9cc48b", "primary": "#111d1b", "secondary": "#455a44"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.749052	2026-04-25 13:46:57.692457
234	18	13	13	Imox	The golden light of the hero’s dawn begins to soften, shifting into the violet hues of twilight. You walk through the field of sunflowers, their heads bowing gently as you pass.\n\nThe path leads you to the edge of the Obsidian Garden. But there is no cliff, no wall. The black rock simply slopes down and dissolves into a vast, silent ocean.\n\nThe water is dark, but not empty. It is filled with the reflection of a billion stars, swirling in currents of deep teal and indigo bioluminescence. It is the Cosmic Ocean. The primordial soup.\n\nYou step off the solid earth. You do not sink. You float.\n\nThe water is warm, holding you like a memory. As you drift out from the shore, you feel the boundaries of your body beginning to soften. The name you carried, the debt you owed, the hero you became—all of it begins to dissolve into the mist.\n\nYou are no longer the individual drop; you are returning to the sea.\n\nThe sky opens up, and a gentle rain begins to fall. But it is not water; it is starlight. Tiny motes of glowing white light drift down, melting into the ocean, melting into you.\n\nIn this vastness, there is no fear. There is only connection. You feel the dreams of the ancestors, the pulse of the earth, the breath of the galaxy. It is all one thing, and you are part of it.\n\nYou close your eyes and let the current take you. The fire is gone. The blade is gone. The storm is gone. There is only the rhythm of the tide, rocking you into the dream of what comes next.	The cycle is done. Stop trying to hold onto the shore. Let go. Today's energy is the ocean; you are the drop. Surrender isn’t giving up; it’s joining something bigger.\n\nThe veil is thin today. Pay attention to your dreams—waking and sleeping. The universe is speaking in symbols now, not words. You have graduated from the classroom of fire to the library of water. Float, and let the current carry you home.	I surrender to the flow of the universe and trust the wisdom of my dreams.	Lie down and close your eyes. Imagine you are floating on the surface of a deep, dark ocean under a starry sky. The water is warm and supports you completely.\n\nVisualize your thoughts as waves on the surface—moving, chopping, changing. But beneath the waves, your consciousness is the deep, still water. Vast. Silent. Eternal.\n\nSink slowly into that depth. Let the surface noise fade away. You are the ocean. You are the depth. Rest in the silence.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Primordial Dreamer", "content": "Imox is the nawal of the dreamer, the mystic, and the primordial waters. It represents the collective consciousness, imagination, intuition, and the subconscious ocean where creation begins. Imox is the energy of the womb and the deep psychological currents that drive us. Associated with the element of water and the color blue, it carries a fluid, chaotic, and highly creative energy. It is the archetype of the artist who pulls visions from the ether. In daily life, Imox manifests as vivid dreams, emotional sensitivity, and 'crazy' ideas. Its shadow aspect can be emotional overwhelm, disconnection from reality, or getting lost in the delusion of the mind. Imox teaches us to navigate the depths.", "keywords": ["Intuition", "Dreams", "Imagination", "Emotion", "Psychic Flow"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascended Renewal", "content": "Tone 13 is the energy of completion, transcendence, and the spirit realm. It is the final step of the cycle, where the energy transforms into a new octave. It represents the ancestors, the universal movement, and the unseen forces. Experientially, Tone 13 feels light, magical, and sometimes ungrounded. It is a day where the rules of the physical world feel less rigid. It marks the end of the trecena, wrapping up the lessons and preparing the seed for the next cycle. While it offers spiritual connection and a sense of accomplishment, its shadow can be spaciness or a feeling of being 'done' before the work is truly finished. It is the spirit rising from the body.", "keywords": ["Completion", "Ascension", "Transformation", "Ancestors", "Spirit"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Spend time near a natural body of water to honor the end of the cycle.", "Pay attention to your dreams; they contain messages from the spirit world.", "Create art from a place of pure flow and intuition.", "Protect your energy field; you are highly porous today.", "Offer gratitude to the water spirits for the cleansing of the last 13 days."], "title": "The Ascended Dream", "content": "The transcendent energy of Tone 13 culminates in the mystic waters of Imox, creating a day of 'Cosmic Consciousness.' 13 Imox is the return to the Source. The Toj trecena began with a fire offering, and it ends by dissolving into the great ocean of Spirit. This is a day to commune with waters and protect sensitivity. The energy is dreamy, psychic, and boundless. It feels like floating in a warm sea under the stars. 13 Imox connects us to the collective mind and the ancestors. It is a powerful time for deep meditation, channeling, or artistic incubation. The boundaries of reality are fluid today. The challenge is to stay tethered to the earth; it is easy to drift away into fantasy or madness. The opportunity is to dream a new world into being, knowing that the end of one cycle is just the first drop of the next."}}	{"title": "The Master of Collective Dreams", "content": "To be born on 13 Imox is to be a mystic of the highest order and a vessel for the collective unconscious. You possess a soul that is vast, deep, and incredibly sensitive. Tone 13 places you at the threshold of the spirit world, while Imox connects you to the primordial waters of creation. You are a dreamer, a psychic, and an artist who draws inspiration from realms that others cannot access. You feel the emotions of the world as if they were your own. You are here to bring the divine dream into reality.\\n\\nYour life path is one of spiritual transcendence through creativity. You are not bound by the rules of the mundane world; you live in a reality that is fluid and magical. You may be drawn to the arts, psychology, or metaphysics—ways to explore the deep ocean of the mind. You have a powerful connection to the ancestors and to the spirit of water. Your presence can be mesmerizing, as you seem to vibrate at a different frequency than everyone else.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 13 Imox soul is grounding. You are so open and so high-frequency that the physical world can feel harsh and overwhelming. You may struggle with mental stability or addiction, using substances to numb your sensitivity or to escape back to the spirit world. You might also get lost in illusions, unable to distinguish between a vision and a delusion. Your lesson is to build a strong vessel. When you discipline your mind and body, you become a holy grail—capable of holding the infinite waters of spirit and pouring them out to heal the thirst of the world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#3fa490", "primary": "#0c110d", "secondary": "#334436"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#a4a1a8", "primary": "#1f2539", "secondary": "#565a6e"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#acc6cf", "primary": "#1c2548", "secondary": "#44567b"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#607885", "primary": "#141a2d", "secondary": "#384358"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.87473	2026-04-25 13:46:58.025533
235	19	1	1	Tz'i'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Faithful Guide of Law", "content": "Tz'i' is the nawal of law, justice, and the dog. It represents the principle of divine order and the instinctual guidance that keeps us on the path of truth. Tz'i' is the faithful companion who guards the threshold, ensuring that we remain loyal to our highest purpose and to our community. Associated with the element of fire and the concept of authority, it brings a protective and corrective energy. It is the archetype of the judge, the lawyer, and the loyal friend. In daily life, Tz'i' manifests as questions of ethics, fidelity, and the right use of power. Its shadow aspect can be judgmentality, rigidity, or the corruption of authority. Tz'i' teaches us that true justice is not about rules, but about alignment with cosmic love.", "keywords": ["Justice", "Loyalty", "Faith", "Guidance", "Protection"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Fire", "content": "Tone 1 represents the initial spark of creation, the singularity from which all potential unfolds. It is the number of unity, beginnings, and the pure, unadulterated impulse to exist. Like a seed lying in the dark earth, Tone 1 contains the blueprint for the entire cycle that follows, holding immense power in a concentrated form. Experientially, this energy feels like a sudden clarity or a surge of new intent—a moment where the past falls away and only the future's possibility remains. It is a day of initiation, where your thoughts and actions plant the vibrations that will ripple through the next thirteen days. In its shadow aspect, Tone 1 can feel isolating or overwhelming, a blinding light with no direction. However, when embraced, it offers the profound gift of focus and the authority to define a new narrative.", "keywords": ["Beginnings", "Unity", "Potential", "Initiation", "Focus"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Write down your core values or a personal code of ethics.", "Make a vow of loyalty to yourself and your path.", "Stand up for someone who cannot stand up for themselves.", "Meditate on the difference between human law and divine law.", "Release a judgment you have held against yourself."], "title": "Initiating the Law of Love", "content": "When the initiating spark of Tone 1 meets the authoritative law of Tz'i', we begin a new cycle of unconditional love and justice. 1 Tz'i' is the day to set the standard for how you will walk in the world. It is the 'Seed of Integrity.' Today, we are asked to define our moral compass not by what society dictates, but by what our spirit knows to be true. The energy is sharp, clear, and protective. It feels like making a vow or signing a sacred contract with yourself. 1 Tz'i' initiates a thirteen-day journey of aligning our actions with our values. It is a day to drop the 'us vs. them' mentality and plant the seeds of a justice that heals rather than punishes. The challenge is to be discerning without being dogmatic. The opportunity is to claim your spiritual authority and become a faithful guide for your own life."}}	{"title": "The Initiator of Divine Justice", "content": "To be born on 1 Tz'i' is to be a natural leader in the realms of law, ethics, and community protection. You possess a strong internal compass and the will to follow it, regardless of external pressure. Tone 1 gives you a sense of independence and new beginnings, while Tz'i' grants you the instincts of the faithful guide. You are often the 'first' to spot an injustice and the first to speak up about it. You carry a natural authority that makes people listen when you speak on matters of right and wrong.\\n\\nYour life path is one of establishing order and protecting the vulnerable. You are here to initiate new ways of being that are aligned with spiritual truth. You may be drawn to legal professions, advocacy, or spiritual leadership—any role where you can set the standard. You are fiercely loyal to your 'pack,' whether that is your family, your team, or your cause. However, your definition of loyalty is not blind; it is rooted in integrity.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 1 Tz'i' soul is the risk of becoming self-righteous or isolated. Because you trust your own instincts so implicitly (Tone 1), you may struggle to take advice from others or see nuance in complex situations. You might feel that you are the only one who cares about the 'truth.' Your lesson is to lead with compassion. When you use your authority to serve rather than to judge, you become a beacon of divine law, showing others that true justice is an act of love."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b1d2de", "primary": "#181a1b", "secondary": "#455561"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.876622	2026-04-25 13:46:58.047846
246	19	12	12	Imox					{"nawal": {"title": "The Primordial Dreamer", "content": "Imox is the nawal of the dreamer, the mystic, and the primordial waters. It represents the collective consciousness, imagination, intuition, and the subconscious ocean where creation begins. Imox is the energy of the womb and the deep psychological currents that drive us. Associated with the element of water and the color blue, it carries a fluid, chaotic, and highly creative energy. It is the archetype of the artist who pulls visions from the ether. In daily life, Imox manifests as vivid dreams, emotional sensitivity, and 'crazy' ideas. Its shadow aspect can be emotional overwhelm, disconnection from reality, or getting lost in the delusion of the mind. Imox teaches us to navigate the depths.", "keywords": ["Intuition", "Dreams", "Imagination", "Emotion", "Psychic Flow"]}, "number": {"title": "The Understanding of the Whole", "content": "Tone 12 is the energy of understanding, gathering, and the retrospective view. It represents the summation of the cycle's lessons before the final transcendence. It is the number of the 'crystal clear' comprehension that comes after the storm of the 11. Experientially, Tone 12 feels communal, settled, and wise. It is a day to gather the scattered pieces and make sense of them. It fosters cooperation and the ability to summarize complex experiences. While it is generally a positive energy, its shadow can be a refusal to move on or looking backward for too long. It is the librarian who organizes the stories.", "keywords": ["Understanding", "Unity", "Cooperation", "Summary", "Review"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Participate in a group meditation or prayer.", "Reflect on how your personal dreams connect to the collective good.", "Spend time by the ocean or a large body of water.", "Engage in a collaborative art project.", "Practice empathy; try to feel what the world is feeling."], "title": "The Collective Dream", "content": "The synthesizing wisdom of Tone 12 meets the oceanic depth of Imox to create a day of 'Universal Connection.' 12 Imox is the day where we plug into the collective and reflect on the lessons of the trecena. It is a time to understand the shared dream we are all living. The energy is soft, fluid, and psychic. It feels like the merging of all rivers into the sea. 12 Imox supports artistic collaboration, group meditation, and connecting with the global consciousness. It is a day to gather the intuitive insights of the past 12 days and see the pattern they form. The challenge is to maintain your individual identity while feeling the oneness of all things. The opportunity is to feel the profound comfort of belonging to the great ocean of life."}}	{"title": "The Universal Dreamer", "content": "To be born on 12 Imox is to be a vessel for the collective soul. You possess a psychic sensitivity and an artistic genius that is rare. Tone 12 gives you the ability to understand the whole picture, while Imox connects you to the deep, swirling waters of the subconscious. You are the artist who paints the world's pain and beauty, the musician who plays the song of the universe. You feel everything—the joy, the sorrow, the madness of humanity. You are here to help us understand our shared emotional reality.\\n\\nYour life path is one of translating the invisible into the visible. You are a natural medium, often picking up on thoughts and feelings that are not your own. You have a gift for bringing people together through shared emotion or vision. You may be drawn to the arts, psychology, or spiritual leadership—roles where you can guide others through the depths. You are a compassionate soul, always seeking to merge and connect.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 12 Imox soul is boundaries. You can easily lose yourself in the collective, becoming overwhelmed by the noise of the world. You might struggle with mental health, as your reality is so fluid. There is a risk of escapism, preferring the dream world to the hard edges of physical life. Your lesson is to build a strong container for your gifts. When you learn to filter the input and ground your energy, you become a visionary leader who can help the world dream a new and better dream."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#8dcdb4", "primary": "#0f1d1c", "secondary": "#2f5b54"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.879321	2026-04-25 13:46:58.052542
102	8	11	11	E'	You leave the spire and the weather turns. The clear blue sky darkens to a bruised purple. The wind picks up, howling and erratic. You are on the Storm Road.\n\nThe path of stones you were walking on begins to shift. Some stones drop away into the void. Others pop up where there was nothing.\n\n11 is the number of dissonance and change. E’ is the Path. Today, the path is not straight. It is a zigzag. It is a test of your adaptability.\n\nYou cannot walk this road with a rigid plan. If you try to march in a straight line, you will fall. You have to dance with the chaos.\n\nYou step on a stone, and it moves. You adjust your balance. You jump to the next one. It feels like a game of hopscotch played at the edge of the world.\n\nYou realize that the "path" isn’t the stones; the path is your ability to move. The stones are just temporary supports. You are the path.\n\nThe wind tries to blow you off, but you are aerodynamic now. You learned from the Stag to flow, from the Serpent to ground, from the Monkey to play. You use all these skills now.\n\nYou laugh into the storm. It’s exhilarating. You are surfing the chaos.\n\nYou reach the other side, breathless and alive. You didn’t just survive the storm; you rode it.	Expect the unexpected today. The road is taking a sharp turn. If you try to grip the steering wheel too tight, you’ll crash. Loosen up. The energy of 11 E’ is wild and adventurous.\n\nMaybe you get lost. Maybe your meeting gets cancelled. Maybe you have a sudden desire to drive to the beach. Follow that impulse. The universe is trying to show you something that isn’t on your itinerary.	I embrace the twists and turns of my path, trusting that every detour leads me home.	Visualize a river. It flows over rocks, around bends, down waterfalls. It never stops, and it never worries about where it’s going.\n\nImagine you are the water. Feel the freedom of flowing around obstacles. You are unstoppable.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Sacred Pathfinder", "content": "E' is the Nawal of the path, the road, and the journey. It represents the energy of movement, exploration, and the exchange of wisdom that comes from travel. E' governs the physical roads we walk as well as the spiritual destiny we are carving out. In human experience, it manifests as curiosity, restlessness, and a desire to see what lies beyond the horizon. It is the archetype of the Guide. When aligned, E' brings clarity of direction; when misaligned, it can lead to aimless wandering.", "keywords": ["Path", "Journey", "Exploration", "Destiny", "Guidance"]}, "number": {"title": "The Force of Change", "content": "The number Eleven represents dissonance, resolution through change, and the stripping away of the non-essential. In Mayan cosmology, Eleven is a high-frequency energy that shakes the foundation to test its strength. It is not necessarily negative, but it is turbulent. Experientially, this energy feels like a strong wind or a sudden shift in plans. It breaks the static perfection of Ten to allow for higher growth. The shadow of Eleven can be chaos, but its light is liberation and the clearing of the path. Today, the universe unbinds the knots.", "keywords": ["Change", "Liberation", "Dissonance", "Clearing", "Transformation"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Be flexible with travel plans; delays are opportunities.", "Explore a new route or a new idea; leave the beaten path.", "If you feel stuck, move your body; physical movement shifts the energy.", "Let go of a goal that no longer resonates with your soul.", "Trust your internal compass when the external map fails."], "title": "The Divergent Path", "content": "The changing energy of Tone 11 meets the traveling spirit of E' to create a day of 'Unexpected Detours.' 11 E' is the fork in the road. It represents a sudden shift in direction or a realization that the path you are on is no longer the right one. This energy can feel unsettling, as E' likes a clear map and 11 likes to tear maps up. However, this disruption is divine. It is liberating you from a destiny that was too small for you. Today, expect travel plans to change, or for a new opportunity to appear out of nowhere. Be willing to get lost; that is where the discovery lies. The energy asks you to be a flexible traveler. Pack light and be ready to move. The road is reshaping itself under your feet, guiding you toward a higher destination. Trust the detour."}}	{"title": "The Radical Explorer", "content": "To be born on 11 E' is to be a traveler of the unknown. You are the 'Path Breaker'—a soul who is not content with the paved roads of society. You have a restless, adventurous spirit that drives you to constantly seek new experiences and new truths. You are likely an innovator, a nomad, or a pioneer in your field. The number 11 gives you a non-conformist edge; you don't just walk the path, you change it.\\n\\nYour life path is one of discovery through disruption. You may have a life filled with sudden changes of direction, but each twist leads you closer to your true destiny. Your challenge is to find stability within the movement, to carry your home in your heart so that you don't feel lost in the chaos. You are here to blaze trails for others to follow, showing us that the most beautiful destinations are often found off the map."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#ccd0c7", "primary": "#101717", "secondary": "#424847"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#9acc99", "primary": "#1c321d", "secondary": "#538550"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#fefefe", "primary": "#a1b2b9", "secondary": "#d7e8f4"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#969cc3", "primary": "#363246", "secondary": "#676481"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.799688	2026-04-25 13:46:57.793341
237	19	3	3	E'					{"nawal": {"title": "The Pathfinder of Destiny", "content": "E' is the nawal of the path, the road, and the journey. It represents the destiny that unfolds as we walk, the physical roads we travel, and the spiritual path of life. E' is the explorer, the guide, and the energy of movement toward a destination. Associated with the element of air (and sometimes earth) and the color white, it carries a forward-moving, adventurous energy. It is the archetype of the traveler who gains wisdom through experience. In daily life, E' manifests as travel, starting a new venture, or seeking a better way. Its shadow aspect can be aimlessness, restlessness, or the refusal to commit to a direction. E' teaches us that the destination is less important than the wisdom gathered along the way.", "keywords": ["Journey", "Path", "Exploration", "Guidance", "Destiny"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Movement", "content": "Tone 3 is the energy of movement, vibration, and communication. It breaks the static balance of the number 2, introducing flow and dynamism. If 1 is the point and 2 is the line, 3 is the triangle—the first geometric form that implies stability yet encourages motion. It represents the integration of the right brain, left brain, and the central nervous system, or the union of mind, body, and spirit. Experientially, Tone 3 feels busy, expressive, and sometimes restless. It is a day of 'doing,' where ideas seek to be spoken and energies seek to be circulated. While it fosters creativity and connection, its shadow can manifest as scattered energy, anxiety, or a lack of focus. It is the pulse that keeps the universe from standing still.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Expression", "Energy", "Instability", "Flow"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Go for a long walk without a destination (wandering).", "Practice walking meditation or mindful movement.", "Journal about your life path and where you feel called to go.", "Explore a new neighborhood or route to break your routine.", "Communicate your long-term goals to a friend or guide."], "title": "The Active Journey Inward", "content": "When the rhythmic movement of Tone 3 meets the path-finding energy of E', we experience a day of 'Dynamic Exploration.' 3 E' is the energy of the inward path and meditation in motion. While E' usually rules physical travel, the influence of the 3 (mind/body/spirit connection) turns the journey into a spiritual quest. Today is an excellent day to move your body to quiet your mind. Walking meditation, pilgrimage, or a road trip with a spiritual purpose are highly supported. The energy is restless but purposeful. It asks us to communicate with the road itself—to listen to the signs and signals of the environment. 3 E' breaks up stagnation; if you have been stuck, this energy gets you moving again. The challenge is to not run away from yourself. The opportunity is to discover that the path is not something you find, but something you make by walking."}}	{"title": "The Communicator of the Path", "content": "To be born on 3 E' is to be a restless seeker and a gifted communicator of the journey. You possess a spirit that cannot be contained; you need to move, explore, and share what you find. Tone 3 gives you a rhythmic, expressive nature, while E' calls you to the road. You are the travel writer, the tour guide, the inspirational speaker who uses the metaphor of the journey to teach others. You learn by doing and by going. You likely have a talent for languages or for bridging cultural gaps.\\n\\nYour life path is one of movement and expression. You are not meant to stay in one place for too long, either physically or mentally. You are a collector of experiences. Your nervous system is highly tuned (Tone 3), making you sensitive to the energy of places and people. You are a natural guide because you are always a few steps ahead, scouting the terrain. You inspire others to take the first step, to leave their comfort zones, and to trust the road.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 3 E' soul is anxiety and lack of focus. You may feel like you are always running but never arriving. The grass may always look greener on the other side. You might struggle to commit to a home, a job, or a partner because you fear missing out on what's around the bend. Your lesson is to find the stillness within the movement. When you realize that the ultimate destination is your own center, your wandering transforms into a sacred pilgrimage, and your words become maps for the soul."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#b4dadd", "primary": "#141615", "secondary": "#29586d"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.877341	2026-04-25 13:46:58.055289
117	9	13	13	Kame					{"nawal": {"title": "The Transformer", "content": "Kame is the Nawal of death, rebirth, and the ancestors. It represents the only certainty in life: change. Kame is the energy that closes one door so another can open. It governs spiritual initiation, mediumship, and the courage to face the unknown. In human experience, Kame manifests as a connection to the spirit world, a talent for helping others through transitions, and deep inner strength. It is the peaceful rest after the struggle. When aligned, Kame brings profound transformation and ancestral protection; when misaligned, it can lead to fear of change.", "keywords": ["Death", "Rebirth", "Ancestors", "Transformation", "Courage"]}, "number": {"title": "The Ascension", "content": "The number Thirteen represents the completion of the cycle, the ascension to the next level, and the spirit world. In Mayan cosmology, Thirteen is the number of the ancestors and the highest vibration of time. It is the moment where the wave crashes onto the shore and recedes to become part of the ocean again. Experientially, this energy feels magical, heightened, and sometimes ungrounded. It is a day of 'déjà vu' and profound intuition. The shadow of Thirteen can be a disconnection from reality, but its light is the ultimate transformation.", "keywords": ["Completion", "Ascension", "Ancestors", "Transformation", "Spirit"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create a memorial altar for your ancestors.", "Meditate on the cycles of life and death; find peace in the impermanence.", "Release a past version of yourself with love and gratitude.", "Ask the spirit world for guidance on your next step.", "Celebrate the mystery of existence; you are part of an eternal chain."], "title": "Ascended Transformation", "content": "The Ix trecena concludes with the profound energy of 13 Kame. Here, the ascension power of Tone 13 meets the transformer Kame. This is a day of 'Spiritual Rebirth.' We have walked the path of Earth Magic (Ix) and now we stand at the gateway to the ancestors. 13 Kame represents the ultimate metamorphosis—the shedding of the physical to become pure spirit, or the shedding of an old identity to become who you truly are. The energy is thin, ghostly, and incredibly sacred. It is the best day in the calendar to communicate with those who have passed on and to ask for their blessing as you close this cycle. The death of the old is complete. You are ready to rise. There is no fear here, only the quiet peace of knowing that life is eternal. Honor the endings today, for they are the soil of your new beginning."}}	{"title": "The Cosmic Transformer", "content": "To be born on 13 Kame is to be a bridge between the worlds of the living and the dead. You are the 'Ascended Mystic'—a soul who carries the wisdom of the ancestors in your very bones. You have a foot in both realities, giving you a fearlessness regarding change and mortality that others find awe-inspiring. You are likely a powerful medium, healer, or spiritual guide, helping others navigate the deepest transitions of their lives.\\n\\nYour life path is one of spiritual evolution. You are here to master the art of letting go. The number 13 vibrates at the highest frequency, meaning you often experience life more intensely and psychically than others. Your challenge is to stay grounded in the physical world while honoring your connection to the spirit. You are here to remind us that death is not an end, but a beautiful ascension into a new form of light."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d5d3bc", "primary": "#0f1919", "secondary": "#404b46"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.804843	2026-04-25 13:46:57.853737
243	19	9	9	Tijax					{"nawal": {"title": "The Obsidian Blade of Truth", "content": "Tijax is the nawal of the obsidian blade, the mirror, and the healer. It represents the double-edged sword of truth that cuts away illness and illusion. Tijax is the warrior for the light, the surgeon, and the spark of divinity. Associated with the element of fire and the mineral obsidian, it carries a sharp, decisive, and purifying energy. It is the archetype of the spiritual warrior who is willing to suffer to uncover the truth. In daily life, Tijax manifests as discernment, ending relationships or habits, and sudden healing crises. Its shadow aspect can be cruelty, gossip, or a tongue that cuts too deep. Tijax teaches us that sometimes we must wound in order to heal.", "keywords": ["Healing", "Truth", "Cutting", "Discernment", "Purification"]}, "number": {"title": "The Patience of Gestation", "content": "Tone 9 is the energy of patience, cycles, and the feminine. It represents the nine months of human gestation and the nine levels of the Mayan underworld (Xibalba). It is a number of deep, slow-moving power. Unlike the flash of the 1 or the action of the 5, Tone 9 is the energy of the seed swelling underground just before it breaks the surface. Experientially, it feels heavy, emotional, and sometimes secretive. It is a day for working behind the scenes, nurturing projects, and trusting the dark. While it fosters deep creativity and empathy, its shadow can be depression, lethargy, or getting stuck in the past. It is the womb that holds the future.", "keywords": ["Patience", "Gestation", "Feminine", "Completion", "Depth"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Schedule a deep tissue massage or acupuncture session.", "Journal about a deep-seated fear or pattern you are ready to release.", "Allow yourself to rest and recover after an emotional release.", "Visualize obsidian absorbing any negative energy from your body.", "Be gentle with yourself; deep healing takes time."], "title": "Gestating the Cure", "content": "When the deep feminine energy of Tone 9 meets the sharp masculinity of Tijax, we experience a day of 'Deep Healing.' 9 Tijax is the energy of feminine healing and obsidian release. It represents the long, slow process of recovering from a wound. Today is not about the quick cut; it is about the deep surgery that removes the root of the problem. The energy feels intense, private, and transformative. 9 Tijax asks us to look at the patterns we have been carrying for a long time—perhaps nine years or nine generations—and finally excise them. It is a day for therapy, shadow work, and facing the truth that has been hidden in the dark. The challenge is the pain that may surface; healing is not always comfortable. The opportunity is to clear the infection so that true rebirth can occur. Trust that the blade is in the hands of the Great Mother."}}	{"title": "The Healer of Deep Wounds", "content": "To be born on 9 Tijax is to be a soul surgeon, capable of reaching the deepest roots of pain and suffering. You possess a profound capacity for healing, both for yourself and others. Tone 9 gives you patience, empathy, and a connection to the feminine mysteries, while Tijax grants you the discernment and the tools to cut away illness. You are not interested in band-aid solutions; you want to cure the disease. You are likely drawn to depth psychology, surgery, shamanic healing, or investigative work—anything that requires digging deep to find the truth.\\n\\nYour life path is one of purification. You often undergo intense personal transformations, shedding skins and healing old wounds. This makes you an incredibly empathetic guide for others who are suffering. You have a 'laser' vision that can see right to the heart of a problem. You are a warrior for the light, but your battleground is often the internal world of the psyche. You protect the vulnerable by cutting away the lies that bind them.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 9 Tijax soul is the intensity of your own process. You may carry a heavy load of suffering, feeling that you must heal the whole world. You can be prone to depression or self-harm if you turn your blade inward without compassion. There is a risk of becoming addicted to the 'drama' of healing, always looking for something wrong to fix. Your lesson is to learn when to put the knife down. When you balance your capacity for surgery with the capacity for rest and joy, you become a true healer who restores wholeness."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#c7a18b", "primary": "#171917", "secondary": "#58403a"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.878761	2026-04-25 13:46:58.062489
256	20	9	9	Aq'ab'al	You are near the top, but the sun sets. The world plunges into darkness. You are camping on the Last Ledge before the summit.\n\nThis is the Womb of the Morning.\n\n9 is Gestation. Aq’ab’al is the Dawn. You are in the dark, but it is the pregnant dark. The dark before the light.\n\nYou sit wrapped in your cloak, watching the stars. They seem incredibly close. You can feel the new day forming underneath the horizon. It is not just another day; it is the culmination of your vision.\n\nYou realize that vision requires patience. You cannot force the sun to rise. You have to wait for it. You have to trust the cycle.\n\nYou think about the seeds you planted on Day 5, the flow you found on Day 6, the wind you rode on Day 8. All of it is cooking in the pot of the night.\n\nShadows move around you—the doubts of "Am I ready?" and "Is it real?" You greet them. They are just the guardians of the threshold. You are not afraid of the dark anymore because you know what is coming.\n\nA faint line of purple appears in the east. The gestation is almost over.\n\nYou stand up. You turn your face toward the light that isn’t there yet, but you know is coming. This is faith.\n\nYou are ready to be born.	It’s always darkest before the dawn, but the dawn is definitely coming. The energy of 9 Aq’ab’al is pregnant with possibility. You might feel a sense of anticipation, a quiet knowing that something big is about to shift.\n\nDon’t rush it. Let it cook. Use this time to prepare yourself, to rest, and to get your house in order. The light is on its way, and when it breaks, it’s going to be beautiful.	I trust the timing of my life and wait with joy for the new dawn.	Visualize a seed underground. It is dark, warm, and safe. It feels the heat of the sun above the soil.\n\nFeel the energy gathering inside the seed. The pressure to grow. The excitement. \n\nNow visualize the sprout breaking the surface. The first breath of air. The first ray of light.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Dawn of Possibility", "content": "Aq'ab'al is the nawal of the dawn, the twilight, and the new day. It represents the bridge between night and day, dream and reality. Symbolizes new beginnings, awakening, and creative potential being born. Associated with the colors red and black (dawn/dusk), it carries a hopeful, transitional, and clarifying energy. It is the archetype of the early riser who witnesses the first light. In daily life, Aq'ab'al manifests as sudden realizations, the start of new relationships, and the shifting of polarity. Its shadow aspect can be fear of the unknown, hesitation, or getting stuck in the 'grey area' between choices. Aq'ab'al teaches us that every ending is a new beginning.", "keywords": ["Beginnings", "Potential", "Revelation", "Transition", "Dawn"]}, "number": {"title": "The Patience of Gestation", "content": "Tone 9 is the energy of patience, cycles, and the feminine. It represents the nine months of human gestation and the nine levels of the Mayan underworld (Xibalba). It is a number of deep, slow-moving power. Unlike the flash of the 1 or the action of the 5, Tone 9 is the energy of the seed swelling underground just before it breaks the surface. Experientially, it feels heavy, emotional, and sometimes secretive. It is a day for working behind the scenes, nurturing projects, and trusting the dark. While it fosters deep creativity and empathy, its shadow can be depression, lethargy, or getting stuck in the past. It is the womb that holds the future.", "keywords": ["Patience", "Gestation", "Feminine", "Completion", "Depth"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Wake up before sunrise and sit in the dark.", "Journal about the 'new you' that is waiting to be born.", "Honor the feminine aspects of yourself and your life.", "Practice patience with a project that is not yet ready.", "Meditate on the balance of light and dark within you."], "title": "Gestating the New Dawn", "content": "When the deep patience of Tone 9 meets the dawning light of Aq'ab'al, we experience a day of 'Feminine Mystery.' 9 Aq'ab'al is the darkness just before the dawn. It is the energy of the womb preparing to birth the light. Today is a time of quiet anticipation. The new idea or the new self is fully formed but has not yet emerged. The energy supports deep feminine work, shadow work, and the honoring of transitions. It feels like the hush of the early morning. 9 Aq'ab'al asks us to trust the dark, knowing that it is the mother of the light. It is a day to look at our polarities—our hope and our fear—and hold them both with compassion. The challenge is the wait; the 9 moves slowly. The opportunity is to prepare yourself so that when the sun rises, you are ready to greet it fully."}}	{"title": "The Keeper of the Twilight", "content": "To be born on 9 Aq'ab'al is to be a guardian of the thresholds. You possess a soul that is comfortable in the deep, quiet spaces of transformation. Tone 9 gives you patience, depth, and a connection to the feminine mysteries, while Aq'ab'al grants you the hope of the dawn and the insight of the dusk. You are the one who helps others navigate the dark times, assuring them that the light will return. You are likely a natural counselor, artist, or midwife—someone who facilitates birth and change.\\n\\nYour life path is one of bringing the hidden into the light. You nurture potential until it is ready to be seen. You have a profound understanding of cycles and timing; you never rush the sunrise. You are comfortable with ambiguity, able to see the validity in opposing viewpoints. You are a bridge between the subconscious and the conscious mind, often bringing deep truths to the surface.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 9 Aq'ab'al soul is the risk of getting stuck in the transition. You may linger in the twilight, afraid to fully step into the bright light of day or the deep dark of night. You might struggle with depression or secrecy, hiding your true self from the world. Your lesson is to trust the cycle of birth. When you have the courage to release what you have been nurturing, you become a bringer of new days, illuminating the world with your unique light."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#cb9e69", "primary": "#17191a", "secondary": "#503f3e"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#da7f3b", "primary": "#0b0d0a", "secondary": "#653123"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#cfaa59", "primary": "#1a243f", "secondary": "#5e5853"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#7b668a", "primary": "#0e0d13", "secondary": "#352c3f"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.885713	2026-04-25 13:46:58.090488
224	18	3	3	B'atz'	The path beyond the guardians is not smooth. It is a field of fractured slate, loose and shifting under your feet. Every step sends a cascade of small stones rattling down into the dark crevices below.\n\nThis world is restless. The ground shudders intermittently, not with the violence of the eruption, but with a twitching, nervous energy. You feel it in your teeth. You feel it in the way your thoughts refuse to sit still, jumping from worry to memory to hope and back again.\n\nThen, you see it.\n\nA crack in the black rock widens, and from it pulses a vein of light. But this isn’t the angry red of magma. It is gold. Solid, vibrant, living gold, running through the charcoal earth like a exposed nerve.\n\nIt hums.\n\nYou crouch down to inspect it. The vein isn’t liquid; it’s a thread. A physical line of conductive energy that winds its way through the chaos of the landscape. It pulses with a rhythm—*thump-thump, thump-thump*—steady and persistent.\n\nYou realize the Obsidian Garden isn’t just a pile of burning rocks. It has a nervous system. It has a weave.\n\nThe golden thread dives under a massive boulder and re-emerges further down, winding into the shadowy unknown. It looks fragile, but when you touch the rock near it, you feel a vibration of immense power.\n\nYour instinct tells you to find high ground, to get away from this unstable, twitching earth. But the thread pulls at your curiosity. It feels connected to the ember in your hand, as if they are singing the same note.\n\nTo follow the thread is to walk into the dark. It is to trust a pattern you cannot see the end of.\n\nYou stand up. The restless energy in your legs urges you to move. Instead of fighting the tremors, you let your body sway with them. You surrender to the rhythm.\n\nYou step onto the line of the golden vein. The humming travels up through your boots, vibrating in your spine. It feels like music. It feels like a beginning.\n\nYou start to walk, not away from the chaos, but deeper into it, following the single golden strand that holds the story together.	Life is trying to weave a new pattern for you, but you keep tugging at the thread. Stop trying to control the design.\n\nThe energy today brings movement—it might feel like restlessness or anxiety, but it’s actually just creativity looking for a place to go. Don’t bottle it up. Speak, write, dance, or run. The knots in your mind will untangle the moment you let your body take the lead.\n\nYou are the artist, but today you are also the canvas. Let the paint fly.	I am the weaver of my own story, choosing threads of joy.	Stand up. Shake your hands out. Shake your legs. Let your jaw loosen. Visualize the stagnant energy of worry as grey dust clinging to your skin.\n\nWith every shake, imagine the dust falling away, revealing a body made of golden light. Feel the rhythm of your heart. It is the drum of your own life.\n\nNow, imagine a spool of blue light in your solar plexus. As you breathe, visualize pulling a thread from this spool and weaving a protective cocoon around yourself. You are safe in your own creation.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Weaver of Time", "content": "B'atz' is the nawal of the thread, the monkey, and the weaver. It represents the creative life force that spins the fabric of time and reality. B'atz' is the artist, the trickster, and the initiator of new cycles. Associated with the element of fire and the arts, it carries a playful, clever, and masterful energy. It is the archetype of the artisan who weaves scattered threads into a beautiful tapestry. In daily life, B'atz' manifests as artistic expression, marriage, scheduling, and the unfolding of destiny. Its shadow aspect can be arrogance, manipulation, or becoming tangled in one's own complexities. B'atz' reminds us that we are the weavers of our own lives.", "keywords": ["Creativity", "Weaving", "Time", "Artistry", "Initiation"]}, "number": {"title": "The Rhythm of Movement", "content": "Tone 3 is the energy of movement, vibration, and communication. It breaks the static balance of the number 2, introducing flow and dynamism. If 1 is the point and 2 is the line, 3 is the triangle—the first geometric form that implies stability yet encourages motion. It represents the integration of the right brain, left brain, and the central nervous system, or the union of mind, body, and spirit. Experientially, Tone 3 feels busy, expressive, and sometimes restless. It is a day of 'doing,' where ideas seek to be spoken and energies seek to be circulated. While it fosters creativity and connection, its shadow can manifest as scattered energy, anxiety, or a lack of focus. It is the pulse that keeps the universe from standing still.", "keywords": ["Movement", "Expression", "Energy", "Instability", "Flow"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Engage in a creative hobby or art form without worrying about the result.", "Listen to music that moves you and allow your body to respond.", "Weave a new connection between two friends or colleagues.", "Decorate your home space to reflect your inner beauty.", "Approach a problem with a playful, 'trickster' mindset to find a solution."], "title": "The Dance of Creation", "content": "When the rhythmic movement of Tone 3 meets the creative weaving of B'atz', we enter a day of 'Artistic Flow.' 3 B'atz' is the inner artist waking up to play. The energy is vibrant, expressive, and fun. It is not a day for rigid plans, but for improvisation. The Monkey (B'atz') loves to move, and the 3 provides the beat. This is an ideal day to start a creative project, engage in the arts, or simply approach your daily tasks with a sense of style and flair. It feels like a dance where the steps are being invented in the moment. The combination supports weaving together different aspects of your life—work, play, spirit—into a cohesive whole. The challenge is the potential for distraction; the Monkey can get easily bored and jump from branch to branch. The opportunity is to find the joy in the process of creation itself."}}	{"title": "The Dynamic Artist of Life", "content": "To be born on 3 B'atz' is to be a perpetual motion machine of creativity and charm. You possess a quick wit, a restless spirit, and an innate talent for the arts. Tone 3 gives you a need for expression and movement, while B'atz' gifts you with the dexterity of the master weaver. You are the entertainer, the storyteller, the one who brings color and rhythm to a grey world. You likely have manual dexterity—whether in painting, playing an instrument, or simply fixing things—and a mind that weaves complex patterns instantly.\\n\\nYour life path is one of creative initiation. You are here to remind people that life is a game to be played, a song to be sung. You may be drawn to the performing arts, design, or any field that requires quick thinking and innovation. You are a natural connector, weaving people together into social tapestries. However, your energy can be frantic. You are like the hummingbird or the monkey, always moving to the next flower or branch, driven by an insatiable curiosity.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 3 B'atz' soul is depth and follow-through. You may start a hundred projects and finish three. You might struggle with silence or stillness, using constant activity to avoid deeper feelings. There is also a risk of using your cleverness to manipulate rather than to create. Your lesson is to find the stillness within the dance. When you learn to focus your immense creative energy on a singular purpose, you can weave a masterpiece that stands the test of time, rather than just a fleeting moment of entertainment."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#d5b39a", "primary": "#12100e", "secondary": "#614331"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#90779c", "primary": "#18132b", "secondary": "#4f3d67"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#e7cbad", "primary": "#c3b1bf", "secondary": "#c2cdb9"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#a08548", "primary": "#17191c", "secondary": "#373e47"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.866189	2026-04-25 13:46:58.030572
251	20	4	4	Tijax	You reach the plateau. It is a flat expanse of white stone, open to the winds. In the center stands a monolith of black obsidian, sharp as a razor, reflecting the sun.\n\nThis is the Cutting Floor.\n\n4 is Stability. Tijax is the Obsidian Blade, the Healer, the Truth. To go higher, you must be lighter. You cannot carry the ropes that tether you to the ground.\n\nYou look down at your body. You see them now—thick, heavy ropes tied around your waist, your ankles, your wrists. They stretch down into the clouds, anchoring you to old fears, limiting beliefs, and people who want you to stay small.\n\nYou walk to the obsidian monolith. You run your hand along its edge. It is terrifyingly sharp, but it hums with a clean, surgical vibration.\n\nYou understand what you must do. You are not here to hack or slash. You are here to sever with precision.\n\nYou take a rope labeled "I am not enough." You pull it taut against the obsidian edge. *Snick.* It parts instantly. You feel a sudden rush of buoyancy.\n\nYou take a rope labeled "Scarcity." *Snick.* Gone.\n\nYou take a rope labeled "The Need to Please." This one is thick and braided. You have to saw at it a little. But then—*snap*—it gives way.\n\nWith every cut, you become more unstable in the earthly sense, but more stable in the aerial sense. You are balancing on the wind now.\n\nYou stand in the center of the plateau, surrounded by the severed ends of the ropes. You are untethered. It is scary. It is exhilarating. You are free to fly.\n\nYou realize that healing is not always about adding something; sometimes it is about cutting something away.	The truth is sharp today, but it heals. The energy of 4 Tijax is like a surgeon’s scalpel—precise, necessary, and ultimately life-saving. You might feel the urge to cut something out of your life: a toxic relationship, a self-defeating thought, a clutter pile.\n\nDo it. Don’t hesitate. The incision might sting for a moment, but the relief will be instant. You are carving out the shape of your new life. Cut away anything that isn’t you.	I release what no longer serves me, cutting the cords to claim my freedom.	Visualize yourself holding a sword of blue light. It is weightless. Scan your body for dark cords attaching you to old drains.\n\nSwing the sword. Watch the cords sever and dissolve into light. Feel the rush of energy returning to you. You are whole. You are protected.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Obsidian Blade of Truth", "content": "Tijax is the nawal of the obsidian blade, the mirror, and the healer. It represents the double-edged sword of truth that cuts away illness and illusion. Tijax is the warrior for the light, the surgeon, and the spark of divinity. Associated with the element of fire and the mineral obsidian, it carries a sharp, decisive, and purifying energy. It is the archetype of the spiritual warrior who is willing to suffer to uncover the truth. In daily life, Tijax manifests as discernment, ending relationships or habits, and sudden healing crises. Its shadow aspect can be cruelty, gossip, or a tongue that cuts too deep. Tijax teaches us that sometimes we must wound in order to heal.", "keywords": ["Healing", "Truth", "Cutting", "Discernment", "Purification"]}, "number": {"title": "The Foundation of Form", "content": "Tone 4 is the energy of stability, structure, and definition. After the movement of 3, the 4 establishes a base, like the four walls of a house or the four legs of a table. It represents the four directions (East, West, North, South) and the four elements (Earth, Air, Fire, Water), grounding spiritual energy into physical reality. Experientially, Tone 4 feels calm, ordered, and reliable. It is a day for planning, organizing, and establishing boundaries. It brings the vague potential of the earlier numbers into concrete form. While it offers safety and predictability, its shadow can be rigidity, stagnation, or being 'boxed in.' It is the number of the builder who lays the cornerstone.", "keywords": ["Structure", "Balance", "Grounding", "Manifestation", "Stability"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Set a firm boundary with a person or situation that drains you.", "Declutter your physical space, cutting away the excess.", "Create a health plan or schedule a medical check-up.", "Use discernment to make a practical decision.", "Meditate on the four directions to ground your energy before acting."], "title": "The Structure of Healing", "content": "When the stabilizing force of Tone 4 meets the cutting truth of Tijax, we experience a day of 'Grounded Healing.' 4 Tijax is the energy of the Operating Room—a sterile, structured environment where precise work can be done. It is not a day for chaotic emotional releases, but for planned, methodical clearing. The energy supports establishing boundaries that protect your well-being. It is a day to define what is true for you and to cut away anything that threatens your stability. 4 Tijax asks us to build a foundation of truth. It feels like the relief of setting a bone or cleaning a wound. The combination suggests that healing requires structure—a plan, a schedule, a safe space. The challenge is to not become rigid in your discernment, cutting people out too quickly. The opportunity is to create a life that is structurally sound because it is free of lies."}}	{"title": "The Builder of Truth", "content": "To be born on 4 Tijax is to be a person of immense integrity and practical discernment. You possess a soul that craves order and truth. Tone 4 gives you a love for structure and stability, while Tijax grants you the sharp eye of the surgeon. You are the one who builds systems that work because you have cut away the inefficiencies. You are a natural protector, establishing safe boundaries for yourself and your loved ones. You are likely drawn to medicine, architecture, law, or editing—roles where precision and structure are key.\\n\\nYour life path is one of refining reality. You are here to separate the wheat from the chaff. You build your life on a foundation of honesty, and you expect the same from others. You have a 'bullshit detector' that is always on. People trust you because you are consistent and clear. You are a healer, but your method is practical—you fix the problem at the root.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 4 Tijax soul is rigidity. You can be so focused on the 'right' way to do things that you become critical or controlling. You may struggle to forgive mistakes, seeing them as structural failures. There is a risk of becoming defensive, using your blade to keep people at a distance. Your lesson is to learn that truth can be soft. When you allow your structures to have a little give, your healing power becomes a sanctuary where others feel safe to be imperfect."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#ba9891", "primary": "#131614", "secondary": "#4b3b37"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#d5d5d4", "primary": "#323232", "secondary": "#979796"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#cbe4f8", "primary": "#8eaacd", "secondary": "#b2cae9"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#d0d4d3", "primary": "#123245", "secondary": "#507286"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.882368	2026-04-25 13:46:58.081075
239	19	5	5	Ix					{"nawal": {"title": "The Jaguar of Earth Magic", "content": "Ix is the nawal of the jaguar, the shaman, and the magic of the earth. It represents the feminine mysteries, high magic, and the connection to nature spirits. Ix is the energy of the night seer who walks without fear in the darkness. Associated with the element of earth and the spirit, it carries a stealthy, potent, and highly intuitive energy. It is the archetype of the healer who uses nature's tools to transform reality. In daily life, Ix manifests as intuition, synchronicity, and a deep pull toward the mysteries of life. Its shadow aspect can be the misuse of power, black magic, or becoming reclusive and disconnected from the human world. Ix teaches us that the earth is alive.", "keywords": ["Magic", "Intuition", "Nature", "Jaguar", "Mystery"]}, "number": {"title": "The Hand of Power", "content": "Tone 5 is the energy of empowerment, work, and the center. In Mayan numerology, it represents the hand (five fingers) and the ability to grasp, shape, and work with materials. It breaks the stability of the 4 to add a new dimension of agency and action. Tone 5 is the central pivot point of the single-digit numbers (1-9), representing the core or the heart of the matter. Experientially, it feels energetic, capable, and sometimes demanding. It is a day to gather resources and apply effort. While it empowers us to get things done, its shadow can manifest as over-exertion, grasping for control, or losing sight of the spiritual in favor of the material work. It is the number of the worker who makes the vision real.", "keywords": ["Action", "Discipline", "Work", "Empowerment", "Center"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Perform a ritual or spell with clear, tangible intentions.", "Work in the garden or clean up a natural area.", "Gather herbs or natural materials for healing.", "Trust your hands to know what to do (massage, craft, cooking).", "Channel your energy into a project that protects the Earth."], "title": "Empowered Earth Magic", "content": "When the working hand of Tone 5 meets the magical power of Ix, we enter a day of 'Practical Sorcery.' 5 Ix is the energy of Jaguar magic and work for the Earth. It is not a day for passive wishing; it is a day for active ritual. The energy supports doing the work required to manifest change in the physical world using spiritual tools. It feels potent, stealthy, and effective. 5 Ix asks us to get our hands dirty—literally, in the soil, or metaphorically, in the work of the soul. It is a powerful day for healers, gardeners, and activists who work on behalf of the planet. The combination suggests that magic is a craft (5) that requires discipline and effort. The challenge is to use this power responsibly, not for manipulation, but for the greater good. The opportunity is to become a conscious co-creator with the forces of nature."}}	{"title": "The Practitioner of Earth Magic", "content": "To be born on 5 Ix is to be a natural shaman with a roll-up-your-sleeves attitude. You possess a unique blend of mystical intuition and practical capability. Tone 5 gives you a drive to work and to see results, while Ix connects you to the invisible forces of nature and the night. You are not the mystic on the mountain top; you are the village healer who is mixing the poultice, the environmentalist planting the trees, the artist carving the totem. You believe that magic is real, but you also know it requires effort.\\n\\nYour life path is one of active service to the Earth and the Spirit. You are here to bridge the gap between the seen and unseen worlds through your labor. You may be drawn to bodywork, herbalism, geology, or conservation. You have a magnetism that can be intense; like the Jaguar, you have a presence that commands respect. You are unafraid of the dark places in the human psyche, often helping others to navigate their own shadows through your practical guidance.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 5 Ix soul is the temptation of power. Because you can make things happen, you may try to force outcomes or manipulate situations to your will. You might also become a workaholic, driven by a restless energy that finds it hard to settle. There is a risk of becoming isolated, preferring the company of nature to the complexity of humans. Your lesson is to use your power with humility. When you serve the life force rather than trying to control it, your work becomes a sacred offering that heals the world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#cabe66", "primary": "#121b13", "secondary": "#49512e"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.877821	2026-04-25 13:46:58.057635
248	20	1	1	Tz'ikin	The path begins in a mist that smells of morning rain. You cannot see the top of the Spire; you can only see the few steps in front of you. The quartz beneath your boots is slippery with dew.\n\nSuddenly, the mist parts. Not slowly, but violently, as if a giant wing has swept it aside.\n\nStanding on a ridge above you is a Bird of prey, larger than a man. Its feathers are not made of keratin, but of gold leaf and sapphire. It looks at you with an eye that is sharp, unblinking, and fiercely intelligent.\n\n1 is the Spark. Tz’ikin is the Vision.\n\nThe Bird screeches, a sound that pierces your eardrums and wakes up every nerve ending in your body. It is asking you a question without words: *What do you see?*\n\nYou look around. You see rocks. You see fog.\n\nThe Bird clacks its beak impatiently. It wants you to look *better*.\n\nYou close your eyes and take a breath. You let go of the physical details and look with your inner eye. You sense the potential of the mountain. You sense the energy rising. You sense that this path leads to something magnificent.\n\nWhen you open your eyes, the Bird is gone. But where it stood, a single golden coin rests on the rock. It is not currency from any nation you know. It is stamped with the image of an open eye.\n\nYou pick it up. It is warm. It hums against your palm.\n\nYou realize that this is the seed of your prosperity. It is not a lot—just one coin, one spark, one moment of clarity. But it is enough to begin.\n\nYou pocket the coin. As you do, the fog lifts completely for a hundred yards. The path is clear.\n\nYou have initiated the cycle. You have chosen to see.	Lift your head. The fog is clearing, and for a split second, the universe is showing you the roadmap. The energy of 1 Tz’ikin is pure, concentrated potential. It’s the eagle spotting the prey from a mile high.\n\nDon’t worry about the "how" today. Just focus on the "what." What does your highest, most abundant life look like? Hold that image. Do not dilute it with realism. Your job today is to see the peak, not to climb it yet. The vision itself is the first step of manifestation.	I open my eyes to the infinite possibilities and prosperity surrounding me.	Visualize yourself standing on a high cliff edge. The wind is strong and clean. Below you, the world is covered in clouds.\n\nSuddenly, the clouds break, revealing a landscape of gold and green—a valley of pure abundance. Feel the excitement in your chest. This is your life waiting for you. Breathe in the view.	{"nawal": {"title": "The Visionary Bird of Prosperity", "content": "Tz'ikin is the nawal of the bird, the eagle/condor, and vision. It represents the ability to see the big picture, rising above the details to perceive the interconnectedness of all things. Tz'ikin is the energy of prosperity, abundance, and the freedom of the spirit. Associated with the element of air and the sky, it carries a light, expansive, and high-frequency energy. It is the archetype of the visionary who brings messages from the divine to the earth. In daily life, Tz'ikin manifests as financial luck, good news, dreaming, and artistic inspiration. Its shadow aspect can be spacing out, greed, or becoming distracted by 'shiny objects' without grounding. Tz'ikin teaches us that abundance is a natural state.", "keywords": ["Vision", "Prosperity", "Freedom", "Abundance", "Perspective"]}, "number": {"title": "The Seed of Fire", "content": "Tone 1 represents the initial spark of creation, the singularity from which all potential unfolds. It is the number of unity, beginnings, and the pure, unadulterated impulse to exist. Like a seed lying in the dark earth, Tone 1 contains the blueprint for the entire cycle that follows, holding immense power in a concentrated form. Experientially, this energy feels like a sudden clarity or a surge of new intent—a moment where the past falls away and only the future's possibility remains. It is a day of initiation, where your thoughts and actions plant the vibrations that will ripple through the next thirteen days. In its shadow aspect, Tone 1 can feel isolating or overwhelming, a blinding light with no direction. However, when embraced, it offers the profound gift of focus and the authority to define a new narrative.", "keywords": ["Beginnings", "Unity", "Potential", "Initiation", "Focus"]}, "combined_energy": {"notes": ["Create a vision board or write down your biggest goals.", "Meditate on the feeling of freedom and flight.", "Ask for a sign from the spirit world to guide your next step.", "Seed a financial investment or savings plan.", "Look at a current problem from a 'bird's eye view' to find the solution."], "title": "Initiating the Vision", "content": "When the initiating spark of Tone 1 meets the soaring vision of Tz'ikin, we begin a cycle of prosperity and higher perspective. 1 Tz'ikin is the 'Seed of Vision.' Today is the day to plant the dream of what you wish to manifest. The energy supports a radical shift in perspective, allowing you to see your life from the viewpoint of the Eagle—high, clear, and unencumbered by the petty details of the ground. It is the perfect day to start a business, launch a creative project, or simply set an intention for abundance. 1 Tz'ikin asks us to believe in our ability to fly. It initiates a thirteen-day journey of bringing heaven down to earth. The challenge is to trust the vision before it has taken physical form. The opportunity is to align your mind with the infinite possibilities of the universe, knowing that what you conceive today will shape your reality."}}	{"title": "The Initiator of Abundance", "content": "To be born on 1 Tz'ikin is to be a pioneer of prosperity and a natural visionary. You possess a spirit that is constantly looking upward and forward. Tone 1 gives you a strong sense of individuality and the drive to start new things, while Tz'ikin gifts you with the ability to see opportunities that others miss. You are a self-starter, often preferring to blaze your own trail rather than follow the flock. You have a magnetic quality that attracts resources and people to your cause.\\n\\nYour life path is one of manifesting the new. You are here to prove that abundance is available to everyone if they have the eyes to see it. You may be drawn to entrepreneurship, the arts, or spiritual leadership—any field where you can use your vision to create something from nothing. You are a messenger of hope, often bringing good news or inspiring ideas to your community. Your optimism is your greatest tool.\\n\\nThe challenge for a 1 Tz'ikin soul is patience. You see the destination so clearly that you can become frustrated with the journey. You may struggle with the details, preferring the high-level concept to the nitty-gritty work. There is also a risk of being too independent, forgetting that even eagles need to land sometimes. Your lesson is to trust the process of flight. When you learn to navigate the air currents with patience and precision, your vision becomes a reality that uplifts the entire world."}	{"birthday": {"accent": "#79b6c1", "primary": "#121515", "secondary": "#414c50"}, "horoscope": {"accent": "#b98740", "primary": "#342013", "secondary": "#704824"}, "affirmation": {"accent": "#e9debb", "primary": "#c5ab77", "secondary": "#aad2d7"}, "story_primary": {"accent": "#b8af94", "primary": "#25323f", "secondary": "#6e6e61"}}	2025-12-10 15:51:35.88119	2026-04-25 13:46:58.067065
