18	toj	Toj	You do not arrive in this world by walking. You arrive by falling.\n\nOne moment, you are standing in the grey static of your ordinary life—holding onto the invisible weight of everything you owe, everything you haven’t said, everything you promised but couldn’t keep. The next, the ground beneath you dissolves.\n\nYou wake up mid-impact, slamming into a shelf of glossy, hot black rock. The air is deafening. It roars with the sound of earth cracking open. The sky above is not blue, but a churning ceiling of smoke and ember-orange light, thick with ash that falls like heavy, dark snow.\n\nYou scramble to your feet, the heat pressing against your skin like a physical hand. This is a volatile place. A landscape of raw, flowing magma rivers cutting through jagged banks of obsidian glass. Massive shards of black rock jut violently out of the fire, sharp as knives, reflecting the chaotic glow of a world in the middle of being born.\n\nThere is no path here. There is no map. There is only the overwhelming, terrifying heat of transformation.\n\nYou look down at your hands. They are covered in soot, but they feel lighter. The heavy coat of invisible debts you were carrying has vanished, burned away in the descent. But in its place, the world itself demands your attention.\n\nA geyser of fire erupts nearby, spraying molten gold into the air. It is beautiful and deadly, a reminder that energy cannot be created or destroyed, only changed. You realize with a jolt that you are standing in the cosmic furnace.\n\nThis is not a punishment. It is a transaction.\n\nThe heat isn’t trying to consume you; it is trying to refine you. The shaking ground isn’t trying to throw you off; it is trying to wake you up.\n\nYou take a breath, and the air tastes of sulfur and ozone—the scent of lightning striking rock. You are miles from the cool, comfortable numbness of the place you came from. Here, everything costs something. Every step requires focus. Every breath is a negotiation with