ed.	You reach the far rim of the canyon just as the amber light begins to deepen into a rich, velvety twilight. You turn back to look at the distance you have crossed.\n\nThe Valley of the Gathered looks different now. The chaotic tangles of the first days are gone. The nets hang in graceful, intentional curves. The heaviness is gone, replaced by a sense of spaciousness. The bundles that remain are glowing brightly—true abundance, not clutter.\n\nYou look at your hands. They feel free. You look at your spirit. It feels unburdened.\n\nYou have walked the path of the Net. You have faced the serpent of vitality, the death of old patterns, the stability of the wilderness, and the ripening of true seeds. You have paid your spiritual debts, stayed loyal to your truth, woven your own artistry, and walked the road of destiny. You have built your inner pillar, touched the magic of the earth, and seen the vision from above.\n\nAnd finally, you have forgiven.\n\nThe last knot has been untied. The last unnecessary weight has been dropped into the abyss below, turning into compost for the valley floor.\n\nK’at has taught you the difference between holding on and hoarding. It has shown you that true abundance requires space. You cannot receive the new if your hands are full of the old.\n\nA cool breeze rises from the canyon, carrying the scent of rain and wet earth. The golden nets dissolve slowly into the air, turning into drifting sparks.\n\nYou are no longer a collector of burdens. You are a harvester of light.\n\nYou turn toward the horizon, where the first stars of the next cycle are beginning to shine. You are light. You are open. You are ready to receive.	2025-12-10 15:51:35.816161	2025-12-10 15:51:35.816161
